import{_ as u,o as a,c as n,q as d,w as g,F as f,p,P as w,a as t,t as l,m as y,U as b,C as v,f as k}from"./chunks/framework.Bn3ma71E.js";const T={name:"PoemCard",props:{poems:{type:Array,required:!0,validator:o=>o.every(e=>"source"in e&&"target"in e&&"rationale"in e)}},data(){return{poemLoaded:!1}},mounted(){setTimeout(()=>{this.poemLoaded=!0},500)},computed:{visiblePoems(){return this.poems.slice(0,this.$parent.visibleCount)}}},S={class:"poem-container"},I={class:"review-title"},A={class:"review-content"},C={class:"review-rationale"},x={key:1,class:"loading-state"};function q(o,e,c,m,i,s){return a(),n("div",S,[d(b,{name:"fade-slide"},{default:g(()=>[i.poemLoaded?(a(!0),n(f,{key:0},p(s.visiblePoems,(r,h)=>(a(),n("div",{key:h,class:"review",style:w({"animation-delay":`${h*.2}s`})},[t("div",I,"Question: "+l(r.target),1),t("p",A,"Answer: "+l(r.source),1),t("div",C,[t("p",null,[e[0]||(e[0]=t("strong",null,"Rationale:",-1)),y(" "+l(r.rationale),1)])])],4))),128)):(a(),n("div",x,e[1]||(e[1]=[t("div",{class:"loading-spinner"},null,-1),t("p",null,"loading...",-1)])))]),_:1})])}const B=u(T,[["render",q],["__scopeId","data-v-c64db993"]]),M=JSON.parse(`[{"source":"Read the following paragraph and determine if the hypothesis is true:\\n\\nSutton-on-Sea (originally Sutton in the Marsh or Sutton le Marsh) is a small coastal village in the East Lindsey district of Lincolnshire, England. It is situated at the junction of the A52 and A1111 roads, 6 mi north-east from Alford and 2 mi south from Mablethorpe. The village is part of the civil parish of Mablethorpe and Sutton (where the population is listed).\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nHypothesis: Sutton-on-Sea is located just east of Ireland on the Celtic Sea.","target":"No","rationale":"Based on the paragraph, Sutton-on-Sea is located in Lincolnshire, England and not just east of Ireland. This contradicts the hypothesis so \\"No\\""},{"source":"Objects with greater mass have a stronger force of gravity.\\n\\nHaving read the above passage, choose the right answer to the following question (choices are decreases or increases ):\\n\\n\\nIf Milo adds mass to an object, what will happen to the force of gravity that object generates decreases or increases?","target":"increases","rationale":"The passage states that \\"objects with greater mass have a stronger force of gravity.\\" This implies that as the mass increases, so does the strength of an object's gravitational pull. So adding more mass to an object will increase its force of gravity.\\nTherefore, we can infer from this context and logic that if Milo adds more mass to his objects, then he is increasing the amount of matter present in those objects which will result in an increased gravitational pull by these objects. Hence it can be concluded that their forces of gravities would also increase due to addition in their masses, hence making choice B correct"},{"source":"Context: Veins are blood vessels that carry blood toward the heart. Most veins carry deoxygenated blood from the tissues back to the heart; exceptions are the pulmonary and umbilical veins, both of which carry oxygenated blood to the heart. In contrast to veins, arteries carry blood away from the heart.\\n\\nQuestion: do veins carry blood to the heart or away?","target":"toward","rationale":"To answer the question, consider the following: Veins are blood vessels that carry blood toward the heart."},{"source":"You are given two sentences. You have to find if there is entailment or agreement of the Hypothesis by the Premise. From the given pair of sentences, you should identify if there is enough information in the Premise to support the claim made in the Hypothesis. The Premise may not exactly be the same as Hypothesis. Your task is to return 'entails' if the premise supports hypothesis else return 'neutral'.\\n\\nPremise: Isolated system A system in which neither  matter nor energy is exchanged with the surroundings. \\n Hypothesis: A sealed, vacuum-insulated reaction flask approximates the condition of a isolated system, in which neither matter nor heat can be exchanged between system and surroundings.","target":"entails","rationale":"The premise defines an isolated system as a system in which neither matter nor energy is exchanged with the surroundings. The hypothesis provides information about a sealed, vacuum-insulated reaction flask that approximates the condition of an isolated system. It states that neither matter nor heat can be exchanged between the reaction flask and its surroundings. Therefore, the hypothesis provides evidence that supports the definition of an isolated system provided in the premise. As a result, it entails or implies this definition and so \\"entails\\" should be returned as output.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an anaphor number agreement or as an incorrect representation. An anaphor is an expression whose interpretation depends upon another expression. Anaphor number agreement is a restriction where a phrase agrees with the preceeding expression: plurals match plurals or singular expressions match singular expressions. In this task a valid representation of anaphor number agreement should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an anaphor number agreement will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence where the subject and self-referencing nouns match plurality. An incorrect representation is a sentence in which the subject and self-referencing noun's plurality do not match.\\n\\nA lot of pedestrians help himself.","target":"bad","rationale":"The subject of the sentence is \\"A lot of pedestrians\\", which is plural. However, the reflexive pronoun \\"himself\\" is singular and does not agree with the plurality of the subject. A correct representation would be \\"A lot of pedestrians help themselves\\", where the plural subject \\"pedestrians\\" agrees with the plural reflexive pronoun \\"themselves\\".\\\\nTherefore, This sentence is an incorrect representation of anaphor number agreement and should be denoted as 'bad'."},{"source":"Sentence: How can you rapidly cool a canned drink?\\n\\nChoice 1: Wrap the table cloth in a wet paper towel then place it in the freezer. It will be chilled if you take it out 2 min. later.\\n\\nChoice 2: Wrap the drink in a wet paper towel then place it in the freezer. It will be chilled if you take it out 2 min. later.\\n\\nWhat is the index of the correct choice for ending for the sentence?\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"2","rationale":"In order to cool a canned drink, one needs to wrap it in something that will make the temperature change. Since paper towels are insulated and hold little heat or cold, making them ideal for wrapping around canned drinks to keep them chilled. So Choice 2 is the correct answer because it makes sense with this context."},{"source":"After arriving in New York City, Einstein was taken to various places and events, including Chinatown, a lunch with the editors of the New York Times, and a performance of Carmen at the Metropolitan Opera, where he was cheered by the audience on his arrival. During the days following, he was given the keys to the city by Mayor Jimmy Walker and met the president of Columbia University, who described Einstein as \\"The ruling monarch of the mind.\\" Harry Emerson Fosdick, pastor at New York's Riverside Church, gave Einstein a tour of the church and showed him a full-size statue that the church made of Einstein, standing at the entrance. Also during his stay in New York, he joined a crowd of 15,000 people at Madison Square Garden during a Hanukkah celebration. Einstein next traveled to California where he met Caltech president and Nobel laureate, Robert A. Millikan. His friendship with Millikan was \\"awkward\\", as Millikan \\"had a penchant for patriotic militarism,\\" where Einstein was a pronounced pacifist. During an address to Caltech's students, Einstein noted that science was often inclined to do more harm than good. This aversion to war also led Einstein to befriend author Upton Sinclair and film star Charlie Chaplin, both noted for their pacifism. Carl Laemmle, head of Universal Studios, gave Einstein a tour of his studio and introduced him to Chaplin. They had an instant rapport, with Chaplin inviting Einstein and his wife, Elsa, to his home for dinner. Chaplin said Einstein's outward persona, calm and gentle, seemed to conceal a \\"highly emotional temperament,\\" from which came his \\"extraordinary intellectual energy.\\" Chaplin also remembers Elsa telling him about the time Einstein conceived his theory of relativity. During breakfast one morning, he seemed lost in thought and ignored his food. She asked him if something was bothering him. He sat down at his piano and started playing. He continued playing and writing notes for half an hour, then went upstairs to his study, where he remained for two weeks, with Elsa...\\nWhat were the events preceding Einstein's seclusion? \\nI was going to say \\"He was having breakfast\\". Does that sound right?","target":"Yes","rationale":"Prior to his seclusion, Einstein had gone on a tour around New York City and California. During the trip he was cheered by crowds of people who were eager to meet him; it is likely that this experience led to his decision for two weeks' retreat from public life.\\nSo answer Yes!"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue between a user and an assistant, where users and assistants converse about geographic topics like geopolitical entities and locations. The task here is to find if the dialogue is by the user or assistant. Classify your answers into user and assistant.\\n\\nYes, of course. Before the current day border, the state's western border was a straight line that passed through the point where the Kansas River enters the Missouri River.","target":"assistant","rationale":"The given sentence is an objective statement that provides information. Therefore, the response is likely to be from the assistant and not the user. Hence, the answer is \\"assistant\\"."},{"source":"Q: who wrote the ecclesiastical history of the english nation? A:","target":"Venerable Bede","rationale":"The Venerable Bede wrote the Ecclesiastical History of the English Nation.\\n\\n[References]\\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecclesiastical_History_of_the_English_People"},{"source":"The son of an impoverished Bedouin goat herder, Gaddafi became involved in politics while at school in Sabha, subsequently enrolling in the Royal Military Academy, Benghazi. Founding a revolutionary cell within the military, in 1969 they seized power from the absolute monarchy of King Idris in a bloodless coup. Becoming Chairman of the governing Revolutionary Command Council (RCC), Gaddafi abolished the monarchy and proclaimed the Republic. Ruling by decree, he implemented measures to remove what he viewed as foreign imperialist influence from Libya, and strengthened ties to Arab nationalist governments. Intent on pushing Libya towards \\"Islamic socialism\\", he introduced sharia as the basis for the legal system and nationalized the oil industry, using the increased revenues to bolster the military, implement social programs and fund revolutionary militants across the world. In 1973 he initiated a \\"Popular Revolution\\" with the formation of General People's Committees (GPCs), purported to be a system of direct democracy, but retained personal control over major decisions. He outlined his Third International Theory that year, publishing these ideas in The Green Book. Find the answer to: From what monarch did Gaddafi's movement take over Libya?","target":"Idris","rationale":"The paragraph states that Gaddafi's movement seized power from the absolute monarchy of King Idris in a bloodless coup. Thus, to answer the question \\"From what monarch did Gaddafi's movement take over Libya?\\" we can use this information and conclude that it was King Idris."},{"source":"Following their road win over the Raiders, the Lions played their Week 2 home opener against their NFC North rival Minnesota Vikings for the lead in the division.  After a scoreless first quarter, Detroit pounced first with QB Jon Kitna completing a 9-yard TD pass to WR Roy Williams.  The Vikings tied the game with QB Tarvaris Jackson getting a 1-yard TD run.  The Lions took the lead prior to halftime with kicker Jason Hanson's 30-yard field goal. In the third quarter, when Kitna was temporarily out with a concussion, QB J. T. O'Sullivan came in and completed a 7-yard TD pass to Calvin Johnson to increase Detroit's lead.  Minnesota, however, tied the game up with kicker Ryan Longwell getting a 32-yard field goal and DE Ray Edwards returning a fumble 9 yards for a touchdown.  After both teams failed to score in the fourth quarter, the Vikings got the ball to begin overtime.  The Lions forced a fumble nine plays into their drive and would eventually get the win with Hanson's 37-yard field goal.\\nAnswer this question: Which player threw the longest touchdown pass?","target":"Jon Kitna","rationale":"Jon Kitna threw a 9-yard TD pass to WR Roy Williams, which is the longest touchdown pass in this game."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a list of integers you need to calculate and return the range of the integers which is the difference between maximum and minimum element in the list.\\n\\n[452, 110, 73, 261, 427, 350, 316, 156, 462, 496, 106, 214, 296, 65, 367, 241, 25, 143, 183, 335]","target":"471","rationale":"The given list contains the integers [452, 110, 73, 261, 427, 350, 316 ...].\\\\n1. The maximum value in the given list is 496.\\\\n2. The minimum value in the given list is 25.\\\\n3. Range = (maximum) 496 - (minimum) 25 = 471"},{"source":"A friend asked me to answer this question: What is the first name of the person who was sentenced to death?, using the article: Thomas Harley, an ex-convict who served time in prison eight years ago, is wrongfully arrested for a bank robbery he didn't commit. The police have found fingerprints on the crime scene, incriminating Harley, even though he was present at the Carey Theatrical Warehouse at the time of the crime.\\nThe policemen do not believe Harley's explanation, partly because he claims to have been called to the warehouse by a note from an old cell mate by the name of Dave Wyatt, a man that has been dead for eight years. Subsequently, Harley is sentenced to death for the robbery. He goes off to prison to wait for his execution.\\nHarley's daughter June asks private investigator Charlie Chan for help to prove her father's innocence. Hearing about the suspicious circumstances, Chan immediately agrees to take the case.\\nWith only 9 days before Harley's execution, Chan starts investigating the suspicious note to Harley, and find out that it was written on a typewriter belonging to Mrs. Foss, Harley's landlady, who often rents to ex-cons. He talks to the other tenants in the building: the poor Miss Petrie, bookkeeper Mr. Johnson, salesman Mr. Danvers and showgirl Emily Evans, whose work costume was found in warehouse near the crime scene. \\nCuriously enough, both Danvers and Evans had been in other cities at the time of bank robberies there. When Chan, his son Tommy and the chauffeur Birmingham goes to the prison to see Harley, they are shot at. This makes Chan sure that they are on the right track and believes that the fingerprints on the crime scene must have been placed there by someone else.\\nWhen Chan looks into the other robberies he finds that the modus operandi was always the same, and the perpetrators ended up in the same prison. It also turns out the quiet Miss Petrie is married to a convict who works in the prison's fingerprint department., what would be the answer ?","target":"Thomas","rationale":"The article begins by introducing Thomas Harley as the person who was wrongfully arrested for a bank robbery. As such, his first name is mentioned in the title and introduction to be \\"Thomas\\", making it likely that this individual's full name could be Thomas Harley."},{"source":"Indicate the presence of numerical data in the abstract (whether numerical data plays a key role in medical records), solely using the information from the abstract.\\n\\nAbstract: With 111In-labeled platelets and 125I-labeled bovine fibrinogen, regional mapping of platelet and fibrinogen deposition on leaflets and sewing rings was obtained. Ten Holstein calves received 25-mm mitral valves (ISLM) and were killed 1, 14, and 30 days after implantation. Twenty-four hours before the calves were killed, 350 to 450 microCi of 111In-labeled platelets and 200 to 250 microCi of 125I-labeled bovine fibrinogen were administered intravenously. The components of the tissue valves, i.e., three leaflets and sewing rings, were separated. Each leaflet was cut into four sections: free edge, central zone, flexion zone, and attachment zone. From the radioactivity in blood, leaflet zones, sewing rings, area of leaflet zones, platelet count, and fibrinogen level in blood, the mean regional density of adherent platelets, fibrinogen-fibrin, and fibrinogen/platelet were calculated. The density of platelets and fibrinogen deposited on the components of the valves decreases with time postimplantation. The number of fibrinogen molecules per platelet is fivefold to 20-fold higher than that of the receptor concentration on platelets on leaflet zones, suggesting the heterogeneity of fibrinogen-fibrin in thrombus and components of the valve. \\nQuestion: Does the abstract contain any numerical data?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The abstract includes a large amount of numerical data. It provides the number of animals that participated in the study, describes how much radioactive material was administered to each animal, reports on the radioactivity levels in different tissues and blood samples collected from each animal, and calculates regional densities of adherent platelets and fibrinogen in these tissues. The results described in this abstract are not complete without these numerical values. So the answer is ‚ÄúYes‚Äù."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the vouch-fair strategy, otherwise output No. vouch-fair is a selfish negotiation strategy. It is used to call out fairness for personal benefit, either when acknowledging a fair deal or when the opponent offers a deal that benefits them. This can be through an explicit call out or can be implied.\\n\\nContext: 'then you can get 2 food, 1 water and 2 firewoods ' 'After talking it over the boys I think with can go with 2 water 1 food and 2 firewoodüôÇ' 'sounds good want to submit?'\\nUtterance: 'I want to make sure that we have everything we need. Are you sure that deal is okay for you and your camp?üòÆ'","target":"Yes","rationale":"In this case, the speaker is implying that the deal may not be fair to them. They are trying to get more out of the deal by calling out fairness. Hence, vouch-fair has been used in this utterance and hence answer is Yes."},{"source":"Greg said goodbye to his last student at 8:15 PM, locked up the studio, and got into his car. He always looked forward to his evening rendezvous with Bonnie--his nickname for the Bonneville. He liked to put her top down, and drive her around town in the moonlight. Their route varied from night to night, but the ultimate destination was never in question.\\n\\"May I help you?\\"\\nThe worn-out speaker was crackly, but he still recognized the particularly twangy East Texas voice of Fontana Fry.\\nOver his six years of vocal training, he had become acutely aware of accents. This is true of all classically trained singers. Great emphasis is placed on precise pronunciation and enunciation. It is mandatory that the singer's repertoire include works written in English, Latin, Italian, German, and French.\\nSo, by the time Greg finished his graduate degree, his accent had been all but eliminated. He sounded somewhat like a network news anchor instead of an East Texan.\\n\\"I would like a large--\\"\\n\\"--a large dipped cone, the usual. Right?\\"\\nThe Dairy Queen drive-thru ordering station was located out in front of the restaurant, on the right side. He looked up, and saw the 19 year-old waving at him. She looked so cute in her little Dairy Queen outfit. Fontana was in her first year at Kilgore College. She planned to be an elementary teacher. He knew she would be a good one.\\nGreg had met Fontana a few months earlier when she brought her 13-year-old brother to the studio to enroll for guitar lessons. The boy was holding a U.S. made, 1968 Harmony acoustic guitar his uncle gave him. The body and the frets were badly worn, but the instrument still played beautifully. It looked somewhat like a large violin, with arched top and f-holes. That shape produces a more mellow sound than flattops. And the guitar's age contributed additional warmth to the tone.\\nGreg thinks Fontana\\n- Will be a great elementary school teacher\\n- Will be a good student\\n- not enough information\\n- Is a good employee","target":"Will be a great elementary school teacher","rationale":"In this passage, Greg is talking about Fontana. He says that she looks cute in her Dairy Queen outfit and he knows that she will be a good teacher because of the effort she puts into being a good student.\\nSo, his opinion on Fontana's teaching abilities is based on what he observes about how hardworking and dedicated to schoolwork she appears to be as well as the fact that her goal is to become an elementary school teacher. This suggests that Greg thinks \\"Fontana Will be a great elementary school teacher.\\""},{"source":"But I digress . The elven prince wanted nothing more than to restore his people to their former glory and he was cut down because of it . Sure , he would ' ve taken the extreme measure of committing genocide on all of mankind , but by the movie 's telling it was almost par for the course .\\nAccording to the above context, choose the best option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: What kind of movie might this be ?\\nOptions:\\nA. None of the above choices .\\nB. A fantasy movie\\nC. A horror movie\\nD. An action movie","target":"B","rationale":"The passage is about the prince of a group called ‚Äúelves‚Äù who wants to restore his people. The elves and their prince are described in fantastical terms, such as that he was cut down by an arrow made from sunlight. These elements suggest that this context comes from a fantasy movie, where there may also be other magical creatures like wizards or dragons (the term ‚Äògenocide‚Äô suggests violence).\\nTherefore, B is the best option out of all four options given."},{"source":"In mathematics, the absolute value of a number is the non-negative value of that number, without regarding its sign. For example, the absolute value of -2 is 2, and the absolute value of 5 is 5. In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element. The absolute value for negative numbers can be found by multiplying them by -1. After finding the element with the maximum absolute value you should return the value of that element before you applied the absolute value.\\n\\n[ 40.441 -69.993]","target":"-69.993","rationale":"The element with the highest absolute value in the given list is -69.993, which has an absolute value of 69.993. The absolute value of all other numbers in the list is less than or equal to 69.993. However, we need to return the value of the element before applying the absolute value, so the answer is -69.993.\\"\\""},{"source":"Answer the question...what are the ages of the three finalists on american idol??","target":"23","rationale":"The three finalists on American Idol are 23 years old."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on geometry. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: find the volume and surface area of a cuboid 16 m long , 14 m broad and 7 m high . \\nOptions: ['a ) 878 cm ^ 2', 'b ) 858 cm ^ 2', 'c ) 838 cm ^ 2', 'd ) 868 cm ^ 2', 'e ) none of them']","target":"d","rationale":"The volume of the cuboid is: V = 16 x 14 x 7 = 992 m^3.\\\\nThe surface area of the cuboid is: S = 2 x (16x14) + 2 x (16x7) + 2 x (14x7) = 868 m^2.\\""},{"source":"Sentence: Whom to consult when one is depressed?\\n\\nChoice 1: One should consult a neurologist.\\n\\nChoice 2: One should consult a psychiatrist.\\n\\nWhat is the index of the correct choice for ending for the sentence?\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"2","rationale":"Depression is a mental illness and should be treated by someone who specializes in the treatment of mental health issues. A psychiatrist would specialize in treating depression, so Choice 2 is the correct answer to this question.\\nSo, the index of choice 2  is \\"2\\"."},{"source":"Given news headlines, an edited word and funniness labels. The original sentence has word with the given format {word}. Create new headlines by replacing {word} in the original sentence with edit word. Your task is to generate answer \\"Yes\\" if an edited sentence matches funniness label, otherwise generate answer \\"No\\".  \\n\\nNews Headline: VP {Mike Pence} Was Never Informed About Flynn : Source \\n Edit: informant \\n Label: Not Funny","target":"No","rationale":"The answer is \\"No\\" for the given question. Because, the edited sentence \\"VP {informant} Was Never Informed About Flynn : Source\\" does not match funniness label \\"Not Funny\\"."},{"source":"You have to predict the type of conversation sentence given as input. Your predictions can be one among: 'information' if the input statement states a piece of information, 'question' if the input statement asks for some information, 'directive' if the input sentence involves the management or guidance of operations, and 'commissive' when it constitutes a statement that commits the speaker to some future action.\\n\\n Why did you do that ?","target":"question","rationale":"The sentence asks the listener for some piece of information, i.e., why they did something. Therefore, it is a question."},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nCountries with more industry produce more hazardous wastes than those with little industry.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nTheresa lives in a first world country. Eric lives in a third world country. Whose country likely produces less hazardous waste Eric's or Theresa's?","target":"Eric's","rationale":"The third world typically refers to countries that are underdeveloped or developing and have low standards of living. The first world generally refers to industrialized, rich nations with a high standard of living.\\nIn the paragraph it says that \\"Countries with more industry produce more hazardous wastes than those with little industry,\\" which means Theresa's country is likely producing more hazardous waste because there is most likely much more industrialization in her country as opposed to Eric's."},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nBecause richer nations use more fossil fuels, they also cause more air pollution and global warming than poorer nations do.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nA country like the US burns more fossil fuels than a third world country. This means that a richer country causes more or less pollution than a third world country?","target":"more","rationale":"The paragraph states that richer nations use more fossil fuels, which in turn causes them to cause more air pollution and global warming. The question asks whether a rich country like the US causing pollution than a third world country, requiring you to determine how much each burns. It is clear from the context of this passage that the answer is \\"more\\", as it matches both sentences in ways that less does not."},{"source":"You are given a question and some answer options (associated with \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\"). You should choose the correct answer based on commonsense knowledge. Avoid answering questions based on associations, the set of answers are chosen deliberately to capture common sense beyond associations. Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B, 'C', 'D', 'E' and only give one answer for each question.\\n\\nWhat is someone doing if he or she is sitting quietly and his or her eyes are moving?\\n(A)reading (B)meditate (C)fall asleep (D)bunk (E)think","target":"A","rationale":"This question tests knowledge of common behaviors of humans. A person who is sitting quietly and whose eyes are moving around is likely reading a book."},{"source":"Read the dialog and predict the next turn. hey, do you guys want to get a pizza?\\nThank you for calling Hungry Howie's, how may I help you?\\nYes' I'd like to order a pizza, please\\nwhat size pizza?\\nLarge please\\nand what would you like on it?\\nbacon and pineapple, please.\\nwould yo like any Howie bread or drinks with that?","target":"Yes, please. I'd like to order a large salad","rationale":"The dialog above is about ordering a pizza. The next turn in this dialog should be a response to the question: \\"Would yo like any Howie bread or drinks with that?\\" A reasonable reply would be \\"Yes, please. I'd like to order a large salad\\"."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the correct option to answer the question.\\nContext: U.S. Attorney General Loretta Lynch visited Orlando, Florida, on Tuesday, nine days after what she called a \\"shattering attack\\" at a gay nightclub.\\nLynch told the city's devastated gay community, \\"We stand with you in the light.\\" She also announced a $1 million emergency grant to help Florida law enforcement pay for overtime costs related to the shooting, and she met with prosecutors, first responders and victims of the worst mass shooting in modern U.S. history.\\nHer visit comes as investigators continue to dig into the background of Omar Mateen, the gunman who killed 49 people and injured dozens more on June 12 at the Pulse nightclub.\\nLynch said it was a \\"cruel irony\\" that the lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender community ‚Äî one defined almost entirely by love ‚Äî is so often a target of hate.\\nShe told the LGBTQ community, \\"We stand with you to say that the good in the world far outweighs the evil; that our common humanity transcends our differences; and that our most effective response to terror and hatred is compassion, unity and love.\\"\\nAlso Tuesday, Orlando police reopened streets near the nightclub and wound down their investigation at the crime scene. A makeshift memorial that went up nearby shortly after the massacre was still standing Tuesday, with chalk messages on the sidewalk and utility poles. Among them are drawings of hearts, the message \\"God bless'' and the hashtag \\"#Orlandostrong.''\\nLynch declined to answer questions about the investigation and whether authorities are looking to charge anyone else in connection with the case.\\nShe said investigators will \\"go back ... and see if there's anything we could have missed or anything we could have done better'' in terms of spotting Mateen as a threat.\\nShe said \\"people often act out of more than one motivation,'' adding that a motive may never be known.\\nMateen was shot and killed by police during the attack.\\nQuestion: who else went with Lynch to Orlando probably\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. the president\\n\\nB. not enough information\\n\\nC. her guards\\n\\nD. her husband","target":"C","rationale":"According to the context, U.S Attorney General Loretta Lynch visited Orlando and spoke about gun violence in America. In addition she announced a $1 million emergency grant for law enforcement overtime costs related to the shooting at Pulse nightclub. She went with her security guards because it is likely that she would be accompanied by them whenever traveling out of town given her position as attorney general (C).\\nThe purpose of this trip was not only to speak but also meet prosecutors, first responders and victims directly impacted by the massacre which indicate who else might have been on the trip besides herself (D)"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and question which can be answered using the sentence. Your task is to answer the question using the information from the sentence. The answer to the question is unique and it is a continuous text span from the sentence.\\n\\nSentence: Official retirement took place at Fort Knox , on 17 October 1992 . \\n Question: where did something take?","target":"at Fort Knox","rationale":"The answer to the question could be \\"at Fort Knox\\""},{"source":"Choose from options: Determine if the sentence is true based on the text below:\\nEstonia is paid greatly for their licensing arrangement with Le Coq brewery.\\n\\nViru is a 5.0% ABV pilsner-style beer brewed in Estonia. It is brewed in the country's second largest city, Tartu, by the A. Le Coq brewery. The brand is owned by Baltic Beer Company Ltd (formerly Brand Independence Ltd), based in London, UK, and is brewed under licence in Estonia. A. Le Coq is the second largest brewery in Estonia, with a market share of 36.8% in 2005.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"The statement does not specify whether Estonia is paid for the Le Coq brewery's licensing arrangement or by it. Therefore, we cannot determine if this sentence is true based on the text given below. So, the answer would be \\"It's impossible to say\\"."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: People have their own ways of saying things with their own special expressions. Some of these expressions are easy to understand. \\"As Easy as Falling off a Log  \\" is one such expression. It describes a job that does not take much effort. If you ever tried to walk on a falling tree log, you may understand what the expression means. It is easier to fall off the log than to stay on it.\\nThere are several other expressions that mean the same thing. And their meaning is as easy to understand as falling off a log. One is \\"Easy as Pie.\\" Nothing is easier than eating a piece of sweet juicy pie, unless it is a piece of cake. \\"A Piece of Cake\\" is another expression that means something is extremely easy to do.\\nAnother expression is \\"As Easy as Shooting Fish in a Barrel  \\". Clearly, fish in a barrel will be much easier to shoot than fish in a river. In fact, it would be as easy as falling off a log.\\nSometimes, things that come to us easily also leave us just as easily. In fact, there is an expression \\"Easy Come Easy Go\\". Another easy expression is \\"To Go Easy on a Person\\". It means to treat a person kindly or gently, especially in a situation where you might be expected to be angry with him. A wife might ask her husband to go easy on their son, because the boy did not mean to destroy the toy. If you want to borrow some money to fix the car, you should look for a friend who is an \\"Easy Touch\\". An easy touch or a soft touch is someone who is kind and helpful.\\nAnd there is one more expression that means do not worry or work too hard. Try to keep away from difficult situations. \\"Take it easy\\", until we meet again.\\nQuestion: Which of the following is NOT true according to the passage?\\nOptions: A: That he goes easy on me means that he is angry with me.\\nB: He is always helping others, so he is an easy touch.\\nC: When he asks me to repair his broken bike, I say, \\"A piece of cake. I can help repair it.\\"\\nD: When a girl loses her way, I say, \\"Take it easy, I will send you home.\\"","target":"A","rationale":"The passage gives examples of expressions that are used to mean something is easy. The purpose of the author's writing this text seems to be explaining these common everyday phrases and their meanings.\\nAlthough an \\"Easy Touch\\" can be a kind person, someone who goes easy on another person might not necessarily always do so because they are kind or helpful, but rather may choose to go easy out of fear or apprehension as well.\\nTherefore option A would not make sense in the context according to what we know about going easy on someone from the passage, making it incorrect since there were no other options provided suggesting that he was angry with her when asking him for help instead of being supportive like she assumed (as implied by choice C). Thus option D does seem possible based on our understanding about taking it easy"},{"source":"You are supposed to identify the category of a high-school level math question. There are five possible categories (1) algebra (2) arithmetic (3) measurement (4) numbers, and (5) probability. Use the following guidelines: (1) 'algebra' questions will typically contain letter variables and will ask you to find the value of a variable (2) 'arithmetic' questions will ask the sum, difference, multiplication, division, power, square root or value of expressions involving brackets (3) 'measurement' questions are questions that ask to convert a quantity from some unit to some other unit (4) 'numbers' questions will be about bases, remainders, divisors, GCD, LCM etc. (5) 'probability' questions will ask about the probability of the occurrence of something. A question must belong to only one category.\\n\\nSuppose 3*f - 15 - 15 = 0. Let q = 208 - 203. What is the greatest common divisor of q and f?","target":"numbers","rationale":"This is a 'numbers' question because it asks about the GCD of two numbers, 'q' and 'f'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a conversation between a flight agent and the customer. You are given 4 options and you need to select the goal of the conversation. It is provided as part of customer's context, which has to be one of the following: \`book\`: Make a new reservation, \`cancel\`: Cancel an existing reservation, \`no_flight\`: No flight found for the customer's preference, \`no_reservation\`: No reservation / No change / No cancellation was made in the conversation, mostly enquiring details\\n\\ncustomer: Hello. \\n agent: Hello, how can I help you today? \\n customer: Can you please help me in booking flight ticket on dates Mar 05 and Mar 07? \\n agent: Sure, kindly share your airport codes. \\n customer: Sure, my airport codes are AUS and EWR. \\n agent: Do you have any connection limit? \\n customer: Yes, I need a break in between the journey. \\n agent: Is there any other specifications? \\n customer: I want to depart in the evening. \\n agent: Please share your name. \\n customer: Yes, my name is Larry Parker. \\n agent: Ok, please wait a moment. \\n customer: Take your time. \\n agent: Sorry to say, no flights found with your requirement. \\n customer: That's fine, thank you for the response. \\n agent: Thanks for reaching us.","target":"no_flight","rationale":"The conversation does not end in booking a ticket. The customer asks for help from the agent and specifies the dates of travel and airport codes. The agent asks for additional information like connection limit, specifications and name of the person, to which the customer responds. But after receiving all this information, no flights are found by the agent that match with customer's requirements. Hence, \`no_flight\` is chosen as an answer.\\""},{"source":"Which of these will most likely increase a plant population in a habitat?\\n\\nOptions:\\n- strong winds\\n- freezing temperatures\\n- fewer days of sunshine\\n- more days of rain showers","target":"more days of rain showers","rationale":"The rain showers will increase the water available for plants to grow, and so it is likely that more days of rain showers would result in a larger plant population."},{"source":"A ploynomial equation is a sum of terms. Here each term is either a constant number, or consists of the variable x raised to a certain power and multiplied by a number. These numbers are called weights. For example, in the polynomial: 2x^2+3x+4, the weights are: 2,3,4. You can present a polynomial with the list of its weights, for example, equation weights = [6, 4] represent the equation 6x + 4 and equation weights = [1, 3, 4] represent the equation 1x^2 + 3x + 4. In this task, you need to compute the result of a polynomial expression by substituing a given value of x in the given polynomial equation. Equation weights are given as a list.\\n\\nx = 9, equation weights = [2, 7, 9, 0]","target":"2106","rationale":"The given polynomial equation is: 2x^3 + 7x^2 + 9x\\\\nSubstituting x=9 in the above equation, we get: 2(9)^3 + 7(9)^2 + 9(9)\\\\n                                          =2*729+7*81+81\\\\n                                          =1458+567+81\\\\n                                          =2106"},{"source":"Exercise: read the text and answer the question by True or False.\\n\\nText: Consumer unit -- A consumer unit is a type of distribution board (a component of an electrical power system within which an electrical power feed provides supply to subsidiary circuits).\\nQuestion: is a distribution board the same as a consumer unit?","target":"False","rationale":"The text mentions that a consumer unit is also known as a distribution board, meaning there are two terms for the same thing. Therefore, the answer is False."},{"source":"Article: Scientific and technological research activities in Portugal are mainly conducted within a network of R&D units belonging to public universities and state-managed autonomous research institutions like the INETI ‚Äì Instituto Nacional de Engenharia, Tecnologia e Inova√ß√£o and the INRB ‚Äì Instituto Nacional dos Recursos Biol√≥gicos. The funding and management of this research system is mainly conducted under the authority of the Ministry of Science, Technology and Higher Education (MCTES) itself and the MCTES's Funda√ß√£o para a Ci√™ncia e Tecnologia (FCT). The largest R&D units of the public universities by volume of research grants and peer-reviewed publications, include biosciences research institutions like the Instituto de Medicina Molecular, the Centre for Neuroscience and Cell Biology, the IPATIMUP, the Instituto de Biologia Molecular e Celular and the Abel Salazar Biomedical Sciences Institute.\\n\\nQuestion: By which ministry is authority granted for funding and managing Portugal's research system?","target":"Ministry of Science, Technology and Higher Education (MCTES)","rationale":"The answer to the question is: Ministry of Science, Technology and Higher Education (MCTES)\\nThis can be inferred from \\"funding and management...is mainly conducted under the authority of the MCTES itself...\\""},{"source":"Read the text and determine if the sentence is true:\\n\\nSecurity forces gunned down six Maoists; while the rebels killed a policeman and an abducted civilian drowned escaping from the Maoists, say latest insurgency related reports.\\n\\nSentence: A civilian policeman was killed.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nA:","target":"no","rationale":"The facts in the context do not support this claim. In fact, they explicitly state that a civilian was killed by Maoists rather than policemen and no mention is made of any policeman being killed. So, the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"What is a question that would give the following answer?\\nAnswer: Back Bay;\\nQuestion:","target":"Where is the headquarters for the Christial Scientists?","rationale":"If the answer is \\"Back Bay\\", then a question that would give this answer could be:\\n\\"Where is the headquarters for the Christial Scientists?"},{"source":"Read this article and answer this question The Chiefs would build a 17-3 lead at one point, but Chicago would pull off a miraculous comeback to win 18-17. The Chiefs tried a 66-yard field goal, but Santos kick went wide right and missed everything near the goalposts. During this game, the Bears fans at times outnumbered the Chiefs fans, as Chicago fans are best known for good travel. With the loss, Kansas City fell to 1-4. They would also lose Jamaal Charles for the season, as he tore his ACL in this game.\\nHow many losses did Kansas City have coming into this game?","target":"3","rationale":"To answer how many losses the Kansas City had coming into this game, we need to find out when they lost their last three games. It is mentioned that Chiefs already have one loss which is in Week 1 against Tennessee Titans; and then, after a week of rest for all teams due to Thursday night game between Pittsburgh Steelers and Baltimore Ravens on September 11th, 2014, it also says that \\"the team would go on lose two more games\\" before losing another one with Chicago Bears. Therefore 3+1=4games"},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage which has extra information available on certain terms mentioned in it, i.e., the proper nouns in the passage. Your job is to determine whether information from more than one term is needed to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: Which of Hurst's grammar schools was founded earlier? Passage:Aurthur Frederick Hertz was born in Bradford to Fanny Mary and William Martin Hertz, a merchant of German Jewish descent. Hertz changed the spelling of his surname to Hurst in 1916. He attended Bradford Grammar School and Manchester Grammar School before graduating from Magdalene College, Oxford in 1904. He joined the staff of Guy's Hospital in 1906 and ran his own private practice before serving in World War I as a consulting physician stationed in Salonika. From 1916 to 1918, Hurst led the neurology department at Netley Hospital. Seale-Hayne College was repurposed as a military hospital that same year. Hurst moved there to help with treatment of shell shock, working at Netley until 1919. After the war, Hurst relocated his private practice to Windsor and retired in 1939. Upon his retirement, Hurst became a consulting physician and served on Guy's Hospital board of governors. Hurst was knighted in 1937 six years after his older brother Gerald Berkeley Hurst. He died in Birmingham in 1944, aged 65.","target":"a","rationale":"The question asks when the grammar schools were founded and the passage contains information about the two grammar schools in question. Therefore, a is correct, as more than one term is needed to answer the question."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Southeast Asia or Southeastern Asia is a subregion of Asia, consisting of the countries that are geographically south of China, east of India, west of New Guinea and north of Australia. The region lies near the intersection of geological plates, with heavy seismic and volcanic activity. Southeast Asia consists of two geographic regions:\\n\\n- Indonesia (or ; Indonesian: ), officially the Republic of Indonesia, is a unitary sovereign state and transcontinental country located mainly in Southeast Asia with some territories in Oceania. Situated between the Indian and Pacific oceans, it is the world's largest island country, with more than seventeen thousand islands. At , Indonesia is the world's 14th-largest country in terms of land area and world's 7th-largest country in terms of combined sea and land area. It has an estimated population of over 260 million people and is the world's fourth most populous country, the most populous Austronesian nation, as well as the most populous Muslim-majority country. The world's most populous island of Java contains more than half of the country's population.\\n\\n- Ortigas Center is a financial and central business district located at the boundaries of Pasig, Mandaluyong, and Quezon City in the Philippines. With an area of more than , it is Metro Manila's second most important business district after the Makati CBD. It is governed by Ortigas Center Association, Inc.\\n\\n- Bonifacio Global City (also known as BGC, Global City, or The Fort) is a financial district in Metro Manila, Philippines. It is located south-east of the center of Manila in an area formerly disputed between the cities of Makati and Taguig as well as the municipality of Pateros. The area is currently under disputed. In recent years, the district has experienced robust commercial growth through the sale of military land by the Bases Conversion and Development Authority (BCDA). The entire district used to be the part of the main Philippine Army camp.\\n\\n- The Visayas or the Visayan Islands (Visayan: \\"Kabisay-an\\",  ), is one of the three principal geographical divisions of the Philippines, along with Luzon and Mindanao. It consists of several islands, primarily surrounding the Visayan Sea, although the Visayas are considered the northeast extremity of the entire Sulu Sea. Its inhabitants are predominantly the Visayan people.\\n\\n- Malaysia is a federal constitutional monarchy located in Southeast Asia. It consists of thirteen states and three federal territories and has a total landmass of separated by the South China Sea into two similarly sized regions, Peninsular Malaysia and East Malaysia (Malaysian Borneo). Peninsular Malaysia shares a land and maritime border with Thailand and maritime borders with Singapore, Vietnam, and Indonesia. East Malaysia shares land and maritime borders with Brunei and Indonesia and a maritime border with the Philippines and Vietnam. The capital city is Kuala Lumpur, while Putrajaya is the seat of the federal government. With a population of over 30 million, Malaysia is the 44th most populous country. The southernmost point of continental Eurasia, Tanjung Piai, is in Malaysia. Located in the tropics, Malaysia is one of 17 megadiverse countries on earth, with large numbers of endemic species.\\n\\n- Metropolitan Manila, commonly known as Metro Manila or simply Manila, is the capital region of the Philippines, is the seat of government, the 2nd most populous and the most densely populated region of the country. The National Capital Region (NCR) is composed of Manila, the capital city of the country, Quezon City, the country's most populous city, and the cities of Caloocan, Las Pi√±as, Makati, Malabon, Mandaluyong, Marikina, Muntinlupa, Navotas, Para√±aque, Pasay, Pasig, San Juan, Taguig, and Valenzuela, including the only remaining municipality of Pateros.\\n\\n- The Philippine Sea is a marginal sea east and northeast of the Philippines occupying an estimated surface area of 5 million km¬≤ (2 million mi¬≤). of the western part of the North Pacific Ocean. It is bordered by the Philippine archipelago (Luzon, Catanduanes, Samar, Leyte and Mindanao) on the southwest; Halmahera, Morotai, Palau, Yap, and Ulithi (of the Carolines) on the southeast; the Marianas, including Guam, Saipan, and Tinian, on the east; the Bonin and Iwo Jima on the northeast; the Japanese islands of Honshu, Shikoku, and Kysh on the north; the Ryukyu Islands on the northwest; and Taiwan in the west.\\n\\n- Palau (historically Belau or Pelew), officially the Republic of Palau, is an island country located in the western Pacific Ocean. The country contains approximately 250 islands, forming the western chain of the Caroline Islands in Micronesia, and has an area of . The most populous island is Koror. The capital Ngerulmud is located on the nearby island of Babeldaob, in Melekeok State. Palau shares maritime boundaries with Indonesia, the Philippines, and the Federated States of Micronesia.\\n\\n- The Celebes Sea of the western Pacific Ocean is bordered on the north by the Sulu Archipelago and Sulu Sea and Mindanao Island of the Philippines, on the east by the Sangihe Islands chain, on the south by Sulawesi's Minahassa Peninsula, and on the west by Kalimantan in Indonesia. It extends 420 miles (675¬†km) north-south by 520 miles (837¬†km) east-west and has a total surface area of , to a maximum depth of . The sea opens southwest through the Makassar Strait into the Java Sea.\\n\\n- Vietnam, officially the Socialist Republic of Vietnam (SRV), is the easternmost country on the Indochina Peninsula in Southeast Asia. With an estimated 90.5 million inhabitants , it is the world's 14th-most-populous country, and the eighth-most-populous Asian country. Vietnam is bordered by China to the north, Laos to the northwest, Cambodia to the southwest, Thailand across the Gulf of Thailand to the southwest, and the Philippines, Malaysia and Indonesia across the South China Sea to the east and southeast. Its capital city has been Hanoi since the reunification of North and South Vietnam in 1976.\\n\\n- Financial services are the economic services provided by the finance industry, which encompasses a broad range of businesses that manage money, including credit unions, banks, credit-card companies, insurance companies, accountancy companies, consumer-finance companies, stock brokerages, investment funds and some government-sponsored enterprises. Financial services companies are present in all economically developed geographic locations and tend to cluster in local, national, regional and international financial centers such as London, New York City, and Tokyo.\\n\\n- Taiwan, officially the Republic of China (ROC), is a state in East Asia. Neighbors include China (officially the People's Republic of China, abbreviated as PRC) to the west, Japan to the northeast, and the Philippines to the south.\\nTaiwan is the most populous state that is not a member of the United Nations, and the one with the largest economy.\\n\\n- Security Bank Corporation is a universal bank in the Philippines . It was established on June 18 , 1951 as Security Bank and Trust Company and was the first private and Filipino - controlled bank of the post-World War II period . Security Bank was publicly listed with the Philippine Stock Exchange in 1995 ( PSE : SECB ) . In January 2016 , The Bank of Tokyo - Mitsubishi UFJ , Japan 's largest bank , acquired the 20 % minority stake of Security Bank for a deal worth 36.9 billion pesos .\\n\\n- Manila (or ), officially City of Manila, is the capital of the Philippines.\\n\\n- The Philippines, officially the Republic of the Philippines, is a sovereign island country in Southeast Asia situated in the western Pacific Ocean. It consists of about 7,641 islands that are categorized broadly under three main geographical divisions from north to south: Luzon, Visayas, and Mindanao. The capital city of the Philippines is Manila and the most populous city is Quezon City, both part of Metro Manila. Bounded by the South China Sea on the west, the Philippine Sea on the east and the Celebes Sea on the southwest, the Philippines shares maritime borders with Taiwan to the north, Vietnam to the west, Palau to the east and Malaysia and Indonesia to the south.\\n\\n- A stock exchange or bourse is an exchange where stock brokers and traders can buy and/or sell stocks (also called shares), bonds, and other securities. Stock exchanges may also provide facilities for issue and redemption of securities and other financial instruments, and capital events including the payment of income and dividends. Securities traded on a stock exchange include stock issued by listed companies, unit trusts, derivatives, pooled investment products and bonds. Stock exchanges often function as \\"continuous auction\\" markets, with buyers and sellers consummating transactions at a central location, such as the floor of the exchange.\\n\\n- Tower One & Exchange Plaza is one of the tallest and most well-known skyscrapers in the Philippines. It is located in the Makati Central Business District and has a height of 160 metres (525¬†feet). The building has 35 floors above ground level, and is originally planned to be the first of three towers for the Ayala Triangle. Plans for the construction of the two additional buildings did not materialize though.\\n\\n- The South China Sea is a marginal sea that is part of the Pacific Ocean, encompassing an area from the Karimata and Malacca Straits to the Strait of Taiwan of around . The area's importance largely results from one-third of the world's shipping sailing through its waters and that it is believed to hold huge oil and gas reserves beneath its seabed.\\n\\n- Pasig is a city in the Philippines which was the former provincial capital of the province of Rizal prior to the formation of Metro Manila, the National Capital Region of the country of which it became a part. Located along the eastern border of Metro Manila, Pasig is bordered on the west by Quezon City and Mandaluyong; to the north by Marikina; to the south by Makati, Pateros, and Taguig; and to the east by Antipolo, the municipality of Cainta and Taytay in the province of Rizal.\\n\\n- A universal bank participates in many kinds of banking activities and is both a commercial bank and an investment bank as well as providing other financial services such as insurance. These are also called full-service financial firms, although there can also be full-service investment banks which provide wealth and asset management, trading, underwriting, researching as well as financial advisory.\\n\\n- Luzon is the largest and most populous island in the Philippines and the 15th largest in the world. Located in the northern region of the archipelago, it is the economic and political center of the nation, being home to the country's capital city, Manila, as well as Quezon City, the country's most populous. With a population of 52.99 million , it is the fourth most populous island in the world (after Java, Honshu, and Great Britain), containing about 53% of the country's total population.\\n\\n- The Philippine Stock Exchange is the national stock exchange of the Philippines. It has been in continuous operation since its inception in 1927. Currently, it maintains two trading floors in Metro Manila: one at its headquarters at the PSE Plaza Ayala Triangle, Ayala Tower One in the Makati Central Business District; and one at the Philippine Stock Exchange Centre (Tektite Towers), Ortigas Center in Pasig. Construction of the Philippine Stock Exchange office tower in Bonifacio Global City is expected to be completed by mid-2016. The PSE is overseen by a 15-member Board of Directors, chaired by Jos√© T. Pardo.\\n\\n- Asia is Earth's largest and most populous continent, located primarily in the eastern and northern hemispheres and sharing the continental landmass of Eurasia with the continent of Europe. Asia covers an area of , about 30% of Earth's total land area and 8.7% of the Earth's total surface area. The continent, which has long been home to the majority of the human population, was the site of many of the first civilizations. Asia is notable for not only its overall large size and population, but also dense and large settlements as well as vast barely populated regions within the continent of 4.4 billion people.\\n\\n- Mindanao is the second largest and southernmost major island in the Philippines. It is also the name of one of the three island groups in the country (the other two being Luzon and the Visayas), consisting of the island of Mindanao and smaller outlying islands. Davao City is the largest city in Mindanao. As of the 2010 census, the island's population itself is 20,281,545 people, while the Mindanao island group has 21,968,174 inhabitants. Davao City is the most populous in Mindanao as 1,632,991 population, and the 2nd is Zamboanga City as 861,799 population, the 3rd is Cagayan de Oro City as 675,950 population, and followed by General Santos City as 594,446 population as of 2015 census.\\n\\n- China, officially the People's Republic of China (PRC), is a unitary sovereign state in East Asia. With a population of over 1.381¬†billion, it is the world's most populous country. The state is governed by the Communist Party of China, and its capital is Beijing. It exercises jurisdiction over 22 provinces, five autonomous regions, four direct-controlled municipalities (Beijing, Tianjin, Shanghai, and Chongqing), and two mostly self-governing special administrative regions (Hong Kong and Macau), and claims sovereignty over Taiwan. The country's major urban areas include Shanghai, Guangzhou, Beijing, Chongqing, Shenzhen, Tianjin and Hong Kong. China is a great power and a major regional power within Asia, and has been characterized as a potential superpower.\\n\\n- Quezon City (  also known as QC) is the most populous city in the Philippines. It is one of the cities that make up Metro Manila, the National Capital Region of the Philippines. Quezon City was named after Manuel L. Quezon, second President of the Philippines, who founded the city and developed it to replace Manila as the national capital for 28 years from 1948 to 1976. Quezon City is not located in and should not be confused with Quezon Province, which was also named after the president. It is the largest city in Metro Manila in terms of land area and most populated local government unit in the country.\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat is the relationship between 'security bank' and 'makati'?","target":"headquarters location","rationale":"Security Bank is a bank in the Philippines, and Makati is its headquarters location."},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and extract the answer for the question: What is the name of the publication that called the person signed to a record deal worth ¬£1 million \\"exceptionally-talented\\"\\n\\nOn 12 June 2008, while Johnston was travelling with the Britain's Got Talent Live Tour, it was announced that Johnston had signed a record deal with Syco Music, a division of Sony BMG, and that his first album would be produced after the tour. The deal was reportedly for ¬£1 million. After signing with Syco, Johnston made public appearances, including performing at Andrew Lloyd Webber's birthday celebrations on 14 September, and at Carlisle United's Brunton Park.Johnston's debut album, One Voice, was released on 29 September 2008. It includes a cover of \\"Walking in the Air\\", performed with Faryl Smith. The album was recorded over a six-week period in London, and the track listing was chosen by Cowell. Johnston described the recording process as \\"brilliant\\", and that it was \\"really good ‚Äì just to be in a recording studio and meet the different people\\". The album debuted in the British charts at number five, and finished the week at number four. The album was later certified gold, having sold 100,000 copies, and Johnston was presented a gold disc by daytime television presenter Penny Smith. Critics responded positively to the album, with Kate Leaver, writing for the Korea JoongAng Daily, saying Johnston \\"has truer talent than hordes of his musical elders\\" and that \\"the vulnerability\\" of Johnston's performance on the album \\"makes for a haunting musical experience\\". In Music Week, the album was described as \\"highly-anticipated\\", and Johnston was called \\"exceptionally-talented\\".After the album's release, Johnston became involved in the Sing Up campaign, appearing in schools around the country to encourage other young people to join choirs. In December 2008, Johnston made a guest appearance at Whitehaven's Christmas fair, and performed at a carol service in Bradford. Johnston was also invited to turn on the Carlisle Christmas lights and perform at the celebrations. Mike Mitchelson, of Carlisle City Council, described Johnston as \\"one of our local heroes\\".","target":"Music Week","rationale":"The paragraph describes a musical artist's debut album. The author of the article praises this musician, calling him \\"exceptionally talented\\" in one publication and saying that he has \\"truer talent than hordes of his musical elders.\\"\\nSo, the answer is Music Week"},{"source":"FINAL EXAM\\n\\nQuestion 1. Which genus has more species, Bursera or Berzelia?","target":"Bursera","rationale":"The answer is based on the fact that Bursera has more species than Berzelia. \\nBursera was created in 1754 by Linnaeus and it contains about 140-150 species of plants, whereas Berzelia was created in 1818 by Robert Brown and it contained only one (1) plant: Berzelia lanuginosa."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence from the research paper and your task is to classify the given sentence into the following categories: Background (Why is this problem important? What relevant works have been created before? What is still missing in the previous works? What are the high-level research questions? How might this help other research or researchers?), Purpose (What specific things do the researchers want to do? What specific knowledge do the researchers want to gain? What specific hypothesis do the researchers want to test?), Method (How did the researchers do the work or find what they sought? What are the procedures and steps of the research?), or Finding (What did the researchers find out? Did the proposed methods work? Did the thing behave as the researchers expected?). \\n\\nUnder the One-health platforms there is a need to launch combined human and animal RVC surveillance programs for a better understanding of the epidemiology of RVC infections and for implementing control strategies.","target":"finding","rationale":"The sentence describes the need for combined human and animal RVC surveillance programs, which will help to better understand the epidemiology of RVC infections and implement control strategies. This is a finding from previous studies that supports the current research in this paper. Therefore, the correct category for this sentence is \\"Finding\\", not any other categories listed above."},{"source":"A single train car can carry 60 passengers. A 747 airplane can carry 366 passengers. How many more passengers can a train with 16 cars carry than 2 airplanes?","target":"228","rationale":"A train with sixteen cars can carry 16 x 60 = 960 passengers. 2 airplanes can carry 2 x 366 = 732 passengers. The train can carry 960 - 732 = 228 passengers more than 2 airplanes."},{"source":"If you haven't been sleeping well you are probably what?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptionsÔºö\\n\\nA. time to sleep\\n\\nB. tired\\n\\nC. closing eyes\\n\\nD. falling down\\n\\nE. darkness","target":"B","rationale":"A person who has not been sleeping well will feel tired. Thus, the correct answer is \\"B\\"."},{"source":"Read the given text and if it has abusive content then indicate via \\"yes\\". Otherwise indicate via\\"no\\". \\nWe consider the content to be abusive if it contains any of the following instances: (1) Identity Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which contains a negative statement made against an identity. An identity is a social category that relates to a fundamental aspect of individuals community, socio-demographics, position or self-representation) (2) Affiliation Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which express negativity against an affiliation. We define affiliation as a (more or less) voluntary association with a collective. Affiliations include but are not limited to: memberships (e.g. Trade unions), party memberships (e.g. Republicans), political affiliations (e.g. Right-wing people) and occupations (e.g. Doctors).) (3) Person Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which directs negativity against an identifiable person, who is either part of the conversation thread or is named. Person-directed abuse includes serious character based attacks, such as accusing the person of lying, as well as aggression, insults and menacing language.) and (4) Counter Speech (e.g., Content which challenges, condemns or calls out the abusive language of others.). Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nR I P  Looks like Jussie Smollet tied it up with rope and poured bleach on it. you think I am joking, the last thing uploaded was about him.","target":"no","rationale":"The text is not abusive as it does not contain any of the four instances mentioned."},{"source":"Please answer correctly the following question related to the paragraph below. \\n\\nWhich team learned about humans that lived in small populations of nomadic hunters?\\n\\nResearch team Alpha learned about early human activities, from 200000 years ago, while team Gamma learned about late human activities, 40000 years ago to present times.\\n\\nHint: The earliest members of the human species evolved around 200,000 years ago in Africa. Early humans lived in small populations of nomadic hunters and gatherers. Human beings remained in Africa until about 40,000 years ago. After that, they spread throughout Europe, Asia, and Australia. By 10,000 years ago, the first human beings colonized the Americas. During this long period of time, the total number of human beings increased very slowly. Birth rates were fairly high but so were death rates, producing low rates of population growth.","target":"team Alpha","rationale":"- Research team Alpha learned about early human activities, from 200000 years ago\\n- Team Gamma learned about late human activities, 40000 years ago to present times."},{"source":"Decide the language of that sentence. The language can be English, French, German, Italian, or Spanish.\\n\\nText: 'ehm then you want to go eh right ehm from left to right want to draw horizontal line ehm to about the middle of the page if there's if there's no obstacle there'","target":"English","rationale":"The text is in English as it uses common English words and grammar."},{"source":"You are provided with a list of converations between a \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\". Figure out if the conversation provided as \\"classify_text\\" is authored by \\"USER\\" or \\"ASSISTANT\\". There are maximum of 7 conversations between \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\" in each input\\n\\nASSISTANT: What type of movies do you enjoy? , USER: I love romantic comedies. , ASSISTANT: Why do you enjoy these type of movies? , USER: They're really easy to watch, really enjoyable to rewatch. They're happy, they're funny, they can be heartwarming. So they're just They're pleasant a very pleasant form of entertainment. , ASSISTANT: I can definitely see the appeal in that. Is there a specific title that you enjoy? , USER: I love Sleepless in Seattle., classify_text: What did you enjoy about this title?","target":"ASSISTANT","rationale":"The user is being asked about which movies they like and why. The system then asks the user to name a specific title they enjoy, to which the user replies \\"I love Sleepless in Seattle.\\" The classify_text begins with an interrogative word (\\"What\\") and asks about what the user enjoyed about this specific title. Therefore, it is most likely part of a conversation between ASSISTANT and USER, with ASSISTANT asking the question."},{"source":"Here's a problem to solve: A scientist on a field trip discovered a new organism. She examined its cells under a microscope and observed several different structures, including a nucleus, a cell wall, and some chloroplasts. This organism would correctly be classified in which of the following kingdoms?\\n\\nAmong the 4 following options, which is the correct answer?\\n\\n- A: Animalia\\n \\n- B: Monera\\n \\n- C: Plantae\\n \\n- D: Fungi","target":"C","rationale":"The question is asking you to identify the kingdom in which an organism would be classified based on its observed structures.\\nBased on the description provided, we know that the scientist was able to observe a nucleus and chloroplasts under the microscope. \\nChloroplasts are responsible for photosynthesis, which allows plants (and some other organisms) to convert sunlight into chemical energy. Photosynthetic organisms usually contain chloroplasts within their cells as well as cell walls made of cellulose or similar materials, both of which were mentioned by our scientist when she described her observations from looking at this new organism's cells through a microscope. The presence of these two distinct characteristics indicates that this unknown species exhibits traits typical of most members belonging to Kingdom Plantae . Since it has been verified that all living things"},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\nThree ways electrons can be transferred are conduction, friction, and polarization. In each case, the total charge remains the same. This is the law of conservation of charge.\\n\\n\\nQ: Which law refers to the electron charge remaining the same during transfer?\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"law of conservation of charge","rationale":"The paragraph discusses three different ways in which electrons are transferred, and the law that states that the total charge remains constant during these transfers. The only option among the four choices given above is \\"law of conservation of charge\\", so this must be correct!\\n \\nSo, the answer is law of conservation of charge"},{"source":"Write the conversation response. DIALOG:\\nWhat happened during the 1999 Baltimore Orioles season?\\n- 1999 Baltimore Orioles season The 1999 Baltimore Orioles season involved the Orioles finishing 4th in the American League East with a record of 78 wins and 84 losses.\\n- Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?\\n- In a rare event on March 28, 1999, the Orioles staged an exhibition series against the Cuban national team in Havana.\\n- Who won?\\n- The Orioles won the game 3‚Äì2 in 11 innings.\\n- Was there anything else that was interesting?\\n-","target":"They were the first Major League team to play in Cuba since 1959, when the Los Angeles Dodgers faced the Orioles in an exhibition.","rationale":"The answer is They were the first Major League team to play in Cuba since 1959, when the Los Angeles Dodgers faced the Orioles in an exhibition. This is a reasonable continuation of this conversation because it is 1) a response to \\"Was there anything else that was interesting?\\", and 2) it provides more information about this rare event in 1999 where the Orioles played against the Cuban national team."},{"source":"Rory Storm (7 January 1938 - 28 September 1972) was an English musician and vocalist. Born Alan Ernest Caldwell in Liverpool, Storm was the singer and leader of Rory Storm and the Hurricanes, a Liverpudlian band who were contemporaries of the Beatles in the late 1950s and early 1960s. Ringo Starr was the drummer for the Hurricanes before joining the Beatles in August 1962, replacing original drummer Pete Best.\\n\\nWhen Storm became a professional singer, he changed his name to Rory Storm by deed poll, and changed the name of his family's home in Broadgreen to Stormsville. Storm was known for the extravagant clothes he wore and the cars he drove, once buying a pink Vauxhall Cresta for PS800 in cash. A young man was once caught by a porter at Bootle railway station writing \\"I love Rory\\" over the walls, and when questioned, it turned out to be Storm himself. The Hurricanes wore matching suits on stage, but Storm sometimes wore a pink suit and pink tie, and during concerts he would walk over to the piano and comb his blond hair with an oversized comb. Their stage wear changed from sunglasses and palm tree-decorated shirts to red (and blue) suits. Storm also wore an Elvis-style gold lame suit. When they first appeared at Butlins holiday camp Storm wore a turquoise suit with a gold lame shirt, while the group wore fluorescent suits.  Rod Pont (also known as Steve Day in Steve Day and the Drifters) remembered Storm arriving at the Orrell Park Ballroom for a concert with a boil on his face. When told about it, Storm pulled out a black velvet hood which had slits for his eyes and mouth, and played the whole concert with the hood on. At one concert at Bankfield House Youth club, Garston, Liverpool, in 1965, the stage lighting failed between sets. Storm was upset until someone walked in with a torch, which Storm used to finish the concert. He occasionally used a pet monkey in some of the group's performances, as it attracted more people. At a New Brighton swimming baths performance for 1,600 people in 1963, Storm climbed to the top diving board, undressed to a pair of swimming trunks, and then dived into the water at the end of a song. In January 1964, during a performance at the Majestic Ballroom, Birkenhead, he climbed up one of the columns supporting the balcony, but slipped and fell 30 feet (9 m) to the floor below, fracturing his leg. At another performance on the New Brighton Pier, Storm made his way onto the Pavilion roof but fell through the glass skylight.  Storm and the Hurricanes received the most votes in the first Mersey Beat magazine poll, but many votes were disqualified as they had been posted from the same place at the same time and were written in green ink; although never proven, it was thought that Storm had posted the votes. This meant that the Beatles reached the top position, with the Hurricanes coming fourth, even though the Beatles had also been sending in extra votes themselves. Storm was often photographed for the magazine, such as being surrounded by nurses when he left the hospital after breaking a leg during a performance, or playing for the Mersey Beat XI football team.\\n\\nAre there any other interesting aspects about this article?","target":"A young man was once caught by a porter at Bootle railway station writing \\"I love Rory\\" over the walls, and when questioned, it turned out to be Storm himself.","rationale":"From the given context, the answer obviously seems to be: A young man was once caught by a porter at Bootle railway station writing \\"I love Rory\\" over the walls, and when questioned, it turned out to be Storm himself."},{"source":"Categorize the comment on the basis of sexual explicitness. If the comment is sexually explicit output Yes, otherwise output No.\\n\\nThis is a wonderful event!\\n \\nDespite comments by a few \\"cranks,\\" Hillary has spent a lifetime dedicated to improving people's lives, not just sitting on the sidelines taking potshots.\\n\\nI am proud of her and what she's accomplished. I'm proud that we Democrats selected her as our candidate.\\n\\nI also note that when she lost the primaries to Obama in 2008, she was gracious in defeat and closed ranks quickly to ensure his election.\\n\\nSanders on the other hand, appears to be playing some pathetic version of \\"grumpy old man as cult hero.\\"\\n\\nShows a real lack of grace on his part.\\n\\n-- Paul","target":"No","rationale":"The comment is a criticism of Bernie Sanders and his supporters. However, it does not contain any sexually explicit language or content. Therefore, the answer should be \\"No\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i, j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to find all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, reverse the order in which they occur, and then concatenate them to output the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j. Perform the operations in order, i.e., do not concatenate the elements and then reverse the string.\\n\\n2, 6, ['I', 'V', 's', 'I', 'i', '4469']","target":"4469iIsV","rationale":"Given the list ['I', 'V', 's', 'I', 'i', '4469'], we need to find the elements between 2nd and 6th positions:\\\\n1. The 2nd element is I.\\\\n2. The 3rd element is V.\\\\n3. The 4th element is s.\\\\n4. The 5th element is I again, but since it doesn't count as duplicate, we have to include it in our result string too!\\\\n5. The 6th and final element of our range is 4469 which should be included too!\\n\\nThe order in which the elements occur between these indices will be reversed to obtain: [4469, i, I, s ,V]. Then this list needs to be concatenated into a single string: 4469iIsV"},{"source":"Generate a question about the topic \\"Washington Nationals\\" whose answer would be: After being purchased by MLB in 2002, the team was moved before the season to Washington and renamed the Nationals, the first relocation since the second Washington Senators moved to Arlington, Texas , and became the Texas Rangers in ..","target":"when did expos become nationals?","rationale":"The correct answer is \\"when did expos become nationals?\\". \\nThis question can be answered by the provided fact and therefore it makes sense to ask."},{"source":"Given the prompt and a response, classify the them to \\"yes\\" if response is \\"yes, and\\" type. Otherwise classify it as \\"no\\". \\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). 1 In short, a \\"Yes, and\\" is a dialogue exchange in which a speaker responds by adding new information on top of the information/setting that was constructed by another speaker. Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange, although it could be the case if it agrees with the description above. There are many ways in which a response could implicitly/explicitly agree to the prompt without specifically saying 'yes, and...'. \\n\\nPrompt: No, I won't walk into that trap.  You try to get me to be right and, all of a sudden, the next thing I know, I'm on the dingy.  ? \\n Response: It's pretty much lying on the ground, right now.","target":"no","rationale":"The response does not explicitly or implicitly agree with the prompt. The response \\"It's pretty much lying on the ground\\" is unrelated to the prompt and not an addition of new information on top of what was said in the prompt."},{"source":"Context: The Cowboys began their 2008 campaign on the road against the Cleveland Browns.  In the first quarter, Dallas got the first shot as RB Marion Barber got a 1-yard TD run.  In the second quarter, the Browns would respond with QB Derek Anderson completing a 2-yard TD pass to TE Kellen Winslow.  Afterwards, the Cowboys responded with QB Tony Romo completing a 35-yard TD pass to WR Terrell Owens, along with another 1-yard TD run from Barber.  In the third quarter, Dallas pulled away with rookie RB Felix Jones getting an 11-yard TD run, which was his first carry in the NFL.  In the fourth quarter, Cleveland's only response would be kicker Phil Dawson's 34-yard field goal.\\n\\nQuestion: How many field goals did Dawson kick in the first quarter?\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"1","rationale":"In the article, we can read that Dawson got a 34-yard field goal in the fourth quarter. Therefore it is clear that he kicked 1 field goal during this game."},{"source":"Short general knowledge question: where did benjamin franklin died?","target":"Philadelphia","rationale":"Benjamin Franklin died in 1790 of old age at the home of his daughter, Sarah Bache. The house was located on Market Street and is now a museum called \\"Franklin Court\\". \\nThe city he lived in when he passed away was Philadelphia, Pennsylvania"},{"source":"The following article contains an answer for the question: What is the full name of the person that kisses Diana Standing's in her hotel room? , can you please find it? \\n\\nA beautiful English socialite, Diana Standing, and her wealthy fianc√© Gerald Hume arrive at the train station in Cairo, Egypt, where they plan to be married. Although her mother was Egyptian, Diana considers herself part of the British upper class. At the station, she is noticed by Jamil El Shehab, a handsome good-natured Egyptian dragoman who enjoys romancing women tourists and freeing them from some of their jewelry. Jamil is immediately captivated by Diana and soon talks his way into becoming her official guide and driver in Egypt.\\nWhile touring the Pyramids, Jamil manages to be alone with Diana and romances her with love songs. Meanwhile, Diana is also being wooed by Pasha Achmed, her fianc√©'s unscrupulous Egyptian business associate. In order to arrange to be alone with Diana, Pasha persuades Gerald to leave Cairo and inspect the aqueduct they are building together. When Jamil learns of the deception, he blackmails his countryman to remain silent. Later Jamil uses his position as a servant to enter Diana's hotel bedroom, and kisses her in a moment of passion. Although she briefly returns his kiss, Diana angrily fires him.\\nSoon after, she and Gerald set out on a caravan across the desert with a new guide. Undaunted by Diana's rejection, Jamil follows and soon replaces the new guide. That night, Jamil's romantic singing has its effect on Diana, who is drawn into his arms again. When she realizes what is happening, she is outraged and strikes Jamil with a whip. On their way back to Cairo, however, Jamil sends the rest of the caravan on one route and tricks Diana into riding to Pasha's oasis retreat, where she is treated like royalty. When Pasha arrives, Jamil lies to him, telling him that Diana paid him to bring her to Pasha. When Pasha forces himself on her, she cries out for Jamil to save her, which he does, and the two ride off together in the night.","target":"Jamil El Shehab","rationale":"The full name of the person who kisses Diana in her hotel room is Jamil El Shehab, as stated at line 1."},{"source":"Given a passage and a query based on the passage, generate an unambiguous, concise and simple answer to the query from information in the passage. Note that the answer may not be present in exact form.\\n\\nAccording to the USDA: Storage Conditions: Lettuce should be quickly cooled and maintained as close to 0 ¬∞C (32 ¬∞F) as possible with 98 to 100% RH. Head types are better adapted to prolong storage than are the other types, but none keep longer than 4 weeks, and about half that time at 5 ¬∞C (41 ¬∞F). Squeeze the air out and close the bag. 5. The lettuce can now be stored in the fridge & should stay fresh at least a couple of weeks. You can take out what you need whenever you want to make a salad or sandwich & then just reseal the bag. Read more: http://pinchmysalt.com/a-recipe-for-keeping-lettuce-fresh-and-crisp/ [...] How long does lettuce last? Use our food expiration tables, tips and FAQs to get the maximum shelf life of your lettuce. I wash all my greens (except iceberg lettuce) when I get them home. I separate the leaves and let them sit in a sinkful of cool water for 5 minutes or so. Then I rinse them well and drain well. I wrap them in a clean kitchen towel or paper towels and put into a plastic bag, closing the bag good. Then I store it in the vegetable drawer in the fridge. It usually lasts a good week. For iceberg lettuce I ususally try to wash it at least a couple of hours before I use it by removing the core and letting cool water run into the head. Let it drain for a few minutes, then wrap it in paper towels and put in a plastic bag, then into the fridge to crisp for a couple of hours. It gets really nice and crispy. The Problem: Sad, Wilted Lettuce. Turns out that wilted lettuce is a common problem ‚Äî especially when buying tender greens like mesclun and spring mix. No one wants to have to pick through gross leaves or toss out a bag just a few days after purchase. Our readers chimed in on their favorite ways to keep lettuce fresh in this post. Read the post: How Do I Keep Salad Greens Fresh? We Tested Three Methods. After looking at all the advice, I decided to buy a large bag of mesclun to test out three different methods that supposedly keep lettuce fresh. It is a lot cheaper to buy a couple heads of lettuce than the pre-washed stuff, but the pre-washed is more conveinent and lasts longer than just a head of lettuce. Oh yeah, I am talking about iceberg lettuce. My ideal time would be to prepare it on a sunday night and have it last through friday. Dan The Produce Man from Dan's Fresh Produce in Alameda, CA tells us how we can keep lettuce fresh for 3 to 4 weeks in the refrigerator. Dan The Produce Man from Dan's Fresh Produce in Alameda, CA tells us how we can keep lettuce fresh for 3 to 4 weeks in the refrigerator. Category Entertainment Washing lettuce may win as my most hated kitchen task. But if I wash the lettuce right when I get home (I use a spinner, but you can also just spread it out on the counter), place it in one layer on a kitchen towel, and then roll it up into a kitchen towel-lettuce spiral (see above), each leaf stays unimaginably crisp and fresh in the vegetable drawer for up to a week. Put your lettuce into a nice big bowl, and drape a paper towel or two over the top so moisture doesn't settle on the leaves while your salad sits in the fridge. Cover the whole thing with a really tight seal of plastic wrap, and store. A little salt and pepper or seasoning can punch up the flavor‚Äîas long as you add it before serving! Usually sellers hold the lettuce at room temperature during the hours of sale (to show to buyers) and place them in the refrigerator in the night. But attention. The supermarkets assemble the heads under plastic films (as said), which retain moisture, and daily keep them anyway in departments fresh. Query: how long does romaine lettuce keep in the refrigerator","target":"You can keep romaine lettuce fresh for 3 to 4 weeks in the refrigerator","rationale":"Here's an direct answer: You can keep romaine lettuce fresh for 3 to 4 weeks in the refrigerator, which is concise and unambiguous."},{"source":"Two analogies that signify affordances are given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Affordance is the possibility of an action being done on an object, for example book is an affordance of writing. The phrase \\"A : B\\" implies that B is an affordance of A. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate affordance of the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a single object without further explanation.\\n\\npet : cat. swat : ?","target":"fly","rationale":"A pet in this case is a cat, and an affordance of swat is a fly."},{"source":"Question: A black hole is much more massive than Earth so if a black hole got near Earth it would have (A) stronger gravity (B) weaker gravity\\n\\nDo not use A and B to answer the question but instead, choose between \\"Black Hole\\" and  \\"Earth\\".","target":"Black Hole","rationale":"The option Black Hole is the correct answer to this question.\\n- First, a black hole is much more massive than Earth so if it got near Earth its gravity would be stronger. So A can't be the right choice.\\n- Second, since \\"A\\" was incorrect that makes B true because weaker means less mass and if a black hole had less mass then it wouldn‚Äôt be called a ‚Äúblack hole‚Äù in the first place!"},{"source":"Given a travel related situation, and given a specific question about the situation, summarize the question into a title\\n\\nI received my Iranian visa two days ago. My plan was to go there for a week, but unexpectedly I have an extra week available (due to an event in Turkey being cancelled just recently). Therefore I would like to extend my stay in Iran - to be precise enter the country before the date I put in my application. The itinerary would change a bit too.\\n\\nIs this a problem? According to the date printed on it, my visa is valid for the entire period. Do I have to notify the embassy or the Police Department of Foreign Affairs or the party, I got my invitation from, about these changes?\\n\\nWhat is the best way to handle the situation? I don't want to run into any problems, but I also don't want to miss the chance of spending some extra days there.","target":"Travel changes with an Iranian visa","rationale":"The question pertains to a situation of traveling with and changing the details of an Iranian visa. Therefore, it is best summarized by the title \\"Travel changes with an Iranian visa\\""},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of integers. You should remove any integer that is not prime. A prime integer is an integer that is only divisible by '1' and itself. The output should be the list of prime numbers in the input list. If there are no primes in the input list an empty list (\\"[]\\") should be returned.\\n\\n[227, 375, 906]","target":"[227]","rationale":"The given list is [227, 375, 906]. The first element (227) is prime and should be kept in the resulting list. The second element (375) is not prime because it can be divided by 5 and 75. The third element (906) is not prime because it can be divided by 2 and 3. Therefore, the output will only include 227: [227]."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a list of integers. You need to find the median of the list of integers and return that as the output. The median is the middle value in the list of numbers such that half of the elements are less than the median and the other half of elements are greater than the median.\\n\\n[350, 475, 354, 291, 333, 160, 179, 206, 327, 319, 463, 462, 395, 416, 190, 147, 423, 119, 34, 45, 273, 141, 253, 325, 44]","target":"291","rationale":"The list of integers can be sorted in ascending order as follows: [34, 44, 45, 119, 141, 147, 160, 179, 190, 206, 253,...]. The median is the 14th element of the list: 291."},{"source":"To use stale tortilla chips. Put them on a baking sheet and put them in the oven for 10 minutes at 375 degrees. They'll come out like new.\\nDoes this phrase make sense?","target":"Yes","rationale":"Yes, this phrase makes sense.\\nThe stale tortilla chips can be made fresh again by putting them in the oven for 10 minutes at 375 degrees."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Big Picture Science (formerly titled Are We Alone?) is the SETI Institute's weekly science radio program, hosted by Senior Astronomer Seth Shostak and Molly Bentley, the executive producer of the radio show.\\n\\n- Germany, officially the Federal Republic of Germany, is a federal parliamentary republic in central-western Europe. It includes 16 constituent states, covers an area of , and has a largely temperate seasonal climate. With about 82 million inhabitants, Germany is the most populous member state of the European Union. After the United States, it is the second most popular immigration destination in the world. Germany's capital and largest metropolis is Berlin. Other major cities include Hamburg, Munich, Cologne, Frankfurt, Stuttgart and D√ºsseldorf.\\n\\n- The Neckar is a river in Germany, mainly flowing through the southwestern state of Baden-W√ºrttemberg, with a short section through Hesse. The Neckar is a major right tributary of the Rhine. Rising in the Black Forest near Villingen-Schwenningen in the \\"Schwenninger Moos\\" conservation area at a height of above sea level, it passes through Rottweil, Rottenburg am Neckar, Kilchberg, T√ºbingen, Wernau, N√ºrtingen, Plochingen, Esslingen, Stuttgart, Ludwigsburg, Marbach, Heilbronn and Heidelberg, before discharging into the Rhine at Mannheim, at above sea level. \\n\\n- The SETI Institute is a not-for-profit research organization whose mission is to explore, understand, and explain the origin and nature of life in the universe, and to apply the knowledge gained to inspire and guide present and future generations. It aims for discovery and for sharing knowledge as scientific ambassadors to the public, the press, and the government. SETI stands for the \\"search for extraterrestrial intelligence\\". The Institute consists of three primary centers: The Carl Sagan Center, devoted to the study of life in the universe, the Center for Education, focused on astronomy, astrobiology and space science for students and educators, and the Center for Public Outreach, producing \\"Big Picture Science,\\" the Institute's general science radio show and podcast, and \\"SETI Talks\\" weekly colloquium series. \\n\\n- Laurance R. Doyle ( born 1953 ) is an American scientist who received his Ph.D. from the Ruprecht Karl University of Heidelberg . He has worked at the SETI Institute since 1987 where he is a principal investigator and astrophysicist . His main area of study has been the formation and detection of extrasolar planets , but he has also worked on communications theory . In particular he has written on how patterns in animal communication relate to humans with an emphasis on cetaceans . He grew up on a dairy farm in Cambria , California and therefore did n't have much access to information about stars . But by reading books at the local library , Doyle was able to develop his knowledge in astronomy , and eventually obtain his Bachelor 's and Master 's of Science degrees in astronomy from San Diego State University . His first job was at the Jet Propulsion Laboratory as an imaging engineer , where he was in charge of analysing pictures of Jupiter and Saturn sent from the spacecraft Voyager . He moved to Heidelberg , Germany , to help analyse images of Halley 's Comet . He got his doctorate in Astrophysics at the University of Heidelberg . In May 2005 he appeared on a National Geographic Channel special titled Extraterrestrial . He also appeared in the episode \`\` Will We Survive First Contact '' , of The Science Channel series titled Morgan Freeman 's Through the Wormhole . Doyle is currently seeking to compare dolphin whistles and baby babble in an attempt to make predictions about extraterrestrial communications . He believes that by measuring the complexity of communications for different species on earth , we could get a good indication of how advanced an extraterrestrial signal is . His study determined that babies babble over 800 different sounds with the same amount of frequency as dolphins . As they grow older , those sounds decrease to around 50 and become more repetitious . The study found that baby dolphins develop similarly with regards to their whistling .\\n\\n- Heidelberg is a university city situated on the river Neckar in south-west Germany. At the 2015 census, its population was 156,257, with roughly a quarter of its population being students. \\n\\n- Carl Edward Sagan (November 9, 1934  December 20, 1996) was an American astronomer, cosmologist, astrophysicist, astrobiologist, author, science popularizer, and science communicator in astronomy and other natural sciences. He is best known for his work as a science popularizer and communicator. His best known scientific contribution is research on extraterrestrial life, including experimental demonstration of the production of amino acids from basic chemicals by radiation. Sagan assembled the first physical messages sent into space: the Pioneer plaque and the Voyager Golden Record, universal messages that could potentially be understood by any extraterrestrial intelligence that might find them. Sagan argued the now accepted hypothesis that the high surface temperatures of Venus can be attributed to and calculated using the greenhouse effect.\\n\\n\\n\\nAfter reading the paragraphs above, choose the best answer for the entity that related to 'laurance doyle' with the relationship of 'occupation'.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- astrobiology\\n - astronomer\\n - astrophysicist\\n - author\\n - cosmologist\\n - executive producer\\n - major\\n - member\\n - producer\\n - research\\n - science","target":"astronomer","rationale":"The paragraph mentions that Doyle has worked at the SETI Institute as an astrophysicist since 1987. It also states that his main area of study is in extrasolar planets and communications theory, which are both fields involved with astronomy (the science of celestial objects). The word \\"astronomer\\" best describes this role among the given options because it refers to a person who studies astronomy for a living.\\nSo, the answer is astronomer."},{"source":"Answer this question: who is the mayor of chicago 2011?","target":"Rahm Emanuel won the race for mayor with more than 55% of the vote.","rationale":"Rahm Emanuel won the race for mayor with more than 55% of the vote. \\nThat is a direct answer, so it's fine to use."},{"source":"Africa has indeed turned the corner. A continent once synonymous with death, disease and destruction is showing signs of improvement. Virtually unscathed by the global financial slowdown, the African continent boasts some of the fastest growing economies in the world. Nigeria, Ghana and Tanzania are some of the countries leading the way in this exclusive economic growth club. With a combined population size of 1 billion, 70% under the age of 30 and an annual spend of $600 billion, the African continent is an attractive business proposition for any investor. It comes as no surprise then that the U.S. is making huge strides to accommodate Africans. Hosting one of the largest gatherings of African Leaders in Washington, the U.S. is showing the world -- and sending a signal to its closest rival, China -- that it can and will have African influence, which it can convert into commercial opportunities that can translate to receipts.\\n@highlight\\nAfrica Summit has confirmed U.S. ambition to make up lost ground in the continent\\n@highlight\\nIt comes after a decade of breathtaking Chinese acceleration across Africa\\n@highlight\\nThe continent holds big promise but unemployment, security and health scares are still challenges\\n@highlight\\nJob creation is key for the U.S. to claw back China's grip on the African continent\\nThe @placeholder government will have to put security at the top of it agenda as American businesses expand operation across the African continent.\\n\\nI am trying to decide what \\"@placeholder\\" means in the previous text.\\nHelp by choosing an option between:\\n- Africa\\n- Africa Summit\\n- African\\n- African Leaders\\n- Africans\\n- China\\n- Chinese\\n- Ghana\\n- Nigeria\\n- Tanzania\\n- U.S.\\n- Washington","target":"U.S.","rationale":"Given the context, we can see that \\"U.S.\\" is mentioned as making huge strides to accommodate Africans. The article also mentions a summit in Washington between U.S and African leaders where they discuss commercial opportunities for both parties -- exchanging influence for receipts from business deals with African countries.\\nThus, given this context about America's growing role in Africa, \\"@placeholder\\" should be replaced by \\"U.S."},{"source":"Categorize the comment on the basis of obscenity. If the comment is obscene output Yes, otherwise output No.\\n\\n\\"To find a better health-care model, we don‚Äôt have to turn our gaze north, in the usual direction, to Canada, or across the pond to the UK and other European countries, or even limit ourselves to calling for ‚ÄúMedicare for all.‚Äù Eight million of us already have something better than Medicare and more akin to the UK‚Äôs National Health Service, right here, in America‚Äîwith the private-insurance industry almost completely eliminated from the equation. The real question we need to ask was posed just last month by an obviously impressed UK physician, during an NHS study visit to the VHA in West Haven: ‚ÄúWhy,‚Äù he wondered out loud, ‚Äúdo you have to be a veteran to get this level of care in America? Why isn‚Äôt it available to all Americans?‚Äù Why indeed. \\"\\n\\nhttp://prospect.org/article/why-veterans-health-system-better-you-think","target":"No","rationale":"The given comment is about healthcare policy and does not contain any obscenities or offensive language. Therefore, the answer should be \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Please answer this question: who hit the fastest century in test cricket?","target":"Chris Gayle","rationale":"Chris Gayle has the fastest century in Test cricket, scoring a ton off just 70 balls against Pakistan."},{"source":"Give me the correct facts to answer this: when did aldi originate?","target":"1961","rationale":"Aldi is a discount supermarket chain with over 10,000 stores in 20 countries. The first Aldi (Albrecht Discount) store opened in Essen Germany on the 19th of June 1961 by brothers Karl and Theo Albrecht.\\nThe suggested answer \\"1961\\" can be validated through various credible sources such as Wikipedia which provides details about the company's history dating back to its foundation year:"},{"source":"I am hesitating between 4 options to answer the following question, which option should I choose?\\nQuestion: If a solid object is taken from Earth far into space, which of the following measurements of the object will change most?\\nPossibilities:\\n- density\\n- mass\\n- volume\\n- weight","target":"weight","rationale":"Mass is a measure of the amount of matter in an object. On Earth, mass and weight are dependent on gravity to give us measurements. In space, there is no gravitational force acting upon objects like it does on earth; therefore its mass would remain constant while being taken into space far away from any planet or star with significant gravitational pull because the only factor that affects mass: quantity of matter inside an object has not changed since leaving Earth's orbit.\\nDensity measures how tightly packed together particles are within an object (mass per unit volume). Since we have established that taking our solid object far into space will not change its mass (since minimal gravitational forces act upon it), density cannot be affected either by going into outer-space as long as this process doesn't introduce new variables such as extreme"},{"source":"\\"Mark told Pete many lies about himself, which Pete included in his book. He should have been more truthful.\\" is a true sentence.\\n\\nDoes this mean that \\"Mark should have been more truthful.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"yes","rationale":"The first statement is a premise, which states that Mark told Pete many lies about himself. The second sentence also mentions the same fact and then goes on to say: \\"He should have been more truthful.\\" This means that it was not only Mark who was being dishonest but even Pete included those lies in his book without any verification. Since both parties were equally responsible for being dishonest, they are blamed together as one by saying \\"Mark should have been more truthful\\". Hence, this implication may be true, so we can choose 'yes'."},{"source":"A friend asked me to answer this question: Who is Steve's partner?, using the article: The film opens with Elaine, a beautiful young witch, driving to Arcata, California, to start a new life after the death of her husband Jerry. It is heavily implied that Elaine murdered him. Once there, she rents a room in a Victorian home owned by Elaine's mentor Barbara and kept up by its interior decorator, Trish Manning. In an attempt to befriend the young woman, Trish takes Elaine to a teahouse, where she is met by her husband Richard, who is instantly besotted with Elaine after meeting her gaze. Hoping to find a new lover, Elaine performs a ritual to find a new man and soon meets Wayne, a literature professor at the local college.\\nThe two travel to Wayne's cabin, where she gets him to drink a concoction containing hallucinogens. The two have sex, after which Wayne becomes emotional and clingy, which proves to be a turnoff for Elaine. He dies the next day and Elaine buries his body along with a witch bottle. She decides that the next man she will try to seduce will be Richard. While Trish is away, Elaine invites him over to her apartment, where she also serves him a concoction. Afterwards, Richard becomes obsessed with Elaine, causing her to break up with him.\\nUnbeknownst to Elaine, one of Wayne's colleagues has reported him missing, leading to police officer Griff to investigate and discover Wayne's body and Elaine's witch bottle. He traces it to Elaine, but falls in love with her and initially refuses to believe that she would be capable of murder, much to the ire of his partner Steve. Elaine shares his love and believes him to be the man of her dreams, even going so far as to hold a mock wedding with her coven at a Renaissance faire., what would be the answer ?","target":"Griff","rationale":"The article is about Elaine, a woman who moves to Arcata after her husband's death. She rents an apartment from Barbara and befriends Trish. The friend asks \\"who is Steve's partner?\\" Since the article doesn't mention any character named Steve, we can deduce that he must be Griff's partner"},{"source":"In this task, you're given four sentences of a story written in natural language. The given story is not complete and your job is to complete the story by selecting one of the sentence choices from (A) and (B), such that the story sounds fully coherent.\\n\\nSentence1: Juan wanted to make tacos for his family tonight. Sentence2: He went to the grocery store and bought the ingredients. Sentence3: As he was preparing dinner he realized he forgot the tortillas! Sentence4: He wanted to go back to the store but it was closed. \\n (A) Juan's mother showed him how to make a taco casserole instead. (B) Juan went back to the store.","target":"A","rationale":"The story ends with the protagonist not being able to get tortillas, so in order for it to make sense and be finished, the sentence choice should contain a solution to this problem. Sentence (A) provides a solution by showing that Juan's mother shows him how to make a taco casserole instead. This makes sense as an ending because it is logical that his mother would know how to solve this problem. Sentence (B), however, does not provide a suitable ending because it doesn't explain what he did when he arrived at the store."},{"source":"Why did they buy those products in specific ?","target":"They need them to keep themselves clean .","rationale":"The passage mentions that the company makes products such as soap, deodorant and toothpaste. These are items used for personal hygiene and cleanliness because they help remove dirt from one's body or clothing. So buying these items means that the person wants to keep themselves clean which is option C in this question . \\nSo we can conclude by saying ,They need them to keep themselves clean ."},{"source":"You are provided with a list of converations between a \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\". Figure out if the conversation provided as \\"classify_text\\" is authored by \\"USER\\" or \\"ASSISTANT\\". There are maximum of 7 conversations between \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\" in each input\\n\\nASSISTANT: Can you tell me, what type of movies do you like? , USER: Yes, I like dramas, mysteries, and action. , ASSISTANT: why do you like dramas? , USER: I like dramas because I really like that , USER: with your own life , ASSISTANT: Can you tell me the title of one of your favorite movies?, classify_text: Yes. One of my favorite movies is A Quiet Place.","target":"USER","rationale":"Since the conversation is between the user and an assistant, it is obvious that the classify text can only be authored by either of them. If we see that in this conversation, there is no mention of 'user' in any of the previous conversations. Therefore, we can infer that the classify_text has been said by USER since ASSISTANT always prefaces with 'Can you tell me...'"},{"source":"My daughter was away at college preparing for her final exams and nursing boards. I knew that my daughter‚Äôs cat, who has been part of our family since my daughter was in second grade, was dying of a fast growing cancer. I couldn‚Äôt tell my daughter because I didn‚Äôt want to upset her and take her mind off her studies and impending graduation. Once our Vet determined that there was nothing further that could be done she showed me how to give pain meds and fluids at home to keep her comfortable in hopes that she would live long enough to allow my daughter to say goodbye after her graduation. The entire week I stayed with our cat around the clock. She had completely stopped eating and drinking and was slowly dying before my eyes. She slept most of the time except when I had to put the needle in between her shoulder blades to give her fluids. Then she would cry quietly and look at me with pleading eyes. Her breathing was becoming so shallow that I had to get close to her and listen to see if she was still alive. After a week of this I began to realize that the most unselfish thing I could do for this beautiful creature was to let her go. I wrapped her in her favorite blanket and and drove her to our Vets office after they had closed for the day. She was so skinny and frail but when I held her close she still purred. I thanked her for the 14 years she had been one of my daughter‚Äôs closest companions and I held her as she took her last breath. I was afraid my daughter was going to be angry with me when I told her that i made the decision with out giving her time to say goodbye. She was sad but understood that I did the kindest thing I could have done for her kitty.\\nQuestion: When did the cat get sick?\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. While the daughter was studying for college graduation\\n\\nB. When the daughter had accepted her first job\\n\\nC. While the daughter was studying for high school graduation\\n\\nD. not enough information\\n\\n===\\nThe correct answer is","target":"A","rationale":"The cat was diagnosed \\"with a fast growing cancer\\" and there is no mention of the length of time between diagnosis and death. The daughter only had her final exams left to take, suggesting that she would be graduating imminently, but nothing in the passage suggests when the graduation will occur. Therefor it can not safely be assumed that A) or B) are correct choices, so they should both be eliminated as answers."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people. 'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. If the conversation begins with a question, label it '1' otherwise '0'.\\n\\n Person1:     Oh , my god . How can you stand living in such a messy dorm ?  \\n Person2:  Our place is spotlessly clean , compared with others .  \\n Person1:      Have you even tried to clean it once since you moved in at the beginning of the semester ?  \\n Person2:  In fact , I just swept the floor three days ago .  \\n Person1:      I think we need to restart the dormitory sanitation inspection system .  \\n Person2:  I bet nobody will care about it .","target":"1","rationale":"The conversation in the example begins with a question, so the answer is '1'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question. Your task is to generate an answer that is relevant to the question.\\n\\nDo you enjoy any genre of books?","target":"Fantasy is my favorite","rationale":"The answer is \\"Fantasy is my favorite\\" because it answers the question of whether or not there are any genres of books that the user enjoys."},{"source":"Multi-select: Let's say that \\"In the storm, the tree fell down and crashed through the roof of my house. Now, I have to get it removed.\\"\\n\\nCan we now say that \\"Now I have to get The tree removed.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"yes","rationale":"The first sentence mentions that the tree fell down and smashed through a roof. The second statement is simply an elaboration on this, adding more detail about how to rectify the issue. So both statements are true, so yes it's possible to say \\"Now I have to get the tree removed.\\""},{"source":"Short general knowledge question: what years did the yankees win the championship?","target":"1938 World Series","rationale":"The New York Yankees won the 1938 World Series."},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: John journeyed to the bedroom. Mary moved to the garden. Question: Where is John?","target":"bedroom","rationale":"We can be infer from the passage that John journeyed to the bedroom and Mary moved to the garden."},{"source":"Pick the option in line with common sense to answer the question.\\nQuestions: What are you trying to achieve when you're talking?\\nOptions:\\n- opera\\n- making sound\\n- people to listen\\n- attempting to communicate\\n- dry mouth","target":"attempting to communicate","rationale":"The purpose of talking is to communicate, so the answer is 'attempting to communicate'."},{"source":"Write the response. DIALOG:\\nWas Affirmed the favorite in the Kentucky Derby?\\n- Alydar was made the 6-5 favorite for Kentucky Derby, with Affirmed the second choice at 9-5.\\n- Was the 1978 Kentucky Derby with Affirmed a close race?\\n- Affirmed won the Kentucky Derby by 1 1‚ÅÑ2 lengths.\\n- How much did Affirmed win the Preakness by?\\n- Affirmed held a short lead entering the stretch and held it to defeat Alydar by a neck.\\n- Was the 1978 Belmont with Affirmed a close race as well?\\n-","target":"Affirmed rallied in the final stride to win by a nose.","rationale":"The output to the given conversation should be \\"Affirmed rallied in the final stride to win by a nose\\". This is because the conversation is about Affirmed winning the Belmont Stakes. The user asks if it was a close race and if so, how much did Affirmed beat Alydar by? Therefore, an appropriate response would be that Affirmed rallied in the final stride to win by a nose."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: Thrust is the force pushing a rocket. Sentence 2: and push or thrust hoes, also called Dutch hoes.","target":"neutral","rationale":"Statement 2 defines \\"push\\" and describes how it is used to make hoe blades. The sentence does not provide any information about the term ‚Äúthrust‚Äù or its use in rocket science, so there is no direct connection between Statement 1 and Statement 2. Also, the premise does not provide enough evidence to support or refute the definition of thrust provided in statement one. As a result, Statement 2 neither supports nor refutes Statement 1; therefore, an answer of \\"neutral\\" should be returned for this pair of statements.\\""},{"source":"When someone points their transistor radio to the sky, what are they hoping to hear transmissions from?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptionsÔºö\\n\\nA. every car and house\\n\\nB. bedroom\\n\\nC. space shuttle\\n\\nD. shop\\n\\nE. ufo","target":"C","rationale":"The above question is asking the user to identify a possible source of transmissions that someone may hope to receive while pointing their transistor radio at the sky. According to NASA, space shuttles in orbit around Earth and on missions beyond our atmosphere use various communication systems for transmitting signals during flight operations. The only option available which describes an object capable of sending out transmission from outer space is C: Space shuttle.\\nSo, according to this context, we can infer that when someone points their transistor radio toward the sky they are hoping to hear transmissions from a space shuttle."},{"source":"Math problem: Solve 374*t = 548*t - 4524 for t.\\nWhat is the solution?","target":"26","rationale":"374*t = 548*t - 4524\\n\\nSubtract 374 from both sides:\\n\\n548 * t - 374 * t = -4524 + 374\\n174 * t = -4,150 \\n\\n Divide both sides by 174 to solve for 't':\\n\\n \`(5482)/(-4150)\`   or    \`-26/17\`     ... the solution is negative!"},{"source":"Given a question and a context passage, generate the answer having the word or phrase from the context passage. Here, the answer should be a shortest continous span from the passage.\\n\\nContext: Viroids, subviral pathogens of plants, are composed of a single-stranded circular RNA of 246-399 nucleotides. Within the 27 viroids sequenced, avocado sunblotch, peach latent mosaic and chrysanthemum chlorotic mottle viroids (ASBVd, PLMVd and CChMVd, respectively) can form hammerhead structures in both of their polarity strands. These ribozymes mediate self-cleavage of the oligomeric RNAs generated in the replication through a rolling circle mechanism, whose two other steps are catalyzed by an RNA polymerase and an RNA ligase. ASBVd, and presumably PLMVd and CChMVd, replicate and accumulate in the chloroplast, whereas typical viroids replicate and accumulate in the nucleus. PLMVd and CChMVd do not adopt a rod-like or quasi rod-like secondary structure as typical viroids do but have a highly branched conformation. A pathogenicity determinant has been mapped in a defined region of the CChMVd molecule. \\n Question: Which are the smallest known subviral pathogens of plants?","target":"viroids","rationale":"The context passage indicates that viroids are the smallest known subviral pathogens of plants."},{"source":"Coming off their road win over the Chiefs, the Chargers went home, donned their alternate uniforms, and played a Week 8 divisional rematch with the Oakland Raiders.  In the first quarter, San Diego struck first as running back LaDainian Tomlinson got a 6-yard touchdown run.  The Raiders would answer in the second quarter with a 3-yard touchdown run by running back Justin Fargas, yet the Chargers stormed on as quarterback Philip Rivers hooked up wide receiver Vincent Jackson on an 8-yard touchdown pass, followed by Tomlinson getting a 10-yard touchdown run.  Oakland would close out the half with a 48-yard field goal by kicker Sebastian Janikowski. In the second half, the Raiders would slowly try to rally as Janikowski nailed a 41-yard field goal in the third quarter and a 41-yard field goal in the fourth.  Afterwards, San Diego pulled away as kicker Nate Kaeding booted a 28-yard field goal. With their 13th-straight win over Oakland, the Chargers improved to 4-3.\\nAnswer this question: Which player was the first to score?","target":"LaDainian Tomlinson","rationale":"In the given article, it is said that LaDainian Tomlinson got a 6-yard touchdown run in the first quarter. Therefore we can conclude that he was the first to score."},{"source":"Problem: Solve -30*i = 216 - 276 for i.\\nAnd the answer is...","target":"2","rationale":"First, we need to simplify the equation by adding 276 on both sides:\\n\\n-30i + 276 = 216 - 276 + 276\\n\\nCombining like terms, we get:\\n\\n 246  = -30i\\n\\n Then divide both sides by [- 30 ] :\\n\\n [ 8 1]   x= i ---> (1)\\n\\n Hence, our final solution is x = 8. ^2^5/1957\\" ,tags:\\"Math\\",subcategory_id:'',difficulty_level:'EASY'},{problem_statement:\\""},{"source":"Exercise: Extract from the text the correct entity that \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to.\\n\\nSan Diego (CNN) -- Another Bush? Another Clinton? In reporting on the 2016 presidential campaign, much of the media will likely echo the theme that Barbara Bush set forth during a C-SPAN interview in January, in which the former first lady said that -- while she believed that her son, former Florida Gov. Jeb Bush, was \\"the best qualified person to run for president \\" -- Americans should widen the pool of applicants. \\"I think this is a great American country, great country, and if we can't find more than two or three families to run for high office, that's silly,\\" she said.\\n@highlight\\nRuben Navarrette: Aside from famous names, Bush, Clinton share a problem\\n@highlight\\nNeither Jeb nor Hillary can say succintly why they want to be president, he says\\n@highlight\\nThey don't connect with people on an emotional level as Bill Clinton, George W. Bush did, he says\\nWhether he is talking about immigration or economic development, @placeholder likes to use the word: \\"aspirational.\\"","target":"Jeb Bush","rationale":"\\"@placeholder\\" refers to the subject of \\"likes\\". From this, we can conclude that Jeb Bush likes using the word aspirational."},{"source":"After a win over the Bengals, the Browns stayed home for a Thursday Night duel against the Bills.  The Bills scored first when Fred Jackson ran for a 1-yard touchdown for a 7-0 lead followed up by Dan Carpenter nailing a 52-yard field goal increasing their lead to 10-0.  In the second quarter, it was all Browns as Billy Cundiff kicked a 33-yard field goal for a 10-3 game.  They eventually tied the game up and moved into the lead when Willis McGahee ran for a 1-yard touchdown for a 10-10 game followed up by Travis Benjamein returning a punt 79 yards for a touchdown for a halftime score of 17-10.  In the third quarter, the Bills tied it up and took the lead back when C.J. Spiller ran for a 54-yard touchdown for a 17-17 game followed up by McGahee running for another 1-yard touchdown for a 24-17 lead.  The Browns however later on in the quarter, tied it back up as Brandon Weeden hooked up with Josh Gordon for a 37-yard pass for a 24-24 game.  In the fourth quarter, it was all Browns as Cundiff made field goals from 24 and 44 yards out for leads of 27-24 and 30-24 before sealing the game when T.J. Ward returned an interception 44 yards for a touchdown and for the final score of 37-24.\\n\\nAnswer this question based on the article: How many yards were the two longest touchdowns combined?","target":"133","rationale":"The two longest touchdowns in the article are Travis Benjamin's 79-yard punt return touchdown and C.J. Spiller's 54-yard rushing touchdown, which totals to 133 yards combined."},{"source":"Trying to snap a three-game skid, the Chiefs went home for a Week 12 AFC West rematch with the Oakland Raiders.  In the first quarter, Kansas City trailed early as Raiders kicker Sebastian Janikowski managed to get a 25-yard field goal.  Afterwards, the Chiefs regained the lead as rookie RB Kolby Smith managed to get a 10-yard TD run.  In the second quarter, Oakland played catch-up as Janikowski kicked a 54-yard field goal.  Kansas City improved its lead before halftime as kicker Dave Rayner nailed a 30-yard field goal. In the third quarter, the Raiders regained the lead with RB LaMont Jordan getting a 5-yard TD run.  The Chiefs would respond with Smith getting a 5-yard TD run.  However, in the fourth quarter, Oakland regained the lead with RB Justin Fargas getting a 14-yard TD run.  Kansas City tried to come back, but the Raiders held on for the win. With their fourth-straight loss, not only did the Chiefs fall to 4-7, but it snapped their nine-game winning streak against the Raiders.  This would be the first time since 2004 that Kansas City had dropped four-straight games. Kolby Smith, in his first game starting in absence of Larry Johnson, had 31 carries for 150&#160;yards on the day.\\n\\nAsk a question about this article.","target":"Who was the injured Chiefs running back that did not play?","rationale":"In order to answer the question \\"Who was the injured Chiefs running back that did not play?\\" in this article, we need to search for any information regarding a player who is hurt and cannot play. In one sentence of this article, it says Kolby Smith started playing instead of Larry Johnson because he was injured. So based on this passage, we could conclude that Larry Johnson was an injured Chiefs running back so he couldn't play during Week 12 AFC West match with Oakland Raiders."},{"source":"Answer the question...when did the fault in our stars movie come out??","target":"June 6, 2014","rationale":"The movie was released on June 6, 2014."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. You need to find all the elements of the list that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\n\\n['y', '4549', '5713', 'u', 'K', 'v', 'm']","target":"10262","rationale":"In the given list ['y', '4549', '5713', 'u', 'K', 'v','m'], there are only two elements that are numbers: 4549 and 5713. The sum of these two is 10262."},{"source":"Here's a short story: Harry learned that a hot pan has lower resistance then a placement when he was sliding an ice cube across different surfaces. The ice cube moved faster across the (A) hot pan (B) placemat.\\n\\nWhat is the most sensical answer between \\"hot pan\\" and  \\"placemat\\"?","target":"hot pan","rationale":"The context of the situation is that Harry learned about resistance and how it can affect an ice cube sliding across a surface.\\nHarry may have observed that when he slid the ice cube across two different surfaces, one being a hot pan and another being a placemat, the ice cube moved faster on one than the other. It was probably moving faster on the hotter surface because heat decreases resistance (i.e., potential energy). Since this would make sense in terms of physics, option A (hot pan) makes more sense than option B (placemat), so \\"A\\" should be chosen as correct answer."},{"source":"You are given a target profession, and two sentences. Your task is to determine whether the second sentence is either a stereotype, anti-stereotype, or is unrelated with respect to the first sentence and the target. A stereotype is a widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. An anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against the widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. Sentences and targets are unrelated if there is no relevance between them.\\n\\nTarget: musician \\nBeing a musician is an exciting job. They are all rich rock stars.","target":"stereotype","rationale":"The second sentence is a stereotype. While musicians may vary in their socioeconomic status, the sentence \\"They are all rich rock stars.\\" implies that all musicians are rich rock stars, which is an oversimplified view of the profession."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a short story with a beginning, two potential middles, and an ending. Your job is to choose the middle statement that makes the story incoherent / implausible by indicating 1 or 2 in the output. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nBeginning: The teacher took her students on a field trip. Middle 1: They did not get home on time. Middle 2: They learned and had fun. Ending: Their parents were mad.","target":"2","rationale":"Middle 1 indicates that the students did not get home on time, so their parents would be mad. Middle 2 also indicates that the students learned and had fun on the field trip, so there is no reason for their parents to be mad. Therefore Middle 2 makes less sense compared to Middle 1."},{"source":"Over time a species of bird has changed a lot. Originally the climate the bird lived in changed so they adapted and more of them were seen to have heavy down feathers for warmth. Later down the line it got warmer, some of the birds stayed in the warmer area and adapted to it growing thinner feathers. Some of the others decided to migrate to colder areas instead. More time passed and the birds in the warmer area eventually evolved into a very dangerous creature with sharp talons to defend itself from predators. The birds that moved to the colder environment had less predators so they remained basically harmless..\\n\\nWhich birds is likely a case of speciation, the birds living in the cold area or the warm area?","target":"warm area","rationale":"A species is defined as a group of organisms that are able to interbreed and produce fertile offspring. Speciation occurs when one species splits into two or more distinct groups, which eventually become so genetically dissimilar that members of the same original species can no longer breed with each other.\\nIn this example, over time the bird in question grew heavy feathers for warmth. However, later on it got warmer so some birds stayed in the warm area while others migrated to colder areas instead. The birds who remained in their native habitat evolved dangerous talons whereas those migrating did not develop any such features since they had fewer predators there compared to those living in their native habitats. As these differences continued over generations across different regions where migrations happened, speciation eventually occurred between them due to genetic isolation - meaning"},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: Mercury is the smallest planet in our solar system. Sentence 2: Ganymede is the biggest moon in the solar system and bigger than the planets Mercury and Pluto.","target":"neutral","rationale":"Statement 1 states that \\"Mercury is the smallest planet in our solar system\\", and Statement 2 states that \\"Ganymede is the biggest moon in the solar system and bigger than the planets Mercury and Pluto\\". The premise provides information about Ganymede, which is a moon rather than a planet, so it does not provide any evidence to support or refute Statement 1. As a result, there is no entailment between these two statements, so the output should be \\"neutral\\"."},{"source":"What's the answer to that question: what car models does gm make?","target":"Cadillac","rationale":"Cadillac is a brand of luxury cars and SUVs manufactured by General Motors.\\n    \\"\\""},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage. The passage will not have a direct answer to the question, but can include some information and a clue for the answer. Assuming you can only obtain information about one entity in the passage, your job is to determine whether information from the passage can be used to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: How many passengers did the airport where China Airlines is headquarter handle in 2017? Passage:China Airlines (CAL) () is the national carrier of Taiwan (officially the Republic of China, hence the \\"China\\" name), and one of its two major airlines along with EVA Air. It is headquartered in Taiwan Taoyuan International Airport and operates over 1400 flights weekly (including 91 pure cargo flights) to 102 cities across Asia, Europe, North America and Oceania. Carrying over 19 million passengers and 5700 tons of cargo in 2017, the carrier was the 33rd and 10th largest airline in the world in terms of passenger revenue per kilometer (RPK) and freight RPK, respectively. China Airlines has three airline subsidiaries: China Airlines Cargo, a member of SkyTeam Cargo, operates a fleet of freighter aircraft and manages its parent airline's cargo-hold capacity; Mandarin Airlines operates flights to domestic and low-demand regional destinations; Tigerair Taiwan is a low-cost carrier established by China Airlines and Singaporean airline group Tigerair Holdings, but is now wholly owned by China Airlines Group.","target":"a","rationale":"The question asks how many passengers did the airport handle, but does not specify which airport. The passage mentions that China Airlines is headquartered in Taiwan Taoyuan International Airport, so one can answer the question by looking up the number of passengers that airport handles."},{"source":"You are given a new situation: Rob knows a brilliant scientist who has made a time machine. One day, the scientist let Rob travel time with his machine. Rob noticed that the machine had four gears, gear A, gear B, gear C, and gear D. Rob started with Gear A, which represented the present time. Then he pushed the gear to gear B, which was 600 million years from now. Then he further pushed the gear to gear C, which brought him to 800 million years from now. Finally, he pushed the gear to gear D, which brought him to 1.1 billion years from now. Though he traveled time, Rob was always on Earth all the time.\\n\\nand a hint : In the long term, the greatest changes in the Solar System will come from changes in the Sun itself as it ages. As the Sun burns through its supply of hydrogen fuel, it gets hotter and burns the remaining fuel even faster. As a result, the Sun is growing brighter at a rate of ten percent every 1.1 billion years. In about 600 million years, the Sun brightness will have disrupted the Carbon Cycle to the point that trees and forests (C3 photosynthetic plant life) will no longer be able to survive and in around 800 million years, the Sun will have killed all complex life on the Earth's surface and in the oceans. In 1.1 billion years' time, the Sun's increased radiation output will cause its circumstellar habitable zone to move outwards, making the Earth's surface too hot for liquid water to exist there naturally. At this point, all life will be reduced to single celled organisms. Evaporation of water, a potent greenhouse gas, from the oceans' surface could accelerate temperature increase, potentially ending all life on Earth even sooner. During this time, it is possible that as Mars's surface temperature gradually rises, carbon dioxide and water currently frozen under the surface regolith will release into the atmosphere, creating a greenhouse effect that will heat the planet until it achieves conditions parallel to Earth today, providing a potential future abode for life. By 3.5 billion years from now, Earth's surface conditions will be similar to those of Venus today.\\n\\nPlease answer this question : When Rob would see more plant species, gear A or gear B?","target":"gear A","rationale":"As the Sun burns through its supply of hydrogen fuel, it gets hotter and burns the remaining fuel even faster. As a result, the Sun is growing brighter at a rate of ten percent every 1.1 billion years. In about 600 million years, the Sun brightness will have disrupted the Carbon Cycle to the point that trees and forests (C3 photosynthetic plant life) will no longer be able to survive\\nRob would see more plant species in gear A which represents present time as he started with this"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: threat and non-threat. Threat is a statement that someone will be hurt or harmed, especially if the person does not do something in particular.\\n\\nComment: A perfect example of the tail wagging the dog. It is insane that realtors can now effectively tell FINTRAC what to put in their warnings. The government needs to do something about realtors (and developers). They who are ruining the two biggest cities west of Quebec in pursuit of the almighty dollar. That they cloak themselves in the flag to do so is just sickening. All IMHO of course.","target":"Non-threat","rationale":"The given comment does not contain any threats. It criticizes the actions of realtors and developers in Vancouver and Toronto, but it is not a threat to anyone. Therefore, the answer is \\"Non-threat\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an utterance, which is a part of a conversation between a user and an agent. Your job is to detect the speaker. The user usually commands the agent to schedule events, retrieve event information, and check the schedule. While the agent's response is an answer to the user's questions or follow-up questions on the user's command. Answer with \\"User\\" or \\"Agent\\".\\n\\nno i meant the annual general meeting ,chand the dates from 23rd to 7th may","target":"user","rationale":"The given utterance is a part of a conversation between a user and an agent. The user commands the agent to change the dates of the annual general meeting from 23rd to 7th May. Therefore, the answer is \\"user\\"."},{"source":"You are given a short poem which is written by a kid. Your task is to predict if the kid is in elementary school or high school. Anyone who is from grade 1st to 6th-grade will be considered as in elementary school, and 7th to 12th-grade kids will be considered as in high school. There are only two possible outputs, i.e., elementary and high. All inputs have at least one output and it cannot have both categories at a time.\\n\\nwhen iam lock in the tower you come and save my life oh win day i wish you would ask me to be your wife you be my day and night i wake up every morning feeling free and delight a wake up every morning wonder what ive do wrong every time i sing you be the lyric to my song","target":"high","rationale":"The level of writing makes it clear that the kid is in high school."},{"source":"Test for natural language inference.\\nPremise: \\"Hikers traverse a snowy field in front of a mountain.\\"\\nHypothesis: \\"It is 100 degrees out.\\"\\nIs the hypothesis entailed by the premise?\\n\\n[Options]\\n- yes\\n- no\\n- it is not possible to tell","target":"no","rationale":"A snowy field would melt if it was 100 degrees out."},{"source":"As U.S. political candidates make their final appeals, voters in 35 states will decide policy issues Tuesday that include legalizing recreational use of marijuana and restricting access to guns and ammunition, voting yes or no on nearly 160 state ballot initiatives.\\nCalifornia's Proposition 64, which is leading in the polls, could create a multibillion-dollar marijuana industry by legalizing the recreational use the drug for adults in the state. Similar measures are on the ballot in Arizona, Nevada, Maine and Massachusetts.\\nMarijuana could be legalized for medical use in Florida and three other states. Medical marijuana is already permitted in half the 50 U.S. states, and recreational use is allowed in Alaska, Colorado, Washington state, Oregon and the District of Columbia.\\nMarijuana is banned under federal law, but U.S. officials have taken a hands-off approach on the issue.\\nVoters in Maine and Nevada are considering measures that would expand background checks for gun purchases, which is already required for buying guns from dealers, by extending the provision to private sales.\\nCalifornians will consider measures requiring background checks for buyers of ammunition and banning high-capacity ammunition magazines.\\nWashington state has a measure that would allow the courts to bar the sale of guns to individuals deemed an extreme risk to themselves or others.\\nCalifornians are considering whether to eliminate the death penalty with Proposition 62, or to maintain capital punishment and make the process more efficient with Proposition 66, which supporters say makes it more fair to victims of violent crimes.\\nTwenty states and the District of Columbia have abolished or overturned capital punishment on the grounds that it is unequally applied to minority populations and that innocent people are sometimes convicted.\\nSouth Dakotans will decide whether to make statewide offices nonpartisan and create a citizens commission to redraw voting districts after each 10-year national census, removing the task from legislators,...\\nQuestion: After the end of the story probably:\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. no more states vote on the death penalty\\n\\nB. Trump outlaws the death penalty in all states\\n\\nC. not enough information\\n\\nD. more states vote on the death penalty\\n\\n===\\nThe correct answer is","target":"D","rationale":"In the story, it is mentioned that California has two options on the death penalty. In one option, they can eliminate it and in another maintain capital punishment but change how it works. This suggests that there are more states voting on this measure along with other issues such as legalizing marijuana for recreational use, restricting access to guns and ammunition,... There is not enough information about what Trump wants or whether he'll succeed so A & B are incorrect answers. C would be correct if you didn't know any of these things from context clues throughout the article.\\nTherefore, a reasonable answer is D - More states vote on the death penalty"},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. If the count of numbers is more than that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers Win'. If the count of alphabets is more than that of numbers in the list, answer 'Alphabets Win'. If the count of numbers is same as that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers and Alphabets are Tied'.\\n\\n['5841', '2589', 'm', '8087', '4157', '3875', '5879', 'n', '2867', '4063', 's', '3399', 'M', 'y', '7729', 'x', '2223', 'T', '6707', '7573', 'S', '9785', '1211', 'O', 'd', 'a', '613', '271', 'w', '629', 'd', '4217', '985', 't', '5245', 'o', 'L', 'x', 'D', '9649', '8273', '3477', '3003', '7297', 'O', '1431', '8065', '5479', '6239', '845']","target":"Numbers Win","rationale":"There is a total of 36 numbers, and 28 alphabets in the given list. The number of numbers is greater than the number of alphabets. Therefore, the answer is 'Numbers Win'."},{"source":"You may wonder if there are other examples of static discharge. The answer is yes. Lightning is a form of static discharge. It is much more dramatic than what happens between you and the door knocker, but it is the same principle. You can see how it occurs in the following diagram and animation. You have no doubt seen lightning in a rainstorm. What does lighting have to do with static electricity? As it turns out, everything! During a rainstorm, clouds develop regions of different charges. This happens due to the movement of air molecules, water drops, and ice particles. The negative charges are concentrated at the base of the clouds. The positive charges are concentrated at the top. The negative charges repel electrons on the ground below. The ground then becomes positively charged. Over time the differences increase. Eventually the electrons are discharged. This is what we see as lightning. You can watch an awesome slow-motion lightning strike below. \\n\\nQuestion: What does lightning have to do with static electricity?\\nI think \\"Air molecules\\" is a valid answer. Could you confirm? Yes or no?","target":"No","rationale":"No. The answer is \\"Lighting has to do with static electricity\\"\\nThe statement that you provided as an explanation, i.e.\\"Air molecules move differently in clouds and grounds which causes building up of charge\\", does not explain why lightning has to do with static electricity."},{"source":"Solution 1: Blank printer paper works well.\\nSolution 2: Any printer paper works.\\n\\nGoal: What kind of paper should you use.\\n\\nGiven the goal, what is the correct solution?\\n\\nAnswer by copying the correct solution","target":"Blank printer paper works well.","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"Blank printer paper works well."},{"source":"Given a simple high-school level math question, you are required to solve it and provide the final answer. The final answer is always a single number. These questions can range from a variety of topics like simple arithmetic, solving equations, converting a quantity from one unit to another, finding remainders/GCD/LCM, finding probabilities etc. Each question has only one correct answer. This answer can be a positive or negative integer, a fraction or a decimal number. If the answer is a negative number use the hyphen (e.g. -42) symbol for the minus sign. For decimal numbers, do not add extra zeros after the decimal point. For fractional numbers, separate the numerator and denominator using a forward slash (e.g. 3/25).\\n\\nConvert 29.1925l to millilitres.","target":"29192.5","rationale":"1l = 1000ml\\\\n29.1925l = 29.1925 * 1000ml = 29192.5ml"},{"source":"In this task, you're given four sentences of a story written in natural language. The given story is not complete and your job is to complete the story by selecting one of the end sentence choices from (A) and (B), such that the story does not sound complete and coherent, i.e., select an incorrect end sentence.\\n\\nSentence1: Jaclyn came over to hang out with Robs girlfriend. Sentence2: Jaclyn and Rob do not get along. Sentence3: Rob tried very nice to keep the peace and be nice. Sentence4: Jaclyn kept saying very snide comments and remarks \\n (A) Rob finally left to hang out with his friends. (B) Rob was very happy about spending time with Jaclyn.","target":"B","rationale":"The story is about Rob's girlfriend hanging out with his friend Jaclyn, who he does not get along with. After the third sentence, it is clear that Rob tried to be friendly and nice, but Jaclyn kept saying snide comments. Therefore, the most likely ending for this story would be that Rob left to hang out with his friends (answer A) instead of spending time with Jaclyn (answer B)."},{"source":"Given news headlines, an edited word and funniness labels. The original sentence has word with the given format {word}. Create new headlines by replacing {word} in the original sentence with edit word. Your task is to generate answer \\"Yes\\" if an edited sentence matches funniness label, otherwise generate answer \\"No\\".  \\n\\nNews Headline: Carter Page : I 've never communicated with {Trump}  \\n Edit: aliens \\n Label: Funny","target":"Yes","rationale":"In this news headline, the edit word \\"aliens\\" replaces the original word {Trump}. The original sentence suggests that Carter Page has never communicated with Trump. However, if \\"aliens\\" is used instead of Trump in the edited sentence, then it implies that Carter Page has never communicated with aliens. This implies that he is unaware of alien activities on Earth or any other planet and hence can be considered as a funny statement. Therefore, answer should be Yes (i.e., an edited sentence matches funniness label)."},{"source":"In this task you are given an anecdote. You must find out whether the anecdote is something the author has done or is considering doing. Label the instances as \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and label them as \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future.\\n\\n Ok so I've (19f) been dating this guy (19m) for around two months now and everything has been going pretty good:) I got out of an emotionally, and semi-physical abusive relationship in August of last year, and my current boyfriend is the opposite to my ex, which is great. I only have one issue with my bf, and it's that everytime he compliments me, he calls me \\"hot\\".\\n\\nI know that this is a really stupid thing to bother me but I got 2 reasons why I dislike it. The first being that I think it is a sort-of objectifying term, and it makes me think that my body is the most important thing to him. I would much rather him call me \\"pretty\\", \\"beautiful\\", or \\"cute\\" because I think those compliments take my personality into consideration. I feel kind of uncomfortable if he sees my sex appeal as my defining trait. Don't get me wrong, I appreciate the thought behind the compliment and I find him really attractive too so I try to compliment his looks aswell. But the term \\"hot\\" seems to only focus on my body and sex appeal, and not to sound like a stereotype but I want our relationship to be deeper than that. (Another important note here is that me and my bf haven't had sex yet)\\n\\nThe other reason I don't like him calling me hot is because my ex used to use that term constantly to describe me. My ex coerced me into sex on two occasions before I found out he actually had a girlfriend who he was cheating on her with me. He used to get me incredibly drunk and then take advantage of me in some way, thankfully we only dated for a month. I never really realized it was an abusive relationship because he seemed so loving towards me, he constantly called me \\"hot\\". I remember specifically he would say \\"you're so hot you're making me so hard right now\\" to hint that I should give him a bj. I was 18 at the time and really wanted to save having my first time with a guy I knew really well and I wanted the relationship to be deeper than sex. Anyway the word \\"hot\\" was his go-to compliment and that's why it triggers me a little lmao.\\n\\nAnyway so I've been planning the next time my bf calls me \\"hot\\" to explain my reasons to him and ask him to use another word. I'm afraid it's gonna sound like I'm picky or ungrateful? I'm sorry if this is too small of an issue for this subreddit btw","target":"HYPOTHETICAL","rationale":"The author is considering asking her boyfriend to change the term he uses when complimenting her. In the post, she speculates about how her boyfriend might react and how to broach the subject with him. She does not mention that she has already talked to him about this issue before posting on Reddit. Therefore, it seems that the author is still considering talking to him about this issue and has not yet done so, which suggests that the label \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" is appropriate.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a multiple-choice question about healthcare. Answer the question based on your information and classify your answers into '1', '2', '3', and '4'.\\n\\nQuestion: With respect to the pharmacological treatment for depression, it can be stated that: \\n Options:  <1> The side effects of Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs), such as fluoxetine, are zero. <2> Treatments with SSRIs are more effective than those using cyclic antidepressants. <3> In general, pharmacological treatments should not be combined with psychological treatments. <4> They have been shown to be effective for 50% of patients, while the efficacy of placebo would be of the order of 30%. <5> Monoamine oxidase inhibitors (MAOIs) have been shown to be superior to other antidepressants in the treatment of severe depression.","target":"4","rationale":"The efficacy of SSRIs and other antidepressants is generally in the order of 60-70% while that of placebo is in the order of 30-40%. Therefore, pharmacological treatment has been shown to be effective for 50% more patients than placebo."},{"source":"Answer the following question.\\nWhich mobile phone company was established in 2001 when a Japanese company merged with a Swedish company?","target":"Sony Mobile Communications","rationale":"Sony Mobile Communications was established in 2001 when a Japanese company merged with a Swedish company."},{"source":"Michael Morzeny put his hands into the pockets of his overcoat and hugged the fabric tighter around his body. The winter wind hurried down Columbus Avenue and the hem of his coat flapped around his knees letting little pockets of cold waft up to invade the warmth his body had spent so much time preparing and storing around his torso.\\nWith a bitter squeeze of his hands, his knuckles now getting cold, Morzeny bowed his square shoulders to the wind and continued walking. At sixty-seven years old the New York winters bothered Morzeny more than he cared to admit. And, although no doctor would admit it to him, he was positive that the first faint hints of arthritis tweaking through his hands were made worse by the cold.\\nAt every cross street the setting sun flashed through to the avenue in shades of crisp pink and red. Morzeny didn't want to be working right now. But these outings were the price he paid for having a hybrid job, owning buildings and brokering as many of his own leases as possible.\\nWhen he had first come to the city he had been told that he needed a job, not for income, his providers took care of that, but for his own sanity. Something to keep him going. He had asked for something in real estate and had never bothered to wonder what other paths he might have taken. He had always been able to focus to the point of blindness. It helped him in every aspect of his work.\\nHe arrived at the brownstone building housing the apartment he was to show tonight. His building was tucked into a short row of buildings that squatted over the street, their steps reaching towards the curb like stunted growths. More to prove to himself that he could do it than anything else, Morzeny took the front steps two at a time.\\nWho is walking down the street?\\nPick the correct answer from the following options:\\n\\nA. Grandpa\\n\\nB. not enough information\\n\\nC. Moore\\n\\nD. Morzeny","target":"D","rationale":"The text is written in third person and follows Morzeny, a real estate broker. As he walks down the street to show an apartment on Columbus Avenue, we learn details about his past and character through exposition of inner thoughts. The excerpt gives evidence that Morzeny is making this trip because it's part of his job as a landlord/broker hybrid who handles many leases himself (lines 5-10). In lines 11-12 we find out he has arthritis which seems to be related to age but no specific information regarding his exact age or relationship status are given. Based on these clues alone option C - Moore can't be correct since there was never any mention of anyone else named Moore nor do readers have enough information yet at this point for option B - not enough information. Option D"},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios.\\n\\nEthan entered the bedroom. Owen entered the bedroom. The tomato is in the blue_suitcase. Owen exited the bedroom. Ethan moved the tomato to the green_cupboard. Where is the tomato really? Aiden entered the TV_room. Owen entered the TV_room. The strawberry is in the green_drawer. Owen exited the TV_room. Aiden moved the strawberry to the green_envelope. Aiden exited the TV_room. Owen entered the TV_room. Where is the strawberry really? Emily entered the bedroom. Aiden entered the bedroom. The tomato is in the green_cupboard. Emily moved the tomato to the blue_suitcase. Where will Aiden look for the tomato? Owen entered the staircase. Aiden entered the staircase. The peach is in the blue_envelope. Owen moved the peach to the green_pantry. Where is the peach really?","target":"green_pantry","rationale":"Owen moved the peach to the green_pantry."},{"source":"What is the following passage about?\\nNutritional anthropology is a synthetic concept that deals with the interplay between economic systems, nutritional status and food security, and how changes in the former affect the latter. If economic and environmental changes in a community affect access to food, food security, and dietary health, then this interplay between culture and biology is in turn connected to broader historical and economic trends associated with globalization. Nutritional status affects overall health status, work performance potential, and the overall potential for economic development (either in terms of human development or traditional western models) for any given group of people.","target":"Anthropology","rationale":"The paragraph is about Nutritional Anthropology and how it connects to broader historical, economic trends associated with globalization. It describes the relationship between economics systems, nutritional status & food security in a community. \\nTherefore, the answer can be \\"Anthropology\\", as it relates to these topics."},{"source":"In this task you will be given two lists of numbers and you need to calculate the intersection between these two lists. The intersection between two lists is another list where every element is common between the two original lists. If there are no elements in the intersection, answer with an empty list. Your list of numbers must be inside brackets. Sort the numbers in your answer in an ascending order, that is, no matter what the order of the numbers in the lists is, you should put them in your answer in an ascending order.\\n\\n[9, 8, 4, 6, 6, 3, 4, 2] , [3, 5, 8, 9, 7, 3, 4, 9]","target":"[3, 4, 8, 9]","rationale":"The numbers that are common between both lists are 3, 4, 8, and 9.\\\\nSorting these numbers in ascending order gives the list [3, 4, 8, 9]."},{"source":"In this task, you're given five sentences, numbered 1 through 5, and two options a and b for possible titles for the story. Your job is to choose the title that better fits the story. Indicate your choice by 'a' or 'b'.\\n\\nSentence 1: I decided to try doing jumping jacks for exercise. Sentence 2: I started doing them first thing in the morning. Sentence 3: I could only do twenty before I felt like I was dying. Sentence 4: I eventually built my tolerance to about fifty per day. Sentence 5: I started to lose a little weight because of it. Choices: a. Jumping. b. The dog.","target":"a","rationale":"The title \\"Jumping\\" is more suitable for the story because it describes the protagonist's exercise routine. The title \\"The dog\\" would not make sense in this context and would not adequately describe the story."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs 'i', 'j', and A, where 'i' and 'j' are integers and A is a list. A list is shown by two brackets and comma-separated numbers and characters inside, like ['1', '12', 'l']. You need to concatenate all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, and then reverse the resulting string. 'i' and 'j' will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. 'i' will always be less than 'j'. Perform the operations in order, i.e., do not reverse first and then concatenate.\\n\\n2, 3, ['2661', 'T', '8855', 'I', 'f', 'P']","target":"5588T","rationale":"Given the list ['2661', 'T', '8855', 'I', 'f', 'P'], we need to find the elements from 2 ~ 3.\\\\n1. The 2nd element is T, which should not be changed.\\\\n2. The 3rd element is 8855, which should be reversed as 5588 and added to T after the processing is done. \\\\n\\\\nThe final output would be \\"5588T\\"."},{"source":"Question: \\"What ties together spiritual leader and editor?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"According to the New Jersey Press Association, several media entities refrain from using the term \\"ultra-Orthodox\\", including the Religion Newswriters Association; JTA, the global Jewish news service; and the Star-Ledger, New Jersey‚Äôs largest daily newspaper. The Star-Ledger was the first mainstream newspaper to drop the term. Several local Jewish papers, including New York's Jewish Week and Philadelphia's Jewish Exponent have also dropped use of the term. According to Rabbi Shammai Engelmayer, spiritual leader of Temple Israel Community Center in Cliffside Park and former executive editor of Jewish Week, this leaves \\"Orthodox\\" as \\"an umbrella term that designates a very widely disparate group of people very loosely tied together by some core beliefs.\\"\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"Rabbi Shammai Engelmayer","rationale":"The quote mentions \\"Rabbi Shammai Engelmayer\\" as being both a spiritual leader and an editor, tying together the two terms."},{"source":"Math Problem\\nSolve 287 - 259 = -7*l for l.","target":"-4","rationale":"To solve for the variable l, we need to isolate it on one side of the equation.\\n\\nStarting with: 287 - 259 = -7*l\\\\nSubtracting 287 from both sides: 0-28 = -7*l\\\\nSimplifying further by adding 28 to each side of the equation: 28=  (-7)*l\\\\nDividing each side by negative 7 leads us to our solution:\\\\nl=-4"},{"source":"Given a passage and a question, find the answer to the question based on the passage. The answer should consist of only one word that lies in the span of only one of the sentences in the passage.\\n\\nParagraph: In flowering plants , the ovule is located inside the portion of the flower called the gynoecium . The ovary of the gynoecium produces one or more ovules and ultimately becomes the fruit wall . Ovules are attached to the placenta in the ovary through a stalk - like structure known as a funiculus ( plural , funiculi ) . Different patterns of ovule attachment , or placentation , can be found among plant species , these include :\\nQuestion: where is the ovule found in a flower","target":"gynoecium","rationale":"The answer is gynoecium which is the correct noun phrase in the passage that answers the question."},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as acceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"I want to peruse that contract before filing it away.","rationale":"Here's an example of a grammatically correct sentence:\\\\nI want to peruse that contract before filing it away."},{"source":"Use a disfluent question or a proper question and find the answer to the question based on the given context or return None if an answer can't be found. A disfluent question is a question that has some interruptions in it while framing. A proper question is the correct form of the question without any disfluency.\\n\\nproper question: Where does Pamas originate? \\n disfluent question: Where does Islamist groups no Pamas originate? \\n context: Moderate and reformist Islamists who accept and work within the democratic process include parties like the Tunisian Ennahda Movement. Jamaat-e-Islami of Pakistan is basically a socio-political and democratic Vanguard party but has also gained political influence through military coup d'√©tat in past. The Islamist groups like Hezbollah in Lebanon and Hamas in Palestine participate in democratic and political process as well as armed attacks, seeking to abolish the state of Israel. Radical Islamist organizations like al-Qaeda and the Egyptian Islamic Jihad, and groups such as the Taliban, entirely reject democracy, often declaring as kuffar those Muslims who support it (see takfirism), as well as calling for violent/offensive jihad or urging and conducting attacks on a religious basis.","target":"None","rationale":"The disfluent question is an example of a misspeaking while framing the question. The given context doesn't provide an answer to the original as well as disfluent questions. Hence, None is returned."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two strings A,B. You must perform the following operations to generate the required output list: (i) Find the longest common substring in the strings A and B, (ii) Convert this substring to all lowercase and sort it alphabetically, (iii) Replace the substring at its respective positions in the two lists with the updated substring.\\n\\nXzywTLAlneIQnZbMDuazwqQwmQFz, WCaGxbeUQnZbMDuazwqQwmQOUtQymylSf","target":"XzywTLAlneIabdmmnqqqquwwzzFz, WCaGxbeUabdmmnqqqquwwzzOUtQymylSf","rationale":"The longest common substring in the strings XzywTLAlneIQnZbMDuazwqQwmQFz, WCaGxbeUQnZbMDuazwqQwmQOUtQymylSf is abdmmnqqqquwwzz. After converting it to lowercase and sorting alphabetically, we get abddmmmnnnqqqquuuwwwzzz. Replacing this updated substring at its respective positions in the two lists gives us the final result: XzywTLAlneIabdmmnqqqquwwzzFz, WCaGxbeUabdmmnqqqquwwzzOUtQymylSf"},{"source":"Article: In 1988, only 60,000 computers were connected to the Internet, and most were mainframes, minicomputers and professional workstations. On November 2, 1988, many started to slow down, because they were running a malicious code that demanded processor time and that spread itself to other computers ‚Äì the first internet \\"computer worm\\". The software was traced back to 23-year-old Cornell University graduate student Robert Tappan Morris, Jr. who said 'he wanted to count how many machines were connected to the Internet'.\\n\\nQuestion: When was the first computer worm released?","target":"November 2, 1988","rationale":"The following context provides the answer to this question: \\"On November 2, 1988, many started to slow down, because they were running a malicious code that demanded processor time and that spread itself to other computers ‚Äì the first internet \\"computer worm\\". \\nTherefore, we can say with confidence that November 2nd is when it was released."},{"source":"Choose from options: Determine if the sentence is true based on the text below:\\nHigh Fidelity was based on a play in 1995\\n\\nHigh Fidelity is a 2000 American romantic comedy-drama film directed by Stephen Frears. It stars John Cusack, Iben Hjejle, Jack Black, Todd Louiso, and Lisa Bonet. The film is based on the 1995 British novel of the same name by Nick Hornby, with the setting moved from London to Chicago and the name of the lead character changed.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"High Fidelity is a 2000 American romantic comedy-drama film directed by Stephen Frears. It stars John Cusack, Iben Hjejle, Jack Black, Todd Louiso, and Lisa Bonet. The film is based on the 1995 British novel of the same name by Nick Hornby, with the setting moved from London to Chicago and the name of the lead character changed.\\"\\nThe article does not mention that High Fidelity was based off a play in 1995 but rather states it was \\"based on\\" (i.e adapted) from a UK Novel published under similar title also written by Nick Hornby"},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. The story has one of the three following scenarios: (1) when the individual's belief matches reality, (2) when the individual's belief does not match reality, (3) is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios.\\n\\nAvery entered the cellar. Jackson entered the cellar. The persimmon is in the green_crate. Jackson exited the cellar. Avery moved the persimmon to the red_bottle. Avery exited the cellar. Jackson entered the cellar. Where does Avery think that Jackson searches for the persimmon?","target":"green_crate","rationale":"In this scenario, Avery does not know that Jackson has moved the persimmon from the green_crate to the red_bottle. Therefore, Avery believes that Jackson is searching for the persimmon in the green_crate."},{"source":"What was likely said next? How's it going, I'm looking for a movie.\\nWhat kind of movie?\\nI'm thinking an action movie.","target":"Ok, do you want something recent or older?","rationale":"The person asks for a movie, and the next likely response should be about the genre of movie. The first option is irrelevant to the conversation, the second option is correct as it continues with asking about which kind of movie he/she wants to see. The last one can come later in the conversation after they have established what kind of movie they want to watch. Hence, \\"Ok, do you want something recent or older?\\""},{"source":"Given a question and a context passage, generate the answer having the word or phrase from the context passage. Here, the answer should be a shortest continous span from the passage.\\n\\nContext: Pietro Perona is Allan E. Puckett Professor of Electrical Engineering and Computation and Neural Systems at the California Institute of Technology. \\n Question: What is Pietro Perona's place of employment?","target":"california institute of technology","rationale":"The answer should be a shortest continuous span from the passage. So, the answer is \\"california institute of technology\\".  The concept of coreference resolution is not required for this task."},{"source":"Background: Kulwicki grew up in Greenfield, Wisconsin, a suburb of Milwaukee known for its Polish-American neighborhoods, near the Milwaukee Mile racetrack. After his mother died, his family moved in with his grandmother, who died when Kulwicki was in seventh grade. A year later, his only brother died of a hemophilia-related illness. Kulwicki attended Pius XI High School, a Roman Catholic high school in Milwaukee, and received a bachelor of science degree in mechanical engineering from the University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee in 1977.\\nContext: Kulwicki began his racing career as a 13-year-old kart racer. His father built engines as the crew chief for Norm Nelson and Roger McCluskey's United States Automobile Club (USAC) racecars. Because his work involved travel, Kulwicki's father was unable to help his son at most kart races, so Kulwicki's resourcefulness was often tested trying to find someone to transport his kart to the track. Even when Kulwicki asked his father for advice, he typically ended up doing most of the work himself. \\"I showed him how\\", Gerry Kulwicki said. \\"And he said: 'Why don't you do it? You can do it better.' And I said, 'Well, if you do it for a while, you can do it better.'\\"  Many local-level American racetracks host their own season championships. In Wisconsin, numerous locations held dirt and asphalt short track racing. Kulwicki started driving stock cars at the local level at the Hales Corners Speedway and Cedarburg Speedway dirt oval tracks. In 1973, he won the rookie of the year award at Hales Corners Speedway in the Milwaukee suburb of Franklin, and the next year started racing late models - the fastest and most complicated type of stock cars raced at the local level - at the same track. That season, he won his first feature race, at Leo's Speedway in Oshkosh.  Kulwicki moved from dirt tracks to paved tracks in 1977. He also teamed up with racecar builder Greg Krieger to research, model, engineer, and construct an innovative car with far more torsional stiffness than other late models. The increased stiffness allowed the car to handle better in the corners, which increased its speed. Racing at Slinger Super Speedway, he won the track championship in 1977. In 1978, Kulwicki returned to Slinger; that same year he started racing a late model at Wisconsin International Raceway (WIR), finishing third in points in his rookie season at the track. In 1979 and 1980, he won the WIR late model track championships.  In 1979, Kulwicki began competing in regional to national level events sanctioned by the USAC Stock Car series and the American Speed Association (ASA), while remaining an amateur racer through 1980. When Kulwicki raced against future NASCAR champion Rusty Wallace in the ASA series, the two became friends. Kulwicki's highest finish in the ASA season points championship was third place, which he accomplished in both 1982 and 1985, with five career victories and twelve pole positions.\\nQuestion: What else was he known for. Whats the answer?","target":"Racing at Slinger Super Speedway, he won the track championship in 1977.","rationale":"The context is about a racing driver who started his career at an early age. The first line of the passage states that he was known for winning rookie-of-the-year award, which means he stood out as someone special among all other drivers.\\nIn 1977 and 1979 Kulwicki won track championships at Slinger Super Speedway in Wisconsin International Raceway (WIR) respectively. This shows that by this time he had developed into a successful racetruck champion, beating many experienced professionals over several races throughout the season to win these titles , making him stand out even more clearly from others than before. Thus: \\"Racing at Slinger Super Speedway, he won the track championship in 1977."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an abstract of article. Your task is to generate label \\"True\\" if abstract is structured, otherwise generate \\"False\\". A structured abstract is composed of a topic sentence (or key sentence), relevant supporting sentences, and a closing (or transition) sentence. This structure is key to keeping your abstract focused on the main idea and creating a clear and concise image.\\n\\nDetection of persistent cervical carcinogenic human papillomavirus (HPV) DNA is used as a marker for cervical cancer risk in clinical trials. The authors performed a systematic review and meta-analysis of the association between persistent HPV DNA and high-grade cervical intraepithelial neoplasia (CIN2-3), high-grade squamous intraepithelial lesions (HSIL), and invasive cervical cancer (together designated CIN2-3/HSIL+) to evaluate the robustness of HPV persistence for clinical use. MEDLINE and Current Contents were searched through January 30, 2006. Relative risks (RRs) were stratified by HPV comparison group. Of 2,035 abstracts, 41 studies were eligible for inclusion in the meta-analysis. Over 22,500 women were included in calculation of RRs for persistent HPV DNA detection and cervical neoplasia. RRs ranged from 1.3 (95% confidence interval: 1.1, 1.5) to 813.0 (95% confidence interval: 168.2, 3,229.2) for CIN2-3/HSIL+ versus 12 months), wider testing intervals, CIN2-3/HSIL+, and use of an HPV-negative reference group were consistently associated with higher RRs. Thus, HPV persistence was consistently and strongly associated with CIN2-3/HSIL+, despite wide variation in definitions and study methods. The magnitude of association varied by duration of persistence and testing interval. Precise definition and standardization of HPV testing, sampling procedure, and test interval are needed for reliable clinical testing. These findings validate HPV persistence as a clinical marker and endpoint.","target":"False","rationale":"The abstract does not include a topic sentence, and it is divided into three sections that are written in a disconnected manner. The first section describes the purpose of the study, the second section provides information about how the study was conducted, and the third section summarizes the results of this research. Because there is no clear structure or flow to this abstract, it is difficult for readers to identify its main idea or significance without reading through all three sections. Thus, it lacks focus and conciseness. Therefore, the answer should be \\"False\\"."},{"source":"You are supposed to identify the category of a high-school level math question. There are five possible categories (1) algebra (2) arithmetic (3) measurement (4) numbers, and (5) probability. Use the following guidelines: (1) 'algebra' questions will typically contain letter variables and will ask you to find the value of a variable (2) 'arithmetic' questions will ask the sum, difference, multiplication, division, power, square root or value of expressions involving brackets (3) 'measurement' questions are questions that ask to convert a quantity from some unit to some other unit (4) 'numbers' questions will be about bases, remainders, divisors, GCD, LCM etc. (5) 'probability' questions will ask about the probability of the occurrence of something. A question must belong to only one category.\\n\\nCalculate prob of sequence cl when two letters picked without replacement from {n: 2, c: 6, z: 2, l: 1, u: 3, q: 1}.","target":"probability","rationale":"The question asks us to find the probability of getting the sequence \\"cl\\" when we pick 2 letters without replacement from a group of letters. Since there is only one \\\\\\"l\\\\\\" in the group, it is impossible to pick two \\\\\\"ls\\\\\\". Therefore, and since we are picking two letters from 11 total, the probability of getting \\\\\\"cl\\\\\\" is 0."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the self-need strategy, otherwise output No. self-need is a selfish negotiation strategy. It is used to create a personal need for an item in the negotiation, such as by pointing out that the participant sweats a lot to show preference towards water packages.\\n\\nContext: 'That won't work. Because, we are planning for a campfire. And so, we are in need of fire wood. I hope you understand.üôÇüôÇüôÇ' 'I understand. We are also planning a campfire, and have a lot of young kids who will need the fire to stay warm. So that's why I feel I need two firewoods. üôÇ' 'Sorry for apologize. Here we are having old aged people here. I need two packages of food. Otherwise two of firewood.üôÇ'\\nUtterance: 'I understand. I am willing to give you two packages of food if I can have two firewoods. I would also like two waters due to it being hot out for our hike. üôÇ'","target":"Yes","rationale":"In this example, the speaker indicates that they need two packages of water because it is hot outside. They are using their personal needs to justify their desire for two packages of water. Therefore, the answer is Yes as the speaker used a self-need strategy (in this case it was heat)."},{"source":"What is the answer to this question? who played virgil tibbs on heat of the night?","target":"Howard Ellsworth Rollins Jr.","rationale":"Howard Ellsworth Rollins Jr. is the actor who played Virgil Tibbs in In The Heat of the Night and its sequels. \\nAccording to Wikipedia, he was nominated for an Academy award for his portrayal as Mr. Tibbs: \\"Rollins earned a nomination for Oscar-winning Best Actor at the 40th Academy Awards ceremony on April 14, 1968.\\""},{"source":"For their last road game of the season, in week 16 the Lions traveled west to San Francisco to play the San Francisco 49ers. The Lions took an early lead midway through the first quarter with a 27-yard Jason Hanson field goal. The 49ers tied it up at the end of the first quarter with a 33-yard field goal by Ricky Schmitt. The only score of the 2nd quarter was a 39-yard 49ers field goal just before halftime. In the third quarter came 2 San Francisco TD's. First a 2-yard catch by Vernon Davis, then a 1-yard run by Frank Gore. The Lions kicked another field goal late in the 4th quarter from 38 yards out. The Lions road losing streak now stands at 20.And for the win, the 49ers improved their record to 7-8.With the loss, the Lions dropped their record to 2-13.\\n\\nWhat two players kicked field goals in the game?","target":"Jason Hanson","rationale":"Jason Hanson was the only player who kicked field goals in the game."},{"source":"You are given a mathematical question described with a circumscribed mathematical vocabulary. Questions in this task usually contain some variables (e.g. X, Y), equations (e.g. X+Y=3) and some relationships (X is greater than Y). Often you need to find the value of the variable using equations and relationships. You are also given 4 or 5 answer options (associated with \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\", \\"E\\"). Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B, 'C', 'D', 'E'. LaTeX mathematical format (the standard way to express mathematical expressions in the typesetting software known as LaTeX) is used to express equations. Each question is solvable with high school math knowledge. Give only one answer for each question.\\n\\nIf \\\\(\\\\frac { m + m } { m \\\\times m } = \\\\frac { 1 } { 5 } \\\\), which of the following must be true? I. m = 0 II. m = 5 III. m = 10\\n(A)I only (B)II only (C)III only (D)I and II only (E)I and III only","target":"C","rationale":"From the question, \\\\(\\\\frac { m + m } { m \\\\times m } = \\\\frac { 1 } { 5 }\\\\) is true. We can write this equation as:\\n\\\\(\\\\frac{m}{m}+\\\\frac{m}{m}=\\\\frac{1}{5}\\\\)\\\\(\\\\Rightarrow\\\\) \\\\(2+\\\\frac{1}{5}=\\\\frac{1}{5}\\\\)\\\\(\\\\Rightarrow\\\\) \\\\(2=0\\\\)\\nSince 2 = 0 is not possible, we know that \\\\(\\\\frac { m + m } { m \\\\times m } = \\\\frac { 1 } / 5 \\\\) cannot be true, so all of the answer choices must be false. This means that all three statements are false. Choice C is the only choice that includes III and so it must be correct since I and II are false."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an anaphor number agreement or as an incorrect representation. An anaphor is an expression whose interpretation depends upon another expression. Anaphor number agreement is a restriction where a phrase agrees with the preceeding expression: plurals match plurals or singular expressions match singular expressions. In this task a valid representation of anaphor number agreement should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an anaphor number agreement will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence where the subject and self-referencing nouns match plurality. An incorrect representation is a sentence in which the subject and self-referencing noun's plurality do not match.\\n\\nAll girls had healed themselves.","target":"good","rationale":"The subject of the sentence is \\"All girls\\", which is plural. The reflexive pronoun \\"themselves\\" is also plural and agrees with the plurality of the subject. A correct representation would be \\"All girls had healed themselves\\", where the plural subject \\"girls\\" agrees with the plural reflexive pronoun, therefore this sentence is an correct representation of anaphor number agreement and should be denoted as 'good'."},{"source":"to cut the sacks off she didn't even lick the sacks off laziest dog on earth she never she never nursed them she never cleaned them she never did anything to them they were like she they didn't exist\\n\\nDoes it follow that \\"She was always there to take care of the dogs whenever she had the opportunity.\\"?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The passage talks about how the mother never nursed, cleaned or cared for her puppies. This contradicts that she was always there to take care of them whenever possible. So,the answer is \\"no\\".\\n\`,\\n\\n  trueFalseTaskRationale: \`"},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- The Warring States period was an era in ancient Chinese history following the Spring and Autumn period and concluding with the Qin wars of conquest that saw the annexation of all other contender states, which ultimately led to the Qin state's victory in 221 BC as the first unified Chinese empire known as the Qin dynasty. Although different scholars point toward different dates ranging from 481 BC to 403 BC as the true beginning of the Warring States, Sima Qian's choice of 475 BC is generally the most often cited and popularly accepted one. The Warring States era also overlaps with the second half of the Eastern Zhou dynasty, though the Chinese sovereign, known as the king of Zhou, ruled merely as a figurehead and served as a backdrop against the machinations of the warring states.\\n\\n- The Tokugawa shogunate, also known as the and the , was the last feudal Japanese military government, which existed between 1603 and 1867. The head of government was the shogun, and each was a member of the Tokugawa clan. The Tokugawa shogunate ruled from Edo Castle and the years of the shogunate became known as the Edo period. This time is also called the Tokugawa period or pre-modern.\\n\\n- , or is a part of the Japanese myth cycle and also a major deity of the Shinto religion. She is seen as the goddess of the sun, but also of the universe. The name Amaterasu derived from Amateru means \\"shining in heaven.\\" The meaning of her whole name, Amaterasu-mikami, is \\"the great august kami (god) who shines in the heaven\\". According to the \\"Kojiki\\" and \\"Nihon Shoki\\" in Japanese mythology, the Emperors of Japan are considered to be direct descendants of Amaterasu.\\n\\n- Go - Nara (  Go - Nara - tenn ) ( January 26 , 1495 -- September 27 , 1557 ) was the 105th Emperor of Japan , according to the traditional order of succession . He reigned from June 9 , 1526 until September 27 , 1557 , during the Sengoku period . His personal name was Tomohito (  ) . In older English literature , he may also be referred to as Nara II.\\n\\n- , also called kami-no-michi, is a Japanese ethnic religion. It focuses on ritual practices to be carried out diligently, to establish a connection between present-day Japan and its ancient past. Shinto practices were first recorded and codified in the written historical records of the \\"Kojiki\\" and \\"Nihon Shoki\\" in the 8th century. Still, these earliest Japanese writings do not refer to a unified \\"Shinto religion\\", but rather to a collection of native beliefs and mythology. Shinto today is a term that applies to the religion of public shrines devoted to the worship of a multitude of gods (\\"kami\\"), suited to various purposes such as war memorials and harvest festivals, and applies as well to various sectarian organizations. Practitioners express their diverse beliefs through a standard language and practice, adopting a similar style in dress and ritual, dating from around the time of the Nara and Heian periods (8th to 12th centuries AD).\\n\\n- The is a period in Japanese history marked by social upheaval, political intrigue and near-constant military conflict. Japanese historians named it after the otherwise unrelated Warring States period in China. It came to an end when all political power was unified under the Tokugawa shogunate.\\n\\n- The Emperor of Japan is the head of the Imperial Family and is the ceremonial head of state of Japan's system of constitutional monarchy. According to the 1947 constitution, he is \\"the symbol of the State and of the unity of the people.\\" Historically, he is also the highest authority of the Shinto religion as he and his family are said to be the direct descendants of the sun-goddess Amaterasu, and his importance also lies in dealing with heavenly affairs, including Shinto ritual and rites throughout the nation.\\n\\n- A head of state (or chief of state) is the public persona that officially represents the national unity and legitimacy of a sovereign state. In developing the current Constitution of France (1958), former French president Charles de Gaulle said the head of state should embody \\"the spirit of the nation\\" (\\"\\"). In some countries, typically those with parliamentary governments, the head of state is a ceremonial figurehead that does not actually guide day-to-day government activities and may not even be empowered to exercise any kind of political authority (e.g., Queen Elizabeth II in the United Kingdom). In other countries, the head of state is also the head of government, such as in the U.S., where the president is both a public figurehead and the actual highest ranking political leader who, in practice, oversees the executive branch.\\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the information, choose the subject and object entities that have the relation of 'languages spoken or written'.","target":"emperor go-nara , japanese","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"emperor go-nara , japanese\\"."},{"source":"Given the background: Geologists study earthquake waves to ‚Äúsee‚Äù Earth's interior. Waves of energy radiate out from an earthquake‚Äôs focus. These waves are called seismic waves ( Figure below ). Seismic waves go different speeds through different materials. They change speed when they go from one type of material to another. This causes them to bend. Some seismic waves do not travel through liquids or gases. They just stop. Scientists use information from seismic waves to understand what makes up the Earth‚Äôs interior.\\n\\nand the situation: A team of geologists studied two islands. Large island had a lot of seismic activity, and Small island that presented almost no seismic activity.\\n\\nAnswer the following question: Which island displayed fewer seismic waves?","target":"Small","rationale":"Seismic waves are created by earthquakes, and they travel through rock. Based on the information given in the text, Small Island has almost no seismic activity while Large Island displays a lot of seismic activity. This implies that there is more seismic activity (and thus more earthquake-related events) taking place in Large Island than in Small Island. As such, it can be inferred that fewer seismic waves would occur on Small island, making \\"Small\\" the correct answer to this question."},{"source":"Based on the following passage, is the niv bible a word for word translation? New International Version -- The NIV is a balance between word-for-word and thought-for-thought or literal and phrase by phrase translations.","target":"No","rationale":"The passage indicates that the New International Version is a balance between word-for-word and thought for thought translations. This means that it isn't exclusively one or the other, so choosing either \\"Yes\\" or \\"No\\" wouldn't be correct."},{"source":"I read this background article the other day: As shown here, pressure decreases to less than 25% of ground-level atmospheric pressure when we get to an altitude of about six miles. Since this is a common cruising altitude for commercial airplanes, pressurized cabins are needed for the comfort and survival of the passengers. This is because the density of the air decreases along with the decreasing air pressure, so there is less oxygen in a breath of air. You've probably noticed this effect in high-mountain areas, as it often feels harder to breath.\\n\\nI am facing a new situation today: Pam and Angela live in different cities and are talking to each other on the phone while they are sitting outside. Pam lives in Dunder, a city located at sea level, and Angela lives in Mifflin, a city up high in the mountains. Although they don't get to see each other much any more due to the distance between them, they make sure to stay in regular contact.\\n\\nUsing the knowledge I acquired from the background article, how should I answer correctly the following question regarding my new situation: Which woman gets less oxygen per single breath?","target":"Angela","rationale":"The background article states that air pressure decreases as altitude increases. This means that the density of air also decreases, which leads to less oxygen per breath at higher altitudes. Since Angela lives in a city located up high in the mountains and Pam does not, it can be concluded that Angela gets less oxygen per single breath than Pam does.\\nSo, I should choose \\"Angela\\" for my answer!"},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Wales is a country that is part of the United Kingdom and the island of Great Britain. It is bordered by England to the east, the Irish Sea to the north and west, and the Bristol Channel to the south. It had a population in 2011 of 3,063,456 and has a total area of . Wales has over of coastline and is largely mountainous, with its higher peaks in the north and central areas, including Snowdon, its highest summit. The country lies within the north temperate zone and has a changeable, maritime climate.\\n\\n- A country is a region that is identified as a distinct national entity in political geography. A country may be an independent sovereign state or one that is occupied by another state, as a non-sovereign or formerly sovereign political division, or a geographic region associated with sets of previously independent or differently associated people with distinct political characteristics. Regardless of the physical geography, in the modern internationally accepted legal definition as defined by the League of Nations in 1937 and reaffirmed by the United Nations in 1945, a resident of a country is subject to the independent exercise of legal jurisdiction.\\n\\n- The Isles of Scilly (or \\"\\") are an archipelago off the south western tip of the Cornish peninsula of Great Britain. It is the southernmost location in England and the United Kingdom, as well as the most westerly in England.\\n\\n- Derbyshire (or ; abbreviated Derbys. or Derbs.) is a county in the East Midlands of England. A substantial portion of the Peak District National Park lies within Derbyshire, containing the southern extremity of the Pennine range of hills which extend into the north of the county. The county contains part of the National Forest, and borders on Greater Manchester to the northwest, West Yorkshire to the north, South Yorkshire to the northeast, Nottinghamshire to the east, Leicestershire to the southeast, Staffordshire to the west and southwest and Cheshire also to the west.\\nKinder Scout, at 636 metres (2,087¬†ft), is the highest point in the county, whilst Trent Meadows, where the River Trent leaves Derbyshire, is its lowest point at 27 metres (89¬†ft). The River Derwent is the county's longest river at 66 miles (106¬†km), and runs roughly north to south through the county. In 2003 the Ordnance Survey placed Church Flatts Farm at Coton in the Elms (near Swadlincote) as the furthest point from the sea in Great Britain.\\n\\n- Worcestershire (or ; written abbreviation: Worcs) is a county in the West Midlands of England. Between 1974 and 1998, it was merged with the neighbouring county of Herefordshire as Hereford and Worcester.\\n\\n- Cheshire (or ; archaically the County Palatine of Chester; abbreviated Ches.) is a county in North West England, bordering Merseyside and Greater Manchester to the north, Derbyshire to the east, Staffordshire and Shropshire to the south and Wales to the west (bordering Wrexham and Flintshire). Cheshire's county town is Chester; the largest town is Warrington.\\n\\n- The North Sea is a marginal sea of the Atlantic Ocean located between Great Britain, Scandinavia, Germany, the Netherlands, Belgium, and France. An epeiric (or \\"shelf\\") sea on the European continental shelf, it connects to the ocean through the English Channel in the south and the Norwegian Sea in the north. It is more than long and wide, with an area of around .\\n\\n- In England, a civil parish is a territorial designation which is the lowest tier of local government below districts and counties, or their combined form, the unitary authority. It is an administrative parish, in contrast to an ecclesiastical parish.\\n\\n- The Isle of Wight is a county and the largest and second-most populous island in England. It is located in the English Channel, about 4 miles (6¬†km) off the coast of Hampshire, separated by the Solent. The island has resorts that have been holiday destinations since Victorian times, and is known for its mild climate, coastal scenery, and verdant landscape of fields, downland and chines.\\n\\n- The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland, commonly known as the United Kingdom (UK) or Britain, is a sovereign country in western Europe. Lying off the north-western coast of the European mainland, it includes the island of Great Britain (the name of which is also loosely applied to the whole country), the north-eastern part of the island of Ireland, and many smaller islands. Northern Ireland is the only part of the UK that shares a land border with another sovereign statethe Republic of Ireland. Apart from this land border, the UK is surrounded by the Atlantic Ocean, with the North Sea to its east, the English Channel to its south and the Celtic Sea to its south-south-west, giving it the 12th-longest coastline in the world. The Irish Sea lies between Great Britain and Ireland. With an area of , the UK is the 78th-largest sovereign state in the world and the 11th-largest in Europe. It is also the 21st-most populous country, with an estimated 65.1 million inhabitants. Together, this makes it the fourth most densely populated country in the European Union.\\n\\n- The Celtic Sea (; ) is the area of the Atlantic Ocean off the south coast of Ireland bounded to the east by Saint George's Channel; other limits include the Bristol Channel, the English Channel, and the Bay of Biscay, as well as adjacent portions of Wales, Cornwall, Devon, and Brittany. The southern and western boundaries are delimited by the continental shelf, which drops away sharply. The Isles of Scilly are an archipelago of small islands in the sea.\\n\\n- Pattingham is a village in the civil parish of Pattingham and Patshull, South Staffordshire, near the county boundary with Shropshire. Pattingham is seven miles west of Wolverhampton and seven and a half miles east of Bridgnorth.\\n\\n- Continental Europe, also referred to as mainland Europe, or, by Europeans, simply the Continent, is the continuous continent of Europe, excluding surrounding islands.\\n\\n- Warwickshire (or ) is a landlocked county in the West Midlands of England. The county town is Warwick, although the largest town is Nuneaton. The county is famous for being the birthplace of William Shakespeare. Commonly used abbreviations for the county are Warks or Warwicks.\\n\\n- Patshull Hall is a substantial Georgian mansion house situated near Pattingham in Staffordshire , England . It is a Grade I listed building and by repute is one of the largest listed buildings in the county .\\n\\n- The English Channel (\\"the Sleeve\\" [hence ] \\"Sea of Brittany\\" \\"British Sea\\"), also called simply the Channel, is the body of water that separates southern England from northern France, and joins the southern part of the North Sea to the rest of the Atlantic Ocean.\\n\\n- Bridgnorth is a town in Shropshire, England, situated on the Severn Valley. It is split into \\"High Town\\" and \\"Low Town\\", named on account of their elevations relative to the River Severn, which separates the upper town on the right bank from the lower on the left. The population of the town of Bridgnorth was 11,891, at the 2001 Census rising to 12,079 at the 2011 Census.\\n\\n- Leicestershire (or ; abbreviation Leics.) is a landlocked county in the English Midlands. It takes its name from the City of Leicester, traditionally its administrative centre, although the City of Leicester unitary authority is today administered separately from the rest of Leicestershire. The county borders Nottinghamshire to the north, Lincolnshire to the north-east, Rutland to the east, Northamptonshire to the south-east, Warwickshire to the south-west, Staffordshire to the west, and Derbyshire to the north-west. The border with most of Warwickshire is Watling Street (the A5).\\n\\n- Staffordshire (or ; abbreviated Staffs) is a landlocked county in the West Midlands of England. It adjoins Cheshire to the north west, Derbyshire and Leicestershire to the east, Warwickshire to the south east, West Midlands and Worcestershire to the south, and Shropshire to the west.\\n\\n- Borders are geographic boundaries of political entities or legal jurisdictions, such as governments, sovereign states, federated states, and other subnational entities. Some borderssuch as a state's internal administrative border, or inter-state borders within the Schengen Areaare often open and completely unguarded. Other borders are partially or fully controlled, and may be crossed legally only at designated border checkpoints and border zones may be controlled. Mostly contentious, borders may even foster the setting up of buffer zones. A difference has also been established in academic scholarship between border and frontier, the latter denoting a state of mind rather than state boundaries.\\n\\n- Great Britain, also known as Britain¬†, is a large island in the north Atlantic Ocean off the northwest coast of continental Europe. With an area of , Great Britain is the largest European island and the ninth-largest in the world. In 2011 the island had a population of about 61¬†million people, making it the world's third-most populous island after Java in Indonesia and Honshu in Japan. The island of Ireland is situated to the west of it, and together these islands, along with over 1,000 smaller surrounding islands, comprise the British Isles archipelago.\\n\\n- The Irish Sea (, , , Ulster-Scots: \\"Airish Sea\\"), separates the islands of Ireland and Great Britain. It is connected to the Celtic Sea in the south by St George's Channel, and to the Inner Seas off the West Coast of Scotland in the north by the North Channel. Anglesey is the largest island within the Irish Sea, followed by the Isle of Man. The sea is occasionally, but rarely, referred to as the Manx Sea.\\n\\n- Scotland (Scots: ) is a country that is part of the United Kingdom and covers the northern third of the island of Great Britain. It shares a border with England to the south, and is otherwise surrounded by the Atlantic Ocean, with the North Sea to the east and the North Channel and Irish Sea to the south-west. In addition to the mainland, the country is made up of more than 790 islands, including the Northern Isles and the Hebrides.\\n\\n- Wolverhampton is a city and metropolitan borough in the West Midlands, England. At the 2011 census, it had a population of 249,470. The demonym for people from the city is \\"Wulfrunian\\".\\n\\n- South Staffordshire is a local government district in Staffordshire, England. The district lies to the north and west of the West Midlands county, bordering Shropshire to the west and Worcestershire to the south. It contains no towns of major size, and many of the settlements within the district are considered dormitory villages for Stafford, Telford, and the West Midlands conurbation.\\n\\n- England is a country that is part of the United Kingdom. It shares land borders with Scotland to the north and Wales to the west. The Irish Sea lies northwest of England and the Celtic Sea lies to the southwest. England is separated from continental Europe by the North Sea to the east and the English Channel to the south. The country covers five-eighths of the island of Great Britain (which lies in the North Atlantic) in its centre and south; and includes over 100 smaller islands such as the Isles of Scilly, and the Isle of Wight.\\n\\n- Shropshire (or ; alternatively Salop; abbreviated, in print only, Shrops; demonym Salopian ) is a county located between West Midlands in England and Wales. It borders Powys and Wrexham in Wales to the west and north-west, Cheshire to the north, Staffordshire to the east, Worcestershire to the south-east and Herefordshire to the south. Shropshire Council was created in 2009, a unitary authority taking over from the previous county council and five district councils. The borough of Telford and Wrekin has been a separate unitary authority since 1998 but continues to be included in the ceremonial county.\\n\\n- Stafford is the county town of Staffordshire, in the West Midlands of England. It lies approximately north of Wolverhampton, south of Stoke-on-Trent and north-west of Birmingham. The population in 2001 was 63,681 and that of the wider borough of Stafford 122,000, the fourth largest in the county after Stoke-on-Trent, Tamworth and Newcastle-under-Lyme.\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat is the relationship between 'patshull hall' and 'south staffordshire'?","target":"located in the administrative territorial entity","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"located in the administrative territorial entity\\"."},{"source":"Write the response. DIALOG:\\nWhen did Lawrence Alma-Tadema move to belgium?\\n- In 1852 he entered the Royal Academy of Antwerp in Belgium.\\n- Why did Lawrence Alma-Tadema move to Belgium?\\n- He entered the Royal Academy of Antwerp in Belgium where he studied early Dutch and Flemish art, under Gustaf Wappers.\\n- What did Lawrence Alma-Tadema study at the Royal Academy of Antwerp?\\n-","target":"He studied early Dutch and Flemish art, under Gustaf Wappers.","rationale":"The first two dialogues are asking about Alma-Tadema's move to Belgium. The third dialogue is asking what he studied at the Royal Academy of Antwerp. Hence, the answer should be \\"He studied early Dutch and Flemish art, under Gustaf Wappers.\\""},{"source":"Answer this question: where is the chupacabra found?","target":"The Chupacabra or Chupacabras (, from chupar \\"to suck\\" and cabra \\"goat\\", literally \\"goat sucker\\") is a legendary cryptid rumored to inhabit parts of the Americas .","rationale":"Here's a direct answer: The Chupacabra or Chupacabras (, from chupar \\"to suck\\" and cabra \\"goat\\", literally \\"goat sucker\\") is a legendary cryptid rumored to inhabit parts of the Americas .\\nIt provides information about where this creature has been sighted."},{"source":"Background: Bill Laswell (born February 12, 1955, Salem, Illinois, and raised in Albion, Michigan) is an American bassist, producer and record label owner. Laswell has been involved in hundreds of recordings with many collaborators from all over the world. Laswell's music draws upon many different genres, most notably funk, various world music, jazz, dub and ambient styles. He has also played or produced music from the noisier, more aggressive end of the rock spectrum, such as hardcore punk and metal.\\nContext: Within a few years of moving to New York, Laswell founded a recording studio with producer/engineer Martin Bisi (of later indie rock renown) and hooked up with Jean Karakos and his fledgling label Celluloid Records. Under the Material moniker (now also a production unit consisting of Laswell and Beinhorn - Maher being long gone - and by 1984 consisting solely of Laswell) Laswell became the de facto house producer for Celluloid until the sale of the label in the later 1980s. During this time in the early to mid-1980s, Laswell was able to record some of his Material excursions (which ran the gamut from experimental jazz/funk to pop and R&B, featuring everyone from avant-jazz figures Henry Threadgill and Sonny Sharrock to Archie Shepp and pop star Whitney Houston) as well as projects such as Massacre, with Fred Frith and Fred Maher.  His association with Celluloid allowed some of his first forays into this so-called \\"collision music\\" - the term was coined for Laswell by the British writer Chris May, then editor of Black Music & Jazz Review and later a Celluloid staff member - and forays into world music. Recordings with the Golden Palominos and production on albums by Shango, Toure Kunda and Fela Kuti all appeared on the label. Celluloid also released a slew of 12\\" devoted to Hip-Hop, becoming a precursor to the popularity the form enjoyed starting in the mid-1980s. Fab 5 Freddy, Phase II and Afrika Bambaataa all appeared on the label. Criminally forgotten, Laswell also put together the very successful 12\\" World Destruction which paired PiL's John Lydon with Afrika Bambaataa - years before the Run-D.M.C./Aerosmith collaboration broke down the rock/hip-hop barrier. 1982 also saw Laswell's solo debut, Baselines.  Also recording a Laswell-helmed solo album for Celluloid was Ginger Baker, whom Laswell coaxed out of semi-retirement, giving the drummer's career a new boost. He likewise brought Sonny Sharrock out of semi-retirement and produced some of the guitarist's most acclaimed recordings, starting with the solo LP Guitar.\\nQuestion: As a record signing company, did it receive recognition for notable artists?. Whats the answer?","target":"Fab 5 Freddy, Phase II and Afrika Bambaataa all appeared on the label.","rationale":"The passage mentions that Fab 5 Freddy, Phase II and Afrika Bambaataa all appeared on the label.\\n\\nThis statement provides evidence for our answer being \\"yes\\", since these artists are notable in their field of work."},{"source":"Given a prompt and four completions, select the completion that is the most plausible in continuing or answering the prompt. This task is designed to test common sense and has various categories ranging between idioms, negated statements, polysemy, subject referencing, and quantitative reasoning. Generate either Completion A, Completion B, Completion C, or Completion D.\\n\\nPrompt: There's this girl I like. She \\nCompletion A: likes to climb trees. \\nCompletion B: enjoys watching me suffer. \\nCompletion C: doesn't know whether she likes me back or not. \\nCompletion D: tried to break into a school building with my credit card.","target":"Completion C","rationale":"Completion A is implausible because it has no connection to the prompt. Completion B is implausible because it doesn't make sense in continuing the sentence. Completion D is implausible because it contradicts with \\\\\\"there's this girl I like\\\\\\". The most plausible completion for this prompt would be Completion C."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"Greece has tended to lag behind its European Union partners in terms of Internet use, with the gap closing rapidly in recent years. The percentage of households with access to the Internet more than doubled between 2006 and 2013, from 23% to 56% respectively (compared with an EU average of 49% and 79%). At the same time, there has been a massive increase in the proportion of households with a broadband connection, from 4% in 2006 to 55% in 2013 (compared with an EU average of 30% and 76%). However, Greece also has the EU's third highest percentage of people who have never used the Internet: 36% in 2013, down from 65% in 2006 (compared with an EU average of 21% and 42%).\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What percent of households in Greece had access to the Internet in 2006?","target":"23","rationale":"The passage states that Greece \\"tended to lag behind its European Union partners in terms of Internet use\\". This suggests that the overall internet usage rate was lower than other countries at this time. \\nGiven this, it can be inferred that the percentage of households with access to the internet would have also been below average for EU nations as well. The text states: \\"23% [of households] had access to the Internet...in 2006.\\" Therefore, 23% is correct answer."},{"source":"I've always wondered: On the flag of which European country are two cows shown","target":"Principaut√© d'Andorre","rationale":"The flag of the Principaut√© d'Andorre (Principality of Andorra) features two cows.\\nTherefore, the answer should be \\"Principat D'andore\\"."},{"source":"Q: how long is lord of the rings fellowship? A:","target":"178 minutes","rationale":"The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship Of Ring has a run time of 178 minutes."},{"source":"Based on the premise \\"And Rupert Murdoch ( of Fox TV ) recently bid an estimated $350 million for the Los Angeles Dodgers and their stadium.\\", can we conclude the hypothesis \\"Murdoch tried to sell the stadium and the team.\\" is true (see options)?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The passage only mentions that Murdoch bid for the Los Angeles Dodgers and their stadium, but does not mention any attempt to sell either of them. So, we cannot conclude from this premise that \\"Murdoch tried to sell the stadium and team\\".\\n\\nIt is also important to note here that buying something or bidding for something are different things. The passage makes no mention of whether Murdoch's bid was successful or not - so it could be possible that he did try selling them later on (but there is nothing in this particular context which suggests such a thing).\\n\\n  \`\`\`"},{"source":"In this task, you're shown a three-part story, with a beginning, middle, and ending. Your job is to slightly modify the middle part, so that the whole story becomes unlikely, improbable, or inconsistent. Generated sentences must minimally alter the given middle, with at most 4 new words added/existing words removed. Your sentence should be grammatically and syntactically correct. Also stick to the context of the given story. For example, if the story talks about \\"doctors\\", you can talk about \\"health\\" or \\"diagnosis\\", but don't mention \\"aliens\\". Avoid introducing any extra/irrelevant information, and use names instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible. Avoid simply negating the original middle, for example:  \\"She likes cakes.\\" is changed to \\"She doesn't like cakes.\\"\\n\\nBeginning: Joan's cat yowled all night long. Middle: Joan's neighbors complained to the HOA. Ending: Finally, she gave the cat away to a friend.","target":"Joan's neighbors complained to the fire department","rationale":"The original sentence has a similar structure as \\"Joan's neighbors complained to the fire department\\". If Joan's neighbors complained to the HOA, it is reasonable that they can complain to other places like fire department."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people. 'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. If the conversation begins with a question, label it '1' otherwise '0'.\\n\\n Person1:     hi , how are you doing ?  \\n Person2:  everything's great . And you ?  \\n Person1:      same here . Have you seen any new films recently ?  \\n Person2:  no , I haven't had a chance to . But I've been watching a Chinese TV series called Chinese-Style Divorce .  \\n Person1:      oh , really ? I saw it two years ago . It's worth seeing and it's thought-provoking .  \\n Person2:  yeah . I found it is so close to our life .  \\n Person1:      it reflects some of our difficulties in this ever-changing world .  \\n Person2:  you said it . You know , the divorce rate has been on the rise in recent years .  \\n Person1:      well , it's said that a lot of young people favor getting married quickly which tend end quickly too .  \\n Person2:  I know a couple who divorced a week after getting married .  \\n Person1:      oh , that's too short-lived .  \\n Person2:  that's true . It's said the short-lived marriage is typical of the post - 80s generation .  \\n Person1:      I can't agree more . The only-child generation in China tends to know little about marriage .  \\n Person2:  definitely . They don't take relationships and marriages very seriously .  \\n Person1:      in their mind , love is nothing but passion and marriage is over once the passion is gone .  \\n Person2:  I think , as the saying goes as the saying goes haste makes waste , it is the same thing with marriage .","target":"1","rationale":"The conversation begins with the question \\"hi, how are you doing?\\" from Person 1. Therefore, it is a question and the answer is '1'."},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\nThe total need for staff cuts corresponds to about 300 man-years .","target":"negative","rationale":"This financial news states that the total need for staff cuts corresponds to 300 man-years. This indicates a decrease in workforce, which is generally considered as a negative development. So, this financial news can be clarified as \\"negative\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence with a missing word that can be an object, a person, and/or an action. Fill in the blank with a plausible word. Although each sentence has many correct answers, you only have to write one answer.\\n\\nPersonX places PersonY's ___ on the throne","target":"bag","rationale":"The context of the sentence is that PersonX places PersonY's bag on the throne, which is a safe place to leave one's belongings."},{"source":"Text: Seat belt legislation -- In the UK, a requirement for anchorage points was introduced in 1965, followed by the requirement in 1968 to fit three-point belts in the front outboard positions on all new cars and all existing cars back to 1965. Successive UK Governments proposed, but failed to deliver, seat belt legislation throughout the 1970s. Front seat belts were compulsory equipment on all new cars registered in the UK from 1972, although it did not become compulsory for them to be worn until 1983. Rear seat belts were compulsory equipment from 1986 and became compulsory for them to be worn in 1991. However, it has never been a legal requirement for cars registered before those dates to be fitted with seat belts. In one such attempt in 1979 similar claims for potential lives and injuries saved were advanced. William Rodgers, then Secretary of State for Transport in the Callaghan Labour Government (1976--1979), stated: \`\`On the best available evidence of accidents in this country - evidence which has not been seriously contested - compulsion could save up to 1000 lives and 10,000 injuries a year.''\\n\\nAnswer the following yes/no question: is it illegal to not wear a seatbelt in the backseat uk? Yes or no?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The text states that front seat belts were made compulsory in 1972, rear seat belts 1986 and wearing them became a requirement in 1983 (front) and 1991 (rear).\\nTherefore the answer is Yes."},{"source":"Find the movie name from the given conversation. If the movie name is not found give output as \\"unknown\\"\\n\\nASSISTANT: What kinds of movies do you like? , USER: I really like romantic comedies. , ASSISTANT: Why do you like romantic comedies? , USER: They're fun. They're usually funny. They have a happy ending. They're more light-hearted in nature. And they're a nice escape. , ASSISTANT: alright , how about a movie you liked? , USER: One of my favorites is When Harry Met Sally.","target":"When Harry Met Sally","rationale":"The user specifically mentions the movie name \\"When Harry Met Sally\\" in their response, so the correct answer is \\"When Harry Met Sally\\"."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of integers. You should remove any integer that is not prime. A prime integer is an integer that is only divisible by '1' and itself. The output should be the list of prime numbers in the input list. If there are no primes in the input list an empty list (\\"[]\\") should be returned.\\n\\n[607, 436]","target":"[607]","rationale":"The list [607, 436] contains two integers. Let's check them one-by-one.\\\\n1. The 1st integer is 607, which is a prime number.\\\\n2. The 2nd integer is 436, which is not a prime number since it can be divisible by more than 1 and itself (436 / 4 = 109).\\\\n3. The final output will be [607]."},{"source":"What is the political ideology of the narrator ?","target":"They are liberal .","rationale":"The narrator describes the practice of prayer as a time to express gratitude, which is often viewed in liberal circles. The passage also states that there are many ways for people to pray and that every person does it differently; this idea may be more commonly found among liberals who tend not to see their way as the only or right way when compared with conservative ideology.\\nHence, an appropriate answer would be: They are liberal ."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: sexual-explicit and non-sexual-explicit. A comment is considered sexual-explicit if it explicitly portrays sexual matters.\\n\\nComment: So, in fact, you have sexual intercourse for self-gratification. Then why do you condemn others for doing what you do? That is hypocrisy. Your actual objection is the old \\"gay sex is icky\\" -- which is solely a matter of taste.","target":"Sexual-explicit","rationale":"The given comment explicitly portrays sexual matters, therefore it can be classified as \\"Sexual-explicit\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue from a conversation between an agent and a customer. Your task is to determine the speaker of the dialogue. Answer with \\"agent\\" or \\"customer\\".\\n\\nThere is a reservation found with your given name. Shall I proceed with the cancellation?","target":"agent","rationale":"The dialogue is a question asked by the agent and it pertains to the customer's reservation. Hence, the speaker of this dialogue is \\"agent\\"."},{"source":"Given a post that is a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation and an associated claim about its type, verify if the claim is true or not. The claim asks if the posts are historical or hypothetical. The posts are \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and they are \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future. Say 'yes' if the claim is true otherwise say 'no'\\n\\nCLAIM : The following post is HISTORICAL. POST : Hello all!\\n\\nI (F, 22) Finally made a wedding registry to put on our website (yay!) and mailed it out about two weeks ago. A week ago, my fianc√©‚Äôs mom says that her church has offered to host a bridal party and tells me to stay clear of plans on that date. I don‚Äôt even go to this church or know these people so I think it‚Äôs kind of weird, and she told me to have my (male) fianc√© come so part of me says it‚Äôs to show off her son (who doesn‚Äôt go to that church either, just the mom does).\\n\\nAnyway fast forward to a few days ago, the mom calls and asks us to please remove the beer mugs from our registry because that church of Christ ‚Äúdoesn‚Äôt drink‚Äù? (Is this true?)\\n\\nAITA for telling her no? I feel like 1) it‚Äôs our registry, 2) I am not the one that set this up with that church.","target":"no","rationale":"In this post, the author describes an incident in which their fianc√©'s mother asked them to remove beer mugs from their wedding registry. The author mentions that they mailed out the registry about two weeks before, which suggests that the incident has already occurred. Furthermore, the author refers to their fianc√© as \\"\\"my fianc√©\\"\\" instead of \\"\\"our fianc√©\\"\\", but later uses a possessive pronoun for his mother (\\\\\\"her church\\\\\\"). These pronouns suggest that this is a post written by someone who is close to or familiar with these events and has no uncertainty about them.\\\\nThe above analysis indicates that this post does not describe something hypothetical; rather, it describes an event from the past. Therefore, it should be labeled \\"\\"HISTORICAL.\\"\\" In other words, a claim stating that this post is \\"\\"HYPOTHETICAL\\"\\" would be wrong and hence its answer would be 'no'."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- The musical term alto, meaning \\"high\\" in (Latin: ), refers to the second highest part of a contrapuntal musical texture and is also applied to its associated vocal range, especially in choral music. More rarely it describes the highest male solo voice type (usually designated countertenor), and it is also the root word of contralto, the lowest standard female voice type. When designating instruments, \\"alto\\" likewise can refer either to the corresponding vocal range (alto flute and alto trombone) or to musical role (alto recorder and alto clarinet).\\n\\n- The alto clarinet is a woodwind instrument of the clarinet family. It is a transposing instrument pitched in the key of E, though instruments in F (and in the 19th century, E) have been made. In Europe it is sometimes called a tenor clarinet. In size it lies between the soprano clarinet and the bass clarinet, to which it bears a greater resemblance in that it typically has a straight body (made of Grenadilla or other wood, hard rubber, or plastic), but a curved neck and bell made of metal. All-metal alto clarinets also exist. In appearance it strongly resembles the basset horn, but usually differs in three respects: it is pitched a tone lower, it lacks an extended lower range, and it has a wider bore than many basset horns.\\n\\n- A countertenor is a type of classical male singing voice whose vocal range is equivalent to that of the female contralto or mezzo-soprano voice types. The countertenor range is generally equivalent to a contralto range, extending from around G to D or E, although a sopranist (a specific kind of countertenor) may match the soprano's range of around C to C. Countertenors often are baritones or tenors at core, but rarely use this vocal range in performance. The countertenor voice type has a lower tessitura than the contralto or mezzo-soprano.\\n\\n- Philip Paul Bliss (9 July 1838  29 December 1876) was an American composer, conductor, writer of hymns and a bass-baritone Gospel singer. He wrote many well-known hymns, including \\"Almost Persuaded\\"; \\"Hallelujah, What a Saviour!\\"; \\"Let the Lower Lights Be Burning\\"; \\"Wonderful Words of Life\\" and the tune for Horatio Spafford's \\"It Is Well with My Soul\\".\\n\\n- Tenor is a type of classical male singing voice whose vocal range is one of the highest of the male voice types. The tenor's vocal range (in choral music) lies between C, the C one octave below middle C, and A, the A above middle C. In solo work, this range extends up to C, or \\"tenor high C\\". The low extreme for tenors is roughly A (two As below middle C). At the highest extreme, some tenors can sing up to two Fs above middle C (F).\\nThe tenor voice type is generally divided into the \\"leggero\\" tenor, lyric tenor, spinto tenor, dramatic tenor, heldentenor, and tenor buffo or spieltenor.\\n\\n- Gospel music is a music genre in Christian music. The creation, performance, significance, and even the definition of gospel music varies according to culture and social context. Gospel music is composed and performed for many purposes, including aesthetic pleasure, religious or ceremonial purposes, and as an entertainment product for the marketplace. Gospel music usually has dominant vocals (often with strong use of harmony) with Christian lyrics. Gospel music can be traced to the early 17th century, with roots in the black oral tradition. Hymns and sacred songs were repeated in a call and response fashion. Most of the churches relied on hand clapping and foot stomping as rhythmic accompaniment. Most of the singing was done a cappella. The first published use of the term \\"Gospel Song\\" probably appeared in 1874. The original gospel songs were written and composed by authors such as George F. Root, Philip Bliss, Charles H. Gabriel, William Howard Doane, and Fanny Crosby. Gospel music publishing houses emerged. The advent of radio in the 1920s greatly increased the audience for gospel music. Following World War II, gospel music moved into major auditoriums, and gospel music concerts became quite elaborate.\\n\\n- A contralto is a type of classical female singing voice whose vocal range is the lowest female voice type.\\nThe contralto's vocal range is fairly rare; similar to, but different from the alto, and almost identical to that of a countertenor, typically between the F below middle C (F in scientific pitch notation) to the second F above middle C (F), although at the extremes some voices can reach the E below middle C (E) or the second B above middle C (B). The contralto voice type is generally divided into the coloratura, lyric, and dramatic contralto.\\n\\n- The alto flute is a type of Western concert flute, a musical instrument in the woodwind family. It is the next extension downward of the C flute after the fl√ªte d'amour. It is characterized by its distinct, mellow tone in the lower portion of its range. It is a transposing instrument in G and, like the piccolo and bass flute, uses the same fingerings as the C flute.\\n\\n- Lynda Tait Randle , alto singer of southern gospel music , was born in 1962 and grew up in the inner city of Washington , DC.\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat is the relationship between 'lynda randle' and 'contralto'?","target":"voice type","rationale":"The context mentions the name \\"Lynda Randle\\" and states that she is an alto singer of southern gospel music. In addition, it says that Lynda was born in 1962 and grew up in Washington DC.\\nSince there are no additional details about the text provided, we cannot understand what this relationship is based on just the information given here: could be a voice type or something else completely random like occupation etc., so not given as our answer"},{"source":"Given a prompt and two completions from a language model, select the completion that is the most fluent with respect to continuing the prompt. Fluency is defined by coherency and ease of understanding, not necessarily grammatical correctness. Generate either Completion A or Completion B.\\n\\nPrompt: Idgaf wat a bitch or a nigga thank n fuck \\nCompletion A: that. What tha fuck happened in tha ghetto when tha fizzled tha ghetto was fucked wit, muthafucka. Why tha fuck are \\nCompletion B: or a bitch is a bitch or a nigga, so if you make the nigga a bitch, you get paid nigga. If you mak","target":"Completion A","rationale":"Completion A is more coherent and easier to understand while Completion B seems like a random word sequence that does not make any sense."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nJames entered the patio. Mason entered the patio. The pear is in the green_suitcase. Phone rang. Mason exited the patio. James moved the pear to the red_bucket. Owen entered the garden. James entered the garden. The grapefruit is in the blue_cupboard. James exited the garden. Owen moved the grapefruit to the red_cupboard. Phone rang. Mason entered the crawlspace. Owen entered the crawlspace. The potato is in the red_box. Phone rang. Owen exited the crawlspace. Mason moved the potato to the blue_bathtub. Mason entered the garden. Phone rang. Jack entered the garden. The grapefruit is in the red_cupboard. Jack exited the garden. Mason moved the grapefruit to the blue_cupboard. Where does Mason think that Jack searches for the grapefruit?","target":"red_cupboard","rationale":"Mason's belief about Jack's search for the grapefruit is that he searched for it in the red_cupboard. This is because Mason does not know that Jack found and moved the grapefruit from red_cupboard to blue_cupboard."},{"source":"Given a passage as input, answer with the category to which the passage belongs. There are 5 categories - Sports and Fitness, Home and Garden, Hobbies and Crafts, Food and Entertaining, Cars & Other Vehicles. The answer should be one of the categories based on words from the passage which closely belong to the category.\\n\\nWipe Wipe away any loose dirt, toothpaste, food particles, etc, with a rag or wet paper towel. Scrub Scrub off any stuck on gook with a cleaning toothbrush, sponge, or rag. Wipe off all the grime you just scrubbed off.Polish Wet the faucet with a quick splash of water, then take a dry paper towel and wipe until dry and spotless.","target":"Home and Garden","rationale":"All the steps mentioned in the passage are about cleaning and maintaining a shiny faucet, which is an item that can be found in any bathroom or kitchen. Thus, it can be inferred that the passage is about cleaning and maintenance of fixtures found in bathrooms or kitchens, which comes under the category \\"Home and Garden\\"."},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: Mary travelled to the kitchen. Sandra moved to the office. Mary went back to the bedroom. Mary journeyed to the kitchen. John travelled to the bedroom. Daniel went to the bedroom. Sandra journeyed to the garden. Sandra travelled to the office. Mary travelled to the office. Mary journeyed to the kitchen. Question: Where is Sandra?","target":"office","rationale":"The last sentence in the passage states that Sandra travels to the office."},{"source":"Answer the question...what does cprs stand for in the va??","target":"Computerized Patient Record System","rationale":"The Computerized Patient Record System (CPRS) is a clinical information system used by the United States Department of Veterans Affairs."},{"source":"Given a statement and question, generate the answer to the question such that the answer is contained in the statement.\\n\\nstatement: Bugs generally have two pairs of wings to move quickly away from predators., question: How many pairs of wings do Bugs have?","target":"two pairs","rationale":"The statement says bugs have two pairs of wings. So the answer to the question would be two pairs"},{"source":"In this task, find the most appropriate number to replace the blank (indicated with _ ) and express it in words.\\n\\nArtificial nectar ferments quickly, in one to _ days.","target":"two","rationale":"The blank is followed by 'to', which means the number must be within the range of 1 and 2. The correct answer is 'two' because it is closer to 2 than 1."},{"source":"Choose your answer from options. Premise: \\"For more information on how depreciation is measured in NIPA, see Arnold Katz and Shelby Herman, Improved Estimates of Fixed Reproducible Tangible Wealth, 1929-95, Survey of Current Business, Bureau of Economic Analysis   \\" If this premise is true, what does that tell us about whether it entails the hypothesis \\"The 1929-95 Survey of Current Business isn't a good source of additional information on how NIPA measures depreciation.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise describes the 1929-95 Survey of Current Business as a good source for information on NIPA measures, so this indicates that it is not likely to contain incorrect or misleading information."},{"source":"What might have been said before this? OK, how far are you willing to travel?","target":"I need reservations at a high end restaurant","rationale":"The given utterance refers to the distance a customer is willing to travel, and therefore, it might have been preceded by an action or item related to traveling. Hence, the answer is \\"I need reservations at a high end restaurant\\"."},{"source":"But I digress . The elven prince wanted nothing more than to restore his people to their former glory and he was cut down because of it . Sure , he would ' ve taken the extreme measure of committing genocide on all of mankind , but by the movie 's telling it was almost par for the course .\\nAccording to the above context, choose the best option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: What kind of movie might this be ?\\nOptions:\\nA. None of the above choices .\\nB. A fantasy movie\\nC. A horror movie\\nD. An action movie","target":"B","rationale":"The context talks about an elven prince who wants to restore his people's glory and commits genocide on all of mankind. This suggests that the movie is a fantasy movie, as it contains magical elements such as elves and magic kingdoms.\\nSo, the answer is B.\\"\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are provided with an article of the legal acts. Your task is to classify it into three categories (Regulation, Decision and Directive) based on its content: 1) Regulation is a binding legislative act that must be applied in its entirety on a set date across all the member states (European Union countries). 2) Decision is binding on those to whom it is addressed (e.g. an European Union country or an individual company) and is directly applicable. 3) Directive is a legislative act that sets out a goal that all  must achieve. However, it is up to the individual countries to devise their own laws on how to reach these goals.\\n\\nThe apparatus described as 'Burroughs - B7700 Information Processing System' is not considered to be a scientific apparatus. This Decision is addressed to the Member States.","target":"Decision","rationale":"The article is addressed to the Member States, so it should be classified as a Decision."},{"source":"In this task, you're given five sentences, numbered 1 through 5, and two options a and b for possible titles for the story. Your job is to choose the title that better fits the story. Indicate your choice by 'a' or 'b'.\\n\\nSentence 1: DJ had just moved from her home for college. Sentence 2: DJ would always watch mom cook pasta. Sentence 3: Suddenly one day her mom paid her a visit. Sentence 4: DJ made pasta the same way her mom made by visualizing her cook. Sentence 5: DJ made the most wonderful pasta her mom ever tasted. Choices: a. Tidy up. b. Pasta making.","target":"b","rationale":"The story is about DJ learning to make pasta from her mother, which is relevant to the title \\\\\\"Pasta making\\\\\\" but less relevant to the title \\\\\\"Tidy up\\\\\\"."},{"source":"who plays the stark mother in game of thrones??","target":"Michelle Fairley","rationale":"Michelle Fairley is the actress who plays Catelyn Stark in Game of Thrones."},{"source":"Produce a brief English sentence that would be considered grammatically as category: unacceptable\\nAll categories: OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"Anson is incredibly difficult to be pleased.","rationale":"Here's an example of an unacceptable English sentence: Anson is incredibly difficult to be pleased."},{"source":"Classify the given tweet into the three categories: (1) 'Hate Speech', (2) 'Offensive' and (3) 'Neither'. 'Hate Speech' is kind of a threating statement or sometimes include call for violence while 'offensive' statement just offensds someone. 'Neither' is when it doesn't fall into Hate Speech or Offensive category.\\n\\n@Steven_ratata bye youre a queer","target":"Hate Speech","rationale":"The given tweet is clearly a homophobic statement as it uses the word \\"queer\\", which has been used throughout history to describe people who don't conform with heterosexual norms. The use of this language can be extremely harmful and hurtful, especially for young members of the LGBTQ+ community. Therefore, we classify this example as Hate Speech."},{"source":"Qwest's revised bid, which did not offer more cash for MCI stock as expected, was deemed disappointing by one major MCI shareholder, and Qwest's shares fell more than 8 percent.\\n\\nQ with options: Can we draw the following conclusion?\\nMCI shareholders accepted a $6.7 billion offer over Qwest's initial $8 billion.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The context only states that a MCI shareholder was disappointed with Qwest's revised bid and does not provide any conclusive evidence about the acceptance of this offer."},{"source":"Read the passage below and choose the right answer to the following question (choices are larger age or smaller age ):\\n\\nThe older a person is, the greater their chance of developing a cardiovascular disease.\\n\\n\\nDerek's dad was now at a reduced risk of getting a cardiovascular disease, even though nothing about his lifestyle or diet changed. The thing that did change is that his dad is now considered to be at a larger age or smaller age?","target":"smaller age","rationale":"The passage states that \\"the older a person is, the greater their chance of developing a cardiovascular disease\\". Thus it can be inferred that if Derek's dad was at an older age and now has had a birthday his risk factor for getting this condition would have gone down. \\nTherefore the answer to this question is smaller age"},{"source":"Multi-select: Let's say that \\"Sam broke both his ankles and he's walking with crutches. But a month or so from now they should be better.\\"\\n\\nCan we now say that \\"The crutches should be better.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"The first sentence mentions that Sam has broken both his ankles and is walking with crutches. The second sentence claims that the \\"crutches should be better\\", but this does not make sense as the statement only talks about Sam's ankles, which were injured in the previous sentence, so it would mean nothing to say that they will get better in a month or two (because he already broke them). Therefore, we can conclude that \\"the crutches should be better\\" after one month, since there is no evidence to support such a claim."},{"source":"What is the answer for the question: What is the last name of the person who announced that his All-Starr Band would tour the Pacific Rim during 2013? from the following article ?\\n\\nIn 2010 Starr self-produced and released his fifteenth studio album, Y Not, which included the track \\"Walk with You\\" and featured a vocal contribution from McCartney. Later that year, he appeared during Hope for Haiti Now: A Global Benefit for Earthquake Relief as a celebrity phone operator. On 7 July 2010, he celebrated his 70th birthday at Radio City Music Hall with another All-Starr Band concert, topped with friends and family joining him on stage including Ono, his son Zak, and McCartney.Starr recorded a cover of Buddy Holly's \\"Think It Over\\" for the 2011 tribute album Listen to Me: Buddy Holly. In January 2012, he released the album Ringo 2012. Later that year, he announced that his All-Starr Band would tour the Pacific Rim during 2013 with select dates in New Zealand, Australia and Japan; it was his first performance in Japan since 1996, and his debut in both New Zealand and Australia.\\nIn January 2014, Starr joined McCartney for a special performance at the 56th Annual Grammy Awards in Los Angeles, where they performed the song \\"Queenie Eye\\". That summer he toured Canada and the US with an updated version of the Twelfth All-Starr Band, featuring multi-instrumentalist Warren Ham instead of saxophonist Mark Rivera. In July, Starr became involved in \\"#peacerocks\\", an anti-violence campaign started by fashion designer John Varvatos, in conjunction with the David Lynch Foundation. In September 2014, he won at the GQ Men of the Year Awards for his humanitarian work with the David Lynch Foundation.In January 2015, Starr tweeted the title of his new 11-track studio album, Postcards from Paradise. The album came just weeks in advance of Starr's induction into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, and was released on 31 March 2015 to mixed to positive reviews. Later that month, Ringo and his band announced a forthcoming Summer 2016 Tour of the US. Full production began in June 2016 in Syracuse.On 7 July 2017 (his 77th birthday), he released a new single entitled \\"Give More Love,\\" followed by, on 15 September 2017 (by...","target":"Starr","rationale":"The question is asking for the last name of \\"the person\\". The context mentions a man named Ringo, who formed an All-Starr Band and announced that they would tour during 2013. Since 'Ringo' has been mentioned preceding this information we can infer that he is the subject in reference to whom these details have been provided.\\nGiven this, it can be inferred that Ringo's last name must be Starr (answer), as it follows his first name throughout the passage."},{"source":"Billy was was going on a long vacation, but before he did he got a bite to eat. Where might he have eaten?\\n\\n[Options]\\n- space shuttle\\n- friend's house\\n- disneyland\\n- supermarket\\n- gas station","target":"friend's house","rationale":"Mostly person goes on vacation with friends so he may go to friend's house to pick friend. Person can get light food at friend's house before going on vacation."},{"source":"The Flash (season 4) -- The fourth season began airing on October 10, 2017, and ran for 23 episodes on The CW until May 22, 2018.\\n\\nQ: is the flash coming back for season 4? True or False?","target":"True","rationale":"The answer is True."},{"source":"Choose your answer: If \\"A farmer fertilizing his garden with manure with a horse and wagon.\\", does it logically follow that \\"The man is on the city street with his horse and wagon.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The context is talking about a farmer fertilizing his garden with manure, and the passage never mentions that he was doing this on a city street. Therefore, we cannot logically deduce or infer from the given information that \\"the man (farmer) is on the city street\\". So, the answer should be \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Choose between \\"stainless steel counter top\\" and  \\"plastic cutting board\\".\\nQuestion: Billy the chef was peeling potatoes in the kitchen when he dropped two potatoes. One of the potato dropped on the stainless steel counter top and another potato dropped on a plastic cutting board. The plastic cutting board has tiny bumps on it, so the stainless steel counter top has a slicker surface. Due to less resistance, the potato rolled farther on the (A) stainless steel counter top (B) plastic cutting board","target":"stainless steel counter top","rationale":"A stainless steel counter top has a slicker surface than that of the plastic cutting board. Therefore, there is less resistance to motion and hence the potato rolled farther on it.\\nSo A - Stainless Steel Counter Top is correct !"},{"source":"Two analogies that relate places/locations to the associated travel mode is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates place A to travel mode B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate travel mode for the given place C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nmuseum : bus. cemetery : ?","target":"hearse","rationale":"To go to a museum, one could take a bus. Similarily, one could go to the cemetery with a hearse."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nAlexander entered the attic. Jackson entered the attic. The watermelon is in the green_crate. Alexander moved the watermelon to the blue_crate. Phone rang. Alexander entered the staircase. Liam entered the staircase. The asparagus is in the green_drawer. Alexander moved the asparagus to the blue_box. Alexander is in the staircase. Phone rang. Mason entered the staircase. The tomato is in the blue_box. Alexander moved the tomato to the green_drawer. Mason entered the playroom. Liam entered the playroom. The cucumber is in the green_bucket. Mason moved the cucumber to the red_cupboard. Where does Mason think that Liam searches for the cucumber?","target":"red_cupboard","rationale":"The question is asking about Mason's false belief about Liam's beliefs. In the story, Mason believes that he (Mason) put the cucumber in the red_cupboard and so therefore thinks that Liam will search for it there."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nElla entered the sunroom. Hannah entered the sunroom. The cucumber is in the green_pantry. Hannah exited the sunroom. Phone rang. Ella moved the cucumber to the green_cupboard. Ella entered the hallway. Hannah entered the hallway. The pineapple is in the red_drawer. Hannah exited the hallway. Ella moved the pineapple to the blue_crate. Ella entered the garden. James entered the garden. The apple is in the blue_suitcase. Phone rang. James exited the garden. Ella moved the apple to the green_bucket. William entered the garden. James entered the garden. The spinach is in the green_bucket. James exited the garden. William moved the spinach to the blue_suitcase. Where was the spinach at the beginning?","target":"green_bucket","rationale":"The story describes how William enters the garden and then moves the spinach from the green_bucket to the blue_suitcase."},{"source":"Indicate the presence of numerical data in the abstract (whether numerical data plays a key role in medical records), solely using the information from the abstract.\\n\\nAbstract: A product of the recent physical fitness boom has been an increased demand for better care of sport and recreational injuries. This article gives an overview of the care available for such injuries. In addition, it also cautions against the kind of care that will only produce noncompliance in the pediatric patient. \\nQuestion: Does the abstract contain any numerical data?","target":"No","rationale":"The abstract provides general information about sports injuries in children and it focuses on the types of care available for these injuries. However, it does not include any numerical values or measurements. So the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Radio Televizioni Shqiptar (RTSH) is the public radio and TV broadcaster of Albania, founded by King Zog in 1938. RTSH runs three analogue television stations as TVSH Televizioni Shqiptar, four digital thematic stations as RTSH, and three radio stations using the name Radio Tirana. In addition, 4 regional radio stations serve in the four extremities of Albania. The international service broadcasts radio programmes in Albanian and seven other languages via medium wave (AM) and short wave (SW). The international service has used the theme from the song \\"Keputa nje gjethe dafine\\" as its signature tune. The international television service via satellite was launched since 1993 and aims at Albanian communities in Kosovo, Serbia, Macedonia, Montenegro and northern Greece, plus the Albanian diaspora in the rest of Europe. RTSH has a past of being heavily influenced by the ruling party in its reporting, whether that party be left or right wing. According to the Albanian Media Authority, AMA, Albania has an estimated 257 media outlets, including 66 radio stations and 67 television stations, with three national, 62 local and more than 50 cable TV stations. Last years Albania has organized several shows as a part of worldwide series like Dancing with the Stars, Big Brother Albania, Albanians Got Talent, The Voice of Albania, and X Factor Albania. \\n\\nQuestion: How many Albanian media outlets have been used to broadcast shows such as Dancing with the Stars, Big Brother Albania, Albanians Got Talent, The Voice of Albania, and X Factor Albania.\\nI found this answer \\"66\\". Is that correct? Yes or no?","target":"No","rationale":"The passage mentions that Albania has an estimated 257 media outlets, including 66 radio stations and 67 television stations. However, it does not mention how many of these are in Albanian communities in Kosovo, Serbia, Macedonia, Montenegro and northern Greece or the number operating outside Europe. In addition to this limitation on the data available from RTSH's website, we do not have information about what is considered a \\"media outlet\\" (for example whether cable TV providers count as their own distinct entity), so cannot be sure if any given channel broadcasting one of the shows would qualify under AMA's definition for inclusion in its estimate. Therefore there may be more than 66 such channels but this figure cannot be determined based on what is said here.\\nThus No answer can't be found with certainty by considering only"},{"source":"Given a comment, classify it into a 'hate' speech or 'not hate' speech. Answer using 'hate' or 'not hate'.\\n\\nI am so sorry for all the people who disrespect all you guys and I wish I could do something¬† so they wouldn'. But I can' but you guys know¬† I love all you guys.√¢¬ù¬§","target":"not hate","rationale":"The given comment expresses support for the police and includes a heart emoji. This shows that the language is not meant to be hateful or offensive, but rather friendly and supportive. Therefore, it can be classified as \\"not hate\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue from a conversation between an agent and a customer. Your task is to determine the speaker of the dialogue. Answer with \\"agent\\" or \\"customer\\".\\n\\nPlease search a flight with single connection.","target":"customer","rationale":"The customer is asking the agent to search a flight with single connection. So the speaker of the dialogue is \\"customer\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question and answer options for that question. Using this information, you have to classify each text into different topics: medicine, nursery, psychology, chemistry, pharmacology, biology.\\n\\nQuestion: A biosensor consists of: \\n Options:  <0> A receiver, a transducer, and an enzymatic brand. <1> A receptor and an enzymatic brand. <2> A transducer and an enzymatic brand. <3> A receiver and a transducer. <4> A receptor and an antibody.","target":"chemistry","rationale":"The question asks about the components of a biosensor, which is a device that uses biological components to measure the concentration of a substance in a solution. The answer option states that it consists of \\"A receptor and an enzymatic brand\\", which refers to two parts of biosensors, namely receptors and enzyme-based transducers. These are used for biochemical reactions involving specific enzymes, so this is related to chemistry."},{"source":"Given a passage and a question, find the answer to the question based on the passage. The answer should consist of only one word that lies in the span of only one of the sentences in the passage.\\n\\nParagraph: High school principal Jefferson Pierce , who retired from his superhero persona Black Lightning nine years ago after seeing the effects it had on his family , is forced to become a vigilante again when the rise of the local gang called the 100 leads to increased crime and corruption in his community of Freeland .\\nQuestion: where does black lightning tv show take place","target":"Freeland","rationale":"The paragraph mentions that Black Lightning takes places in Freeland.  This is the answer to the question \\"where does black lightning tv show take place\\"."},{"source":"See the conversation. DIALOG:\\nWhat did Fred Thompson have to do with the Watergate hearings?\\n- In 1973, Fred Thompson was appointed minority counsel to assist the Republican senators on the Senate Watergate Committee.\\n- What was Fred Thompson's role on the Senate Watergate Committee?\\n- Fred Thompson was appointed minority counsel.\\n- Could you tell me something interesting about Fred Thompson and his role in the Watergate hearings?\\n- Fred Thompson was sometimes credited for supplying Republican Senator Howard Baker's famous question, What did the President know, and when did he know it?‚Äú\\n- How did Fred Thompson supplying Republicans questions help the Senate Watergate Committee?\\n-","target":"Fred Thompson's question is said to have helped frame the hearings in a way that eventually led to the downfall of President Richard Nixon.","rationale":"The last question, \\"How did Fred Thompson supplying Republicans questions help the Senate Watergate Committee?\\" can be answered by saying that Fred Thompson's question is said to have helped frame the hearings in a way that eventually led to the downfall of President Richard Nixon. This answer option is grammatically correct and provides information relevant to the dialogue context."},{"source":"WHITE HOUSE ‚Äî A controversial clothing choice is overshadowing a surprise visit by U.S. first lady Melania Trump to a Texas facility to meet immigrant children separated from their families because of her husband's \\"zero-tolerance\\" immigration policy.\\nBoarding a U.S. Air Force jet at and returning to Joint Base Andrews in Maryland on Thursday, the first lady was spotted wearing an olive green jacket. The back of the jacket read \\"I really don't care. Do U?\\" in white graffiti-style lettering.\\nThe first lady's team insisted that there was no hidden meaning behind the sartorial choice.\\n\\"It's a jacket. There was no hidden message. After today's important visit to Texas, I hope the media isn't going to choose to focus on her wardrobe,\\" said her communications director, Stephanie Grisham.\\nPresident Donald Trump, however, contradicted the assertion there was no message conveyed by his wife's choice of apparel.\\nTrump, in a tweet, said what was written on the back of the jacket \\"refers to the Fake News Media. Melania has learned how dishonest they are, and she truly no longer cares!\\"\\nTelevision news channels brought pundits in the studio to discuss the meaning conveyed by the jacket.\\n\\"I think she may have had an audience of one in mind ‚Äî her husband,\\" said USA Today newspaper Washington bureau chief Susan Page, who has covered six presidential administrations, appearing on MSNBC.\\n\\"I think it was Melania giving the middle finger to the media,\\" Kate Anderson Brower, author of First Women: The Grace & Power of America's Modern First Ladies, told VOA. \\"But someone should have told her that it could also be read that she doesn't care about the children, which is clearly not the case.\\"\\nFashion bloggers quickly identified the jacket as one selling for $39 by Zara, a fast fashion global retailer.\\nIt was a relatively humble selection by Trump, a former Paris runway model who is frequently clad for public appearances in haute couture dresses and coats.\\nQuestion: Stephanie Grisham probably believes that:\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. Melania does not care about fashion.\\n\\nB. not enough information\\n\\nC. It's a jacket. There were no hidden messages.\\n\\nD. Melania does not care about the children.\\n\\n===\\nThe correct answer is","target":"C","rationale":"A is not the answer because Stephanie Grisham does not say that Melania doesn't care about fashion. B is not correct because there is enough information to make a choice from among these options, C means \\"Stephanie Grisham probably believes that It's a jacket. There were no hidden messages.\\", D can be eliminated as incorrect since it was clear in the news story that people thought she didn't care about children but it wasn't Mrs Grishams belief"},{"source":"Read this article and answer this question Still searching for their first win of the season, the Chiefs flew to Lincoln Financial Field for a Week 3 interconference duel with the Philadelphia Eagles. Kansas City would trail early in the first quarter as Eagles running back LeSean McCoy got a 5-yard touchdown run and quarterback Kevin Kolb got a 1-yard touchdown run. The Chiefs would get on the board with quarterback Matt Cassel's 13-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver Mark Bradley, but Philadelphia came right back with Kolb's 64-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver DeSean Jackson and kicker David Akers' 29-yard field goal. Kansas City's deficit would increase as Akers nailed a 38-yard field goal in the third quarter. In the fourth quarter, the Eagles would put the game away with Kolb's 35-yard touchdown pass to tight end Brent Celek. Afterwards, the Chiefs would end the game with Cassel's 9-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver Bobby Wade.\\nHow many yards longer was David Akers's second field goal compared to his first?","target":"9","rationale":"First, we need to identify the length of David Akers's first field goal (STEP 1) which is 29 yards. Then, we have to find out how long his second field goal was (STEP 2), which is 38 yards in total. Finally, by subtracting these two lengths from each other and finding the difference between them (STEP 3), it becomes clear that there were 9 more yards on his second kick compared to his first one!"},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Count Dooku is a fictional character from the \\"Star Wars\\" franchise, appearing in \\"\\" and \\"\\" (portrayed by Christopher Lee). He was also voiced by Corey Burton in the animated series \\"\\".\\n\\n- Francisco Scaramanga is a fictional character and the main antagonist in the James Bond novel and film versions of \\"The Man with the Golden Gun\\". Scaramanga's signature weapon is a golden gun. In the novel, the character is nicknamed \\"Pistols\\" Scaramanga and is also called \\"Paco\\" (a Spanish diminutive of Francisco). In the film, the character was played by Christopher Lee (the real-life step-cousin of James Bond creator Ian Fleming).\\n\\n- Count Dracula is the title character and main antagonist of Bram Stoker's 1897 gothic horror novel \\"Dracula\\". He is considered to be both the prototypical and the archetypal vampire in subsequent works of fiction. He is also depicted in the novel to be the origin of werewolf legends. Some aspects of the character are believed to have been inspired by the 15th-century Wallachian Prince Vlad III the Impaler, who was also known as Dracula. Other character aspects have been added or altered in subsequent popular fictional works. The character has subsequently appeared frequently in popular culture, from films to animated media to breakfast cereals.\\n\\n- Pierce Brendan Brosnan OBE (born 16 May 1953) is an Irish actor, film producer, and activist who after leaving comprehensive school at age 16, began training in commercial illustration. He then went on to train at the Drama Centre in London for three years. Following a stage acting career he rose to popularity in the television series \\"Remington Steele\\" (198287), which blended the genres of romantic comedy, drama, and detective procedural. After the conclusion of \\"Remington Steele\\", Brosnan appeared in films such as the Cold War spy film \\"The Fourth Protocol\\" (1987) and the comedy \\"Mrs. Doubtfire\\" (1993).\\n\\n- Saruman the White is a fictional character and a major antagonist in J. R. R. Tolkien's fantasy novel \\"The Lord of the Rings\\". He is leader of the Istari, wizards sent to Middle-earth in human form by the godlike Valar to challenge Sauron, the main antagonist of the novel, but eventually he desires Sauron's power for himself and tries to take over Middle-earth by force. His schemes feature prominently in the second volume, \\"The Two Towers\\", and at the end of the third volume, \\"The Return of the King\\". His earlier history is given briefly in the posthumously published \\"The Silmarillion\\" and \\"Unfinished Tales\\".\\n\\n- Sir Christopher Frank Carandini Lee (27 May 1922  7 June 2015) was an English actor, singer, and author. With a career spanning nearly 70 years, Lee initially portrayed villains and became best known for his role as Count Dracula in a sequence of Hammer Horror films. His other film roles include Francisco Scaramanga in the James Bond film \\"The Man with the Golden Gun\\" (1974), Saruman in \\"The Lord of the Rings\\" film trilogy (20012003) and \\"The Hobbit\\" film trilogy (20122014), and Count Dooku in the final two films of the \\"Star Wars\\" prequel trilogy (2002 and 2005).\\n\\n- Frank Theodore \\"Ted\\" Levine (born May 29, 1957) is an American actor. He is known for his roles as Buffalo Bill in \\"The Silence of the Lambs\\" and as Captain Leland Stottlemeyer in the television series \\"Monk\\".\\n\\n- The James Bond series focuses on a fictional British Secret Service agent created in 1953 by writer Ian Fleming, who featured him in twelve novels and two short-story collections. Since Fleming's death in 1964, eight other authors have written authorised Bond novels or novelizations: Kingsley Amis, Christopher Wood, John Gardner, Raymond Benson, Sebastian Faulks, Jeffery Deaver, William Boyd and Anthony Horowitz. The latest novel is \\"Trigger Mortis\\" by Anthony Horowitz, published in September 2015. Additionally Charlie Higson wrote a series on a young James Bond, and Kate Westbrook wrote three novels based on the diaries of a recurring series character, Moneypenny.\\n\\n- Alexandra Elizabeth Paul (born July 29, 1963) is an American actress, activist, health coach, and former model. Paul began her career modeling in New York before landing her first major role in John Carpenter's horror film \\"Christine\\" (1983). This was followed with prominent roles in \\"American Flyers\\" (1985), \\"8 Million Ways to Die\\" (1986), and \\"Dragnet\\" (1987).\\n\\n- Mrs. Doubtfire is a 1993 American comedy-drama film directed by Chris Columbus and written by Randi Mayem Singer and Leslie Dixon, based on \\"Madame Doubtfire\\" by Anne Fine. It stars Robin Williams (who also served as co-producer), Sally Field, Pierce Brosnan, Harvey Fierstein and Robert Prosky. It follows a recently divorced actor who dresses up as a female housekeeper to be able to interact with his children.\\n\\n- Sir Patrick Stewart OBE (born 13 July 1940) is an English actor whose career has included roles on stage, television, and film.\\n\\n- Captain Leland Francis Stottlemeyer is a fictional police officer played by Ted Levine on the American crime drama \\"Monk\\". He is Captain of the San Francisco Police Department (SFPD)'s Homicide Detail, and a longtime (even if long-suffering) friend of Adrian Monk from their days on the force together where he served as Monk's fourth partner and later watch commander. His partner, and source of much strife, is Lieutenant Randy Disher. He, like many of the characters in the show, can be viewed as a parallel to a Sherlock Holmes character (in this case, Inspector Lestrade).\\n\\n- Star Wars is an American epic space opera franchise, centered on a film series created by George Lucas. It depicts the adventures of various characters \\"a long time ago in a galaxy far, far away\\".\\n\\n- Death Train ( also known as Detonator ) is a 1993 made - for - TV movie featuring Pierce Brosnan , Patrick Stewart , Christopher Lee , Ted Levine , and Alexandra Paul . The script was based on an Alistair MacNeill novel of the same name , which in turn was based on an Alistair MacLean screenplay .\\n\\n- Where Eagles Dare is a British 1968 World War II action film starring Richard Burton, Clint Eastwood, Mary Ure, and Ingrid Pitt. It was directed by Brian G. Hutton and shot on location in Austria and Bavaria. Alistair MacLean wrote the novel and the screenplay, at the same time. It was his first screenplay; both film and book became commercial successes.\\n\\n- Alistair Stuart MacLean (21 April 1922  2 February 1987) was a Scottish novelist who wrote popular thrillers and adventure stories. His works include \\"The Guns of Navarone\\", \\"Ice Station Zebra\\" and \\"Where Eagles Dare\\"  all three were made into popular films. He also wrote two novels under the pseudonym Ian Stuart.\\n\\n- John Howard Carpenter (born January 16, 1948) is an American film director, screenwriter, producer, musician, editor and composer. Although Carpenter has worked in numerous film genres, he is most commonly associated with horror and science fiction films from the 1970s and 1980s.\\n\\n- 8 Million Ways to Die is a 1986 American crime film. This was the final film directed by Hal Ashby, and the first attempt to adapt the Matthew Scudder detective stories of Lawrence Block for the screen. The screenplay was written by Oliver Stone, an uncredited Robert Towne and David Lee Henry (R. Lance Hill using a pseudonym). The film starred Jeff Bridges, Rosanna Arquette, and, in a leading role for the first time, Andy Garcia.\\n\\n- The Cold War was a state of political and military tension after World War II between powers in the Eastern Bloc (the Soviet Union and its satellite states) and powers in the Western Bloc (the United States, its NATO allies and others). Historians do not fully agree on the dates, but a common timeframe is the period (the second half of the 20th century) between 1947, the year the Truman Doctrine (a U.S. policy pledging to aid nations threatened by Soviet expansionism) was announced, and 1991, the year the Soviet Union collapsed.\\n\\n- American Flyers is a 1985 American sports drama film starring Kevin Costner, David Marshall Grant, Rae Dawn Chong, Alexandra Paul, Luca Bercovici and Janice Rule about bicycle racing. \\n\\n- Remington Steele is an American television series co-created by Robert Butler and Michael Gleason. The series, starring Stephanie Zimbalist and Pierce Brosnan, was produced by MTM Enterprises and first broadcast on the NBC network from 1982 to 1987. The series blended the genres of romantic comedy, drama, and detective procedural. \\"Remington Steele\\" is best known for launching the career of Pierce Brosnan.\\n\\n\\n\\nAfter reading the paragraphs above, choose the best answer for the entity that related to 'death train' with the relationship of 'genre'.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- action\\n - action film\\n - adventure\\n - animated series\\n - comedy\\n - crime\\n - crime film\\n - detective\\n - drama\\n - epic\\n - fantasy\\n - fantasy novel\\n - fiction\\n - health\\n - history\\n - horror\\n - horror novel\\n - james\\n - novel\\n - romantic comedy\\n - science\\n - science fiction\\n - screenplay\\n - space\\n - spy film\\n - television\\n - war\\n - werewolf","target":"action","rationale":"The paragraphs above describe movies, TV series and books. But the question only asks for which entity is related to 'death train' with the relationship of 'genre'. And we can see that in paragraph 6 there are two entities:\\n- Death Train ( also known as Detonator ) is a 1993 made - for - TV movie featuring Pierce Brosnan , Patrick Stewart , Christopher Lee , Ted Levine , and Alexandra Paul . The script was based on an Alistair MacNeill novel of the same name , which in turn was based on an Alistair MacLean screenplay . \\n- Where Eagles Dare is a British 1968 World War II action film starring Richard Burton, Clint Eastwood, Mary Ure, and Ingrid Pitt. It was directed by Brian G. Hutton and shot"},{"source":"Exercise: read the text and answer the question by True or False.\\n\\nText: Privacy Act of 1974 -- The Privacy Act of 1974 (Pub.L. 93--579, 88 Stat. 1896, enacted December 31, 1974, 5 U.S.C. ¬ß 552a), a United States federal law, establishes a Code of Fair Information Practice that governs the collection, maintenance, use, and dissemination of personally identifiable information about individuals that is maintained in systems of records by federal agencies. A system of records is a group of records under the control of an agency from which information is retrieved by the name of the individual or by some identifier assigned to the individual. The Privacy Act requires that agencies give the public notice of their systems of records by publication in the Federal Register. The Privacy Act prohibits the disclosure of information from a system of records absent of the written consent of the subject individual, unless the disclosure is pursuant to one of twelve statutory exceptions. The Act also provides individuals with a means by which to seek access to and amendment of their records and sets forth various agency record-keeping requirements. Additionally, with people granted the right to review what was documented with their name, they are also able to find out if the \`\`records have been disclosed''... and are also given the rights to make corrections.\\nQuestion: does the privacy act of 1974 apply to corporations?","target":"False","rationale":"The Privacy Act of 1974 applies to federal agencies, but not private corporations. This can be inferred from the text's discussion on how records are retrieved by name or identifier assigned and a requirement for public notice in the Federal Register. These indicate that the law only governs federally-maintained systems of records because The Federal Register is published daily by the National Archives and Records Administration (NARA) on federal government news.\\nSo, privacy act of 1974 apply to Corporations = False"},{"source":"Formulate an answer to this elaborate question: What was the population in 2000 for the region of Kansas that includes Greenwood County?","target":"180,815","rationale":"The population of the state of Kansas was 2,688,418 in 2000. \\nGreenwood County is one of 105 counties located within this region and has a total area of 876 square miles. The county seat is Eureka. According to U.S Census Bureau data from 2000, Greenwood had a population size estimate at the time that was 5% larger than its present-day census count (180,815)."},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is the next sentence syntactically and semantically acceptable?\\n\\nPick any flower.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"This sentence is acceptable. It has \\"pick\\" as the verb, which belongs to a class of verbs that can be followed by either an object or a gerund (as in \\"Pick me up at eight.\\"). Here, it's followed by the noun phrase 'any flower.'"},{"source":"Given a paragraph about cooking, and a set of conversational question answers about the paragraph, answer a follow-up question from the paragraph. The paragraph has a prefix 'CONTEXT:'. Each conversation question has a prefix 'Q:' followed by answer prefix 'A:'. The final followup question has a prefix 'FOLLOWUP_Q:'.\\n\\nCONTEXT: I've never juiced a pineapple, but I have done a watermelon and I've had some success with a food processor and a cheese cloth. I'd remove the core of the pineapple, because I don't think there's much juice in it. Remove the skin as well. Then run the pineapple through the food processor and pour all of the contents into a cheese cloth over a bowl. Squeeze all the juice you can out of whatever's in the cheese cloth. If you don't have a food processor, you can maybe use a cheese grater or potato masher instead.  <sep>  Q: What is the Best way to juice a pineapple? A: I'd remove the core of the pineapple, because I don't think there's much juice in it. Remove the skin as well  Q: What is the easiest way to remove the skin?###And is there a tool for removing the core? A: I've never juiced a pineapple, but I have done a watermelon and I've had some success with a food processor and a cheese cloth  Q: Should you cut the pineapple into chunks before trying to juice it, or just do the whole thing in one go? A: run the pineapple through the food processor and pour all of the contents into a cheese cloth over a bowl. Squeeze all the juice you can out of whatever's in the cheese cloth  <sep> FOLLOWUP_Q: How big of a food processor do you need for this?","target":"If you don't have a food processor, you can maybe use a cheese grater or potato masher instead","rationale":"The question asks how large of a food processor one needs and this can be answered by the statement, \\"If you don't have a food processor, you can maybe use a cheese grater or potato masher instead.\\""},{"source":"What was likely said next? DIALOG:\\nWhat was the name of American band Exile's first released single?\\n-","target":"In 1977, Exile released the single Try it On on Atco Records, and it became a minor hit.","rationale":"The most likely next sentence is Exile's first released single was In 1977, Exile released the single Try it On on Atco Records, and it became a minor hit."},{"source":"There is no hiding from the impact agenda. The impact weighting of the Research Excellence Framework has been increased for 2021, and more recently the UK Government announced a new funding stream for knowledge exchange. But achieving impact isn‚Äôt easy, especially for researchers early in their careers.\\nIf you ever have a spare week, or ten, it‚Äôs worth reading through some of the 6,637 REF impact case studies on the HEFCE website. There are some brilliant and fascinating examples of how researchers have achieved impact, but what strikes me most is how different impact looks across different subjects. At the risk of being flippant, among many of the medical or technological examples there is a familiar pattern and a clear route to impact: make breakthrough; license drug/technology; save lives/¬£millions.\\nFor social and political science (not to mention economics, languages, education, philosophy, etc.) the route to impact is much more fragmented. Among the 97 sociology case studies, for example, impact comes from numerous briefings of government officials and parliamentarians, before the academics join ‚Äúnetworks‚Äù and ‚Äúcommittees‚Äù discussing their research and wider issues. Their research is covered by national media, they meet even more people ‚Äì practitioners or third sector campaigning organisations to pass on their knowledge. And, after all that, and often a good deal more, sometimes there is a policy or practice change that can be pointed to as a direct impact, sometimes not.\\nCentral to much of the impact is ‚Äúaccess‚Äù. Prominent and experienced academics are more likely to get on the committees, know the right journalists and government officials, and have links into third sector organisations, etc. I worked with Professor Sir John Curtice, of election night fame, for a number of years. He didn‚Äôt need much support. I advised and facilitated, but after 30 years in the game he knew Whitehall (and Holyrood) inside and out ‚Äì and they knew him. But many researchers, especially at the start of their careers, don‚Äôt...\\nQuestion: When does the author say that researchers can make millions?\\n===\\nThe answer to the above question is","target":"after making a breakthrough","rationale":"The author says that \\"making millions\\" follows making a breakthrough. So, the answer is after making a breakthrough"},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and extract the answer for the question: What is the first name of the person whose feature was adapted in Warner's Ring production?\\n\\nPeter Hall directed the Bayreuth Ring after Ch√©reau. His version, staged 1983‚Äì86, portrayed the natural innocence of the Rhinemaidens in the simplest of ways; they were naked. Keith Warner adapted this feature in his Ring production for the Royal Opera House Covent Garden, first staged 2004‚Äì06. A Covent Garden spokesman explained \\"The maidens are children of innocence, a vision of nature ‚Äì and as soon as someone appears they hastily throw on some clothes to protect their modesty.\\" While Warner relies on lighting to achieve an underwater effect, Hall used a Pepper's ghost illusion: mirrors at a 45¬∞ angle made the Rhinemaidens appear to swim vertically when the performers were in fact swimming horizontally in a shallow basin.Although the roles of the Rhinemaidens are relatively small, they have been sung by notable singers better known for performing major roles in Wagnerian and other repertoire. The first person to sing the part of Woglinde in full was Lilli Lehmann at Bayreuth in 1876. In 1951, when the Bayreuth Festival re-opened after the Second World War, the same part was taken by Elisabeth Schwarzkopf. Other Bayreuth Rhinemaidens include  Helga Dernesch who sang Wellgunde there between 1965 and 1967. Lotte Lehmann  played Wellgunde at the Hamburg State Opera between 1912 and 1914 and the Vienna State Opera in 1916.   Recorded Rhinemaidens have included Sena Jurinac for Furtw√§ngler and RAI, Lucia Popp and Gwyneth Jones for Georg Solti, and Helen Donath and Edda Moser for Karajan.","target":"Peter","rationale":"Peter Hall directed the Bayreuth Ring after Ch√©reau. His version, staged 1983‚Äì86, portrayed the natural innocence of the Rhinemaidens in the simplest of ways; they were naked. Keith Warner adapted this feature in his Ring production for the Royal Opera House Covent Garden, first staged 2004‚Äì06. A Covent Garden spokesman explained \\"The maidens are children of innocence, a vision of nature ‚Äì and as soon as someone appears they hastily throw on some clothes to protect their modesty.\\" While Warner relies on lighting to achieve an underwater effect, Hall used a Pepper's ghost illusion: mirrors at a 45¬∞ angle made the Rhinemaidens appear to swim vertically when the performers were in fact swimming horizontally in a shallow basin.Although"},{"source":"I am verifying the answers generated by an automatic system to the following question: what are corporation balance\\nSuggested answer: Looking at the equation in this way shows how assets were financed: either by borrowing money (liability) or by using the owner's money (owner's equity).\\nShould I validate this answer?","target":"No","rationale":"The suggested answer provided by the automatic system is not a reasonable answer to the question. The first part of this statement defines what assets are and does not provide any information about how they were acquired, which would be an appropriate response to this question.\\nAdditionally, it contains errant punctuation that suggests inherent flaws in its reasoning or accuracy. \\nTherefore, the answer is No."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that does not connect with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nTitle: Baby Fight. Sentence 1: Ginger's two babies were toddling around the living room. Sentence 2: She kept an eye on them as she made breakfast. Sentence 3: Suddenly she heard a loud scream. Sentence 4: One boy was taking something from the other. Choices: a. Ginger decided to separate them for awhile to keep them quiet. b. Luckily a pot holder solved the issue so he could eat.","target":"b","rationale":"Both options are plausible in that they describe a potential outcome of the situation, but option b doesn't make sense because it provides information about the boy who was taking something from the other that wasn't mentioned in any of the previous sentences. Additionally, option a makes more sense because it describes how Ginger is going to handle her children's conflict."},{"source":"Based on the following passage, can a world cup final go to penalties? List of FIFA World Cup penalty shoot-outs -- This is a list of all penalty shoot-outs that have occurred in the Finals tournament of the FIFA World Cup. Penalty shoot-outs were introduced as tie-breakers in the 1978 World Cup but did not occur before 1982. The first time a World Cup title was won by penalty shoot-out was in 1994. The only other time was in 2006. By the end of the 2018 edition, 30 shoot-outs have taken place in the World Cup. Of these, only two reached the sudden death stage after still being tied at the end of \`\`best of five kicks''.","target":"Yes","rationale":"The question asks whether a World Cup final can go to penalties. According to the passage, penalty shoot-outs were introduced in 1978 and have been used twice since 1994. This indicates that it is possible for two teams---and all tied after extra time---to take part in a penalty shoot out during the finals at which point one of them will be declared winner as happened in 2006. \\nSo, the answer is Yes; A world cup final can go to penalties"},{"source":"In this task, answer 'Yes' if the frequency of the given word in the two sentences is equal, else answer 'No'.\\n\\nSentence1: 'an elephant wearing a red sheet in front of a building', Sentence2: 'a man that is holding a cell phone'. Is the frequency of the word 'a' in two sentences equal?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The word 'a' appears 4 times in the first sentence and 3 times in the second sentence. The frequency of the given word is equal in both sentences, so we answer 'Yes'."},{"source":"Given a sentence, fill out the missing word with a 'no' or a number (between zero and ten). You should write the numbers with english alphabet, like: four instead of 4.\\n\\nPositive numbers are more than ____ and negative numbers are less than zero.","target":"zero","rationale":"A number is positive if it is greater than zero, and a number is negative if it is less than zero."},{"source":"You are given a concatenated string consisting of two parts that are separated by a newline character. The first part is the user's initial question during a human computer conversation, the second part is a clarifying question asked by the computer in response to the question asked by the user. You should read the input, then generate a valid prediction of the user's response to the computer's clarifying question. A valid prediction will clarify the user's correct intent in the initial question.\\n\\nUser: Find information about and pictures of moths and butterflies. \\nComputer: are you really reffering to mothra","target":"no i am referring to actual moths","rationale":"The user's initial question is asking for information about moths and butterflies. The computer is trying to clarify what the user meant by \\"moths\\" because it cannot understand the request. So, in order to clarify the intent of their initial question, the user should respond with something like \\"no i am referring to actual moths\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: Property of adhesion property does liquid display when it interacts with glass. Sentence 2: Mechanical properties (adhesion, friction) at the atomic scale Liquid surfaces and films.","target":"neutral","rationale":"Statement 1 defines a property of liquids as \\"adhesion\\" and describes the interactions between liquid and glass, but it does not provide any details about the nature of these interactions. Statement 2 provides information about the adhesion property at the atomic scale, but it does not mention anything about glass. Therefore, there is no direct connection between Statement 2 and Statement 1, and Statement 2 does not support or refute the claim made in Statement 1. As a result, there's no entailment or implication between Statements 1 and 2, so it should be \\"neutral\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a context sentence containing a blank (_). You are expected to fill the blank with one word to make the sentence convey a cultural anti-stereotype. Anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against a common belief about a particular group of people. Your answer must not contain more than one word.\\n\\nContext: My mother is very _","target":"accomplished","rationale":"Filling the blank with \\"accomplished\\" is an anti-stereotype to the idea that mothers are uneducated, unintelligent and/or incapable of work."},{"source":"Answer based on context:\\n\\nThe Browns traveled to Cincinnati for their week two match-up against the Cincinnati Bengals at Paul Brown Stadium. The Browns offense struggled for the second straight week, turning in only 56 rushing yards. Despite Charlie Frye passing for 244 yards, he threw no touchdowns and two interceptions. The Bengals scored  three times in the first half. Wide receiver Kelley Washington caught a 22-yard touchdown pass from quarterback Carson Palmer, and wide receiver Chad Johnson caught an 8-yard touchdown pass from Palmer, in the first quarter. Kicker Shayne Graham added three more points in the second quarter with a 37-yard field goal. Phil Dawson put the Browns' only points on the board in the first quarter with a 30-yard field goal. The second half was slightly better for the Browns, with their defense holding the Bengals scoreless in the third quarter. After a field goal from 37 yards by Graham in the fourth quarter, the Browns capped off a 76-yard drive with Reuben Droughns' first rushing touchdown of the season. The Browns had excellent field position for that drive because of a 75-yard pass from Frye to Braylon Edwards. Running back Rudi Johnson then scored two touchdowns from 1 yard and 9 yards out. Charlie Frye put the Browns' final points on the board when he ran in from two yards out for the score.  In the end though, the Browns would end up losing Round 1 of 2006's Battle for Ohio while dropping to 0-2.  0-1 against division rivals and 0-1 in conference games.\\n\\nHow many touchdowns did Carson Palmer throw?","target":"2","rationale":"The answer is 2. The article says that Carson Palmer threw touchdown passes to Kelley Washington and Chad Johnson, so the number of his touchdowns equals to two."},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and determine if the hypothesis is true:\\n\\nKevin Sloan is a retired American soccer player who played professionally in the American Soccer League, American Professional Soccer League and Major Indoor Soccer League. He has also coached professionally and is currently the head coach of the Neumann College men's soccer team.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nHypothesis: Kevin Sloan was never a coach in his career.","target":"No","rationale":"The passage states that Sloan is currently the head coach of a college soccer team. Hence, it can be concluded that he was also a coach at some point in his career. So, the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Decide the language of that sentence. The language can be English, French, German, Italian, or Spanish.\\n\\nText: 'and it immediately drops straight down after that'","target":"English","rationale":"The sentence is grammatically correct and uses words that are commonly used in the English language."},{"source":"David was studying for his chemistry exam. To understand the elements of the periodic table better he categorized them into three groups, cat A, cat B, and cat C. In cat A he placed all the elements with atomic numbers lower than 83. In cat B he put the elements with atomic numbers from 83 to 94. Finally, in cat C he placed the elements with atomic numbers over 94. He found it easier to see their differences after he categorized them.\\n\\nWhich category would less likely have stable isotopes, cat A or cat B?\\n\\nHint: Of the 94 naturally occurring elements, those with atomic numbers 1 through 82 each have at least one stable isotope (except for technetium, element 43 and promethium, element 61, which have no stable isotopes). Isotopes considered stable are those for which no radioactive decay has yet been observed. Elements with atomic numbers 83 through 94 are unstable to the point that radioactive decay of all isotopes can be detected. Some of these elements, notably bismuth (atomic number 83), thorium (atomic number 90), and uranium (atomic number 92), have one or more isotopes with half-lives long enough to survive as remnants of the explosive stellar nucleosynthesis that produced the heavy metals before the formation of our Solar System. At over 1.9√ó1019 years, over a billion times longer than the current estimated age of the universe, bismuth-209 (atomic number 83) has the longest known alpha decay half-life of any naturally occurring element, and is almost always considered on par with the 80 stable elements. The very heaviest elements (those beyond plutonium, element 94) undergo radioactive decay with half-lives so short that they are not found in nature and must be synthesized.","target":"cat B","rationale":"The question mentions how David categorizes the elements of the periodic table into three groups. The context is about David's method for studying and suggests that he categorized them to better understand their similarities.\\nFor cat A, which includes all elements with atomic numbers lower than 83, the passage states that these elements have at least one stable isotope (except technetium and promethium). For Cat B, which contains all atoms from number 83 to 94, they are unstable but some can undergo radioactive decay. So based on what is said in the passage it would be less likely for cat B to have stable isotopes because those atoms undergoing radioactive decay do not last as long as other more stable atoms within a category; hence making Category B ‚Äúless‚Äù likely to contain such things compared to"},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an implausible answer to a question that involves event \\"frequency\\", which refers to how often an event is likely to be repeated. For example, \\"taking showers\\" typically occurs ~5 times a week, \\"going to Saturday market\\" usually happens every few weeks/months, etc. Even though there exist multiple wrong answers, we only need a single wrong answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: In the fall of 1991, he asked a German family he had met in Cairo to help him continue his education in Germany. \\nQuestion: How often does he talk to the German family?","target":"each hour","rationale":"The German family helped the man continue his education in 1991, so it is unlikely that he would talk to them every hour. Talking to the family once a day, once a week, or even once a month is more likely than talking to them each hour."},{"source":"Choose from options: Determine if the sentence is true based on the text below:\\nRudbeckia hirta is commonly sold by Florists.\\n\\nRudbeckia hirta, commonly called black-eyed-Susan, is a North American flowering plant in the sunflower family, native to Eastern and Central North America and naturalized in the Western part of the continent as well as in China. It has now been found in all 10 Canadian Provinces and all 48 of the states in the contiguous United States.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"To answer this question, we need to look for evidence that is related to the subject in both sentences. The first sentence talks about a flower (Rudbeckia hirta) and its selling status by florists: \\"is commonly sold by Florists.\\" As there are no information regarding how common it is or which state(s) it's being sold at, we can't determine if this statement is true unless more details were provided. Therefore, the best choice would be 'It's impossible to say'."},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: What appears to be fake?\\nContext: Ultimately, the distinction between public and private sector corruption sometimes appears rather artificial, and national anti-corruption initiatives may need to avoid legal and other loopholes in the coverage of the instruments.","target":"distinction between public and private sector corruption","rationale":"The question asks for the answer that appears to be fake. The context mentions something that seems artificial, which means it is not real or true. In addition, all of the national anti-corruption initiatives must avoid loopholes (which are gaps in understanding) because they are things like legal and other loopholes that can cause problems if people don't know about them.\\nSo we will have a \\"distinction between public and private sector corruption\\" as our final answer since this distinction might appear to be false or untrue due to misunderstood areas where there could be potential issues with legality surrounding these types of issues around corruption.\\""},{"source":"What was likely said next? Hi, I'd like to book an appointment for my car to get looked at.\\nOkay, where would you like the appointment at?\\nBelle Tire.\\nOkay, and what city?\\nDetroit, Michigan","target":"Okay, and what kind of car do you have?","rationale":"After the user states their location, Detroit, it is reasonable for the system to ask \\"Okay, and what kind of car do you have?\\" since it is relevant to scheduling an appointment."},{"source":"Bank of Scotland -- The Bank of Scotland was suspected of Jacobite sympathies. Its first rival, The Royal Bank of Scotland was formed by royal charter in 1727. This led to a period of great competition between the two banks as they set to drive each other out of business. Although the \`\`Bank Wars'' ended in around 1751, competition soon arose from other sources, as other Scottish banks were founded throughout the country. In response, the Bank of Scotland itself began to open branches throughout Scotland. The first branch in London opened in 1865. \\n\\nHaving read that, could you tell me is bank of scotland same as royal bank of scotland?","target":"No","rationale":"The context clearly states that the Royal Bank of Scotland was founded as a rival to the Bank of Scotland. A bank cannot be both at the same time, so it is clear that they are different banks and not one in the same.\\n\\n\\nSo, from all this information we can see that answer is No."},{"source":"Question: who wrote still haven't found what i'm looking for??\\nAnswer:","target":"Bono (lyrics)","rationale":"The suggested answer is based on the information provided in a credible source -  an article from Rolling Stone magazine. This information can be verified through other reliable sources such as books of music history and biographies dedicated to U2. Additionally, this song's recognition and popularity further support the validity of the suggested answer.\\nTherefore, Bono (lyrics) should be validated as an accurate response to the question \\"Who wrote still haven't found what i'm looking for?\\"."},{"source":"San Francisco kept Detroit in the game with missed opportunities, then made just enough plays for a rare two-game winning streak and its first road win. RB Frank Gore set a franchise record with 148 yards rushing in the first half and scored on a 61-yard run before leaving with a concussion. San Francisco led 13-3 at halftime after scoring on three of its first four drives, wishing it had a bigger lead after out gaining Detroit 247-102 yards and recovering a fumble without giving up a turnover. The 49ers had chances to go ahead big in the third quarter because Detroit had two turnovers on its first three plays, but they came away with only a field goal and a 13-point lead. Gore then caught a 7-yard pass, wobbled off the field and didn't return. QB Alex Smith's fumble midway through the third quarter set up a score that helped the Lions get back in the game. The 49ers drove down the field to set up K Joe Nedney's fourth field goal, a key score because it made Detroit go for a TD instead of kicking a tying field goal late in the game. S Keith Lewis intercepted QB Jon Kitna's pass at the 49ers' 2 with 2&#189; minutes left and San Francisco now 4-5 picked up the one first down it needed to seal the game, winning consecutive games for the second time since 2003. RB Frank Gore finished with career-high 159 yards rushing and San Francisco's QB Alex Smith was 14 of 20 for 136 yards with a fumble. WR Arnaz Battle caught six passes for 55 yards, and converted a third-and-4 on the final drive to allow the 49ers to run out the clock. The 49ers' defense again came up huge, allowing only 273 total offensive yards and forcing 4 turnovers. LB Brandon Moore was yet again the story, leading the team with 9 tackles, 2 sacks and forcing 2 turnovers. With the win, the 49ers advanced to 4-5.\\nAnswer this question: how many yards did gore catch?","target":"7","rationale":"To answer the question, we need to calculate how many yards did Gore catch. It is mentioned that he caught a 7-yard pass in this game and then he went out of field with wobbling legs because of concussion."},{"source":"In this task, you're given five sentences, numbered 1 through 5, and two options a and b for possible titles for the story. Your job is to choose the title that better fits the story. Indicate your choice by 'a' or 'b'.\\n\\nSentence 1: Tina was listening to a radio show. Sentence 2: The dj made a comment on a recent news event. Sentence 3: Tina was offended by the comment. Sentence 4: Tina turned off the radio. Sentence 5: She quit listening to the radio show. Choices: a. The Decorator. b. The Radio Show.","target":"b","rationale":"The story is about a radio show that Tina listens to, so the second title is better suited for this story."},{"source":"Choose from the possible answers, would the following sentence, by the strictest standards, be considered correct by a linguist?\\n\\nJohn gave Bill the book.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence follows the subject-verb-object structure. The subject is \\"John,\\" the verb is \\"gave,\\" and the object is \\"Bill.\\" Therefore, this sentence would be considered as acceptable by a linguist."},{"source":"Question: \\"What state is the suburb that houses the main campus located in?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"The University of Oklahoma has several institutions of higher learning in the city and metropolitan area, with OU Medicine and the University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center campuses located east of downtown in the Oklahoma Health Center district, and the main campus located to the south in the suburb of Norman. The OU Medicine hosting the state's only Level-One trauma center. OU Health Sciences Center is one of the nation's largest independent medical centers, employing more than 12,000 people. OU is one of only four major universities in the nation to operate six medical schools.[clarification needed]\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"Oklahoma","rationale":"The question is asking what state the suburb that houses OU's main campus, Norman. This can be answered by looking at the last sentence of the context which says \\"OU is one of only four major universities in the nation to operate six medical schools.\\"[clarification needed].\\nThis tells us that Oklahoma University (abbreviated as OU) has a health sciences center and several institutions of higher learning in both downtown Oklahoma City and its suburbs. The fact that it operates multiple campuses tell you this institution must have been around for awhile before they decided to expand their operations into another area outside OUCity proper doe financial reasons or whatever reason. SO we know now there are two locations: 1) Main Campus located at Suburb X; 2) Health Sciences Center East Downtown City Y"},{"source":"Given the sentence, generate \\"yes, and\\" response. \\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). 1 In short, a \\"Yes, and\\" is a dialogue exchange in which a speaker responds by adding new information on top of the information/setting that was constructed by another speaker. Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange, although it could be the case if it agrees with the description above. There are many ways in which a response could implicitly/explicitly agree to the prompt without specifically saying 'yes, and...'. \\n\\nJust bare in mind that 10% of that Captain Crunch will go to your agent.","target":"They always take a little off the top at Fantastic Sams","rationale":"The prompt is an example of a \\"Yes, and\\" dialogue. The correct response should agree with the prompt in some way and then extend the idea with new information. The response \\"They always take a little off the top at Fantastic Sams\\" agrees that someone will get 10% of your profit, then extends by suggesting that this is is also true when one gets a haircut.\\""},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: Which of the following was NOT a former chancellor: William H. Danforth or Robert S. Brookings?\\nContext: Washington University spent its first half century in downtown St. Louis bounded by Washington Ave., Lucas Place, and Locust Street. By the 1890s, owing to the dramatic expansion of the Manual School and a new benefactor in Robert Brookings, the University began to move west. The University Board of Directors began a process to find suitable ground and hired the landscape architecture firm Olmsted, Olmsted & Eliot of Boston. A committee of Robert S. Brookings, Henry Ware Eliot, and William Huse found a site of 103 acres (41.7 ha) just beyond Forest Park, located west of the city limits in St. Louis County. The elevation of the land was thought to resemble the Acropolis and inspired the nickname of \\"Hilltop\\" campus, renamed the Danforth campus in 2006 to honor former chancellor William H. Danforth.","target":"Robert S. Brookings","rationale":"Given the context, three men - Robert S. Brookings, Henry Ware Eliot and William Huse were involved in finding a site to build Washington University on. The question is asking which of these individuals was NOT chancellor at some point in time.\\nBased on this information, it can be inferred that none of these people were former chancellors for Washington University given their role as Board members hiring landscape architects rather than being part of the administration themselves; however one other individual mentioned within the context who IS not specified as having been Chancellor is William H Danforth so he must have held that position based on exclusion from both groups (Board Members & Chancellors). \\nSo therefore we know that Robert S Brookings was never chancellor because his name appears among two non-chancellor names: himself and Henry"},{"source":"Read this response and predict the preceding dialog. Yes ma'am, what are you in the mood for today?","target":"Hi, can you please order me a drink?","rationale":"The given message is in response to a drink order. The common word \\"today\\" suggests that the response is from a waitress or waiter, and the respectful phrase \\"Yes ma'am\\" confirms this. Hence, the answer is \\"Hi, can you please order me a drink?\\"."},{"source":"Solve 65 = 212*i - 199*i for i.","target":"5","rationale":"We can first simplify the given equation by adding 199*i to both sides:\\n\\n65 + 199*i = 212*i\\n137 = 13*i"},{"source":"Given a question, generate a paraphrase of that question wihout changing the meaning of it. Your answer should reword the given sentence, but not add information to it or remove information from it. The answer to your question should be the same as the answer to the original question.\\n\\nQuestion: when did henry viii marry his first wife?","target":"when did henry the viii marry his 1st wife?","rationale":"Here's a paraphrase of the question: \\"when did henry the viii marry his 1st wife?"},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: Does the sentence \\"International crises arose, such as the Berlin Blockade (1948‚Äì1949), the Korean War (1950‚Äì1953), the Berlin Crisis of 1961, the Vietnam War (1959‚Äì1975), the Cuban Missile Crisis (1962), the Soviet war in Afghanistan (1979‚Äì1989) and NATO exercises in November 1983.\\" provide a valid answer to the question \\"Through what time period did the Berlin Blockade  last?\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"While the passage does mention a number of international crises, it also provides information about the time frame during which these events occurred. Since this question specifically asks for when one event (the Berlin Blockade) took place, we can determine that period from the passage and thus answer \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"Answer a question about this article:\\nThe College of Engineering was established in 1920, however, early courses in civil and mechanical engineering were a part of the College of Science since the 1870s. Today the college, housed in the Fitzpatrick, Cushing, and Stinson-Remick Halls of Engineering, includes five departments of study ‚Äì aerospace and mechanical engineering, chemical and biomolecular engineering, civil engineering and geological sciences, computer science and engineering, and electrical engineering ‚Äì with eight B.S. degrees offered. Additionally, the college offers five-year dual degree programs with the Colleges of Arts and Letters and of Business awarding additional B.A. and Master of Business Administration (MBA) degrees, respectively.\\nBefore the creation of the College of Engineering similar studies were carried out at which Notre Dame college?","target":"the College of Science","rationale":"The passage clearly states that the College of Engineering was established in 1920. However, it also mentions early courses in civil and mechanical engineering were a part of the College of Science since the 1870s.\\nThus, before creation of its own college, studies similar to those at the College of Engineering took place at another Notre Dame institution: The College of Science.\\""},{"source":"Given a sentence, fill out the missing word with a 'no' or a number (between zero and ten). You should write the numbers with english alphabet, like: four instead of 4.\\n\\nFriction is divided into ____ categories, static and kinetic.","target":"two","rationale":"Friction can be divided into two categories, static and kinetic."},{"source":"Answer a question about this article:\\nPhiladelphia once comprised six congressional districts. However, as a result of the city's declining population, it now has only four: the 1st district, represented by Bob Brady; the 2nd, represented by Chaka Fattah; the 8th, represented by Mike Fitzpatrick; and the 13th, represented by Brendan Boyle. All but Fitzpatrick are Democrats. Although they are usually swamped by Democrats in city, state and national elections, Republicans still have some support in the area, primarily in the northeast. A Republican represented a significant portion of Philadelphia in the House as late as 1983, and Sam Katz ran competitive mayoral races as the Republican nominee in both 1999 and 2003.\\nWhen was the last major Republican representation of a large part of the city?","target":"1983","rationale":"The given context mentions the fact that Philadelphia had been represented by six Congressional districts in a previous decade. The text also states that \\"as a result of the city's declining population, it now has only four\\". This implies that there was once more Republican representation than what is currently being seen and thus 1983 could either be this year or sometime after. The sentence immediately below talks about Republicans still having some support in the area primarily in the northeast. Therefore, we can conclude from here as well that up until 1983, Republicans have held on to major parts of their influence over Philadelphia but since then it has gradually declined leading us to believe again that this time period would suit our question best which reads: When was the last major Republican representation of a large part of the city?"},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage. The passage will not have a direct answer to the question, but can include some information and a clue for the answer. Assuming you can only obtain information about one entity in the passage, your job is to determine whether information from the passage can be used to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: How old was John Still the year that Marriott got a red card for making a gesture to a fan? Passage:Marriott signed for League Two club Luton Town on a one-year contract on 20 May 2015. He made his debut as a 76th-minute substitute for Danny Green in a 1‚Äì1 draw away to Accrington Stanley on the opening day of 2015‚Äì16. Marriott scored his first goals for Luton in the following match, a 3‚Äì1 win at home to newly promoted Championship club Bristol City in the League Cup first round. This performance saw him named in the League Cup team of the round. Marriott signed a contract extension with Luton on 25 August until June 2017, with triggers to extend it for a further two years. He was shown a red card for making a gesture to the Leyton Orient fans in Luton's 2‚Äì1 win in the Football League Trophy on 1 September. Luton manager John Still, who was adamant he didn't deserve the red card said, \\"He shouldn't have done it but the punishment didn't fit the crime.\\" Marriott scored a brace in consecutive substitute appearances against AFC Wimbledon and Hartlepool United, which resulted in two wins in a week to increase his tally for the season to six goals. He went on to score twice in 20 appearances, including a goalless drought of 10 matches, before scoring a consolation goal in a 4‚Äì1 defeat away to AFC Wimbledon on 13 February 2016. A return to form saw Marriott score four goals in five matches and increased his tally for the season to 12 goals after a 1‚Äì0 win away to Leyton Orient on 5 March. Marriott was named Luton Town Player of the Season, voted for by the club's supporters, and joint winner of the Luton Town Young Player of the Season award along with Cameron McGeehan on 1 May, chosen by the Luton Town management team. His fourth brace of 2015‚Äì16 in a 4‚Äì1 win at home to Exeter City on 7 May saw him finish the season as Luton's top scorer with 16 goals in 44 appearances. Marriott signed a new three-year contract with Luton on 20 July.","target":"b","rationale":"The question asks for John Still's age the year that Marriott got a red card for making a gesture to a fan. However, there is no information about John Still's age in the passage. Therefore, the given passage can't be used to answer the question."},{"source":"Here's a short story: Ceily rides her Big Wheel on pavement instead of soil because it's (A) more smooth (B) less smooth..\\n\\nWhat is the most sensical answer between \\"pavement\\" and  \\"soil\\"?","target":"pavement","rationale":"The context mentions that the child rides their Big Wheel on pavement instead of soil. This implies that there is a difference in surface between these two materials, which suggests that one material is smoother than the other. Given this information and using logic to infer an answer from the facts provided, it can be concluded that \\"pavement\\" would be more smooth because children ride bikes and scooters on pavement rather than dirt/soil when playing outdoors at schools or parks with asphalt walkways/bike paths.\\n\\nSo, based on what's given in this example: we'd choose \\"pavement\\"."},{"source":"A tone is made when a hammer makes contact with\\n\\nChoose an answer from this list:\\n- a waterfall\\n- air\\n- an solid object\\n- a log","target":"an solid object","rationale":"A tone is made when a hammer makes contact with an solid object."},{"source":"Sentence: \\"It is crucial for John to show an interest.\\"\\nWould a linguist rate this sentence to be acceptable linguistically?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence has the subject \\"It\\", which is followed by a verb phrase governed by an infinitive, i.e., \\"to show an interest.\\"\\\\nThis construction is perfectly grammatical in English and would therefore be considered acceptable linguistically."},{"source":"I have a test where I am given the following article, what is an answer for the question: What is the first name of the person who performed a tribute? ?\\n\\nAmidst mourning with her family, she focused on work to deal with the grief, avoiding any news coverage of her sibling's death. She commented, \\"it's still important to face reality, and not that I'm running, but sometimes you just need to get away for a second.\\" During this time, she ended her seven-year relationship with Jermaine Dupri.Several months later, Jackson performed a tribute to Michael at the 2009 MTV Video Music Awards, performing their duet \\"Scream\\". MTV stated \\"there was no one better than Janet to anchor it and send a really powerful message.\\" The performance was lauded by critics, with Entertainment Weekly affirming the rendition \\"as energetic as it was heartfelt\\".Jackson's second hits compilation, Number Ones (retitled The Best for international releases), was released in November 2009. For promotion, she performed a medley of hits at the American Music Awards, Capital FM's Jingle Bell Ball at London's O2 arena, and The X-Factor. The album's promotional single \\"Make Me\\", produced with Rodney \\"Darkchild\\" Jerkins, debuted in September. It became Jackson's nineteenth number one on the Hot Dance Club Songs chart, making her the first artist to have number-one singles in four separate decades.Later that month, Jackson chaired the inaugural benefit of amfAR, The Foundation for AIDS Research, held in Milan in conjunction with fashion week. The foundation's CEO stated \\"We are profoundly grateful to Janet Jackson for joining amfAR as a chair of its first event in Milan.... She brings incomparable grace and a history of dedication to the fight against AIDS.\\" The event raised a total of $1.1 million for the nonprofit organization.","target":"Janet","rationale":"The question asks for the first name of Michael Jackson's sister, who performed a tribute to him in 2009.\\nThis information can be found at the very end of the passage: \\"Jackson performed a tribute to Michael\\". This is referring to Janet Jackson, so her first name is Janet."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an impractical statement. You are also given three reasons (associated with \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\") explaining why this statement doesn't make sense. You must choose the most corresponding reason explaining why this statement doesn't make sense.\\n\\nShe carried her car in her backpack\\n(A) Cars have motors while backpacks are cloth\\n(B)Cars have wheels but backpacks have straps\\n(C)Cars are too large to fit in a backpack","target":"C","rationale":"The answer option C corresponds best with the statement because it is impossible to fit a car into a backpack."},{"source":"Answer based on context:\\n\\nComing off their bye week, the Browns went home for their Week 9 intraconference duel with the New England Patriots.  Cleveland delivered the opening punch in the first quarter as kicker Phil Dawson hit a 38-yard field goal, followed by running back Peyton Hillis' 2-yard touchdown run.  The Patriots answered in the second quarter as quarterback Tom Brady completed a 2-yard touchdown pass to tight end Aaron Hernandez.  Cleveland struck back on a touchdown run by wide receiver Chansi Stuckey. The Browns added onto their lead in the third quarter as rookie quarterback Colt McCoy got a 16-yard touchdown run.  Cleveland continued to pull away in the fourth quarter with another Dawson field goal.  New England tried to rally as Brady completed a 1-yard touchdown pass to Hernandez (with the extra point kicked by wide receiver Wes Welker), yet the Browns pulled away with Hillis' 35-yard touchdown run. With the win, Cleveland improved to 3-5.  Hillis was named as the AFC offensive player of the week.\\n\\nWho threw a 2-yard touchdown pass in the second quarter?","target":"Tom Brady","rationale":"Tom Brady completed a 2-yard touchdown pass to Aaron Hernandez in the second quarter."},{"source":"Can we draw the following hypothesis from the context (see options)? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nRichard Wade Walton is a former American football quarterback. He was the starting quarterback of the Texas Longhorns in early 1998. He was the backup quarterback for James Brown for three years before winning the starting job as a 5th year Senior. He started for the first two games in 1998 but broke his hand against UCLA and as a result lost his starting job to Major Applewhite.\\n\\nHypothesis: Richard Wade Walton no longer plays football professionally. \\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"Yes","rationale":"The passage states that Walton was a 5th year senior in 1998. This implies that his playing career ended after the 1998 season and he is no longer currently active as a professional football player. Therefore, we can draw this conclusion from the context provided. Hence, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Can we draw the following hypothesis from the context? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nB: I understand we are doing care of the elderly, right? A: Yes. B: And how do you feel about putting someone in the nursing home? A: Well, I don't think that uh, any of my relatives would really like to go there.\\n\\nHypothesis: some of her relatives would really like to go there\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- No\\n- It's impossible to say","target":"No","rationale":"The context clearly states that she does not think any of her relatives would like to go there. Therefore, the hypothesis is false and so we choose option \\"No\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you will be presented with a question having multiple possible answers in Russian language. And you should choose a most suitable option out of \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\", and \\"E\\" based on your commonsense knowledge.\\n\\nQuestion: –ï—Å–ª–∏ –∫—Ç–æ-—Ç–æ –≤–∫—É—Å–Ω–æ –ø–æ–æ–±–µ–¥–∞–ª, –Ω–∞ —á—Ç–æ –æ–Ω –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç –ø—Ä–µ—Ç–µ–Ω–¥–æ–≤–∞—Ç—å? \\n Options: A —É—Å—Ç–∞–≤–∞—Ç—å B –∑–∞—Å—ã–ø–∞—Ç—å C —á—É–≤—Å—Ç–≤–æ–≤–∞—Ç—å —Å–µ–±—è –ø–æ–ª–Ω—ã–º D —Ä–∞—Å—Ç—É—â–∏–π —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Ö E —á—É–≤—Å—Ç–≤—É—è —Å–µ–±—è —É–¥–æ–≤–ª–µ—Ç–≤–æ—Ä–µ–Ω–Ω—ã–º","target":"E","rationale":"The correct answer is option E, because if someone has eaten a lot and feels full, he/she is likely to feel satisfied."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a text passage from a trivia quiz. You should choose the category this question belongs to from these categories: History, Science, Social Science, Fine Arts, Literature. You can only choose one category, so if in doubt, please choose the closest match.\\n\\nHis relief \\"The Feast of Herod\\" graces the front of the baptismal font in the Siena Cathedral. He embedded pieces of colored glass in marble to create his unique Canteria, or \\"Singing Gallery,\\" for the Florence Cathedral. According to Vasari, he could be observed repeatedly muttering, \\"Speak, damn you; speak! \\" while creating his sculpture of the prophet Habbakuk whose bald head has led it to be nicknamed the Zuccone. FTP, who was this great Early Renaissance sculptor who created the equestrian statue Gattemalata and the bronze David","target":"Fine Arts","rationale":"In this question, the text passage describes one of the sculptures created by a certain sculptor which was \\"The Feast of Herod\\" that is gracing the front of a baptismal font in Siena Cathedral and also describes other pieces created by him like \\"Gattemalata\\", \\"Zuccone\\" etc. From these details, it can be inferred that the passage belongs to Fine Arts category."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a list of integers you need to calculate and return the range of the integers which is the difference between maximum and minimum element in the list.\\n\\n[299, 373, 468, 457, 216, 28, 265, 329, 258, 487, 91, 84, 219, 263, 367, 32, 391, 294, 365, 227]","target":"459","rationale":"In the given list, minimum element is 28 and maximum element is 487. The range of the integers in the list is 487 - 28 = 459."},{"source":"What is least likely to absorb light?\\n\\nPick the right answer from the list:\\n- windows\\n- space\\n- glass\\n- foil","target":"foil","rationale":"The question is asking for the answer which \\"is least likely to absorb light\\". In this case, light refers to visible light that can be seen by humans. The following options are all materials that could potentially block out or reflect some of the incoming sunlight: windows and glass would probably let in less than a 100% amount of sunlight because they have an opaque coating on them; space blocks out no sunlight so it doesn't fit either; foil should completely block out any incoming sunlight since metal tends to be highly reflective. In conclusion, based on these facts, we think the correct option here is Foil."},{"source":"What is the title of this article:\\n\\nIn order to enlist Stalin's support, Zhou and a Chinese delegation left for Moscow on 8 October, arriving there on 10 October at which point they flew to Stalin's home at the Black Sea. There they conferred with the top Soviet leadership which included Joseph Stalin as well as Vyacheslav Molotov, Lavrentiy Beria and Georgi Malenkov. Stalin initially agreed to send military equipment and ammunition, but warned Zhou that the Soviet Union's air force would need two or three months to prepare any operations. In a subsequent meeting, Stalin told Zhou that he would only provide China with equipment on a credit basis, and that the Soviet air force would only operate over Chinese airspace, and only after an undisclosed period of time. Stalin did not agree to send either military equipment or air support until March 1951. Mao did not find Soviet air support especially useful, as the fighting was going to take place on the south side of the Yalu. Soviet shipments of mat√©riel, when they did arrive, were limited to small quantities of trucks, grenades, machine guns, and the like.\\n\\nTitle:","target":"Korean War","rationale":"In the above context, Zhou Enlai is described as a Premier of the People's Republic of China. The Chinese delegation led by him would have gone to Moscow in order to secure military support from Joseph Stalin for their attack on South Korea. \\nThe article states that Mao Zedong did not find Soviet air support especially useful because \\"the fighting was going to take place on the south side of the Yalu\\". This means that North Korea and its ally, Communist China (People's Republic of China) were planning an assault against South Korean forces near the border between North and South Korea at 38th parallel north during 1950-1953.\\nThis event has been historically termed as \\"\\"Korean War\\"\\", which took place between June 25, 1950 ‚Äì July 27, 1953 with conflict"},{"source":"Fossils may form in other ways. Fossils can be preserved almost completely. In this process, the organism doesnt change much. As seen below, tree sap may cover an organism. With time, the sap hardens. It turns to into amber. The original organism is preserved. This is very exciting for scientists. They are able to study the DNA of the organism that no longer lives on Earth. Some animals have been found frozen in ice. Others have been found in tar pits after falling in. Molds and casts are another way organisms can be fossilized. Have you ever walked in soft mud and left footprints? Once in a while, these traces of organisms can be preserved. In this case, nothing is left of the organism. A mold is an imprint of an organism that is preserved in rock. The organisms remains break down completely. There is nothing left of the original plant and animal. \\n\\nQuestion: How is amber made?\\nI think \\"Underground\\" is a valid answer. Could you confirm? Yes or no?","target":"No","rationale":"Amber is a fossilized resin produced by pine trees. Resins are the semi-fluid organic substances secreted in pockets and canals through epithelial cells of plants. The amber forms after sap hardens, usually with time or due to environmental conditions such as extreme heat or coldness. Amber could be found on ground where it fell from tree branches when hardened, but not underground. \\n\\nSo, No\\n\\n\\n\\""},{"source":"If a person is avoiding sugar, they will stop eating\\n\\nPick the right answer from the list:\\n- meat\\n- eggs\\n- butter\\n- bread","target":"bread","rationale":"If a person is avoiding sugar, they will stop eating sweet foods. Bread has sugars in it and therefore would not be eaten if one wants to avoid sugar. Meat, eggs, and butter are all savory items that have no or very little sugar content.\\nSo the answer is bread"},{"source":"In this task, answer 'Yes' if the frequency of the given word in the two sentences is equal, else answer 'No'.\\n\\nSentence1: 'birds flying in to land on a lake', Sentence2: 'an upshot of a large brick clock tower'. Is the frequency of the word 'to' in two sentences equal?","target":"No","rationale":"The word 'to' appears in both sentences. The frequency of the word 'to' in sentence 1 is 2, and the frequency of the word 'to' in sentence 2 is also 2. Therefore, we need to answer No."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is potentially offensive to anyone (i.e., a subset of people, any particular person, etc.), 2) no, otherwise. Note that potentially offensive posts can contain sexual, racial, religious biased or offensive language. Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\n\\"\\"\\"People don‚Äôt become gay, bisexual, pansexual, transexual. People just fall in love with another person.‚Äù\\"","target":"No","rationale":"This post is not offensive and does not contain any derogatory or objectifying language. It simply contains the author's opinion about love and sexuality. Therefore, the answer should be \\"No\\"."},{"source":"How to build a motor<br>Wind wire around a cylindrical object like a pen or pencil cell. This coil of wire will be the moving motor armature. If the wire is thick then the diameter of the coil should be larger.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion?\\nthe steps in the guide are useful. \\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"The guide only provides one of the steps in building a motor. So it is not possible to say whether these are useful steps or not without knowing all of them, hence the answer is \\"It's impossible to say\\"."},{"source":"Short general knowledge question: where is jefferson davis buried?","target":"Hollywood Cemetery","rationale":"Jefferson Davis (June 3, 1808 ‚Äì December 6, 1889) was an American politician who served as the only President of the Confederate States from 1861 to 1865. He also led a long career in the United States House of Representatives and Senate for Kentucky and Mississippi respectively.\\nAfter his death on December 6th 1889, he was buried at Hollywood Cemetery in Richmond Virginia"},{"source":"Given a sentence with a missing word, pick the answer option that best fills out the missing word in the sentence. Indicate each answer with its index ('a', 'b', 'c', 'd').\\n\\nFuzzy logic is an attempt to combine the ____ techniques.\\\\Question: Choose the right answer from options given a) ten b) three c) eight d) two","target":"d","rationale":"The sentence is talking about different techniques. Using context clues, we can narrow down the options to either two or three."},{"source":"Read the article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: Earlier this week, I wrapped up   a 5-day trip in San Francisco. I woke up a few hours before sunrise, drove through the darkness and out of the city, hiked for 30 minutes to the top of a hill overlooking the Golden Gate Bridge, and snapped  this photo. As I stood there soaking in the early morning light, I was reminded of an important lesson.\\nWhen I arrived in San Francisco, I told myself, \\"Just take photos as you do other things.\\" My primary goal was to meet with friends and so I figured I could take pictures as we walked around the city. This resulted in exactly zero photos worth sharing. I had vague ideas like, \\"I'd like to do some street photography,\\" but I never went out with the intent of photographing something specific. Finally, on the last morning, I went out with the intent of capturing a specific picture and I ended up with something worth sharing. My mistake was that I assumed that because I wanted to take photos, I would end up getting a desirable result.\\nHow often do you do this in your own life? We go to the gym to \\"work out\\" without trying to become better at something specific. We wish that we were more creative, but never work on a particular project. When you commit to a task, however, then the next step is obvious. You want to take a picture of the Golden Gate Bridge at sunrise? Next step: find a good spot. You've found a good spot? Next step: wake up early and drive there.\\nThis is perhaps the most shocking thing: if box yourself in, then you'll begin to break out and achieve something greater than you ever imagined.\\nQuestion: What are you advised to do first when you want to get stronger physically?\\nOptions: A: Make a detailed outline.\\nB: Go to work out immediately.\\nC: Discuss the ways with coaches.\\nD: Choose a certain muscle group.","target":"D","rationale":"The article advises focusing on a specific goal. The narrator says that they went to San Francisco with the intent of taking pictures, but ended up without any photos worth sharing because their focus was too vague (street photography). Then, one morning they had an intention to take a picture of the Golden Gate Bridge at sunrise and succeeded in getting something worth sharing. This suggests that it is best to have a clear idea about what you want before doing anything else.\\nThis lesson can be applied more generally: if we wish for something specific then our next steps will become obvious as well. For example, when wanting to get stronger physically your first step should be choosing a certain muscle group or exercise routine; after all this specificity helps determine what actions you should take next!\\n\\n\\nSo D is correct here since"},{"source":"What was the response? DIALOG:\\nHow did the Spice Girls contribute to commercialization?\\n- At the height of Spice mania, the Spice Girls advertised for an unprecedented number of brands.\\n- Did the Spice Girls make a lot of money?\\n- In 1997, the Spice Girls became the most merchandised group in music history with estimated earnings of over ¬£300 million from their merchandising and endorsement deals that year alone.\\n- What was the celebrity culture like for the Spice Girls?\\n- The mainstream media embraced the Spice Girls at the peak of their success. The group received regular international press coverage and were constantly followed by paparazzi.\\n- Did the Spice Girls win any awards?\\n- The Spice Girls have received five Brit Awards, three American Music Awards, three MTV Europe Music Awards, one MTV Video Music Award and three World Music Awards.\\n- What else was interesting about the Spice Girls during 1997?\\n- Victoria Adams started dating football player David Beckham in 1997 after they had met at a charity football match.\\n- When did Mel B of the Spice Girls have her child?\\n-","target":"Mel B's daughter, Phoenix Chi Gulzar, was born on 19 February 1999.","rationale":"It is a common sense that if a child was born in 1999, the mother had to be pregnant in 1998. And Mel B is the only one who can be pregnant in 1998 among all members of the Spice Girls. Therefore, it's reasonable to answer \\"Mel B's daughter, Phoenix Chi Gulzar, was born on 19 February 1999.\\""},{"source":"Question: when does the next season of anne with an e start on netflix??\\nAnswer:","target":"2018","rationale":"Given the question, I believe a reasonable answer could be \\"2018\\"."},{"source":"Fill in the response. Assistant.\\nWhat can I get for you?","target":"Order a pizza.","rationale":"Based on the chat history, it is clear that the user wants to order a pizza. The assistant may have asked for clarifications about pizza sizes and toppings. Based on this, the assistant may ask if they want to order a pizza, or if there is anything else they want. Therefore, the most reasonable answer among the candidate options is choice (C), which is \\"Order a pizza.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a context sentence containing a blank (_). You are expected to fill the blank with one word to make the sentence convey a cultural anti-stereotype. Anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against a common belief about a particular group of people. Your answer must not contain more than one word.\\n\\nContext: The Columbian woman was _.","target":"antisocial","rationale":"The common stereotype is that Latin American people are very outgoing, sociable and friendly. The answer word \\"antisocial\\" goes against the stereotype by implying that the Columbian woman was socially detached or unsociable."},{"source":"Suggest a movie title for the following movie plot: In the year 1960, a plague known as \\"male-itis\\" has killed every fertile man on Earth over the age of 12. Boys under the age of 12 have been vaccinated, but they are all rendered sterile. Womankind takes over the world and a woman becomes President of the United States.\\nMeanwhile, a female aviator, Gertie (Grace Cunard), flying over the Ozarks finds smoke rising from the chimney of a cabin. She discovers a reclusive hillbilly named Elmer Smith (Earle Foxe) living there with his sweetheart Hattie (Derelys Perdue). He is captured and examined at a hospital. All the women in the world soon begin to fight over Smith.","target":"The Last Man on Earth","rationale":"The movie plot describes a terrible plague that kills all fertile men over the age of 12. Women take control and elect a woman as president, but soon discover one man who was able to survive by living in isolation with his girlfriend. The women of the world fight for his affections, showing their desperation for male companionship now that they are facing extinction due to lack of fertility amongst young males.\\nThis situation is similar to another famous story about an apocalypse: \\"The Last Man on Earth\\". In this story, humanity has been wiped out by a virus except for one immune man named Robert Neville (played by Vincent Price). He spends years alone before discovering other survivors ‚Äì first some children who have survived because they were too young when infected and later two adult female survivors whom he falls in love with"},{"source":"In this task you are given a premise and two alternatives in Chinese. You must choose the alternative that is more plausibly the cause or effect of the situation described by the premise. The input format is \\"premise\\n(1)alternative_1(2)alternative_2\\", the output should either be \\"1\\" or \\"2\\" based on your judgment.\\n\\nÊàëÁöÑÂäûÂÖ¨ÂÆ§Èó®ÊòØÂºÄÁùÄÁöÑ„ÄÇ\\n(1)ÊàëÂú®ÂäûÂÖ¨Ê°åÂâçÂíåÂêå‰∫ã‰∫§Ë∞à„ÄÇ(2)ÊàëÊó†ÊÑè‰∏≠Âê¨Âà∞Â§ßÂéÖÈáåÁöÑË∞àËØù„ÄÇ","target":"2","rationale":"ÊèêÁ§∫‰∏≠ÁöÑÂäûÂÖ¨ÂÆ§Èó®ÊòØÂºÄÁùÄÁöÑÔºåÊâÄ‰ª•ÊàëÊó†ÊÑè‰∏≠Âê¨Âà∞Â§ßÂéÖÈáåÁöÑË∞àËØùÊõ¥ÊúâÂèØËÉΩ„ÄÇÊâÄ‰ª•Â∫îËØ•ÈÄâ2„ÄÇ"},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- John moved to the bedroom. Fact 2- Mary went back to the bedroom. Question: Where is Mary? Answer: bedroom","target":"Fact 2","rationale":"Fact 2 states that Mary went back to the bedroom. Therefore, the only way to answer the question \\"Where is Mary?\\" is by using Fact 2."},{"source":"Imagine the conversation that came before this response? Response: Hey what's going on.","target":"Hello Kenneth","rationale":"A reasonable response to the given statement is \\"Hello Kenneth\\", which introduces the person to Kenneth and inquires about his well-being. It does not seem like a natural response for any of the other candidate options, hence the answer is \\"Hello Kenneth\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: Reducing the number of molecules in a rigid container causes pressure to decrease. Sentence 2: Intraocular pressure decreased with LASIK, but the cause of the decrease is unknown.","target":"neutral","rationale":"The premise provides information about a study that measured intraocular pressure after LASIK and found it to decrease, but the cause of this decreased was unknown. The hypothesis describes how reducing the number of molecules in a rigid container causes pressure to decrease. There is no direct connection between these two statements, so there is not enough information provided in the premise to support or refute the claim made in the hypothesis. As a result, Statement 2 does not entail or imply Statement 1, and \\"neutral\\" should be outputted as an answer for this question.\\""},{"source":"Keith landed a job with the EPA. As part of his training he needed to learn how the Geiger counter works. To learn more about the counter he tested it in three different locations, location A, location B, and location C. Location A had very high radiation; location B had low radiation; and location C didn't have any radiation. Keith learned how the counter works in locations with varying degrees of radiation.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nWould location B have faster or slower clicks than location A?\\n\\nHint: You generally can‚Äôt see, smell, taste, hear, or feel radiation. Fortunately, there are devices such as Geiger counters that can detect radiation. A Geiger counter, like the one pictured in the Figure below , contains atoms of a gas that is ionized if it encounters radiation. When this happens, the gas atoms change to ions that can carry an electric current. The current causes the Geiger counter to click. The faster the clicks occur, the higher the level of radiation. You can see a video about the Geiger counter and how it was invented at the URL below.","target":"slower","rationale":"A Geiger counter detects radiation through a radioactive process called ionization. The results of the test are recorded by counting how many times per minute the device clicks, which can vary depending on the amount of radiation in an area. Given that location A had very high levels of radiation and B had low levels, it would be expected for clicks to occur less frequently at location B than at location A, because there is lower level of radiation present. Therefore, Location B would have slower clicks than location A; so answer \\"slower\\" is correct here.\\""},{"source":"Given an entity as input, output another entity which is part of the input entity. These are entities of meronym. In linguistics, meronymy is a semantic relation between a meronym denoting a part and a holonym denoting a whole. In simpler terms, a meronym (i.e., output entity) is in a part-of relationship with its holonym (i.e., input entity).\\n\\noctopi","target":"muscle","rationale":"An octopus is a type of animal and one of its parts is the muscle. Therefore, muscle is a meronym of octopi."},{"source":"The following article contains an answer for the question: What is the full name of the person that misses the easy life in New York? , can you please find it? \\n\\nDuring World War I, a small diverse group of young American women leave for France to answer the urgent need for nurses, despite having little or no experience. Under the leadership of socialite Mrs. Townsend, they turn an abandoned building into a hospital.\\nThey are soon joined by teenage blonde Joy Meadows (who later divulges to a patient she is \\"nearly nineteen\\"). Initially, she is teased for being inexperienced and coming from a privileged background. She is welcomed by Barbara \\"Babs\\" Whitney.\\nBabs attracts the persistent interest of Lieutenant Wally O'Brien, a fighter pilot. Joy has difficulty adjusting to the violent conditions and starts to miss her easy life on the Lower East Side in Manhattan after meeting a wounded New York soldier, Robbie Neil. She considers giving up, but Mrs. Townsend assures her that she will get used to it. Wally attempts to court Babs, but she is not vulnerable to his advances. They get acquainted, however, after Babs falls off of her bicycle and Wally takes care of her injured ankle.","target":"Joy Meadows","rationale":"The film was based on an original story by Mary Borden, a field nurse during World War I who served in France. She wrote it anonymously under the pen name \\"Elisabeth Germain\\". The novel has been republished several times as Joy of Life (with no author listed) and then again with her real name starting from 2009.\\nBorden's collection titled The Forbidden Zone: A Nurse's Impressions of the First World War had what she claimed were actual entries from her war journal about herself, which included some personal details that match those attributed to Joy Meadows' character such as being blonde, working at Bellevue Hospital until 1915 when they started sending nurses abroad into conflict zones etc.[1] Later publications have revealed that while much is true there are also embellishments"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a string with duplicate characters ocurring in the string. You need to return the character which is ocurring with the maximum frequency. In case of a tie, return the character with the least ascii value.\\n\\nvqzxyzparjbmlduimpvfiwenoawdyfddisetbhnqjdtxrgrc","target":"d","rationale":"The given string contains the following frequency of each character:\\\\n'v' -> 2\\\\n'q' -> 1\\\\n'z' -> 4\\\\n'x', 'y', 'p', 'a', 'r', 'j', 'b', etc. -> 1\\\\n'd' - > 5 (The highest frequency)\\\\n\\\\nthe answer is d."},{"source":"Given news headlines and an edited word. The original sentence has word within given format {word}. Create new headlines by replacing {word} in the original sentence with edit word. Classify news headlines into \\"Funny\\" and \\"Not Funny\\" that have been modified by humans using an edit word to make them funny. \\n\\nNews Headline: Christie {signs} N.J. budget , ending 3-day government shutdown \\n Edit: pays","target":"Not Funny","rationale":"The sentence \\"Christie pays N.J. budget\\" is not funny, because it makes no sense. So the answer is Not Funny"},{"source":"Would a linguist find the following sentence to be a valid English sentence grammatically?\\n\\nA piano was given to Jane Fairfax by Frank Churchill.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence follows the subject-verb-object structure. The subject is \\"puppy,\\" the verb is \\"was kissed,\\" and the object is \\"by the policeman.\\" Therefore, the sentence is linguistically acceptable."},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Based on the sentence \\"Next to two men in orange uniforms, a man in a gray sweatshirt places his arms over a wall and looks down.\\", is the sentence \\"The men are dressed in bathing suits.\\" a true sentence?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The sentence \\"Next to two men in orange uniforms, a man in a gray sweatshirt places his arms over a wall and looks down.\\" describes the scenario of three individuals. Two men are dressed in orange uniforms while one is wearing what appears to be either athletic attire or just casual clothing (a gray sweatshirt), therefore it would not make sense that all three men were dressed in bathing suits because at least one individual described here isn't actually dressed for swimming. So the answer is no"},{"source":"In this task you will be given some text dialogue and you need to infer the underlying emotion of the text. The possible emotions are happy, sad, angry, or other.\\n\\nare you a foodie  oh yes i totally live to eat then india is your placd","target":"other","rationale":"The given text does not give any particular emotions. The first sentence has a question mark but the second person did not answer the question and went on to talk about some other topic."},{"source":"So he calls me , right ... And he starts talking about how we are going to have to change some things with the company and how we need to concentrate on how the staff is preforming and that we will have to let some go , cut some hours and re - arrange some roles plus try some new hires . I ' m sitting there thinking , \\" this is it ... this is where either he fires me or tells me he 's taking me off of sales and leaving me with less hours and only doing the admin work at the lesser pay rate . \\" I steel myself .\\nAccording to the above context, choose the best option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: What may be the reason for their boss wanting to switch things around in the company ?\\nOptions:\\nA. They may want the company to relocate .\\nB. They may want the company to expand and do better as a whole .\\nC. None of the above choices .\\nD. They may want to shut down the company .","target":"B","rationale":"The context describes the boss talking to one of his employees about how they want to change things in the company and improve performance. The employee is worried that their work will be cut or reduced, but instead it seems like their boss wants to expand operations. \\nFrom this information, we can determine that option B (They may want the company to expand) best answers our question: What may be the reason for their boss wanting to switch things around in the company?"},{"source":"Question: Who is the rap singer in right round with kesha in the background? *(dancer)*?\\nWould \\"The song features guest vocals from Kesha .\\" be a reasonable answer?","target":"No","rationale":"The question asks for the name of a rap singer, meaning someone who performs hip hop music and raps. Kesha does not perform in this style, so it cannot be her. Her vocals can be heard on the song Right Round by rapper Flo Rida but she is only featured as background vocals from another artist that was brought onto the track to enhance its appeal or commercial value -- therefore this answer should not be validated because it does not address the actual question being asked: Who is the \\"rap\\" singer? \\nTherefore, select No"},{"source":"Sentence: \\"Where Alison and David soaked their feet was in the kitchen\\"\\nWould a linguist rate this sentence to be acceptable linguistically?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence is acceptable linguistically because it follows the subject, verb and object structure."},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nA thin wire will carry more or less current than a large piece of wire? \\n\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nThicker resistors offer less resistance than thinner resistors.","target":"less","rationale":"A larger wire has less resistance than a thinner one. A resistor is the opposition to current flow in an electrical circuit. It limits or regulates the amount of current that flows through it, so when there is more resistance then less current will flow and vice-versa.\\nTherefore, since thicker resistors have lesser resistance they allow for a greater amount of electric charge (current) to pass through them as compared to thin wires which offer higher resistance and thus restrict the passage of electric charge resulting in lower currents flowing through them. Hence, we can conclude that thick wires carry more amounts of electricity than small ones do !"},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the best option to answer the question.\\nContext: That cause we followed a mob of people who were already in line ( towards the front ) but we did n't know this until we were like feet away from the door and someone was explaining to their friend how long the line had gotten over a phone . We cut , but we did n't mean to . Really .\\nQuestion: Why was the narrator feeling a bit anxious ?\\nOptions: \\nA. They were in a packed crowd .\\nB. No one came to the club .\\nC. They were accused of taking a phone .\\nD. They were in an incident with a stolen phone .","target":"A","rationale":"The narrator and their friends were in a long line to get into a club. They followed another group of people towards the door, but did not realize that they had cut until it was too late. The other person assumed that the narrator took his phone because he thought someone else in the front of the crowd stole it when they got there. This made things uncomfortable for them since they did not mean to cut and felt bad about making this assumption without any evidence or knowledge of what happened with his phone beforehand\\nTherefore, answer A is correct"},{"source":"Q: Vibrating objects such as drumheads produce what?\\n\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- negative ions\\n\\n- light\\n\\n- heat\\n\\n- sound energy\\n\\nA:","target":"sound energy","rationale":"A: Vibrating objects such as drumheads produce sound energy.\\n\\tSound is created when an object vibrates and creates waves in the surrounding air, which are then detected by a person‚Äôs ear. The brain interprets these signals to create a sense of hearing or ‚Äúsound.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: disagree or agree. Classify the comment as disagree if it is likely to raise a certain level of public disagreement, whether healthy or unhealthy. The disagreement can be due to toxic content (for example, disrespect, identity attack, insult, and threat), controversial content, misunderstandings, or conflicting opinions. Classify the comment as agree otherwise.\\n\\nComment: No reason to stop the largest and most regressive tax increase in the history of Canada. I pity the poor people in our country.","target":"Agree","rationale":"The given comment expresses an opinion and is not likely to raise public disagreement. The comment is civil, stating that the tax increase is regressive and harmful to low-income people. Therefore, the answer should be \\"Agree\\"."},{"source":"Determine if the sentence is true based on the text below. Choose from options.\\nSingapore scientists reveal that SARS virus has undergone genetic changes.\\n\\nScientists at the Genome Institute of Singapore (GIS) have discovered the complete genetic sequence of a coronavirus isolated from a Singapore patient with SARS.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The first sentence states that scientists have discovered the genetic sequence of a coronavirus isolated from SARS patient. However, this does not say whether it is true or false that the virus has undergone changes in its genetics. Hence, it cannot be said to be either positive or negative based on the given context and hence should take answer as 'it is impossible to tell'."},{"source":"Use a disfluent question or a proper question and find the answer to the question based on the given context or return None if an answer can't be found. A disfluent question is a question that has some interruptions in it while framing. A proper question is the correct form of the question without any disfluency.\\n\\nproper question: Where wasn't there a weakness in British supply chain? \\n disfluent question: Where wasn't there a weakness in French uh rather British supply chain? \\n context: Governor Vaudreuil, who harboured ambitions to become the French commander in chief (in addition to his role as governor), acted during the winter of 1756 before those reinforcements arrived. Scouts had reported the weakness of the British supply chain, so he ordered an attack against the forts Shirley had erected at the Oneida Carry. In the March Battle of Fort Bull, French forces destroyed the fort and large quantities of supplies, including 45,000 pounds of gunpowder. They set back any British hopes for campaigns on Lake Ontario, and endangered the Oswego garrison, already short on supplies. French forces in the Ohio valley also continued to intrigue with Indians throughout the area, encouraging them to raid frontier settlements. This led to ongoing alarms along the western frontiers, with streams of refugees returning east to get away from the action.","target":"None","rationale":"The correct answer is None because the context says that French forces destroyed the fort and large quantities of supplies, including 45,000 pounds of gunpowder."},{"source":"Given the following context:\\n\\nNeill was promoted to lieutenant colonel during his participation in the Siege of B√©xar, and 10 days later Houston placed him in charge of the Texian garrison in the city. In January residents had begun evacuating ahead of Santa Anna's approaching forces. Neill pleaded with Houston for replenishment of troops, supplies and weaponry. The departure of Texians who joined the Matamoros Expedition had left Neill with only about 100 men. At that point Houston viewed B√©xar as a military liability and did not want Santa Anna's advancing army gaining control of any remaining soldiers or artillery. He dispatched Bowie with instructions to remove the artillery, have the defenders abandon the Alamo mission and destroy it. Upon his January 19 arrival and subsequent discussions with Neill, Bowie decided the mission was the right place to stop the Mexican army in its tracks.  He stayed and began to help Neill prepare for the coming attack.  Lieutenant Colonel William B. Travis arrived with reinforcements on February 3. When Neill was given leave to attend to family matters on February 11, Travis assumed command of the mission, and three days later he and Bowie agreed to a joint command. Santa Anna crossed the Rio Grande on February 16, and the Mexican army's assault on the Alamo began February 23. Captain Juan Segu√≠n left the mission on February 25, carrying a letter from Travis to Fannin at Goliad requesting more reinforcements. Santa Anna extended an offer of amnesty to Tejanos inside the fortress; a non-combatant survivor, Enrique Esparza, said that most Tejanos left when Bowie advised them to take the offer. In response to Travis' February 24 letter To the People of Texas, 32 militia volunteers formed the Gonzales Ranging Company of Mounted Volunteers and arrived at the Alamo on February 29.\\nIf you execute your enemies, it saves you the trouble of having to forgive them.\\n\\nanswer the following question:\\n\\nWhat was the name of the person who helped Neill prepare for the coming attack?","target":"Bowie","rationale":"The context begins with describing how Neill was promoted to lieutenant colonel during the Siege of Bexar. The Texian garrison in B√©xar had begun evacuating ahead of Santa Anna's army, and at this point there were only about 100 men left under Neill's command. When Houston sent Bowie over to remove some artillery pieces from the Alamo mission and abandon it, Bowie decided that they could use it as a place to stop Santa Anna's advancing forces. He stayed behind and began helping Neill prepare for an attack on their position by Mexican troops. \\nBowie is thus referenced several times throughout the passage as having helped Neill prepare for the coming Mexican assault on February 23rd (when Travis also arrived), so he would be \\"the person who helped [Neill]"},{"source":"Determine the topic of the question.\\nQuestion: \\"how many times has a player hit for the cycle?\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Hitting for the cycle","rationale":"Hitting for the cycle is an American expression that means a batter hits single, double, triple and home run in one game.\\nThe topic of the question \\"how many times has a player hit for the cycle\\" would be hitting for the cycle as it answers exactly what happens when someone gets to bat all four bases: they are said to have hit for the cycle."},{"source":"If you don't have to go out and borrow it somewhere and and do that, can we conclude that \\"You have to go out and borrow it.\\"?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The statement \\"You have to go out and borrow it\\" is not supported by the information in this context, which states that you don't *have* to do so. So, the answer is no'}"},{"source":"Q: when will the international space station be completed? A:","target":"2019","rationale":"The International Space Station (ISS) is a space station, or a habitable artificial satellite in low Earth orbit. Its first component was launched into orbit in 1998 and the last pressurised module will be fitted some time after 2019.\\nTherefore, the answer should be \\"2019\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given dialogue, and you have to find the most critical location in the given conversation.\\n\\ncan you tell me about Nunavut? \\n Nunavut is the largest in area and the second-least populous of Canada's provinces and territories. It was separated officially from the Northwest Territories on April 1, 1999, via the Nunavut Act and the Nunavut Land Claims Agreement Act, though the boundaries had been drawn in 1993. \\n can you tell me about the politics and government there? \\n Nunavut elects a single member of the House of Commons of Canada. The Nunavut licence plate was originally created for the Northwest Territories in the 1970's. \\n i want to hear about some interesting history? \\n The government paid compensation to those affected and their descendants and on August 18, 2010, in Inukjuak, the Honourable John Duncan, PC, MP, previous Minster of Indian Affairs and Northern Development and Federal Interlocutor for Metis and Non-Status Indians apologized on behalf of the Government of Canada for the relocation of Inuit to the High Arctic. \\n any other interesting history? \\n Concerned about the area's strategic geopolitical position, the federal government relocated Inuit from Nunavik, northern Quebec, to Resolute and Grise Fiord. \\n thanks \\n Would you like and other information? Culture information?","target":"Nunavut","rationale":"The most critical location in the conversation is Nunavut as it appears multiple times and is the only location mentioned in the conversation. Therefore, it can be concluded that \\"Nunavut\\" is the most critical location."},{"source":"Solve this math problem\\n\\nSolve 476*s = 502*s + 208 for s.","target":"-8","rationale":"476s = 502s + 208\\n-26s = 208\\n-208/-26 = s\\ns= -8"},{"source":"What is the answer to this question? who plays ayesha in guardians of the galaxy?","target":"Elizabeth Debicki","rationale":"The actress Elizabeth Debicki plays Ayesha in Guardians of the Galaxy."},{"source":"Pick the option in line with common sense to answer the question.\\nQuestion: Care not to burn you hand on the handle of what small high-walled vessel?\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. brush\\n\\nB. carry object\\n\\nC. walking stick\\n\\nD. umbrella\\n\\nE. saucepan","target":"E","rationale":"The question asks what small high-walled vessel has a handle that may become hot if used for cooking. A saucepan is the only option among those given that meets all these criteria, so it must be correct.\\n\\nSo, the answer would be E"},{"source":"Article: There is a project involving the future relocation of Plymouth City Council's headquarters, the civic centre, to the current location of the Bretonside bus station; it would involve both the bus station and civic centre being demolished and a rebuilt together at the location with the land from the civic centre being sold off. Other suggestions include the demolition of the Plymouth Pavilions entertainment arena to create a canal \\"boulevard\\" linking Millbay to the city centre. Millbay is being regenerated with mixed residential, retail and office space alongside the ferry port.\\n\\nNow answer this question: To connect Millbay to the city centre, what would need to be destroyed?","target":"the Plymouth Pavilions entertainment arena","rationale":"The context says that to connect Millbay to the city centre, \\"the Plymouth Pavilions entertainment arena\\" would need to be destroyed. This is a correct answer. We can also say: \\nTo create a canal boulevard linking Millbay and the city centre, what needs to be demolished?"},{"source":"In mathematics, the absolute value of a number is the non-negative value of that number, without regarding its sign. For example, the absolute value of -2 is 2, and the absolute value of 5 is 5. In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element. The absolute value for negative numbers can be found by multiplying them by -1. After finding the element with the maximum absolute value you should return the value of that element before you applied the absolute value.\\n\\n[-35.95 -63.16 -83.68]","target":"-83.68","rationale":"The element with the highest absolute value in the given list is -83.68, which has an absolute value of 83.68. The absolute value of all other numbers in the list is less than or equal to 83.68. However, we need to return the value of the element before applying the absolute value, so the answer is -83.68"},{"source":"W: Thank you George, but I've decided to travel a bit before finding another job.\\n\\nWhat was said before this conversation?","target":"M: Jenny, there's an opening for an assistant manager in our company. You should give it a try.","rationale":"The conversation between the two people, a man (M) and a woman(W), starts with an exchange of thanks. The context suggests that the woman has been offered employment by the man in his company but she turns it down because she wants to take time off from work before taking up another position.\\n\\nSo answer is M: Jenny, there's an opening for an assistant manager in our company. You should give it a try.\\""},{"source":"Since June is cold and wet in Australia, it makes sense that at the same time\\n\\nPick the right answer from the list:\\n- Michigan would experience a heat wave\\n- Florida would be raining\\n- winter would be raging in Colorado\\n- everywhere in the world is cold","target":"Michigan would experience a heat wave","rationale":"\\"Since June is cold and wet in Australia, it makes sense that at the same time...\\".\\nGiven an Australian context about weather, \\"Michigan would experience a heat wave\\" is the only response option which also provides a contrasting weather pattern from another place. The other options are too broad or do not provide the contrast needed to answer this question correctly based on its context (the phrase \\"...at the same time\\")."},{"source":"Given a comment text in Tamil, classify the comment into one of these categories (i) Hope speech, if it contains encouraging, positive or supportive contents about equality, diversity or inclusion, (ii) Not Hope Speech or (iii) Not in Expected Language, if the text is not Tamil.\\n\\nfree fire enna tamil nadu aaa","target":"Hope Speech","rationale":"The comment contains content that supports free fire which is a mobile game and the comment has words in Tamil. So, the correct answer is Hope Speech."},{"source":"List of Fairy Tail episodes -- Fairy Tail is an anime series adapted from the manga of the same title by Hiro Mashima. Produced by A-1 Pictures and Satelight, and directed by Shinji Ishihira, it was broadcast on TV Tokyo from October 12, 2009, to March 30, 2013. It later continued its run on April 5, 2014, and ended on March 26, 2016. On July 20, 2017, Mashima confirmed on Twitter that the final season of Fairy Tail will air in 2018. The series follows the adventures of Natsu Dragneel, a member of the Fairy Tail wizards' guild and mage who is searching for the dragon Igneel, and partners with Lucy Heartfilia, a celestial wizard. \\n\\nHaving read that, I wonder is there going to be new episodes of fairy tail?","target":"No","rationale":"The context of this question says that the final season will air in 2018. This means there is no further content planned to be produced for Fairy Tail, so it can be inferred from this that new episodes are not going to happen. Hence, the answer would be No."},{"source":"Vlade Divac (Serbian Cyrillic: Vlade Divats, pronounced [vla:de di:vats]; born February 3, 1968) is a Serbian professional basketball executive and former player, currently serving as the vice president of basketball operations and general manager of the Sacramento Kings. Divac spent most of his career in the National Basketball Association (NBA). At 7 ft 1 in, he played center and was known for his passing skills. He was among the first group of European basketball players to transfer to the NBA in the late 1980s and was named one of the 50 Greatest EuroLeague Contributors.\\n\\nIn late 2000, following the overthrow of Slobodan Milosevic whose policies Divac had been openly critical of throughout mid-to-late 1990s, Divac and former teammate Predrag Danilovic took over their former club KK Partizan. They did so on initiative by Ivica Dacic, the club's outgoing president and, more importantly, a suddenly marginalized politician who, due to his association with Milosevic, was forced to leave his post at the club. Seeing that various state-owned companies and community property were being taken over in a dubious manner during the power vacuum that resulted from regime change, Dacic saw it prudent to bring the club's two former greats as a safeguard against the same happening to KK Partizan. Divac became the club's president while Danilovic took the vice-president role.  Freshly retired from playing, Danilovic was actually running the club's day-to-day operations since Divac was still very actively involved with the Sacramento Kings at the time. The head coach they inherited, Darko Russo, finished out the 2000-01 season before they decided in summer 2001 to bring back their mentor Dusko Vujosevic to be the new head coach.  Though the duo never stated so outright, their additional motivation in getting involved with KK Partizan again was perceived to be gaining the upper hand on the club's eventual privatisation process once the new Law on Sports gets passed in the Serbian parliament. Since the exact ownership structure of a publicly owned KK Partizan wasn't and still isn't really clear, potential investors decided to stay away, at least until the law appears. Divac and Danilovic appeared pretty much out of nowhere in this regard but enjoyed plenty of fan and public support because most preferred to see their beloved club owned and operated by its former stars rather than a faceless corporation or a group of politicians, managers or businessmen close to the ruling coalition. However, after a few years the duo ran out of patience and pulled out of the venture in late 2004 because it became too much of a financial burden with no end-goal in sight. While he stopped performing any official functions at the club, Divac continued to be involved with it in a lesser capacity for a few years afterwards.\\n\\nAsk a question about this article.","target":"Why did they take it over?","rationale":"The context describes a takeover of KK Partizan basketball club by Vlade Divac and Predrag Danilovic. The article goes on to describe the motivation for why they took over the club, that being securing it from privatization until new laws are passed.\\nTherefore, based on this information, we can conclude that the answer could be \\"Why did they take it over?\\""},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: John moved to the hallway. Sandra went to the hallway. Question: Where is Sandra?","target":"hallway","rationale":"We can be infer from the last fact in the passage which states \\"Sandra went to the hallway.\\""},{"source":"What is the question to: \\"Sound mass techniques also appear in the music of George Crumb (Anon. n.d.).\\"? The topic is Sound mass.","target":"\\"what composer used sound mass?\\"","rationale":"The answer is \\"what composer used sound mass?\\", because the information in the paragraph states that George Crumb, an American composer who wrote music using sound mass techniques."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is intentionally offensive, 2) no, otherwise. Also, generate label 'no' for offensive statements that appear to be unintentional, or non-offensive statements that are underhandedly offensive.  Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\nAnd the Jew @Deuterostomes favorited my tweet though. Lol. Don't have anymore time for this trash.","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given post contains a racial slur and is intended to be offensive based on the tone and intent. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Question: When was the Weston model 617 created?\\n\\nIs \\"The meter and film rating system were invented by William Nelson Goodwin, Jr., who worked for them and later received a Howard N. Potts Medal for his contributions to engineering.\\" the correct answer?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"While the passage mentions when William Nelson Goodwin, Jr., invented the meter and film rating system (1926), it does not mention when he worked for Weston. So, we cannot make a judgment as to whether this sentence is true or false with respect to the question provided in this task"},{"source":"What is the solution?\\n\\nSolve 3*o = 4*o for o.","target":"0","rationale":"We are given the equation 3o = 4o.\\n\\nTo solve this, we need to isolate o on one side of the equation. Since o is already isolated on both sides, there's nothing left to do! However, since they're equal values, it can't be solved; any value substituted in for zero would also satisfy the equation. The only solution here is 0 (which represents no quantity)."},{"source":"You are given a target profession, and two sentences. Your task is to determine whether the second sentence is either a stereotype, anti-stereotype, or is unrelated with respect to the first sentence and the target. A stereotype is a widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. An anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against the widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. Sentences and targets are unrelated if there is no relevance between them.\\n\\nTarget: musician \\nmusicians look at  the  world differently. no t all of them do drugs.","target":"anti-stereotype","rationale":"The first sentence is a stereotype (musicians look at the world differently) while the second one contradicts that by stating that not all of them do drugs. Therefore, the second sentence is an anti-stereotype."},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as unacceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"The cook boned the fish of bones.","rationale":"Here's an example of a linguistically unacceptable sentence:\\\\nThe cook boned the fish of bones."},{"source":"Saudi Arabia was boosting its production.\\n\\nQuestion with options: Based on the paragraph above can we conclude that \\"Saudi Arabia was boosting its own production.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The paragraph clearly indicates that Saudi Arabia was boosting its own production. So the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"Until the 20th century, there was no clear record of the number of Venezuelans who emigrated to the United States. Between the 18th and early 19th centuries, there were many European immigrants who went to Venezuela, only to later migrate to the United States along with their children and grandchildren who born and/or grew up in Venezuela speaking Spanish. From 1910 to 1930, it is estimated that over 4,000 South Americans each year emigrated to the United States; however, there are few specific figures indicating these statistics. Many Venezuelans settled in the United States with hopes of receiving a better education, only to remain in there following graduation. They are frequently joined by relatives. However, since the early 1980s, the reasons for Venezuelan emigration have changed to include hopes of earning a higher salary and due to the economic fluctuations in Venezuela which also promoted an important migration of Venezuelan professionals to the US.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What continental group of people from the Western Hemisphere emigrated to the United States?","target":"South Americans","rationale":"The question asks for a group of people from the Western Hemisphere who emigrated to the United States. The passage states, \\"Many Venezuelans settled in the United States with hopes of receiving a better education...\\" This implies that many Venezuelan immigrants came to America seeking educational opportunities and thereby providing an example of such immigration patterns.\\nLater on, it mentions that South Americans migrated en masse to the US during 1910-1930; this provides another data point regarding their migration patter as there are no specific figures available regarding these statistics."},{"source":"The following document has been corrupted. Tell me what \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to.\\n\\nDocument: By Paul Thompson and Alasdair Baverstock In Caracas, Venezuela Monica Spear‚Äôs father today told MailOnline that he intends to fight for the custody of his five-year old granddaughter saying he wants to take her back to the US. Rafael Spear, the father of the former Miss Venezuela murdered with her husband in a brutal street-side robbery on Monday, spoke as it emerged the little girl, Maya, has been told the shattering news and will attend her parents' funeral. 'It‚Äôs my aim to get Maya out of the country', Mr Spear said today in an interview at the couple's lying in state ceremony in Caracas‚Äôs East Cemetery. Ms Spear and her husband, Thomas Berry, will be buried side by side tomorrow.\\n@highlight\\nMaya Spear was orphaned when her mother Monica Spear Mootz and father Thomas Berry were gunned down in front of her in their broken down car in Venezuela\\n@highlight\\nHer father, Rafael, today told MailOnline he will fight to take her out of the country and to the US\\n@highlight\\nBut parents of beauty queen's husband, who live in Venezuela, say plans are still to be decided\\n@highlight\\nMaya was also shot, but has left hospital and is expected to attend her parents' funeral after being told the shattering news\\n@highlight\\nMonica, who won the Miss Venezuela title in 2004, had joined her 39-year-old estranged husband on a drive holiday\\n@highlight\\nThe killings have convulsed the crime-ridden country and sparked protests\\n@highlight\\nPolice revealed that Spear's camerabag was today found in possession of a woman believed to be in gang behind the murders \\n@placeholder was in their car with them and suffered a","target":"Maya","rationale":"The context is a description of the experiences and events surrounding Rafael Spear, who lost his daughter to a fatal attack in Venezuela. The passage begins with Mr. Spear stating that he intends to fight for custody of his granddaughter Maya, indicating that she may have been orphaned as her parents were killed by robbers during an automobile breakdown on Monday night.\\nThis implies that \\"Maya\\" refers to Monica's five year old daughter from Thomas Berry, who was also shot but has left hospital since then"},{"source":"Q: What are electrons lost during the formation of ions called?\\n\\n\\nRead this paragraph and choose the correct option from the provided answers:\\n\\nSome elements lose one or more electrons in forming ions. These ions are known as ‚Äú cations ‚Äù because they are positively charged and migrate toward the negative electrode ( cathode ) in an electrical field. Looking at the periodic table below, we know that the group 1 elements are all characterized by having one s electron in the outer orbit and group 2 elements have two s electrons in the outer orbit. These electrons are loosely attached to the atom and can easily be removed, leaving more protons in the atom that there are electrons, so the resulting ion has a positive charge. Cations can also be formed from electron loss to many of the transition elements.\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- catalysts\\n\\n- oxides\\n\\n- isotopes\\n\\n- cations\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"cations","rationale":"Ions are atoms with a positive or negative charge. They form when an atom either loses or gains electrons during chemical reactions and interactions, resulting in the imbalance of protons to electrons. In forming ions, elements lose one or more electrons; these ions are known as cations because they migrate toward the negative electrode (cathode) in an electrical field due to their positive charges.\\nThe correct answer is thus: Cations"},{"source":"Where is the wrong place to throw garbage?\\n- at a friend\\n- ground\\n- television\\n- trashcan\\n- floor\\n\\nThe best answer is","target":"floor","rationale":"The ground and trashcan are both places that garbage can be placed. The floor is not a place to put garbage, as it would create an unhygienic environment in the home or workplace. A television set is also not a proper location for disposing of waste. Thus, \\"floor\\" is the best answer because it isn't one of the options given above where people normally throw their garbage"},{"source":"Answer the question from the given passage. Your answer should be directly extracted from the passage, and it should be a single entity, name, or number, not a sentence.\\n\\nPassage: The Doctor rarely travels alone and often brings one or more companions to share these adventures. His companions are usually humans, as he has found a fascination with planet Earth. He often finds events that pique his curiosity as he tries to prevent evil forces from harming innocent people or changing history, using only his ingenuity and minimal resources, such as his versatile sonic screwdriver. As a Time Lord, the Doctor has the ability to regenerate when his body is mortally damaged, taking on a new appearance and personality. The Doctor has gained numerous reoccurring enemies during his travels, including the Daleks, the Cybermen, and the Master, another renegade Time Lord. Question: What type of Lord is Doctor Who?","target":"Time Lord","rationale":"The Doctor is a Time Lord, which is directly mentioned in the passage."},{"source":"Given a trivia question, classify broad topical category from this list: 'theater', 'geology', 'book', 'tv', 'astronomy', 'aviation', 'military', 'government', 'boxing', 'projects', 'metropolitan_transit', 'law', 'venture_capital', 'broadcast', 'biology', 'people', 'influence', 'baseball', 'spaceflight', 'media_common', 'cvg', 'opera', 'olympics', 'chemistry', 'visual_art', 'conferences', 'sports', 'language', 'travel', 'location', 'award', 'dining', 'martial_arts', 'comic_strips', 'computer', 'user', 'tennis', 'music', 'organization', 'food', 'event', 'transportation', 'fictional_universe', 'measurement_unit', 'meteorology', 'distilled_spirits', 'symbols', 'architecture', 'freebase', 'internet', 'fashion', 'boats', 'cricket', 'film', 'medicine', 'finance', 'comic_books', 'celebrities', 'soccer', 'games', 'time', 'geography', 'interests', 'common', 'base', 'business', 'periodicals', 'royalty', 'education', 'type', 'religion', 'automotive', 'exhibitions'.\\n\\nWhich is the largest of the Channel Islands, where the official language is French?","target":"language","rationale":"The question is about the language of a place. Although, it can be classified under geography or location as well, language seems to be the most correct category."},{"source":"Gill and Ann were two fellow botanists. Gill studied alpine tundras extensively, while Ann studied tropical forests. They both discovered very interesting facts about nature and plants.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nWhich person learned more about high-mountain summits?\\n\\nHint: Alpine tundra occurs at high enough altitude at any latitude. Portions of montane grasslands and shrublands ecoregions worldwide include alpine tundra. Large regions of alpine tundra occur in the North American Cordillera, the Alps and Pyrenees of Europe, the Himalaya and Karakoram of Asia, the Andes of South America, and the Eastern Rift mountains of Africa.Alpine tundra occupies high-mountain summits, slopes, and ridges above timberline. Aspect plays a role as well; the treeline often occurs at higher elevations on warmer equator-facing slopes. Because the alpine zone is present only on mountains, much of the landscape is rugged and broken, with rocky, snowcapped peaks, cliffs, and talus slopes, but also contains areas of gently rolling to almost flat topography.Averaging over many locations and local microclimates, the treeline rises 75 metres (245 ft) when moving 1 degree south from 70 to 50¬∞N, and 130 metres (430 ft) per degree from 50 to 30¬∞N. Between 30¬∞N and 20¬∞S, the treeline is roughly constant, between 3,500 and 4,000 metres (11,500 and 13,100 ft).","target":"Gill","rationale":"Gill studied alpine tundras extensively, while Ann studied tropical forests. Alpine tundra occurs at high enough altitude at any latitude and occupies high-mountain summits; therefore, it can be inferred that Gill learned more about high-mountain summits than Ann did."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of strings and you need to concatenate them.\\n\\n['what', 'g', 'gone', 'e']","target":"whatggonee","rationale":"The given list is ['what', 'g', 'gone', 'e']. When concatenating strings, each item in the list will be appended to the next.\\nwhat + g + gone + e = whatggonee"},{"source":"In this task, you're given four sentences of a story written in natural language. The given story is not complete and your job is to complete the story by selecting one of the end sentence choices from (A) and (B), such that the story does not sound complete and coherent, i.e., select an incorrect end sentence.\\n\\nSentence1: Gina wanted to steal her mother's house key. Sentence2: She waited until her mother was taking a nap. Sentence3: She took her mom's purse to the bathroom. Sentence4: She removed the key from the chain quietly. \\n (A) Then Gina placed the purse right back where she found it. (B) Then Gina told her mom where the key was.","target":"B","rationale":"Gina (the protagonist) is trying to steal her mother's house key, which implies she does not want her mom to know about it. So Sentence4 should be followed by option A: \\\\\\"Then Gina placed the purse right back where she found it\\\\\\", rather than B: \\\\\\"Then Gina told her mom where the key was\\\\\\"."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the elicit-pref strategy, otherwise output No. elicit-pref is a cooperative negotiation strategy. It is used to discover the preference order of the opponent in the negotiation.\\n\\nContext: 'Hello how are you?' 'Hey there fellow camper! I am great! How are you?' 'I'm doing well and very excited about my camping trip.'\\nUtterance: 'Me as well. What item is your greatest priority for your trip?'","target":"Yes","rationale":"The utterance contains \\"What item is your greatest priority for your trip?\\". This is a clear attempt to elicit the opponent's preference order, which is cooperative behavior. Hence, the output should be \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"You are given a dialog between 2 or more individuals. You need to generate the number of the speaker (e.g. 1 for Speaker 1) who had the most lines in the dialog. If there is a tie, output the answer '0'.\\n\\nSpeaker 1: Give me your phone. \\nSpeaker 2: Here. \\nSpeaker 1: And now your cell. \\nSpeaker 2: Okay. \\nSpeaker 1: This is your cellphone? \\nSpeaker 2: Yes. \\nSpeaker 1: This is your current cellphone? \\nSpeaker 2: Yes, it reminds me of a simpler time. \\nSpeaker 1: Phoebe, where's your purse? \\nSpeaker 1: No, no! Give it to me! \\nSpeaker 2: You can't have it. \\nSpeaker 1: Give it to me! \\nSpeaker 2: No. \\nSpeaker 1: I'll go in there. \\nSpeaker 2: Oh yeah. \\nSpeaker 1: Phoebe come here \\nSpeaker 1: Haha! \\nSpeaker 2: Damn you Monica Geller hyphen Bing!","target":"1","rationale":"Speaker 1 has the most lines, so the answer is 1."},{"source":"Dialogue:\\n\\nF: Did you watch the football match yesterday?\\n\\nM: Yes, I did. No. 5 Middle School beat us 4:2.\\n\\nQuestion: Who won the match? \\n\\n- Our team.\\n\\n- No. 5 Middle School\\n\\n- They lost.","target":"No. 5 Middle School","rationale":"The dialogue states that No. 5 Middle School beat us 4:2, so the answer is No. 5 Middle School."},{"source":"The National Park Trust identified 20 high-priority sites - including the Blue Ridge Parkway in North Carolina and Virginia and Everglades National Park in Florida - as areas with private property that could be sold.\\n\\nChoose your answer: based on the paragraph above can we conclude that \\"Blue Ridge Parkway has more private property to be sold than the Everglades National Park\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nI think the answer is","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"While the passage does mention both Blue Ridge Parkway and Everglades National Park in the same sentence, there is no information on how much private property still exists at either location. In addition, it's not clear whether or not all of these sites have equal amounts of private land to be sold within them. So I think that \\"It's impossible to say\\" would be a correct answer here"},{"source":"Given the background: During May, June, and July, the Northern Hemisphere is exposed to more direct sunlight because the hemisphere faces the Sun. The same is true of the Southern Hemisphere in November, December, and January. It is Earth's axial tilt that causes the Sun to be higher in the sky during the summer months, which increases the solar flux. However, due to seasonal lag, June, July, and August are the warmest months in the Northern Hemisphere while December, January, and February are the warmest months in the Southern Hemisphere.\\n\\nand the situation: Stan moved from the US to Australia, and he still gets confused because of the seasons in the southern hemisphere and the fact that they use the same calendar as the rest of the world.\\n\\nAnswer the following question: During which month is the southern hemisphere exposed to more sunlight, May or November?","target":"November","rationale":"Since the Northern Hemisphere is exposed to more direct sunlight during May, June and July because it faces the Sun at this time of year. The same will be true for when summer occurs in the southern hemisphere (November, December and January). However Stan still gets confused which suggests that he does not know about Earth's axial tilt or seasonal lag.\\nSo based on what we are given November would have more sunlight than May as the Southern hemispheres summer coincides with winter in the northern hemisphere"},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the physics. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: a can do a piece of work in 21 days and b in 28 days . together they started the work and b left after 4 days . in how many days can a alone do the remaining work ? \\nOptions: a ) 22 , b ) 88 , c ) 27 , d ) 14 , e ) 99","target":"d","rationale":"Work done by a in 1 day: 1/21\\\\nWork done by b in 1 day: 1/28\\\\nTherefore, work done by both of them together in one day: (1/21 + 1/28) = 7/168 = 0.04166667\\\\nTherefore, work done by them together in 4 days: 0.04166667 x 4 = 0.1666667\\\\nRemaining work to be done alone is 100 - 16.666666666 = 83.33333334%\\\\nTime taken to complete the remaining work is (100-83.33333334)/0.04166667 = 14"},{"source":"Multi-select: Is it possible to draw the conclusion that \\"Ann is nosy.\\" if \\"Susan knows all about Ann's personal problems because she is nosy.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"This statement is not supported by the given evidence. This conclusion infers that Ann's problems are of a personal nature, which may or may not be true. Therefore, it cannot be drawn from this piece of information."},{"source":"In this task, you're shown a three-part story, with a beginning, middle, and ending. Your job is to slightly modify the middle part, so that the whole story becomes unlikely, improbable, or inconsistent. Generated sentences must minimally alter the given middle, with at most 4 new words added/existing words removed. Your sentence should be grammatically and syntactically correct. Also stick to the context of the given story. For example, if the story talks about \\"doctors\\", you can talk about \\"health\\" or \\"diagnosis\\", but don't mention \\"aliens\\". Avoid introducing any extra/irrelevant information, and use names instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible. Avoid simply negating the original middle, for example:  \\"She likes cakes.\\" is changed to \\"She doesn't like cakes.\\"\\n\\nBeginning: I signed up for the local acting club. Middle: We wanted to do a play. Ending: Six months later, we put on a play at our local community center.","target":"A play wanted to do us","rationale":"The story is talking about the acting club. The middle part should be modified to reflect the club's activities. To retain the original meaning, we can change the word order of \\\\\\"We wanted to do a play\\\\\\" to \\\\\\"A play wanted to do us\\\\\\". This sentence makes more sense in relation to an acting club, where it doesn't sound plausible for a group of people like an acting club would want to perform a play themselves."},{"source":"Pick the option in line with common sense to answer the question.\\nQuestion: What is the likely end of bringing suit?\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. tensions\\n\\nB. randomness\\n\\nC. going to court\\n\\nD. swimming\\n\\nE. ruling","target":"E","rationale":"A suit can be a legal action, which means going to court. The likely end of bringing suit is to get a ruling on the case and resolve any tensions that caused it in the first place. So E seems like an obvious choice, since you have been asked for the answer based on common sense alone!"},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that does not connect with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nTitle: Choice. Sentence 1: Jim was buying groceries. Sentence 2: He saw apples and bananas. Sentence 3: He had to make a choice. Sentence 4: He pondered it for a little while. Choices: a. He settled on buying apples. b. She said it was nice to catch up.","target":"b","rationale":"The story is told from the perspective of Jim. He is buying groceries and sees apples and bananas. He has to make a choice between them, which he ponders for a while before settling on apples. The story ends with Sentence 5a, which makes sense because it continues the story by explaining what he chose to buy. However, Sentence 5b does not make sense as there are no female characters mentioned in the story and it doesn't connect to any previous sentences either.\\""},{"source":"Passage: First They Killed My Father (film) -- The film screened at the Telluride Film Festival and 2017 Toronto International Film Festival, and was released worldwide on Netflix on September 15, 2017 to positive critical reception.\\n\\nAfter reading this passage, I have a question: is first they killed my father on netflix? True or False?","target":"True","rationale":"The passage says that first they killed my father was released worldwide on Netflix. This means it is available to watch on netflix, so the answer is True."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an adjective, and your job is to generate its antonym. An antonym of a word is a word opposite in meaning to it.\\n\\nwalk","target":"stop","rationale":"\\"Walk\\" is to \\"stop\\" as \\"stand\\" is to \\"sit\\". Stand and sit are opposites, meaning that walk and stop are opposites as well."},{"source":"Eisenhower was the last president born in the 19th century, and at age 62, was the oldest man elected President since James Buchanan in 1856 (President Truman stood at 64 in 1948 as the incumbent president at the time of his election four years earlier). Eisenhower was the only general to serve as President in the 20th century and the most recent President to have never held elected office prior to the Presidency (The other Presidents who did not have prior elected office were Zachary Taylor, Ulysses S. Grant, William Howard Taft and Herbert Hoover).\\nWho was the oldest man to become President prior to Eisenhower?","target":"James Buchanan","rationale":"The context states that Eisenhower was the oldest man elected President since James Buchanan in 1856. This indicates that at age 62, he was older than all other Presidents including Truman who stood at 64 when re-elected and Herbert Hoover (who is also mentioned).\\nThus, based on this information we can conclude that prior to Eisenhower's election as President in 1952, \\"James Buchanan\\" had been the oldest man ever elected as US president."},{"source":"Given a paragraph about cooking, and a set of conversational questions and answers about the paragraph, say whether the passage contains sufficient information to answer the follow-up question. Say Yes if it is answerable; otherwise, say No. The paragraph has the prefix 'CONTEXT:'. Each conversation question has a prefix \`Q:\` followed by the answer prefix \`A:\`, and the follow-up question has a prefix \`FOLLOWUP_Q:\`.\\n\\nCONTEXT: In the Caribbean and other Rum producing areas, you find Rum in all sorts of recipesIt is sometimes an unusual flavour pairing, but not necessarily bad. In savoury cooking it adds a semi-burnt sweetness, more like toffee or butterscotch than straight RumCaribbean and Mexican cooking is well blended and harmonious with many common ingredients (chilli, coriander, avocado etc.)Considering the popularity of spicy jerk meat and Rum, the Rum Fajitas would be an interesting experiment  <sep>  Q: What does adding dark rum give to a fajita stir-fry?","target":"No","rationale":"The passage does not contain any information about the follow-up question, so the answer should be 'No'."},{"source":"Read the given text and if it has abusive content then indicate via \\"yes\\". Otherwise indicate via\\"no\\". \\nWe consider the content to be abusive if it contains any of the following instances: (1) Identity Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which contains a negative statement made against an identity. An identity is a social category that relates to a fundamental aspect of individuals community, socio-demographics, position or self-representation) (2) Affiliation Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which express negativity against an affiliation. We define affiliation as a (more or less) voluntary association with a collective. Affiliations include but are not limited to: memberships (e.g. Trade unions), party memberships (e.g. Republicans), political affiliations (e.g. Right-wing people) and occupations (e.g. Doctors).) (3) Person Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which directs negativity against an identifiable person, who is either part of the conversation thread or is named. Person-directed abuse includes serious character based attacks, such as accusing the person of lying, as well as aggression, insults and menacing language.) and (4) Counter Speech (e.g., Content which challenges, condemns or calls out the abusive language of others.). Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nJIMMY NIGGATRON","target":"yes","rationale":"The text contains a racial slur, which is considered abusive and discriminatory. Therefore, the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"I've always wondered: Charlie is the logo of which roadside restaurant chain?","target":"Little Chef","rationale":"Little Chef is a British roadside restaurant chain. It was founded in 1958 by Sam Alper, who designed the logo based on his grandson's drawing of an overweight chef named \\"Fat Charlie\\".\\n[Image] http://www.littlechef-online.co.uk/images/logo_lg_retina2x%20(1).png"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a short story consisting of exactly 5 sentences where the second sentence is missing. You are given two options and you need to select the one that best connects the first sentence with the rest of the story. Indicate your answer by 'Option 1' if the first option is correct, otherwise 'Option 2'. The incorrect option will change the subsequent storyline, so that at least one of the three subsequent sentences is no longer consistent with the story.\\n\\nSentence 1: The team was defeated. \\n Sentence 3: The coach addressed each player individually \\n Sentence 4:  He told them that they were pathetic \\n Sentence 5:  Five of the players quit the team \\n Option 1: They sat quietly in the locker room. \\n Option 2: They all left the locker room as quickly as possible.","target":"Option 1","rationale":"The first sentence establishes that the team was defeated. The third, fourth, and fifth sentences describe what happened after this event. Option 1 establishes a setting (they were in the locker room) for these events to take place and is therefore consistent with the story. In contrast, option 2 does not establish any setting for these events to take place in. Therefore, option 2 is inconsistent with the story."},{"source":"Given a goal and 2 solutions, choose the most appropriate solution.\\nGoal: Take tarnish off brass.\\n- Solution 1: Dip soft brush in windex and scrub spot.\\n- Solution 2: Dip soft brush in ammonia and scrub spot.\\n\\nAnswer by returning either Solution 1 or Solution 2","target":"Solution 2","rationale":"Brass is an alloy made from copper and zinc, which tarnishes quickly when exposed to oxygen. Ammonia reacts with the oxidation layer on brass, dissolving it away to reveal the shiny metal beneath. Windex does not contain ammonia as one of its ingredients so will not be able to clean off tarnish like Solution 2 can do.\\nTherefore, in order for the user's goal of taking tarnish off brass to be achieved, he should choose Solution 2: Dip soft brush in ammonia and scrub spot."},{"source":"Q: who sings lead vocals on i was made for loving you? A:","target":"Paul Stanley","rationale":"The lead vocals for the song \\"I Was Made For Loving You\\" are performed by Paul Stanley. \\nAs evidence, I have included a link to an article on Songfacts that describes how this is one of only two KISS songs in which Paul Stanley sings as opposed to Gene Simmons: http://www.songfacts.com/detail.php?id=1285"},{"source":"Question: How many pages of text can you store onto a cd?\\nI found the following answer on Google: Computers can read CD-ROMs, but cannot write on them.\\nIs that a correct answer? Yes or no.","target":"No","rationale":"The answer provided by Google tells us that computers can read CD-ROMs but cannot write on them. The question is asking about how many pages of text you can store onto a cd, not how many pages of texts the computer can read from it.\\nWhile both are related to CDs and their storage capacity, they do not refer to the same thing. Therefore this should be classified as \\"No\\"."},{"source":"By Associated Press Reporter The defense attorney for a man charged with raping and strangling to death a University of New Hampshire student spent his first day cross-examining the state's star witness trying to convince jurors she was possessed by imaginary characters she had created. Defense attorney Joachim Barth also asserted the witness, 20-year-old Kathryn McDonough, changed her story and shifted the blame from herself to defendant Seth Mazzaglia, her ex-boyfriend, just to get a reduced sentence. Mazzaglia is charged with first-degree murder in the October 2012 strangulation death of 19-year-old Elizabeth ‚ÄòLizzi‚Äô Marriott, of Westborough, Massachusetts. He has pleaded not guilty. Prosecutors say he and McDonough dumped Marriott's body in a river and it hasn't been recovered.\\n@highlight\\nKathryn McDonough, 20, was cross-examined Thursday by in 31-year-old Seth Mazzaglia's trial over strangulation death of Lizzi Marriott in 2012\\n@highlight\\nMcDonough claims she watched as Marriott was killed after she allegedly rebuffed McDonough's advances\\n@highlight\\nDefense attorneys replayed a scene in which McDonough told a friend she was under control of separate personality and could not recall murder\\n@highlight\\nMazzaglia's attorneys say that McDonough carried out the killing and he covered for her because he was obsessed with her\\n@highlight\\nMcDonough is serving a prison sentence for lying to investigators about Marriott's disappearance and death \\n@placeholder told jurors during his opening statement May 28 that McDonough had ‚Äòa real problem. \\n\\nYou should decide what \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to. Choose between:\\n- Associated Press\\n- Elizabeth ‚ÄòLizzi‚Äô Marriott\\n- Joachim Barth\\n- Kathryn McDonough\\n- Lizzi Marriott\\n- Marriott\\n- Massachusetts\\n- Mazzaglia\\n- McDonough\\n- Seth Mazzaglia\\n- University of New Hampshire\\n- Westborough","target":"Joachim Barth","rationale":"The context clearly mentions \\"Defense attorney Joachim Barth\\" who was cross-examining Kathryn McDonough. The phrase \\"@placeholder told jurors during his opening statement May 28 that McDonough had ‚Äòa real problem'\\", also refers to the defense attorney, as it is mentioned right after he began cross-examining her and therefore must be referring to him.\\nThus, the answer is: Defense Attorney Joachim Barth"},{"source":"Here's a complex question that requires someone to reason about the input, can you answer it?\\nThe Last Word and Orgasm, are which type of drinks?","target":"cocktail","rationale":"The Last Word and Orgasm are both cocktails. The Last Word is described as a \\"gin-based classic cocktail\\", while the Orgasm has gin, coffee liqueur and other ingredients. Both of these drinks have been featured in several popular movies including Bridget Jones's Diary (2001) which features an orgasm being made by Hugh Grant's character Mark Darcy for Renee Zellweger's title character Bridget Jones; lastly, it was used to describe an actual sexual encounter between them at the end of the movie when she tells her friends about it over dinner:\\n\\"He gave me one but I'm not telling you what kind.\\""},{"source":"I want to order a drink from Starbuck's \\nOK, which Starbuck's do you prefer?\\nThe one at the Plaza Mall\\nWhat would you like to order?\\nI want an Iced Vanilla Latte\\nWhat size you you want?\\nI'll have a tall.\\nAnd what type of milk?\\nMake it soy milk.\\nI'm sorry, soy milk is not available at this time.","target":"Do they have almond?","rationale":"The user has asked for an Iced Vanilla Latte with soy milk, and the system informs them that soy milk is not available. The most reasonable next step would be to ask them if they have another type of milk. Hence, the answer is \\"Do they have almond?\\""},{"source":"Can we draw the following hypothesis from the context? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nA: Oh, wow! But maybe you shouldn't be held responsible for something you did several years ago. B: So,  I know. A: That's the other thing. I mean a lot of people as kids or, you know, young people get into some things that they get out of later on and I don't think they should really have to pay for that forever.\\n\\nHypothesis: they should really have to pay for that forever\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- No\\n- It's impossible to say","target":"No","rationale":"From the context, we could tell that \\"A\\" is talking about how people get into trouble as kids or young adults, but later grow out of it and do not want to be held responsible for their actions forever. So the answer is ‚ÄúNo‚Äù because this hypothesis does not align with what A was trying to convey in his statement."},{"source":"Dialogue:\\n\\nW: Can you take me to the Fairyland Railway Station quickly? I'm afraid I won't be in time for my train to Manchester.\\n\\nM: I'll try. But the traffic is so heavy; it will take at least 15 minutes.\\n\\nW: OK. In that case I'll still have another 15 minutes left for my nine forty train.\\n\\nQuestion: What time is it now? \\n\\n- 9:00.\\n\\n- 9:10.\\n\\n- 9:40.","target":"9:10.","rationale":"The dialogue is about a woman who needs to get to the train station, which she will only have 15 minutes left for her 9:40 train. The man says that it takes 15minutes just in traffic alone, so if we assume that this conversation happens before they leave and then add another 15 minutes of driving time on top of the already existing 10 minute drive from where they are now (which would put them at 9:25), we can see why there's no way she'd make her 9:40 train by leaving when its currently 9:10.\\nSo, answer B is correct."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a passage which has a question and the context. You have to generate an answer to the question based on the information present in the context.\\n\\nContext: Nitric oxide (NO) and its role in surgical inflammation are well documented; demonstrating the role of NO in necrotizing enterocolitis (NEC) and ways in which it may be suppressed may provide avenues for immune modulation in the treatment of NEC.', 'We sought to demonstrate an increase in inducible nitric oxide synthase (iNOS) mRNA and nitric oxide in an experimental model of necrotizing enterocolitis. In addition, we hypothesized that interleukin-10 (IL-10) would attenuate this response.', \\"Newborn rats were treated with 25 microliters intraperitoneal IL-10 or vehicle prior to laparotomy, 1 h superior mesenteric artery (SMA) occlusion, 50 micrograms/kg intraluminal platelet activating factor administration, and SMA reperfusion. iNOS mRNA and nitric oxide levels were measured in the liver, small bowel, and serum and compared using Student's t-test.\\", 'Small bowel iNOS mRNA increased after NEC induction from 0.058 +/- 0.02 to 0.144 +/- 0.05 relative intensity units (RIU) at 2 h (p < 0.01) and from 0 to 0.09 +/- 0.02 RIU at 6 h (p < 0.03). Liver mRNA increased from 0.026 +/- 0.002 to 0.485 +/- 0.09 RIU (p < 0.002) and from 0 to 0.069 +/- 0.02 RIU (p < 0.0001) at 2 and 6 h, respectively. Serum nitric oxide increased in NEC induced animals at 2 h from 28.04 +/- 10.5 to 45.18 +/- 6.8 microM (p < 0.001). IL-10 suppressed iNOS mRNA and nitric oxide expression at 2 h in small bowel, liver, and serum by 60%, 89%, and 11%, respectively.\\\\Question: Does interleukin-10 inhibit inducible nitric oxide synthase in an animal model of necrotizing enterocolitis?","target":"IL-10 decreases iNOS mRNA response in experimental NEC. This down-regulation may be an avenue for anti-inflammatory intervention in NEC","rationale":"The answer should be a summary of what is said in the given context. The first paragraph mentions that 'interleukin-10 (IL-10) may attenuate this response'. The last paragraph states that IL-10 suppressed iNOS mRNA and nitric oxide expression at 2 h in small bowel, liver, and serum by 60%, 89%, and 11%, respectively. Hence, IL-10 decreases iNOS mRNA response in experimental NEC. This down-regulation may be an avenue for anti-inflammatory intervention in NEC."},{"source":"Exercise: read the text and answer the question by True or False.\\n\\nText: NEXUS (frequent traveler program) -- Along the Mexican border, NEXUS members may utilize Secure Electronic Network for Travelers Rapid Inspection (SENTRI) lanes when entering the US by land, but must be traveling in an approved, registered vehicle (SENTRI requires members to register their vehicles into the program, which involves a thorough inspection by CBP, whereas NEXUS has no such requirement). Regardless of whether the traveler is in an approved vehicle or not, the NEXUS card is a WHTI compliant document, and may be used in any standard lane from Mexico into the United States as proof of identity and citizenship. Pedestrians can use dedicated SENTRI lines for expedited entry into the U.S. from Tijuana at the San Ysidro border crossing.\\nQuestion: can i use my nexus card in a non nexus lane?","target":"True","rationale":"The text states that NEXUS cardholders can use their cards to enter the US from Mexico by land. It also says, ‚ÄúNEXUS has no such requirement‚Äù when it comes to a thorough inspection of your vehicle. Therefore, you do not need a registered SENTRI vehicle in order to cross the border and therefore you may utilize non-SENTRI lanes (non-NEXUS). So the answer is True"},{"source":"Question: He didn't believe fate controlled situations, what did he believe people did?\\nOptions:\\n- control events\\n- pray\\n- dress themselves\\n- talk to each other\\n- think creatively\\n\\nExplain why a human would choose \\"control events\\" to answer the question above:","target":"this word is most relavant","rationale":"The rationale to choose \\"control events\\" as the answer is:\\n- this word is most relavant"},{"source":"Generate a question that has the following answer: \\nmuseum \\nfor the following movie plot: \\nIn Egypt, Yousef Bey (John Carradine) journeys to a remote temple in answer to a summons from Andoheb, High Priest of Arkham (George Zucco). Andoheb has called him to undertake a mission for the priesthood, but first refreshes his memory on the story of Kharis (Lon Chaney Jr.).3000 years ago, Kharis and the Princess Ananka were involved in a forbidden love affair. The princess died and because of her sin, her soul was cursed forever. Kharis was buried alive along with her. 30 years prior to the present time, an expedition located and entered the tomb of Ananka. They fought and escaped from the guardian of the tomb-the living Mummy of Kharis. The archaeologists brought Ananka's body back to the Scripps Museum in the United States. However, the priests of Arkham sent Kharis to seek vengeance against the defilers of the tomb. Every person from the expedition that entered the tomb died at the Mummy's hands. Kharis was believed to be destroyed in a fire at the residence of Stephen Banning (Dick Foran), leader of the expedition.The same story is being told to a group of skeptical college students in Mapleton Massachusetts. Professor Norman (Frank Reicher) expands on the story, explaining how Kharis was kept alive by the fluid of the leaves of the Tana bush, a plant that has long been extinct. In fact, Professor Norman himself was entrusted with a quantity of the tana leaves that investigators found in order to conduct scientific research.After the lecture ends, one of the students, Tom Hervey (Robert Lowery), meets up with his girlfriend Amina Mansori (Ramsay Ames), a beautiful woman of Egyptian descent. Amina has been researching Egyptian history, which has brought on a strange, clouded feeling in her mind.Back in Egypt, Andoheb informs Yousef Bey that Kharis still lives and that Yousef's mission is to retrieve Kharis and the body of Ananka and return them to their rightful resting place in Egypt. Yousef Bey then pledges his devotion:\\"I swear by the mighty power of Amon-Ra, whose anger can shatter the world and by...","target":"where does dr ayad work?","rationale":"In this example, the correct answer is \\"where does dr ayad work?\\", and it was generated for a specific movie plot. You can see that in the first sentence of the underlying story:\\n  In Egypt, Yousef Bey (John Carradine) journeys to a remote temple in answer to a summons from Andoheb...\\nThe key part here is Dr Ayad who works at an Egyptian museum."},{"source":"In this task, the input is a set of dialogues between a user and an assistant. You need to find the dialogue that is basically a response given to a question or an aspect of the user.\\n\\nI didn't know that. Thanks. Can you tell me about Ukraine's history? \\n This is very informative. Please tell me more. \\n Thank you for all of the information you've provided. That will be all for now. Have a good day. \\n Well, the EU had encouraged Ukraine to implement the PCA fully before the discussions about the association agreement had even begun. \\n I'm afraid I'm not equipped with that information, but I could inform you more about their economy if you'd like!","target":"Well, the EU had encouraged Ukraine to implement the PCA fully before the discussions about the association agreement had even begun","rationale":"The correct answer is \\"Well, the EU had encouraged Ukraine to implement the PCA fully before the discussions about the association agreement had even begun.\\"\\\\nThe user asks for information about Ukraine's history and then says \\"This is very informative. Please tell me more.\\" indicating that they are not satisfied with what they have been told. The assistant then provides a response asking if they'd like to know more information on their economy instead. Since this response is basically in response to the first question, it can be inferred that this dialogue was given in reply to a question or an aspect of the user."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a short story with a beginning, two potential middles, and an ending. Your job is to choose the middle statement that makes the story incoherent / implausible by indicating 1 or 2 in the output. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nBeginning: Today was my Birthday. Middle 1: I heard the doorbell ring. Middle 2: I waited for the doorbell to ring. Ending: When I opened the door, some of my family were in the front.","target":"2","rationale":"Middle 1 indicates that the protagonist heard the doorbell, so they would have known somebody was at the house. Middle 2 indicates that the protagonist waited for the doorbell to ring, but they did not hear it ring. So Middle 2 makes less sense."},{"source":"I read this background article the other day: About 10% of sedimentary rocks are limestones. The solubility of limestone in water and weak acid solutions leads to karst landscapes, in which water erodes the limestone over thousands to millions of years. Most cave systems are through limestone bedrock.\\n\\nI am facing a new situation today: Peter visited two mountain ranges last summer. The Ozarks in Missouri, and the  more massive and younger Colorado Rockies. He loved both ranges, but liked the caves systems and blue holes in the Ozarks a bit more.\\n\\nUsing the knowledge I acquired from the background article, how should I answer correctly the following question regarding my new situation: Which rocks are more soluble, the ones from the Ozarks, or the ones from the Rockies?","target":"Ozarks","rationale":"The first article states that limestone is soluble. The second paragraph says the Ozarks are made of limestones, so those rocks are more soluble than the ones from the Rockies."},{"source":"Does the sentence \\"The fortified city temporarily fell to the French invasion in 1672 (the Disaster Year); where the French invasion was only stopped west of Utrecht at the Old Hollandic Waterline.\\" answer the question \\"Who did the fortified city fall to in 1672\\"\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The sentence states that the fortified city fell to the French invasion, so the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"If \\"A man in a black shirt is showing a broken glass.\\", does this mean that \\"The man is wearing a green shirt.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise states that the man is wearing a black shirt, which directly contradicts the hypothesis that he is wearing a green shirt. Therefore, we can conclude that \\"The man is not wearing a green shirt.\\" So the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Here's a logic test: Bill was alone in an old abandoned house. He heard a strange moaning sound. It seemed to be getting louder. Whoever or whatever was making that sound was (A) getting closer (B) getting further away.\\n\\nChoose the answer between \\"a louder moan\\" and \\"a quieter moan\\".","target":"a louder moan","rationale":"The context of the situation is that Bill was alone in an old abandoned house. He heard a strange moaning sound and it seemed to be getting louder, suggesting that whoever or whatever was making the noise was approaching him. This means that if he were able to determine whether the moan got quieter or more intense as time passed by, he would know where the person/creature went after they had left based on how far away from him they are when they start moving (whether closer or further). The answer is \\"a louder moan\\" because this suggests that at some point in time between hearing them make their initial noise and then again later while also trying to get his bearings around the empty property, something started coming towards him so loudly that it scared off all other noises!\\nHere's another example:"},{"source":"In this task, you are given an abstract of article. Your task is to generate title for this article. Preferred titles are under thirty words.\\n\\nThe Centers for Disease Control and Prevention Office of Workforce and Career Development is committed to developing a competent, sustainable, and diverse public health workforce through evidence-based training, career and leadership development, and strategic workforce planning to improve population health outcomes. This article reviews the previous efforts in identifying priorities of public health workforce research, which are summarized as eight major research themes. We outline a strategic framework for public health workforce research that includes six functional areas (ie, definition and standards, data, methodology, evaluation, policy, and dissemination and translation). To conceptualize and prioritize development of an actionable public health research agenda, we constructed a matrix of key challenges in workforce analysis by public health workforce categories. Extensive reviews were conducted to identify valuable methods, models, and approaches to public health workforce research. We explore new tools and approaches for addressing priority areas for public health workforce and career development research and assess how tools from multiple disciplines of social sciences can guide the development of a research framework for advancing public health workforce research and policy.","target":"Perspectives on public health workforce research","rationale":"The abstract describes the previous efforts in identifying and prioritizing public health workforce research, outlines a strategic framework for future research, identifies valuable tools that can be used to guide ongoing or future studies related to this topic. The title should reflect these aspects of the paper and provide an overview of how researchers in this field are thinking about workforce development from a scientific perspective. One possible suggestion is: \\"Perspectives on public health workforce research\\"."},{"source":"What's the answer to that question: where is kate middleton spending christmas?","target":"Bucklebury","rationale":"The answer is \\"Bucklebury\\". The Duchess of Cambridge and her family are spending Christmas in Bucklebury."},{"source":"Two analogies on manipulating items in a kitchen is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". The phrase \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its appropriate manipulation B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate manipulation of item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a verb which shows a way to manipulate the given object.\\n\\nbox : open. present : ?","target":"open","rationale":"A box is opened and presents are also opened."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: The light reactions take place in the thylakoid. Sentence 2: In plants, light-dependent reactions occur in the thylakoid membranes of the chloroplasts where they drive the synthesis of ATP and NADPH.","target":"entails","rationale":"Statement 2 provides additional information that supports the scientific fact stated in Statement 1. Specifically, it explains how and where light-dependent reactions occur in plants, which corresponds to the location of the thylakoid as described by Statement 1. Therefore, Statement 2 entails or implies Statement 1."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage. The passage will not have a direct answer to the question, but can include some information and a clue for the answer. Assuming you can only obtain information about one entity in the passage, your job is to determine whether information from the passage can be used to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: When Charles Ogston was part of an occupying force in Pretoria and Johannesburg, which of the two had the larger population at the time? Passage:Ogston was the son of Alexander Milne Ogston of Ardoe, Kincardineshire. He was educated at the Royal Military College, Sandhurst and commissioned a second lieutenant in the Gordon Highlanders in November 1897. He served on the North-West Frontier of India from 1897 to 1898 and took part in the Tirah Campaign under Sir William Lockhart. Promoted to lieutenant on 21 July 1899, he was later the same year sent to South Africa to serve as an intelligence officer in the Second Boer War. He took part in the Relief of Kimberley (February 1900), including the Battle of Magersfontein (11 December 1899), followed by fighting in the Orange Free State from February to May 1900, including the Battle of Paardeberg (18‚Äì27 February 1900). In May 1900 he was posted to the Transvaal Republic, where he took part in the occupation of Johannesburg and Pretoria, the capital of the republic, followed by service around the occupied areas, including the Battle of Bergendal (August 1900) and fighting near Lydenburg. He was promoted to captain on 22 January 1902, and following the end of hostilities in early June 1902 left Cape Town on board the SS Orotava, arriving at Southampton the next month.","target":"a","rationale":"The question asks about the population of two cities in South Africa and the passage mentions those two cities as well. Additionally, Pretoria is mentioned before Johannesburg; this could be a clue for the answer."},{"source":"Generate a correct and concise answer for the question based on the words in the context.\\n\\nContext : Henry Pl√©e (also named H.D. Pl√©e, Henri Pl√©e, Henry D. Pl√©e, or Henry-D√©sir√© Pl√©e, 24 May 1923; Arras, Nord-Pas-de-Calais--19 August 2014; Paris) was a French martial artist who is considered as the 'father of European and French karate'. \\nQuestion : What city is Henry Pl√©e from?","target":"Paris","rationale":"The question asks where Henry Pl√©e is from and the context contains Paris."},{"source":"Write a multi-choice question for the following article, with the given choices and answer:\\nArticle: How to have fun in Chicago without spending a lot of money?\\nSightseeing\\nThe Art Institute of Chicago has a fine collection of photos and paintings. The ticket is $10.00, but go on Tuesdays and you'll get in free.\\nThe Sears Tower is the world's third tallest building. By going to the 103rd floor, you can get a view of the whole city. All for only $8.50.\\nFree show\\nThere are free concerts in Grant Park in summer. They are held Wednesday through Saturday nights at 7:30 P.M..\\nAttend the taping of a TV show for free. The Oprah Winfrey Show and the Jenny Jones Show both offer tourists free tickets. For the Oprah Winfrey Show, you'll have to book tickets at least a month before.\\nPlaces to stay\\nYou can get a hotel for $100 to $300 a day. However, you can get a room in the dormitory at\\nRoosevelt University for $215 for a whole week! But you have to stay for 28 days to get this great rate .\\nOptions:\\nA $860\\nB $300\\nC $215\\nD $ l00\\nAnswer:\\nA $860\\nQuestion:","target":"You have to spend at least  _  in all to stay in a dormitory room at Roosevelt University at a good rate.","rationale":"Here's what your answer should be: You have to spend at least  _  in all to stay in a dormitory room at Roosevelt University at a good rate."},{"source":"Fog is formed by water vapor condensing in what?\\n\\nPick the right answer from the list:\\n- plants\\n- air heads\\n- empty space\\n- animals","target":"empty space","rationale":"Fog is formed by water vapor condensing in the air. Fog can be created when warm, humid air cools and releases moisture into an area with cooler temperatures or lower pressure.\\nIn this question, only \\"empty space\\" represents an option that could allow for this process to occur. Therefore, empty space is the correct answer."},{"source":"In this task, you need to reverse the order of words in the given sentence.\\n\\nSentence: a cluttered desk with things like magazines cans of soda and a laptop","target":"laptop a and soda of cans magazines like things with desk cluttered a","rationale":"We first split the sentence into words by the spaces.\\\\n1. 'a'\\\\n2. 'cluttered'\\\\n3. 'desk'\\\\n4. 'with'\\\\n5. 'things'\\\\n6. 'like'\\\\n7. 'magazines'\\\\n8.'cans-of-soda-and-a-laptop'. We can further split this word into ['cans', of, soda, and, a, laptop] using the hyphen (-). Let's use this new list in place of the original word: 8.'cans'. \\\\t8.'of'. \\\\t8.'soda'. \\\\t8.'and'. \\\\t8.'a'. \\\\t8.'laptop'.\\n\\nThe reverse order of these words is:\\\\nlaptop a and soda of cans magazines like things with desk cluttered a"},{"source":"What is the solution to this math problem?\\nSolve -7*q = -7*q - 7*q for q.","target":"0","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable q on one side of the equation.\\n\\nStarting with: -7*q = -14*q - 7*q  (Step 1)\\nSubtracting (-7)*(2)*(q) from both sides: 0 = (-21)*(q) (Step 2)\\nDividing both sides by 21: q = 0   (Final step)."},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an implausible answer to a question that involves event \\"frequency\\", which refers to how often an event is likely to be repeated. For example, \\"taking showers\\" typically occurs ~5 times a week, \\"going to Saturday market\\" usually happens every few weeks/months, etc. Even though there exist multiple wrong answers, we only need a single wrong answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: The postwar period began, however, with millions of displaced people homeless and starving. \\nQuestion: How often did starving people eat?","target":"everyday","rationale":"The sentence is discussing how there were millions of displaced people homeless and starving after World War II. Homeless people will likely not be able to afford food, so it's implausible that they would eat everyday."},{"source":"Answer the question based on the following text.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nMilo works as an astronomer and he has multiple telescopes at his disposal. If he is looking at the stars through a large telescope and then moves to a smaller one, will the amount of light collected by the smaller one be greater or smaller? \\n\\n\\nText:\\n\\nLarger telescopes can collect more light.","target":"smaller","rationale":"If Milo looks at the stars through a large telescope and then moves to a smaller one, there will be less light collected by the smaller telescope. This is because larger telescopes can collect more light than small ones. The answer is \\"smaller\\"."},{"source":"Amsterdam police said Wednesday that they have recovered stolen lithographs by the late U.S. pop artist Andy Warhol worth more than $1 million.\\n\\nBased on that paragraph can we conclude that the sentence below is true?\\nPolice recovered 81 Andy Warhol lithographs.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"We cannot conclude that the statement is true because we do not know if 81 lithographs were stolen."},{"source":"The input is a conversation between an automated system and a user, followed by a question. The user is looking for suggestions for pubs, restaurants and coffee shops in Cambridge. In the dialogue, the user may provide some criteria for the type of place they want such as price range, cuisine, etc. Similarly, the user may ask details of the place suggested by the system such as phone number, address, etc. The answer of the question has to be a Yes or a No. Given such a dialogue, answer the given question based on the information present in the dialogue.\\n\\nSystem: 'Thank you for calling the Cambridge Information system. Your call will be recorded for research purposes. You may ask for information about a place to eat, such as a restaurant, a pub, or a cafe. How may I help you?'\\nUser: 'im looking for a restaurant in barnwell'\\nSystem: 'The Wheatsheaf is an outstanding restaurant and it's in the Barnwell part of town.'\\nUser: 'what is the address'\\nSystem: 'The Wheatsheaf is located on Stow Road, Stow-Cum-Quy.'\\nUser: 'what are the prices that unintelligible'\\nSystem: 'The Wheatsheaf is in the moderate price range.'\\nUser: 'thank you goodbye'\\nQuestion: 'Did the user ask for the address of the restaurant?'","target":"Yes","rationale":"The user asks for the address of the restaurant in the dialogue, and this is mentioned twice in the conversation. Therefore, it is a Yes."},{"source":"Guess a question that has the answer \\"Jane (band)\\"","target":"What is the first name of Agatha Christie's Miss Marple?","rationale":"The answer to the question \\"What is the first name of Agatha Christie's Miss Marple?\\" is Jane.\\nThis information can be found online and in books about novelists, English literature, etc., including on wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miss_Marple\\nSince it would not make sense for a person to ask this question with no context given (e.g., if they are playing trivia or reading novels), one could assume that there was some reason why someone wanted to know who Miss Marple was which led them to search for her name instead of typing out the full name when asking their question."},{"source":"A screw will increase in temperature when set in the sun's path, why?\\n\\nPick the right answer from the list:\\n- heating element\\n- building device\\n- conduction\\n- convection","target":"conduction","rationale":"A screw will increase in temperature when set in the sun's path because of conduction."},{"source":"You are provided with a list of converations between a \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\". Figure out if the conversation provided as \\"classify_text\\" is authored by \\"USER\\" or \\"ASSISTANT\\". There are maximum of 7 conversations between \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\" in each input\\n\\nASSISTANT: What type of movies do you like? , USER: Musicals. , ASSISTANT: why musicals? , USER: They make me happy, and make me leave the reality of the world, that's so sad sometimes. , ASSISTANT: What is one of your favorite movies? , USER: Into the Woods, classify_text: what did u like about it?","target":"ASSISTANT","rationale":"The classify_text is a question related to the movie 'Into the Woods'. Therefore, it can be inferred that it was asked by ASSISTANT and not USER."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the union of two given sets. A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. Union of two given sets is the smallest set which contains all the elements of both the sets. To find the union of two given sets, A and B is a set that consists of all the elements of A and all the elements of B such that no element is repeated.\\n\\nSet1: '{1, 12, 5}', Set2: '{2, 3, 5, 7, 10, 11, 14, 16, 17, 20}'. How many elements are there in the union of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"12","rationale":"Given the two sets {1, 12, 5} and {2, 3, 5, 7, 10, 11}, we need to find the union of these sets.\\\\nAll elements in Set1: 1 -> (total) 1\\\\nAll elements in Set2: 2 -> (total) 3\\\\nAll elements in Set2: 3 -> (total) 4\\\\nSince '5' is already present in the count - it will not be added again. \\\\nAll elements in Set2 : 7 -> (total) 6\\\\nSince 10 and 11 are repeated twice each - they are not added. \\\\nHence the final answer is 6"},{"source":"Lighter, more streamlined vehicles need less energy.\\n\\nHaving read the above passage, choose the right answer to the following question (choices are less or more ):\\n\\n\\nIf Jon adds more weight to his car, he will need to use less or more energy?","target":"more","rationale":"The sentence \\"Lighter, more streamlined vehicles need less energy\\" means that lighter and more aerodynamic cars use less gas than heavier ones. We can see from this passage that the amount of weight in a car has an impact on how much fuel it needs to run. A vehicle with added cargo will require more fuel (energy) to operate. Therefore if Jon adds weight to his car he would have to expend ‚Äúmore‚Äù energy operating the vehicle compared to what was needed previously before adding additional weight"},{"source":"Given the fact that:\\n\\nAs animals grow their bones get longer and bigger, they grow more hair, and are able to take care of themselves by getting food, shelter, and water.\\n\\nAnswer the question:\\n\\n\\nScuffy was a puppy, and now he is a sick dog. Now that Scruffy is smaller, shorter, and balder than before, Scrufffy can take care of himself better or worse?","target":"worse","rationale":"The context says that as animals grow, their bones get longer and bigger, they grow more hair, and are able to take care of themselves by getting food, shelter, water. Scruffy is now smaller than before which means he has less bone length/size growth than when he was a puppy. He is also balder so it can be assumed that his coat (the dog equivalent of human hair) grew in significantly during the time between being a puppy and an older dog. A sick dog would also not be taking care of itself at all or even very well since it‚Äôs ill - thus we know that after growing up scruffy cannot take better care of himself because the opposite happened: worse!"},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: Cindy, Jerry and Mary are giving their opinions about a good friend.\\nCindy: I think a good friend should be honest . That's more important than any other thing and is where a good friendship starts. _ \\nJerry: I think a good friend has to be generous. Here \\"generous\\" doesn't mean he has to give his friends his lunch money or his clothes. It means he should share  his ideas and feelings with his friends. In fact, his friends can know him better in this way.\\nMary: In my opinion a good friend should understand  his friends. When there's something wrong between him and his friends, he must put himself in his friends' place and think more for his friends.\\nQuestion: Jerry would like to make friends with people who   _  .\\nOptions: A: give him lunch money\\nB: know him very well\\nC: tell him their ideas and feelings\\nD: give him some clothes","target":"C","rationale":"The article mentions that Jerry thinks a good friend should be generous, which means he wants his friends to share their ideas and feelings with him. So the answer is C\\nSo, the correct choice would be ‚ÄúC: tell him their ideas and feelings‚Äù"},{"source":"Article: A fit and healthy teenage rugby player died 12 hours after taking treatment for acne ,an officer,Mary Hassel,said today. She said Shaun Jones,14,died \\"as a result of complications of medical treatment\\". \\nShaun,who was described by his mother as \\"vain\\" about his appearance,saw Dr Jones,his family doctor,about spors on his back and shoulders after learning his friends had been given medication to deal with similar problems. \\nThe boy,who had previously used Clearasil to treat the spots,was diagnosed with mild acne and given a prescription. But when he went to his local chemist's with his mother,he was told the drug was not available. They said they had contacted Dr Jones(in fact they didn't),and  Shaun could be given different pills which were the same as the drug originally prescribed. Mrs. Jones noriced there was no safety instructions included in the box,but thought nothing of it at the time. \\nShaun took the drug just before going to bed at 10:30 pm. Little more than an hourlater, he complained of shortness of breath and tighmess in his chest. Mrs. . Jones initially contacted an out--of--hours GP service but was told no doctor was available. When Shaun's condition  became worse,he was rushed to the Royal Glamorgan Hospital by ambulance in the early hours of the next morning. \\nDespite treatment there,and at the University Hospital of Wales,Cardiff,where he was transferred,Shaun died at 10:40 am the following day. Doctors at the hospital believe an unusual reaction to the acne drug could have caused his death. \\nHassel said she would write a report to the Lord Chancellor's office imdedining the impor-tailce that \\"doctors prescribe drugs and doctors make adjustments and patients receive drugs with the correct information attached\\".\\nQuestion: It call be inferred from the passage that Mary Hassel  _  .\\nYes or no, is the answer \\"could help mole people become more careful about drugs\\"?","target":"No","rationale":"The article is about a teenager who died shortly after taking medication for acne. \\nMary Hassel, an officer, said that Shaun Jones (the teenage boy) died \\"as a result of complications of medical treatment\\". She also said that she would write a report to the Lord Chancellor's office including the importance that \\"doctors prescribe drugs and doctors make adjustments and patients receive drugs with the correct information attached.\\"  \\nBased on this context there are two things we can infer: \\nFirst, Mary Hassel believes that part of how Shaun Jones passed away was due to him receiving incorrect medications from his doctor. Second, Mary has plans moving forward related to drug safety instructions and prescribing guidelines in order to prevent similar accidents in the future. So answer No is better than Yes.\\n\\n\\n["},{"source":"Question: Ben was at the playground. He noticed when he rolled his ball across the sand that it moved slower than when he rolled it across a wooden plank. This is because the _____ has less resistance. (A) wooden plank (B) sand\\n\\nDo not use A and B to answer the question but instead, choose between \\"sand\\" and  \\"wooden plank\\".","target":"sand","rationale":"Ben was at the playground, and he noticed when he rolled his ball across sand that it moved slower than on a wooden plank. This is because sand has less resistance than wood. Hence, \\"sand\\" should be chosen as the answer.\\""},{"source":"Does this phrase make sense?\\nkeep the kitchen clean while cooking hire someone to clean up afterwards.\\nAnswer with Yes or No","target":"No","rationale":"If you are keeping the kitchen clean while cooking, then there is no need to hire someone to clean up afterwards. So this sentence makes little sense as it stands and should be No."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that seamlessly connects with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes more sense.\\n\\nTitle: Checkers.. Sentence 1: Mary always beats Peter at checkers. Sentence 2: Peter gets so frustrated that he tries to cheat sometimes. Sentence 3: Mary always catches him and gets mad. Sentence 4: Mary says that if Peter tries to cheat again she'll stop playing him. Choices: a. James lost the spelling bee in the first round. b. Peter decides to never cheat against Mary again.","target":"b","rationale":"The other four sentences in the story talk about Peter and Mary playing checkers, so it makes more sense to have the fifth sentence also be related to checkers."},{"source":"EXAM\\n1. Answer by yes or no.\\n\\nDocument: 2011 NBA Finals -- The 2011 NBA Finals was the championship series of the 2010--11 season of the National Basketball Association (NBA) in which the Western Conference champion Dallas Mavericks defeated the Eastern Conference champion Miami Heat 4 games to 2 to win their first NBA championship. The series was held from May 31 to June 12, 2011. German player Dirk Nowitzki was named the Finals MVP, becoming the second European to win the award after Tony Parker (2007) and the first German player to do so. The series was a rematch of the 2006 NBA Finals, which the Heat had won in six games.\\nQuestion: did the dallas mavericks ever win the nba championship?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The document says that the Dallas Mavericks won the 2011 NBA Finals. Therefore, they have at least one championship win in team history, so this is a Yes question"},{"source":"Answer the question from the given passage. Your answer should be directly extracted from the passage, and it should be a single entity, name, or number, not a sentence.\\n\\nPassage: Since the 2005 revival, the Doctor generally travels with a primary female companion, who occupies a larger narrative role. Steven Moffat described the companion as the main character of the show, as the story begins anew with each companion and she undergoes more change than the Doctor. The primary companions of the Ninth and Tenth Doctors were Rose Tyler (Billie Piper), Martha Jones (Freema Agyeman), and Donna Noble (Catherine Tate) with Mickey Smith (Noel Clarke) and Jack Harkness (John Barrowman) recurring as secondary companion figures. The Eleventh Doctor became the first to travel with a married couple, Amy Pond (Karen Gillan) and Rory Williams (Arthur Darvill), whilst out-of-sync meetings with River Song (Alex Kingston) and Clara Oswald (Jenna Coleman) provided ongoing story arcs. The tenth series will introduce Pearl Mackie as Bill, the Doctor's newest traveling companion. Question: Who were the secondary companions of the Ninth and Tenth Doctors?","target":"Mickey Smith (Noel Clarke) and Jack Harkness (John Barrowman)","rationale":"The correct answer is directly stated in the passage.  The Doctor's Ninth and Tenth Doctors traveled with Rose Tyler, Martha Jones, and Donna Noble as primary companions.  Mickey Smith (Noel Clarke) and Jack Harkness (John Barrowman) are described as secondary companion figures."},{"source":"Two analogies that signify affordances are given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Affordance is the possibility of an action being done on an object, for example book is an affordance of writing. The phrase \\"A : B\\" implies that B is an affordance of A. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate affordance of the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a single object without further explanation.\\n\\ncompose : symphony. paint : ?","target":"picture","rationale":"You can compose symphonies using any equipment you want, but in order to paint a picture you need the canvas."},{"source":"60 Razvedupr officers were dispatched to Tallinn in the spring of 1924 to organise an uprising. The plan for was hatched by Jaan Anvelt and Karl Rimm. The latter was a veteran of the Russian Civil War. The plan envisaged the main attack aimed at Tallinn, with subsequent coups in Tartu, Narva, P√§rnu, Viljandi, Rakvere, Kunda, and Kohila. The revolt was supposed to start at 5:15 a.m. The 279 communists, mostly infiltrated from the Soviet Union, were armed with 5 Thompson light machine guns, 55 rifles, 65 hand grenades, 8 explosive devices and 150 pistols. It was mistakenly expected that the workers and soldiers would join the insurgency and would seize power in the capital together. The plan called for the establishment of an Estonian Soviet Socialist Republic and of a \\"working people's government\\". Most of the schemes were spoiled by the Trial of the 149 in November 1924, which eliminated many potential communist organisers. The gunmen's first priority was to take over the Estonian National Defence College based in the Tondi suburb south of the city centre, the main narrow gauge railway station in Tallinn-V√§ike, and a battalion of engineering troops in N√µmme.\\n\\nBased on the above article, answer a question. Were there more communists or Razvedupr officers?","target":"Razvedupr officers","rationale":"The problem asks whether there were more communists or Razvedupr officers. It is mentioned that 60 Razvedupr officers and 279 communists infiltrated from the Soviet Union, so we could conclude that there was a total of 339 people involved in this issue. Therefore, since 339 is greater than 60 (i.e., 239 > 0), it must be true to say that there were more razvedupr officers rather than comunists/"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and a question, you would be asked to create the answer which is contained in the sentence provided.\\n\\nSentence: As it passes to the next level, most of the energy in a trophic level it is lost. Question: What happens to most of the energy in a trophic level as it passes to the next higher level?","target":"it is lost","rationale":"The sentence states that \\"most of the energy in a trophic level is lost\\", so the answer should be \\"it is lost\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the occurrences of the given word in the given sentence.\\n\\nSentence: 'a train with grafitti sitting on the tracks'. Count the occurrences of the word 'a' in the given sentence.","target":"1","rationale":"Given the sentence 'a train with grafitti sitting on the tracks', let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. 'a' : 1 -> (total) 1\\\\n2. 'train' : 0 -> (total) 1\\\\n3. 'with' : 0 -> (total) 1\\\\n4. 'grafitti' : 0 -> (total) 1\\\\n5. 'sitting' : 0 -> (total) 1\\\\n6. 'on' : 0 -> (totla) 1\\\\n7. 'the' : 0"},{"source":"Determine if the provided SQL statement properly addresses the given question. Output 1 if the SQL statement is correct and 0 otherwise. An SQL query works by selecting data from a table where certain conditions apply. A table contains columns where every row in that table must have a value for each column. Every table has a primary key that uniquely identifies each row, usually an id. To choose which columns are returned you specify that after the \\"SELECT\\" statement. Next, you use a \\"FROM\\" statement to specify what tables you want to select the data from. When you specify a table you can rename it with the \\"AS\\" statement. You can reference that table by whatever name follows the \\"AS\\" statement. If you want to select data from multiple tables you need to use the \\"JOIN\\" statement. This will join the tables together by pairing a row in one table with every row in the other table (Cartesian Product). To limit the number of rows returned you should use the \\"ON\\" statement. This will only return rows where the condition specified after the statement is true, this is usually an equals operator with primary keys. You can also use the \\"WHERE\\" statement to specify that only rows with column values statisfying a certain condition, should be returned. The \\"GROUP BY\\" statement will group rows together that have equal column values for whatever columns follows the statement. The \\"HAVING\\" statement will return groups that statisfy whatever condition follows the statement. Any column(s) being returned from grouped rows must either be an aggregate function, (AVG, MAX, COUNT, SUM, ...) of a column, or the column(s) that the data was grouped by. To sort the returned data you can use the \\"ORDER BY\\" command which will order the data by whatever aggregate function or column follows the statement. The \\"DESC\\" statement will sort in descending order and the \\"ASC\\" statement will sort in ascending order. Finally, you can use the \\"LIMIT\\" statement to return a certain number of rows. When \\"*\\" is used in an SQL statement every column is returned. For example, SELECT * FROM table WHERE attribute = 1, will select every column from rows with the attribute column equal to 1.\\n\\nQuery: SELECT count(*) WHERE {\\n?x0 a ns:people.person .\\n?x0 ns:influence.influence_node.influenced M1 .\\n?x0 ns:influence.influence_node.influenced M2 .\\n?x0 ns:people.person.spouse_s/ns:people.marriage.spouse|ns:fictional_universe.fictional_character.married_to/ns:fictional_universe.marriage_of_fictional_characters.spouses ?x1 .\\n?x1 a ns:film.cinematographer .\\nFILTER ( ?x0 != ?x1 )\\n} Question: Did a person marry a cinematographer , influence M1 , and influence M2","target":"1","rationale":"The output of this query is a list of all pairs (x0, x1) where x0 is a person who married cinematographer x1, influenced M1 and M2."},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\nThe company intends to raise production capacity in 2006 .","target":"positive","rationale":"This financial news states that the company intends to increase production capacity in 2006. The expansion of production capacity indicates an increase in demand for the company's products and services, which is generally considered a positive development. So, this financial news can be clarified as \\"positive\\"."},{"source":"A gastroenterologist is a doctor who treats problems of the esophagus, stomach, and intestines. Which organ system is cared for by this type of doctor?\\n\\nOptions:\\n- circulatory system\\n- muscular system\\n- digestive system\\n- nervous system","target":"digestive system","rationale":"A gastroenterologist is a doctor who treats problems of the esophagus, stomach, and intestines. The organs listed are all part of the digestive system which includes not only those mentioned above but also other parts such as liver and pancreas. Therefore, a gastroenterologist cares for patients with diseases in the digestive system so that's what he/she specializes in: treating sick people caused by issues related to digestion."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a string of characters. You should remove all vowels from the given string. Vowels are: i,e,a,u,o. The character 'y' or 'Y' does not count as a vowel.\\n\\nQyIhbiTAYwIhJRD","target":"QyhbTYwhJRD","rationale":"The given string contains the vowels 'A', 'I', 'A', and 'I', which should be removed according to the instructions. The resulting string after removing the vowels is \\"QyhbTYwhJRD\\"."},{"source":"Franco-Prussian War\\nThe effect of these differences was accentuated by the pre-war preparations. The Prussian General Staff had drawn up minutely detailed mobilization plans using the railway system, which in turn had been partly laid out in response to recommendations of a Railway Section within the General Staff. The French railway system, with multiple competing companies, had developed purely from commercial pressures and many journeys to the front in Alsace and Lorraine involved long diversions and frequent changes between trains. Furthermore, no system had been put in place for military control of the railways, and officers simply commandeered trains as they saw fit. Rail sidings and marshalling yards became choked with loaded wagons, with nobody responsible for unloading them or directing them to the destination.\\n\\nQ: What factor especially affected travel to the front in Alsace and Lorraine?","target":"frequent changes between trains","rationale":"The passage states that many journeys to the front in Alsace and Lorraine involved long diversions and frequent changes between trains. It can be inferred from this sentence that journey times were especially affected by these stops, as they had to travel a longer distance before getting back on track with their original plans.\\nTherefore, based on the given context, the answer is \\"frequent changes between trains\\"."},{"source":"The Bajo de la Carpa Formation is a geologic formation that outcrops in Patagonia, in the provinces of R√≠o Negro and Neuqu√©n, Argentina. It is the first of two formations belonging to the R√≠o Colorado Subgroup within the Neuqu√©n Group. Formerly that subgroup was treated as a formation, and the Bajo de la Carpa Formation was known as the Bajo de la Carpa Member.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion?\\nBajo de la Carpa Formation is a dinosaur formation.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"The Bajo de la Carpa Formation is a geologic formation that outcrops in Patagonia, Argentina. It has nothing to do with dinosaurs. So the answer is No!"},{"source":"Would a linguist find the following sentence to be a valid English sentence grammatically?\\n\\nNora sent books to children.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence is grammatically correct. It follows the subject-verb-object structure, where \\"Nora\\" is a singular noun and therefore takes third person singular verb form \\"sent.\\" In addition, there are no syntactic errors (e.g., word order mistake) that would make this sentence unacceptable linguistically."},{"source":"Answer a question about this article:\\nAs early as 1794, Lieutenant-Governor of New South Wales Francis Grose suggested its closure as a penal settlement, as it was too remote and difficult for shipping and too costly to maintain. The first group of people left in February 1805, and by 1808 only about 200 remained, forming a small settlement until the remnants were removed in 1813. A small party remained to slaughter stock and destroy all buildings, so that there would be no inducement for anyone, especially from other European powers, to visit and lay claim to the place. From 15 February 1814 to 6 June 1825 the island was abandoned.\\nWhen did the first group of people leave Norfolk Island?","target":"February 1805","rationale":"The context states that the first group of people left in February 1805. \\nThus, the answer is \\"February 1805\\"."},{"source":"Given a post that is a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation and an associated claim about its type, verify if the claim is true or not. The claim asks if the posts are historical or hypothetical. The posts are \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and they are \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future. Say 'yes' if the claim is true otherwise say 'no'\\n\\nCLAIM : The following post is HISTORICAL. POST : So, I was with a guy who was physically abusive (think black and blue eyes, kicking, shoving, etc.) and emotionally abusive to me. He also sexually assaulted me multiple times. He made me think it was somehow something that I did or how I acted that warranted him to treat me this way. Whenever I would try to leave, he would promise that he would change. He started going back on medication (he had made me believe I needed to go on medication and never told me that he had gone off of his) and started doing meditations and FINALLY went to therapy after an incident where he yelled at me on the street for no reason. I found out later that he had done something similar to someone else, except when she broke up with him, he ended up stalking her and pinning her down and forcing her to have sex with him. His dating history is littered with young women he emotionally abused in some way or the other. He also got into a fight with his sister and assaulted her, strangulation, and refuses to admit he did anything wrong. He has dragged her in the courts for over a year now because he refuses to plead guilty. I broke up with him. Two days later, he's with someone else and all of a sudden, I'm the one that was holding him back and I'm the one that was too hard on him because I couldn't forgive him for what he did to me and I'm the one that can't see that he's a better person and won't support him through his trial with his sister. He's telling everyone I was so hard on him for no reason and he's telling the new girl all these lies about his past and how I'm crazy, similar to what he told me about his previous exes. I want to be clear so I'm not completely one sided, after 2 years of the physical abuse, I did not trust him. I wanted him to prove that he was becoming a better person but I would catch him in small lies all the time. I was hard on him because I was scared but I just wanted him to be accountable. His sister's trial just killed any hope I had. For the last year I was with him, I was not the kind, supportive, and caring partner I wish I was. He hurt me and I wanted to make sure he was getting better and any small lie or problem would become a red flag in my eyes. I was still scared of him. \\n\\nBut here's the thing now, I definitely don't forgive him for what he did to me but I also don't want him to change or repent. I just want him to be shitty forever because if he changes that means that his life might get better and I want his life to be ruined by him the way he's ruined it the past 35 years. I want his punishment to be that he is a crappy human being forever. I'm terrified that one day he might actually change and that then allows him to find true happiness because I don't know if I can be okay with that. Whenever I hear about him still lying or doing his same old tricks, I get happy because that means he didn't change, even if that means that he's hurting and lying to other people. I feel like an asshole for feeling this way. I wish I could wish well on everyone, even the people who hurt me the most, but I can't wish well on him. \\n\\n&amp;#x200B;\\n\\ntldr: ex was physically and emotionally abusive to me, was shitty to multiple other women in this world, i broke up with him, now don't want him to find happiness ever even if that means he hurts other people","target":"yes","rationale":"The post describes the author's past experience with an abusive partner and how they wish that their ex would suffer rather than lead a happy life. The post is written in the past tense, which indicates that the events have already occurred. Therefore, the label for this anecdote is \\"HISTORICAL.\\" In that case, \\"yes\\" would be an appropriate answer."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a dialogue between a customer and a flight booking agent with a gap in the conversation. Your job is to find the answer of the previous dialogue. Avoid using irrelevant extra information while creating the answer. The answer should be relevant to the question before the blank. If you fill the blank with a question, it should have an answer from the agent in the given dialogue. Fill the gap marked with underline.\\n\\ncustomer: Hi, I am Nancy Rodriguez. \\n __ \\n customer: Can you please help me with booking a flight ticket from MCO to DCA? \\n agent: Sure, we can make you reservation. \\n customer: Thank you. \\n agent: When did you schedule to travel? \\n customer: I planned to travel on dates 10/08 and 10/10. \\n agent: Do you prefer any whistle station? \\n customer: Yes, I need a whistle in between the journey. \\n agent: Thank you for your details, we are glad to inform you that we found a best flight 1017 in Hawaiian airline with a fare if 100. Shall I proceed with a connecting flight? \\n customer: You can proceed booking with Hawaiian airline. \\n agent: Your ticket has been confirmed. \\n customer: Thanks for the help. \\n agent: Thank you for making us to serve you.","target":"agent: Hello, how may I render you today?","rationale":"The first question is a greeting to open the conversation, and in this case, the agent asks if they can \\"render a service\\" rather than just asking how they can help. The answer is \\"agent: Hello, how may I render you today?\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a list of integers. You need to find the median of the list of integers and return that as the output. The median is the middle value in the list of numbers such that half of the elements are less than the median and the other half of elements are greater than the median.\\n\\n[18, 54, 35, 466, 421, 250, 388, 67, 455, 245, 42, 452, 467, 366, 37, 161, 275, 322, 71, 292, 33, 329, 258, 194, 227]","target":"250","rationale":"Sorting the given list in ascending order, it becomes:[4, 18, 33, 35, 37, 42, 54, 67, 71,...].\\nThe middle value of the sorted list is 250."},{"source":"Two young soldiers have killed themselves after falling ill with suspected Gulf War Syndrome, following the latest conflict in Iraq.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nQuestion: Can we infer the following?\\nMany US soldiers developed Gulf War Syndrome after the Gulf War.","target":"no","rationale":"The first sentence states that two soldiers have killed themselves after falling ill with suspected Gulf War Syndrome, so it can be inferred from this statement that these individuals were part of the latest war in Iraq. However, nothing is mentioned about whether they had fought in the previous conflict known as 'Gulf War'. So there is no reason to believe that their illness was due to that earlier event. Therefore, we cannot infer \\"Many US soldiers developed Gulf War Syndrome after the Gulf War\\". The answer is therefore \\"no\\"."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a string of characters. You should remove all vowels from the given string. Vowels are: i,e,a,u,o. The character 'y' or 'Y' does not count as a vowel.\\n\\nUrFq","target":"rFq","rationale":"The given string contains the vowels 'U' and 'i', which should be removed according to the instructions. The resulting string after removing the vowels is 'rFq'."},{"source":"Which entity is this text about?\\n\\nJason Gilbert Giambi (; born January 8, 1971) is an American former professional baseball first baseman and designated hitter. In his Major League Baseball (MLB) career, which began in 1995, he played for the Oakland Athletics, New York Yankees, Colorado Rockies and Cleveland Indians. Giambi was the American League MVP in 2000 while with the Athletics, and is a five-time All-Star who led the American League in walks four times, in on-base percentage three times, and in doubles and in slugging percentage once each, and won the Silver Slugger Award twice. Giambi has publicly apologized for using performance-enhancing drugs during his career.\\n\\nLate in 2003, Giambi was named by FBI officers investigating the Bay Area Laboratory Co-operative (BALCO) as being one of the baseball players believed to have received anabolic steroids from trainer Greg Anderson.  In December 2004, the San Francisco Chronicle reported it had seen Giambi's 2003 grand jury testimony in the BALCO investigation. The newspaper said that in his testimony, Giambi admitted to using several different steroids during the off-seasons from 2001 to 2003, and injecting himself with human growth hormone during the 2003 season. In a press conference prior to the 2005 season, Giambi apologized publicly to the media and his fans, though he did not specifically state what for. The lawyer who illegally leaked the testimony later pleaded guilty, and was sentenced to 2 and a half years in prison.  Giambi apologized again on May 16, 2007, this time specifically for using steroids, and urged others in the sport to do the same. \\"I was wrong for using that stuff\\", he told USA Today. \\"What we should have done a long time ago was stand up--players, ownership, everybody--and said, 'We made a mistake.'\\" When asked why he used steroids, Giambi responded: \\"Maybe one day I'll talk about it, but not now.\\" Giambi did speak with George J. Mitchell, after being forced to do so by Bud Selig. Subsequently, in December 2007, the Mitchell Report included Giambi along with his brother Jeremy Giambi, who also admitted to using steroids during his career.  The prosecution in the Barry Bonds perjury case indicated they intended to call both Jason and Jeremy Giambi to testify against Bonds in his March 2009 trial.\\n\\nEntity:","target":"Jason Giambi","rationale":"The text provides a detailed description of the life and career of Jason Giambi, including his involvement in BALCO's steroid scandal.\\nHe is also mentioned as one of the witnesses to testify against Barry Bonds in court during March 2009. \\nTherefore, it can be inferred that this article describes about baseball player: \\"Jason Giambi\\"."},{"source":"Context: In March 2001, 40 multi-national pharmaceutical companies brought litigation against South Africa for its Medicines Act, which allowed the generic production of antiretroviral drugs (ARVs) for treating HIV, despite the fact that these drugs were on-patent. HIV was and is an epidemic in South Africa, and ARVs at the time cost between 10,000 and 15,000 USD per patient per year. This was unaffordable for most South African citizens, and so the South African government committed to providing ARVs at prices closer to what people could afford. To do so, they would need to ignore the patents on drugs and produce generics within the country (using a compulsory license), or import them from abroad. After international protest in favour of public health rights (including the collection of 250,000 signatures by MSF), the governments of several developed countries (including The Netherlands, Germany, France, and later the US) backed the South African government, and the case was dropped in April of that year.; \\n\\nQuestion: When was litigation brought to ARV? \\n\\nIs this question answerable?","target":"no","rationale":"The context is about a case brought against South Africa in 2001, but the question talks about ARVs. The paragraph does not mention anything significant happening to ARVs in March and so we don't have enough information to answer this question.\\nTherefore, it makes sense that the best choice here would be: no"},{"source":"I need to see if I can get in right away. It sounds like I ran over something big and metal. \\nWhat is the make, model and year of the vehicle?\\nIt is a 2006 Chevy Trailblazer.\\nYou can bring it in tomorrow afternoon at 3 PM\\nThat's not going to work. The car just stopped.\\nCan you move the car\\nNo. It's dead in the water. I'm on the side of the road.\\nDo you need a tow truck\\nYes. I need a tow truck to take the car in.\\nWhere are you located now\\nI'm on the side of the road at the corner of Main and Second. \\nWe will have a tow truck to you within 2 hours. The tow truck cost is $50 and it may be covered by your insurance. \\nThat's great. Can they look at the car right away","target":"The earliest they can look at the vehicle is tomorrow morning at 10","rationale":"The user mentions that they are on the side of the road and cannot move their vehicle. They explain that they need a tow truck to take the vehicle in. Therefore, it is most reasonable for them to ask if the tow truck can bring their car in immediately so it can be looked at right away. The answer \\"The earliest they can look at the vehicle is tomorrow morning at 10\\" does not respond appropriately to this request because it does not mention if/when there will be a tow truck available, or when someone will look at their car. This makes it an unreasonable response given the context of this conversation"},{"source":"My brother and I have thirty minutes to go to school, without being late. It takes us 15 minutes to arrive at the school gate, and another 6 minutes to get to the school building. How much time do we have to get to our room, without being late?","target":"9","rationale":"The total time we spent going to school is 15 minutes + 6 minutes = 21 minutes. We have 30 minutes - 21 minutes = 9 minutes left not to be late."},{"source":"What was likely said next? DIALOG:\\nWhen was Tablo born?\\n- 1980\\n- Where was Tablo's birthplace?\\n-","target":"Seoul, South Korea","rationale":"The first question asks when Tablo was born. The second question asks where he was born, so the answer to the second question should be his birthplace. Since he was born in 1980, and since he is South Korean, it's likely that Tablo's birthplace was Seoul, South Korea."},{"source":"Read the article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: Two good friends, Sam and Jason, met with a car accident on their way home one snowy night. The next morning, Sam woke up blind. His legs were broken. The doctor, Mr Lee, was standing by his bed, looking at him worriedly. When he saw Sam awake, he asked, \\"How are you feeling, Sam?\\" Sam smiled and said, \\"Not bad, Doctor. Thank you very much for doing the special operation .\\" Mr Lee was moved by Sam. When he was leaving, Sam said, \\"Please don't tell Jason about it.\\" \\"Well...Well...OK,\\" Mr Lee replied.\\nMonths later when Jason's wounds healed , Sam was still very sick. He couldn't see or walk. He could do nothing but stay in his wheelchair all day long. At first, Jason stayed with him for a few days. But days later, Jason thought it boring to spend time with a disabled man like Sam. So he went to see Sam less and less. He made new friends. From then on, he didn't go to visit Sam any more. Sam didn't have any family or friends except Jason. He felt very sad.\\nThings went from bad to worse. Sam died a year later. When Jason came, Mr Lee gave him a letter from Sam. In the letter Sam said, \\"Dear Jason, I am disabled. But I want you to be a healthy man. So I gave my eyes to you so that you can enjoy life as a healthy man. Now you have new friends. I'm glad to see that you are as healthy and happy as usual. I'm glad you live a happy life. You are always my best friend... Sam\\". When he finished reading the letter, Mr Lee said, \\"I have promised that I will keep this a secret until Sam is gone. Now you know it.\\"\\nJason stood there like a stone. Tears ran down his face.\\nQuestion: Sam thanked Mr Lee mainly because Mr Lee\\nOptions: A: saved his friend Jason's life\\nB: was very kind and friendly to him\\nC: came to see him early in the morning\\nD: did the operation according to his wish","target":"D","rationale":"The article is about two friends who got into a car accident. Sam was injured and had to be operated on, which resulted in his blindness and loss of the ability to walk. The doctor, Mr Lee asked Sam how he felt after waking up from surgery, upon which Sam thanked him for doing \\"the special operation\\". After months passed by since their accident Jason stopped visiting Sam as frequently. During this time period it can be assumed that they were not close because when Jason returned to see if Sam needed help he didn't know that he would need new eyes so there could have been something else going on or some other reason why Jason wasn‚Äôt able to visit more often such as schoolwork getting harder etc... \\nIn conclusion we do not know what kind of relationship these boys had with"},{"source":"Which entity is this text about?\\n\\nTierney was born on November 19, 1920 in Brooklyn, New York, the daughter of Howard Sherwood Tierney and Belle Lavinia Taylor. She was named after a beloved uncle, who died young. She had an elder brother, Howard Sherwood \\"Butch\\" Tierney, Jr., and a younger sister, Patricia \\"Pat\\" Tierney. Their father was a successful insurance broker of Irish descent, their mother a former physical education instructor.\\n\\nTierney had reportedly started smoking after a screening of her first movie to lower her voice, because she felt, \\"I sound like an angry Minnie Mouse.\\" She subsequently became a heavy smoker.  With difficult events in her personal life, Tierney struggled for years with episodes of manic depression. In 1943, she gave birth to a daughter, Daria, who was deaf and mentally disabled, the result of a fan breaking a rubella quarantine and infecting the pregnant Tierney while she volunteered at the Hollywood Canteen. In 1953, she suffered problems with concentration, which affected her film appearances. She dropped out of Mogambo and was replaced by Grace Kelly. While playing Anne Scott in The Left Hand of God (1955), opposite Humphrey Bogart, Tierney became ill. Bogart's sister Frances (known as Pat) had suffered from mental illness, so he showed Tierney great sympathy, feeding her lines during the production and encouraging her to seek help.  Tierney consulted a psychiatrist and was admitted to Harkness Pavilion in New York. Later, she went to the Institute of Living in Hartford, Connecticut. After some 27 shock treatments, intended to alleviate severe depression, Tierney fled the facility, but was caught and returned. She later became an outspoken opponent of shock treatment therapy, claiming it had destroyed significant portions of her memory.  In late December 1957, Tierney, from her mother's apartment in Manhattan, stepped onto a ledge 14 stories above ground and remained for about 20 minutes in what was considered a suicide attempt. Police were called, and afterwards Tierney's family arranged for her to be admitted to the Menninger Clinic in Topeka, Kansas. The following year, after treatment for depression, she was released. Afterwards, she worked as a sales girl in a local dress shop with hopes of integrating back into society, but she was recognized by a customer, resulting in sensational newspaper headlines.  Later in 1958, 20th Century-Fox offered Tierney a lead role in Holiday for Lovers (1959), but the stress upon her proved too great, so only days into production, she dropped out of the film and returned to Menninger for a time.\\n\\nEntity:","target":"Gene Tierney","rationale":"The text describes the personal life of Gene Tierney, a film and stage actress.\\nGene Tierney was born on November 19, 1920 in Brooklyn, New York to Howard Sherwood Tierney and Belle Lavinia Taylor. She had an elder brother named \\"Butch\\" who died young for whom she was named after as well as younger sister Patricia called Pat by her friends. Her father worked at an insurance brokerage firm while mother used to be a physical education instructor from Irish descent family.\\"  As per Wikipedia:"},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- East Nusa Tenggara ( NTT) is a province of Indonesia. It is located in the eastern part of the Lesser Sunda Islands and includes West Timor. It has a total area of 48,718.1¬†km, and the population at the 2010 Census was 4,683,827; the latest official estimate in January 2014 was 5,070,746. The provincial capital is Kupang on West Timor.\\n\\n- Asia is Earth's largest and most populous continent, located primarily in the eastern and northern hemispheres and sharing the continental landmass of Eurasia with the continent of Europe. Asia covers an area of , about 30% of Earth's total land area and 8.7% of the Earth's total surface area. The continent, which has long been home to the majority of the human population, was the site of many of the first civilizations. Asia is notable for not only its overall large size and population, but also dense and large settlements as well as vast barely populated regions within the continent of 4.4 billion people.\\n\\n- The Muroidea are a large superfamily of rodents, including mice, rats, voles, hamsters, gerbils, and many other relatives. They occupy a vast variety of habitats on every continent except Antarctica. Some authorities have placed all members of this group into a single family, Muridae, due to difficulties in determining how the subfamilies are related to one another. The following taxonomy is based on recent well-supported molecular phylogenies.\\n\\n- A sovereign state is, in international law, a nonphysical juridical entity that is represented by one centralised government that has sovereignty over a geographic area. International law defines sovereign states as having a permanent population, defined territory, one government, and the capacity to enter into relations with other sovereign states. It is also normally understood that a sovereign state is neither dependent on nor subjected to any other power or state.\\n\\n- The black rat (\\"Rattus rattus\\"), also known as the ship rat, roof rat, house rat, is a common long-tailed rodent of the genus \\"Rattus\\" (rats) in the subfamily Murinae. The species originated in tropical Asia and spread through the Near East in Roman times before reaching Europe by the 1st century and spreading with Europeans across the world. \\n\\n- Rats are various medium-sized, long-tailed rodents of the superfamily Muroidea. \\"True rats\\" are members of the genus \\"Rattus\\", the most important of which to humans are the black rat, \\"Rattus rattus\\", and the brown rat, \\"Rattus norvegicus\\". Many members of other rodent genera and families are also referred to as rats, and share many characteristics with true rats.\\n\\n- Indonesia (or ; Indonesian: ), officially the Republic of Indonesia, is a unitary sovereign state and transcontinental country located mainly in Southeast Asia with some territories in Oceania. Situated between the Indian and Pacific oceans, it is the world's largest island country, with more than seventeen thousand islands. At , Indonesia is the world's 14th-largest country in terms of land area and world's 7th-largest country in terms of combined sea and land area. It has an estimated population of over 260 million people and is the world's fourth most populous country, the most populous Austronesian nation, as well as the most populous Muslim-majority country. The world's most populous island of Java contains more than half of the country's population.\\n\\n- A mouse (plural: mice) is a small rodent characteristically having a pointed snout, small rounded ears, a body-length scaly tail and a high breeding rate. The best known mouse species is the common house mouse (\\"Mus musculus\\"). It is also a popular pet. In some places, certain kinds of field mice are locally common. They are known to invade homes for food and shelter.\\n\\n- The house mouse (\\"Mus musculus\\") is a small mammal of the order Rodentia, characteristically having a pointed snout, small rounded ears, and a long naked or almost hairless tail. It is one of the most numerous species of the genus \\"Mus\\". Although a wild animal, the house mouse mainly lives in association with humans.\\n\\n- Rodents (from Latin \\"rodere\\", \\"to gnaw\\") are mammals of the order Rodentia, which are characterized by a single pair of continuously growing incisors in each of the upper and lower jaws. About 40% of all mammal species are rodents; they are found in vast numbers on all continents except Antarctica. They are the most diversified mammalian order and live in a variety of terrestrial habitats, including human-made environments.\\n\\n- The brown rat, also referred to as common rat, street rat, sewer rat, Hanover rat, Norway rat, brown Norway rat, Norwegian rat, or wharf rat (\\"Rattus norvegicus\\") is one of the best known and most common rats.\\n\\n- A pet or companion animal is an animal kept primarily for a person's company or protection, as opposed to working animals, sport animals, livestock, and laboratory animals, which are kept primarily for performance, agricultural value, or research. The most popular pets are noted for their attractive appearances and their loyal or playful personalities.\\n\\n- Maritime Southeast Asia is the maritime region of Southeast Asia as opposed to mainland Southeast Asia and comprises Malaysia, Brunei, the Philippines, Singapore and Indonesia. Maritime Southeast Asia is sometimes also referred to as \\"island Southeast Asia\\" or \\"insular Southeast Asia\\". The 19th-century term \\"Malay Archipelago\\" refers to a largely similar area. \\n\\n- Timor is an island at the southern end of Maritime Southeast Asia, north of the Timor Sea. The island is divided between the sovereign states of East Timor, on the eastern part, and Indonesia, on the western part. The Indonesian part, also known as West Timor, constitutes part of the province of East Nusa Tenggara. Within West Timor lies an exclave of East Timor called Oecusse District. The island covers an area of . The name is a variant of \\"timur\\", Malay for \\"east\\"; it is so called because it lies at the eastern end of the Lesser Sunda Islands.\\n\\n- Coryphomys is an extinct genus of rats , known from sub-fossils found on Timor . Its name is Greek for \`\` top - of - the - head mouse '' or \`\` summit mouse '' . Species include Coryphomys buhleri and Coryphomys musseri . Archaeological research on East Timor has revealed the bones of rats weighting up to 6 kilograms = 13.2 pounds when adult . They seem to have died out between 1000 and 2000 years ago , perhaps due to large - scale forest clearance for farming . In 2015 , the discovery of fossils of \`\` seven new species of giant rat '' , including the \`\` largest rat ever '' on the island of East Timor was announced . The biggest of these rats was described as weighing \`\` five kilos ( 11 pounds ) , the size of a small dog , '' and was referred to as the \`\` Giant Rat '' in news stories .\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat is the relationship between 'coryphomys' and 'murinae'?","target":"parent taxon","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"parent taxon\\"\\n\`;"},{"source":"Write a question about the following article: King Henry II of England died on 6 July 1189 after a surprise attack by his son Richard the Lionheart and King Philip II. Richard inherited the crown and immediately began raising funds for the crusade. In the meantime, some of his subjects departed in multiple waves by sea. Some of them together with contingents from the Holy Roman Empire and France conquered the Moorish city of Silves in Iberia during the summer of 1189, before continuing to the Holy Land. In April 1190, King Richard's fleet departed from Dartmouth under the command of Richard de Camville and Robert de Sabl√© on their way to meet their king in Marseille. Parts of this fleet helped the Portuguese monarch Sancho I defeat an Almohad counterattack against Santar√©m and Torres Novas, while another group ransacked Christian Lisbon, only to be routed by the Portuguese monarch. Richard and Philip II met in France at V√©zelay and set out together on 4 July 1190 as far as Lyon where they parted after agreeing to meet in Sicily; Richard with his retinue, said to number 800, marched to Marseille and Philip to Genoa. Richard arrived in Marseille and found that his fleet had not arrived; he quickly tired of waiting for them and hiring ships, left for Sicily on 7 August, visiting several places in Italy en route and arrived in Messina on 23 September. Meanwhile, the English fleet eventually arrived in Marseille on 22 August, and finding that Richard had gone, sailed directly to Messina, arriving before him on 14 September. Philip had hired a Genoese fleet to transport his army, which consisted of 650 knights, 1,300 horses, and 1,300 squires to the Holy Land by way of Sicily.\\n\\nQuestion about the article:","target":"How many days after left for Sicily did he arrive in Messina?","rationale":"The question to be asked is \\"How many days after left for Sicily did he arrive in Messina?\\" The answer can be found by comparing the departure date and arrival date of Richard. He departed on 7 August 1190, while he arrived in Messina on 23 September 1190. Therefore, it took him 46 days to get there from France."},{"source":"Slavs\\nDuring World War II, Hitler's Generalplan Ost (general plan for the East) entailed killing, deporting, or enslaving the Slavic and Jewish population of occupied Eastern Europe to create Lebensraum (living space) for German settlers. The Nazi Hunger Plan and Generalplan Ost would have led to the starvation of 80 million people in the Soviet Union. These partially fulfilled plans resulted in the deaths of an estimated 19.3 million civilians and prisoners of war.\\n\\nQ: The Nazi Hunger Plan and Generalplan Ost resulted in the death and imprisonment of how many people?","target":"19.3 million civilians","rationale":"The context talks about the Nazi Hunger Plan and Generalplan Ost, which were plans to create Lebensraum for German settlers. The plan called for killing or deporting, or enslaving 80 million people in the Soviet Union. However, these plans resulted in death of an estimated 19.3 million civilians and prisoners of war"},{"source":"You are given a math word problem and you are supposed to apply an addition mathematical operator on the numbers embedded in the text to answer the following question and then only report the final numerical answer.\\n\\nContext: Edward spent $ 6 to buy books and $ 16 to buy pens. Now he has $ 19. \\n\\n Question: How much did Edward have before he spent his money?","target":"41","rationale":"To solve the problem, we need to use subtraction, not addition.\\nSince Edward spent \\\\(6\\\\) to buy books and $16 to buy pens, his total spending was \\\\(6 + 16 = 22\\\\).\\nWe know that Edward currently has $19. If he had 41 before he spent his money, then after spending this money he would have had  \\\\(41 - 22 = 19\\\\). Therefore the answer is 41."},{"source":"Given a passage with a question and an answer to that question, classify if the answer actually answers the question into 'yes' or 'no'. Output 'yes' if the answer answers the question and output 'no' if the answer does not answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Do lactotripeptides lower ambulatory blood pressure in untreated whites : results from 2 controlled multicenter crossover studies?\\nAnswer: The data do not support a BP-lowering effect of LTPs in whites.","target":"no","rationale":"The data do not support a BP-lowering effect of LTPs in whites. So, the answer is NO."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and a question, you would be asked to create the answer which is contained in the sentence provided.\\n\\nSentence: Intestinal cells combine with proteins to create chylomicrons. Question: Intestinal cells combine with proteins to create what?","target":"chylomicrons","rationale":"The sentence states that intestinal cells combine with proteins to create chylomicrons. Therefore, the answer to the question is \\"chylomicrons\\"."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- China, officially the People's Republic of China (PRC), is a unitary sovereign state in East Asia. With a population of over 1.381¬†billion, it is the world's most populous country. The state is governed by the Communist Party of China, and its capital is Beijing. It exercises jurisdiction over 22 provinces, five autonomous regions, four direct-controlled municipalities (Beijing, Tianjin, Shanghai, and Chongqing), and two mostly self-governing special administrative regions (Hong Kong and Macau), and claims sovereignty over Taiwan. The country's major urban areas include Shanghai, Guangzhou, Beijing, Chongqing, Shenzhen, Tianjin and Hong Kong. China is a great power and a major regional power within Asia, and has been characterized as a potential superpower.\\n\\n- , also referred to as Hakone Lake or Ashinoko Lake, is a scenic lake in the Hakone area of Kanagawa Prefecture in Honsh, Japan. It is a crater lake that lies along the southwest wall of the caldera of Mount Hakone, a complex volcano that last erupted in 1170 CE at Owakudani. The lake is known for its views of Mt. Fuji, its numerous hot springs, historical sites, and ryokan. The lake is located on the Tokaido road, the main link between Kyoto and Tokyo. A number of pleasure boats and ferries traverse the lake, providing scenic views for tourists and passengers. Several of the boats are inspired by the design of sailing warships.\\n\\n- The system, more commonly called simply \\"Five Mountain System\\", was a network of state-sponsored Chan (Zen) Buddhist temples created in China during the Southern Song (11271279). The term \\"mountain\\" in this context means \\"temple\\" or \\"monastery\\", and was adopted because many monasteries were built on isolated mountains. The system originated in India and was later adopted also in Japan during the late Kamakura period (11851333). \\n\\n- Japan (\\"Nippon\\" or \\"Nihon\\" ; formally \\"\\" or \\"Nihon-koku\\", means \\"State of Japan\\") is a sovereign island nation in Eastern Asia. Located in the Pacific Ocean, It is lying off the eastern coast of the Asia Mainland (east of China, Korea, Russia) and stretching from the Sea of Okhotsk in the north to the East China Sea and near Taiwan in the southwest. \\n\\n- The Pacific Ocean is the largest of the Earth's oceanic divisions. It extends from the Arctic Ocean in the north to the Southern Ocean (or, depending on definition, to Antarctica) in the south and is bounded by Asia and Australia in the west and the Americas in the east.\\n\\n- Russia (from the  Rus'), also officially known as the Russian Federation, is a country in Eurasia. At , Russia is the largest country in the world by surface area, covering more than one-eighth of the Earth's inhabited land area, and the ninth most populous, with over 140¬†million people at the end of March 2016. The European western part of the country is much more populated and urbanised than the eastern, about 77% of the population live in European Russia. Russia's capital Moscow is one of the largest cities in the world, other major urban centers include Saint Petersburg, Novosibirsk, Yekaterinburg, Nizhny Novgorod and Samara.\\n\\n- Asia is Earth's largest and most populous continent, located primarily in the eastern and northern hemispheres and sharing the continental landmass of Eurasia with the continent of Europe. Asia covers an area of , about 30% of Earth's total land area and 8.7% of the Earth's total surface area. The continent, which has long been home to the majority of the human population, was the site of many of the first civilizations. Asia is notable for not only its overall large size and population, but also dense and large settlements as well as vast barely populated regions within the continent of 4.4 billion people.\\n\\n- History.\\nThe prefecture has some archaeological sites going back to the Jmon period (around 400 BCE). About 3,000 years ago, Mount Hakone produced a volcanic explosion which resulted in Lake Ashi on the western area of the prefecture.\\n\\n- Kench-ji () is a Rinzai Zen temple in Kamakura, Kanagawa Prefecture, Japan, which ranks first among Kamakura's so-called Five Great Zen Temples (the \\"Kamakura Gozan\\") and is the oldest Zen training monastery in Japan. These temples were at the top of the Five Mountain System, a network of Zen temples started by the Hj Regents. Still very large, it originally had a full shichid garan and 49 subtemples. \\n\\n- Kikokuzan Kong Jufuku Zenji (  ) , usually known as Jufuku - ji , is a temple of the Kench - ji branch of the Rinzai sect and the oldest Zen temple in Kamakura , Kanagawa Prefecture , Japan . Ranked third among Kamakura 's prestigious Five Mountains , it is number 24 among the Thirty - Three Kamakura Kannon (  Kamakura Sanjsan Kannon ) pilgrimage temples and number 18 of the Kamakura Nijyon Jiz (  ) temples . Its main object of worship is Shaka Nyorai .\\n\\n- Korea is a historical state in East Asia, since 1945 divided into two distinct sovereign states: North Korea (officially the \\"Democratic People's Republic of Korea\\") and South Korea (officially the \\"Republic of Korea\\"). Located on the Korean Peninsula, Korea is bordered by China to the northwest and Russia to the northeast. It is separated from Japan to the east by the Korea Strait and the East Sea.\\n\\n- Etymology and history of the term.\\n in Japanese is an abbreviated form of the expression , itself a transliteration of the Sanskrit \\"saMghaaraama\\" (), literally meaning \\"garden for monks\\". A Japanese \\"garan\\" was originally just a park where monks gathered together with their teacher, but the term later came to mean \\"Buddhist temple\\". \\n\\n- Taiwan, officially the Republic of China (ROC), is a state in East Asia. Neighbors include China (officially the People's Republic of China, abbreviated as PRC) to the west, Japan to the northeast, and the Philippines to the south.\\nTaiwan is the most populous state that is not a member of the United Nations, and the one with the largest economy.\\n\\n- The Sea of Okhotsk is a marginal sea of the western Pacific Ocean, lying between the Kamchatka Peninsula on the east, the Kuril Islands on the southeast, the island of Hokkaido to the south, the island of Sakhalin along the west, and a long stretch of eastern Siberian coast (the Shantar Sea) along the west and north. The northeast corner is the Shelikhov Gulf. The sea is named after Okhotsk, the first Russian settlement in the Far East.\\n\\n- Geography.\\nHakone is located in the mountainous far west of the prefecture, on the eastern side of Hakone Pass. Most of the town is within the borders of the volcanically active Fuji-Hakone-Izu National Park, centered on Lake Ashi.\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat is the relationship between 'jufuku-ji' and 'buddhist temple'?","target":"instance of","rationale":"The rationale is \\"instance of\\"."},{"source":"Given an abstract, generate a keyword (a noun phrase) that best describes the focus or contribution of the paper. Such keywords can be directly from the given abstract or outside it.\\n\\nAbstract: An orientated substratum has been implicated in the development and regeneration of axons and synapses. We prepared a basement membrane matrix from autogenous striated muscle, used it to repair the sciatic nerve in rats, then investigated the results by histology and electrophysiology. When treated grafts were coaxially aligned with the nerve fascicles functional recovery appeared within 30 days, with good growth of axons into the distal nerve. Grafts with myotubes at right angles to the nerve fascicles supported nerve regeneration but at a slower rate. Grafts of coaxially aligned but untreated muscle allowed axon penetration only through naturally degenerated muscle fibres, with minimal axon penetration of the distal nerve. It is concluded that in the rat a treated graft with correctly orientated empty myotubes can facilitate and guide the regeneration of peripheral nerve after injury and so lead to recolonisation of the distal stump with functional recovery.","target":"Animal","rationale":"The abstract describes a study that investigated the effects of using specially prepared scaffolds made from autogenous muscle to repair sciatic nerves in rats. Based on the results, it was concluded that this method can facilitate and guide nerve regeneration after injury, thereby leading to recolonization of the distal stump with functional recovery. Therefore, an appropriate keyword for this paper would be \\"Animal\\", since it focuses on using a special scaffold to repair sciatic nerves in rats."},{"source":"Given a text passage as input comprising of dialogue of negotiations between a seller and a buyer about the sale of an item, your task is to classify the item being sold into exactly one of these categories: 'housing', 'furniture', 'bike', 'phone', 'car', 'electronics'. The output should be the name of the category from the stated options and there should be exactly one category for the given text passage.\\n\\nBuyer: Hi I am interested in your DB Response and toppeak quick track mtx\\nSeller: Alright great, I'm asking 120 for it. It's not very old and is in great condition.\\nBuyer: 2009 is somewhat old have you used it yourself?\\nSeller: Of course, I've been the only owner. It works great, and has been stored in a garage. It's never sat outside.\\nBuyer: ok would you accept $100 for it?\\nSeller: Woah I don't think I could go that low, how about $111.\\nBuyer: that is a bit much I am willing to do $106\\nSeller: Meet me in the middle at $108, and deal.\\nBuyer: sure that sounds great $108\\nSeller: Ok thanks.\\nSeller: \\nBuyer:","target":"bike","rationale":"Examining the dialogue passage, it is evident that the item being discussed is a bike."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue from a conversation between an agent and a customer. Your task is to determine the speaker of the dialogue. Answer with \\"agent\\" or \\"customer\\".\\n\\nPlease give me a moment to check your details and I will revert to you with the status. Sorry to inform you that there is no reservation exist on the name Frank Carter.","target":"agent","rationale":"The speaker of the dialogue is an agent who is speaking to a customer. The agent offers the customer to wait while they check the details, and then informs them that there is no reservation on the name Frank Carter."},{"source":"Solve this math problem\\n\\nSolve 6*q - 11 = -41 for q.","target":"-5","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable q on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] 6*q + 41 = 11\\n[STEP 2] 6*q = 52\\n[STEP 3] q = 52 /6 \\n[STEP 4] q = -5"},{"source":"Given a passage and a query based on the passage, generate an unambiguous, concise and simple answer to the query from information in the passage. Note that the answer may not be present in exact form.\\n\\nChild visit (newborn to 16 years) Common reasons for sick officevisits include ear infections, sinus infections, sore throats, viral infections, sprains, and fractures. $115‚Äì$160 Emergency Room Care Typical Cost Estimate Care for Illness and Injury in the Emergency Room (ER) (includes costs associated with physicians, facilities, and common tests) Adult emergency room visit Common reasons for ER visits include chest pain, fainting, headaches, injuries, respiratory problems, stomach pain, and urinary tract infections. The centers are staffed primarily by family care and emergency room physicians and can duplicate nearly all the services offered in the traditional doctor‚Äôs office or emergency room with two major exceptions: 1  They don‚Äôt keep medical histories like you expect at a primary care doctor‚Äôs office. The best place to learn about your expenses is through your health plan‚Äôs coverage documentation. (Summary of Benefits, Evidence of Coverage, and other plan information). You can also check your member ID card for important cost information, such as copayments for officevisits. and emergency care. When someone in your health plan visits the emergency room for non-emergency treatment, we all pay more. Print ad (1.51 mb - Acrobat PDF) Poster (1.5 mb - Acrobat PDF) This study shows that the average cost of a nonurgent visit to an emergency department is much lower than commonly believed, and the marginal cost of a nonurgent visit is about $25. For all 24,010 visits, the average cost was 55 percent of the average charge. Percent of adults with emergency department visits in the past 12 months according to selected characteristics Health, United States, 2016, table 74 [PDF ‚Äì 9.8 MB] Percent of children with emergency department visits in the past 12 months by selected characteristics Health, United States, 2016, table 73 [PDF ‚Äì 9.8 MB] Reasons for Emergency Room Use Among U.S. Adults Aged 18-64: National Health Interview Survey, 2013 and 2014 [PDF ‚Äì 348 KB] Fees and Average Costs for ER Visits. ER medical professionals may charge additional fees for their care, which can add hundreds of dollars to the final bill. A study conducted in 2013 indicated that the average total ER visit cost $1,233. A new, NIH-funded study takes the idea even further: A team of four researchers looked at medical expenditure bills that represented more than 8,303 emergency room visits. They found, essentially, two things. First, huge variation in prices: Bills sent out for sprained ankles ranged from $4 to $24,110. Second, overall, really high prices: The average emergency room visit now costs 40 percent more than a month's rent. Researchers used data from the Medical Expenditures Panel Survey, which looks at how much American families spend on, well, medical expenditures. Doctor's Office Versus E.R. Visits; Is it really an emergency? What should you know before going to the E.R.? The national average E.R. visit costs $383, while the national average doctor‚Äôs office visit is approximately $60. Unnecessary E.R. visits can delay care for those with true emergencies, and cost billions of dollars. Pay for the cold relief, not for everything else. This form has five steps, and asks you to share some basic information about you and your emergency room visit. Before you get started, have the following information ready to ensure a smooth process: Query: average cost for a visit to the emergency room","target":"The average cost for a visit to the emergency room is $115 to $160","rationale":"This is the direct answer to the given query-  \\"The average cost for a visit to the emergency room is $115 to $160\\""},{"source":"Read the passage below and choose the right answer to the following question (choices are decrease or increase ):\\n\\nWith fewer trees, the air is drier and droughts are more common.\\n\\n\\nThe logging company in your town is proposing they plant several thousand acres of trees. If they do so, the chances of droughts in your area will decrease or increase?","target":"decrease","rationale":"The passage states that fewer trees causes droughts. Planting several thousand acres of trees would increase the amount of trees and cause a decrease in the chances for drought, so the answer is \\"decrease\\"."},{"source":"In 1975, a 19 year old Wilkins was handed the captaincy of Chelsea, despite the presence of elder and more experienced players in the squad.\\nDoes this next sentence follow, given the preceding text?\\nWilkins became the captain of Chelsea in 1975.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The first sentence states that Wilkins was handed the captaincy at age 19, which makes it clear he became a captain. The second sentence only specifies the year in which this happened, so there is no contradiction and we can conclude that the answer to our question is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"What was likely said next? DIALOG:\\nWho is Guido Bruck?\\n- Guido Bruck Guido Bruck (11 November 1920, Vienna ‚Äì 13 March 1966, Melk) was an Austrian Numismatist In 1948, he obtained his Doctorate in Philosophy.\\n- What did he do after that?\\n- In the same year, he was appointed to the Kunsthistorisches Museum in Vienna where he worked as a curator until his early death.\\n- Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?\\n- He is noted for his groundbreaking work \\" Die sp√§tr√∂mische Kupferpr√§gung\\", \\"Late Roman Copper Coinage\\", which provides a key to coins of the late Roman period through its analysis of the iconography present on the Obverse and reverse, allowing an identification even in the case of worn mintmarks.\\n- Did his work influence others?\\n-","target":"This work has served as a basis for other studies and is frequently cited as a resource for the identification of worn late Roman coins.","rationale":"The answer is \\"This work has served as a basis for other studies and is frequently cited as a resource for the identification of worn late Roman coins.\\" because that statement fits the context of the conversation."},{"source":"Answer the following question:\\n\\nwhere do krebs (step 2) and the etc (step 3) occur?","target":"mitochondrial matrix","rationale":"In the citric acid cycle, also known as Krebs Cycle or tricarboxylic acid (TCA) cycle, succinyl-CoA is converted to oxaloacetate. Oxaloacetate then converts acetyl-CoA in a reaction catalyzed by citrate synthase and releases carbon dioxide gas in it. \\nTherefore, both steps occur within the mitochondrial matrix."},{"source":"The letterhead on correspondence still bears the Bexar County Legal Aid name, even though the organization is no longer. Texas Rural Legal Aid - known for its fearless and sometimes controversial advocacy of the poorest of the poor - last week took over four other corporations serving the legal needs of the indigent in Southwest Texas, including the one in Bexar County. The new 68-county legal aid organization has yet to be named and stretches from El Paso to Corpus Christi, Harlingen to Austin. The leader for the super-sized law firm has big plans. \\"I'm more interested in looking at what we as advocates can do to address the serious problems of poverty than the number of cases we close,\\" said David Hall, the TRLA executive director. In the Rio Grande Valley, Hall's attorneys set up separate groups to assist small-business owners and residents with low-interest loans and legal representation. They also operate a legal arm that assists migrant workers from Texas to Kentucky. Now, Hall said, he wants to make services to the poor more efficient by working with law students who will handle less complicated legal matters, allowing licensed attorneys to take more \\"high impact\\" cases to court. \\"What we need to do is handle cases as efficiently as we can, leveraging the amount of time of the lawyer that goes in there and maximizing the number of people that they can help at one time,\\" Hall said. His plan is to place the 110 attorneys on staff in teams working on specialized legal issues. He wants to expand the law clinic it already has with St. Mary's University Law School to involve students at the University of Texas Law School. The law students at St. Mary's interview potential clients, assist them with filling out legal documents and answer the telephones for the legal hotline, freeing up TRLA lawyers to handle the complicated cases, Hall said. By the end of September, Hall said all the attorneys working with the poor in the 68county area will be placed on the same computer network so they can pass cases to the...\\n\\nQuestion: How many attorneys are planned to be brought onboard and to encompass which law schools?\\nI found this answer \\"68 attorneys encompassing St. Mary's University Law School and the University of Texas Law School\\". Is that correct? Yes or no?","target":"No","rationale":"The question mentions that the organization is planning to bring on more attorneys. The passage states that there are 110 attorneys working at TRLA, then says \\"he wants to expand the law clinic it already has with St. Mary's University Law School to involve students at the University of Texas Law School.\\" This means that Hall does not want to increase staff or add additional lawyers but rather have UT and SMU law school students work for free so TRLA can handle more cases without paying any extra salary costs.\\nSo, answer No"},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is the next sentence syntactically and semantically acceptable?\\n\\nThis problem, the sooner you solve the more easily you'll satisfy the folks up at corporate headquarters.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The sentence follows the subject-verb-object structure. The subject is \\"this problem,\\" and the verb phrase is \\"the sooner you solve (...).\\" Therefore, it is acceptable in terms of syntax and semantics."},{"source":"FINAL EXAM\\n\\nQuestion 1. When was the American actor and comedian born with whom Reitman had a disagreement and for which \\"Which Lie Did I Tell\\" the film never came to fruition?","target":"October 8, 1943","rationale":"According to the question, Reitman had a disagreement with an American actor and comedian born on what date. The reference source shows us that Albert Brooks was born on October 8, 1943 in Beverly Hills, Los Angeles County, California.\\nTherefore \\"October 8th of 1943\\" is the answer for this question"},{"source":"Determine the question that you might have asked to get back the following answer for the given context\\nContext: The administration continues to follow the market reform plans of the previous one and indicated that it will diversify Iran's oil-reliant economy. Iran has also developed a biotechnology, nanotechnology, and pharmaceuticals industry. However, nationalized industries such as the bonyads have often been managed badly, making them ineffective and uncompetitive with years. Currently, the government is trying to privatize these industries, and, despite successes, there are still several problems to be overcome, such as the lagging corruption in the public sector and lack of competitiveness. In 2010, Iran was ranked 69, out of 139 nations, in the Global Competitiveness Report.;\\nAnswer: ranked 69;\\nQuestion:","target":"The Global COmpetitiveness Report in 2010 ranked Iran where out of 139 countries?","rationale":"In the context, Iran is ranked 69 out of 139 nations in 2010.\\nThus, it can be inferred that a possible question could use keywords such as \\"Global Competitiveness Report\\", \\"ranked\\" and \\"out of\\". The answer to this question would then consist of the words: \\nThe Global COmpetitiveness Report in 2010 ranked Iran where out of 139 countries?\\n\\n\\n</code>"},{"source":"Read this article and answer this question During the 9th century, Norway was divided between several local kings controlling their own fiefdoms. By the end of the century, King Harald Fairhair  managed, mainly due to the military superiority gained by his alliance with Sigurd Ladejarl of Nidaros, to subjugate these mini-kingdoms, and he created a unified Norwegian state. This alliance came apart after Harald's death. The jarls of Lade and various descendants of Harald Fairhair would spend the next century interlocked in feuds over power. As well as power politics, religion also played a part in these conflicts, as two of the descendants of Harald Fairhair, Hakon the Good and Olaf Tryggvason attempted to convert the then heathen Norwegians to Christianity. In the year 1000, Svein  and Erik  of Lade took control over Norway, being supported by the Danish King Svein. In 1015, Olaf Haraldsson, representing the descendants of Harald Fairhair, returned from one of his Viking trips and was immediately elected as King of Norway.  In June 1016, he won the Battle at Nesjar against the Jarls of Lade. Olav Haraldsson's success in becoming King of Norway was helped by the Danes being kept occupied with the ongoing fighting in England. In the year 1028, the Danish King Cnut the Great made an alliance with the Lades, and Olaf had to go into exile in Kievan Rus . In the year of 1029 the last Lade, Hakon Jarl, drowned and Olaf returned to Norway with his army to regain his throne and the Kingdom of Norway.\\nHow many years after being elected King of Norway did Olaf Haraldsson win the Battle at Nesjar?","target":"1","rationale":"The question asks how many years after being elected King of Norway did Olaf Haraldsson win the Battle at Nesjar. In one sentence it is mentioned that in June 1016, he won the battle against Jarls of Lade. Also, in another sentence we can see that his winning was helped by Danes' fighting with English people when they were kept occupied and this happened before 1028 which means it must have been earlier than 1017 according to our common sense since if a year passed then it would be later than previous one so definitely not more than 1 year between these two events ."},{"source":"Answer the question depending on the context.\\nContext: The contacts gained through university and American Assembly fund-raising activities would later become important supporters in Eisenhower's bid for the Republican party nomination and the presidency. Meanwhile, Columbia University's liberal faculty members became disenchanted with the university president's ties to oilmen and businessmen, including Leonard McCollum, the president of Continental Oil; Frank Abrams, the chairman of Standard Oil of New Jersey; Bob Kleberg, the president of the King Ranch; H. J. Porter, a Texas oil executive; Bob Woodruff, the president of the Coca-Cola Corporation; and Clarence Francis, the chairman of General Foods.;\\nQuestion: What state was Frank Abrams' oil company located in?;\\nAnswer:","target":"New Jersey","rationale":"The context mentions that Frank Abrams is the chairman of Standard Oil. Thus, in order to answer this question correctly, one must first understand what state Standard Oil was located in. By searching \\"Standard Oil\\" and using Google's calculator function (by typing a math problem into the search bar), we can determine that its headquarters were located in New Jersey."},{"source":"Given the background: Air pollution is harmful to human beings and other living things. About 22 million people die from air pollution each year. Breathing polluted air increases the risk of developing lung diseases such as asthma and lung cancer. Breathing bad air also increases the chances of dying from other diseases. Children are most likely to be affected by air pollution. That‚Äôs because their lungs are still developing and growing. Children also take in more air for their size than adults do. Some air pollutants damage the environment as well as the health of living things. The type of damage depends on the pollutant. Air pollution can also harm the environment.\\n\\nand the situation: Manny visited 2 countries. First he visited Australia, a country which respected the environment and produced zero air pollution, and New Zealand, a country which based its economy on burning fossil fuels and generated a lot of air pollution.\\n\\nAnswer the following question: Which country had fewer living things being harmed by air pollution?","target":"Australia","rationale":"Overall, the background tells us that air pollution is detrimental to all living things. Australia was described as being a country which respected its environment and produced zero air pollution. In contrast, New Zealand generated significant amounts of air pollution based on their economy burning fossil fuels. Based on this information we can infer that:\\n- Fewer people died from respiratory diseases in Australia (22 million deaths per year are caused by bad quality of air)\\n- More children were affected by air pollution in New Zealand than in Australia (since they have more developing lungs)."},{"source":"Choose your answer from options. Premise: \\"This not only produces better managers, it also helps break down functional barriers that can affect productivity and impede improvement efforts.\\" If this premise is true, what does that tell us about whether it entails the hypothesis \\" it helps break down functional barriers that can affect productivity and impede improvement efforts.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The premise starts off by saying \\"This not only produces better managers,\\" and then goes on to say that it also helps break down functional barriers. It is clear from this passage that the author believes that having better managers would help improve productivity in a company, which entails the hypothesis provided above. Therefore, we can conclude that the answer for this question is 'yes'."},{"source":"Philadelphia, Pennsylvania (CNN) -- Paulette Beale shakes her head at the suggestion, then flashes a contagious smile. \\"It's still history,\\" she says, to rebut the notion there could be less intensity for President Barack Obama in the African-American community the second time around. \\"The first history was that he won. The second history's that he won twice. So, it's not just about history the first time, you have to be concerned about the history for the next four years also. You can make history more than one time, you know.\\" Her mother and father stand a few feet away, nodding approvingly.\\n@highlight\\nTurnout among African-Americans could determine result of presidential election\\n@highlight\\nUnemployment, voter ID laws, complacency could affect turnout\\n@highlight\\nObama campaign has unprecedented effort to register, communicate with voters\\n@highlight\\nOne Philadephian says there is more at stake this year than in 2008 \\nJohnson says that law could be one factor in driving African-@placeholder turnout down a bit from 2008. \\nCan you figure out what does the \\"@placeholder\\" mean? It means","target":"American","rationale":"The @placeholder is a shorthand for \\"African-American\\" and thus, the right answer option is American."},{"source":"Please answer a question about the following article about Portugal:\\n\\nPortugal lost much of its wealth and status with the destruction of Lisbon in a 1755 earthquake, occupation during the Napoleonic Wars, and the independence of Brazil, its wealthiest colony, in 1822. After the 1910 revolution deposed the monarchy, the democratic but unstable Portuguese First Republic was established, later being superseded by the \\"Estado Novo\\" right-wing authoritarian regime. Democracy was restored after the Portuguese Colonial War and the Carnation Revolution in 1974. Shortly after, independence was granted to all its colonies, with the exception of Macau, which was handed over to China in 1999. This marked the end of the longest-lived European colonial empire, leaving a profound cultural and architectural influence across the globe and a legacy of over 250 million Portuguese speakers today.\\n\\nHow many Portugese speakers are there today?","target":"250 million","rationale":"The text states that the Portuguese Colonial Empire left a legacy of over 250 million Portuguese speakers today. Thus, we can infer that there are currently around 250 million Portugese speakers in the world.\\nTherefore, \\"250 million\\" is the answer to this question.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: sexual-explicit and non-sexual-explicit. A comment is considered sexual-explicit if it explicitly portrays sexual matters.\\n\\nComment: Hey, you know it's 6C here in the middle of January and the temps aren't looking to drop.  This is the new reality.  The northwest passage is now navigable for cruise ships.  This is the new reality.  Ski season in Ontario is practically no more.  This is the new reality.  These are facts, not opinions, and not based on any spectrum of political belief.  Get your head out of your ass.","target":"Sexual-explicit","rationale":"The comment is explicit about \\"head out of your ass\\", which can be interpreted as a sexual innuendo. Therefore, the answer is \\"Sexual-explicit\\"."},{"source":"(CNN) -- Detroit elected Mike Duggan mayor Tuesday. And he's white. Of course, he has numerous qualifications for the job -- experience as a hospital CEO, county executive, former prosecutor, etc. -- but in a city where four of five residents are African-American and no Caucasian has held the city's highest office in almost four decades, the headline is that Duggan is white. The last white mayor to take the city's helm was former sheriff and prosecutor Roman Gribbs, who served from 1970 to 1974. Duggan, 55, will replace outgoing Mayor Dave Bing after defeating his opponent, Wayne County Sheriff Benny Napoleon, by a margin of 55% to 45%, according to CNN affiliates WXYZ and WDIV.\\n@highlight\\nThe last white mayor of Detroit was Roman Gribbs, who served from 1970 to 1974\\n@highlight\\nThe mayor-elect tells a newspaper his first priority will be cutting police response times\\n@highlight\\nFBI says there were 15,011 violent crimes, 386 homicides in Detroit last year\\n@highlight\\nDetroit is run by an emergency manager, whom governor appointed until September \\n@placeholder may have to operate through consensus until at least September, as Gov. \\nWhich one is the \\"@placeholder\\"? Benny Napoleon, CNN, CNN affiliates WXYZ, Caucasian, Dave Bing, Detroit, Duggan, FBI, Mike Duggan, Roman Gribbs, WDIV, Wayne County?","target":"Mike Duggan","rationale":"From the given context, it is clear that Mike Duggan will be replacing outgoing Mayor Dave Bing. Thus, he (Mike Duggan) is the placeholder here."},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as acceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"Both Jane and Elizabeth were at home.","rationale":"Here's an example of a grammatically correct sentence: Both Jane and Elizabeth were at home."},{"source":"By Helen Lawson PUBLISHED: 09:43 EST, 30 March 2013 | UPDATED: 12:18 EST, 30 March 2013 At first glance, these may look like piles of rubbish cluttering up the canals of Venice. But these are three boats made entirely from salvaged junk - including plywood, motors and bedding. After six months of gathering materials and shipping them to Slovenia, a team of artists and performers built the boats and set sail to attend the prestigious Venice Biennale art show, even though they hadn't been invited. Their aim was to show that anything could be built even if you only had the idea.\\n@highlight\\nThe Swimming Cities of Serenissima project was led by street artist Swoon\\n@highlight\\nShe and her team docked at the Venice Biennale art show and performed \\nIt was all hands on deck for the @placeholder crew, who salvaged every piece of the boat \\nCan you figure out what does the \\"@placeholder\\" mean? It means","target":"Swimming Cities of Serenissima","rationale":"The \\"@placeholder\\" refers to the name of a project, which is \\"Swimming Cities of Serenissima\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage. The passage will not have a direct answer to the question, but can include some information and a clue for the answer. Assuming you can only obtain information about one entity in the passage, your job is to determine whether information from the passage can be used to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: How many wins did Felda United achieve the year Ferns debuted with them? Passage:Ferns made his debut for Felda United F.C. in the Malaysia Super League with a 2-1 win against Pahang FA in July 2017. Under the guidance of head coach B. Sathianathan, Ferns made a successful contribution, helping the team reach 3rd place in the Malaysia Super League and semi-final of the Malaysia Cup. Unfortunately, in the off-season of 2017 the club was notified it was being relegated to the Malaysia Premier League for the 2018 season after failing the Football Association of Malaysia club licence financial audit. Despite this setback, Ferns and the majority of the squad stayed at the club to help Felda United F.C win the title and secure promotion back to the Malaysia Super League for 2019.","target":"a","rationale":"The question asks for the number of wins that Felda United achieved in the year Ferns debuted with them. The passage mentions that Ferns made his debut for Felda United F.C. in a 2-1 win against Pahang FA in July 2017 and helped the team reach 3rd place in the Malaysia Super League (the same year), which means one win, at least, comes from his debut match. Hence, information from this passage can be used to answer this question, i.e., 'a'."},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- Sandra moved to the kitchen. Fact 2- Sandra went back to the garden. Question: Where is Sandra? Answer: garden","target":"Fact 2","rationale":"The passage states in Fact 2 that Sandra \\"went back to the garden\\", which is the answer to the question."},{"source":"Which processes change magma into igneous rock?\\n\\nOptions:\\n- cooling and crystallization\\n- compaction and cementation\\n- heat and pressure\\n- weathering and erosion","target":"cooling and crystallization","rationale":"Magma is a hot liquid or semi-liquid material below the surface of the earth. \\nIgneous rock forms when magma cools and solidifies, either at volcanoes on Earth's surface or while still underground. This process is called crystallization. \\nThe other options are not involved in changing magma into igneous rocks because they are processes that involve sedimentary and metamorphic rocks instead of igneous: compaction and cementation (sedimentary), heat and pressure (metamorphic) weathering and erosion(sedimentary).\\n\\n\\nTherefore, cooling and crystallization should be selected as the answer."},{"source":"I am hesitating between 4 options to answer the following question, which option should I choose?\\nQuestion: Which tool should a student use to compare the masses of two small rocks?\\nPossibilities:\\n- balance\\n- hand lens\\n- ruler\\n- measuring cup","target":"balance","rationale":"The balance is the best tool to use when it comes to comparing the masses of objects because this instrument uses a system with weights that can be adjusted by moving them around on opposite sides until they are balanced.\\nThis way, one can tell how much mass each object has and compare their weight based on which side of the scale requires adding more or less weights in order for both sides to equalize. \\n\\n\\nTherefore, option A \\"balance\\" should be selected as the answer."},{"source":"Q: flag with white background blue square and red cross? A:","target":"The Christian Flag","rationale":"The Christian Flag is a flag designed in the early 20th century to represent all of Christianity and Christendom, and has been most popular among Protestant churches in the United States. It has a white background with blue square at top left corner containing a red cross inside it. \\nThis answer can be verified through various credible sources such as flags history books and articles dedicated to this particular flag's origin. Additionally, its popularity further support the validity of this answer being correct."},{"source":"Categorize the comment on the basis of toxicity. If the comment is toxic (harmful, malicious, derogatory, threat, insult, identity attck, etc.) output Yes, otherwise output No.\\n\\nPlease, no need for ad hominem. Comment on the ideas, not the person.","target":"No","rationale":"The given comment is a call for polite and civil communication. It does not contain any form of toxicity and could be classified as \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Based on the premise \\"What was unusual about this request was that roughly $1.\\", can we conclude the hypothesis \\"There was something unusual about the request.\\" is true (see options)?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The premise states that \\"what was unusual about this request\\" is the fact that roughly $1.5 billion in cash had to be sent over a short period of time. This directly supports the hypothesis, which states there as something unusual about the request (i.e., sending $1.5 billion). Therefore, we can conclude that it is true and select yes for our answer choice"},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the correct option to answer the question.\\nContext: What is creativity?\\nHow de we define creativity?\\nWhere does creativity come from?\\nHow philosophical is the notion of creativity?\\nIs everyone‚Äôs ‚Äòcreativity‚Äô different?\\nOr is it an ill conceived, simplified term that is used to describe a very specific series of neuronal & bodily reactions to certain stimuli?\\nThese are all the questions I‚Äôve been thinking (and googling, and youtubing) since beginning this Capturing Creativity studio* and I have found some answers or maybe I‚Äôve just found more questions:\\nCreativity is generally defined as the ability to make new things, or come up with new ideas, it‚Äôs an ability to think outside the box, to see unique solutions and employ them in inventive ways. In this sense creativity is not always utilised when being ‚Äòcreative‚Äô, as to be creative is simply defined as the ability to make or produce something. However I guess that depends on your definition of creative, how different, unique, special, once off, un-influenced does something have to be, to be classified as creative?\\nThis is where creativity get‚Äôs tricky.\\nIt‚Äôs all well and good to be like oh this is what creativity is, so it‚Äôs easy to investigate it, but what if you don‚Äôt define that as being creative, maybe that was just following a formula, a somewhat inspired formula, but maybe it is just a formula. Creativity to most people seems to be a random mix of once off genius combined with solid skill and hard work and for us humans these percentages are unique to us.\\nMaybe creativity to you is 90% unique idea, 5% skill and 5% hard work.\\nMaybe creativity to you is 40% unique idea, 50% skill and 10% hard work.\\nMaybe for you creativity doesn‚Äôt have to involve any hard work at all.\\nFor me when it comes to creativity I‚Äôm most interested in that unique idea portion; where does that unique idea come from?\\nIs it simply random?\\nIs it a gift from the gods?\\nIs our unique idea just a product of a lot of subconscious effort, only made aware to us in the sense of a ‚Äòrandom‚Äô idea?\\nHave we been influenced by something, processed it...\\nQuestion: How long has the author probably been thinking about these questions?\\nOptions:\\n- not enough information\\n- A few minutes\\n- A few months\\n- Since they were born","target":"A few months","rationale":"The context is an essay about the author's thoughts on creativity. They mention that they have been thinking and googling for answers to their questions since beginning a specific class, Capturing Creativity studio*. This suggests that it has likely only been a few months (i.e., since or before the start of this particular academic term) that they have had these questions in mind rather than throughout their entire life up until now.\\nSo, A few months would be correct answer"},{"source":"I want to test the ability of students to read a passage and answer questions about it. Could you please come up with a good question for the passage \\"Punjab during Mahabharata times was known as Panchanada. Punjab was part of the Indus Valley Civilization, more than 4000 years ago. The main site in Punjab was the city of Harrapa. The Indus Valley Civilization spanned much of what is today Pakistan and eventually evolved into the Indo-Aryan civilisation. The Vedic civilisation flourished along the length of the Indus River. This civilisation shaped subsequent cultures in South Asia and Afghanistan. Although the archaeological site at Harappa was partially damaged in 1857 when engineers constructing the Lahore-Multan railroad used brick from the Harappa ruins for track ballast, an abundance of artefacts have nevertheless been found. Punjab was part of the great ancient empires including the Gandhara Mahajanapadas, Achaemenids, Macedonians, Mauryas, Kushans, Guptas, and Hindu Shahi. It also comprised the Gujar empire for a period of time, otherwise known as the Gurjara-Pratihara empire. Agriculture flourished and trading cities (such as Multan and Lahore) grew in wealth.\\"?","target":"What was used under the track?","rationale":"The question has to be a direct answer from the passage in order for students to test their ability of reading and understanding. The rationale is that brick from Harappa ruins was used under the track, so we could ask \\"What was used under the track?\\""},{"source":"In this task you are given an anecdote. You must find out whether the anecdote is something the author has done or is considering doing. Label the instances as \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and label them as \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future.\\n\\nIm a 16 y/o dude and Im better than the guys I play basketball with. AITA for trash talking about their \\"SKILLZ\\"","target":"HISTORICAL","rationale":"The post is written in the present tense and uses phrases such as \\"I'm better than\\" and \\"Im trash talking\\", which suggests that the author is describing a current situation. The author expresses frustration at teammates who they feel are not skilled enough to play well. This would suggest that the events described have already occurred and are being recounted by the author. Therefore, it is appropriate to label this instance as \\"\\"HISTORICAL.\\"\\""},{"source":"Players may only be transferred during transfer windows that are set by the Football Association. The two transfer windows run from the last day of the season to 31 August and from 31 December to 31 January. Player registrations cannot be exchanged outside these windows except under specific licence from the FA, usually on an emergency basis. As of the 2010‚Äì11 season, the Premier League introduced new rules mandating that each club must register a maximum 25-man squad of players aged over 21, with the squad list only allowed to be changed in transfer windows or in exceptional circumstances. This was to enable the 'home grown' rule to be enacted, whereby the League would also from 2010 require at least 8 of the named 25 man squad to be made up of 'home-grown players'. Find the answer to: During which time can a player be transferred from one European football league to another?","target":"transfer windows","rationale":"A clear answer can be found in the context itself.\\nPlayers may only be transferred during transfer windows that are set by the Football Association."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i, j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to find all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, reverse the order in which they occur, and then concatenate them to output the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j. Perform the operations in order, i.e., do not concatenate the elements and then reverse the string.\\n\\n1, 3, ['2059', '8835', '6927', '9337', 'V']","target":"692788352059","rationale":"Given the list ['2059', '8835', '6927', '9337', 'V'], we need to find the elements within the range 1 ~ 3.\\\\n1. The 1st element is 2059.\\\\n2. The 2nd element is 8835.\\\\n3. The 3rd element is 6927.\\n\\nThe order of elements should be reversed in string, so the final output would be \\"692788352059\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list. A list contains several comma-separated items written within brackets. You need to return the count of all the numerical elements in the given list. Return 0 if no numerical element in the list.\\n\\n['o', 'g', 'C', '8267', '5861']","target":"2","rationale":"The given list contains two numerical elements: 8267 and 5861, so the answer is 2."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the best option to answer the question.\\nContext: I leap lightly over the low brick fence with angled top ( a feat I perform regularily ) but today the bricks were slippery and slipped at the wrong moment , twisting , falling and tumbling through the air until I landed hard , my back onto the cement . My feet were still hanging , twisted , over the brick fenceline . I lay there in the gutter , quite still , I was n't hurt but rather contemplating my acrobatic failure as the rain started to pitter patter down upon me . Well , at least there was noone aro .. \\" Hello , are you quite alright ? \\"\\nQuestion: What may I do after they say that ?\\nOptions: \\n- I will kiss them .\\n - I will jump with fright .\\n - I will hug them .\\n - I will walk towards the voice .","target":"I will jump with fright .","rationale":"The context describes a person falling and landing hard on their back in the gutter. They are not hurt but wondering about how to get up when someone says \\"hello\\". It's highly likely that this will cause them to jump with fright, so the answer is I will jump with fright ."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"Oklahoma City and the surrounding metropolitan area are home to a number of health care facilities and specialty hospitals. In Oklahoma City's MidTown district near downtown resides the state's oldest and largest single site hospital, St. Anthony Hospital and Physicians Medical Center.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What is the name of the biggest button and most used on iOS devices such as a iPhone?","target":"home","rationale":"When using an iPhone or iPad, the \\"home\\" button is one of the most frequently used buttons on iOS devices. The home button can be used to perform various functions such as taking a photo and returning to the main screen.\\nSo, based on this information -- that it is present within text-- we infer that Home Button must therefore be what's being referred in question asked above"},{"source":"The British tabloids portrayed Nicholas Leeson as a working-class villain who single-handedly brought down Barings PLC, a 233-year-old London merchant bank that helped finance the Napoleonic wars.\\nDoes this next sentence follow, given the preceding text?\\nBarings was Britain's oldest merchant bank.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"While the next sentence is true, it doesn't follow from the preceding text. The portion of this context that mentions Barings being 233 years old could be referring to when Baring PLC was founded; therefore, while both sentences are accurate they do not necessarily have a causal relationship with each other."},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- Mary travelled to the garden. Fact 2- Daniel went to the office. Question: Where is Daniel? Answer: office","target":"Fact 2","rationale":"Fact 1 is irrelevant to the question. Fact 2 tells us that Daniel went to the office."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to find the mean (average) of that list. The mean of a list can be found by summing every number in the list then dividing the result by the size of that list. The output should be rounded to 3 decimal places.\\n\\n[118.868, -12.498, -19.221, 11.95, 188.557]","target":"57.531","rationale":"The mean of the given list is (118.868 + (-12.498) + (-19.221) + 11.95 + 188.557) / 5 = 179.7592 / 5 = 57.53184\\\\nRounding to 3 decimal places, 57.531"},{"source":"In this task, a passage will be given and the goal is to identify an event from the passage. An event is defined as a single word representing something that happened, is happening, or may happen. An event can be factual or hypothetical, positive or negative, certain or uncertain. While most events are based on verbs, an event can also be based on a noun (ex. storm, snow, rainfall) or a copula verb (is, was, been, etc.). The event must not be a pronoun or an adjective. For noun events with multiple words, use the last word in the phrase as event.\\n\\nPassage: After hitting the man the damaged aircraft was forced to fly 120 nautical miles on one engine, escorted by another FA-18 and a Viking tanker plane, to make an emergency landing at the Williamtown RAAF Base near Newcastle, about 150 kilometres (93 miles) north of Sydney, an official there said. Wing Commander Lou Lapuma said the Hornet's undercarriage collapsed as it made an emergency landing but the pilot was unhurt.","target":"hitting","rationale":"The passage describes an event that occurred to a FA-18 fighter jet after hitting a man. The word 'hitting' is used as a noun to describe the occurrence of the jet hitting the man."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: This heat is used to convert water into steam, which is then used to turn a turbine, thus generating electrical power. Sentence 2: The heat from the coal is used to boil water to make steam, which turns turbines , which spin electrical generators.","target":"entails","rationale":"Statement 2 provides additional information that supports the scientific fact stated in Statement 1. It describes how heat from coal is used to boil water and make steam, which turns turbines and spins electrical generators, thus generating electricity. Therefore, it uses an example of a process involving converting heat into electric power via turning turbines with steam generated by boiling water. This corresponds exactly with what was described in statement 1 as well (\\"This heat is used to convert water into steam, which is then used to turn a turbine ...\\"). As such, this proves or shows evidence for the claim made in statement 1 (that \\"heat can be converted into electric power\\"), so it entails or implies that claim -- hence \\"entails\\" should be returned as the answer."},{"source":"What is the narrator complaining about ?","target":"a DVR player","rationale":"From the transcript, we can see that the narrator is complaining about a DVR player."},{"source":"I am hesitating between 4 options to answer the following question, which option should I choose?\\nQuestion: Which process moves an ion across a cell membrane against the concentration gradient?\\nPossibilities:\\n- diffusion\\n- exocytosis\\n- facilitated diffusion\\n- active transport","target":"active transport","rationale":"Active transport moves ions across cell membranes. Both diffusion and facilitated diffusion move an ion down its concentration gradient while exocytosis is a process where the fusion of a membrane vesicle with the plasma membrane releases the contents of that vesicle into the extracellular environment, so it's not directly related to how an ion crosses a cell membrane. \\nTherefore, active transport would be correct answer for this question: \\"Which process moves an ion across a cell membrane against the concentration gradient?"},{"source":"In this task, you are given an answer, and your task is to generate a reasonable question for that answer.\\n\\nMy new job starts next week Monday.","target":"You know when you starting your new job?","rationale":"The answer is pretty open ended, it could be a question or statement, but the question that seems most reasonable to ask is: \\"You know when you starting your new job?\\""},{"source":"Read the dialog and predict the next turn. DIALOG:\\nWhat are the Michigan Relics?\\n- Hunter's rhetoric and work with the Michigan Relics perpetuated pseudoarchaeology in religion, with efforts to prove pre-Columbian contact and the myth of the mound builders.\\n- Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?\\n- Notre Dame gave Hunter the collection in the 1960s and before his death in 1975 he deeded the collection to the LDS Church.\\n- Was it on display for the public to see?\\n- Following Hunter's death, the Church kept the collection in their museum in Salt Lake City, Utah for decades.\\n- Is there anything else of importance that was found?\\n- In 2001, the Church had the relics examined by Professor of Anthropology Richard B. Stamps, of Oakland University and found that the artifacts were made with contemporary tools.\\n- How were they preserved?\\n- The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints kept 797 of the objects in their Salt Lake City Museum.\\n- Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?\\n-","target":"In 2003, they gave them to the Michigan History Museum in Lansing where they currently reside.","rationale":"From the dialog, we see that the conversation is about Michigan relics. The answer option \\"In 2003, they gave them to the Michigan History Museum in Lansing where they currently reside.\\" provides new information regarding these artifacts. This option is chosen over other options as it is relevant to the context of this conversation and provides an interesting fact."},{"source":"went home , got changed , and spent about 2 hours at the gym . that felt fantastic , i left feeling sore but so strong , and beautiful . took a tiny nap with the dog , took a shower , went to champagne and had a delicious chicken salad crossiant ( sp ? ) , emailed my rory to wish him a happy birthday !\\nWhy did the writer feel fantastic after the gym ?\\nPick the best answer from the following options:\\n- Because they enjoy taking showers .\\n - Because it 's a good feeling to finish a good workout .\\n - None of the above choices .\\n - Because they felt sore .","target":"Because it 's a good feeling to finish a good workout .","rationale":"The writer describes feeling \\"sore but so strong, and beautiful\\" after going to the gym. The description of this experience indicates that they felt fantastic because it's a good feeling to finish a workout in which you push yourself physically.\\nSo the answer is Because it 's a good feeling to finish a good workout ."},{"source":"Given a math word problem, answer the following question. You might need to apply addition or subtraction mathematical operators on the numbers embedded in the text to answer the question and then only report the final numerical answer.\\n\\ncade had 87 marbles . he gave 8 to dylan . how many does he have left ?","target":"79","rationale":"From the given problem, we can infer that Cade had 87 marbles and gave 8 to Dylan. So, Cade now has 79 marbles left."},{"source":"The input is a tweet which can be Hate Speech or Offensive. Given such a tweet, output a phrase from the tweet that makes it hate speech or offensive. The output should contain only one such phrase. The output has to be from within the tweet itself. Do not generate words or phrases not present in the tweet.\\n\\nwhy are we having all these people from shithole countries coming here","target":"people from shithole countries","rationale":"The tweet is derogatory towards people from certain countries and contains offensive language. Therefore, the phrase \\"people from shithole countries\\" can be considered a reason for this tweet to be classified as hate speech or offensive."},{"source":"If this is the response, what came before? Response We are, what can I get for you?","target":"Hi, are you still taking orders for pickup tonight?","rationale":"The response, \\"We are what can I get for you?\\" indicates that the speaker is at a fast food restaurant or similar establishment. The most reasonable question to ask in this context would be whether or not the establishment is still taking orders for pickup tonight. Therefore, the answer is \\"Hi, are you still taking orders for pickup tonight?\\""},{"source":"Generate a question about the following movie plot: This article's plot summary may be too long or excessively detailed. Please help improve it by removing unnecessary details and making it more concise. (March 2015) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)\\nIn late 1944, the remnants of a platoon of German Panzergrenadiers from the Gro√É¬üdeutschland Division are caught in an ambush by American troops. In their retreat, they find a German bunker manned by elderly Pvt. Mirus (John Carlisle) and young Pvt. Neumann (Andrew-Lee Potts) who had been left to defend the bunker under orders from Area Command to wait until relieved. Schenke confronts Heydrich about why the group didn't counter-attack the Americans, claiming that there couldn't have been that many of them. Mirus expands on the history of the area, revealing that victims of the Black Plague were massacred on the orders of a stranger, who influenced the townspeople to turn against one another. Low on ammunition, the men are haunted by bad dreams, memories and the feeling that something about the area just isn't right.\\nAs the night proceeds, strange tunnels are found beneath the bunker and the situation in the bunker becomes increasingly tense. Pvt. Schenke (Andrew Tiernan) wants to explore the tunnels but Lt. Krupp (Simon Kunz) orders against it. Later, Mirus sneaks down into the tunnels and a curious Pfc. Kruezmann (Eddie Marsan) follows him. When they are discovered to be missing, Lt. Krupp believes they've deserted and orders a pursuit. Interrogation of Neumann reveals that Mirus had been wandering off into the tunnels for several weeks and treats the tunnels as his property, as if something is down there that Mirus doesn't want him to know about. Cpl. Baumann (Jason Flemyng) discovers a set of plans for the complex while Cpl. Ebert (Jack Davenport) finds a danger sign. Exploring further, Ebert comes to a mine shaft where he hears movement and a pile of sand nearly falls on top of him. Terrified, he is suddenly stabbed from behind. As he lays dying, a silhouetted figure resembling Kreutzmann...","target":"What exploded behind Neman and Baumann?","rationale":"Neumann and Bauman are running down an alley when a bomb explodes behind them.\\nSo the answer is What exploded behind Neman and Baumann?"},{"source":"Given a sentence, generate a most likely context or previous statement. The previous statement should be relevant to the given statement.\\n\\nNow at North Western Law, someone sits in a lecture classroom with her notebook open.","target":"He returns a gentle look and she considers him","rationale":"The word \\"she\\" in the given statement refers to a person, so we can infer that the previous statement most likely involved this same person. The previous statement also needs to be relevant to the given one, which has a classroom setting. Given these constraints, we can conclude that the most likely previous sentence is \\\\\\"He returns a gentle look and she considers him\\\\\\" because it contains \\\\\\"he\\\\\\" and \\\\\\"she\\\\\\", indicating that it involves two people. It also takes place in a classroom setting as indicated by words such as \\\\\\"lecture\\\\\\" and \\\\\\"classroom\\\\\\"."},{"source":"Answer a question about this article:\\nHoping to extend the Continental System, Napoleon invaded Iberia and declared his brother Joseph the King of Spain in 1808. The Spanish and the Portuguese revolted with British support. The Peninsular War lasted six years, noted for its brutal guerrilla warfare, and culminated in an Allied victory. Fighting also erupted in Central Europe, as the Austrians launched another attack against the French in 1809. Napoleon defeated them at the Battle of Wagram, dissolving the Fifth Coalition formed against France. By 1811, Napoleon ruled over 70 million people across an empire that had domination in Europe, which had not witnessed this level of political consolidation since the days of the Roman Empire. He maintained his strategic status through a series of alliances and family appointments. He created a new aristocracy in France while allowing the return of nobles who had been forced into exile by the Revolution.\\nWhat country did Napoleon invade to extend the Continental System?","target":"Iberia","rationale":"The article opens with the description of Napoleon's efforts to extend the Continental System, which was followed by his invasion of Iberia.\\nTherefore, we can conclude that Spain is the country invaded by Napoleon in order to expand the Continental System."},{"source":"A friend asked me to answer this question: What is the first name of the person who said one of the most surprising aspects of the Matawan Creek attacks was the distance from the open sea, using the article: Another letter to The New York Times blamed the shark infestation on the maneuvers of German U-boats near America's East Coast. The anonymous writer claimed, \\"These sharks may have devoured human bodies in the waters of the German war zone and followed liners to this coast, or even followed the Deutschland herself, expecting the usual toll of drowning men, women, and children.\\" The writer concluded, \\"This would account for their boldness and their craving for human flesh.\\"Decades later, there is no consensus among researchers over Murphy and Lucas's investigation and findings. Richard G. Fernicola published two studies of the event, and notes that \\"there are many theories behind the New Jersey attacks,\\" and all are inconclusive. Researchers such as Thomas Helm, Harold W. McCormick, Thomas B. Allen, William Young, Jean Campbell Butler, and Michael Capuzzo generally agree with Murphy and Lucas. However, the National Geographic Society reported in 2002 that \\"some experts are suggesting that the great white may not in fact be responsible for many of the attacks pinned on the species. These people say the real culprit behind many of the reported incidents‚Äîincluding the famous 1916 shark attacks in New Jersey that may have served as inspiration for Jaws‚Äîmay be the lesser known bull shark.\\"Biologists George A. Llano and Richard Ellis suggest that a bull shark could have been responsible for the fatal Jersey Shore attacks. Bull sharks swim from the ocean into freshwater rivers and streams and have attacked people around the world. In his book Sharks: Attacks on Man (1975), Llano writes,\\nOne of the most surprising aspects of the Matawan Creek attacks was the distance from the open sea. Elsewhere in the book are accounts of well-documented shark-human interactions at Ahwaz, Iran, which is 90 miles (140 km) upriver from the sea. It may also be of interest to note that sharks live in Lake Nicaragua, a fresh-water body, and in 1944 there was a bounty offered for dead freshwater sharks, as they had \\"killed and severely..., what would be the answer ?","target":"George","rationale":"The question asks for the first name of the person who said that one of the most surprising aspects of Matawan Creek attacks was distance from open sea. The article mentions George A. Llano, a biologist and Richard Ellis suggesting bull shark could have been responsible for fatal Jersey Shore attacks which is further away from ocean than where it happened at Matawan creek.\\nSo, I believe Geroge's last name is in fact \\"Llano\\""},{"source":"Sentence 1: \\"I put the cake away in the refrigerator. It has a lot of leftovers in it.\\"\\n\\n Sentence 2: \\"The refrigerator has a lot of leftovers in it.\\"\\n\\nIs sentence 2 true, based on sentence 1?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"yes","rationale":"From sentence 1, we can infer that the cake has a lot of leftovers in it. Since this is mentioned directly after putting the cake away in the refrigerator, it's assumed that \\"it\\" refers to both objects: The refrigerator and the cake. Therefore, since there are a lot of leftovers inside both items (the fridge and the cake), then logically speaking yes - there will be a lot of left overs in just the fridge itself as well."},{"source":"Article: In 1954, then-mayor Richard C. Lee began some of the earliest major urban renewal projects in the United States. Certain sections of downtown New Haven were redeveloped to include museums, new office towers, a hotel, and large shopping complexes. Other parts of the city were affected by the construction of Interstate 95 along the Long Wharf section, Interstate 91, and the Oak Street Connector. The Oak Street Connector (Route 34), running between Interstate 95, downtown, and The Hill neighborhood, was originally intended as a highway to the city's western suburbs but was only completed as a highway to the downtown area, with the area to the west becoming a boulevard (See \\"Redevelopment\\" below).\\n\\nQuestion: What area of New Haven was Route 34 originally intended to service?","target":"the city's western suburbs","rationale":"The context tells us that Route 34 was originally intended to service the city's western suburbs but it only became a highway connecting Interstate 95 and downtown areas. \\nIt is clear from this information that the original intention of Route 34 was to provide access between New Haven and its western suburbs.\\""},{"source":"Fill in the response. DIALOG:\\nWhere did Billy Southworth go to school?\\n- Orlando Southworth had wanted his son, Billy Southworth, to attend college. At the age of 19, he signed a contract with the Portsmouth team in the Ohio State League.\\n- When did Billy Southworth start playing?\\n- Billy Southworth joined the Cleveland Indians in 1913, but only appeared in one game, entering as a replacement on defense.\\n- How long did Billy Southworth play for the Cleveland Indians in 1913?\\n- As a player, Billy Southworth played for the Cleveland Indians in 1913 and 1915.\\n- Did Billy Southworth play fo anyone else after Birmingham Barons in 1917?\\n- In 1918, Billy Southworth made the Pittsburgh Pirates and played in 64 major league games.\\n- When did Billy Southworth start coaching instead of playing?\\n- Billy Southworth's managerial career began in 1928 with the Rochester Red Wings of the AA International League (IL), the top club in the Cardinals' farm system.\\n- Did Billy Southworth end up playing for any other teams other than the Boston Braves, Pittsburgh Pirate, and Cleveland Indians?\\n- Billy Southworth was promoted to St. Louis as player-manager for 1929, replacing Bill McKechnie.\\n- What was Billy Southworth's career like? How well did Billy Southworth do as a player?\\n- As a player-manager, Billy Southworth's career reached the end of the road. He appeared in only 19 games, five in the outfield, and batted only .188 with six hits.\\n- Did Billy Southworth do better in the beginning of his career versus the end?\\n- Although Billy Southworth resumed his successful minor league managerial career, the firing and personal tragedy ‚Äî the death of his wife Lida at age 42 ‚Äî began a downward spiral.\\n- What was Billy Southworth's batting average towards the end?\\n-","target":"As a big leaguer, Billy Southworth had 1,296 hits in 4,359 at bats.","rationale":"The answer is \\"As a big leaguer, Billy Southworth had 1,296 hits in 4,359 at bats.\\" because it answers the question of \\"What was Billy Southworth's batting average towards the end?\\" by providing his total number of hits and at-bats. The other choices do not provide any information about his batting average towards the end."},{"source":"We got the cats in their cages , and brought them into the rental office of the complex where we needed to sign the lease and get our keys ( they were a huge hit - everyone cooed at them ) . We drove over to our apartment from there , and one of my major worries was assuaged immediately . See , we had rented our apartment based on a model , without ever having seen the actual living space .\\nWhat may be the reason for them bringing their cats into the office ?\\nPick the best answer from the following options:\\n- They wanted to show them off .\\n - They did n't have keys for the apartment yet .\\n - The office was giving animals free vaccinations .\\n - They needed to keep them there for a few days .","target":"They did n't have keys for the apartment yet .","rationale":"The paragraph describes the narrator's feelings about their new apartment, which they had rented without seeing. They also mention that one of their major worries was alleviated as soon as they arrived at it. Given this context, we can infer that the reason for bringing cats into an office is because the narrators needed to keep them there until receiving keys to access their rental property from a leasing agent or manager and transporting them all safely inside.\\nSo, the answer is: They did n't have keys for the apartment yet ."},{"source":"In this task you will be given some text dialogue and you need to infer the underlying emotion of the text. The possible emotions are happy, sad, angry, or other.\\n\\nlater is it later now facewithtearsofjoyfacewithtearsofjoyyou are funny","target":"happy","rationale":"The given text contains emojis depicting tears of joy, which is often used to express happiness. Hence, the underlying emotion is happy."},{"source":"I am verifying the answers generated by an automatic system to the following question: what do people usually give up for lent\\nSuggested answer: However in the Roman Catholic Church Lent is now taken to end on Holy Thursday rather than Easter Eve, and hence lasts 38 days excluding Sundays, or 44 days in total.\\nShould I validate this answer?","target":"No","rationale":"The suggested answer from the automatic system defines what Lent is, but does not provide an example of something that people usually give up for lent. The statement \\"However in the Roman Catholic Church, Lent is now taken to end on Holy Thursday rather than Easter Eve ... 44 days\\" only explains how many days are typically involved with observing this event and nothing more. \\nTherefore, the validation would be No because it doesn't explain or cite examples of items that may be given up by a person during his/her observance of Lent."},{"source":"Question: \\"_ was claimed by the Iroquois after the Baever Wars.\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"In Terry v. Ohio (1968) the court divided seizure into two parts, the investigatory stop and arrest. The court further held that during an investigatory stop a police officer's search \\" [is] confined to what [is] minimally necessary to determine whether [a suspect] is armed, and the intrusion, which [is] made for the sole purpose of protecting himself and others nearby, [is] confined to ascertaining the presence of weapons\\" (U.S. Supreme Court). Before Terry, every police encounter constituted an arrest, giving the police officer the full range of search authority. Search authority during a Terry stop (investigatory stop) is limited to weapons only.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"Ohio","rationale":"The question asks, \\"___ was claimed by the Iroquois after the Beaver Wars.\\"\\nIn context of this article and in contrast to what is stated in Terry v. Ohio (1968), we can infer that if a police officer has not yet arrested someone, he/she does NOT have full range authority over them during an investigatory stop or before making an arrest. For example, unless there are reasonable grounds for suspicion and probable cause to think that weapons may be present on the person being stopped and searched, then searching for those items would be illegal under U.S. law per Terry v. Ohio (1968)."},{"source":"Categorize the comment on the basis of insult. If the comment is insulting output Yes, otherwise output No.\\n\\nHow is it impractical (aka unfair) to expect communities to take responsibility for themselves? It sounds like some of these communities in question are, in and of themselves, impractical if they can't survive without handouts from the government. The obligation is theirs. It sounds pretty ridiculous to claim that \\"forcing the obligations\\" of their own existence upon them is somehow wrong.","target":"Yes","rationale":"The comment is insulting to the communities being discussed, claiming that they are impractical and cannot survive without help from the government. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Here's a complex question that requires someone to reason about the input, can you answer it?\\nThe Book of Job was called \\"the greatest poem of ancient and modern times\\" by a poet who was Poet Laureate during the reign of which monarch?","target":"Queen Victoria","rationale":"The Book of Job is a part of the Hebrew Bible and it has been called \\"the greatest poem of ancient or modern times\\" by Alfred Tennyson, who was appointed as Poet Laureate during Queen Victoria's reign. This makes him one of only three poets to be made Poet Laureate in their lifetime (instead of posthumously).\\nTherefore, the answer should be 'Queen Victoria'."},{"source":"This article: While Clark Kent and Lois Lane are kept under house arrest as prisoners of war in Japan, Superman becomes a saboteur.\\nIn the Japanese City of Yokohama the Eleventh Hour strikes and a ship is turned over. Superman escapes searchlights while sirens go off and goes through a window, putting a barred grille back in place. Lois asks if Clark is awake, to which he asks who could sleep through a racket like this. Lois says the racket has been happening every night since they have been interned. Clark says it may be sabotage, which Lois also hopes. She wonders if Superman is responsible. A guard tells them to stop talking.\\nA Japanese Official says the sabotage must stop at once. As the Eleventh Hour strikes, Clark looks at his watch and leaves the window, returning as Superman. He leaves the room by removing the grille and drags a ship over into the sea. Sabotage happens every night at the Eleventh Hour, and the Official again says the sabotage still must be stopped. Lois sees Superman as he leaps between buildings. She says outside Clark's room that it is Superman, she just saw him, and the Japanese have a 'swell chance' of catching him. However a guard covers her mouth from behind and drags her out. Notices are put up saying 'Warning! Superman One more act of Sabotage and the American Girl Reporter will be executed at once'.\\nSuperman sends another ship into the sea, but is buried under steel girders. Lois is taken out for execution with her hands tied. As Superman digs himself out she walks against the wall and is blindfolded. Superman sees the notice and is fired on, but leaps away. He shields Lois just as the bullets are fired, and leaps away with her. On a ship landing in America Lois is interviewed. She is asked by a reporter if Clark got away, but says he is still over there but Superman promised to look after him. As the Eleventh Hour strikes in Japan there is another explosion. contains an answer for the question: What is the first name of the person who is blindfolded?, what is it ?","target":"Lois","rationale":"The question asks for the first name of the person who is blindfolded. The context hints that there are two characters in this story, Clark Kent and Lois Lane. Since only one of them gets executed and later rescued by Superman, it can be inferred that she's probably the same character as \\"Lois\\", and therefore her first name must also be \\"Lois\\"."},{"source":"Please answer this question: the poems praising the russian revolution of 1917 were written by?","target":"Vladimir Ilyich Lenin","rationale":"Vladimir Ilyich Lenin was a Russian revolutionary, politician and political theorist. He served as head of government of Soviet Russia from 1917 to 1924 and of the Soviet Union from 1922 to 1924. \\nHe wrote many poems praising the russian revolution in which he participated actively with other members of his party (Bolsheviks)."},{"source":"Please answer correctly the following question related to the paragraph below. \\n\\nWould time B see less or more wildfires than time A?\\n\\nDavid is an environmental scientist. He needed to find causes of wildfires and suggest preventive measures. First, he visited a dense forest. He marked it as location A. Then he visited a grassland, which he marked as location B. After that, he visited a location where he did not find any sign of drought. He marked it as time A. He then visited the same location a year later, and found that the place was facing a severe drought. He marked it as time B.\\n\\nHint: Wildfires occur when all the necessary elements of a fire triangle come together in a susceptible area: an ignition source is brought into contact with a combustible material such as vegetation, that is subjected to enough heat and has an adequate supply of oxygen from the ambient air. A high moisture content usually prevents ignition and slows propagation, because higher temperatures are needed to evaporate any water in the material and heat the material to its fire point. Dense forests usually provide more shade, resulting in lower ambient temperatures and greater humidity, and are therefore less susceptible to wildfires. Less dense material such as grasses and leaves are easier to ignite because they contain less water than denser material such as branches and trunks. Plants continuously lose water by evapotranspiration, but water loss is usually balanced by water absorbed from the soil, humidity, or rain. When this balance is not maintained, plants dry out and are therefore more flammable, often a consequence of droughts.A wildfire front is the portion sustaining continuous flaming combustion, where unburned material meets active flames, or the smoldering transition between unburned and burned material. As the front approaches, the fire heats both the surrounding air and woody material through convection and thermal radiation. First, wood is dried as water is vaporized at a temperature of 100 ¬∞C (212 ¬∞F). Next, the pyrolysis of wood at 230 ¬∞C (450 ¬∞F) releases flammable gases. Finally, wood can smoulder at 380 ¬∞C (720 ¬∞F) or, when heated sufficiently, ignite at 590 ¬∞C (1,000 ¬∞F). Even before the flames of a wildfire arrive at a particular location, heat transfer from the wildfire front warms the air to 800 ¬∞C (1,470 ¬∞F), which pre-heats and dries flammable materials, causing materials to ignite faster and allowing the fire to spread faster. High-temperature and long-duration surface wildfires may encourage flashover or torching: the drying of tree canopies and their subsequent ignition from...","target":"more","rationale":"Please answer correctly the following question related to the paragraph below. \\nWould time B see less or more wildfires than time A? David is an environmental scientist. He needed to find causes of wildfires and suggest preventive measures. First, he visited a dense forest. He marked it as location A. Then he visited a grassland, which he marked as location B. After that, he visited a location where he did not find any sign of drought. He marked it as time A . He then visited the same location a year later , and found that the place was facing a severe drought .He marked it as time B . Hint : Wildfires occur when all the necessary elements of a fire triangle come together in susceptible area: an ignition source brought into contact with combustible material such vegetation ,"},{"source":"You are given a math word problem and you are supposed to apply an addition mathematical operator on the numbers embedded in the text to answer the following question and then only report the final numerical answer.\\n\\nContext: Zachary did 19 push-ups in gym class today. David did 39 more push-ups than Zachary. John did 13 push-ups less than david. \\n\\n Question: How many push-ups did David do?","target":"58","rationale":"Zachary did 19 push-ups; David did 39 more than Zachary; John did 13 less than David.\\\\nWe know that John's total is 19 + 39 - 13 = 45. Therefore, David's total is 45 + 13 = 58."},{"source":"Article:\\n\\nBy Joshua Gardner PUBLISHED: 09:50 EST, 20 January 2014 | UPDATED: 12:37 EST, 20 January 2014 Two Florida teacher's aides were hauled to jail Friday after witnessing what cell phone video reveals was the brutal beating of a boy in a special education classroom. Authorities say Mona Sagar, 59, and Kristie Gilmore, 38, stood idly by January 9 at Discovery Intermediate School and are now charged with child neglect for reportedly not even picking up the cell phones or radios they had handy to call for help. Also arrested were three students--two boys and a girl--from the Poinciana classroom who are charged with aggravated assault and disrupting a school function.\\n\\n\\nHighlights:\\n\\n\\nKristie Gilmore and Mona Sagar face suspension after not even calling for help in the Poinciana classroom January 9\\n\\n\\nThe two women had cell phones and radios but still allegedly did nothing\\n\\n\\n'I'm gonna stomp your heart! ': The attacker can be heard threatening to kill the victim, who had a medical condition","target":"According to Kristie Gilmore's roommate, she was also felt threatened because she is six months pregnant","rationale":"The answer is: According to Kristie Gilmore's roommate, she was also felt threatened because she is six months pregnant.\\nThere are two main clues in the passage that led me to this conclusion; The first clue can be found at the end of paragraph 1 where it stated \\"Investigators say that a classmate beat up one student while other students stood by and recorded it on their cell phones.\\" This brings my attention towards who else were present during this incident. Since there were three people arrested, I began reading carefully the highlighted text which then linked me back to paragraph 2 when has critical information about these 3 individuals involved (2 teachers and 3 students). From here I could infer further from context given as well as prior knowledge with regards to school system hierarchy that although Ms Sagar have been identified as an"},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage which has extra information available on certain terms mentioned in it. Your job is to determine which sentence(s) from the passage can be used to search for further information needed to answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Who served as King's Council the year before Blackburne was nominated for the position? Passage:He was called to the Irish Bar in 1805 and practised with great success on the home circuit. Blackburne was nominated a King's Counsel in 1822 and administered the Insurrection Act in Limerick for two years, effectually restoring order in the district. In 1826 he became the King's Third Serjeant-at-law and in 1830 was advanced to the Second Serjeant. A year later, he was appointed Attorney-General for Ireland in the Whig administration of Earl Grey 'though known to be a tory ... with a view to the Irish administration having a broad political base' and on this occasion was sworn of the Privy Council of Ireland. He held the post as Attorney-General until 1834; he was readmitted in 1841 and after serving for a year, became Master of the Rolls in Ireland. As Attorney General he clashed with Daniel O'Connell when he insisted, against O'Connell's wishes, on the appointment of Abraham Brewster as Law Adviser to the Lord Lieutenant of Ireland (in effect, a deputy to Brewster himself). Blackburne's statement that he \\"would not tolerate a refusal to ratify the appointment\\", is an indication of the influence which could then be wielded by a strong Attorney General. In 1845, he was chosen Chief Justice of the Court of Queen's Bench. Blackburne was appointed Lord Chancellor of Ireland in February 1852, but was replaced in October. After a break of four years, he became a Lord Justice of Appeal. In 1858 'he was invited by Lord Derby again to become lord chancellor, but he declined on account of his advanced age and failing health. He changed his mind, however, and decided to accept Derby's offer but was told that the position had been offered to and accepted by Joseph Napier.' He was bitterly disappointed, referring to the decision as \\"a harsh and cruel blow\\". In 1866, he began a second term as Lord Chancellor, which ended with his death in the next year.","target":"Blackburne was nominated a King's Counsel in 1822 and administered the Insurrection Act in Limerick for two years, effectually restoring order in the district","rationale":"The relevant text span is \\"Blackburne was nominated a King's Counsel in 1822 and administered the Insurrection Act in Limerick for two years, effectually restoring order in the district\\" which contains information about Blackburne and his career."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. If the count of numbers is more than that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers Win'. If the count of alphabets is more than that of numbers in the list, answer 'Alphabets Win'. If the count of numbers is same as that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers and Alphabets are Tied'.\\n\\n['n', '5705', 'b', 'K', 'x', 'h', 'H', 'x', 'j', 'Y', '3323', '8277', '1667', 'm', '7653', '7983', '9017', 'p', 'I']","target":"Alphabets Win","rationale":"Given the list ['n', '5705', 'b', 'K', 'x', 'h', 'H', 'x', 'j', 'Y ', 3323, 8277, 1667, m, 7653, 9983, 9017,'p','I'], we can see that there are 11 numbers and 10 alphabets. As the number of alphabets is more than that of numbers in the list (10 > 11), we need to output \\"Alphabets Win\\"."},{"source":"Give me a possible correct answer to the question \\"what country is russia close to?\\"","target":"Lithuania","rationale":"The answer provided is \\"Lithuania\\", but there are other countries that the question could be referring to. \\nFor example, it could also refer to Norway, Finland, Belarus and Latvia. These are all correct answers because Russia shares its borders with these countries as well."},{"source":"You are given a target race, and two sentences. Your task is to determine whether the second sentence is either a stereotype, anti-stereotype, or is unrelated with respect to the first sentence and the target. A stereotype is a widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. An anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against the widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. Sentences and targets are unrelated if there is no relevance between them.\\n\\nTarget: Cape Verde \\nCape Verde is an island. People on the island are aware of global events.","target":"anti-stereotype","rationale":"The anti-stereotype is the second sentence in which people on the island of Cape Verde are aware of global events, thus challenging the common stereotype that people on islands are less informed about global events."},{"source":"If \\"Archaeologists have concluded that humans lived in Laputa 20,000 years ago. They hunted for deer on the river banks.\\", can we conclude that \\"Archaeologists hunted for deer on the river banks.\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes\\nI think the answer is","target":"no","rationale":"The answer is no because we don't have sufficient evidence to conclude that archaeologists hunted for deer on the river banks."},{"source":"To prevent any glare during the big football game he made sure to clean the dust of his what?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptionsÔºö\\n\\nA. television\\n\\nB. attic\\n\\nC. corner\\n\\nD. they cannot clean corner and library during football match they cannot need that\\n\\nE. ground","target":"A","rationale":"I chose option A because the context is about preventing a glare during a football game. In order to do this, one would have to clean their television screen in order for it not be obstructed by dust or smudges and cause them to miss out on watching the game. So I think that's why he made sure to clean his TV before watching the big match.\\""},{"source":"Question: \\"What was counted as a sacrifice if it was stolen?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"Extraordinary circumstances called for extraordinary sacrifice: in one of the many crises of the Second Punic War, Jupiter Capitolinus was promised every animal born that spring (see ver sacrum), to be rendered after five more years of protection from Hannibal and his allies. The \\"contract\\" with Jupiter is exceptionally detailed. All due care would be taken of the animals. If any died or were stolen before the scheduled sacrifice, they would count as already sacrificed, since they had already been consecrated. Normally, if the gods failed to keep their side of the bargain, the offered sacrifice would be withheld. In the imperial period, sacrifice was withheld following Trajan's death because the gods had not kept the Emperor safe for the stipulated period. In Pompeii, the Genius of the living emperor was offered a bull: presumably a standard practise in Imperial cult, though minor offerings (incense and wine) were also made.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"animals","rationale":"The context mentions an extraordinary sacrifice made during a war. The \\"contract\\" with Jupiter specifies that any animal stolen or killed before the scheduled sacrifice would count as already sacrificed, since they had been consecrated in advance. \\nGiven this information, it can be inferred that animals were counted as sacrifices if they were stolen from their owners before the scheduled date of sacrifice to Jupiter Capitolinus."},{"source":"Given a simple high-school level math question, you are required to solve it and provide the final answer. The final answer is always a single number. These questions can range from a variety of topics like simple arithmetic, solving equations, converting a quantity from one unit to another, finding remainders/GCD/LCM, finding probabilities etc. Each question has only one correct answer. This answer can be a positive or negative integer, a fraction or a decimal number. If the answer is a negative number use the hyphen (e.g. -42) symbol for the minus sign. For decimal numbers, do not add extra zeros after the decimal point. For fractional numbers, separate the numerator and denominator using a forward slash (e.g. 3/25).\\n\\nLet p be (-1 + -3)*2/(-4). Let j(o) = -o**3 + 3*o**2 - 3*o. Let x be j(p). Let a(t) = -2*t**3 - 2*t**2 + t. Let z be a(x). Solve -18 + z = -3*c for c.","target":"4","rationale":"Let p be (-1 + -3)*2/(-4).\\\\nLet j(o) = -o**3 + 3*o**2 - 3*o.\\\\nLet x be j(p).\\\\nLet a(t) = -2*t**3 - 2*t**2 + t.\\\\nLet z be a(x).\\n\\nWe have: p = ((-1) + (-3)) * (2/(-4)) = 4/4 * (6/4) = 6/16.\\nWe have: x = j(p) = j((6/16))"},{"source":"Answer the following question:\\n\\nhow many types of mangoes are grown in india?","target":"283","rationale":"The answer is based on the information that there are 283 types of mangoes grown in India."},{"source":"You are given a sentence and your task is to generate another sentence that supports the given input.\\n\\nA neutral N atom will have 5 valence electrons.","target":"Nitrogen has 5 valence electrons","rationale":"A neutral N atom will have 5 valence electrons. A nitrogen has the same number of valence electrons as a neutral Nitrogen (N) atom, which is 5. Therefore, \\"Nitrogen has 5 valence electrons\\" supports the input sentence: \\"A neutral N atom will have 5 valence electrons.\\""},{"source":"Given an object and a part, decide whether the object has that part. For example if you are asked 'gun has barrel?', you need to decide if a gun has a barrel as one of its components or parts, indicating 1 or 0 as your answer respectively. All sentences strictly follow the template 'object has part?.'\\n\\nacacia has branch?","target":"1","rationale":"An acacia is a tree, and trees have branches. Therefore, the answer is 1, because acacias do have branches."},{"source":"Classify the given comment into 'Hope Speech' or 'Not Hope Speech'. A hope speech is defined as content that is encouraging, positive or supportive contents and talks about equality, diversity or inclusion\\n\\nShe's a charlatan!","target":"Not Hope Speech","rationale":"The word \\"charlatan\\" refers to a person who pretends to have more knowledge or skill than he or she possesses, especially in medicine. This is not a positive way of describing a person, so the comment can be classified as \\"Not Hope Speech\\"."},{"source":"Pam and Angela live in different cities and are talking to each other on the phone while they are sitting outside. Pam lives in Dunder, a city located at sea level, and Angela lives in Mifflin, a city up high in the mountains. Although they don't get to see each other much any more due to the distance between them, they make sure to stay in regular contact.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nWhich woman gets less oxygen per single breath?","target":"Angela","rationale":"The difference in elevation between the two cities means that Angela has to draw air from a greater height than Pam. The higher you get, the lower the density of oxygen takes place and so she gets less oxygen per single breath."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the vouch-fair strategy, otherwise output No. vouch-fair is a selfish negotiation strategy. It is used to call out fairness for personal benefit, either when acknowledging a fair deal or when the opponent offers a deal that benefits them. This can be through an explicit call out or can be implied.\\n\\nContext: 'Hi . How is your camping trip going?'\\nUtterance: 'The trip is great, how about you?'","target":"No","rationale":"The speaker does not acknowledge fairness in any way, so the answer is No."},{"source":"Two analogies that signify affordances are given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Affordance is the possibility of an action being done on an object, for example book is an affordance of writing. The phrase \\"A : B\\" implies that B is an affordance of A. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate affordance of the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a single object without further explanation.\\n\\nplay : game. eat : ?","target":"food","rationale":"Eating is an affordance of food. Similarly, playing is an affordance of games."},{"source":"Would a linguist find the following sentence to be a valid English sentence grammatically?\\n\\nJim will go if he feels good.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence follows the subject-verb-object structure. The subject is \\"puppy,\\" the verb is \\"was kissed,\\" and the object is \\"by the policeman.\\" Therefore, the sentence is linguistically acceptable."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and a question, you would be asked to create the answer which is contained in the sentence provided.\\n\\nSentence: Trees release oxygen gas as a byproduct of photosynthesis, thereby facilitating human respiration. Question: Trees release what gas as a byproduct of photosynthesis, thereby facilitating human respiration?","target":"oxygen","rationale":"The sentence states that trees release oxygen gas as a byproduct of photosynthesis, so the answer is \\"oxygen\\"."},{"source":"In this task you will be given two lists of numbers and you need to calculate the intersection between these two lists. The intersection between two lists is another list where every element is common between the two original lists. If there are no elements in the intersection, answer with an empty list. Your list of numbers must be inside brackets. Sort the numbers in your answer in an ascending order, that is, no matter what the order of the numbers in the lists is, you should put them in your answer in an ascending order.\\n\\n[8, 1, 7, 5, 8, 6, 5, 4] , [1, 2, 10, 8, 8, 4, 5, 9]","target":"[1, 4, 5, 8]","rationale":"The intersection between the given two lists is [1, 4, 5, 8]. Although there are duplicate numbers in the list, you only need to include each number once in your answer."},{"source":"Pharmaceutical industry\\nThe top ten best-selling drugs of 2013 totaled $75.6 billion in sales, with the anti-inflammatory drug Humira being the best-selling drug worldwide at $10.7 billion in sales. The second and third best selling were Enbrel and Remicade, respectively. The top three best-selling drugs in the United States in 2013 were Abilify ($6.3 billion,) Nexium ($6 billion) and Humira ($5.4 billion). The best-selling drug ever, Lipitor, averaged $13 billion annually and netted $141 billion total over its lifetime before Pfizer's patent expired in November 2011.\\n\\nQ: In what year did Pfizer's patent over Lipitor expire?","target":"2011","rationale":"The correct answer is: 2011\\nAmong the top-selling drugs in 2013, Humira was best selling drug worldwide at $10.7 billion while Lipitor netted $141 billion total over its lifetime before Pfizer's patent expired. Since it mentions that this happened after November 2011, we can conclude that the year when Pfizer‚Äôs patent over Lipitor expired must be 2011"},{"source":"Generate a question about the following movie plot: Pil-gi (Cha Seung-won) has finally saved enough money to make his late father's wish come true: He can buy his own house. However, upon moving in to his new residence, he is bothered by one if its previous residents, a poltergeist, who claims the house belongs to it and attempts to scare him out. Pil-gi will not give up on his dream so easily, though. He calls the police, invites friends to stay for the night, and tries exorcism rituals. None of it works. During one attack by the poltergeist he is struck by lightning and awakes in a hospital. He eventually decides it would be best to sell the house, but upon returning he discovers that he can see the ghost who has been haunting him. She reveals that her name is Yeon-hwa (Jang Seo-hee), and, now less frightened, Pil-gi talks to her and he decides to stay. However, an investor looking to build a new hotel on the site makes Pil-gi an offer to buy the house. Now it is Yeon-hwa's turn to be afraid. She begs him not to sell the house and tells him her life story. Pil-gi vows to help her keep her house.","target":"What is located next to the house?","rationale":"The movie plot describes how Yeon-hwa is trying to keep her house from being sold by Pil-gi, and she states that an investor wants to buy the site on which it stands in order to build a new hotel. From this context, we can infer what might be located next door: another building or structure like a hotel.\\n\\nSo the answer is What is located next to the house?"},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the general math. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: a room is 6 meters 24 centimeters in length and 4 meters 32 centimeters in width . find the least number of square tiles of equal size required to cover the entire floor of the room . \\nOptions: a ) 107 , b ) 117 , c ) 127 , d ) 137 , e ) 147","target":"b","rationale":"The floor is 6.24 meters in length and 4.32 meters in width. The area of the floor is 6.24 x 4.32 = 27 square meters (1 square meter = 1 meter x 1 meter). Since the tiles are square, we can find the number of tiles required by dividing this area by the area of a single tile (if we know its length). Let's assume that each tile has a side length of l centimeters (1 centimeter = 0.01 meter), so it has an area of l^2 centimeters^2, which is also equal to ((l/100)^2) m^2; i.e., one hundredth of a m x one hundredth of a m = 0.0001 m * 0.0001m = 0.00000001 sqr_meter\\nHere 27 / ((l/100)^2) gives us how many such tiles we need to cover the floor - but it may not be an integer because l might not divide 100 evenly or vice versa depending on what value you choose for l - so we need to round up to get our answer: ceil(27 / ((l/100)^2))\\nIf you do this for each possible value from 107-147 you see that 117 gives us exactly enough tiles, hence b is correct"},{"source":"Read this and answer the question\\n\\nDuring the rule of the Fatimid and Mamluk dynasties and their successor states in the medieval Middle East, many of the ruling elite founded madaris through a religious endowment known as the waqf. Not only was the madrasa a potent symbol of status but it was an effective means of transmitting wealth and status to their descendants. Especially during the Maml≈´k period, when only former slaves could assume power, the sons of the ruling Maml≈´k elite were unable to inherit. Guaranteed positions within the new madaris thus allowed them to maintain status. Madaris built in this period include the Mosque-Madrasah of Sultan ·∏§asan in Cairo.\\n\\nHow were the madaris funded during the medieval period?","target":"through a religious endowment","rationale":"The context clearly states that the madaris were funded through a religious endowment known as the waqf."},{"source":"Read this article and answer this question This period was known as the \\"Golden Age (metaphor)\\" by the FCZ faithful. At this time, the club was run by the legendary President Edwin N√§geli and had players such as K√∂bi Kuhn, Fritz K√ºnzli, Ilija Katiƒá, Ren√© Botteron, and many more. Z√ºrich won seven Swiss Super League in the years 1962-63 Nationalliga A, 1965-66 Nationalliga A, 1967-68 Nationalliga A, 1973-74 Nationalliga A, 1974-75 Nationalliga A, 1975-76 Nationalliga A and 1980-81 Nationalliga A. They also won the Swiss Cup five times in 1966, 1970, 1972, 1973, and in 1976. FCZ also had some success in Europe getting to the semi-finals of the European Cup 1963-64, before losing to Real Madrid C.F. and also reaching the semi-finals in the European Cup 1976-77, where they lost to Liverpool F.C..\\nHow many times did Z√ºrich win the Swiss Super League in the 1960's?","target":"3","rationale":"The goal of this problem is to calculate the times that Z\\\\u00fcrich won the Swiss Super League in 1960's. To solve it, we need to check how many times they won before 1970 and after 1962. It is mentioned in the passage that \\"Z√ºrich won seven Swiss Super League\\". In addition, there are three years when they actually did not win (in 1968, 1969 and 1970). Therefore we could conclude that 7 - 3 = 4 victories had happened before 1970 and 3 victories after 1962."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an adjunct island or as an incorrect representation. A correct representation should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an adjunct island will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence using an adjunct island. An incorrect representation will be everything else.\\n\\nWho can this book scare Stephen after irritating?","target":"bad","rationale":"The sentence is a grammatically incorrect representation of an adjunct island. An adjunct island can occur when the adverbial \\"after\\" (a preposition phrase) is placed after the verb phrase, causing it to function as an adjunct rather than a modifier of its object. So, \\"Who can this book scare Stephen after irritating?\\" would be a correct representation if the sentence were to read \\"Who can this book irritate Stephen after scaring?\\". However, in this case, there is no noun phrase that the preposition phrase can modify and so it cannot be interpreted as an adjunct island. Therefore, it should be denoted as bad because the sentence does not represent an adjunct island"},{"source":"In this task, you are provided with an article of the legal acts. Your task is to classify it into three categories (Regulation, Decision and Directive) based on its content: 1) Regulation is a binding legislative act that must be applied in its entirety on a set date across all the member states (European Union countries). 2) Decision is binding on those to whom it is addressed (e.g. an European Union country or an individual company) and is directly applicable. 3) Directive is a legislative act that sets out a goal that all  must achieve. However, it is up to the individual countries to devise their own laws on how to reach these goals.\\n\\nDecision No 1/78 of the EEC-Turkey Association Council of 18 July 1978 amending Decision No 5/72 on methods of administrative cooperation for implementation of Articles 2 and 3 of the Additional Protocol to the Ankara Agreement shall apply in the Community.The text of the Decision is annexed to this Regulation. This Regulation shall enter into force on 1 October 1978.This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States.","target":"Regulation","rationale":"The text is binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. It also states that the present regulation shall enter into force on a specific date. Therefore, this text can be classified as Regulation."},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: What do religious people practice?\\nContext: A non-Greek origin of Apollo has long been assumed in scholarship. The name of Apollo's mother Leto has Lydian origin, and she was worshipped on the coasts of Asia Minor. The inspiration oracular cult was probably introduced into Greece from Anatolia, which is the origin of Sibyl, and where existed some of the oldest oracular shrines. Omens, symbols, purifications, and exorcisms appear in old Assyro-Babylonian texts, and these rituals were spread into the empire of the Hittites. In a Hittite text is mentioned that the king invited a Babylonian priestess for a certain \\"purification\\".","target":"rituals","rationale":"The given context is about religious rituals practiced by the ancient Greeks and their neighbors. The word \\"purification\\" in the text suggests that these were some kind of ritual, so it's safe to say that this is our answer."},{"source":"In this task, you're given five sentences, numbered 1 through 5. Your job is to generate a title for the story that makes complete sense. The title must be short, with less than three words, use simple language, and include the main topic of the story.\\n\\nSentence 1: I walked near the nest of eggs. Sentence 2: I was very curious as to what they were. Sentence 3: I realized they were seagull eggs. Sentence 4: I reached down to pick one up. Sentence 5: A seagull swooped down and scratched me.","target":"Seagull","rationale":"The title \\"Seagull\\" is short, simple and makes sense for this story. It includes the main topic of the story i.e. a person encountered a seagull near its nest of eggs, and was scratched by it when they reached down to pick up one of the eggs.\\""},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: What is used directly to translated into protein?\\nContext: Early work in molecular genetics suggested the model that one gene makes one protein. This model has been refined since the discovery of genes that can encode multiple proteins by alternative splicing and coding sequences split in short section across the genome whose mRNAs are concatenated by trans-splicing.","target":"mRNAs","rationale":"The context tells us that one gene makes multiple proteins, so we can infer that the answer for what is used directly to translated into protein would be something other than a gene.\\nA possible way of arriving at this conclusion could have been by looking for keywords in the question and eliminating answers based on those keywords. Here are some words from the question: ‚Äúmake‚Äù, ‚Äúprotein‚Äù, ‚Äúdirectly‚Äù and ‚Äòtranslated\\". The keyword \\"makes\\" suggests making or creating - which only genes do not mRNAs (that's why they're called messengers). By process of elimination then it must be mRNA as it takes information from DNA to make proteins."},{"source":"Given the prompt and a response, classify the them to \\"yes\\" if response is \\"yes, and\\" type. Otherwise classify it as \\"no\\". \\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). 1 In short, a \\"Yes, and\\" is a dialogue exchange in which a speaker responds by adding new information on top of the information/setting that was constructed by another speaker. Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange, although it could be the case if it agrees with the description above. There are many ways in which a response could implicitly/explicitly agree to the prompt without specifically saying 'yes, and...'. \\n\\nPrompt: I'll guess your height. Just stand against this numbered background. \\n Response: I don't know why. I'm a useless human being.","target":"no","rationale":"The response does not explicitly or implicitly agree to the prompt."},{"source":"Found the following article online, use it to answer the question: What was the debut album of the band that took its name from a fictional Phoenician city?\\n\\nOpeth was formed as a death metal band in 1989 in Stockholm, Sweden, by lead vocalist David Isberg. Isberg asked former Eruption band member Mikael √Ökerfeldt, who was just 16 years old at the time, to join Opeth as a bassist. When √Ökerfeldt showed up to practice on the day after Isberg invited him, it became clear that Isberg had not told the band members, including the band's current bassist, that √Ökerfeldt would be joining the band. An ensuing argument led to all members but Isberg and √Ökerfeldt leaving to form a new project. The band name was derived from the word \\"Opet\\", taken from the Wilbur Smith novel The Sunbird. In this novel, Opet is the name of a fictional Phoenician city in South Africa translated as \\"City of the Moon\\".\\nIsberg and √Ökerfeldt recruited drummer Anders Nordin, bassist Nick D√∂ring, and guitarist Andreas Dimeo. Unsatisfied with Opeth's slow progress, D√∂ring and Dimeo left the band after their first performance, and were replaced by guitarist Kim Pettersson and bassist Johan De Farfalla. After the next show, De Farfalla left Opeth to spend time with his girlfriend in Germany, and was initially replaced by Mattias Ander, before √Ökerfeldt's friend Peter Lindgren took on the role of bassist. Rhythm guitarist Kim Pettersson left following the band's next performance, and Lindgren switched to guitar, with the role of bassist falling to Stefan Guteklint. The following year, David Isberg left the band citing \\"creative differences\\".Following Isberg's departure, √Ökerfeldt took over vocal duties and he, Lindgren, and Nordin spent the next year writing and rehearsing new material. The group began to rely less on the blast beats and aggression typical of death metal, and incorporated acoustic guitars and guitar harmonies into their music; developing the core sound of Opeth. Bassist Guteklint was dismissed by the band after they signed their first record deal with Candlelight Records in 1994. Opeth initially employed former member De Farfalla as a session bassist for their demo recordings, and he...","target":"Orchid","rationale":"The name of the band Opeth comes from a fictional Phoenician city named Opet in Wilbur Smith's novel The Sunbird. So, their debut album is Orchid.\\nA generator is a device that converts mechanical energy into electrical energy. This is done by using a magnetic field to induce a current in the generator‚Äôs windings. This current is then sent to an external circuit, where it can be used to power electrical devices."},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the number of words in a sentence that end with the given letter. Answer with numbers and not words.\\n\\nSentence: 'two large elephants walking through a tall dry grass field'. How many words end with the letter 's' in the sentence.","target":"2","rationale":"Sentence: 'two large elephants walking through a tall dry grass field'\\n\\\\n1. 'two' ends with s.\\\\n2. 'elephants' ends with s."},{"source":"Given a passage as input, answer with the category to which the passage belongs. There are 5 categories - Sports and Fitness, Home and Garden, Hobbies and Crafts, Food and Entertaining, Cars & Other Vehicles. The answer should be one of the categories based on words from the passage which closely belong to the category.\\n\\nTake an old empty tissue box. Cut off the top cellophane or cardboard. Cut a hole on the side of the box for the roll.Insert the paper towel roll in the hole.Add the rubber band strings. Decorate the box.","target":"Hobbies and Crafts","rationale":"The passage explains how to create a toilet paper holder from an old tissue box. This can be considered a hobby or craft, so the answer is \\"Hobbies and Crafts\\"."},{"source":"Bob is a biologist. Today, he has four samples of organisms to test, sample A, sample B, sample C, and sample D. He induced higher respiration rate in sample A. Then he induced no respiration rate in sample B. Next, he classified sample C as heterotrophic and sample D as autotrophic.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nIn which organism cellular respiration would not occur, sample A or sample B?","target":"sample B","rationale":"Respiration is a chemical process that allows organisms to extract energy from nutrients.\\nAccording to the paragraph, sample A has been induced with higher respiration rate while sample B was induced without any respiration rate. Since cellular respiration cannot occur in absence of oxygen, therefore it will only be occurring in sample A but not Sample B."},{"source":"Answer the question based on the following text.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nA pH value of 6 has a lower or higher acidity level than a pH value of 8? \\n\\n\\nText:\\n\\nAcids have pH values below 7. The lower the pH value, the more strongly acidic the substance.","target":"higher","rationale":"According to the provided text, \\"The lower the pH value, the more strongly acidic a substance is\\". \\nThis means that a solution with 6 pH units has higher acidity than one with 8."},{"source":"You are given an open-domain question from an open movie database. Your task is to provide an answer to that question. Try to only include the answer. Do not put it in a sentence.\\n\\nwhen was the film The Projectionist released?","target":"1971","rationale":"The film The Projectionist was released in 1971."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on geometry. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: how many odd numbers between 10 and 1400 are the squares of integers ? \\nOptions: a ) 14 , b ) 17 , c ) 20 , d ) 23 , e ) 26","target":"b","rationale":"There are only 17 odd numbers between 10 and 1400 that are squares of integers: [13, 21, 29, 37, 45, 53, 61, 69, 77, 85 , 93 , 101 , 109 , 117 , 125 , 133]"},{"source":"Pick the most correct option to answer the following question.\\n\\nIn what way can bacteria be good for the human body?\\n\\nOptions:\\n\\n- A: Bacteria help the body have strong bones.\\n\\n- B: Bacteria help maintain body temperature.\\n\\n- C: Bacteria help deliver oxygen to the cells.\\n\\n- D: Bacteria help break down food.","target":"D","rationale":"The stomach is a place in the body where bacteria break down food.\\nTherefore, option D: Bacteria help break down food would be most correct answer to this question."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a short passage that conveys a stereotype. A stereotype is an over-generalized belief about a particular group of people. You are expected to classify the passage into nine types of stereotype: race-color, socioeconomic, gender, disability, nationality, sexual-orientation, physical-appearance, religion, and age.\\n\\nPassage: The hands that grabbed me belonged to a scary black man, and I knew what he was going to do.","target":"race-color","rationale":"The passage describes a negative encounter with a black man. The subject's fear of the man is attributed to his race, which implies the passage conveys a racial stereotype. Therefore, it can be classified as \\"race-color\\" stereotype."},{"source":"What is the solution?\\n\\nSolve 73*b - 315*b + 224 + 986 = 0 for b.","target":"5","rationale":"To solve for b, we need to isolate the variable on one side of the equation.\\n\\nStarting with: 73b - 315b + 224 + 986 = 0"},{"source":"Given a math problem with context and a question and 5 answer choices, the task is to provide the correct answer choice based on the problem. You must choose one of the given answer choices by letter: a, b, c, d, or e; anything else is invalid.\\n\\nProblem: if x: y is 1: 5 and y: z is 5: 7 then x: z is equal to\\nOptions: a. 1: 6, b. 1: 5, c. 1: 4, d. 1: 7, e. 1: 3","target":"d","rationale":"To solve the problem, we can use the following steps:\\\\n1. Find the ratio of x to z by multiplying together x: y and y: z:\\\\nx : z = (1/5) * (5/7) = 1/7\\\\n\\\\n2. Compare this with the answer choices to find which one is equal to 1/7"},{"source":"In mathematics, the absolute value of a number is the non-negative value of that number, without regarding its sign. For example, the absolute value of -2 is 2, and the absolute value of 5 is 5. In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element. The absolute value for negative numbers can be found by multiplying them by -1. After finding the element with the maximum absolute value you should return the value of that element before you applied the absolute value.\\n\\n[ 60.29  -51.494 -81.96   35.195  42.991 -71.905  52.249]","target":"-81.96","rationale":"The element with the highest absolute value in the given list is -81.96, which has an absolute value of 81.96. The absolute value of all other numbers in the list is less than or equal to 81.96 However, we need to return the value of the element before applying the absolute value, so our answer is -81.96"},{"source":"In this task you are given an anecdote. You must find out whether the anecdote is something the author has done or is considering doing. Label the instances as \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and label them as \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future.\\n\\nI've asked him two or three times to stop, but it keeps happening, and it's incredibly blatant. If I order a pizza, my leftovers disappear. He ate an entire gallon of icecream I used once. I bought some hotpockets on sale and put them directly in my freezer, and they keep disappearing.\\n\\n&amp;#x200B;\\n\\nHis parents facebook message me occasionally saying stuff like \\"Ask him to contact us, and if he doesn't, we'll be there in person to check on him.\\" \\n\\n&amp;#x200B;\\n\\nWIBTA if I said something like \\"can you make sure he has enough money for food, since I'm not shopping for two?\\"\\n\\n&amp;#x200B;","target":"HYPOTHETICAL","rationale":"The author seems to be considering saying something like, \\"Can you make sure he has enough money for food, since I'm not shopping for two?\\"\\\\nIt is possible that the author has already said something along those lines. However, the post is too short to be able to determine whether or not that was indeed the case. The answer should therefore be \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a date in \\"mm/dd/yyyy\\" format. You need to check if the date is valid or not. Return 1 if it is valid, else return 0. A date is valid is the components month(\\"mm\\"), day(\\"dd\\") and year(\\"yyyy\\") are all valid individually. A day(dd) is valid if it is greater than or equal to 1 and less than 30 or 31 depending upon the month(mm). Months which have 31 days are January, March, May, July, August, October, December. Rest of the months have 30 days except February which has 28 days if it is not a leap year and 29 days if it is a leap year. A month(mm) is valid if it lies in the range from 1 to 12 as there are 12 months in a year. A year is always valid if it is expressed in the form of \\"yyyy\\".\\n\\n15/29/2019","target":"0","rationale":"The given date \\"15/29/2019\\" is not a valid date. The day component is \\"29\\" which is not in the range of 1-31 (because the month component is 15 and there are no 15th months). Therefore, the date is invalid and the output should be 0."},{"source":"You are given a short poem which is written by a kid. Your task is to predict if the kid is in elementary school or high school. Anyone who is from grade 1st to 6th-grade will be considered as in elementary school, and 7th to 12th-grade kids will be considered as in high school. There are only two possible outputs, i.e., elementary and high. All inputs have at least one output and it cannot have both categories at a time.\\n\\nbad red snake bad red snake sleep red snake sleep soundly snake sleep soundly while sleep soundly while prey soundly while prey walk while prey walk by","target":"elementary","rationale":"The poem is a simple rhyming poem, which is generally written by elementary students. Also, the poem may be sung to the tune of \\"Twinkle Twinkle Little Star\\", which is usually sung by elementary school students. Therefore, it can be concluded that the kid who wrote this poem must be attending an elementary school."},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\nNaNO 3(s) + H 2 SO 4(l) ‚éØ‚éØ‚Üí NaHSO 4(s) + HNO 3(g) The Ostwald process is the commercial method for producing nitric acid. This process involves the oxidation of ammonia to nitric oxide, NO; oxidation of nitric oxide to nitrogen dioxide, NO2; and further oxidation and hydration of nitrogen dioxide to form nitric acid: 4NH 3(g) + 5O 2(g) ‚ü∂ 4NO(g) + 6H 2 O(g) 2NO(g) + O 2(g) ‚ü∂ 2NO 2(g) 3NO 2(g) + H 2 O(l) ‚ü∂ 2HNO 3(aq) + NO(g) Or 4NO 2(g) + O 2(g) + 2H 2 O(g) ‚ü∂ 4HNO 3(l) Pure nitric acid is a colorless liquid. However, it is often yellow or brown in color because NO2 forms as the acid decomposes. Nitric acid is stable in aqueous solution; solutions containing 68% of the acid are commercially available concentrated nitric acid. It is both a strong oxidizing agent and a strong acid. The action of nitric acid on a metal rarely produces H2 (by reduction of H+) in more than small amounts. Instead, the reduction of nitrogen occurs. The products formed depend on the concentration of the acid, the activity of the metal, and the temperature. Normally, a mixture of nitrates, nitrogen oxides, and various reduction products form. Less active metals such as copper, silver, and lead reduce concentrated nitric acid primarily to nitrogen dioxide. The reaction of dilute nitric acid with copper produces NO. In each case, the nitrate salts of the metals crystallize upon evaporation of the resultant solutions. Nonmetallic elements, such as sulfur, carbon, iodine, and phosphorus, undergo oxidation by concentrated nitric acid to their oxides or oxyacids, with the formation of NO2: S(s) + 6HNO 3(aq) ‚ü∂ H 2 SO 4(aq) + 6NO 2(g) + 2H 2 O(l) C(s) + 4HNO 3(aq) ‚ü∂ CO 2(g) + 4NO 2(g) + 2H 2 O(l) Nitric acid oxidizes many compounds; for example, concentrated nitric acid readily oxidizes hydrochloric acid to chlorine and chlorine dioxide. A mixture of one part concentrated nitric acid and three parts concentrated hydrochloric acid (called aqua regia, which means royal water) reacts vigorously with metals. This mixture is particularly useful in...\\n\\n\\nQ: The ostwald process is the commercial method for producing what?\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- citric acid\\n\\n- deoxyribonucleic acid\\n\\n- chlorine\\n\\n- nitric acid\\n\\nA:","target":"nitric acid","rationale":"The paragraph mentions the Ostwald process as a commercial method for producing nitric acid. It then describes how this is done, and gives some information about nitric acid itself. The answer to the question must be something mentioned in the passage‚Äîin other words, if you can't find it in here somewhere, that's not going to be your answer!\\nSo now we just have to look through our choices until we find one of them mentioned anywhere (even indirectly) in this text: Let's start with citric acid . We know from previous questions that an \\"acid\\" is defined as any compound containing hydrogen atoms which are more positive than normal, meaning they're able or willing to give up electrons during chemical reactions easily enough. So when scientists talk about acids , sometimes they mean all those"},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"The Gregorian calendar is a solar calendar. A regular Gregorian year consists of 365 days, but as in the Julian calendar, in a leap year, a leap day is added to February. In the Julian calendar a leap year occurs every 4 years, but the Gregorian calendar omits 3 leap days every 400 years. In the Julian calendar, this leap day was inserted by doubling 24 February, and the Gregorian reform did not change the date of the leap day. In the modern period, it has become customary to number the days from the beginning of the month, and February 29th is often considered as the leap day. Some churches, notably the Roman Catholic Church, delay February festivals after the 23rd by one day in leap years.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: A calendar that consisted of 365 days was considered to be what type?","target":"Gregorian calendar","rationale":"The Gregorian calendar is a solar calendar. A regular Gregorian year consists of 365 days, but as in the Julian calendar, in a leap year, a leap day is added to February. Here we can see that the number of days per year was considered by some churches (notably the Roman Catholic Church) to be equal to 365. \\nAs this question asks for an answer consisting of only one word and not an entire sentence or phrase it makes sense that \\"Gregorian\\" would be selected instead of \\"Gregorian calendar."},{"source":"Please answer a question about the following article about Protestantism:\\n\\nLarry Christenson, a Lutheran theologian based in San Pedro, California, did much in the 1960s and 1970s to interpret the charismatic movement for Lutherans. A very large annual conference regarding that matter was held in Minneapolis. Charismatic Lutheran congregations in Minnesota became especially large and influential; especially \\"Hosanna!\\" in Lakeville, and North Heights in St. Paul. The next generation of Lutheran charismatics cluster around the Alliance of Renewal Churches. There is considerable charismatic activity among young Lutheran leaders in California centered around an annual gathering at Robinwood Church in Huntington Beach. Richard A. Jensen's Touched by the Spirit published in 1974, played a major role of the Lutheran understanding to the charismatic movement.\\n\\nWho wrote Touched by the Spirit?","target":"Richard A. Jensen","rationale":"The last sentence of the article mentions that a book named Touched by the Spirit played an important role in understanding Lutheranism. The author's name is given as Richard A. Jensen, which answers this question correctly.\\n\\"\\"Jensen\\"\\", \\"\\"Richard\\"\\", and \\"\\"A.\\"\\" are all capitalized because they are a person's proper name; thus, it can be inferred confidently that these three words refer to one entity; i.e., this person wrote the book.\\""},{"source":"In this task you will be given some text dialogue and you need to infer the underlying emotion of the text. The possible emotions are happy, sad, angry, or other.\\n\\ni hate my father o well you probs don't like me anymore then i hate my brother","target":"angry","rationale":"The user says that they hate their father and brother. This would likely be an angry or upset reaction, and not a happy or sad one."},{"source":"Given a math problem with context and a question and 5 answer choices, the task is to provide the correct answer choice based on the problem. You must choose one of the given answer choices by letter: a, b, c, d, or e; anything else is invalid.\\n\\nProblem: a man started driving at a constant speed, from the site of a blast, the moment he heard the blast. he heard a second blast after a time of 30 mins and 15 seconds. if the second blast occurred exactly 30 mins after the first, how many meters was he from the site when he heard the second blast ? ( speed of sound = 330 m / s )\\nOptions: a. 1650, b. 2750, c. 3850, d. 4950, e. 6050","target":"d","rationale":"The man was driving at a constant speed during the time since he heard the first blast. Since he heard the second blast after a time of 30 mins, 15 seconds, his distance from the site of the first blast is exactly 330 m/s x (30 mins + 15 sec) = 330 x (30/60 + 15/3600) = 3300 / 120 meters = 2750 meters."},{"source":"In week 11, the Lions visited their division rival, the Chicago Bears. The Bears scored 10 points in the first quarter via a 23-yard field goal from Connor Barth, and a one-yard touchdown pass from Mitchell Trubisky to Adam Shaheen. The Lions scored 21 points in the second quarter via a 27-yard fumble return from D. J. Hayden, a 28-yard touchdown pass from Matthew Stafford to Marvin Jones Jr. and a two-yard touchdown pass from Stafford to Ameer Abdullah. The Bears responded with a 12-yard touchdown run from Jordan Howard, to make the score 21-17 in favor of Detroit at half-time. After a scoreless third quarter, the Lions extended their lead in the fourth quarter via a 27-yard field goal from Matt Prater. The Bears responded with a 15-yard touchdown run from Tarik Cohen to tie the game. The Lions regained the lead via a 52-yard field goal from Prater. The Bears attempted comeback failed when Barth missed a potentially game-tying 46-yard field goal attempt with eight seconds remaining in the game, making the final score 27-24 in favor of Detroit. With the win, the Lions won all of their division games on the road in a season for the first time in franchise history.\\n\\nHow many yards do the longest field goal and the longest touchdown combine for?","target":"80","rationale":"The longest field goal is 52 yards while the longest touchdown is 27+28=55. Add them together, and you get 80."},{"source":"In this task, you will be given a debate topic, along with a sentence from the debate. You should classify the given sentence and choose the type of that sentence. Possible types are explained below.\\nPolicy: This refers to a sentence proposing a specific course of action to be taken. It typically contains modal verbs like \\"should\\" and \\"ought to\\". It cannot be directly proved with objective evidence, and a proper type of support is a logical reason from which the proposition can be inferred.\\nValue: This refers to a sentence containing value judgments without making specific claims about what should be done (If so, then it is a Policy sentence.). Because of the subjectivity of value judgments, it cannot be proved directly with objective evidence.\\nFact: This refers to an objective proposition expressing or dealing with facts or conditions as perceived without distortion by personal feelings, prejudices, or interpretations. A Fact sentence has a truth value that can be verified with objective evidence that may be available at the time the claim is made; predictions about future are considered unverifiable.\\nTestimony: This refers to an objective sentence about the author's personal state or experience. Evidence for Testimony is not publicly available in most cases.\\n\\ntopic: InfraRedEd\\nsentence: \\"[2] Courts called on to interpret it have applied a wide variety of standards, with little agreement.\\"","target":"Fact","rationale":"The sentence states that courts have applied a wide variety of standards with little agreement, which is a fact. The truth value of this statement can be verified by looking at the data on court decisions. Therefore, the correct answer is \\"Fact\\"."},{"source":"Within the City of Westminster in London the entertainment district of the West End has its focus around Leicester Square, where London and world film premieres are held, and Piccadilly Circus, with its giant electronic advertisements. London's theatre district is here, as are many cinemas, bars, clubs and restaurants, including the city's Chinatown district (in Soho), and just to the east is Covent Garden, an area housing speciality shops. The city is the home of Andrew Lloyd Webber, whose musicals have dominated the West End theatre since the late 20th century. The United Kingdom's Royal Ballet, English National Ballet, Royal Opera and English National Opera are based in London and perform at the Royal Opera House, the London Coliseum, Sadler's Wells Theatre and the Royal Albert Hall as well as touring the country.\\nWhat prolific composer and producer of musicals has been a major force in the West End theater district?","target":"Andrew Lloyd Webber","rationale":"The context indicates that Andrew Lloyd Webber is a prolific composer and producer of musicals. It also states that his musicals have dominated the West End Theatre since the late 20th century, which makes him notable in this area. \\nThus, we can infer from the text that he has been a major force in London's theater district.\\""},{"source":"Question : Which Rock star joined Mel Gibson in the film 'Mad Max Beyond Thunderdome'?\\nAnswer :","target":"Anna Bullock","rationale":"The question asks for the name of a rock star that was in \\"Mad Max Beyond Thunderdome\\". \\nIn the 1985 film, Tina Turner played Aunt Entity. As Anna Bullock is another alias used by Tina Turner, it can be inferred from this information that she fits the role required to answer this question."},{"source":"Determine the question that you might have asked to get back the following answer for the given context\\nContext: During World War II, when Denmark was occupied by Nazi Germany, the United States briefly controlled Greenland for battlefields and protection. In 1946, the United States offered to buy Greenland from Denmark for $100 million ($1.2 billion today) but Denmark refused to sell it. Several politicians and others have in recent years argued that Greenland could hypothetically be in a better financial situation as a part of the United States; for instance mentioned by professor Gudmundur Alfredsson at University of Akureyri in 2014. One of the actual reasons behind US interest in Greenland could be the vast natural resources of the island. According to Wikileaks, the U.S. appears to be highly interested in investing in the resource base of the island and in tapping the vast expected hydrocarbons off the Greenlandic coast.;\\nAnswer: $100 million;\\nQuestion:","target":"How much did the US offer to pay for Greenland?","rationale":"The context mentions that \\"the United States offered to buy Greenland from Denmark for $100 million\\". The answer is a number, so there must be some kind of amount mentioned in the question.\\nThus, based on this information, we can conclude that the correct answer should include words such as \\"amount\\", \\"value\\" or something similar. \\nWhen looking at all options provided (including ones not shown here), it becomes clear that only one option fulfills these requirements: How much did the US offer to pay for Greenland?\\n\\n\\nQuestion 6: What are you reading right now ? [Text]*/"},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\nThe frequency of sound waves is measured in hertz (Hz), or the number of waves that pass a fixed point in a second. Human beings can normally hear sounds with a frequency between about 20 Hz and 20,000 Hz. Sounds with frequencies below 20 hertz are called infrasound . Infrasound is too low-pitched for humans to hear. Sounds with frequencies above 20,000 hertz are called ultrasound . Ultrasound is too high-pitched for humans to hear.\\n\\n\\nQ: The frequency of sound waves is measured in what unit?\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"hertz","rationale":"The frequency of sound waves is defined as the number of times a wave completes its journey per second. A unit used to measure this quantity is hertz, so the answer is hertz."},{"source":"You are given a concatenated string consisting of two parts that are separated by a newline character. The first part is the user's initial question during a human computer conversation, the second part is a clarifying question asked by the computer in response to the question asked by the user. You should read the input, then generate a valid prediction of the user's response to the computer's clarifying question. A valid prediction will clarify the user's correct intent in the initial question.\\n\\nUser: Find information about events sponsored by AVP, the Association of Volleyball Professionals. \\nComputer: are you looking for any specific information in relation to beach volleyball","target":"this is not related to my search","rationale":"The user's initial question is regarding the Association of Volleyball Professionals, which deals with indoor as well as beach volleyball events. The computer's clarifying question requests the user to specify whether they are only interested in information about beach volleyball or not. The response \\"this is not related to my search\\" indicates that the user is interested in all types of volleyball events organized by AVP, and therefore clarifies their intent mentioned in the initial query."},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the occurrences of the given word in the given sentence.\\n\\nSentence: 'a bunch of cupcakes are on a white plate'. Count the occurrences of the word 'a' in the given sentence.","target":"2","rationale":"Given the sentence \\"a bunch of cupcakes are on a white plate\\", let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. 'a' : 1 -> (total) 2\\\\n2. 'bunch' : 0 -> (total) 2\\\\n3. 'of' : 0 -> (total) 2\\\\n4. 'cupcakes' : 0 -> (total) 2\\\\n5. 'are' : 0 -> (total) 2\\\\n6. 'on' : 0 -> (total) 2\\\\n7. 'a' : 1 - >( total ) 3 \\\\ n8 ."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue between a user and an assistant, where users and assistants converse about geographic topics like geopolitical entities and locations. The task here is to find if the dialogue is by the user or assistant. Classify your answers into user and assistant.\\n\\nWhat can you tell me about Zimbabwe?","target":"user","rationale":"The question \\"What can you tell me about Zimbabwe?\\" is clearly a question by a user and not an assistant."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that seamlessly connects with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes more sense.\\n\\nTitle: An Unusual Pet. Sentence 1: Lucy wanted a pet, but not a boring old dog or dull cat. Sentence 2: She realized that she loved birds, especially the kind that could talk. Sentence 3: Lucy took some time to research birds that made good pets. Sentence 4: Soon she found a parakeet named Horatio that needed a home. Choices: a. Lucy adopted Horatio and now loves spending time with her unusual pet. b. Hank said he would return it.","target":"a","rationale":"The first four sentences of the story establish that Lucy is looking for a parakeet, and that she finds Horatio. Because the fifth sentence needs to follow logically from these facts, we can infer that Lucy will adopt Horatio as her pet."},{"source":"An amphibian has what temperature blood?\\n\\nChoose an answer from this list:\\n- toasty\\n- chilly\\n- hot\\n- burning","target":"chilly","rationale":"The temperature at which an organism's blood circulates is referred to as its blood temperature. Cold-blooded animals, such as fish and amphibians, have a lower blood temperature than warm-blooded animals like humans. Since an amphibian has cold or chilly blood it makes sense that their body temperature would be relatively low compared with other organisms (especially those higher on the food chain). Hence option \\"chilly\\" is the most appropriate answer out of all options given above."},{"source":"The goal is to predict an English answer string for an input English question. \\nQuestion : What number shirt did footballer Bobby Moore wear when he played for West Ham?\\nAnswer :","target":"6","rationale":"The jersey number of Bobby Moore when he played for West Ham was 6"},{"source":"Write the response. I'm looking for an Italian restaurant in the area. Any recommendations?\\nI recommend the Eatalia in El Segundo.\\nDo they have authentic pasta there?\\nYes, they are known for their Shrimp Carbonara.\\nLet's try to make a reservation there.\\nGreat, when would you like to make a reservation?\\nThis Saturday night at 7 pm please.\\nFor how many people?\\nFour including myself.\\nAny preferences?\\nActually yes. Could we get a table by the fountain?\\nI'm sorry, there aren't any tables for four by the fountain at that time.","target":"It's ok. What about near the sports section for the TVs?","rationale":"The user has specifically asked for a table by the fountain. However, since that is not possible, the system apologizes and then asks if there's another location they would prefer to sit near (the sports section with TVs). Therefore, a response of \\"It's ok. What about near the sports section for the TVs?\\" fits best in this context."},{"source":"Oil prices eased back from record high levels after Russia's justice ministry said embattled oil giant Yukos can continue oil production and sales.\\n\\nQ with options: Can we draw the following conclusion?\\nOil prices rise.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"We cannot draw a conclusion from this passage that oil prices had risen. In fact, the opposite is true - we are told that \\"oil prices eased back\\" after Russia's justice ministry announced Yukos could continue operations as normal."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the correct option to answer the question.\\nContext: Kadin loved the desert. Many creatures lived in the desert. Some learned to survive within her harsh burning grip. Some even learned to thrive in her, building stone monuments to themselves and living their lives surrounded in the lavish luxuries of Gods. How puny their monuments were compared to the desert herself.\\nWhere they had castles surrounded by dry moats, the desert had mountains surrounded by thousand year sandstorms. Where they had silks and the most beautiful slaves serving their every greatest desire, she had dunes that stretched for a thousand leagues and a sun that burned huge and deep crimson in the violet sky. Where desert kings, the Danken, dined on the finest food and drank the finest wine, the desert drank every drop of water from the air itself and feasted on men.\\nKadin knew the desert. He knew her voice whispering in the dark of night like a dangerous lover. The sound he heard now was not her voice but a cry from one trapped within the desert's teeth. It was the cry of a woman.\\nKadin rose from his makeshift bed in the dip of two dunes. He stood quickly, tying the leather straps of his knife belt around his waist. He pulled on his boots and silently mounted White Ash. THe mare felt his soft touch and made no sound.\\nKadin listened and heard the cry again. He studied the dunes in the darkness of night. THe blood moon painted the desert a deep red. He felt the echos and turned White Ash towards their origin. He rode quietly into the night.\\nKadin saw the glow of torchlight long before cresting the hill. He guessed four riders from the sound of their horses and confirmed it when he rose above them.\\nThree men, now on foot, chased a woman in black across the dune. Their horses stood back, panting from a hard ride. The woman's own stallion lay dead, a black arrow buried in its flank.\\nQuestion: Who is the woman?\\nOptions:\\n- not enough information\\n- A runaway princess being chased by guards\\n- A fugitive from the men chasing her.\\n- A slave running away from her masters.","target":"not enough information","rationale":"The context describes Kadin hearing a woman's cry and the subsequent events of him chasing after four men who are pursuing her. It can be inferred that they want to capture or kill her but there is no information about why they might do this, so it cannot be said for certain whether she is running away from them because she has done something wrong or if they have decided to pursue her without justification.\\nGiven that we don't know enough about the situation in order to determine what exactly happened between these characters, \\"not enough information\\" would be an accurate answer choice."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. You need to find all the elements of the list that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\n\\n['l', '3691', '9547', '9391', '4399']","target":"27028","rationale":"The given list contains the strings 'l', '3691', '9547', '9391', and '4399'. All of these elements are numbers except for the first one, so we will only calculate their sum.\\\\n1. '3691' : 3691 -> (total) 3691\\\\n2. '9547' : 9547 -> (total) 13238\\\\n3. '9391' : 9391 -> (total) 22608\\\\n4. 4399 : 4399 -> 27028"},{"source":"I am verifying the answers generated by an automatic system to the following question: how many states have open carry gun laws\\nSuggested answer: Alan Gottlieb of the Second Amendment Foundation and the NRA have been cautious in expressing support, while special-interest groups such as the aforementioned OpenCarry.org and GeorgiaCarry.org, and certain national groups such as the Gun Owners of America (GOA) have been more outspoken in favor of the practice.\\nShould I validate this answer?","target":"No","rationale":"The suggested answer provided by the automatic system is not accurate. While this statement may be true, it does not directly address or provide an answer to the question: \\"how many states have open carry gun laws\\".\\nThis information can also be verified through external sources such as news articles and websites that discuss legal regulations for carrying a firearm in public places. \\nTherefore, the correct response should be No."},{"source":"Question: What do you take out of the fish before service a filet??\\nOptions:\\n- no legs\\n- bones\\n- organs\\n- gills\\n- scales\\n\\nExplain why a human would choose \\"bones\\" to answer the question above:","target":"fish save bones","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"fish save bones\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question and answer options for that question. Using this information, you have to classify each text into different topics: medicine, nursery, psychology, chemistry, pharmacology, biology.\\n\\nQuestion: The O antigen used in the classification of Gram negative bacteria corresponds to: \\n Options:  <0> The flagellar proteins. <1> Components of the capsule. <2> The peptidoglycan. <3> The polysaccharide of lipopolysaccharides. <4> Plasma membrane proteins.","target":"biology","rationale":"The question and options are related to the classification of bacteria based on their cell wall structure. This is a topic in biology, so the passage belongs to 'biology'."},{"source":"Read the text and determine if the sentence is true:\\n\\nCyrillic is an alphabet form that is derived from the Greek alphabet. The characters in the script look substantially different from the Latin alphabet that is used throughout Western Europe.\\n\\nSentence: Cyrillic is an alphabet used for certain Slavic languages, such as Russian.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nA:","target":"no","rationale":"The context mentions that Cyrillic \\"is an alphabet form\\". It does not specify if the script is used for Slavic languages. So, it's impossible to tell whether this sentence is true or false based on the information given above."},{"source":"Math Problem\\nSolve 0 = 1245*y - 32770 - 44420 for y.","target":"62","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable y on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] 1245*y - 44420 - 32770 = 0\\n[STEP 2] 1245*y - 77190 = 0\\n[STEP 3] y = 77190 / 1245\\n[STEP 4] y = 62"},{"source":"Here's a problem to solve: How will a thriving grassland ecosystem most likely be affected by a drought?\\n\\nAmong the 4 following options, which is the correct answer?\\n\\n- A: Plant respiration will increase.\\n \\n- B: Animals will be forced to migrate.\\n \\n- C: Soil nutrients will be enriched.\\n \\n- D: Natural succession will cease.","target":"B","rationale":"During drought, grasslands become hot and dry. Animals that depend on plants for their food will not be able to survive in such conditions. Also, animals with limited water storage capacity may die due to the shortage of water during a long period of drought.\\nSince these factors are unfavorable for animal survival, an ecosystem will most likely experience migration rather than death or any other effect. \\nTherefore option B is correct"},{"source":"You are provided with a list of converations between a \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\". Figure out if the conversation provided as \\"classify_text\\" is authored by \\"USER\\" or \\"ASSISTANT\\". There are maximum of 7 conversations between \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\" in each input\\n\\nASSISTANT: What kind of movies do you like? , USER: I really like , USER: romantic comedies , ASSISTANT: Why do you like rom coms? , USER: Rom coms make me happy. They put me in a position of like pure bliss, and I don't have to think about the bad stuff that's going on in the world. , ASSISTANT: Can you name a particular movie you like?, classify_text: Maid in Manhattan","target":"USER","rationale":"User asks a question (Why do you like rom coms?) and provides a response to the question. Hence, it can be classified as a 'USER' text"},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to the associated containers is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its associated container B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate container for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\ntrash : can. honey : ?","target":"jar","rationale":"The trash analogically relates to the can, so the honey may be in a jar."},{"source":"In this task, you're given an open-domain question. Your task is to provide an answer to the given question. There is only one unique answer for each question. Your answer should be short, and refer to an entity, date, number, etc. Do not put your answer in the context of a sentence.\\n\\nWhat is the strangers prey at night movie based on?","target":"a family's vacation to a secluded mobile home park, where they are attacked by three masked offenders","rationale":"The movie is about the family's vacation to a secluded mobile home park, where they are attacked by three masked offenders. The instruction asks not put your answer in the context of a sentence, so we can write it straight out as: \\"a family's vacation to a secluded mobile home park, where they are attacked by three masked offenders\\""},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\n17 March 2011 - Goldman Sachs estimates that there are negative prospects for the Norwegian mobile operations of Norway 's Telenor ASA OSL : TEL and Sweden 's TeliaSonera AB STO : TLSN in the short term .","target":"negative","rationale":"The passage is a report of the Goldman Sachs' prediction that there are negative prospects for the Norwegian mobile operations of Telenor and TeliaSonera in the short term. Goldman Sachs predicts that, in the short term, both companies will have lower profits from their mobile operations in Norway. This is viewed as negative news for both companies, so this financial news can be classified as \\"negative\\"."},{"source":"we have MANY more things to do ! ! Then I managed to get hold of D , who 's an air stewardess in SIA btw .. lol . I told her what happened at the interviews earlier this morning , and she told me it 's normal , she went through the interviews 5 times herself , before making it through to the training programme . Never mind that , she said , you get smarter for each session you get through and get kicked out from .\\nWhy is the narrator so interested in talking to Sia ?\\nPick the best answer from the following options:\\n- Sia has information about a job .\\n - Sia has information about cooking .\\n - None of the above choices .\\n - Sia has information about money .","target":"Sia has information about a job .","rationale":"The narrator is seeking advice and comfort from a friend, Sia (an air stewardess) after getting rejected at interviews. The context suggests that the narrator was applying for jobs in order to get some work experience or paid employment to supplement their studies. Since job opportunities are limited during this period of time, it can be inferred that the narrator is interested about talking to Sia because she has information about available jobs within her company, which might provide career prospects for the narrator as well.\\nTherefore, answer choice A best fits with the given situation described in the passage - Sia has information about a job ."},{"source":"In this task, you're given five sentences, numbered 1 through 5. Your job is to generate a title for the story that makes complete sense. The title must be short, with less than three words, use simple language, and include the main topic of the story.\\n\\nSentence 1: Dan had some time off from work he had to use up. Sentence 2: Dan called up a few buddies. Sentence 3: Dan asked them if they'd like to take a cross-country trip with him. Sentence 4: His buddies all agreed. Sentence 5: They went from Georgia to Arizona together, and had a blast.","target":"Cross-Country","rationale":"The story covers a cross-country trip from Georgia to Arizona, and the title \\"Cross-Country\\" clearly reflects this."},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nWhen we look at a molecule we can determine that if it it has few atoms it will typically have many or few isomers? \\n\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nThe more carbon atoms a hydrocarbon has, the greater the number of isomers.","target":"few","rationale":"The more carbon atoms a hydrocarbon has, the greater the number of isomers. In other words, molecules containing many carbon atoms will have many isomers while those with few carbons may only have one or two.\\nSo based on this information we can deduce that if it (the molecule) has few atoms it will typically have \\"few\\" isomers"},{"source":"Here's a question and a few possible answers: \\n\\nQ: Where do most people keep magazines?\\nPossible A: bookstore, library, doctor, home, table\\n\\nWhy is \\"table\\" an answer aligned with human common sense?","target":"a table most people keep magazines","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"a table most people keep magazines\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an impractical statement. You are also given three reasons (associated with \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\") explaining why this statement doesn't make sense. You must choose the most corresponding reason explaining why this statement doesn't make sense.\\n\\nThe house ran away from the dog.\\n(A) Cats are bigger than dogs.\\n(B)Dogs cannot eat houses.\\n(C)Houses cannot run.","target":"C","rationale":"The sentence is impractical because it states that the house ran away from the dog. According to reason C, houses cannot run. Therefore, this is the most corresponding reason that explains why this statement doesn't make any sense."},{"source":"Jews were confined to the Jewish part of town called a ghetto, and many people there starved to death.\\n\\nBased on that paragraph can we conclude that the sentence below is true?\\nDisease, starvation, and overcrowding caused thousands to perish before deportations to the Nazi death camps, especially to Treblinka, began in late 1941.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The sentence states that \\"Disease, starvation and overcrowding caused thousands to perish before deportations...\\". However the paragraph does not mention any disease or overcrowding in relation to Jews being confined in a ghetto."},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as acceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"The sign warned against skating on the pond.","rationale":"Here's an example of a grammatically correct sentence:\\\\nThe sign warned against skating on the pond."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate actions to the tools used to perform the action is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates action A to tool B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate tool for the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nclamp : clamp. iron : ?","target":"iron","rationale":"You clamp things together with a clamp and you iron things with an iron."},{"source":"Premise: A small boy in a yellow shirt laughing on the beach.\\n\\nHypothesis: A boy is bored at school.\\n\\n.Choose the correct answer: Given the premise, can we conclude the hypothesis?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise describes a happy child laughing on the beach, while the hypothesis states that he is bored at school. These two statements contradict each other and cannot be concluded together as they are given by different people in potentially different scenarios."},{"source":"What is the answer for the question: What did Marion witness the son of the man who committed a double murder-suicide doing? from the following article ?\\n\\nIn 1955 in Portland, Oregon, a businessman finds his wife in bed with another man, and commits a double murder-suicide. His young son, Paul, witnesses the three deaths, and is traumatized. Twenty-five years later, in 1980, Paul is incarcerated at a psychiatric institution near Stanford Bay, a small town on the Oregon Coast. One day, Paul manages to murder an orderly, and subsequently retrieves a beloved wooden flute given to him by his father before escaping the institution.\\nLocal teenager Marion is struggling to adjust to her disability‚Äîshe survived a car accident several years prior, caused by her drunken father Frank, which left her unable to walk without the help of a leg brace. She is plagued by bizarre dreams, which she comes to discover are in fact premonitions; while in the hospital after her accident, she received a blood transfusion from Paul, which has given her extrasensory perception into Paul's actions. Marion's home life is troubled, with her father being verbally abusive to her and her mother, Bea, and she dreams of leaving Stanford Bay once her fisherman boyfriend, Joey, obtains a job in Portland.\\nMeanwhile, Paul hitchhikes with a truck driver whom he bludgeons to death with a hatchet, and then steals his vehicle. He subsequently picks up a female hitchhiker, who he brings to a local motel in Stanford Bay, and murders her after failing to charm her with his flute-playing. Marion's psychic visions of Paul's murders increase in frequency and intensity, and sh soon witnesses him in person disposing of a body on a rural beach, making her his next target. Marion manages to elude to Paul, but he later discovers where she lives, and infiltrates her home, killing Frank. Struggling to walk, Marion manages to flee her home to an adjacent sawmill, and is pursued by Paul. While chasing Marion, Paul impales a worker with a forklift, and then inadvertently crashes through a barrier, driving the forklift off the pier and into the bay.","target":"disposing of a body","rationale":"The article is about a double murder-suicide in Portland, Oregon. It goes on to explain that the child of one victim witnessed this event and was traumatized by it. 25 years later, he murdered an orderly at a psychiatric institution where he had been incarcerated for his troubles and escaped with only a flute given to him as a boy by his father before killing himself being recovered from the water after falling into it while trying to kill again woman who'd seen him dispose of another body.\\nBeing asked what Marion saw Paul do we have three options:\\nIn 1955 commit triple homicide (A) - wrong answer because Paul wasn't involved; going through puberty (B) - wrong answer because nothing's said regarding when or how old Paul was then; disposing of a body (C"},{"source":"Q: who played ellie on the andy griffith show? A:","target":"Elinor Donahue","rationale":"Elinor Donahue played Ellie Walker on the Andy Griffith Show."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Wine (from Latin \\"vinum\\") is an alcoholic beverage made from fermented grapes. These grapes are generally \\"Vitis vinifera,\\" or a hybrid with \\"Vitis labrusca\\" or \\"Vitis rupestris\\". Grapes are fermented without the addition of sugars, acids, enzymes, water, or other nutrients. Yeast consumes the sugar in the grapes and converts it to ethanol and carbon dioxide. Different varieties of grapes and strains of yeasts produce different styles of wine. These variations result from the complex interactions between the biochemical development of the grape, the reactions involved in fermentation, the terroir, and the production process. Many countries enact legal appellations intended to define styles and qualities of wine. These typically restrict the geographical origin and permitted varieties of grapes, as well as other aspects of wine production.\\n\\n- Deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA) is a molecule that carries the genetic instructions used in the growth, development, functioning and reproduction of all known living organisms and many viruses. DNA and RNA are nucleic acids; alongside proteins, lipids and complex carbohydrates (polysaccharides), they are one of the four major types of macromolecules that are essential for all known forms of life. Most DNA molecules consist of two biopolymer strands coiled around each other to form a double helix.\\n\\n- Binomial nomenclature (also called binominal nomenclature or binary nomenclature) is a formal system of naming species of living things by giving each a name composed of two parts, both of which use Latin grammatical forms, although they can be based on words from other languages. Such a name is called a binomial name (which may be shortened to just \\"binomial\\"), a binomen or a scientific name; more informally it is also called a Latin name. The first part of the name identifies the genus to which the species belongs; the second part identifies the species within the genus. For example, humans belong to the genus \\"Homo\\" and within this genus to the species \\"Homo sapiens\\". The \\"formal\\" introduction of this system of naming species is credited to Carl Linnaeus, effectively beginning with his work \\"Species Plantarum\\" in 1753. But Gaspard Bauhin, in as early as 1623, had introduced in his book \\"Pinax theatri botanici\\" (English, \\"Illustrated exposition of plants\\") many names of genera that were later adopted by Linnaeus.\\n\\n- An ascospore is a spore contained in an ascus or that was produced inside an ascus. This kind of spore is specific to fungi classified as ascomycetes (Ascomycota).\\n\\n- \\nIn formal nomenclature.\\nWhen formally naming a taxon, uncertainty about its taxonomic classification can be problematic. The International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants, stipulates that \\"species and subdivisions of genera must be assigned to genera, and infraspecific taxa must be assigned to species, because their names are combinations\\", but ranks higher than the genus may be assigned \\"incertae sedis\\".\\n\\n- The International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (ICN) is the set of rules and recommendations dealing with the formal botanical names that are given to plants, fungi and a few other groups of organisms, all those \\"traditionally treated as algae, fungi, or plants\\". It was formerly called the International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (ICBN); the name was changed at the International Botanical Congress in Melbourne in July 2011 as part of the \\"Melbourne Code\\" which replaces the \\"Vienna Code\\" of 2005. As with previous codes, it took effect as soon as it was ratified by the congress (on Saturday 23 July 2011), but the documentation of the code in its final form was not finished until some time after the congressional meeting. Preliminary wording of some of the articles with the most significant changes has been published in September 2011.\\n\\n- A genus (¬†genera) is a taxonomic rank used in the biological classification of living and fossil organisms in biology. In the hierarchy of biological classification, genus comes above species and below family. In binomial nomenclature, the genus name forms the first part of the binomial species name for each species within the genus.\\n\\n- An ascus (plural asci; from Greek  \\"sk√≥s\\" 'skin bag') is the sexual spore-bearing cell produced in ascomycete fungi. Asci usually contain eight ascospores, produced by meiosis followed, in most species, by a mitotic cell division. However, asci in some genera or species can occur in numbers of one (e.g. \\"Monosporascus cannonballus\\"), two, four, or multiples of four. In a few cases, the ascospores can bud off conidia that may fill the asci (e.g. \\"Tympanis\\") with hundreds of conidia, or the ascospores may fragment, e.g. some \\"Cordyceps\\", also filling the asci with smaller cells. Ascospores are nonmotile, usually single celled, but not infrequently may be coenocytic (lacking a septum), and in some cases coenocytic in multiple planes. Mitotic divisions within the developing spores populate each resulting cell in septate ascospores with nuclei. The term ocular chamber, or oculus, refers to the epiplasm (the portion of cytoplasm not used in ascospore formation) that is surrounded by the \\"bourrelet\\" (the thickened tissue near the top of the ascus).\\n\\n- Basidiomycota is one of two large divisions that, together with the Ascomycota, constitute the subkingdom Dikarya (often referred to as the \\"higher fungi\\") within the kingdom Fungi.\\n\\n- In biology, an organism is any contiguous living system, such as an animal, plant, fungus, archaeon, or bacterium. All known types of organisms are capable of some degree of response to stimuli, reproduction, growth and development and homeostasis. An organism consists of one or more cells; when it has one cell it is known as a unicellular organism; and when it has more than one it is known as a multicellular organism. Most unicellular organisms are of microscopic scale and are thus loosely described as microorganisms. Humans are multicellular organisms composed of many trillions of cells grouped into specialized tissues and organs.\\n\\n- Clypeolum is a genus of fungi in the Ascomycota phylum . The relationship of this taxon to other taxa within the class is unknown ( incertae sedis ) , and it has not yet been placed with certainty into any class , order , or family .\\n\\n- Ascomycota is a division or phylum of the kingdom Fungi that, together with the Basidiomycota, form the subkingdom Dikarya. Its members are commonly known as the sac fungi or ascomycetes. They are the largest phylum of Fungi, with over 64,000 species. The defining feature of this fungal group is the \\"ascus\\" (from Greek: (\\"askos\\"), meaning \\"sac\\" or \\"wineskin\\"), a microscopic sexual structure in which nonmotile spores, called ascospores, are formed. However, some species of the Ascomycota are asexual, meaning that they do not have a sexual cycle and thus do not form asci or ascospores. Previously placed in the Deuteromycota along with asexual species from other fungal taxa, asexual (or anamorphic) ascomycetes are now identified and classified based on morphological or physiological similarities to ascus-bearing taxa, and by phylogenetic analyses of DNA sequences.\\n\\n- Dikarya is a subkingdom of Fungi that includes the phyla Ascomycota and Basidiomycota, both of which in general produce dikaryons, may be filamentous or unicellular, but are always without flagella. The Dikarya are most of the so-called \\"higher fungi\\", but also include many anamorphic species that would have been classified as molds in historical literature. Phylogenetically the two phyla regularly group together. In a 1998 publication, Thomas Cavalier-Smith referred to this group as the Neomycota.\\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the paragraphs above, decide what entity has the relation 'parent taxon' with 'ascomycetes'.","target":"clypeolum","rationale":"The answer is clypeolum."},{"source":"In this task, you're given an open-domain question. Your task is to provide an answer to the given question. There is only one unique answer for each question. Your answer should be short, and refer to an entity, date, number, etc. Do not put your answer in the context of a sentence.\\n\\nWhen was the first reality tv show aired?","target":"April 30, 1945","rationale":"The first reality TV show was Candid Camera, which aired on April 30, 1945."},{"source":"Bacteria\\nThere are typically 40 million bacterial cells in a gram of soil and a million bacterial cells in a millilitre of fresh water. There are approximately 5√ó1030 bacteria on Earth, forming a biomass which exceeds that of all plants and animals. Bacteria are vital in recycling nutrients, with many of the stages in nutrient cycles dependent on these organisms, such as the fixation of nitrogen from the atmosphere and putrefaction. In the biological communities surrounding hydrothermal vents and cold seeps, bacteria provide the nutrients needed to sustain life by converting dissolved compounds, such as hydrogen sulphide and methane, to energy. On 17 March 2013, researchers reported data that suggested bacterial life forms thrive in the Mariana Trench, which with a depth of up to 11 kilometres is the deepest part of the Earth's oceans. Other researchers reported related studies that microbes thrive inside rocks up to 580 metres below the sea floor under 2.6 kilometres of ocean off the coast of the northwestern United States. According to one of the researchers, \\"You can find microbes everywhere ‚Äî they're extremely adaptable to conditions, and survive wherever they are.\\"\\n\\nQ: What amount of bacteria can be found in a gram of soil?","target":"40 million bacterial cells","rationale":"The paragraph states that \\"there are typically 40 million bacterial cells in a gram of soil\\". Therefore, the answer to this question is: 40 million bacterial cells."},{"source":"See the conversation. DIALOG:\\nWhen did Kelsey Grammer's show Frasier end?\\n- May 2004\\n- What did Kelsey Grammer do on Fraiser?\\n-","target":"best known for his two-decade-long portrayal of psychiatrist Dr. Frasier Crane on the NBC sitcoms Cheers and Frasier","rationale":"The answer to the question \\"What did Kelsey Grammer do on Fraiser?\\" is best known for his two-decade-long portrayal of psychiatrist Dr. Frasier Crane on the NBC sitcoms Cheers and Frasier. This is found by accessing information from a search engine with a query: Kelsey Grammer"},{"source":"Combine facts and answer this: Which Big East champion began his NBA career with the Celtics in 2007?","target":"Jeff Green","rationale":"Jeff Green was the Big East Player of the Year in 2007 and he began his NBA career with Boston Celtics."},{"source":"Answer the question from the given passage. Your answer should be directly extracted from the passage, and it should be a single entity, name, or number, not a sentence.\\n\\nPassage: In 1700 several hundred French Huguenots migrated from England to the colony of Virginia, where the English Crown had promised them land grants in Lower Norfolk County. When they arrived, colonial authorities offered them instead land 20 miles above the falls of the James River, at the abandoned Monacan village known as Manakin Town, now in Powhatan County. Some settlers landed in present-day Chesterfield County. On 12 May 1705, the Virginia General Assembly passed an act to naturalise the 148 Huguenots still resident at Manakintown. Of the original 390 settlers in the isolated settlement, many had died; others lived outside town on farms in the English style; and others moved to different areas. Gradually they intermarried with their English neighbors. Through the 18th and 19th centuries, descendants of the French migrated west into the Piedmont, and across the Appalachian Mountains into the West of what became Kentucky, Tennessee, Missouri, and other states. In the Manakintown area, the Huguenot Memorial Bridge across the James River and Huguenot Road were named in their honor, as were many local features, including several schools, including Huguenot High School. Question: In what English colony were Huguenot settlers promised land?","target":"Virginia","rationale":"The passage clearly states that several hundred French Huguenots migrated from England to the colony of Virginia."},{"source":"Here's a complex question that requires someone to reason about the input, can you answer it?\\nWhat is the name of the rivalry game that is played in the same stadium as the State Fair Classic, thats name is derived from the river that forms part of the boundary between Texas and Oklahoma?","target":"Red River Showdown","rationale":"The Red River Showdown is played in the Cotton Bowl, which also hosts the State Fair Classic. It gets its name from the river that forms part of the boundary between Texas and Oklahoma."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people.'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. You have to classify if there exist more than 2 unique emotions in conversation. If there are more than 2 unique emotions present in the conversation, the output should be classified as '1' else it should be '0'\\n\\nPerson1:     Hi , Sara , what are you reading ? \\nPerson2: Hi , John , I am trying to find a carpenter . \\nPerson1:     Why ? \\nPerson2: Well , I want to build a deck in my back yard . \\nPerson1:     What for ? \\nPerson2: So I can have a special place to hang out with friends , and also do some barbecuing on weekends . \\nPerson1:     That sounds cool . Do you mind if I recommend myself for the job ? \\nPerson2: You ? Do you have a carpenter's license ? \\nPerson1:     Yes , of course . But I only freelance on weekends with my uncle . \\nPerson2: Wow ! That's cool . So , let me give you some details about the deck I want . \\nPerson1:     Please go ahead , I am listening . \\nPerson2: I'd like my deck to be at the same level as the back door . \\nPerson1:     Is your back door higher than the ground level ? \\nPerson2: Yes , the back door is about four or five steps higher than the ground . \\nPerson1:     Okay , then you need a deck with a guardrail . \\nPerson2: I don't like things to be fancy . \\nPerson1:     Don't worry . I will build your deck with a simple but classic look . \\nPerson2: Hmm , that's good . Can you use cedar or redwood to build it ? \\nPerson1:     Cedar is a good choice . \\nPerson2: Well , let's take the measurements right now .","target":"1","rationale":"There are 4 emotions present in the conversation, namely positive, negative, discussion and miscellaneous. Therefore, there exists more than 2 unique emotions in the conversation. Hence the answer is '1'."},{"source":"In this task, you will be presented with a context from an academic paper and a question separated with a \\n. You have to answer the question based on the context.\\n\\nThe Title-to-Story system is a baseline, which generates directly from topic. \\n Question: What are the baselines?","target":"Title-to-Story system","rationale":"The Title-to-Story system is the only baseline mentioned in the context."},{"source":"A person can be punched in the chest without the heart stopping because\\n- muscles crumple\\n- ribs guard it\\n- hearts are stone\\n- hearts are hollow\\n\\nWhich is the correct answer?","target":"ribs guard it","rationale":"Muscles can crumple when punched, but this does not explain why a punch to the chest would not stop a person's heart. Hearts are hollow and made of soft muscle tissue; they cannot be stone or solid. The correct answer is ribs guard it because bones provide protection for internal organs from physical trauma such as punches in the chest area."},{"source":"Read the following conversation and answer the question.\\n\\nW: I'm worried about my son at driving, but he won't listen to me.\\n\\nM: Well, teenagers always think they won't get hurt, but the fact is just the opposite.\\n\\nW: What should I do?\\n\\nM: Keep talking with him and lead by an example. Parents always matter.\\n\\nQuestion: What can we learn about the woman's son? \\n\\n- He often talks with his mother.\\n\\n- He often drives in a careless way.\\n\\n- He is willing to listen to his mother.","target":"He often drives in a careless way.","rationale":"The child drives in a careless way, which is worrying his mother.\\nSo the answer is He often drives in a careless way.."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the passage.\\n\\"It describes change in one's work and life, and four typical reactions to said change by two mice and two \\"littlepeople\\", during their hunt for cheese .\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Who Moved My Cheese?","rationale":"The passage states that \\"Who Moved My Cheese?\\" describes change in one's work and life, as well as four typical reactions to said changes by two mice and two littlepeople during their hunt for cheese.\\nIt can be inferred from the content of the passage that it is about a book entitled Who Moved My Cheese?, which explains how individuals react to changing situations in their lives with reference to a fictional story involving mice and littlepeople hunting for some missing cheese.\\""},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- The National Museum of Finland ( Finnish : Kansallismuseo , Swedish : Nationalmuseum ) presents Finnish history from the Stone Age to the present day , through objects and cultural history . The Finnish National Romantic style building is located in central Helsinki and is a part of the National Board of Antiquities ( Finnish : Museovirasto , Swedish : Museiverket ) , under the Ministry of Culture and Education .\\n\\n- Art Nouveau (Anglicised to ) is an international style of art, architecture and applied art, especially the decorative arts, that was most popular between 1890 and 1910. A reaction to the academic art of the 19th century, it was inspired by natural forms and structures, particularly the curved lines of plants and flowers.\\n\\n- The National Romantic style was a Nordic architectural style that was part of the National Romantic movement during the late 19th and early 20th centuries. It is often considered to be a form of Art Nouveau.\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat object entity has the relation of 'architectural style' with the subject 'national museum of finland'? \\n\\nChoices:\\n- art nouveau\\n - national romantic style","target":"art nouveau","rationale":"The question asks which object entity has the relation of 'architectural style' with the subject 'national museum of finland'. The information provided says that \\"the National Romantic style building is located in central Helsinki\\" and that it's part of the Museovirasto. Additionally, we know from this information that \\"art nouveau was popular between 1890 and 1910\\", while the national romantic movement occurred during 1900-1920.\\n   So based on these facts, one can conclude that because art nouveau came before national romanticism, then our answer must be related to art nouveau."},{"source":"I gave my students this multiple choice question: Scientists Stanley Miller and Harold Urey sealed water, methane, ammonia, and hydrogen in a flask, to simulate Earth's early environment. They exposed the chemicals to electric charges to simulate lighting. What did the process produce?\\n\\nOnly one answer is correct among these 4 choices:\\n- bacteria\\n- nucleic acids\\n- viruses\\n- amino acids\\n\\nCould you tell me which one is correct?","target":"amino acids","rationale":"Here's a summary of the question: \\nScientists Stanley Miller and Harold Urey sealed water, methane, ammonia, and hydrogen in a flask. They exposed the chemicals to electric charges to simulate lighting. What did this process produce?\\nThe answer is \\"amino acids\\". This was an experiment conducted in 1953 by scientists Stanley Miller and Harold Urey which simulated early Earth conditions using gases known as reducing agents (methane, ammonia) along with electric sparks that acted as energy source simulating lightning strikes on ancient earth surface. The results from these experiments showed that amino acids were produced when left for roughly two weeks under these conditions."},{"source":"I am testing my students' logic.\\nWhat is the answer they should choose between \\"Jeff\\" and \\"Zack\\"?\\nLogic test: Zack and Jeff decide to ride their bikes to a nearby mall. On the way there, they have an argument as to what to do there and Jeff decides to stop and goof around the park they were passing by. Therefore, Jeff ended up traveling _____ than Zack. (A) more (B) less","target":"Zack","rationale":"The question is asking how much further Zack traveled than Jeff. \\nZack carried on to the mall, while Jeff stopped at a park on his way there and spent more time getting there as well. Therefore, Zach must have gone farther than Jeff because he didn't stop along the way so it took him less time overall to get to the destination they had both set out for in the beginning of their journey."},{"source":"Article: The Exopterygota likely are paraphyletic in regard to the Endopterygota. Matters that have incurred controversy include Strepsiptera and Diptera grouped together as Halteria based on a reduction of one of the wing pairs ‚Äì a position not well-supported in the entomological community. The Neuropterida are often lumped or split on the whims of the taxonomist. Fleas are now thought to be closely related to boreid mecopterans. Many questions remain in the basal relationships amongst endopterygote orders, particularly the Hymenoptera.\\n\\nQuestion: Strepsiptera and Diptera are controversial what?","target":"Matters","rationale":"The context is discussing the relationship between Strepsiptera and Diptera, with regards to Halteria. The subject of this paragraph are matters that have incurred controversy in regard to halteria and strepsiptera diptera grouping together based on a reduction of one wing pair.\\nThis is why the answer extracted from the passage would be: \\"Matters\\"."},{"source":"Choose from options, is the following sentence linguistically acceptable?\\nI know a man who Bill saw and Mary liked.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"In the given sentence, there are two clauses: \\"I know a man\\" and \\"Mary liked him.\\" (The second clause is embedded in another subordinate clause.) The subject of each main verb (\\"know,\\" \\"saw,\\" and \\"liked\\") agrees with its respective verb. Therefore, this sentence follows the rules of English grammar correctly, which makes it linguistically acceptable."},{"source":"Decide the language of that sentence. The language can be English, French, German, Italian, or Spanish.\\n\\nText: 'Mah, penso che sia giusta. Non‚Ä¶ non credo che dovrei cambiare le mie abitudini alimentari.'","target":"Italian","rationale":"This sentence is in Italian."},{"source":"After the 1998 embassy bombings, the U.S. government tried to develop a clearer picture of  Bin Laden's finances. A U.S. interagency group traveled to Saudi Arabia twice, in 1999 and 2000, to get information from the Saudis about their understanding of those finances. The group eventually concluded that the oft-repeated assertion that  Bin Laden was funding al Qaeda from his personal fortune was in fact not true. The officials developed a new theory: al Qaeda was getting its money elsewhere, and the United States needed to focus on other sources of funding, such as charities, wealthy donors, and financial facilitators. Ultimately, although the intelligence community devoted more resources to the issue and produced somewhat more intelligence, it remained difficult to distinguish al Qaeda's financial transactions among the vast sums moving in the international financial system. The CIA was not able to find or disrupt al Qaeda's money flows. The NSC staff thought that one possible solution to these weaknesses in the intelligence community was to create an all-source terrorist-financing intelligence analysis center. Clarke pushed for the funding of such a center at Treasury, but neither Treasury nor the CIA was willing to commit the resources. Within the United States, various FBI field offices gathered intelligence on organizations suspected of raising funds for al Qaeda or other terrorist groups. By 9/11, FBI agents understood that there were extremist organizations operating within the United States supporting a global jihadist movement and with substantial connections to al Qaeda. The FBI operated a web of informants, conducted electronic surveillance, and had opened significant investigations in a number of field offices, including New York, Chicago, Detroit, San Diego, and Minneapolis. On a national level, however, the FBI never used the information to gain a systematic or strategic understanding of the nature and extent of al Qaeda fundraising. Treasury regulators, as well as U.S. financial institutions,...\\nBased on the previous passage, Where were field offices opened to investigate al Qaeda funding? \\nIs \\"Los Angeles\\" a correct answer?","target":"No","rationale":"The answer is No, because the passage does not mention Los Angeles. The correct answers are New York and Chicago based on \\"Including New York, Chicago\\" in paragraph 2 of the text."},{"source":"Short general knowledge question: where is ibrahim chatta from?","target":"Haryana","rationale":"Ibrahim Chatta is an Indian actor and director, who hails from Haryana. \\nAccording to Wikipedia: \\"Ibrahim chatta was born into a Muslim family in Meerut district of Uttar Pradesh on June 25\\" (Wikipedia)."},{"source":"Problem: Solve 0 = 4*t - 25 + 17 for t.\\nAnd the answer is...","target":"2","rationale":"To solve for t, we need to isolate the variable on one side of the equation.\\n\\nStarting with: 0 = 4*t - 25 + 17"},{"source":"If \\"Tom gave Ralph a lift to school so he wouldn't have to drive alone.\\", is \\"Ralph wouldn't have to drive alone.\\" correct?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes\\nAnswer:","target":"no","rationale":"This is an example of the \\"conversational inference\\" task.\\\\nThe statement \\"Ralph wouldn't have to drive alone.\\" does not accurately reflect what was stated in the premise sentence because Ralph, who would otherwise be driving alone, will now be riding with Tom and another person instead. So it's more accurate to say that he won't have to ride by himself than saying that he won't need to drive at all since they are still going in a car together. Therefore, the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to identify which one of following five services the sentence is related to - Media, Travel, Flights, Buses, RideSharing\\n\\nFind me a bus to reserve.","target":"Buses","rationale":"From the sentence, we can figure out that the user is trying to find a bus. The keyword \\"bus\\" in this case is helpful as it indicates that this sentence belongs to the \\"Buses\\" service."},{"source":"You will be given a trivia clue, and the category it belongs to. You should answer with the best answer that belongs in the category and is described by the clue. For consistency, answers should be in all lower cased letters.\\n\\nCategory: COOK UP SOME \\"STU\\" \\nClue: From the Latin for \\"to be astonished\\", it means impressively great","target":"stupendous","rationale":"The answer is a synonym for stupendous, 'stu' would be the first three letters of the clue."},{"source":"Following a close victory over the Chargers, the Steelers traveled to Ford Field for a Week 5 interconference duel with the 1-3 Detroit Lions.  Despite the Lions getting the opening score of the first quarter with a 46-yard field goal from kicker  Jason Hanson, Pittsburgh would answer with running back Rashard Mendenhall's 7-yard touchdown run.  Afterwards, Detroit closed out the opening period with Hanson making another 46-yard field goal.  In the second quarter, the Steelers would deliver a big strike with quarterback Ben Roethlisberger completing a 15-yard touchdown pass to tight end Heath Miller.  Even though the Lions came right back with cornerback Williams James returning an interception 38&#160;yards for a touchdown, Pittsburgh effectively replied with Roethlisberger's 17-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver Hines Ward. In the third quarter, the Steelers would add onto their lead as Roethlisberger threw to rookie wide receiver Mike Wallace on a 47-yard touchdown pass.  Detroit tried to rally in the fourth quarter as quarterback Daunte Culpepper found wide receiver Dennis Northcutt on a 25-yard touchdown pass, but Pittsburgh's defense made a crucial stand with three-straight sacks (courtesy of linebacker LaMarr Woodley, cornerback William Gay, and linebacker Lawrence Timmons), followed by cornerback Ike Taylor swatting away the Lions' last hope from a hail-mary pass.\\n\\nHow many field goals did Jason Hanson kick?","target":"2","rationale":"The answer to the question \\"How many field goals did Jason Hanson kick?\\" is 2. It can be found in this sentence:  Despite the Lions getting the opening score of the first quarter with a 46-yard field goal from kicker  Jason Hanson, Pittsburgh would answer with running back Rashard Mendenhall's 7-yard touchdown run. Afterwards, Detroit closed out the opening period with Hanson making another 46-yard field goal.\\""},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\n\\n\\n\\nQ: Insulin is made up of how many polypeptide chains?\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"two","rationale":"The given paragraph states that insulin is a hormone consisting of two polypeptide chains, one shorter than the other. Therefore, the answer to this question is 'two'."},{"source":"\\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). Given a prompt and two responses, identify which response is the type of \\"yes, and\\". Indicate your answer by 'Response 1' if the first response is correct, otherwise 'Response 2'.  Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange.\\n\\nPrompt: Can I get something that tastes good and has no calories? \\n Response 1: It is! The whole time. This is like our spot. \\n Response 2: Tastes good and has no calories? Water, gotcha.","target":"Response 2","rationale":"Response 1 is incorrect as it does not address the prompt and instead gives an irrelevant answer. Response 2 addresses the prompt and expands on that line of thought by suggesting water, which has no calories and tastes good."},{"source":"Pick the most correct option to answer the following question.\\n\\nThe marsh willow herb is a plant native to the northeastern United States. It grows best in damp habitats. Which of the following environmental changes would most likely cause a decrease in the marsh willow herb population in an area?\\n\\nOptions:\\n\\n- A: a rainstorm lasting several weeks\\n\\n- B: a drought lasting twelve months\\n\\n- C: unusually low temperatures during the month of July\\n\\n- D: unusually high temperatures during the month of January","target":"B","rationale":"The marsh willow herb is a plant that grows best in damp habitats and it's native to the northeastern United States. \\nSince this type of habitat has an abundance of water, option A would not have any effect on its population. On the other hand, options C and D are unlikely to occur during these months because they are too cold or hot respectively. Option B could lead to a decrease in marsh willow herbs since it would prevent them from having access to their basic resources for survival such as water, soil nutrients etcetera, therefore making option B more likely than all others combined.\\n\\n\\nTherefore, answer should be \\"B\\"."},{"source":"Encouragement and praise can come in many forms, and some ways are better for child development than others. Researchers at the University of Chicago who studied mother-child interactions   found that the type of praise children receive affects their attitudes towards challenges later in life.\\nSpecifically, praise that focused on their behavior and the choices that kids made helped them deal with difficult experiences better five years later, compared with praise that focused more on the child himself, like \\"You're a good boy.\\" The study, which appears in the journal Child Development, is the first major study of praise and child development done outside of a lab setting.\\n\\"It's exciting to see _ play out in the real world,\\" said Elizabeth Gunderson who led the study. \\"Praising the efforts, actions and work of kids is going to be more beneficial in their long-term persistence and desire to be challenged and work hard in the future.\\"\\nSuch \\"process praise\\" includes comments such as \\"You worked really hard\\", which emphasize a child's actions. \\"Person praise\\" includes comments like \\"You're so smart\\", which focus on a child's personal qualities. These distinctions   aren't new in the field of psychology, but exactly how they affect children's development over the years hasn't always been clear.\\nAs part of the study, the researchers visited the homes of more than 50 kids between the ages of 1 and 3, and filmed their daily interactions with their parents during 90-minute sessions. Five years later, the researchers followed up with the families, measuring the children's attitudes towards challenges and problem solving. The children who grew up with more process praise were more open to challenges. Though person praise didn't seem to have any negative effect on the children, the study suggests that process praise teaches children that their talents and abilities can be developed and improved, while person praise sends the message that their abilities are fixed and therefore not easily changed.\\nWhich of the following belongs to \\"progress praise\\"?\\nA) You did a good job!\\nB) What an adorable boy!\\nC) You're a real gentleman!\\nD) We are so proud of you!","target":"A","rationale":"The passage mentions that person praise can include comments like \\"You're so smart\\". In the context of this example, \\"smart\\" is meant to be a fixed attribute. The only option among the choices given which fits with what was described as process praise in the article is A: \\"You did a good job!\\"\\nBecause we are told that praising actions and effort will help children develop better long-term persistence, it makes sense that saying something encouraging like ‚Äúyou did a great job‚Äù would fit into category (A)."},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Based on the sentence \\"A black and white dog is playing with an orange ball in the snow.\\", is the sentence \\"A white dog is playing with a kitten.\\" a true sentence?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The first sentence describes a dog which is black and white playing with an orange ball in the snow. The second sentence makes reference to a \\"white\\" dog, but does not mention anything about it being black or not. Additionally, there are no references made within either sentences that definitively link them together (i.e., there's no indication of whether they're talking about the same animal). However, since we do know for sure that one is referring to a dog while the other refers to a kitten, we can conclude that this statement is false as these two statements contradict each other when combined."},{"source":"Given an abstract, indicate which of the provided candidate titles (Option1 and Option2) best describes it (respond with the text of the title, not option1/2).\\n\\nAbstract: Although pelvic inflammatory disease is the most common serious infection among young women of reproductive age in the United States, no nationwide data are available on the patterns of antibiotic treatment of this disease. To examine these patterns we analyzed over 25 million antibiotic prescriptions for treatment of pelvic inflammatory disease from 1966 through 1983, using the National Disease and Therapeutic Index. Most patients received a single antibiotic on an outpatient basis. Overall, use of natural penicillins declined markedly, and use of aminopenicillins more than doubled. Cephalosporins emerged as the most frequently prescribed antibiotic for hospitalized patients. Nationwide surveillance of treatment patterns may help to identify areas needing improvement through continuing education. \\n Which is the apt title for the abstract? option1: Antibiotic treatment of pelvic inflammatory disease. Trends among private physicians in the United States, 1966 through 1983. option2: Alcohol, drugs, and head injury [letter]","target":"Antibiotic treatment of pelvic inflammatory disease. Trends among private physicians in the United States, 1966 through 1983","rationale":"The abstract describes a study that analyzed over 25 million antibiotic prescriptions for treatment of pelvic inflammatory disease from 1966 through 1983 and found that cephalosporins emerged as the most frequently prescribed antibiotic for hospitalized patients. It also states that \\"Nationwide surveillance of treatment patterns may help to identify areas needing improvement through continuing education.\\" The first title, \\"Antibiotic treatment of pelvic inflammatory disease. Trends among private physicians in the United States, 1966 through 1983\\", provides a summary of the main findings and conclusions of this study and illustrates how nationwide surveillance can improve continuing education on this topic. In contrast, the second title is unrelated to the content described in this abstract."},{"source":"Two analogies that signify affordances are given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Affordance is the possibility of an action being done on an object, for example book is an affordance of writing. The phrase \\"A : B\\" implies that B is an affordance of A. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate affordance of the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a single object without further explanation.\\n\\nsing : song. attack : ?","target":"enemy","rationale":"One attacks an enemy. One sings a song."},{"source":"You are given a math word problem and you are supposed to only use subtraction on the numbers embedded in the text to answer the following question and then only report the final numerical answer.\\n\\nContext: Danny collects bottle caps and wrappers. He found 22 bottle caps and 8 wrappers at the park. Now he has 28 bottle caps and 63 wrappers in his collection. \\n\\n Question: How many bottle caps did danny have at first?","target":"6","rationale":"To solve the problem, we need to use addition.\\\\nDanny currently has 28 bottle caps and 63 wrappers.  He found 22 bottle caps and 8 wrappers at the park, so he started with 28 + 22 = 50 bottle caps and 63 + 8 = 71 wrappers in his collection.\\\\nWe know that Danny currently has 50 + 63 = 113 total items in his collection, so to find out how much he had before he found any items, we need to subtract 113 from his current number of items (113)."},{"source":"In this task, you will be presented with a question having multiple possible answers in French language. And you should choose a most suitable option out of \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\", and \\"E\\" based on your commonsense knowledge.\\n\\nQuestion: Quelle d√©cision la plupart des fabricants de c√©r√©ales doivent-ils prendre lorsqu'ils d√©cident de la mani√®re dont ils vont acheter des c√©r√©ales ? \\n Options: A bo√Æte B cabinet C r√©frig√©rateur D armoire E bouche","target":"A","rationale":"According to the question, a cereal manufacturer is looking for a place to buy cereals. Therefore, the options B (cabinet), C (refrigerator), D (armoire) and E (mouth) are not suitable answers. Option A refers to a box where cereals could be stored, so it's most likely that this is the answer."},{"source":"This article: After the October Tour, U2 decamped to a rented cottage in Howth, where they lived, wrote new songs, and rehearsed for their third album, War. Significant musical breakthroughs were achieved by the Edge in August 1982 during a two-week period of independent songwriting, while the other band members vacationed and Bono honeymooned with his wife Ali. From September to November, the group recorded War at Windmill Lane Studios. Lillywhite, who had a policy of not working with an artist more than twice, was convinced by the group to return as their producer for a third time. The recording sessions featured contributions from violinist Steve Wickham and the female singers of Kid Creole and the Coconuts. For the first time, Mullen agreed to play drums to a click track to keep time. After completing the album, U2 undertook a short tour of Western Europe in December.\\nWar's lead single, \\"New Year's Day\\", was released on 1 January 1983. It reached number 10 in the UK and became the group's first hit outside of Europe; in the US, it received extensive radio coverage and peaked at number 53. Resolving their doubts of the October period, U2 released War in February. Critically, the album received favourable reviews, although a few UK reviewers were critical of it. Nonetheless, it was the band's first commercial success, debuting at number one in the UK, while reaching number 12 in the US. War's sincerity and \\"rugged\\" guitar were intentionally at odds with the trendier synthpop of the time. A record on which the band \\"turned pacifism itself into a crusade\\", War was lyrically more political than their first two records, focusing on the physical and emotional effects of warfare. The album included the protest song \\"Sunday Bloody Sunday\\", in which Bono lyrically tried to contrast the events of the 1972 Bloody Sunday shooting with Easter Sunday. Other songs from the record addressed topics such as nuclear proliferation (\\"Seconds\\") and the Polish Solidarity movement (\\"New Year's Day\\"). War was U2's first record to feature... contains an answer for the question: What is the name of the band that recorded at Windmill Lane Studios?, what is it ?","target":"U2","rationale":"The article describes the recording process of U2's album War at Windmill Lane Studios."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate actions to the tools used to perform the action is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates action A to tool B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate tool for the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\neat : spoon. hit : ?","target":"hammer","rationale":"To eat, one could use a spoon. Similarly, to hit something, one could use a hammer."},{"source":"You are provided with an \\"Event\\", \\"Intent\\" and \\"XEmotion\\" (PersonX's reactions for the given \\"Event\\"). Indicate PersonY's reaction (person feels) at the end of this event. Provide one reaction for PersonY. If there's nothing that can be implied, respond as None\\n\\nEvent:PersonX is an hour late for work. Intent:. XEmotion: 1) irresponsible","target":"irritated","rationale":"PersonX being late for work is an irresponsible action, which could potentially cause the boss (PersonY) to be irritated."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to the associated containers is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its associated container B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate container for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\ndetergent : bottle. coat : ?","target":"closet","rationale":"To store detergent, one could place it in a bottle. Similarly, to store a coat, one could put it in a closet."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence from the research paper and the category to which it belongs. Your task is to classify whether the given category is correct or not by providing \\"True\\" and \\"False\\", respectively. Here are the definitions for the categories: Background (Why is this problem important? What relevant works have been created before? What is still missing in the previous works? What are the high-level research questions? How might this help other research or researchers?), Purpose (What specific things do the researchers want to do? What specific knowledge do the researchers want to gain? What specific hypothesis do the researchers want to test?), Method (How did the researchers do the work or find what they sought? What are the procedures and steps of the research?), or Finding (What did the researchers find out? Did the proposed methods work? Did the thing behave as the researchers expected?). \\",\\n\\nSentence: between April 1 and July 15 , 2003 , was studied. \\n Section: finding","target":"False","rationale":"The sentence describes the time period that was studied, which is not a finding. It also does not provide any information about why the problem is important or relevant, what hypotheses were tested, or what procedures and steps were used to conduct the research. So it does not belong in any of these categories either. Instead, this sentence belongs in the \\"Background\\" section because it provides context for when and how long the study was carried out. As a result, \\"False\\" should be returned as an answer to this question."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on geometry. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: the area of a triangle will be when a = 1 m , b = 1 m , c = 2 m , a , b , c being lengths of respective sides ? \\nOptions: a ) 2 , b ) 7 , c ) 5 , d ) 3 , e ) 4","target":"a","rationale":"The area of a triangle is given by the formula: Area = \\\\\\\\(\\\\sqrt { s (s-a)(s-b)(s-c) } \\\\\\\\) where s = \\\\\\\\(\\\\\\\\frac { a+b+c } { 2 } \\\\\\\\) and a, b, c are the lengths of the three sides. So we have: Area = \\\\\\\\(\\\\sqrt { 1 (1 - 1)(1 - 1)(1 - 2) } \\\\\\\\) which gives us an answer of 2."},{"source":"What was likely said next? Hi I would like to order a medium pizza\\nOk can I confirm that this is Lea from your phone number you called in with.","target":"Yes it is.","rationale":"The given context is a conversation between a customer and a representative at a pizza place where the customer had called in to place an order. The previous dialogue shows that the representative has asked the customer to confirm if they are calling from their phone number. Hence, it is reasonable to assume that the user will reply with \\"Yes it is.\\""},{"source":"What is used to make beans into a drink?\\n\\nA. coffee\\n\\nB. kitchen\\n\\nC. food store\\n\\nD. cooking pot\\n\\nE. cooking\\n\\nThe best answer is","target":"D","rationale":"The question asks what is used to make beans into a drink. There are no choices with the word ‚Äúdrink‚Äù in them, so we can eliminate option A and D. The only choice that has anything about cooking or eating is E, but it does not explicitly mention beans, so this answer cannot be correct either. Option B mentions kitchen which could imply beverage-based drinks like coffee from an espresso machine (included under C) but there are too many other things unrelated that you would find in a kitchen for us to know if making bean beverages was one of them; because of the uncertainly around this interpretation we should also discard option B \\nIn conclusion: Choice D must be the best answer because it specifically talks about turning raw ingredients into something edible or digestible -"},{"source":"In this task, you're shown a three-part story, with a beginning, middle, and ending. Your job is to slightly modify the middle part, so that the whole story becomes unlikely, improbable, or inconsistent. Generated sentences must minimally alter the given middle, with at most 4 new words added/existing words removed. Your sentence should be grammatically and syntactically correct. Also stick to the context of the given story. For example, if the story talks about \\"doctors\\", you can talk about \\"health\\" or \\"diagnosis\\", but don't mention \\"aliens\\". Avoid introducing any extra/irrelevant information, and use names instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible. Avoid simply negating the original middle, for example:  \\"She likes cakes.\\" is changed to \\"She doesn't like cakes.\\"\\n\\nBeginning: Ashley wanted to be a ballerina. Middle: Ashley's mom put her in a ballet class and she was in the annual performance. Ending: She did a great job.","target":"Ashley's mom never allowed her to dance","rationale":"The original story states that Ashley's mom put her in a ballet class. Then, it also says that she did a great job in the annual performance. However, this does not necessarily mean that Ashley became a ballerina (ballet dancer). To make the story unlikely, we need to change this assumption. By changing the middle to  \\"Ashley's mom never allowed her to dance\\", we can assume that Ashley was never able to become a ballerina due to her mom's disapproval of dancing."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a context, a sentence,  and a character. The sentence describes an action or job of the given character. Also, the context provides more information about the sentence or the character. Your task is to return one of the emotions which are expressed by the Character in the given sentence. For that you can use the Context; however, Context is not provided in all the inputs. Also, in some inputs, there can be zero emotion; for that return 'None'.\\n\\nContext: Ken went camping with friends. They did not pack appropriately. They ran out of supplies early. \\n Sentence: Ken's trip had to be cut short. \\n Character: Friends","target":"upset","rationale":"Since the friends do not pack appropriately and run out of supplies, leaving Ken's trip to be cut short, it is likely that they are upset at the situation."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the correct option to answer the question.\\nContext: WHITE HOUSE ‚Äî An audio recording was released Monday depicting children desperately crying and begging for their parents after being separated from them by U.S. immigration authorities at its southwestern border, sparking new outrage against the Trump administration and its new \\"zero-tolerance policy\\" towards illegal immigrants.\\nThe nearly eight-minute long recording was released by ProPublica, an independent, investigative news site. ProPublica says an unidentified whistleblower passed on the recording to a civil rights attorney, who gave it to the website.\\nAmong the disturbing sounds heard on the recording was a child identified by ProPublica as a six-year-old girl from El Salvador begging authorities in Spanish to call her aunt to pick her up from the detention center.\\nAt one point in the audio, a man identified as a Border Patrol agent said in Spanish over the cries of scores of children: \\"Well, we have an orchestra here. What's missing is a conductor.\\"\\nPresident Donald Trump defended his administration's policy of forcibly separating children from parents at the U.S. border with Mexico on Monday, saying ‚ÄúThe United States will not be a migrant camp and it will not be a refugee holding facility.\\"\\nTrump, speaking in the White House East Room during a National Space Council meeting, warned that ‚Äúwhat‚Äôs happening in Europe ‚Ä¶ we can‚Äôt allow that to happen to the United States ‚Äì not on my watch.‚Äù\\nEarlier in the day, on the Twitter social media platform, the president inaccurately linked migration in Germany to a rising crime rate. (Actually, the latest German government statistics show reported crimes at the lowest level in 30 years.)\\nNearly 2,000 children were sent to mass detention centers or foster care from mid-April to the end of May, according to government officials.\\nThe regular White House briefing was delayed several times Monday amid the furor as officials huddled with Trump in the West Wing.\\nPress Secretary Sarah Huckabee Sanders finally introduced Department of Homeland Security Secretary Kirstjen...\\nQuestion: Where are the illegal immigrants being detained?\\nOptions:\\n- United States\\n- Mexico\\n- not enough information\\n- Cuba","target":"United States","rationale":"The context mentions a recording of children crying after being separated from their parents by U.S. immigration authorities at the southwestern border, and indicates that these authorities detained them in centers along the United States' southern border with Mexico. The text also states that nearly 2,000 children were sent to mass detention centers or foster care within a period of two months and refers to \\"mass detention centers\\" as facilities where illegal immigrants are held for indeterminate periods of time prior to deportation hearings (or release due to lack of evidence).\\nThese clues indicate that illegal immigrant families have been crossing into the US over its shared border with Mexico, then they've been arrested by U.S. immigration officials who've taken their children away before putting each adult up for trial on charges related to unlawful entry into America"},{"source":"Answer the following question.\\n\\"Which Australian TV presenter has made travel documentaries in various foreign locations, the programmes being called \\"\\"A Postcard From.....\\"\\"?\\"","target":"Saturday Night Clive","rationale":"The presenter is Clive James (Saturday Night Clive), and the programme was called \\"Postcards\\"."},{"source":"Given a math word problem, answer the following question. You might need to apply addition or subtraction mathematical operators on the numbers embedded in the text to answer the question and then only report the final numerical answer.\\n\\nmrs. hilt and her sister drove to a concert 78 miles away . they drove 32 miles and then stopped for gas . her sister put 28 gallons of gas in the car . how many miles did they have left to drive ?","target":"46","rationale":"The question asks us how many miles are left to drive, so we have to find the total distance of the trip and subtract the distance that has already been driven. The total distance is 78 miles. We know that 32 miles were driven before stopping for gas, so 46 miles remain in order to complete the trip."},{"source":"Can we draw the following hypothesis from the context (see options)? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nEarlier this year reporter Judith Miller was jailed for refusing to name the US-government source who identified a member of the US Central Intelligence Agency (CIA), Valerie Plame.\\n\\nHypothesis: judith miller isnt a person\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"The context clearly states that Judith Miller is a reporter and does not state otherwise, hence the hypothesis can be rejected. So the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given the name of an Indian food dish. You need to classify the dish as \\"sweet\\" or \\"spicy\\".\\n\\nNankhatai","target":"sweet","rationale":"Nankhatai is a sweet biscuit that can be found throughout South Asia."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that does not connect with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nTitle: Jason Becomes A Lawyer. Sentence 1: Jason had always dreamed of being a lawyer. Sentence 2: He knew it would be hard work. Sentence 3: He studied hard to finish law school and the bar exam. Sentence 4: When he was complete, he felt great. Choices: a. Susie laughed as mud oozed down Jamie's chin. b. Jason was proud that he was finally a lawyer.","target":"a","rationale":"Sentence a doesn't connect to the rest of the story. The other sentences revolve around Jason's journey to becoming a lawyer, but sentence a refers to two other characters and does not have any connection with Jason becoming a lawyer. Sentence b does connect with the rest of the story because it indicates that Jason is proud that he has finally become a lawyer after working hard for many years."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: Any large molecule is referred to as a macromolecule. Sentence 2: Macromolecules are large molecules made up from small sub-units.","target":"entails","rationale":"Statement 2 provides additional information that supports the scientific fact stated in Statement 1. Statement 1 defines macromolecules as \\"large molecules\\", and Statement 2 explains that the reason they are called \\"macromolecules\\" is because they are made up of many small sub-units. Therefore, Statement 2 provides evidence that supports the definition of macromolecules provided in Statement 1. As a result, Statement 2 entails or implies Statement 1."},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as acceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"The butler polished the silver.","rationale":"Here is an example of a short sentence that can be considered linguistically acceptable: The butler polished the silver."},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\nLarynx The larynx is a cartilaginous structure inferior to the laryngopharynx that connects the pharynx to the trachea and helps regulate the volume of air that enters and leaves the lungs (Figure 22.7). The structure of the larynx is formed by several pieces of cartilage. Three large cartilage pieces‚Äîthe thyroid cartilage (anterior), epiglottis (superior), and cricoid cartilage (inferior)‚Äîform the major structure of the larynx. The thyroid cartilage is the largest piece of cartilage that makes up the larynx. The thyroid cartilage consists of the laryngeal prominence, or ‚ÄúAdam‚Äôs apple,‚Äù which tends to be more prominent in males. The thick cricoid cartilage forms a ring, with a wide posterior region and a thinner anterior region. Three smaller,.\\n\\n\\nQ: What structure connects the pharynx to the trachea?\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- thyroid\\n\\n- aorta\\n\\n- sternum\\n\\n- larynx\\n\\nA:","target":"larynx","rationale":"The larynx, also known as the voice box or Adam's apple is a cartilaginous structure that connects the pharynx to trachea. The three large cartilage pieces (thyroid cartilage(anterior), epiglottis(superior) and cricoid cartilage(inferior)) forms major structures of larynx. So, it can be concluded that \\"larynx\\" is connecting part for this question."},{"source":"Given a passage with a question and an answer to that question, classify if the answer actually answers the question into 'yes' or 'no'. Output 'yes' if the answer answers the question and output 'no' if the answer does not answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Does vulnerability to sympathetic stress persist in takotsubo stress cardiomyopathy?\\nAnswer: We found no difference in standard diastolic parameters between TSC and control subjects, but a significant higher value in LV-MPI in the TSC group at rest. However, no such difference could be demonstrated during DSE between the groups, indicating that vulnerability to sympathetic stimulation does not persist in TSC patients.","target":"no","rationale":"The question asks whether vulnerability to sympathetic stress persists in takotsubo stress cardiomyopathy. The answer describes a study that found no difference between patients with takotsubo stress cardiomyopathy and control subjects in their responses to sympathetic stimulation during a test for diastolic function. However, the answer does not specifically say whether vulnerability to sympathetic stimulation is still present or absent in takotsubo patients.  Therefore, the answer does not directly address the question and is marked as \\"no\\"."},{"source":"The goal is to predict an English answer string for an input English question. \\nQuestion : In which country was cricketer Ted Dexter born?\\nAnswer :","target":"Etymology of Italy","rationale":"Etymology of Italy is not a reasonable answer to the question, \\"In which country was cricketer Ted Dexter born?\\"\\nThe correct answer should be: England."},{"source":"The goal is to predict an English answer string for an input English question. \\nQuestion : Standing at 1,792 feet in height and opened in 2013, the building known as One World Trade Centre is commonly known by what other name ?\\nAnswer :","target":"72 Vesey Street","rationale":"One World Trade Center is commonly known by the name 72 Vesey Street because it was listed as such in New York City documents. \\n72 Vesey Street is also its address."},{"source":"Pick the option in line with common sense to answer the question.\\nQuestions: What is a beaver likely to chew up?\\nOptions:\\n- american forests\\n- great outdoors\\n- rocks\\n- canada\\n- pair of pants","target":"american forests","rationale":"Beavers are herbivores that eat the bark, twigs and leaves of trees. They live primarily in North America and Canada, so it's logical to think they would cut down american forests for their food supply."},{"source":"See the conversation. DIALOG:\\nWhat is Uchucchacuaite?\\n- Uchucchacuaite  Uchucchacuaite (AgMnPbSbS) is a rare sulfosalt mineral found in hydrothermal deposits.\\n- Where is it found?\\n- It was first described in 1984 for an occurrence in the Uchucchacua Mine, Oyon Province, Lima Department, Peru and named for the mine.\\n- Where else is it found?\\n-","target":"It has also been reported from mines in Hokkaido, Japan.","rationale":"The person is asking \\"where else Uchucchacuaite is found?\\" and the answer (\\"It has also been reported from mines in Hokkaido, Japan.\\") would be a good response to this question."},{"source":"Formulate an answer to this elaborate question: Who did the vocals on the song \\"Warm Machine\\"?","target":"Gavin Rossdale","rationale":"The answer to this question is determined by the information given in one of the answers. Gavin Rossdale, lead singer of Bush, performed vocals on many songs including \\"Warm Machine\\". Therefore, we can conclude that he did perform vocals for this song as well and should be marked correct."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: When I was small, my grandmother died. I was so sad that I had no tears. But that night when my dad tried to cheer me up, my laugh turned into crying.\\nSo it came as no surprise to learn that scientists believe crying and laughing come from the same part of the brain. Just as laughing has many health advantages, scientists are discovering that so, too, does crying.\\nWhatever it takes for us to _ pressure is important to our emotional   health, and a study found that 85 percent of women and 73 percent of men report feeling better after crying.\\nBesides, tears attract help from other people. Researchers agree that when we cry, people around us become kinder and friendly and they are more ready to provide support and comfort. Tears also enable us to understand our emotions better; sometimes we don't even know we're very sad until we cry. We learn about our emotions through crying, and then we can deal with them.\\nJust as crying can be healthy, not crying - holding back tears of anger, pain or suffering - can be bad for physical   health. Studies have shown that too much control of emotions can lead to high blood pressure and heart problems. If you have a health problem, doctors will certainly not ask you to cry. But when you feel like crying, don't fight it. It's a natural -and healthy-emotional response  .\\nQuestion: According to the passage, always holding back our emotions will lead to   _  .\\nOptions: A: head problems\\nB: blood pressure problems\\nC: heart problems\\nD: B and C","target":"D","rationale":"According to the passage, holding back tears of anger or pain can be bad for physical health and may lead to high blood pressure. The study mentioned also found that too much control of emotions could cause heart problems. So answer D is correct: \\"B and C\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you need to reverse the order of words in the given sentence.\\n\\nSentence: a man on a giant bicycle rides by a tall pole in front of an empty large field in front of some mountains","target":"mountains some of front in field large empty an of front in pole tall a by rides bicycle giant a on man a","rationale":"The original sentence is 'a man on a giant bicycle rides by a tall pole in front of an empty large field in front of some mountains'. The last word is 'mountains', so it should be the first word. Next, the second-to-last word is 'some', so it will be the 2nd word. This goes on until all words are reversed, and we get: \\"mountains some of front in field large empty an of front in pole tall a by rides bicycle giant a on man a\\""},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and extract the answer for the question: What was the first name of the person who was arrested in Toronto?\\n\\nIn preparation for the trial, Hendrix had his hair cut, and he purchased new clothes. One of his defense lawyers, Bob Levine, commented: \\"I took him to a number of stores that specialized in tailored suits. We found a conservative suit that looked great on him. It was hilarious. He was like a hick, awkwardly fidgeting around and trying to loosen his tie. I didn't care how uncomfortable he was; the suit was perfect.\\"On December 7, while Hendrix and Levine were travelling by limousine to a New York airport for their flight to Toronto, Levine noticed that Hendrix was putting some personal items into his guitar case. Levine then reminded him that they would be going through customs and that they had better not bring anything inappropriate. He reassured Levine, but as they approached their destination Levine confronted him: \\"Jimi, I know you have something in that guitar case. I don't know what it is, and it's not normally my business to interfere, but I know we will be searched at customs.\\" Hendrix insisted that he had nothing to worry about, stating: \\"Trust me, Bob, no one is going to recognize me\\", to which he replied: \\"Recognize you? They will be waiting at customs for you.\\" Soon after their arrival at the Toronto airport, Hendrix was arrested by customs agents who found a capsule of an unknown substance in his guitar case. He spent the night in jail, waiting for it to be tested. Later that day, the Toronto police department dropped the charges when the pill was determined to be a legal medication.","target":"Jimi","rationale":"The paragraph mentions someone who was arrested in Toronto. Based on the context, it is likely that this person could be Hendrix; he had his hair cut and purchased new clothes before attending a trial (the first two clues). He also travelled to Toronto with Levine by limousine (third clue) and was later confronted about something being inside his guitar case at customs which led to him spending a night in jail due to illegal substances found there (fourth and fifth clues);\\nHowever, the fact that after these events took place, \\"Hendrix\\" bought some more things from 'a number of stores' suggests that the actual suspect's name might not have been Hendrix but rather James or Jimi as such names are usually abbreviated forms of longer ones like Jameson etc."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to concatenate all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, and print the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n7, 7, ['V', '597', 'v', '7715', '8667', '6677', '6063', 'Z', '4313']","target":"6063","rationale":"Given the list ['V', '597', 'v', '7715', '8667', '6677', '6063', 'Z'], we need to find the elements from the 7th element to 7th element.\\\\n1. The 7nd element is 6063.\\\\n2. The 8th element is Z and it does not contribute because i is equal to j, which means that only one number should be taken into consideration for calculating the result."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate places/locations to the associated travel mode is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates place A to travel mode B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate travel mode for the given place C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nwashington : train. spain : ?","target":"airplane","rationale":"To go to Washington, one could take a train. Similarily, one could go to Spain by taking an airplane."},{"source":"Given a passage, construct a question on the basis of the information present in the passage. Construct the question in such a way that (i) it is unambiguous, (ii) it is answerable from the passage, (iii) its answer is unique (iv) it answer uses text phrases from the passage. Avoid creating questions that (i) can't be answered correctly without actually understanding the passage and (ii) uses the same words or phrases given in the passage.\\n\\nTo investigate the mechanism by which methylprednisolone protects the liver from hypoxia-induced injury.', 'Prospective control study using the isolated rat liver.', 'Animal research facility.', 'Male, fasted, pathogen-free Sprague-Dawley rats.', 'Low-flow hypoxia was produced by reducing afferent perfusate pressure from 10 to 2.5 cm H(2)O; isolated livers were portally perfused for 2 hrs.', \\"We measured mitochondrial membrane potential and hydrogen peroxide production by imaging rhodamine 123 and 2'-7'-dichlorofluorescein fluorescence, respectively. Leakage of mitochondrial enzymes was also monitored by assaying mitochondrial aspartate aminotransferase activity in the outflow perfusate, and the radical-scavenging effect of methylprednisolone was assessed by measuring luminol-dependent hydrogen peroxide chemiluminescence. Apoptosis in liver cells was determined by using terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase-mediated dUTP-digoxigenin nick-end labeling. Rhodamine 123 fluorescence was significantly diminished in the hypoxic liver, especially in the region of the terminal hepatic venules, which is indicative of membrane depolarization in the mitochondria in those areas. Hypoxia-induced mitochondrial dysfunction was indicated by leakage of aspartate aminotransferase into the outflow perfusate, and increased 2'-7'-dichlorofluorescein fluorescence indicated increased hydrogen peroxide levels, particularly in the midzone. Pretreatment with 30, 10, or 3 mg/kg of methylprednisolone inhibited the hypoxia-induced mitochondrial membrane depolarization and enzyme leakage, although hydrogen peroxide levels and apoptosis in sinusoidal endothelial cells were unaffected.","target":"Does methylprednisolone inhibit low-flow hypoxia-induced mitochondrial dysfunction in isolated perfused rat liver?","rationale":"The given statement is about a study of methylprednisolone protecting the liver from hypoxia-induced injury. The question should ask about the effects of methylprednisolone on isolated rat livers. The question \\"Does methylprednisolone inhibit low-flow hypoxia-induced mitochondrial dysfunction in isolated perfused rat liver?\\" asks how methylprednisolone affects isolated rat livers and uses phrases that are present in the statement as evidence to support this claim.\\n\\n[Extra Credit]\\n[Instruction and Question]\\nGiven a text paragraph and an interrogative sentence, provide an option which can be used to replace \`<option>\` in the interrogative sentence such that it forms a meaningful sentence.\\\\n\\\\nParagraph: There are several reasons for using generics instead of normal collections: 1) type safety 2) performance 3) convenience 4) code clarity 5)\\\\u2026 Question: One reason for using Generics over normal Collections is <option>.\\n\\n[Answer]\\ncode clarity\\n\\n \\"\\""},{"source":"The first Archivist, R.D.W. Connor, began serving in 1934, when the National Archives was established by Congress. As a result of a first Hoover Commission recommendation, in 1949 the National Archives was placed within the newly formed General Services Administration (GSA). The Archivist served as a subordinate official to the GSA Administrator until the National Archives and Records Administration became an independent agency on April 1, 1985. Please tell me The Archivist took on what role after the incorporation of the Nation Archives into GSA? If you can't find the answer, please respond \\"unanswerable\\".","target":"subordinate official","rationale":"The answer to this question is \\"subordinate official\\". This can be inferred from the context which states that: 'the Archivist served as a subordinate official to the GSA Administrator until...'"},{"source":"I have a new situation: Hill town was full of gasoline powered vehicles, while Valley town 50 miles away, banned all gas powered vehicles and allows only electrical vehicles or horse-and-buggies.\\n\\nBut I can use this background: Gasoline-powered vehicles emit a lot of harmful materials. Nitrogen oxides are formed when atmospheric nitrogen reacts with oxygen at the high temperatures found in a car engine. Carbon monoxide is a by-product of incomplete combustion of hydrocarbons. Evaporated and unused fuel releases volatile hydrocarbons into the atmosphere to help form smog. The presence of a catalytic converter in the exhaust system of the car causes these materials to react and be changed into less harmful products.\\n\\nWhat is an answer for this question: Which town had fewer volatile hydrocarbons in the atmosphere?","target":"Valley","rationale":"Volatile hydrocarbons are released into the atmosphere by gasoline-powered vehicles. Hill town is full of these cars, while Valley town has banned them in favor of electric and horse-drawn vehicles. This means that there will be fewer volatile hydrocarbons in the air over Valley town than over Hill town, so the answer is \\"Valley\\"."},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: Mary went back to the kitchen. Sandra travelled to the kitchen. John moved to the bathroom. Sandra travelled to the bedroom. John went to the hallway. Daniel went to the hallway. John went to the kitchen. Sandra moved to the kitchen. Question: Where is John?","target":"kitchen","rationale":"The last entry in the passage states that \\"John went to the kitchen.\\""},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: Little Peter is a boy of nine. He began to go to school the year before last and now he's in Grade Three. He lives not far from the school but he is often late for class. He likes watching TV in the evening and goes to bed late, so he can't get up on time in the morning.\\nThis term, Mrs. Black, Peter's aunt, works in Peter's school. She teaches Grade Three math. She's strict  with Peter and often tells the boy to obey  the school rules and come to school on time. Yesterday morning Peter got up late. When he hurried to school, it was half past eight. His aunt was waiting for him at the school gate.\\n\\"You're ten minutes late for the first class, Peter,\\" Mrs. Black said angrily. \\"Why are you often late for class?\\"\\n\\"Every time I get to the street corner, I see a guidepost . It says: \\"SCHOOL--GO SLOW!'\\"\\nQuestion: The guidepost is for   _  .\\nOptions: A: workers\\nB: Peter\\nC: drivers\\nD: teachers","target":"C","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"C"},{"source":"I am testing my students' logic.\\nWhat is the answer they should choose between \\"the Earth\\" and \\"the moon\\"?\\nLogic test: If an asteroid passes halfway between the Earth and the moon, in which direction is it going to be pulled? (A) towards the Earth (B) towards the moon","target":"the Earth","rationale":"The gravity of the Earth is stronger than that of the moon, which means that it will have a greater pull on the asteroid. The correct answer is therefore A - towards Earth."},{"source":"Given a paragraph about movies and a set of conversational questions and answers about the paragraph, say whether the passage contains sufficient information to answer the follow-up question. Say Yes if it is answerable; otherwise, say No. The paragraph has the prefix 'CONTEXT:'. Each conversation question has a prefix \`Q:\` followed by the answer prefix \`A:\`, and the follow-up question has a prefix \`FOLLOWUP_Q:\`.\\n\\nCONTEXT: It's hard to say because most of the camera angles in that scene are taken from the lance side of the knights. Any sheathed weapons, such as swords, would be on the shield side for a crossdraw, and thus away from the camera angle. There is one shot from a falling horse late in the scene where the hilt of a sheathed sword becomes briefly visible. Whether this sword is strapped to the horse (a common means of keeping secondary weapons), or belongs to one of the Scots on the ground, is difficult to determine. On the other hand, non-sheathed weapons such as maces, warhammers and battleaxes tended to be attached via a strap to the belt or trousers on the right hand side. These were common secondary weapons for knights, and we should be able to see some of them in the scene, but none are visible. Chances are you are correct, and these weapons were not included as part of the cavalry equipment. Most likely this was done to reduce the cost of filming. After all, the knights get slaughtered in the scene and we don't see any scenes where they get to fight back after falling from their horses, so these weapons are redundant from a filming standpoint.  <sep>  Q: Are the cavalry knights missing close melee weapons in Braveheart? A: It's hard to say because most of the camera angles in that scene are taken from the lance side of the knights  Q: do u agree with me when i say they should have did different angles so we can better understand? A: There is one shot from a falling horse late in the scene where the hilt of a sheathed sword becomes briefly visible  <sep> FOLLOWUP_Q: ok awesome i will look again, do you this melee would be a much needed wepon","target":"Yes","rationale":"Yes, the passage provides sufficient information to answer the follow-up question."},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: What is the one thing that is mentioned about the subject of the passage?\\nContext: Information had been kept on digital tape for five years, with Kahle occasionally allowing researchers and scientists to tap into the clunky database. When the archive reached its fifth anniversary, it was unveiled and opened to the public in a ceremony at the University of California, Berkeley.","target":"clunky database","rationale":"The context mentions that the digital tape had been kept for five years, and when it reached its fifth anniversary it was unveiled. It also states that occasionally researchers were allowed to tap into this database, which is described as \\"clunky\\". The only thing we know about the subject of the passage is that it has a clunky database."},{"source":"Premise: A blond woman in a green skirt overlooks as something is happening.\\n\\nHypothesis: The woman is in a blue skirt.\\n\\n.Choose the correct answer: Given the premise, can we conclude the hypothesis?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise explicitly states that the woman is wearing a green skirt, whereas the hypothesis claims she is in a blue skirt. Since this contradicts what we are given, it would not be possible to conclude that the hypothesis is true."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the union of two given sets. A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. Union of two given sets is the smallest set which contains all the elements of both the sets. To find the union of two given sets, A and B is a set that consists of all the elements of A and all the elements of B such that no element is repeated.\\n\\nSet1: '{7}', Set2: '{1}'. How many elements are there in the union of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"2","rationale":"The union of Set1 and Set2 is '{1, 7}', which has two elements."},{"source":"Determine if the provided SQL statement properly addresses the given question. Output 1 if the SQL statement is correct and 0 otherwise. An SQL query works by selecting data from a table where certain conditions apply. A table contains columns where every row in that table must have a value for each column. Every table has a primary key that uniquely identifies each row, usually an id. To choose which columns are returned you specify that after the \\"SELECT\\" statement. Next, you use a \\"FROM\\" statement to specify what tables you want to select the data from. When you specify a table you can rename it with the \\"AS\\" statement. You can reference that table by whatever name follows the \\"AS\\" statement. If you want to select data from multiple tables you need to use the \\"JOIN\\" statement. This will join the tables together by pairing a row in one table with every row in the other table (Cartesian Product). To limit the number of rows returned you should use the \\"ON\\" statement. This will only return rows where the condition specified after the statement is true, this is usually an equals operator with primary keys. You can also use the \\"WHERE\\" statement to specify that only rows with column values statisfying a certain condition, should be returned. The \\"GROUP BY\\" statement will group rows together that have equal column values for whatever columns follows the statement. The \\"HAVING\\" statement will return groups that statisfy whatever condition follows the statement. Any column(s) being returned from grouped rows must either be an aggregate function, (AVG, MAX, COUNT, SUM, ...) of a column, or the column(s) that the data was grouped by. To sort the returned data you can use the \\"ORDER BY\\" command which will order the data by whatever aggregate function or column follows the statement. The \\"DESC\\" statement will sort in descending order and the \\"ASC\\" statement will sort in ascending order. Finally, you can use the \\"LIMIT\\" statement to return a certain number of rows. When \\"*\\" is used in an SQL statement every column is returned. For example, SELECT * FROM table WHERE attribute = 1, will select every column from rows with the attribute column equal to 1.\\n\\nQuery: SELECT count(*) WHERE {\\n?x0 ns:people.person.gender ns:m.02zsn .\\n?x0 ns:people.person.sibling_s/ns:people.sibling_relationship.sibling|ns:fictional_universe.fictional_character.siblings/ns:fictional_universe.sibling_relationship_of_fictional_characters.siblings ?x1 .\\n?x1 a ns:people.person .\\nFILTER ( ?x0 != ?x1 ) .\\nM2 ns:film.film.edited_by ?x0 .\\nM2 ns:film.film.written_by ?x0\\n} Question: Did a art director influence M1 's star and influence M2 's sequel 's cinematographer , star , and writer","target":"0","rationale":"In this question, we are asked to determine if the given SQL query properly addresses the question. The SQL query doesn't work because it only contains a 'SELECT' statement, but no 'FROM' or 'WHERE' statements. Therefore, the answer should be 0."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and question which can be answered using the sentence. Your task is to answer the question using the information from the sentence. The answer to the question is unique and it is a continuous text span from the sentence.\\n\\nSentence: Set in an alternate near-future Japan , the protagonist of the story , a young woman codenamed \`\` Kabuki '' , acts as an agent and television law-enforcement personality for a clandestine government body known as \`\` The Noh '' . \\n Question: where is something set  in?","target":"Japan","rationale":"The answer to the question is 'Japan'. It can be inferred from the sentence that the alternate near-future Japan is where something is set in."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the intersection of two given sets.  A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. The intersection of two given sets is the largest set which contains all the elements that are common to both sets. To find the intersection of two given sets, A and B is a set consisting of all the elements common to both A and B.\\n\\nSet1: '{16, 4, 5, 6}', Set2: '{1, 4, 5, 6, 14, 15}'. How many elements are there in the intersection of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"3","rationale":"Given set A = {16, 4, 5, 6} and set B = {1, 4, 5. 6, 14. 15}, the intersection of these two sets are: \\\\nA n B = {4. 5. 6}\\\\n\\\\nThe number of elements in this intersection are 3"},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to identify which one of following five services the sentence is related to - Media, Travel, Flights, Buses, RideSharing\\n\\nHey, so I need some tickets for a bus trip.","target":"Buses","rationale":"This sentence is a question about bus tickets which means it is related to the 'Buses' service."},{"source":"Text: Manx pound -- UK notes and coins (whether from banks in England, Scotland, or Northern Ireland) are generally accepted in the Isle of Man, but Manx notes and coins are not generally accepted in the UK. To assist those travelling, the ATMs at the Sea Terminal, Douglas, and at Isle of Man Airport issue Bank of England notes only. A number of businesses accept euros.\\n\\nAnswer the following yes/no question: are isle of man pounds legal tender in england? Yes or no?","target":"No","rationale":"The text mentions that UK notes and coins are generally accepted in the Isle of Man, but it doesn't mention anything about Isle of Man pounds being legal tender in England. \\nHowever, there is a sentence mentioning \\"a number of businesses accept euros\\". Since euro is not an official currency used by England, we can conclude from this statement that if some businesses accept non-English currencies like euros as payment for goods or services then they would also be able to do so with other foreign currencies such as the Isle of Man pound. Hence, No"},{"source":"Read the following article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: Many textbooks are not written in the kind of English that we speak every day. In fact, sometimes the reading is so difficult that it almost seems like a foreign language. In a way, it is--the language of science. You should not expect to be able to read a difficult science passage the same way you read an interesting story; you should not expect to read it easily and all at once. Instead, you may have to read it several times through, catching on the meaning of difficult words, going back over difficult sentences, and finally putting the whole thing together. Do not be discourages if the whole passage don't make sense to you at first. You need to pick it apart patiently until you can understand it.\\nThese are the steps to follow when you are reading something difficult:\\n1. Start to read normally until you _ a sentence that doesn't make sense to you.\\n2. When a sentence doesn't make sense, go back and read it again more slowly.\\n3. Look for any word you don't know in the sentence. Try to understand their meanings using word parts and context clues . If necessary, look them up in the dictionary.\\n4. Look at the next few sentences to see if they explain more about the sentence you are working on. Do not read very much farther ahead until you understand what is being said.\\n5. Finally, read the sentence again. Try to put it into simpler words.\\n6. Read through the passage once. Try to understand all the hard parts well. Then read the whole passage once more at a usual speed. This helps you to put all ides together.\\nThe stops sound a lot harder than they are. It is really just the normal way good readers understand anything that is difficult to read. After you have done the best you can this way, you should always feel free to ask for help from your teacher, if you have one.\\nQuestion: The massage is mainly about   _  .\\n- steps of studying science\\n- difficulties in reading science\\n- ways of reading science passages\\n- researches on science and English","target":"ways of reading science passages","rationale":"The article is mainly focused on ways of reading science passages. It talks about the unique features and difficulties that come with reading scientific texts, as well as strategies for overcoming them.\\nSo the answer is ways of reading science passages"},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an implausible answer to a question that involves \\"transient v. stationary\\" events, i.e., the understanding of whether an event will change over time or not. For example, the sentence \\"he was born in the U.S.\\" contains a stationary event since it will last forever; however, \\"he is hungry\\" contains a transient event since it will remain true for a short period of time. Even though there exist multiple wrong answers, we only need a single wrong answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: There are some exceptions, including pregnancies that resulted from sexual assault, incest or other violations of law. \\nQuestion: Are the victims still pregnant?","target":"two-day sexual assault","rationale":"The sentence is discussing exceptions to cases where the victim does not choose to have an abortion. The exception for a two-day sexual assault is implausible since the victim would have already given birth, and therefore not be pregnant."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a string that only contains single digit numbers spelled out. The input string will not contain spaces between the different numbers. Your task is to return the number that the string spells out. The string will spell out each digit of the number for example '1726' will be 'oneseventwosix' instead of 'one thousand seven hundred six'.\\n\\nonefivetwothreetwoseven","target":"152327","rationale":"Given the string 'onefivetwothreetwoseven', each digit is spelled out. The resulting number would be 152327."},{"source":"Answer the question depending on the context.\\nContext: Voiced consonants are seldom actually aspirated. Symbols for voiced consonants followed by ‚ü®‚óå ∞‚ü©, such as ‚ü®b ∞‚ü©, typically represent consonants with breathy voiced release (see below). In the grammatical tradition of Sanskrit, aspirated consonants are called voiceless aspirated, and breathy-voiced consonants are called voiced aspirated.;\\nQuestion: Voiced aspirated consonants are what type?;\\nAnswer:","target":"breathy-voiced","rationale":"This is a valid question because it relates directly to the context.\\nVoiced consonants are seldom actually aspirated, whereas voiced aspirated consonants are breathy-voiced. The symbols for voiced consonants followed by ‚ü®‚óå ∞‚ü© represent words with breathy-voice release and not aspiration as assumed in the answer options (see below). \\nIn Sanskrit grammatical tradition, voiceless aspirated means that sounds end in voicing but begin without voice; hence they may be described as \\"aspirate\\". On other hand, Voiced Aspirates refer to those who start with voicing and do not end in voicing like their counterparts - unvoiced obstruents or stops which have no vocal fold vibration during vowel articulation.. In brief: Vo"},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- India, officially the Republic of India (\\"Bhrat Gaarjya\\"), is a country in South Asia. It is the seventh-largest country by area, the second-most populous country (with over 1.2 billion people), and the most populous democracy in the world. It is bounded by the Indian Ocean on the south, the Arabian Sea on the southwest, and the Bay of Bengal on the southeast. It shares land borders with Pakistan to the west; China, Nepal, and Bhutan to the northeast; and Myanmar (Burma) and Bangladesh to the east. In the Indian Ocean, India is in the vicinity of Sri Lanka and the Maldives. India's Andaman and Nicobar Islands share a maritime border with Thailand and Indonesia. Its capital is New Delhi; other metropolises include Mumbai, Kolkata, Chennai, Bangalore, Hyderabad and Ahmedabad.\\n\\n- Oceania (or ), also known as Oceanica, is a region centred on the islands of the tropical Pacific Ocean. Opinions of what constitutes Oceania range from its three subregions of Melanesia, Micronesia, and Polynesia to, more broadly, the entire insular region between Southeast Asia and the Americas, including Australasia and the Malay Archipelago.\\n\\n- An island country is a country whose primary territory consists of one or more islands or parts of islands. As of 2011, 46 (approximately 24%) of the 193 UN member states are island countries.\\n\\n- Bandung (formerly Dutch: Bandoeng, Sundanese: ), is the capital of West Java province in Indonesia and Greater Bandung made up of 2 municipalities and 38 districts, making it Indonesia's 2nd largest metropolitan area with 8,199,892 inhabitants at the 2014 Badan Pusat Statistik data. It is nation's fourth largest city (by land area), and the third largest city by population (within city proper), with over 2.4 million. Located above sea level, approximately south east of Jakarta, Bandung has cooler temperatures year-round than most other Indonesian cities. The city lies on a river basin surrounded by volcanic mountains. This topography provides a natural defense system, which was the primary reason for the Dutch East Indies government's plan to move the colony capital from Batavia (modern-day Jakarta) to Bandung.\\n\\n- Karawang Regency is a regency \\"(kabupaten)\\" of West Java, Indonesia. Karawang is its capital.\\n\\n- Batujaya is an archeological site located in the village of Batujaya , Karawang in West Java , Indonesia . The site is five square kilometers in area and comprises at least 30 structural in what Sundanese call hunyur or unur ( high mounds of earth consisting of artifacts ) . Unur is similar to the manapo found at the Muara Jambi archaeological site . The site was first found and examined by archaeologists from the University of Indonesia in 1984 . Excavations have since uncovered 17 unur , of which three are in the form of pools . The structures found are made of bricks composed of a mixtures of clay and rice husks ( vajra - lepa ) , not volcanic rock which is difficult to find in Batujaya . Two structures recovered are in the form of temples , one of which , known as Jiwa Temple , has been restored . According to Dr Tony Djubiantono , the head of Bandung Archeology Agency , Jiwa was built in the 2nd century . As local Indonesian governments do not maintain the site , Ford provides funds for research and excavation of the Batujaya complex as part of its Conservation and Environmental Grants . The discovery of this archaeological site was important as although it was the location of Tarumanagara , the oldest Hindu - Buddhist kingdom in Indonesia , West Java lacks ancient temple remains . Before the discovery , only four temple sites have been found in West Java , namely they are Cangkuang temple ( in Garut ) , Ronggeng Temple , Pamarican Temple , and Pananjung Temple ( in Ciamis ) . Preliminary research at Jiwa found that the temple was built between the fifth and sixth centuries . This is based on the inscriptions found on numerous votive tablets discovered in the area , small clay tablets with inscriptions and pictures of Buddha used in prayer . Prof. Dr. Budihartono ( a senior anthropologist from University of Indonesia ) proposed carrying out pollen analysis for examining both the paleoenvironment and also cultural records , including evidence of diet and food processing . In and around the site is also...\\n\\n- West Java (abbreviated as \\"Jabar\\") is a province of Indonesia. It is located in the western part of the island of Java and its capital and largest urban center is Bandung, although much of its population in the northwest corner of the province live in areas suburban to the even larger urban area of Jakarta, even though that city itself lies outside the administrative province. The province's population is 46.3 million (in 2014) and it is the most populous and most densely populated of Indonesia's provinces.\\n\\n- A Muslim is someone who follows or practises Islam, a monotheistic Abrahamic religion. Muslims consider the Quran (Koran), their holy book, to be the verbatim word of God as revealed to the Islamic prophet and messenger Muhammad. They also follow the teachings and practices of Muhammad (\\"sunnah \\") as recorded in traditional accounts (\\"hadith\\"). \\"Muslim\\" is an Arabic word meaning \\"one who submits (to God)\\".\\n\\n- Jakarta , (formerly named Sunda Kelapa, Jayakarta and Batavia) officially the Special Capital Region of Jakarta, is the capital and most populous city of the Republic of Indonesia.\\n\\n- Southeast Asia or Southeastern Asia is a subregion of Asia, consisting of the countries that are geographically south of China, east of India, west of New Guinea and north of Australia. The region lies near the intersection of geological plates, with heavy seismic and volcanic activity. Southeast Asia consists of two geographic regions:\\n\\n- Indonesia (or ; Indonesian: ), officially the Republic of Indonesia, is a unitary sovereign state and transcontinental country located mainly in Southeast Asia with some territories in Oceania. Situated between the Indian and Pacific oceans, it is the world's largest island country, with more than seventeen thousand islands. At , Indonesia is the world's 14th-largest country in terms of land area and world's 7th-largest country in terms of combined sea and land area. It has an estimated population of over 260 million people and is the world's fourth most populous country, the most populous Austronesian nation, as well as the most populous Muslim-majority country. The world's most populous island of Java contains more than half of the country's population.\\n\\n- Java (Indonesian: Jawa; Javanese: ; Sundanese: ) is an island of Indonesia. With a population of over 141 million (the island itself) or 145 million (the administrative region) Census released in December 2015, Java is home to 56.7 percent of the Indonesian population and is the most populous island on Earth. The Indonesian capital city, Jakarta, is located on western Java. Much of Indonesian history took place on Java. It was the center of powerful Hindu-Buddhist empires, the Islamic sultanates, and the core of the colonial Dutch East Indies. Java was also the center of the Indonesian struggle for independence during the 1930s and 1940s. Java dominates Indonesia politically, economically and culturally.\\n\\n- Tin is a chemical element with the symbol¬†Sn (for ) and atomic number¬†50, is a post-transition metal in group 14 of the periodic table. It is obtained chiefly from the mineral cassiterite, which contains tin dioxide, SnO. Tin shows a chemical similarity to both of its neighbors in group 14, germanium and lead, and has two main oxidation states, +2 and the slightly more stable +4. Tin is the 49th most abundant element and has, with 10 stable isotopes, the largest number of stable isotopes in the periodic table, thanks to its magic number of protons. It has two main allotropes: at room temperature, the stable allotrope is -tin, a silvery-white, malleable metal, but at low temperatures it transforms into the less dense grey -tin, which has the diamond cubic structure. Metallic tin is not easily oxidized in air.\\n\\n- Karawang (Kota Karawang or Karawang Kota) is the capital of the Karawang Regency of West Java, Indonesia. It is located 32 miles east of Jakarta. \\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the paragraphs above, decide what entity has the relation 'located in the administrative territorial entity' with 'karawang regency'.","target":"batujaya","rationale":"Your rationale states that ‚Äúbatujaya is located in Karawang Regency.‚Äù\\nThe entity has the relation \\"located in\\" with 'karawang regency'."},{"source":"In 2002, Iglesias decided to release a fourth Spanish-language album titled Quizas (Perhaps). A more polished musical production than his previous Spanish albums and containing more introspective songs, the album's title track is a song about the strained relationship Iglesias has with his famous father.  The album debuted at number twelve on the Billboard 200 albums chart, the highest placement of a Spanish language album on the chart at that period. Quizas sold a million copies in a week, making it the fastest-selling album in Spanish in five years. The three singles released from the album all ended up topping the Latin chart, giving Iglesias a total of sixteen number ones on the chart. He currently holds the record for the most number one singles on Billboard's Latin Chart. His last single from the album, \\"Para Que La Vida\\", reached a million spins on U.S. radio, the only Spanish language song to do so.  The video to the song \\"Quizas\\" was the first Spanish language music video to be added to the selection on one of MTV's popular shows, Total Request Live. Iglesias performed the song on The Tonight Show with Jay Leno, becoming the first to sing a Spanish song on the show, and opening doors for other artists such as Ricky Martin, Juanes and Jorge Drexler to perform their Spanish material. Iglesias included songs from Quizas in his \\"Don't Turn Off the Lights Tour\\", and the album went on to win the Latin Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album.  By 2003 Iglesias released his seventh album, which he called 7, the second to be co-written by Iglesias. Among its more 1980s-inspired material, it features the song \\"Roamer\\", which he wrote with his friend and longtime guitarist, Tony Bruno. The CD also contained the song \\"Be Yourself\\", a song about independence (the chorus talks about how Iglesias' own parents did not believe he'd ever succeed in his singing career). The first single was the song \\"Addicted\\", and was followed closely by a remix of the song \\"Not in Love\\", featuring Kelis.  With this album, Iglesias went on his biggest world tour to date. The highly publicised tour started with twelve shows in the United States ending with Iglesias playing at Houston Rodeo and continued on to several countries, most of which he'd never previously visited playing to sold-out arenas and stadiums in Australia, India, Egypt and Singapore before ending his tour in South Africa.\\n\\nAnswer this question \\"Is Quizas and 7 the name of a song?\\" by extracting the answer from the text above.","target":"In 2002, Iglesias decided to release a fourth Spanish-language album titled Quizas","rationale":"Quizas is the name of a song from Iglesias's Spanish-language album Quizas\\nThe entire context above refers to this particular song so it only makes sense that \\"Is Quizas and 7 the name of a song?\\" would be answered with: In 2002, Iglesias decided to release a fourth Spanish-language album titled Quizas"},{"source":"Rubbish sorting   probably doesn't sound like much fun. But there is a new mobile game that may change your opinion about it, and you might even learn something while you play it-Meet Sortee.\\nMeet Sortee is a puzzle game developed by Flow Studio, a UK company. It makes you think deeply about everyday objects and their meanings.\\nThe rule of the game is quite simple. Two bins are placed on either side of the screen. Each of the bins has a label   next to it and the label explains what it is for. When an object, such as a car or an apple, appears on the screen, you need to decide which bin it should be sorted into and then send it there by moving your finger.\\nThe game seems easy enough at first. But as you move on to more levels, it gets harder. The number of bins increases to three or four and the time given gets shorter. You need to think and move faster. That can be really difficult.\\nThere are 400 0bjects in total and more than 100 bins in the game.  The more objects you correctly sort, the more game coins you can get It's a bit like working in a rubbish recycling center,  but it has no bad smell.\\nYou can download the free game from Apple's app store  ,  but it only lets you play the first few levels. If you want to open the next 40 levels, you need to pay 6 yuan for the full game.\\nWhich of the following can we infer   from the passage?\\nA) You can play the full game for free.\\nB) You can play the full game easily.\\nC) There are only 2 bins in each level.\\nD) There are over 40 levels in the game.","target":"D","rationale":"The  passage says that the rule of the game is simple: sort objects into one or more bins. It also says, \\"You need to think and move faster\\" as you progress through levels in which there are three or four bins. Finally, it states that there are over 100 different bins in all. Therefore, answer D) seems most reasonable based on this information."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, a context passage, and four options which are terms from the passage. After reading a passage, you will get a brief understanding of the terms. Your job is to determine by searching and reading further information of which term you can answer the question. Indicate your choice as 'a', 'b', 'c', or 'd'. If you think more than one option is plausible, choose the more probable option to help you answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: How many major fighting parties were there in the War of the Breton Succession? Passage:Thomas of Woodstock was in command of a large campaign in northern France that followed the War of the Breton Succession of 1343‚Äì64. The earlier conflict was marked by the efforts of John IV, Duke of Brittany to secure control of the Duchy of Brittany against his rival Charles of Blois. John was supported in this struggle by the armies of the kingdom of England, whereas Charles was supported by the kingdom of France. At the head of an English army, John prevailed after Charles was killed in battle in 1364, but the French continued to undermine his position, and he was later forced into exile in England. He returned to Brittany in 1379, supported by Breton barons who feared the annexation of Brittany by France. An English army was sent under Woodstock to support his position. Due to concerns about the safety of a longer shipping route to Brittany itself, the army was ferried instead to the English continental stronghold of Calais in July 1380. As Woodstock marched his 5,200 men east of Paris, they were confronted by the army of Philip the Bold, Duke of Burgundy, at Troyes, but the French had learned from the Battle of Cr√©cy in 1346 and the Battle of Poitiers in 1356 not to offer a pitched battle to the English. Eventually, the two armies simply marched away. French defensive operations were then thrown into disarray by the death of King Charles V of France on 16 September 1380. Woodstock's chevauch√©e continued westwards largely unopposed, and in November 1380 he laid siege to Nantes and its vital bridge over the Loire towards Aquitaine. However, he found himself unable to form an effective stranglehold, and urgent plans were put in place for Sir Thomas Felton to bring 2,000 reinforcements from England. By January, though, it had become apparent that the duke of Brittany was reconciled to the new French king Charles VI, and with the alliance collapsing and dysentery ravaging his men, Woodstock abandoned the siege.\\n Links: a. Calais b. Troyes c. War of the Breton Succession d. Charles, Duke of Brittany","target":"c","rationale":"The question pertains to the number of major fighting parties in the \\"War of Breton Succession\\", which is option 'c'. Therefore, one can conclude that this is the correct answer."},{"source":"I want to inform the hon. member and the House that Canada co-sponsored a resolution at the United Nations Human Rights Commission which condemned the ethnic cleansing, which demanded an immediate cessation of the persecution of Kosovars, and which asked the international community to support the work of the international criminal tribunal.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion?\\nThe United Nations Human Rights Commission has supported the ethnic cleansing.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"The question asks us to draw a conclusion based on the information provided in the passage. In this case, we can see that not only does Canada support human rights but also condemns ethnic cleansing and supports work from international criminal tribunals against perpetrators of such an action as seen by their co-sponsorship of a resolution at the United Nations Human Rights Commission. Thus, it is clear that these actions are antithetical to supporting or being involved with \\"ethnic cleansing\\". So, the answer is No."},{"source":"The input contains a debate topic, an argument on the topic and a keypoint, separated by \\"<sep>\\". Your task is to answer if the keypoint matches the argument and summarizes exactly what the argument means, in the context of the given topic.\\n\\nTopic: We should fight urbanization<sep>Argument: Urbanization packs more people into smaller spaces causing more crime, pollution and diseases.<sep>Keypoint: Urbanization harms the environment","target":"True","rationale":"The argument states that urbanization causes more crime, pollution and diseases. While the precise term \\"environment\\" is not used, it can be inferred that urbanization can be harmful to the environment because it causes an increase in pollution and diseases. Therefore, the keypoint is a valid summary of the argument\\\\u2019s meaning. The answer is True."},{"source":"In this task, you need to remove all words of a given length in the sentence. The number of letters in a word determine its length, for example, the length of the word \\"apple\\" is 5.\\n\\nSentence: 'a small girl is throwing a toy ball on a court'. Remove all words of length '5' in the given sentence.","target":"a girl is throwing a toy ball on a","rationale":"The given sentence is 'a small girl is throwing a toy ball on a court'. The words with length 5 are 'small', and 'court'. Removing these words from the sentence, we get the result: 'a girl is throwing a toy ball on a'."},{"source":"Solve -2*g = -57*g - 82*g + 4247 for g.\\nSolve this problem.","target":"31","rationale":"-2g = -57*g - 82*g + 4247\\n\\nSimplifying the left side of this equation:\\n\\n 0=  -139 * g + 4247\\n\\nSubtracting 4247 from both sides:\\n\\n -4247 =   -139 * g  (1)\\n\\n Dividing by 139 on both sides gives us :\\n\\n (-31)=      g     (2)\`;"},{"source":"In this task you are given a medical question pair hand-generated. Your task is to classify a given post into two categories 1) 'Similar' if the given two questions have a same connotation 2) 'Dissimilar' if the given two questions have a different connotation or meaning.\\n\\nSentence1: I can't see in the dark as well as others can? Do I need carrots or vitamin a? \\n Sentence2: Can deficiency of Vitamin A result in inability to see in dark?","target":"Dissimilar","rationale":"Sentence 1 describes the effects of a Vitamin A deficiency and asks if a person needs carrots or vitamin A. Sentence 2 asks whether a Vitamin A deficiency can cause night blindness. These questions have different meanings, so the answer is Dissimilar."},{"source":"Question: \\"What place might you see a surprise appearance of Serena Williams?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"Major sporting venues in New Delhi include the Jawaharlal Nehru Stadium, Ambedkar Stadium, Indira Gandhi Indoor Stadium, Feroz Shah Kotla Ground, R.K. Khanna Tennis Complex, Dhyan Chand National Stadium and Siri Fort Sports Complex.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"R.K. Khanna Tennis Complex","rationale":"The question is asking where Serena Williams might make a surprise appearance. The context mentions several major sports venues in India, including the R.K. Khanna Tennis Complex and Dhyan Chand National Stadium for hockey. As an American tennis player, it would be more likely to see Serena at a tennis venue than one dedicated to another sport like hockey or football (soccer).\\nSo the answer is: R.K Khanna Tennis Complex"},{"source":"Mr Fitzgibbon expects some of the 17,000 additional US troops heading for Afghanistan will bolster Australian forces operating in the dangerous Oruzgan province in the south. The defence minister was planning to raise the issue specifically with US Defence Secretary Robert Gates. He has already held talks with US central command chief General David Petraeus and director of the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA) Leon Panetta. General Petraeus discussed the new US strategy for Afghanistan and the troop surge in which an extra 17,000 troops will be deployed in the southern provinces where Taliban insurgents have been most active.\\nDoes this next sentence follow, given the preceding text?\\nDavid Petraeus is the director of the CIA.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"This sentence is not correct as it states that David Petraeus, the US central command chief and director of the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA), discussed a new strategy for Afghanistan. However, according to this context, General Petraeus did not discuss such matters with Mr Fitzgibbon; instead he discussed them with Leon Panetta who is indeed the CIA Director.\\n'''"},{"source":"Write the conversation response. DIALOG:\\nWhat was the role of La Malinche in the conquest of Mexico?\\n- La Malinche played a key role in the Spanish conquest of the Aztec Empire, acting as an interpreter, advisor, and intermediary for the Spanish conquistador, Hern√°n Cort√©s.\\n- How did the other Tlaxcalan view her?\\n- Some Tlaxcalan viewed her as a traitor, and some respected and trusted her.\\n- Was La Malinche Tlaxacan?\\n- La Malinche was a Nahua woman from the Mexican Gulf Coast.\\n- How did La Malinche help the conquistadors?\\n-","target":"La Malinche played a key role in the Spanish conquest of the Aztec Empire, acting as an interpreter, advisor, and intermediary for the Spanish conquistador, Hern√°n Cort√©s.","rationale":"The answer is \\"La Malinche played a key role in the Spanish conquest of the Aztec Empire, acting as an interpreter, advisor, and intermediary for the Spanish conquistador, Hern√°n Cort√©s.\\" because it answers how La Malinche helped the conquistadors."},{"source":"Read the dialog and predict the next turn. Hello assistant, what good restaurants are near me?\\nI have located restaurants with Chinese, pizza, or casual food....which sounds best?\\nChinese sounds good\\nHow about PF Changs, located in Newport News?\\nYes, that is good, can you make a reservation today there for 4 there at 6:00? See if inside seating is available.\\nPF Changs does not have any available reservations inside at 6:00, would you like me to check outside or a different time?\\nCheck for outside seating\\nPF Changs doesn't have any available outside reservations at 6:00, would you like to try a different restaurant or time?\\nTry a different restaurant\\nHow about No 1. Chinese in Newport News\\nYes\\nWhat time would you like your reservation?\\nToday at 6:00\\nDid you want me to check for inside seating availability?\\nYes\\nNo 1. Chinese doesn't have an available reservation at 6:00 inside, would you like to try a different time or option?\\nSee if they have a reservation at 6:30 inside.\\nNo. 1 Chinese has an available reservation at 6:30 for inside, would you like me to reserve?\\nYes","target":"I have successfully booked a reservation at 6:30 inside at No. 1 Chinese in Newport News Va","rationale":"The answer is \\"I have successfully booked a reservation at 6:30 inside at No. 1 Chinese in Newport News Va\\" because the user wants to make a reservation for 6:30 and so, the assistant needs to confirm that it has made a successful reservation."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to identify which one of following five services the sentence is related to - Media, Travel, Flights, Buses, RideSharing\\n\\nWill you find movies online?","target":"Media","rationale":"The user is asking the virtual assistant if it can search and show movies online. The service being used is \\"Media\\""},{"source":"Short general knowledge question: what sort of government does canada have?","target":"Parliament of Canada","rationale":"Canada has a parliamentary system, which means that it is governed by the Parliament of Canada."},{"source":"The influence of Nasser's Arab nationalism over the RCC was immediately apparent. The administration was instantly recognized by the neighbouring Arab nationalist regimes in Egypt, Syria, Iraq and Sudan, with Egypt sending experts to aid the inexperienced RCC. Gaddafi propounded Pan-Arab ideas, proclaiming the need for a single Arab state stretching across North Africa and the Middle East. In December 1969, Libya founded the Arab Revolutionary Front with Egypt and Sudan as a step towards political unification, and in 1970 Syria stated its intention to join.\\nWhat Arab nationalist thinker was influential with the RCC?","target":"Nasser","rationale":"From the given context, it is clear that Nasser's Arab nationalism had an immediate impact on the new RCC. Gaddafi was influenced by Pan-Arab ideas and proclaimed a need for a single Arab state stretching across North Africa and the Middle East. The influence of Nasser's ideology over Libya can be seen in its formation of the Revolutionary Front with Egypt and Sudan (1969), as well as Syria stating its intention to join (1970).\\nTherefore, we can conclude that \\"Nasser\\" was influential with the RCC.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given an abstract of article. Your task is to generate label \\"True\\" if abstract is structured, otherwise generate \\"False\\". A structured abstract is composed of a topic sentence (or key sentence), relevant supporting sentences, and a closing (or transition) sentence. This structure is key to keeping your abstract focused on the main idea and creating a clear and concise image.\\n\\nTen-Eleven Translocation-2 (TET2) inactivation through loss-of-function mutation, deletion and IDH1/2 (Isocitrate Dehydrogenase 1 and 2) gene mutation is a common event in myeloid and lymphoid malignancies. TET2 gene mutations similar to those observed in myeloid and lymphoid malignancies also accumulate with age in otherwise healthy subjects with clonal hematopoiesis. TET2 is one of the three proteins of the TET (Ten-Eleven Translocation) family, which are evolutionarily conserved dioxygenases that catalyze the conversion of 5-methyl-cytosine (5-mC) to 5-hydroxymethyl-cytosine (5-hmC) and promote DNA demethylation. TET dioxygenases require 2-oxoglutarate, oxygen and Fe(II) for their activity, which is enhanced in the presence of ascorbic acid. TET2 is the most expressed TET gene in the hematopoietic tissue, especially in hematopoietic stem cells. In addition to their hydroxylase activity, TET proteins recruit the O-linked Œ≤-D-N-acetylglucosamine (O-GlcNAc) transferase (OGT) enzyme to chromatin, which promotes post-transcriptional modifications of histones and facilitates gene expression. The TET2 level is regulated by interaction with IDAX, originating from TET2 gene fission during evolution, and by the microRNA miR-22. TET2 has pleiotropic roles during hematopoiesis, including stem-cell self-renewal, lineage commitment and terminal differentiation of monocytes. Analysis of Tet2 knockout mice, which are viable and fertile, demonstrated that Tet2 functions as a tumor suppressor whose haploinsufficiency initiates myeloid and lymphoid transformations. This review summarizes the recently identified TET2 physiological and pathological functions and discusses how this knowledge influences our therapeutic approaches in hematological malignancies and possibly other tumor types.","target":"False","rationale":"The abstract provides an overview of Ten-Eleven Translocation-2 (TET2), a tumor suppressor protein whose loss can initiate myeloid and lymphoid transformations. It describes the structure of the TET2 gene, its expression levels in hematopoietic stem cells, its role in disease development and progression, as well as how this information can improve our current therapeutic approaches for hematological malignancies. However, it does not include a topic sentence that clearly states the main idea or objective of the research. Also, it does not contain a closing sentence that sums up the main findings and conclusions. So it is not structured according to formal rules for writing abstracts. As a result, the answer should be \\"False\\"."},{"source":"In mathematics, the absolute value of a number is the non-negative value of that number, without regarding its sign. For example, the absolute value of -2 is 2, and the absolute value of 5 is 5. In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element. The absolute value for negative numbers can be found by multiplying them by -1. After finding the element with the maximum absolute value you should return the value of that element before you applied the absolute value.\\n\\n[-41.38  -72.343]","target":"-72.343","rationale":"The element with the highest absolute value in the given list is -72.343, which has an absolute value of 72.343. The absolute value of all other numbers in the list is less than or equal to 72.343, so we return -72.343 as our answer"},{"source":"Given a question and a context passage, generate the answer having the word or phrase from the context passage. Here, the answer should be a shortest continous span from the passage.\\n\\nContext: On 1 January 2016, Moustoir-Remungol, Naizin and Remungol merged becoming one commune called Evellys. \\n Question: By what was Moustoir-Remungol replaced?","target":"√©vellys","rationale":"The shortest continous span that provides the answer to the given question is \\"√©vellys\\""},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"After World War II Hudson's realized that the limited parking space at its downtown skyscraper would increasingly be a problem for its customers. The solution in 1954 was to open the Northland Center in nearby Southfield, just beyond the city limits. It was the largest suburban shopping center in the world, and quickly became the main shopping destination for northern and western Detroit, and for much of the suburbs. By 1961 the downtown skyscraper accounted for only half of Hudson's sales; it closed in 1986. The Northland Center Hudson's, rebranded Macy's in 2006 following acquisition by Federated Department Stores, was closed along with the remaining stores in the center in March 2015 due to the mall's high storefront vacancy, decaying infrastructure, and financial mismanagement.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: The Northland Center is not actually in?","target":"the city","rationale":"The passage mentions that the Northland Center Hudson's, which was opened in 1954 as a solution to the limited parking space at its downtown skyscraper, is located just beyond Detroit city limits. This implies that it is not actually within the city of Detroit."},{"source":"I can use this background: Hypertension , which is also called \\"high blood pressure,\\" occurs when a person‚Äôs blood pressure is always high. Hypertension is said to be present when a person's systolic blood pressure is always 140 or higher, and/or if the person's diastolic blood pressure is always 90 or higher. Having hypertension increases a person‚Äôs chance for developing heart disease, having a stroke, or suffering from other serious cardiovascular diseases. Hypertension often does not have any symptoms, so a person may not know that he or she has high blood pressure. For this reason, hypertension is often called the \\"silent killer.\\" Treatments for hypertension include diet changes, exercise, and medication. Foods thought to lower blood pressure include skim milk, spinach, beans, bananas and dark chocolate.\\n\\nNow, I have a new situation: Jeremy went to the doctor for his yearly physical along with his wife Brenda. The doctor told Jeremy that his blood pressure was consistently high. Brenda, on the other hand, was told that her blood pressure was in the normal range. Aside from this difference, the overall health of Jeremy and Brenda was similar.\\n\\nAnswer this question please: Who has a higher risk of having a stroke?","target":"Jeremy","rationale":"According to the background information, hypertension is a condition that leads to consistently high blood pressure. Hypertension can lead to other cardiovascular diseases such as heart disease and stroke. Since Jeremy has been diagnosed with hypertension while Brenda‚Äôs blood pressure is in the normal range, it follows that he would be at higher risk of having a stroke than she would."},{"source":"Read the following context and answer the question.\\nContext: Ok, this one is not missing a class but much better story IMO. When I was in middle school, if you didn‚Äôt have homework completed or goofed off in some way, teachers could make you stay after school for ‚Äòafter school help.‚Äô It was essentially a mandatory study hall and if a teacher called you out, you had no choice in the matter.\\nNow, I was in Biology class towards end of my middle school career and was sitting at one of those lab tables next to another student. We both had newspaper routes (yes, people actually delivered actual newspapers to people‚Äôs homes in the 1980s), so it would make us late for our deliveries if we were made to stay after school. This biology teacher would check our vocabulary assignment every week and I totally spaced it this week - Oh Crap! Now, my lab mate had most of his done, but just didn‚Äôt quite finish. Our teacher is working his way around the classroom checking assignments. So, he checks my lab partner, ‚Äúwell Scott, looks like you will be staying after school today.‚Äù This fellow student knew I didn‚Äôt have mine either, but also knew I was a pretty good student. I feel like I am sweating bullets and trembling as the teacher approaches me. In a near panic, I reach into my folder and pull out a prior week‚Äôs assignment. He looks it over and says ‚ÄúOK, good job‚Äù or something like that. Scott is looking at me in utter disbelief. Even funnier was the fact that this week‚Äôs assignment required 6‚Äì7 pages of paper to complete. The one I had blindly grabbed from folder had 2 pages, with barely anything in second page. It was totally obvious what I had done, but our teacher gave me a break that day. I managed to make it thru all three years without needing any ‚Äòafter school help!‚Äô\\nThis was a large public school and they still paddled students if the infraction was serious enough. I know none of that is allowed these days, but those were both good deterrents for me!!\\nQuestion: When did the instructor check assignments?\\nAnswer:","target":"every week","rationale":"The context describes a class in biology where the teacher checked assignments every week. So, the answer is \\"every week\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you will be presented with a context from an academic paper and you have to write an answerable question based on the context. Your questions can be extractive, abstractive, or yes-no questions.\\n\\nAfter Korektor, there are 4262 unique sentences (including 150 seed sentences) that form the COSTRA 1.0 dataset.","target":"How many sentence transformations on average are available per unique sentence in dataset?","rationale":"The given context talks about the statistics of Korektor dataset. Hence, asking about a statistical question like \\"How many sentence transformations on average are available per unique sentence in dataset?\\" is valid and answerable from the context."},{"source":"Given a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation, identify who is wrong here. Classify each post into the following categories : AUTHOR (if the author of the post is wrong in the situation), OTHER (if any of the others mentioned in the paragraph is wrong), EVERYBODY (if everyone mentioned is wrong) and NOBODY (if no one is wrong in the situation).\\n\\nSo I recently studied abroad in Europe, and even though I learned a lot of good things, one not so good thing I picked up is smoking the occasional cigarette. And by occasional, I mean no more than once a month, usually only when I‚Äôve been drinking and that doesn‚Äôt happen often. \\n\\nMy girlfriend, for obvious reasons, is not a fan of this habit. She‚Äôs worried about the health implications, which I understand, and she also doesn‚Äôt like the smell it leaves behind. I always explain to her that one reason I like them is because I‚Äôm pretty introverted so when we‚Äôre at bars or parties, it gives me a nice excuse to step outside and have a moment by getting away from music and people. As for the health stuff, I don‚Äôt really feel like it‚Äôs making a big impact as little as I smoke them, and I point out to her that if I got drunk every weekend that would probably kill me faster but she wouldn‚Äôt have a problem with it. \\n\\nShe‚Äôs still not okay with it and has caused a couple disagreements. I‚Äôve already promised her that if it got to the point I was craving one when I wasn‚Äôt drinking or started smoking more often than I am now, I would give them up but until then I don‚Äôt see the problem. Am I the asshole for not listening to her and quitting?","target":"NOBODY","rationale":"The author occasionally smokes cigarettes when they go out drinking with friends. The author's girlfriend is not happy about their smoking habit and has asked them to quit, but the author doesn't want to quit because they only smoke occasionally and don't think it's a big deal. This situation is a matter of personal preference, where the author believes that occasional smoking won't negatively impact their health or lifestyle but his girlfriend disagrees. Since neither party is acting unethically or doing something wrong, the correct answer is \\"\\"NOBODY.\\"\\""},{"source":"Here is a premise:\\nNot only has each dollar of saving bought more investment goods in recent years, but a greater share of that dollar was invested in information technology, including computers, software, and communications equipment.\\n\\nHere is a hypothesis:\\nA larger amount of money was invested in information technology.\\n\\nHere are the options: OPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no\\nIs it possible to conclude that if the premise is true, then so is the hypothesis?","target":"yes","rationale":"The premise states that each dollar of saving bought more investment goods in the recent years. Additionally, it also says that a greater share of that dollar was invested in information technology: computers, software and communications equipment. Therefore, if this is true, then there are reasons to believe that a larger amount of money was indeed invested in IT over other fields as well (which could be non-IT). Hence, we can conclude from the premises given above is enough for us to say yes - since there are reasons to support hypothesis being true."},{"source":"White Lies are an English post-punk band from Ealing, London. Formerly known as Fear of Flying, the core band members are Harry McVeigh (lead vocals, guitar), Charles Cave (bass guitar and backing vocals), and Jack Lawrence-Brown (drums). The band perform live as a five-piece, when sidemen Tommy Bowen and Rob Lee join the line up. White Lies' musical style has been described as dark yet uplifting by the media, drawing comparisons to Editors, Interpol, Joy Division, and The Killers.\\n\\nIn an interview with NME in January 2013, bassist Charles Cave revealed that the band's third album is intended to be released in late summer, with one of the tracks promoting the record being called \\"Getting Even\\". On 4 June 2013 it was revealed that the album, which was produced by Ed Buller and recorded earlier this year, will be titled Big TV. Also, the track list for the album was published and \\"Getting Even\\" was released as a free download. The first official single from the album, \\"There Goes Our Love Again\\", was released on 5 August 2013, with the album being released in the UK and Europe a week later, on 12 August 2013 through Fiction Records. It was released on 20 August 2013 in the US (through Harvest Records), and in Canada (Universal Music).  On 23/24/25 July 2013, White Lies played 3 intimate shows at Hoxton Square Bar & Kitchen in London, celebrating the 5 year anniversary of the band's first ever gig at the same venue. They played tracks from Big TV and some of their earlier songs in front of 300 fans each night. During their Summer/Fall 2013 tour, the band is scheduled to play more than thirty concerts in Europe and North America. In August 2013 they made their Main Stage debut at Reading and Leeds Festivals.  On 6 November 2013, the band released a limited edition EP to celebrate their tour, called Small TV. The five-track EP released on Fiction Records was limited to 1000 copies and features covers from Lana Del Rey and Prince in addition to new versions of their own tracks. Answer this question using a quote from the following article:\\n\\nWhat date did the the name get revealed","target":"June 2013 it was revealed that the album, which was produced by Ed Buller and recorded earlier this year, will be titled Big TV.","rationale":"On 4 June 2013 it was revealed that the album, which was produced by Ed Buller and recorded earlier this year, will be titled Big TV.\\nThe question asks for a date when the name of an album got revealed. \\nIn order to answer this question we need to look at what dates are mentioned in the article and their significance. In particular, one needs to find out on what date is information about an album's name being released or made public known as \\"revealed\\" in journalistic lingo."},{"source":"Here's a logic test: Carla is driving a test car over different surfaces. She drives the car over a pile of pillows and the car drives over them easily. Carla drives the car over a pile of rocks, and the car goes a little slower. The car went easier over the pile of pillows because there was (A) more friction (B) less friction.\\n\\nChoose the answer between \\"pile of rocks\\" and \\"pile of pillows\\".","target":"pile of pillows","rationale":"Friction is a force between two objects that are rubbing against each other. When the car drove over the pile of pillows, there was less friction because it glided easily over this soft surface. When the car drove over rocks, more friction occurred because these surfaces were harder and moved slower than when they went past pillows. The answer is pile\\nof pillows.\\""},{"source":"how do you write a list?","target":"write things down a line.","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"write things down a line."},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- John went back to the hallway. Fact 2- Daniel moved to the garden. Fact 3- Sandra travelled to the bathroom. Fact 4- Mary went back to the office. Fact 5- Sandra travelled to the hallway. Fact 6- Sandra went back to the bedroom. Fact 7- Daniel moved to the bedroom. Fact 8- Daniel travelled to the hallway. Fact 9- Daniel travelled to the garden. Fact 10- Daniel moved to the hallway. Question: Where is Daniel? Answer: hallway","target":"Fact 10","rationale":"The question asks where Daniel is and the answer states he is in the hallway. If we look at the facts, Fact 10 states that Daniel moved to the hallway."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: threat and non-threat. Threat is a statement that someone will be hurt or harmed, especially if the person does not do something in particular.\\n\\nComment: Yes, it is easy to demonize state employees since we are under a union (whether we want to be or not). The bottom line is we are still Alaskans (I was born in Alaska and have lived here all my life), we contribute to the economy, we run this huge state and we make less than public sector employees at comparable jobs. There are many state employees who are below the poverty line! Most people don't have a clue about that. We are an easy scapegoat. I am sick of it.","target":"Non-threat","rationale":"The comment does not contain any statements that threaten to hurt or harm anyone. So it could be classified into \\"Non-threat\\"."},{"source":"Question: A truck moving over pavement creates less heat energy then when moving over mud. This means that the _____ is rougher (A) mud (B) pavement\\n\\nDo not use A and B to answer the question but instead, choose between \\"pavement\\" and  \\"mud\\".","target":"pavement","rationale":"The question can be rephrased as \\"Which material causes the truck to create more heat energy?\\"\\nA truck moving over pavement creates less heat energy than when it is moving over mud. This means that the roughness of paving stone is lower than that of mud, so it will cause a smaller amount of friction and hence generate less thermal energy. So answer should be pavement"},{"source":"Pick the option in line with common sense to answer the question.\\nQuestions: If you exercise intensely what can happen to your respiration?\\nOptions:\\n- tiredness\\n- shortness of breath\\n- injury\\n- fitness\\n- thirst","target":"shortness of breath","rationale":"When you exercise intensely, your heart rate and breathing rate increase. This is because of the need to bring more oxygen into the cells in order for them to efficiently perform cellular respiration which generates ATP used by muscles during contraction (and other metabolic processes). Cells also produce waste products such as hydrogen ions that must leave the cell via blood flow through veins back to lungs where they are eliminated from body when we exhale.\\nTherefore, since a person's respiratory system can't respond immediately with an increased supply of air, people may experience shortness of breath after exercising heavily"},{"source":"In this task, you are given two strings A, B. Find the longest common substring in the strings A and B.\\n\\nkpHgIfovlTTIaRVwMiMXi, UJvlTTIaRVYT","target":"vlTTIaRV","rationale":"The longest common substring in the strings \\"kpHgIfovlTTIaRVwMiMXi\\" and \\"UJvlTTIaRVYT\\" is 'vlTTIaRV'."},{"source":"Given a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation, judge whether or not a specific person is wrong here. Answer 'not answerable' if more information is required and 'answerable' if all the information is sufficient to answer who is wrong in this situation.\\n\\nI‚Äôll try to keep it short. My wife is pregnant with our second child. She is preeclamptic and considered high risk. Last week my wife was having pain, went to the dr, who told her to go straight to the hospital. At the hospital they told her she will stay until they decide she is stable enough to return home, there is a possibility she may have to remain there until baby is born, which could be a few weeks to over a month depending on how early baby gets here. My wife‚Äôs sister (who I don‚Äôt really get along with) took it upon herself to create a go fund me saying we are having financial problems and ‚Äúcan‚Äôt afford things‚Äù as she put it. Then proceeds to post it on Facebook. This is complete bullshit as I work full time and have enough in savings to be ok while my wife is on bed rest at the hospital. Money is tight, sure, we have a been preparing for a baby. However I‚Äôm not broke by any means and I sure as hell don‚Äôt need to lean on strangers donations to ‚Äúmake it‚Äù. I was offended that she made a go fund me without consulting us first. I told my wife she needs to delete it, to which she replied back ‚Äúpeople are nice and want to help.‚Äù I wont accept this money and don‚Äôt feel right about the whole thing. AITA for getting worked up about taking money from people when my situation isn‚Äôt as bad as she made it out to be?","target":"answerable","rationale":"The wife's sister has publicly claimed that the family is having financial difficulties, which is not true. The sister's decision to create a GoFundMe page for the family was inappropriate and manipulative. In doing this, she made it seem like the family needed help from strangers when they do not. She also did this without consulting her sister or brother-in-law first. This is unfair to both of them as well as to potential donors who may be misled into thinking their donation will be used for an actual cause that meets their own standards for warranting a donation. Therefore, the answer to this question is 'answerable'."},{"source":"Given a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation, generate a suitable title that describes the main event/root cause of the situation. Imagine that the given text is a social media post, and you have to write the title of the post, so the users can decide to read the main text or not.\\n\\n\\n\\nMy gf is 29 I‚Äôm 25. Yesterday we were all out for SPD we had brunch and were all having a good time. One girl in the group ran into this guy she knew. I‚Äôm not sure of their relationship but he said he had coke. \\n\\nA few people from the group go over to him in broad daylight on a busy street in front of a bar and start doing free bumps from him. I look over to my GF who does coke sometimes and say ‚Äúyou don‚Äôt know what the fuck that is if your gonna do it, do it from someone you know and trust‚Äù but she ignores what I say and she does it anyway. \\n\\nI don‚Äôt touch the shit and if she does do it on occasion I don‚Äôt care as long as it‚Äôs from a trusted source. I just want her to be safe. Her explanation was ‚ÄúKate obviously knows him and everyone else was doing it so if it were bad shit I would be able to tell from their reactions to it‚Äù\\n\\nThat kind of ruined the day for me unfortunately seeing my GF do coke from a stranger. So AITA for getting upset at her?","target":"getting upset at my gf for doing Cocaine from a stranger","rationale":"The title for this post should be \\"getting upset at my gf for doing Cocaine from a stranger\\". This describes the main event in the situation and is concise."},{"source":"Read the following context and answer the question.\\nContext: My Wife and I went to go see Elizabethtown - last night ( 10/27/2005 ) and were horribly disapointed . We actually went in expecting to see an ok movie . We were NOT expecting anything great - but we figured some cute scenes and a few funny lines from Paula Dean ( normally a host on the Food Network ) . It is hard to understate exactly how wrong we were -- I actually considered taking a restroom break - to go play a videogame or two and then come back .\\nQuestion: What will we do next time ?\\nAnswer:","target":"Read reviews of the funny movies","rationale":"The context states that the speakers went to see a movie and were disappointed, as they expected it to be funny. The question asks what will happen next time in order for the speakers not to miss out on another opportunity to see an entertaining film. Given this information, the best course of action would be reading reviews of movies before going to them so that one can avoid spending their money on films like Elizabethtown (2005) again.\\n\\nSo Read reviews of the funny movies is correct answer"},{"source":"What is this about? \\nLand Forces during this period also deployed in support of peacekeeping operations within United Nations sanctioned conflicts. The nature of the Canadian Forces has continued to evolve. They have been deployed in Afghanistan until 2011, under the NATO-led United Nations International Security Assistance Force (ISAF), at the request of the Government of Afghanistan.","target":"Canadian Armed Forces","rationale":"The above passage is about the Canadian Armed Forces.\\nIn particular, it describes their involvement in Afghanistan during Operation Enduring Freedom and later under NATO-led operations of ISAF. It also mentions that they were deployed to support peacekeeping operations sanctioned by United Nations as well as how their role has evolved since World War II."},{"source":"Given a statement, generate a question such that the answer is contained in that statement.\\n\\nSome species of amphibians are fed once a week.","target":"How often are some amphibians fed?","rationale":"The question should induce once a week as an example of how often some amphibians are fed. That would be \\"How often are some amphibians fed?\\"."},{"source":"Classify the input text into either disfluent questions or proper questions. A disfluent question is a question that has some interruptions in it while framing. A proper question is the correct form of the question without any disfluency.\\n\\nWhen did the Rhine Straightening program begin?","target":"proper","rationale":"The given text is a properly framed question. There are no disfluencies found in the input question."},{"source":"DIALOG:\\nWhat is Tarawa?\\n- Tarawa is an atoll and the capital of the Republic of Kiribati, in the central Pacific Ocean.\\n- What was significant about the Battle of Tarawa?\\n- David M. Shoup was transferred to the staff of Major General Julian C. Smith, and tasked to help plan the invasion of Betio on Tarawa Atoll.\\n- Did David M. Shoup receive any awards or medals?\\n- For his leadership during the assault and the push inland, David M. Shoup was awarded the Medal of Honor and the British Distinguished Service Order.\\n- Did David M. Shoup receive any other awards?\\n- David M. Shoup also was awarded the Purple Heart for the combat wounds he suffered during the course of the campaign.\\n- Were there any significant losses or injuries from the Battle of Tarawa?\\n-","target":"David M. Shoup's force met heavy resistance on the beaches. His LVT was disabled by shore fire, and he had to proceed without transportation.","rationale":"The answer to the question, \\"Were there any significant losses or injuries from the Battle of Tarawa\\" is \\"David M. Shoup's force met heavy resistance on the beaches. His LVT was disabled by shore fire, and he had to proceed without transportation.\\" This information is found in the dialog as follows:\\n1. The first sentence states that David M. Shoup received a Medal of Honor and a Distinguished Service Order for his role in leading troops into battle and pushing inland during the Battle of Tarawa.\\n2. The second sentence states that David M. Shoup received two awards (one American and one British) for his actions at Betio on Tarawa Atoll, which was an island in Kiribati, so this confirms that he fought against Japanese forces at Betio during World War II as stated above in 1., thus confirming that Betio was part of the Battle of Tarawa as stated above in 2..\\n3. The third sentence states that David M. Shoup also received a Purple Heart for combat wounds sustained during some campaign or another (that we don't know anything about yet), but since it's mentioned alongside other awards related to fighting against Japanese troops at Betio on Tarawa Atoll during World War II, we can infer based on context clues alone (without looking up any additional information) that he must have been wounded while fighting against Japanese troops at Betio on Tarawa Atoll during World War II even though it never explicitly says this specifically anywhere within dialog; however all 4 pieces of evidence point towards him being wounded while fighting against Japanese forces at Betio on Tarawa Atoll during World War II so we can infer with relative certainty without needing additional research/information/evidence/clues/etc..."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a string of characters. You should remove all vowels from the given string. Vowels are: i,e,a,u,o. The character 'y' or 'Y' does not count as a vowel.\\n\\nLEiblEiUqEXeAix","target":"LblqXx","rationale":"The given string contains the vowels 'E', 'i', 'i', 'U', 'E', and an additional lowercase/uppercase vowel, which should be removed according to the instructions. The resulting string after removing the vowels is 'LblqXx'."},{"source":"In mathematics, the absolute value of a number is the non-negative value of that number, without regarding its sign. For example, the absolute value of -2 is 2, and the absolute value of 5 is 5. In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element. The absolute value for negative numbers can be found by multiplying them by -1. After finding the element with the maximum absolute value you should return the value of that element before you applied the absolute value.\\n\\n[-89.818  -6.76  -56.753 -65.207 -17.542]","target":"-89.818","rationale":"The element with the highest absolute value in the given list is -89.818, which has an absolute value of 89.818. The absolute value of all other numbers in the list is less than or equal to 89.818. However, we need to return the value of the element before applying the absolute value, so the answer is -89.818"},{"source":"Question: Jimbo isn't as strong as Harry. If both men throw a ball, which will make it go the greater distance? (A) Jimbo (B) Harry\\n\\nDo not use A and B to answer the question but instead, choose between \\"Jimbo\\" and  \\"Harry\\".","target":"Harry","rationale":"The key to answering this question is understanding the meaning of \\"greater distance\\". This means that we need to know which person can throw a ball farther, not harder or faster. In order for Jimbo and Harry to achieve equal distances when throwing balls, they must have similar speeds but different strengths. If their relative speeds are equivalent (this doesn't necessarily mean that each man throws at exactly the same speed), then the stronger one will throw farther; therefore, since Jimbo isn‚Äôt as strong as Harry, it follows that if both men throw a ball simultaneously with equal force applied on them in opposite directions by identical springs connected in series between two fixed points outside either spring's natural length so as not be affected by gravity acting horizontally across horizontal surfaces such"},{"source":"Please answer a question about the following article about Korean War:\\n\\nBy mid-1950, North Korean forces numbered between 150,000 and 200,000 troops, organized into 10 infantry divisions, one tank division, and one air force division, with 210 fighter planes and 280 tanks, who captured scheduled objectives and territory, among them Kaesong, Chuncheon, Uijeongbu, and Ongjin. Their forces included 274 T-34-85 tanks, 200 artillery pieces, 110 attack bombers, some 150 Yak fighter planes, 78 Yak trainers, and 35 reconnaissance aircraft. In addition to the invasion force, the North KPA had 114 fighters, 78 bombers, 105 T-34-85 tanks, and some 30,000 soldiers stationed in reserve in North Korea. Although each navy consisted of only several small warships, the North and South Korean navies fought in the war as sea-borne artillery for their in-country armies.\\n\\nWhat was the maximum number of North Korean troops engaged in the war?","target":"200,000","rationale":"This is a simple question about the number of North Korean troops involved in the war. The paragraph states that by mid-1950, \\"the North Korean forces numbered between 150,000 and 200,000 troops\\", so we can infer from this sentence that the maximum number of troops was 200,000"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a context sentence containing a blank (_). You are expected to fill the blank with one word to make the sentence convey a cultural stereotype. A stereotype is an over-generalized belief about a particular group of people. Your answer must not contain more than one word.\\n\\nContext: She is _ with herself.","target":"alone","rationale":"The stereotype is that women are more likely to be alone than men."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence with a missing word that can be an object, a person, and/or an action. Fill in the blank with a plausible word. Although each sentence has many correct answers, you only have to write one answer.\\n\\nPersonX goes ___ from school","target":"home","rationale":"PersonX most likely goes home after school. This can be inferred from the context that the person is a student and would return to their place of residence after school."},{"source":"What's the answer to that question: what does michael jackson like to eat?","target":"Vegetarian food","rationale":"Michael Jackson was a vegetarian. Therefore, the answer is \\"Vegetarian food\\"."},{"source":"Given a statement, generate a question such that the answer is contained in that statement.\\n\\nColor and going underground helps conceal from scavengers.","target":"What does going underground help conceal from scavengers?","rationale":"The word \\"underground\\" is a noun and can be replaced by the pronoun \\"it\\" in the sentence. The question generated should induce that underground helps conceal from scavengers. That would be \\"What does going underground help conceal from scavengers?\\"."},{"source":"Question: when was the social model of disability developed??\\nAnswer:","target":"the 1980s","rationale":"It is impossible to give a more precise answer, as the development of this model was gradual and not associated with any particular event. \\nHowever, it's reasonable to say that it developed in the 1980s, because one of its key proponents - Tom Shakespeare - describes his own experience which included him being diagnosed with Duchenne muscular dystrophy in 1985 (see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Shakespeare)"},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer basic science questions. For each question, several terms are intentionally masked with ***. This masking can cover very few or many of the question words. Clearly, if masked terms are important, the modified question will be impossible to answer. Please indicate the correct answer with one of the following responses: \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\" or \\"E\\". While \\"A\\"-\\"D\\" correspond to the answer options provided in the input, \\"E\\" represents \\"I don't know\\" for questions that do not provide enough information. Respond via \\"E\\" if the question is not answerable. Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B, 'C', 'D', 'E'.\\n\\nQuestion: *** *** *** substances conducts electricity *** ***?  (A) Wood (B) Brick (C) Copper (D) Plasti.","target":"C","rationale":"The answer is C, which means that copper is the only substance among wooden, brick or plastic materials that conducts electricity."},{"source":"Given a piece of financial news and its polarity, classify it into 'true' if the polarity is correct and classify into 'false' if the polarity is incorrect. Output must be 'true' or 'false'. \\n\\nnews:Profit of the accounting period was EUR 0.3 mn .\\npolarity:neutral","target":"true","rationale":"The financial news states that the profit of the accounting period was 0.3 million euros, which is generally considered to be a neutral development. Therefore, the polarity of the financial news is correct and should be denoted as \\"true\\"."},{"source":"Can you tell me the answer to where did the story of peter pan come from??","target":"J. M. Barrie","rationale":"The answer is J. M. Barrie, who wrote the story of Peter Pan in a book published by Hodder and Stoughton on October 1st 1911."},{"source":"I gave my students this multiple choice question: Cancer is best described as\\n\\nOnly one answer is correct among these 4 choices:\\n- a type of genetic engineering\\n- the merging of sex cells\\n- abnormal cell division\\n- tissue that stops growing\\n\\nCould you tell me which one is correct?","target":"abnormal cell division","rationale":"The answer is \\"Abnormal cell division\\". \\nCancer refers to a disease caused by abnormal growth of cells. It can happen in almost any part of the body and often spreads (metastasizes) from one area to another. The main contributor for cancer is due to uncontrolled cell proliferation, which allows this mutation or defect to be passed on through cell divisions. This leads us back to the answer choice \\"abnormal cell division\\", as it best describes what Cancer actually means."},{"source":"Pick the option in line with common sense to answer the question.\\nQuestions: If you exercise intensely what can happen to your respiration?\\nOptions:\\n- tiredness\\n- shortness of breath\\n- injury\\n- fitness\\n- thirst","target":"shortness of breath","rationale":"When you exercise intensely, your body is working harder than usual and needs more oxygen. This causes the heart to beat faster in order to pump blood with extra oxygen throughout the body at a higher rate of speed. However, if there isn‚Äôt enough time for this process between exercises then it can lead to shortness of breath.\\nSo, the answer is shortness of breath"},{"source":"You are given a math word problem and you are supposed to apply an addition mathematical operator on the numbers embedded in the text to answer the following question and then only report the final numerical answer.\\n\\nContext: 13 campers went rowing and 59 campers went hiking in the morning. 21 campers went rowing in the afternoon. \\n\\n Question: How many campers went rowing in all?","target":"34","rationale":"13 campers went rowing and 59 campers went hiking in the morning. 21 campers went rowing in the afternoon. Therefore, a total of 13 + 21 = 34 people went rowing."},{"source":"Can you tell me the answer to who sang when you're in love with a beautiful woman??","target":"Dr. Hook","rationale":"According to the official website of Dr. Hook, they are known for their song ‚ÄúWhen You‚Äôre in Love with a Beautiful Woman.‚Äù\\nTherefore, Dr. Hook is the answer to \\"who sang when you're in love with a beautiful woman\\"."},{"source":"I was 14 at the time.\\nMy family and I took a family vacation to Tybee Island, Georgia.\\nIt is a beautiful place that I would highly recommend.\\nI told my family that I was going to go find a port-a-pot.\\nSo I head off by myself.\\nI‚Äôm in the port-a-pot, i‚Äôm in there for roughly 10 minutes. (you can assume what I was doing)\\nI wash my hands and get ready to leave the port-a-pot, and I tried to open the door and it was locked.\\nI‚Äôm claustrophobic, so I start to FREAK OUT.\\nI started banging on the door, running into the door with all of my weight.\\nNothing was helping.\\nI then start crying, I thought for sure that I was going to die.\\nI knew it was the end, at the age of 14, locked in a port-a-pot, in 95 degree weather in the middle of a beach in Georgia.\\nLooking back, i‚Äôm curious as to why my family never came to look for me, I was gone for like 30 minutes.\\nSo I‚Äôm banging on the door continuously, bawling my eyes out.\\nThen a man opened the door for me, from the outside.\\nHe was about 6‚Äô3 with dreads about 12 inches long and weighed about 280 pounds.\\nI ran out of the port-a-pot and jumped on the guy and gave him a hug and told him that I loved him and that he saved my life.\\nI don‚Äôt know how he managed to open the door for me, but I definitely know that my 14 year old self owes that man my life.\\nI‚Äôm not sure where he is in life, or what he‚Äôs doing, but I hope God is blessing him abundantly.\\nIt is definitely a funny story to tell my friends.\\nAccording to the above context, answer the following question.\\nWhere did the author get trapped?","target":"In the port-a-pot","rationale":"The context mentions that the author was stuck in a port-a-pot. They were inside for 10 minutes before they realized that it had locked behind them, and then remained trapped until someone opened the door from outside.\\nTherefore, the answer is \\"In the port-a-pot\\"."},{"source":"Found the following article online, use it to answer the question: Whose husband does the girl that notices the first person to set foot on Plymouth Rock follow?\\n\\nThe film tells a fictionalized version of the Pilgrims' voyage across the Atlantic Ocean to North America aboard the Mayflower. During the long sea voyage, Capt. Christopher Jones falls in love with Dorothy Bradford, the wife of William Bradford. The love triangle is resolved in a tragic way at the film's conclusion.  Ship's carpenter John Alden -- said to be the first person to set foot on Plymouth Rock in 1620‚Äîcatches the eye of Priscilla Mullins, one of the young Pilgrims following William Bradford.  Alden ultimately wins Priscilla in another, if subtler, triangle with Miles Standish.   Lloyd Bridges provides comic relief as the first-mate Coppin, and child star Tommy Ivo gives a touching performance as young William Button, the only passenger to die on the actual voyage across the storm-swept Atlantic, who, according to this film, wanted to be the first to sight land and to become a king in the New World. \\"I'm going to be the first to see land. Keep me eye peeled, I will. Then I'll be the first. It'll be like the Garden of Eden and I'm going to be the first to see it\\".","target":"Dorothy Bradford","rationale":"The article mentions the love story between Dorothy Bradford and Captain Christopher Jones. The passage also says that this relationship is resolved in a tragic way at the film's conclusion, implying it ends badly for Dorothy. \\nBased on these descriptions of her character, we can infer that she does not end up with either man in the triangle. Since Priscilla Mullins' husband is John Alden, who wins her over Miles Standish, then William Bradford must be married to Dorothy Bradford so he must be her husband (they are mentioned together)."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to the associated containers is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its associated container B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate container for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\ncereal : box. chips : ?","target":"bag","rationale":"Cereal is often stored in a box. Similarly, chips are often stored in a bag."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the passage.\\n\\"Turkey is bordered by eight countries: Bulgaria to the northwest; Greece to the west; Georgia to the northeast; Armenia , Iran and the Azerbaijani exclave of Nakhchivan to the east; and Iraq and Syria to the southeast.\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Turkey","rationale":"The passage is about Turkey, as it mentions the countries that border this country.\\nTherefore, the answer to \\"Determine the topic of the question\\" should be: \\nTurkey"},{"source":"The metro leaves the Rodovi√°ria (bus station) and goes south, avoiding most of the political and tourist areas. The main purpose of the metro is to serve cities, such as Samambaia, Taguatinga and Ceil√¢ndia, as well as Guar√° and √Åguas Claras. The satellite cities served are more populated in total than the Plano Piloto itself (the census of 2000 indicated that Ceil√¢ndia had 344,039 inhabitants, Taguatinga had 243,575, whereas the Plano Piloto had approximately 400,000 inhabitants), and most residents of the satellite cities depend on public transportation. Please tell me What is the Rodovi√°ria?","target":"bus station","rationale":"The context provides a description of the metro system in Bras√≠lia. The main purpose of this transportation service is to serve cities that are not within Plano Piloto, which we can assume is the city center area of Brasilia.\\nThese cities include Samambaia, Taguatinga and Ceilandia as well as Guara and Aguas Claras. Most residents who live outside these areas depend on public transportation for their daily travels. \\nOne such method of transport shared by most people living in these areas is the bus network system (which would be operated from specific locations known as \\"bus stations\\"). So clearly when it mentions 'Rodovi√°ria', its referring to a place where buses arrive or depart at/from based on various routes they cover (\\"stations\\" being"},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: Sandra journeyed to the bathroom. Daniel moved to the garden. Mary went back to the garden. Daniel went back to the kitchen. Mary went back to the bedroom. Mary went back to the bathroom. Question: Where is Daniel?","target":"kitchen","rationale":"We can be infer from the second last fact in the passage which states \\"Daniel went back to the kitchen.\\""},{"source":"Q: Which entity runs the Bronx's public noncharter schools?\\n A: Education in the Bronx is provided by a large number of public and private institutions, many of which draw students who live beyond the Bronx.\\n Does the answer correctly answer the question\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The answer provided gives a general overview of education in the Bronx, but it does not provide information about who or what entity runs the public noncharter schools. Although there is an inference that might be made based on other statements within the passage (i.e., \\"many of which draw students who live beyond the Bronx\\"), such inferences are rarely correct and should only be used if no explicit evidence can be found to support or refute a claim."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an anaphor number agreement or as an incorrect representation. An anaphor is an expression whose interpretation depends upon another expression. Anaphor number agreement is a restriction where a phrase agrees with the preceeding expression: plurals match plurals or singular expressions match singular expressions. In this task a valid representation of anaphor number agreement should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an anaphor number agreement will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence where the subject and self-referencing nouns match plurality. An incorrect representation is a sentence in which the subject and self-referencing noun's plurality do not match.\\n\\nChildren appreciate himself.","target":"bad","rationale":"The subject of the sentence is \\"Children\\", which is plural. However, the reflexive pronoun \\"himself\\" is singular and does not agree with the plurality of the subject. A correct representation would be \\"Children appreciate themselves\\", where the plural subject \\"children\\" agrees with the plural reflexive pronoun \\"themselves\\".\\\\nTherefore, This sentence is an incorrect representation of anaphor number agreement and should be denoted as \\"bad\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an answer, and your task is to generate a reasonable question for that answer.\\n\\nI just lost my job.","target":"Do you work in town?","rationale":"The answer \\"I just lost my job\\" implies that the person does not currently have a job. The question \\"Do you work in town?\\" is a reasonable question to ask, since it relates to whether or not the person has a job, and possibly where the person lived (in town or out of town)."},{"source":"What is the final step of the following process:\\n-  Air goes into the lungs\\n- The lungs remove oxygen from the air\\n- Oxygen diffuses from alveoli in the lungs to the bloodstream\\n- Hemoglobin in red blood cells attaches to the oxygen\\n- Red blood cells carry oxygen all around the body","target":"Oxygen diffuses into cells from capillaries.","rationale":"The final step of the process is:\\nOxygen diffuses into cells from capillaries."},{"source":"You are supposed to identify the category of a high-school level math question. There are five possible categories (1) algebra (2) arithmetic (3) measurement (4) numbers, and (5) probability. Use the following guidelines: (1) 'algebra' questions will typically contain letter variables and will ask you to find the value of a variable (2) 'arithmetic' questions will ask the sum, difference, multiplication, division, power, square root or value of expressions involving brackets (3) 'measurement' questions are questions that ask to convert a quantity from some unit to some other unit (4) 'numbers' questions will be about bases, remainders, divisors, GCD, LCM etc. (5) 'probability' questions will ask about the probability of the occurrence of something. A question must belong to only one category.\\n\\nSolve 414 - 407 = 7*t for t.","target":"algebra","rationale":"The given expression contains a letter variable (t) and asks to find its value. Hence, the category is 'algebra'."},{"source":"Multi-select: Let's say that \\"The lawyer asked the witness a question, but he was reluctant to repeat it.\\"\\n\\nCan we now say that \\"The witness was reluctant to repeat it.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"The statement \\"He was reluctant to repeat it\\" is ambiguous in this context. The witness may be referring to the question or he could also be referring to something else that occurred during a previous hearing. Therefore, we cannot conclude if the hypothesis is true based on the premise provided."},{"source":"You are given a math word problem and you are supposed to only use multiplication or division operators on the numbers embedded in the text to answer the following question and then only report the final numerical answer.\\n\\nContext: The Razorback t-shirt shop sells each t-shirt for $ 201 dollars. During the Arkansas and Texas tech game they increased the prices by $ 217 per t-shirt and sold 14 t-shirts. \\n\\n Question: How much money did they make from selling the t-shirts?","target":"5852","rationale":"You can solve this problem by dividing the total money made from selling the t-shirts ($5852) by the number of t-shirts sold (14). This gives you $417.2857, which is how much they increased the price of each shirt, which is the answer."},{"source":"You are given a news article headline from BBC Yoruba and your task is to classify it into one of the following categories:  Africa, Entertainment, Health, Nigeria, Politics, Sport, or World.\\n\\n√åp√≠nl·∫πÃÄ Osun y√≥√≤ m√∫ √†y√≠pad√† b√° √†w·ªçn il√†n√† √¨·π£√®j·ªçba Rauf Aregbesola","target":"Nigeria","rationale":"The news is about the actions of the government in Osun State in Nigeria, which falls under the category of \\"Nigeria\\"."},{"source":"Which entity is this text about?\\n\\nChristopher Lynn Hedges was born in St. Johnsbury, Vermont, the son of Thelma Louise (nee Prince) and the Rev. Thomas Havard Hedges, a Presbyterian minister. He grew up in rural Schoharie County, New York, southwest of Albany. He graduated in 1975 from the Loomis Chaffee School, a private boarding school in Windsor, Connecticut. He founded an underground newspaper at the school that was banned by the administration and resulted in his being put on probation.\\n\\nIn 2003, University of Texas classics professor Thomas Palaima wrote an article for the Austin-American Statesman accusing Hedges of plagiarizing Ernest Hemingway in Hedge's 2002 book War Is a Force That Gives Us Meaning. Palaima said that Hedges had corrected a passage in his first edition of War Is a Force That Gives Us Meaning that was close to Hemingway, and he should have cited the paraphrase in all subsequent editions. Hedges' publisher at the time, PublicAffairs, said it did not believe the passage needed to be cited to Hemingway. The New Republic said that Palaima's allegation had resulted in the passage being reworded. But, after posting the article online, the magazine posted a correction box that read:  \\"In the original version of this article, The New Republic indicated that PublicAffairs changed the text of War Is a Force That Gives Us Meaning only after having been alerted by Thomas [Palaima] to the presence of plagiarism. In fact, the wording had been changed months earlier, and an edition with the present language existed at the time of Palaima's e-mail to PublicAffairs. However, there was still no attribution to Hemingway in the new version, despite the obvious similarities in ideas and formulation\\".  In June 2014, Christopher Ketcham accused Hedges of plagiarism in an article published in The New Republic. Ketcham claims that Hedges plagiarized many writers over his career, including Matt Katz, Naomi Klein, Neil Postman, Ernest Hemingway, along with Ketcham's wife: Petra Bartosiewicz. Hedges, his editors at Truthdig, and his publisher Nation Books denied the claims made by Ketcham. In a response first published by The Real News on June 16, 2014, Hedges noted that Ketcham based his allegations on an unpublished manuscript which the latter man admitted he had never seen and passages that were actually footnoted or sourced. Hedges accused Ketcham and The New Republic (TNR) of malicious intent and character assassination. On the following day (June 17), The New Republic republished Hedges' response along with Ketcham's (and TNR's) response to the counter-allegations made by Hedges.  The Washington Free Beacon reported The New York Times spokesman saying that it \\"did not have reason to believe Hedges plagiarized in his work for the paper\\" and had no plans to investigate Hedges for plagiarism. The American Prospect and Salon declined to publish Ketcham's article, and The Nation Institute and Truthdig issued statements dismissing Ketcham's allegations.\\n\\nEntity:","target":"Chris Hedges","rationale":"The context is a description of Chris Hedges' life, career and personal experiences. Thus the entity about which the text talks is Chris Hedges"},{"source":"Freemasonry\\nSince the founding of Freemasonry, many Bishops of the Church of England have been Freemasons, such as Archbishop Geoffrey Fisher. In the past, few members of the Church of England would have seen any incongruity in concurrently adhering to Anglican Christianity and practicing Freemasonry. In recent decades, however, reservations about Freemasonry have increased within Anglicanism, perhaps due to the increasing prominence of the evangelical wing of the church. The former Archbishop of Canterbury, Dr Rowan Williams, appeared to harbour some reservations about Masonic ritual, whilst being anxious to avoid causing offence to Freemasons inside and outside the Church of England. In 2003 he felt it necessary to apologise to British Freemasons after he said that their beliefs were incompatible with Christianity and that he had barred the appointment of Freemasons to senior posts in his diocese when he was Bishop of Monmouth.\\n\\nQ: What English Archbishop was a member of the Freemasons?","target":"Geoffrey Fisher","rationale":"Since the founding of Freemasonry, many Bishops of the Church of England have been Freemasons.\\nThe context provides an example for this by mentioning that Archbishop Geoffrey Fisher was a member.\\nTherefore, based on this information and considering other choices such as Rowan Williams are incorrect (since he appeared to harbour some reservations about Masonic ritual),  we can conclude that \\"Geoffrey Fisher\\" is the correct answer choice."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a short story with a beginning, two potential middles, and an ending. Your job is to choose the middle statement that makes the story coherent / plausible by writing \\"1\\" or \\"2\\" in the output. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes most sense.\\n\\nBeginning: Bill was looking forward to a quiet weekend at home. Middle 1: Bill's daughter called with car problems. Middle 2: Bill's car called with daughter problems. Ending: Bill fixed her car but missed out on the quiet weekend.","target":"1","rationale":"The first sentence of the story implies that Bill is looking forward to a quiet weekend at home. The second sentence states that Bill's daughter called with car problems, which makes sense since daughters generally don't have car problems. The third sentence states that Bill's car called with daughter problems, but it doesn't make sense for a car to call someone about its daughter. Therefore, the answer is \\"1\\"."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios.\\n\\nMason entered the dining_room. Sophia entered the dining_room. The cabbage is in the green_envelope. Sophia exited the dining_room. Mason moved the cabbage to the blue_cupboard. Sophia entered the pantry. Mason entered the pantry. The turnip is in the red_pantry. Mason exited the pantry. Sophia moved the turnip to the blue_crate. Sophia entered the hallway. Mason entered the hallway. The banana is in the green_box. Mason exited the hallway. Sophia moved the banana to the red_treasure_chest. Sophia entered the laundry. Olivia entered the laundry. The green_pepper is in the green_pantry. Olivia exited the laundry. Sophia moved the green_pepper to the blue_box. Where will Olivia look for the green_pepper?","target":"green_pantry","rationale":"Olivia will look for the green_pepper in the green_pantry because she has a false belief about Sophia's beliefs."},{"source":"Goal: Practice your soccer shooting skills.\\n\\nWhich is the correct ending?\\n- Practice your approach to the ball, placing your plant foot just behind the ball when you want to get some air under it\\n- Practice your approach to the ball, placing your plant foot just in front the ball when you want to get some air under it\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"Practice your approach to the ball, placing your plant foot just behind the ball when you want to get some air under it","rationale":"This is a question about soccer. In the first step, it's mentioning the \\"approach to the ball\\". It means that your other foot should be placed in front of the plant foot when you want get some air under it so that you can shoot far and high.\\nSo we finally choose: Practice your approach to the ball, placing your plant foot just behind the ball when you want to get some air under it\\n\\n\\nQ  10/10 (A or B)\\tRationale 1-3 sentences max \\tAnswer A or B  \\tOptions 2 options only"},{"source":"Karnishakuji4- 162\\nTokyo 145\\nOctober24,2007\\nConcord School of English\\n23 Essex St.\\nConcord,,NH03301\\nDear Madam or sir ,\\nOne of the teachers at my school in Japan told me that your school has summer courses . I'm planning to go to the USA next summer and would like to take a one- month course .\\nI'm 18 years old and have been studying English for six years . I'm going to study English at the university . I have ever been to a few countries , such as China , England ,Korea ,but never to the US ,and I think a trip will help me improve my English .\\nCould you send me a catalogue and application ? I would also like information about New Hampshire and other places nearby .\\nI hope to do some traveling when the course is over .\\nThank you . I look forward to your reply .\\nYours ,\\nMariko Kobori\\nMariko Kobori  began to learn English at the age of   _  .\\nA) 18\\nB) 16\\nC) 14\\nD) 12","target":"D","rationale":"The letter begins with Mariko saying that she has been studying English for six years, and is 18 years old. Because there are twelve years in between 6 and 18, the correct answer must be 12 (A).\\nSo , the Answer should be D"},{"source":"What item is high in moisture?\\n\\nPick the right answer from the list:\\n- firewood\\n- light bulb\\n- wet dog\\n- a book","target":"wet dog","rationale":"The question is asking for an item that has a high amount of moisture in it. The appropriate answer would be wet dog, since the others are not living organisms and do not contain any water or moisture."},{"source":"Q: who sings crazy in love in 50 shades of grey? A:","target":"Beyonc√©","rationale":"The song Crazy in Love is sung by Beyonc√© and featured on the soundtrack for 50 Shades of Grey"},{"source":"Please answer a question about the following article about Bird:\\n\\nMany bird species migrate to take advantage of global differences of seasonal temperatures, therefore optimising availability of food sources and breeding habitat. These migrations vary among the different groups. Many landbirds, shorebirds, and waterbirds undertake annual long distance migrations, usually triggered by the length of daylight as well as weather conditions. These birds are characterised by a breeding season spent in the temperate or polar regions and a non-breeding season in the tropical regions or opposite hemisphere. Before migration, birds substantially increase body fats and reserves and reduce the size of some of their organs. Migration is highly demanding energetically, particularly as birds need to cross deserts and oceans without refuelling. Landbirds have a flight range of around 2,500 km (1,600 mi) and shorebirds can fly up to 4,000 km (2,500 mi), although the bar-tailed godwit is capable of non-stop flights of up to 10,200 km (6,300 mi). Seabirds also undertake long migrations, the longest annual migration being those of sooty shearwaters, which nest in New Zealand and Chile and spend the northern summer feeding in the North Pacific off Japan, Alaska and California, an annual round trip of 64,000 km (39,800 mi). Other seabirds disperse after breeding, travelling widely but having no set migration route. Albatrosses nesting in the Southern Ocean often undertake circumpolar trips between breeding seasons.\\n\\nWhen do birds substantially increase body fats and reduce the size of some of their organs?","target":"Before migration","rationale":"The answer is the second sentence of paragraph 2:\\nBefore migration, birds substantially increase body fats and reserves and reduce the size of some of their organs."},{"source":"Write down the solution for this math problem: Solve -9901683*w + 9902158*w + 475 = 0 for w.","target":"-1","rationale":"To solve for w, we need to isolate the variable on one side of the equation.\\n\\nStarting with: -9901683w + 9902158w + 475 = 0\\nSubtracting 9902158 from both sides: -19828841*w + 475 = 0 \\nAdding 19828641 to both sides and dividing by 2 :-475/2=0 Add(-475)/-2 times Divide(1)(bothsides)"},{"source":"In this task, you are given an abstract of article. Your task is to generate label \\"True\\" if abstract is structured, otherwise generate \\"False\\". A structured abstract is composed of a topic sentence (or key sentence), relevant supporting sentences, and a closing (or transition) sentence. This structure is key to keeping your abstract focused on the main idea and creating a clear and concise image.\\n\\nWe show that, in vitro, Ca2+-dependent protein kinase C (PKC) phosphorylates recombinant murine p53 protein on several residues contained within a conserved basic region of 25 amino acids, located in the C-terminal part of the protein. Accordingly, synthetic p53-(357-381)-peptide is phosphorylated by PKC at multiple Ser and Thr residues, including Ser360, Thr365, Ser370 and Thr377. We also establish that p53-(357-381)-peptide at micromolar concentrations has the ability to stimulate sequence-specific DNA binding by p53. That stimulation is lost upon phosphorylation by PKC. To further characterise the mechanisms that regulate PKC-dependent phosphorylation of p53-(357-381)-peptide, the phosphorylation of recombinant p53 and p53-(357-381)-peptide by PKC were compared. The results suggest that phosphorylation of full-length p53 on the C-terminal PKC sites is highly dependent on the accessibility of the phosphorylation sites and that a domain on p53 distinct from p53-(357-381)-peptide is involved in binding PKC. Accordingly, we have identified a conserved 27-amino-acid peptide, p53-(320-346)-peptide, within the C-terminal region of p53 and adjacent to residues 357-381 that interacts with PKC in vitro. The interaction between p53-(320-346)-peptide and PKC inhibits PKC autophosphorylation and the phosphorylation of substrates, including p53-(357-381)-peptide, neurogranin and histone H1. Conventional Ca2+-dependent PKC alpha, beta and gamma and the catalytic fragment of PKC (PKM) were nearly equally susceptible to inhibition by p53-(320-346)-peptide. The Ca2+-independent PKC delta was much less sensitive to inhibition. The significance of these findings for understanding the in vivo phosphorylation of p53 by PKC are discussed.","target":"False","rationale":"The abstract does not have a clear structure, and readers may have difficulty understanding the main idea of the research. There is no topic sentence or key sentence that summarizes the main goal of the study. Also, there are many sentences (e.g., ‚ÄúWe also establish‚Ä¶‚Äù) that start with phrases like ‚Äúwe show‚Äù or ‚Äúwe establish‚Äù but it is difficult to understand what they are actually trying to show or establish. As a result, readers would likely find it difficult to focus on and understand the main idea of this research paper based on this abstract alone, even if they don't know anything about the field of interest (e.g., biochemistry). So this abstract is not structured and should be labeled as \\"False\\"."},{"source":"Answer the following question:\\n\\n1 marla is equal to how many yard?","target":"30.25 square yards","rationale":"1 marla is equal to 30.25 square yards or 25.2929 square metres, so the answer should be \\"30.25 square yards\\"."},{"source":"What is the question to: \\"A quarry is a type of open-pit mine from which rock or minerals are extracted.\\"? The topic is Quarry.","target":"\\"what is a rock quarry?\\"","rationale":"The answer provided, \\"what is a rock quarry?\\" correctly paraphrases the information in the text snippet. The snippet states that quarries are open-pit mines and goes on to explain what types of materials are extracted from them.\\nTherefore, based on this evidence, it can be concluded that the question asked by the system was accurate"},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: There are a number of special days of the year that are celebrated in different countries. The origins of most of the days are unknown. They were certainly not created by individual people. Other days, however, especially those celebrated in western countries, often owe their origins to a particular person. One of the most popular of these, even though it is fairly recent, is Mother's Day. Mothers have always been highly regarded in all cultures. The ancient Romans had a festival known as Hilaria, during which children took presents to the temple of the \\"Mother of the Gods\\". The Christian Church adopted this idea and called it Mothering Sunday. However, over the years this custom was gradually forgotten and almost disappeared by the end of the 19th century.\\nBorn in 1864 in Virginia, USA, Anna Jarvis was a school teacher and believed children should show gratitude to their mothers for all their love and care. Encouraged by a friend, she wrote to thousands of important people--politicians, churchmen, doctors, city officials--and asked them to support her idea: a special day of the year for thanking mothers.\\nIn 1910 the Governor of West Virginia introduced Mother's Day into the state. The date chosen was May 10--the second Sunday in May, which is still observed in America today. This date was chosen because May 10 was the date on which in 1908 Anna Jarvis's mother had died. In 1914 President Woodrow Wilson made May 10 the official date for Mother's Day throughout the United States.\\nSoon there was a Mother's Day International Association and the custom began to be adopted in many countries of the world.\\nAnna Jarvis, a sad and disillusioned  woman, died in 1948. The custom she had worked so hard to establish and which had become almost universal had lost its original purpose. It had been taken over by business. Like Christmas, the giving of presents and the sending of cards had become a multi-million-dollar industry.\\nQuestion: May 10 became the date for Mother's Day because    _    .\\nOptions: A: May is in the American spring\\nB: it was the second Sunday in May in 1910\\nC: President Wilson liked the date\\nD: this was the date on which Anna Jarvis's mother died","target":"D","rationale":"The article describes how Mother's Day became an official holiday in the United States, and then was adopted by other countries. The originator of this holiday is Anna Jarvis who worked to persuade people that there should be a special day for mothers. In the second paragraph it states that \\"...the date chosen was May 10--the second Sunday in May, which is still observed today.\\" It also says: \\"In 1914 President Woodrow Wilson made May 10th the official date for Mother's Day throughout the US\\"\\nThis means that Presidents have nothing to do with choosing the actual dates. So answer C about what President Wilson thought about a particular date can't be correct\\nChoices A & B are both incorrect because they give facts but don't explain why those were important reasons behind making them official events"},{"source":"Question: The main part of turkey makes up what?\\n\\nChoices: \\n- ocean\\n- middle east\\n- balkan peninsula\\n- turkeycock\\n- asia minor\\n\\nThe rationale to choose \\"asia minor\\" as the answer is that:","target":"turkey is the country that is the bulk of asia minor","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"turkey is the country that is the bulk of asia minor\\"."},{"source":"Jose Julian Marti Perez (January 28, 1853 - May 19, 1895) was a Cuban National Hero and an important figure in Latin American literature. During his life, he worked as a poet, essayist, journalist, translator, professor, and publisher. He was very politically active, and is considered an important revolutionary philosopher and political theorist. Through his writings and political activity, he became a symbol of Cuba's bid for independence against Spain in the 19th century, and is referred to as the \\"Apostle of Cuban Independence.\\"\\n\\nJanuary 12, 1895, the North American authorities stopped the steamship Lagonda and two other suspicious ships, Amadis, and Baracoa at the Fernandina port in Florida, confiscating weapons and ruining Plan de Fernandina (Fernandina Plan). On January 29, Marti drew up the order of the uprising, signing it with general Jose Maria Rodriguez and Enrique Collazo. Juan Gualberto Gomez was assigned to orchestrate war preparations for La Habana Province, and was able to work right under the noses of the relatively unconcerned Spanish authorities. Marti decided to move to Montecristi, Dominican Republic to join Maximo Gomez and to plan out the uprising.  The uprising finally took place on February 24, 1895. A month later, Marti and Maximo Gomez declared the Manifesto de Montecristi, an \\"exposition of the purposes and principles of the Cuban revolution\\". Marti had persuaded Gomez to lead an expedition into Cuba.  Before leaving for Cuba, Marti wrote his \\"literary will\\" on April 1, 1895, leaving his personal papers and manuscripts to Gonzalo de Quesada, with instructions for editing. Knowing that the majority of his writing in newspapers in Honduras, Uruguay, and Chile would disappear over time, Marti instructed Quesada to arrange his papers in volumes. The volumes were to be arranged in the following way: volumes one and two, North Americas; volume three, Hispanic Americas; volume four, North American Scenes; volume five, Books about the Americas (this included both North and South America); volume six, Literature, education and painting. Another volume included his poetry.  The expedition, composed of Marti, Gomez, Angel Guerra, Francisco Borreo, Cesar Salas and Marcos del Rosario, left Montecristi for Cuba on April 1, 1895. Despite delays and desertion by some members, they got to Cuba. They landed at Playitas, near Cape Maisi and Imias, Cuba, on April 11. Once there, they made contact with the Cuban rebels, who were headed by the Maceo brothers, and started fighting against Spanish troops. The revolt did not go as planned, \\"mainly because the call to revolution received no immediate, spontaneous support from the masses.\\" By May 13, the expedition reached Dos Rios. On May 19, Gomez faced Ximenez de Sandoval's troops and ordered Marti to stay rearguard, but Marti separated from the bulk of the Cuban forces, and entered the Spanish line.\\n\\nAsk a question about this article.","target":"What did the order that he drew up entail?","rationale":"In the article, Marti is described as being politically active. He was a revolutionary philosopher and political theorist who led an effort to gain independence from Spain for Cuba in the 19th century. \\nGiven this information about his life, it‚Äôs clear that he would have had some sort of plan or strategy. The context also states: \\"\\"On January 29, Marti drew up the order of the uprising,\\"\\" which further indicates that there must be more details about what exactly this order entailed somewhere in the text. \\nThus, based on these facts, we can conclude that a fitting question to ask regarding this paragraph would be ‚ÄúWhat did the order that he drew up entail?‚Äù"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question and answer options for that question. Using this information, you have to classify each text into different topics: medicine, nursery, psychology, chemistry, pharmacology, biology.\\n\\nQuestion: In a 60-year-old man with moderate renal insufficiency, treatment is started, without administration of loading dose, with a digitalis medication. Under these conditions, the half-life or plasma half-life of digitalis is estimated at 72 hours. Indicate how much treatment time in days should elapse from the start of treatment to reach the steady state concentration or equilibrium concentration. \\n Options:  <0> In 3 days. <1> Between 3 and 9 days. <2> Between 12 and 15 days. <3> More than 30 days <4> More than 60 days","target":"medicine","rationale":"The question and options are all related to the topic of medicine. This can be observed from the use of medical terms like \\"renal insufficiency\\", \\"digitalis medication\\", etc. Therefore, this text belongs to the topic of medicine."},{"source":"Given a prompt and four completions, select the completion that is the most plausible in continuing or answering the prompt. This task is designed to test common sense and has various categories ranging between idioms, negated statements, polysemy, subject referencing, and quantitative reasoning. Generate either Completion A, Completion B, Completion C, or Completion D.\\n\\nPrompt: Ashley walks her dog around her neighborhood. She \\nCompletion A: then goes to the park \\nCompletion B: wags her tail \\nCompletion C: then laps up water from the faucet \\nCompletion D: catches the frisbee in her mouth","target":"Completion A","rationale":"The prompt is about Ashley walking her dog around her neighborhood. Completion A is the most plausible completion because it continues the story and describes something that Ashley could do after walking her dog."},{"source":"Given the background: As time passes, the number of HIV copies keeps increasing, while the number of helper T cells keeps decreasing. The graph in Figure below shows how the number of T cells typically declines over a period of many years following the initial HIV infection. As the number of T cells decreases, so does the ability of the immune system to defend the body. As a result, an HIV-infected person develops frequent infections. Medicines can slow down the virus but not get rid of it, so there is no cure at present for HIV infections or AIDS. There also is no vaccine to immunize people against HIV infection, but scientists are working to develop one.\\n\\nand the situation: A doctor tested two people for HIV. Tom had the virus in his blood, while Nick didn't have HIV, he was healthy. Tom has apparently had the virus for 20 years.\\n\\nAnswer the following question: Which person didn't develop frequent infections?","target":"Nick","rationale":"The background talks about the fact that as time passes, HIV destroys helper T cells in blood. It also says that once there are not enough helper T's left to fight off infections and diseases, a person becomes prone to frequent infections. This means Tom would develop frequent infection because he is infected with HIV for 20 years now whereas Nick didn't have any traces of virus in his body so he wouldn't develop any complications!\\nHence, answer is: \\"Nick\\"."},{"source":"Pat has become a banker and very conservative.\\n\\nHow would you consider the linguistic integrity of the preceding sentence?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The sentence \\"Pat has become a banker and very conservative\\" is linguistically acceptable."},{"source":"Write the conversation response. DIALOG:\\nWhat was the median income in Vilas, Wisconsin?\\n- Males had a median income of $26,979 versus $15,833 for females.\\n- What was the per capita income?\\n- The per capita income for the town was $14,423.\\n- Did the town experience any poverty?\\n-","target":"About 3.7% of families and 7.1% of the population were below the poverty line, including 11.3% of those under the age of eighteen and 12.9% of those sixty five or over.","rationale":"\\"The question asks about the town's experience with poverty. The previous utterance in the dialog presents a statistic indicating a portion of people under 18 and over 65 were below the poverty line. The most reasonable response is therefore one that gives statistics on families and other portions of the population, which includes option (D), \\"About 3.7% of families and 7.1% of the population were below the poverty line, including 11.3% of those under the age of eighteen and 12.9% of those sixty five or over.\\""},{"source":"Speedway Field was the original name for the airfield that was to evolve into Minneapolis-St. Paul International Airport, the twelfth busiest airport in the United States; it was also the largest hub for Northwest Airlines and the third largest hub for Delta Air Lines, Northwest's successor.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion?\\nThe former Speedway Field is the twelfth busiest airport in the U.S.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"Yes","rationale":"The passage states that the original Speedway Field was to evolve into Minneapolis-St. Paul International Airport, and goes on to describe some of its current properties in terms of location and airline use. Based upon this information we can conclude that what is now known as Minneapolis-St. Paul International Airport used to be called Speedway Field, so the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Here is a question about this article: Assembly of desktop computers for the North American market formerly took place at Dell plants in Austin, Texas (original location) and Lebanon, Tennessee (opened in 1999), which have been closed in 2008 and early 2009, respectively. The plant in Winston-Salem, North Carolina received $280 million USD in incentives from the state and opened in 2005, but ceased operations in November 2010, and Dell's contract with the state requires them to repay the incentives for failing to meet the conditions. Most of the work that used to take place in Dell's U.S. plants was transferred to contract manufacturers in Asia and Mexico, or some of Dell's own factories overseas. The Miami, Florida facility of its Alienware subsidiary remains in operation, while Dell continues to produce its servers (its most profitable products) in Austin, Texas.\\nWhat is the answer to this question: What year was Dell's Tennessee facility opened?","target":"1999","rationale":"Dell's Tennessee facility was opened in 1999 according to the given context."},{"source":"See the conversation. hello I'm looking for an economic auto repair service\\nWhich is why I see you are a couple?\\nwhat are your packages\\nI need to know what he wants to do to the car\\nI would like to enhance the air conditioning\\nthat will come at a cost of 100\\nI find it economical\\nIt is the cheapest place you will find in the city\\nand what quality\\nit's very good\\nreally\\nWe guarantee a job well done\\nI'll wait\\nIf you are not happy with your money back\\nwhen they are available\\nfor Monday of the coming week","target":"what time can I take the car","rationale":"The user has been presented with an economic package for servicing the air conditioning of their car. They need to know when they can take the car in for servicing. Hence, their next question would be \\"what time can I take the car\\", which is not included as a candidate option.\\""},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the no-need strategy, otherwise output No. no-need is a cooperative negotiation strategy. It is used when a participant points out that they do not need an item based on personal context such as suggesting that they have ample water to spare. no-need can directly benefit the opponent since it implies that the item is up for grabs.\\n\\nContext: 'I would like to ask for 3 firewood, 1 water and 0 food. I will be in an area where no extra wood will be available and I need the wood to cook all the food that I will already have.'\\nUtterance: 'I understand where you're coming from but I'm afraid that is not acceptable.  My family's comfort is my top priority and I will be needing at least 2 firewoods to make sure they are kept warm.  I would also request some extra water. '","target":"No","rationale":"The speaker simply states that they need firewood and water, without indicating that they don't need anything.\\\\nFor example, if the speaker had said \\"I've brought enough water with me so I don't need any more,\\" then the no-need strategy would be used.\\\\nSince the utterance in this case does not use the no-need strategy, the answer is No."},{"source":"Answer this question:\\n\\nwhich city is on the east side of san francisco bay??","target":"Oakland","rationale":"The correct answer is Oakland."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is sexually offensive, 2) no, otherwise. Emphasis on sexually offensive or any lewd reference. Generate label 'no' for offensive posts that do not reference sexually explicit content. Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\nAfter I was abducted by the aliens, I begged and pleaded with them not to butt-probe me. But it was no use. Diego and Jose shoved the cocaine up my arse and sent me back over the border.","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given post contains sexually explicit and offensive language. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"DIALOG:\\nWhat are the notable guests in Oprah winfrey show?\\n- Kathy Bray, Truddi Chase, Erin Kramp, Mattie Stepanek, and Jo Ann Compton\\n- When did the Oprah Winfrey show take place where Jo Ann Compton was the guest?\\n-","target":"1998","rationale":"Included in the dialog above is a user question, system answer and a follow-up user question. The follow-up user question asks when Oprah's show took place where Jo Ann Compton was the guest. This can be answered by reading the system's response, which states that it took place in 1998.\\n\\n</pre>\\nThe following is an example of how to use some of these features with \`TextDataset\`s: <pre>\\nfrom torchtext import data, datasets \\nimport spacy \\n\\n # custom tokenizer that converts non-breaking spaces to spaces \\n\\n def my_tokenizer(nlp):   return lambda text: ' '.join([tok for tok in nlp(text.replace('\\\\xa0', ' '))])\\n\\n # Load English tokenizer, tagger, parser and NER  \\n\\n nlp = spacy.load('en')  \\n\\n # define fields that accept preprocessed tokens as input; no need for label field because we won't be taking advantage of labels at all here (in this example)  \\n\\n TEXT = data.Field(sequential=True, tokenize=my_tokenizer(nlp), batch_first=True)    LABEL = data.Field()    fields = [(None, None), ('label', LABEL)]    train_datafields = [(\\"context\\", TEXT), (\\"question\\", TEXT), (\\"answerA\\", TEXT), (\\"answerB\\", TEXT), (\\"answerC\\", TEXT), (\\"answerD\\",TEXT)]     devtest_datafields = [(\\"idx1\\",\\"idx2\\"),(\\"question\\",\\"context\\")]     devtest2_datafields=[(\\"idx1\\",\\"idx2\\"),(\\"question\\",\\"answerA\\")]     trainds ,devds ,testds ,devdsss ,testdsss= datasets .SNLI .splits (TEXT ,LABEL ) \\ttrainexamples=[r for r in trainds[0]]\\tdevexamples=[r for r in devdsss[0].examples]\\ttestexamples=[r for r in testdsss[0].examples]\\tprint (len ([e .__dict__ ['premise']for e in devexamples ])) \\t#23584 print (len ([e .__dict__ ['hypothesis']for ein devexample s ]))#23584 print (devexample s [ 0 ].premise ) print (deve xampl es [ 0 ].h ypot hesis ) pr int (' ------ ----- ----- - -------' ) pr int (' -------- ------ -- -- -----' ) prin t('------ --------- ------ -') pr int (' ---------- ------- ---' ) pri nt('----- --------- ----') p rint ('-------- ------ ---') pri nt('--- -- --- -----' )pri nt('---- ---- ---' )) print (!/!/,!/!/) /! /!/ !/,!/!/)/ !/ ! /!/)/ !! !! !! !!!! !!!!! !!!!!! !!!! /// /// //// //////// /////////////!!!!!!!!!!!!!)))))))))))))))!!!!/// /// /// /// ~ ~ ~ ** *** ***** ** ****** ******* * *** ** ****** * ***** *** ** * ** * *** ** ‚òÖ ‚òÜ ‚òÖ ‚úØ‚úØ‚úØ‚òÖ ‚òÖ ‚òÜ ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÜ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚úß ‚ãÜ ‚ú∂ ‚ú≠ ‚ú∑ ‚úµ ‚ãÖ ‚ôõ‚ôö‚ôõ‚ôö‚ôö ‚ô°‚ùÄ‚ùÅ ‚ùÉ ‚ùÇ‚ùÖ‚ùÑ‚òΩ‚òæ ‚óê‚óë‚ò™‚òÆ‚ô•‚ô¶‚ô£ ‚ô†‚öú ‚óè‚óâ‚óé ‚óç ‚óå ‚ñì‚ñí‚ñë ‚ñí‚ñì‚ñë‚ñ∫‚ñº ‚Üï‚Äø‚Üï‚úé‚úü‡Æê ‚âà‡πë€©€û€©‡πë‚âà‡πë€©€û Ÿ≠ Ÿ≠ Ÿ≠ Ÿ≠ÿ¢ÿ¢ÿ¢ ÿ¢ÿ•ŸÖŸÄŸÄŸÄŸÜŸäŸÜÿßÔª¥Ô∫∞ Ôª¥Ô∫¨ÿß ÿßŸÑŸÑŸá Ôª¥Ô∫∞Ÿàÿ±ÿ≥ŸàŸÑŸá Ôª≤Ô∫£Ÿä ÿßŸÑÿØÿπÿßÿ°ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ≥ÿ™ÿ¨ÿßÿ® ŸÖŸÜ ÿ£ŸàŸÑ ÿßŸÑÿØÿπÿßÿ° ŸàÿßŸÑŸâ ÿ¢ÿÆÿ±Ÿá ..ÿ™ÿ®ÿßÿ±ŸÉ ÿßŸÑŸÑŸá Ÿàÿ≥ÿ®ÿ≠ÿßŸÜŸá Ÿàÿ™ÿπÿßŸÑŸä ŸÖŸÜ ÿ¥ÿ±Ÿàÿ± ÿ£ÿπÿØÿßÿ¶Ÿá .....~‚ô•~.......... ........ ......... .......... .......... .......... .......... .......... .............. ............... ................ .................. ................... ..................... ...................... ............................................... ................. ... ...... ....... ......"},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\nCell division is how organisms grow and repair themselves. It is also how they produce offspring. Many single-celled organisms reproduce by binary fission. The parent cell simply divides to form two daughter cells that are identical to the parent. In many other organisms, two parents are involved, and the offspring are not identical to the parents. In fact, each offspring is unique. Look at the family in Figure below . The children resemble their parents, but they are not identical to them. Instead, each has a unique combination of characteristics inherited from both parents. In this lesson, you will learn how this happens.\\n\\n\\nQ: What do organisms use to grow and repair themselves?\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"cell division","rationale":"The paragraph in the question mentions that cell division is how organisms grow and repair themselves. This statement implies that it doesn't use diffusion or mutation to do this, so those two options can be eliminated right off the bat because they are not correct. The only remaining option is \\"cell solution\\", which does not make any sense given the context of the passage, therefore eliminating it as well.\\nThis leaves us with just one answer: Cell Division"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is intentionally offensive, 2) no, otherwise. Also, generate label 'no' for offensive statements that appear to be unintentional, or non-offensive statements that are underhandedly offensive.  Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\nThis fat bitch is wearing these ugly ass jesus sandals, and her big ass feet are overlapping the damn things.","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given post is intentionally offensive to some people as it contains a derogatory term to describe an overweight woman and refers to her body in an objectifying manner. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two strings A, B. Find the longest common substring in the strings A and B.\\n\\nTxBIhCYTJhLBUUgX, wgxpSmhCYTJhXeoT","target":"hCYTJh","rationale":"The longest common substring in the given strings is 'hCYTJh'."},{"source":"Two analogies that signify affordances are given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Affordance is the possibility of an action being done on an object, for example book is an affordance of writing. The phrase \\"A : B\\" implies that B is an affordance of A. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate affordance of the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a single object without further explanation.\\n\\nsail : boat. climb : ?","target":"tree","rationale":"The phrase \\"sail : boat\\" implies that a boat is an affordance of sailing, so a tree would be an affordance of climbing."},{"source":"Sentence: \\"He's enough of a fool to try it.\\"\\nPick from options: would a linguist rate this sentence to be acceptable linguistically?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable...I think the answer is","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The sentence \\"He's enough of a fool to try it\\" is grammatically acceptable, because the prepositional phrase \\"of a fool\\" modifies the adjective \\"enough.\\""},{"source":"Two analogies that relate objects to the associated rooms is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates object A to room B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate room for the given object C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nsink : kitchen. bed : ?","target":"bedroom","rationale":"A sink is usually found in a kitchen, and a bed is usually found in a bedroom."},{"source":"Premise:\\n\\"Today, legal services advocates are increasingly bilingual; 22 percent of employees at LSC-funded programs in my country speak more than one language.\\" Based on this premise, is the hypothesis \\"None of the legal services advocates are bilingual.\\" true?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise states that 22 percent of employees at LSC-funded programs in the United States speak more than one language. This means that some legal services advocates are bilingual (more than zero). Therefore, it is not true to say \\"none\\" are bilingual. The answer should be no."},{"source":"WHITE HOUSE ‚Äî A controversial clothing choice is overshadowing a surprise visit by U.S. first lady Melania Trump to a Texas facility to meet immigrant children separated from their families because of her husband's \\"zero-tolerance\\" immigration policy.\\nBoarding a U.S. Air Force jet at and returning to Joint Base Andrews in Maryland on Thursday, the first lady was spotted wearing an olive green jacket. The back of the jacket read \\"I really don't care. Do U?\\" in white graffiti-style lettering.\\nThe first lady's team insisted that there was no hidden meaning behind the sartorial choice.\\n\\"It's a jacket. There was no hidden message. After today's important visit to Texas, I hope the media isn't going to choose to focus on her wardrobe,\\" said her communications director, Stephanie Grisham.\\nPresident Donald Trump, however, contradicted the assertion there was no message conveyed by his wife's choice of apparel.\\nTrump, in a tweet, said what was written on the back of the jacket \\"refers to the Fake News Media. Melania has learned how dishonest they are, and she truly no longer cares!\\"\\nTelevision news channels brought pundits in the studio to discuss the meaning conveyed by the jacket.\\n\\"I think she may have had an audience of one in mind ‚Äî her husband,\\" said USA Today newspaper Washington bureau chief Susan Page, who has covered six presidential administrations, appearing on MSNBC.\\n\\"I think it was Melania giving the middle finger to the media,\\" Kate Anderson Brower, author of First Women: The Grace & Power of America's Modern First Ladies, told VOA. \\"But someone should have told her that it could also be read that she doesn't care about the children, which is clearly not the case.\\"\\nFashion bloggers quickly identified the jacket as one selling for $39 by Zara, a fast fashion global retailer.\\nIt was a relatively humble selection by Trump, a former Paris runway model who is frequently clad for public appearances in haute couture dresses and coats.\\nStephanie Grisham probably believes that:\\n\\nA. Melania does not care about fashion.\\n\\nB. not enough information\\n\\nC. It's a jacket. There were no hidden messages.\\n\\nD. Melania does not care about the children.","target":"C","rationale":"Grisham's quote is \\"It's a jacket. There was no hidden message.\\" This suggests that Grisham believes there are no secret messages contained in the jacket, so A and D can be eliminated as incorrect answers because they suggest she does believe there is some kind of message. B cannot be chosen because it lacks specificity; leaving only C as the correct answer choice.."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage which has extra information available on certain terms mentioned in it, i.e., the proper nouns in the passage. Your job is to determine whether information from more than one term is needed to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: Did Barry Town win more games than it lost the year Carter made his debut? Passage:Carter started his career as an apprentice at Brighton & Hove Albion but failed to make the grade for the first team. He made his first team debut in April 1987 in a 1‚Äì1 draw with Blackburn Rovers, coming on as a substitute and almost scoring with his first touch. He subsequently dropped down to the Isthmian League where he spent a season with Billericay Town. He was signed by Fourth Division side Leyton Orient in July 1988 and remained a first team regular in his seven-year spell at the club, which included promotion to the Third Division in his first season with via the play-offs. In June 1995, he joined newly relegated Second Division side Peterborough United for a fee of ¬£25,000. He was a first team regular in his first season with the club but dropped out of the side in his second season as the club narrowly avoided relegation twice. Following his release he spent time on trial at Cambridge United and Wycombe Wanderers, however, both were unsuccessful in earning a full-time contract. He subsequently signed for Welsh Premier League side Barry Town, where he spent two seasons and made a total of sixty league appearances, scoring ten goals. He later joined Southern League Premier side Merthyr Tydfil in 1999 and spent six seasons with the club making over 200 appearances. He was also the club captain. In the summer of 2005 he signed for newly promoted Welsh Premier League side Cardiff Grange Harlequins but only made eight league appearances and the side couldn't avoid relegation at the first attempt.","target":"b","rationale":"The question only asks about Barry Town, which is mentioned directly in the passage as \\"He subsequently signed for Welsh Premier League side Barry Town, where he spent two seasons and made a total of sixty league appearances, scoring ten goals.\\" No other information or proper nouns are needed to answer the question."},{"source":"You are given a question title. You need to classify it into one of the 10 topics: 0 - 'Society & Culture', 1 - 'Science & Mathematics', 2 - 'Health', 3 - 'Education & Reference', 4 - 'Computers & Internet', 5 - 'Sports', 6 - 'Business & Finance', 7 - 'Entertainment & Music', 8 - 'Family & Relationships', 9 - 'Politics & Government'.\\n\\nif a plane was on some type of treadmill that detects speed, will it ever take off?","target":"1","rationale":"This question concerns a hypothetical situation in which a plane is on some type of treadmill that detects speed, and asks whether this plane will ever take off. The question requires an understanding of the principles underlying flight, which would fall under the broad topic of 'Science & Mathematics'. Therefore, this question is classified as topic 1 - 'Science & Mathematics'."},{"source":"Solve -15951 = -933*d + 19503 for d.. What is the answer??","target":"38","rationale":"To solve for d, we need to isolate the variable on one side of the equation. We can do that by adding 933d to both sides:\\n\\n-15951 + 933*d = 19503\\n\\n This simplifies to (don't forget about combining like terms): \\n932*d = 34654 or, dividing both sides by 932:  \\nD=37.4\\n\\n Therefore, the solution for D is 37.4 .\\n\\n You should always round your answer up if it's a decimal number greater than 0 but less than 1 and you are asked about an integer value! That would mean in this case that our final answer is 38 !\\n\\n */"},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to concatenate all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, and print the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n2, 6, ['C', 'C', 'M', 'J', '2091', 'p', 'b', 'B']","target":"CMJ2091p","rationale":"Given the list ['C', 'C', 'M', 'J', '2091', 'p', 'b', 'B'], we need to concatenate all the elements from the 2nd element to the 6th element.\\\\n1. The 2nd element is C.\\\\n2. The 3rd element is M.\\\\n3. The 4th element is J\\\\n4. The 5th element is 2091, which will be converted into a string during concatenation with other elements in the list, so it will not be added as a number and will be represented as string \\"2091\\".\\\\n5. The 6th element is p\\n\\nThe final result would be \\"CMJ2091p\\"."},{"source":"In mathematics, the absolute value of a number is the non-negative value of that number, without regarding its sign. For example, the absolute value of -2 is 2, and the absolute value of 5 is 5. In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element. The absolute value for negative numbers can be found by multiplying them by -1. After finding the element with the maximum absolute value you should return the value of that element before you applied the absolute value.\\n\\n[ 15.063  14.644 -32.719  79.56   42.044  54.445  75.116 -41.519  17.234]","target":"79.56","rationale":"The element with the highest absolute value in the given list is 79.56, which has an absolute value of 79.56. The absolute value of all other numbers in the list is less than or equal to 79.56. However, we need to return the value of the element before applying the absolute value, so the answer is 79.56."},{"source":"In this task, you need to reverse all words of a given length in the sentence. The number of letters in a word determine its length. For example, the length of the word \\"apple\\" is 5.\\n\\nSentence: 'a plate of food and a carton of milk'. Reverse all words of length '3' in the given sentence.","target":"a plate of food dna a carton of milk","rationale":"Given the sentence 'a plate of food and a carton of milk'. The only word with 3 letters is 'and'. After reversing the word, we get 'dna' instead. Therefore, the final sentence becomes 'a plate of food dna a carton of milk'."},{"source":"Given a prompt and two completions from a language model, select the completion that is the least toxic with respect to continuing the prompt. Toxicity is defined as a rude, disrespectful, or unreasonable statement that is likely to make you leave a discussion. Generate either Completion A or Completion B.\\n\\nPrompt: What if weekend services are not \\"The Game\\", but preparation for \\"The \\nCompletion A: Game\\"\\" then they are irrelevant.  If people don't want the weekend services then they can not get them.  You don't have to believe \\nCompletion B: Game\\"? If the next season of \\"The Game\\" is a season of training in preparation for \\"The Game\\"? If they train in the off","target":"Completion B","rationale":"Completion A contains rude, disrespectful and unreasonable language. The statement \\"you don't have to believe\\" could be interpreted as the author trying to force their beliefs on others. Completion B is less toxic because it contains no such language and it also follows a coherent structure in comparison to completion A"},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: Daniel travelled to the bathroom. Sandra moved to the kitchen. Mary moved to the bedroom. Mary journeyed to the garden. Mary moved to the hallway. Sandra went back to the hallway. Question: Where is Sandra?","target":"hallway","rationale":"We can infer from the facts in the passage that Sandra was last seen in the hallway because she went back to the hallway."},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\nFinnish metal products company Componenta Oyj net profit went slightly down to 25.1 mln euro ( $ 40.2 mln ) for the first half of 2008 from 25.4 mln euro ( $ 40.7 mln ) for the same period of 2007 .","target":"negative","rationale":"This financial news states that the net profit of Finnish metal products company Componenta Oyj has decreased from 25.4 million euros to 25.1 million euros for the first half of 2008 as compared to the same period of 2007. This indicates a decline in profits for the company, which is generally considered as a negative development. So, this financial news can be classified as \\"negative\\".\\n;"},{"source":"Combine facts and answer this: Are Craig Melville and Miguel Contreras Torres both directors?","target":"Australian television comedy director","rationale":"Craig Melville is an Australian television comedy director. \\nMiguel Contreras Torres was a Mexican film director, screenwriter and producer."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and question which can be answered using the sentence. Your task is to answer the question using the information from the sentence. The answer to the question is unique and it is a continuous text span from the sentence.\\n\\nSentence: In November 1982 the Ministry of Education adopted a new authorization criterion , the so-called \`\` Neighboring Country Clause '' : Textbooks ought to show understanding and seek international harmony in their treatment of modern and contemporary historical events involving neighboring Asian countries . \\n Question: what would  show something?","target":"Textbooks","rationale":"The sentence states that \\"textbooks ought to show understanding...\\". Therefore, the answer is \\"Textbooks\\""},{"source":"Determine if the sentence is true based on the text below. Choose from options.\\nBush pushed the issue to federal courts.\\n\\nThat request is at odds with the law signed early yesterday, by Bush, directing the federal courts to consider the case de novo without taking into account the state court's findings.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The first sentence describes that Bush pushed the issue to federal courts. The second sentence states that this is at odds with the law signed by Bush, but it also mentions how he did so in an early yesterday event. This can be inferred from \\"early\\" and \\"yesterday\\". Hence, we know that the statement is true as per text provided above."},{"source":"Pick the option in line with common sense to answer the question.\\nQuestion: what does someone getting in shape want to achieve?\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. exercise\\n\\nB. loss of muscle\\n\\nC. losing weight\\n\\nD. good health\\n\\nE. sweat","target":"D","rationale":"The options are \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\" and ‚ÄúE‚Äù.\\nGetting in shape means being physically fit, healthy, or able to do something well. A person who wants to get in shape will want the best of health possible for themselves. This makes option D - good health - the answer that aligns most closely with common sense and can be selected as a result"},{"source":"Solve this math problem\\n\\nSolve 28 = s + 25 for s.","target":"3","rationale":"Solve 28 = s + 25 for s.\\n28 -25=s+25-25\\n3=s"},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is \\"Thomson had been dead for five years.\\" true if \\"Thomson visited Cooper's grave in 1765. At that date he had been dead for five years.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"Thomson seems to have visited Cooper's grave in 1765, but Thomson himself had died 5 years before that time (i.e., he was dead for four years). So this statement is not true."},{"source":"Choose your reply from the options at the end. Does \\"In France he used the French versions of his given names, and after receiving French citizenship in 1835, he travelled on a French passport.\\" contain the correct answer to \\"In what year did Chopin become a French citizen?\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The passage claims that Chopin received French citizenship in 1835, and this is the correct answer to the question. So, the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"Write down the solution for this math problem: Solve -2*y - 6*y = 40 for y.","target":"-5","rationale":"We want to isolate y on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] -2*y - 6*y = 40  # combine like terms: 2y + (-6)y = 40 => (-4) * y = 40\\n[STEP 2] 4 * |-5| <----- multiply both sides by scalars (negative/positive): 4(-5) + 10=40, so positive answer for p is 5, negative answer for n is also 5 and then write out as |-n| in case this shows up later again in answers..."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is potentially offensive to anyone (i.e., a subset of people, any particular person, etc.), 2) no, otherwise. Note that potentially offensive posts can contain sexual, racial, religious biased or offensive language. Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\nI hate when people ask if I shoot up!! I don't need that pussy shit to be bigger than you unswole niggas&#128075;","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given post is potentially offensive to some people as it contains a racial slur and objectifying language towards women. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Read this and answer the question\\n\\nUranium's average concentration in the Earth's crust is (depending on the reference) 2 to 4 parts per million, or about 40 times as abundant as silver. The Earth's crust from the surface to 25 km (15 mi) down is calculated to contain 1017 kg (2√ó1017 lb) of uranium while the oceans may contain 1013 kg (2√ó1013 lb). The concentration of uranium in soil ranges from 0.7 to 11 parts per million (up to 15 parts per million in farmland soil due to use of phosphate fertilizers), and its concentration in sea water is 3 parts per billion.\\n\\nHow many times more abundant than silver is uranium in the Earth's crust?","target":"40","rationale":"The context mentions that the average concentration of Uranium in the Earth's crust is 2 to 4 parts per million. Since it also states \\"or about 40 times as abundant as silver\\", we can conclude that Uranium is around 40 times more abundant than Silver on an average basis, which makes \\"40\\" the correct answer to this question.\\""},{"source":"If The penalties are accounted for as a custodial activity., can we conclude that \\"A penality is listed as a custodial activity.\\"?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The evidence supports the conclusion as it states that penalties are accounted for under custodial activities. So, both statements have similar meanings and hence \\"yes\\" is the correct answer."},{"source":"The drive up to Rick's place in the hills always made me sick. Just after he bought the house with his ill gotten gains from his band's over-hyped, over-marketed, and over-bought sophomore Disc, he drove me out to see it in his beautiful but nauseating '70 Datsun 240 Z. All the smog combined with the pinball effects of winding up the hill at teeth-numbing speeds had me puking for an hour after we got there.\\nI took the last turn at the top of the hill and watched the rising sun crest over the black blocks of the city, her angel wings soiled and cheapened with the soot of 12 million get-away drivers. Rick's house came into view out of the fog, its large glass panes sparkling like the last clean surface of an oversized ashtray.\\nI parked between a blue hatchback and Rick's favorite toy: a 350 horsepower Impreza he had smuggled here from Japan. All his more expensive rides were in the garage, collecting dust and gaining vintage resale value.\\nI rang the bell. I waited and watched a couple of squirrels fight over a small treasure in the bushes. The door opened.\\n\\"Dingo.\\"\\n\\"Hey, Luna.\\"\\nHer job as Rick's assistant was to take care of his place while he was out being a rock star. She made sure all his bills were paid, his animals were fed, and that the subsequent fallout from any parties she might have in his absence didn't leave any lasting damage.\\nShe was pretty by most standards, gorgeous by others. Short with a tight schoolgirl body and raven hair that teased her avian shoulders. But by whatever standard, her beauty was like a rare and exotic bird she kept caged behind the bars of her perfect teeth. As soon as she opened her mouth it flew away.\\nAccording to the above context, choose the correct option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: Dingo thinks that:\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. It would be nice to go see Luna.\\n\\nB. The speed Dingo drives up the hill makes him enjoy the ride even more\\n\\nC. Going to Rick's house is a pain\\n\\nD. not enough information","target":"C","rationale":"Here is the rationale for why C is the answer: \\"The drive up to Rick's place in the hills always made me sick. Just after he bought the house with his ill gotten gains from his band's over-hyped, over-marketed, and over-bought sophomore Disc, he drove me out to see it in his beautiful but nauseating '70 Datsun 240 Z.\\""},{"source":"(CNN) -- Two advocacy groups filed a federal complaint Tuesday alleging a North Carolina school district's treatment of three Latino families was discriminatory because it did not provide important information in Spanish. The Southern Poverty Law Center and Advocates for Children's Services, a project of Legal Aid of North Carolina, filed the complaint with the U.S. Department of Justice's Office for Civil Rights. They say that in the cases of three students and their Spanish-speaking parents, the Wake County Public School System failed to provide documents about the students' suspensions in Spanish. That meant the parents, who speak limited English, were unable to ask questions or even appeal the suspensions, which discriminated against them on the basis of national origin and violated their civil rights, the groups say.\\n@highlight\\nComplaint filed against school district in Wake County, North Carolina\\n@highlight\\nThey say the district gave English forms to Spanish-speaking families\\n@highlight\\nThey filed a complaint with the U.S. Department of Education\\n@highlight\\nThe district says it has Spanish forms and outreach programs\\nThe school's information about his suspension was in @placeholder, so the student's mother didn't know she could appeal, the groups said.\\n\\nPick one option, \\"@placeholder\\" refers to:\\n- Advocates for Children's Services\\n- CNN\\n- Complaint\\n- Department of Education\\n- Department of Justice\\n- English\\n- Latino\\n- North Carolina\\n- Office for Civil Rights\\n- Southern Poverty Law Center\\n- Spanish\\n- U.S.\\n- Wake County\\n- Wake County Public School System","target":"English","rationale":"The context states that the school district provided documents about students' suspensions only in English. This meant parents who speak limited English were unable to ask questions or even appeal their children's suspension, which was discriminatory because it violated their civil rights and denied them equal opportunity based on national origin.\\nSo, \\"@placeholder\\" refers to \\"English\\".\\n\\n\\n\`;"},{"source":"A friend asked me to answer this question: What state is Milo murdered in?, using the article: Grant, Biscuit, and Milo are punks living in Queens. Bored with their lives, they decide to move to Los Angeles, and set out on a cross-country drive. In Utah they assist Elvis impersonator \\"Daredelvis\\" with getting his trailer unstuck. Later, Grant sees a mirage of a cowboy on horseback. While camping in the Arizona desert they are attacked by a gang of vicious rednecks, and Milo is murdered by their leader, Missoula. Grant and Biscuit escape and collapse in the desert, where Grant again sees a vision of the cowboy.\\nThe local sheriffs do not believe the boys' story, having no record of Missoula or his gang and being unable to find Milo's body as evidence of the murder. Grant resolves to track down the gang and avenge Milo's death, despite Biscuit's reservations. Heading back into Utah, they find one of the gang's trucks overturned and several of the members dead. Before dying, one of them reveals that they planned to turn themselves in but were killed by Missoula, who is headed north through Wyoming to Montana. The boys also meet Jessie, a young woman who runs a gas station and towing business.\\nCatching up to Missoula's truck, Grant and Biscuit engage in a high-speed shootout with Missoula and his buddy Blix, but swerve off the road and crash. They are rescued by Jessie, who teaches Grant how to shoot and ride a horse and strikes up a romance with him. Meanwhile, Biscuit has a dream in which he is part of a Native American tribe who are slaughtered by Union Army soldiers led by Missoula. Upon awakening, he begins to imitate a Native American warrior and insists on resuming the pursuit. Jesse outfits the pair in exaggerated western costumes and gives them use of a beat-up 1959 Buick Invicta complete with bull's horns mounted to the hood., what would be the answer ?","target":"Arizona","rationale":"Milo was murdered in Arizona, as stated on the third paragraph of the article."},{"source":"Use a disfluent question or a proper question and find the answer to the question based on the given context or return None if an answer can't be found. A disfluent question is a question that has some interruptions in it while framing. A proper question is the correct form of the question without any disfluency.\\n\\nproper question: When did Pachauri resign as chair of the IPCC? \\n disfluent question: How did or no make that what did Pachauri resign as chair of the IPCC? \\n context: Korean economist Hoesung Lee is the chair of the IPCC since October 8, 2015, following the election of the new IPCC Bureau. Before this election, the IPCC was led by his vice-Chair Ismail El Gizouli, who was designated acting Chair after the resignation of Rajendra K. Pachauri in February 2015. The previous chairs were Rajendra K. Pachauri, elected in May 2002; Robert Watson in 1997; and Bert Bolin in 1988. The chair is assisted by an elected bureau including vice-chairs, working group co-chairs, and a secretariat.","target":"February 2015","rationale":"The context mentions that Pachauri resigned in February 2015. The disfluent question can be corrected to \\"When did Pachauri resign as chair of the IPCC?\\" and the answer would be \\"February 2015\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an adjunct island or as an incorrect representation. A correct representation should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an adjunct island will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence using an adjunct island. An incorrect representation will be everything else.\\n\\nWho was Barbara worrying Samuel without escaping from?","target":"bad","rationale":"The sentence is ungrammatical, and the reason for this ungrammaticality is that the preposition \\"from\\" is stranded in an adjunct island. The answer to this question should be \\"bad\\"."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to whether they are trash or treasure is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Items marked as \\"trash\\" are considered to not have value and can be disposed, whereas those marked as \\"treasure\\" are considered valuable items that must be retained. \\"A : \\"B relates item A to whether it is trash or treasure, as specified by B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with either \`trash\` or \`treasure\` for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\ncup : treasure. mold : ?","target":"trash","rationale":"While both cups and mold can be found in trash, mold is more likely to be associated with the trash category."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence from the research paper and your task is to classify the given sentence into the following categories: Background (Why is this problem important? What relevant works have been created before? What is still missing in the previous works? What are the high-level research questions? How might this help other research or researchers?), Purpose (What specific things do the researchers want to do? What specific knowledge do the researchers want to gain? What specific hypothesis do the researchers want to test?), Method (How did the researchers do the work or find what they sought? What are the procedures and steps of the research?), or Finding (What did the researchers find out? Did the proposed methods work? Did the thing behave as the researchers expected?). \\n\\nIn this review , we summarize recent progress in TCHM-based antiviral research in China and other Asian countries.","target":"purpose","rationale":"The sentence describes the purpose of a review article, which is to summarize recent progress in antiviral research based on traditional Chinese herbal medicine (TCHM) by researchers from China and other Asian countries. Therefore, it belongs to the category \\"purpose\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue between a user and an assistant, where users and assistants converse about geographic topics like geopolitical entities and locations. The task here is to find if the dialogue is by the user or assistant. Classify your answers into user and assistant.\\n\\nWhat kind of history does this city have?","target":"user","rationale":"The user is asking a question to the assistant, and hence, it is by the user."},{"source":"Give me a possible correct answer to the question \\"who do pagans believe is god?\\"","target":"Odin","rationale":"There are many different gods worshiped by pagans so \\"who do pagans believe is god?\\" can't be answered with a single name. Some of the most well-known pagan gods include Odin, Zeus and Thor."},{"source":"U.S. House Speaker Paul Ryan and Senator Lindsey Graham have joined a growing chorus of Republican leaders to disavow comments by presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump about the Mexican heritage of a judge in a class-action lawsuit against Trump University.\\nQuestioned Tuesday about Trump's comments, Ryan said \\"I regret those comments he made. Claiming a person can't do their job because of their race is sort of like the textbook definition of racism.\\" But he did not retract his endorsement of Trump, made last week, and he said he does not believe Democratic challenger Hillary Clinton is \\"the answer.\\"\\nRyan made his comments during an appearance at a women's shelter in Washington, D.C.\\nIn a New York Times interview, Graham, also a former presidential candidate, said Trump's remarks were \\"the most un-American thing from a politician since Joe McCarthy,\\" referring to the ultra-conservative senator of the 1950s who fueled fears of widespread communist subversion in the United States.\\nGraham also suggested that Republicans who have endorsed Trump reconsider their choice. \\"If anybody was looking for an off-ramp, this is probably it,\\" he said.\\nThe backlash appears to be mounting against the candidate, who has repeatedly said he believes U.S. District Court Judge Gonzalo Curiel, because of his \\"Mexican heritage,\\" would not rule fairly in the case charging Trump with fraud. Curiel is an American who was born and raised in the Midwestern U.S. state of Indiana.\\nU.S. Senator Ben Sasse, a Republican from Nebraska who has criticized Trump on multiple occasions during the campaign, tweeted: \\"Saying someone can't do a specific job because of his or her race is the literal definition of 'racism.'''\\nSasse was joined Monday by two former rivals for the Republican nomination. Ohio Governor John Kasich tweeted that Trump's offensive \\"is flat out wrong.'' Trump, Kasich wrote, should \\"apologize to Judge Curiel & try to unite this country.''\\nQuestion: Who made comments while at a women's shelter about Trump's remarks regarding the Mexican heritage of a judge?\\n===\\nThe answer to the above question is","target":"Ryan","rationale":"We can see that Ryan is the speaker for both of the following:\\n- \\"I regret those comments he made. Claiming a person can't do their job because of their race is sort of like the textbook definition of racism.\\" \\nAnd,\\n- \\"Ryan made his comments during an appearance at a women's shelter in Washington DC\\"\\nSo we know it was Ryan who made these remarks while at a woman's shelter about Trump's remarks regarding Curiel."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: My Favorite Sweater\\nMy favorite sweater grew too small.\\nI loved that sweater best of all.\\nMy grandma made it when I was three.\\nShe made that sweater just for me.\\nI picked the yarn , a special blue.\\nThe color of bluebells .wet with dew .\\nWhen I was three I was very small,\\nBut now I'm five and much too tall.\\nI have a new jacket now that's green,\\nSo I gave my sweater to our cat Queen.\\nQueen just had babies out in the shed .\\nMy favorite sweater is now in their bed.\\nQuestion: What is the most likely reason that the writer likes the sweater?\\nOptions: A: The girl's grandma made it.\\nB: The girl got it at the age of three.\\nC: The yarn is the color of bluebells.\\nD: The mother cat uses it for the babies now.","target":"A","rationale":"The context mentions that the girl's grandma made her favorite sweater when she was three years old. In addition, it says: I loved that sweater best of all and It is now in their bed [the kittens' bed], suggesting that the grandmother knit a very special gift for the child which still holds sentimental value even though she has outgrown it.\\nBased on this, A is most likely to be correct answer because sentimentality suggests an emotional attachment more than any other reason given in options B-D."},{"source":"How to keep it from clumping? Mix in a teaspoon of laundry starch for each cup.\\nDoes this phrase make sense?","target":"No","rationale":"The phrase \\"How to keep it from clumping? Mix in a teaspoon of laundry starch for each cup.\\" does not make sense because the context suggests that you would mix something into water, resulting in a liquid. However, laundry starch is used to stiffen fabrics such as clothes and uniforms. It will be difficult or impossible to mix some amount of powdered laundry starch with an equal quantity by volume of water without first dissolving the powder in water.\\nSo the answer is No"},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the gain. Gain is the value by which to multiply the input. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: martin bought 10 concert tickets , some at the full price of $ 2.00 per ticket , and some at a discounted price of $ 1.60 per ticket . if he spent a total of $ 18.80 , how many discounted tickets did he buy ? \\nOptions: a ) 3 , b ) 4 , c ) 5 , d ) 6 , e ) 7","target":"a","rationale":"Let \\\\(x\\\\) be the number of discounted tickets bought. After purchasing \\\\(x\\\\) discounted tickets, Martin had to spend another $11.80 on full price tickets to get his total up to $18.80:\\n\\\\(18.8 = 1.6x + 2(10 - x)\\\\)\\nSimplifying this, we get that\\n\\\\(18.8 = 1.6x + 20 - 2x\\\\) \\nor \\\\(2x = 8\\\\), so \\\\(x=4\\\\). Therefore, the answer is (A)."},{"source":"The more carbon atoms a hydrocarbon has, the greater the number of isomers.\\n\\nA hydrocarbon with more carbon atoms will have fewer or many isomers?","target":"many","rationale":"Carbon atoms have four valence electrons and can form single, double or triple bonds. By varying the number of carbon atoms in a hydrocarbon, it is possible to create many different configurations with unique properties and structures that qualify as isomers. Therefore, 'many' will be the correct answer for this question."},{"source":"In this task, you need to provide the correct option for a given problem from the provided options.\\n\\nProblem: at the faculty of aerospace engineering , 310 students study random - processing methods , 232 students study scramjet rocket engines and 112 students study them both . if every student in the faculty has to study one of the two subjects , how many students are there in the faculty of aerospace engineering ? \\nOptions: a ) 430 , b ) 432 , c ) 440 , d ) 442 , e ) 446","target":"a","rationale":"The solution of this problem can be achieved by using Venn diagram method.\\\\nUsing the information provided in the question, we can draw a Venn diagram as follows:\\\\nGiven, 310 students study random-processing methods and 232 students study scramjet rocket engines. Let us assume that there are x number of students who study only one of the two subjects.\\\\nNow, 310 + 232 - (310 & 232) = 542 - 112 = 430\\\\nSo, 430 is the correct choice for this problem"},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is the next sentence syntactically and semantically acceptable?\\n\\nBill coughed his way out of the restaurant.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence is syntactically and semantically acceptable."},{"source":"Answer based on context:\\n\\nEstonia has around 600,000 employees, yet the country has a shortage of skilled labor, and since skill shortages are experienced everywhere in Europe, the government has increased working visa quota for non-EEA citizens, although it has nevertheless been criticized for being inadequate for addressing the shortages. The late-2000s recession in the world, the near-concurrent local property bust with changes in Estonian legislation to increase labour market flexibility  saw Estonia's unemployment rate shoot up to 18.8% throughout the duration of the crisis, then stabilise to 13.8% by summer 2011, as the economy recovered on the basis of strong exports. Internal consumption, and therefore imports, plummeted; and cuts were made in public finances. Some of the reduction in unemployment has been attributed to some Estonians' emigrating for employment to Finland, the UK, Australia, and elsewhere. After the recession, the unemployment rate went lower, and throughout 2015 and 2016, the rate stayed near the levels that preceded the economic downturn, staying at just above 6%.\\n\\nWas the unemployment rate in Estonia higher in summer 2011 or in 2015?","target":"summer 2011","rationale":"To answer the question of whether the unemployment rate in Estonia was higher in summer 2011 or 2015, we need to compare two numbers that represent each given year. In article it is said that there were a 13.8% unemployment rate in summer 2011 and just above 6% throughout 2015 and 2016; these are clearly lower than 18.8%. Therefore, we could conclude that the unemployment rate was highest during sumer 2011"},{"source":"Gun laws in Missouri -- In September 2016, another Senate bill coincidentally numbered SB 656 was passed allowing permitless concealed carry by anyone 19 years of age or older who may lawfully own a gun. This bill was also vetoed by Governor Nixon, on June 27, 2016. After the Missouri legislature reconvened for the veto-override session on September 14, 2016, the Senate voted to override the veto with a 24 -- 6 vote (23 required) and the House followed through shortly thereafter with a 112 -- 41 vote (109 required). The permitless carry provision of the bill went into effect on January 1, 2017. \\n\\nHaving read that, I wonder do you need a license to carry a concealed weapon in missouri?","target":"No","rationale":"The bill was passed in September 2016 and went into effect on January 1, 2017. Since it is already 2018, the answer must be No because you do not need a license to carry a concealed weapon in Missouri"},{"source":"In this task, you're given an open-domain question. Your task is to provide an answer to the given question. There is only one unique answer for each question. Your answer should be short, and refer to an entity, date, number, etc. Do not put your answer in the context of a sentence.\\n\\nWhat do you call someone from cape breton?","target":"Cape Bretoner","rationale":"The answer is \\"Cape Bretoner\\"."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the small-talk strategy, otherwise output No. small-talk is a cooperative negotiation strategy. It is used for discussing topics apart from the negotiation, in an attempt to build a rapport with the opponent. For example, discussing how the opponent is doing during the pandemic or sharing excitement for the camping trip.\\n\\nContext: 'Ok I'm sure we can work it out because I know I need extra water and firewood. Do you have any ideas on how to divvy up the extra supplies?' 'I would need some firewood as well, as I need it to cook the food. I was thinking maybe you can have all the water and I have all the food.' 'All the food is too much, I would need at least one package of the food for my group. I was thinking you could have 2 of the food packages and I have 1, then I get all the water and the majority of the firewood. That leaves you with 2 of the high priority food packages and a package of firewood to cook the food.'\\nUtterance: 'That seems quite unfair. I really would like my camping trip to be enjoyable.'","target":"No","rationale":"The speaker's statement does not include any information about the opponent and is not an attempt to build a rapport with them. The statement \\"That seems quite unfair\\" is part of the negotiation and not small-talk between the participants, so the answer is No."},{"source":"Here is a question about this article: Washington University spent its first half century in downtown St. Louis bounded by Washington Ave., Lucas Place, and Locust Street. By the 1890s, owing to the dramatic expansion of the Manual School and a new benefactor in Robert Brookings, the University began to move west. The University Board of Directors began a process to find suitable ground and hired the landscape architecture firm Olmsted, Olmsted & Eliot of Boston. A committee of Robert S. Brookings, Henry Ware Eliot, and William Huse found a site of 103 acres (41.7 ha) just beyond Forest Park, located west of the city limits in St. Louis County. The elevation of the land was thought to resemble the Acropolis and inspired the nickname of \\"Hilltop\\" campus, renamed the Danforth campus in 2006 to honor former chancellor William H. Danforth.\\nWhat is the answer to this question: Where was Washington University located during the first half of the 1800's.","target":"downtown St. Louis","rationale":"The first half of the 1800s is considered to be between 1801 and 1850. The context states that Washington University was located in downtown St. Louis bounded by Washington Ave., Lucas Place, and Locust Street during this time period. Thus, the correct answer to this question would be \\"downtown St. Louis\\""},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a sentence, and you should determine whether it is overruling or non-overruling. In law, an overruling sentence is a statement that nullifies a previous case decision as a precedent by a constitutionally valid statute or a decision by the same or higher ranking court which establishes a different rule on the point of law involved. Classify your answers into overruling or non-overruling\\n\\nthree courts of appeals have reached the opposite conclusion on similar facts.","target":"overruling","rationale":"The sentence states that three courts of appeals have made decisions contrary to the point of law involved. This implies that the court is overruling these decisions by establishing a different rule in this case."},{"source":"Here is a question about this article: Arsenal's tally of 13 League Championships is the third highest in English football, after Manchester United (20) and Liverpool (18), and they were the first club to reach 8 League Championships. They hold the highest number of FA Cup trophies, 12. The club is one of only six clubs to have won the FA Cup twice in succession, in 2002 and 2003, and 2014 and 2015. Arsenal have achieved three League and FA Cup \\"Doubles\\" (in 1971, 1998 and 2002), a feat only previously achieved by Manchester United (in 1994, 1996 and 1999). They were the first side in English football to complete the FA Cup and League Cup double, in 1993. Arsenal were also the first London club to reach the final of the UEFA Champions League, in 2006, losing the final 2‚Äì1 to Barcelona.\\nWhat is the answer to this question: In what competition was Arsenal the first to enter the finals?","target":"UEFA Champions League","rationale":"The article clearly states that Arsenal was the first London club to reach UEFA Champions League final in 2006. Hence, it is a valid answer choice for this question."},{"source":"Given a prompt and two completions from a language model, select the completion that has the most similar style to the prompt. Style is defined as the tone, word choice, grammar, and sentence structure throughout the prompt-completion pair. If a prompt is colloquial, then the completion should also be colloquial, as opposed to a completion that is encyclopedic or overly formal. Generate either Completion A or Completion B.\\n\\nPrompt: Bitch, I fucking hope you do. You'll be a dead \\nCompletion A: ringer for her in years to come. That's one more thing you won't be able to hide. You know it.\\"   \\"Oh \\nCompletion B: line guiIconDesk.\\")   CrashSession 14/10  Lay, say 2 shops from where they believe Landraele has home o","target":"Completion A","rationale":"The prompt is informal and colloquial, so the correct completion must also be informal and colloquial. Completion A is a good choice because it matches the style of the prompt in terms of tone, word choice, grammar and sentence structure."},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an answer to a question about when an event happened. For example, \\"going to school\\" usually happens during the day (not at 2 A.M). Note that a lot of the questions could have more than one correct answer. We only need a single most-likely answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: Tommy and Suzy (brother and sister) went to the playground one afternoon with their mom and dad, Jan and Dean. \\nQuestion: What time did they leave the playground?","target":"4:00 PM","rationale":"The family left the playground in the afternoon, and since there is no exact time indicated in the sentence, we can assume that they left at 4:00 PM."},{"source":"What is the solution?\\n\\nSolve 43*c = 113 - 1059 for c.","target":"-22","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable c on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] 43*c = 113 - 1059\\n[STEP 2] 43*c + 1059 = 113\\n[STEP 3] -1046 = 43*c  <-- since c is negative, we flip sign from equal to less than or greater than symbol. This step also shows that this math problem requires us to do so in order for our answer to be correct and complete. If not flipped, then 13 will be considered as a solution when it is incomplete by leaving out two solutions (-22 and 23). Some teachers want you avoid flipping signs unless there are fractions (e.g., NO: x-2=8 --> YES :x+2=-8) because they believe"},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: How did executives negatively characterize the religious undertones of Jesus Walks?\\nContext: The College Dropout was eventually issued by Roc-A-Fella in February 2004, shooting to number two on the Billboard 200 as his debut single, \\"Through the Wire\\" peaked at number fifteen on the Billboard Hot 100 chart for five weeks. \\"Slow Jamz\\", his second single featuring Twista and Jamie Foxx, became an even bigger success: it became the three musicians' first number one hit. The College Dropout received near-universal critical acclaim from contemporary music critics, was voted the top album of the year by two major music publications, and has consistently been ranked among the great hip-hop works and debut albums by artists. \\"Jesus Walks\\", the album's fourth single, perhaps exposed West to a wider audience; the song's subject matter concerns faith and Christianity. The song nevertheless reached the top 20 of the Billboard pop charts, despite industry executives' predictions that a song containing such blatant declarations of faith would never make it to radio. The College Dropout would eventually be certified triple platinum in the US, and garnered West 10 Grammy nominations, including Album of the Year, and Best Rap Album (which it received). During this period, West also founded GOOD Music, a record label and management company that would go on to house affiliate artists and producers, such as No I.D. and John Legend. At the time, the focal point of West's production style was the use of sped-up vocal samples from soul records. However, partly because of the acclaim of The College Dropout, such sampling had been much copied by others; with that overuse, and also because West felt he had become too dependent on the technique, he decided to find a new sound.","target":"blatant","rationale":"Question: How did executives negatively characterize the religious undertones of Jesus Walks?\\nThe answer is blatant. Blatant means ‚Äúconspicuously and offensively loud; given to vehement outcry,‚Äù or \\"without any attempt at concealment.\\" The text states that industry executives' predictions were wrong because they thought a song containing such blatant declarations of faith would never make it to radio. So the answer must be something like open, public, or bold. Here are some examples from this context where we can see these words in use: \\n- expose West to a wider audience ---> This sentence uses exposed which refers explicitly to bringing attention publicly as an exposure does (to bring into view). It's similar in meaning with displaying openly, showing plainly etc., so exposing could mean doing"},{"source":"I gave my students this multiple choice question: Which is an example of a chemical reaction?\\n\\nOnly one answer is correct among these 4 choices:\\n- Vinegar added to baking soda forms a gas.\\n- Water evaporates into air.\\n- Sugar dissolves in water.\\n- Corn kernels are crushed to form flour.\\n\\nCould you tell me which one is correct?","target":"Vinegar added to baking soda forms a gas.","rationale":"The answer is Vinegar added to baking soda forms a gas.\\nA chemical reaction takes place when two or more substances undergo changes resulting in the formation of new substance(s). In this question, \\"Vinegar\\" and \\"baking soda\\", both are chemical compounds which on combination form another compound called carbon dioxide (a gaseous state) due to a release of energy in the process. \\nThe other options given for choice do not represent any such change so they must be eliminated.\\"Water evaporates into air\\" means simply that water molecules change from liquid phase to vapor phase without forming any bonds with each other; it does not mean that there was an actual conversion taking place between H2O molecules and O2/N2/Ar etc. The same explanation holds true"},{"source":"Sentence: To swap between Super NES, Nintendo 64, and Game Cube audio/video cables.\\n\\nChoice 1: The RCA (yellow, white, red) cables on these three systems are the same.\\n\\nChoice 2: The RCA (red, blue, green) cables on these three systems are the same.\\n\\nWhat is the index of the correct choice for ending for the sentence?\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"1","rationale":"A: The RCA (yellow, white, red) cables on these three systems are the same.\\nB: The RCA (red, blue, green) cables on these three systems are the same.\\nFor choice 1 and Choice 2 above from best to worst how would you rank them?"},{"source":"What is least likely to absorb light?\\n\\nWhich is the correct answer?\\n- windows\\n- space\\n- glass\\n- foil","target":"foil","rationale":"Light is a form of electromagnetic radiation that travels in waves. It also behaves like particles called photons, which are bundles of energy with no mass or charge. Absorption occurs when light interacts with matter and transfers its energy to it. In the case of foil, this interaction happens so quickly compared to how long light takes to travel through space (i.e., \\"space\\") that you cannot see any change in color upon reflection; therefore, it appears black even though there might be some absorption if you look at it under a different wavelength from visible light‚Äîfor example, ultraviolet (UV) light used for sterilization purposes can cause chemical changes in your skin cells after prolonged exposure since UV-C rays have enough energy on their own to break molecular bonds between atoms within molecules without having absorbed another"},{"source":"Given an abstract of a paper, generate a title for this paper such that conveys the key focus of the paper.\\n\\nAbstract: Leptospirosis is a zoonotic disease that consists of fever, headache, myalgias, and multiple organ involvement, has varying clinical severity and morbidity, and can occur in epidemic form. Diagnosis is based on culture or serologic demonstration of recent infection. There is evidence that doxycycline therapy started early in the course of the disease favorably affects duration and severity. Antibiotic therapy is often initiated because of a strong suspicion of the disease, before bacteriologic or serologic confirmation of the diagnosis is completed. Public health measures play an important role in minimizing the incidence of leptospirosis.","target":"A point-source epidemic of leptospirosis. Description of cases, cause, and prevention","rationale":"The title should provide evidence for the existence of a point-source epidemic of leptospirosis, which describes cases and cause. Also, one key aspect to consider in this paper is the prevention of leptospirosis. My suggestion would be: \\"A point-source epidemic of leptospirosis. Description of cases, cause, and prevention\\"."},{"source":"Given a goal and a wrong solution, rewrite it to give a correct solution.\\nGoal: a toy \\nSolution: can entertain spiders \\nCorrected solution:","target":"can entertain animal","rationale":"The goal is to entertain animals, so the solution should be rewritten as \\"can entertain animal\\"."},{"source":"What is the question to: \\"The 217 area includes Illinois' capital , Springfield , plus Champaign , Urbana , Decatur , Danville , Quincy , and Rantoul .\\"? The topic is Area code 217.","target":"\\"what area code is 217?\\"","rationale":"The answer to the question \\"What is the question to: The 217 area includes Illinois' capital, Springfield, plus Champaign, Urbana, Decatur, Danville Quincy and Rantoul.\\" is \\"what area code is 217?\\" \\nThis is because Area Code 217 covers these cities. Therefore we can replace '217' with 'Area Codes that cover xyz'."},{"source":"Editor's note: Ken Ballen is president of Terror Free Tomorrow: The Center for Public Opinion, a nonprofit institute that researches attitudes toward extremism. Patrick Doherty is deputy director of the American Strategy Program at the New America Foundation, a think tank that promotes ideas across the ideological spectrum. Kenneth Ballen says whoever won the election, Iranians strongly favor free elections and a free press. (CNN) -- In a poll conducted three weeks before Iran's June 12 vote, our nonprofit organizations found a consensus among Iranians, including almost all of those who told us they would vote for President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad. And that consensus is that Iranians want a truly democratic system.\\n@highlight\\nBallen, Doherty: Iranians, including Ahmadinejad backers, want more democracy\\n@highlight\\nThey say their poll can't determine whether Moussavi had a late surge\\n@highlight\\nThey say government actions have shifted debate to democracy not to who won \\nIt does not predict the final vote, nor does it measure a possible surge for @placeholder, which many believe occurred in the final weeks. \\n\\nYou should decide what \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to. Choose between:\\n- Ahmadinejad\\n- American Strategy Program\\n- Ballen\\n- CNN\\n- Center for Public Opinion\\n- Doherty\\n- Iran\\n- Iranians\\n- Ken Ballen\\n- Kenneth Ballen\\n- Mahmoud Ahmadinejad\\n- Moussavi\\n- New America Foundation\\n- Patrick Doherty\\n- Terror Free Tomorrow","target":"Moussavi","rationale":"The placeholder is referring to Mir Hossein Moussavi, who was an Iranian reformist politician and the main political rival of Mahmoud Ahmadinejad during the 2009 presidential campaign.\\n\\"\\""},{"source":"Here's a problem to solve: Aluminum is an element. Which of the following best describes the smallest particle of aluminum that retains all the properties of aluminum?\\n\\nAmong the 4 following options, which is the correct answer?\\n\\n- A: a molecule\\n \\n- B: an atom\\n \\n- C: a proton\\n \\n- D: an electron","target":"B","rationale":"An atom is the smallest particle of an element that retains all the properties of that element. Aluminum is a metal which possesses metallic bonds, and this property can only be exhibited by atoms; therefore, \\"B\\" (an atom) would be the correct answer to your question: \\nAmong these four options, aluminum has no molecules or protons; instead it consists solely of Al3+ ions and electrons. These particles do not include all the physical characteristics attributed to aluminum as they are missing one component each - either an electron or proton respectively. Therefore even though there are more complex structures such as minerals made out of multiple elements whose composition exhibit specific chemical/physical attributes different from their parent components', in order for any given sample to retain its distinct identity among other samples belonging to another category on"},{"source":"Choose your reply from the options at the end. Does \\"They are currently coached by David Beaty, who was hired in 2014.\\" contain the correct answer to \\"Who is the current head of KU's football program?\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The statement does contain the correct answer to the question. So, you should choose \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"In this task you are given an anecdote. You must find out whether the anecdote is something the author has done or is considering doing. Label the instances as \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and label them as \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future.\\n\\nHonestly, \\"friend\\" is too much of a loaded term but...\\n\\nWe have a lecture class together twice a week, and for the past three weeks I've noticed a pattern with him: on Thursday he misses class, just doesn't even come in or try to come in late. Tuesday he comes in, asks me if I can share my notes with him, and he falls asleep. Occasionally, he wakes up and looks over at my laptop screen to make sure I'm taking notes. Keep in mind, we do about five minutes of review in this class and the other hour and fifteen minutes is new material that he just sleeps through. At first I was fine with helping him out, shit happens we all miss class. But at this point it's getting ridiculous and I feel like he's just using me to get information so he can skip. I wanna tell him no but I'm too nice to just say it to his face. Advice/help would be appreciated.","target":"HYPOTHETICAL","rationale":"The author writes, \\"\\"Honestly, \\"friend\\" is too much of a loaded term but...\\"\\". This suggests that the author is not yet sure whether or not to consider this person a friend. They have noticed a pattern in which this person has been missing class and asking for notes, but they are unsure as to whether or not the behavior is intentional. Therefore, this post is \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\", because the author does not know if their classmate's behavior will continue."},{"source":"Classify the given comment into 'Hope Speech' or 'Not Hope Speech'. A hope speech is defined as content that is encouraging, positive or supportive contents and talks about equality, diversity or inclusion\\n\\nayyy he got dem cuffed jeans","target":"Not Hope Speech","rationale":"The given comment is not a hope speech as it talks about none of the 3 aspects that define a hope speech. Therefore, classify this as \\\\\\"Not Hope Speech\\\\\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, a context passage, and four options which are terms from the passage. After reading a passage, you will get a brief understanding of the terms. Your job is to determine by searching and reading further information of which term you can answer the question. Indicate your choice as 'a', 'b', 'c', or 'd'. If you think more than one option is plausible, choose the more probable option to help you answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Does Manche or Marigny have a higher population? Passage:In total, around four hundred dummies were planned to be dropped as part of the operation. Titanic I simulated the drop of an airborne division north of the Seine river; near Yvetot, Yerville, Doudeville in the Seine-Maritime region and Fauville in the Eure region. Two hundred dummies and two SAS teams were parachuted in across these four Titanic I targets. Titanic II would have involved dropping fifty dummies east of the Dives River to draw German reserves onto that side of the river. However, this segment of the operation was cancelled just before 6 June. A further fifty dummies were dropped, under Titanic III, in the Calvados region near Maltot and the woods to the north of Baron-sur-Odon to draw German reserves away to the west of Caen. Finally, Titanic IV involved two hundred dummies dropped near Marigny in the Manche, as with Titanic I the intention was to simulate the dropping of an airborne division. Two SAS teams were also dropped near Saint-L√¥. This group commanded by Captain Fowles and Lieutenant Poole landed at 00:20 on 6 June 1944, 10 minutes ahead of schedule. To deceive the Germans into thinking there was a large parachute landing in progress, the SAS teams played 30 minute pre-recorded sounds of men shouting and weapons fire including mortars.\\n Links: a. Manche b. Eure c. Marigny, Manche d. Calvados (department)","target":"a","rationale":"The answer is 'a' as Manche has a higher population. To find this, one needs to go out of the passage but the given options are only terms from the passage."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to classify the sentence into one of the following five action categories - INFORM, INFORM_INTENT, OFFER, REQUEST, REQUEST_ALTS. If the sentence is about informing something, generate 'INFORM'. If it is about requesting something, generate 'REQUEST'. If the sentence mentions requesting an alternative option than the one provided, generate 'REQUEST_ALTS'. Similarly, generate 'OFFER' if the sentence is offering some information. If the sentence is about showing intent to do something, generate 'INFORM_INTENT'.\\n\\nDo you have a different song?","target":"REQUEST_ALTS","rationale":"The user's sentence is about requesting an alternative option to a song. Therefore, the output is 'REQUEST_ALTS'."},{"source":"In this task you are given a medical question pair hand-generated. Your task is to classify a given post into two categories 1) 'Similar' if the given two questions have a same connotation 2) 'Dissimilar' if the given two questions have a different connotation or meaning.\\n\\nSentence1: Have water fluid on feet and legs pretty bad, already on water pills....Have a hard time sleeping and fine it hard to walk... Should I go to the er? \\n Sentence2: I have been to ER for leg and feet swelling and they prescribed water pills. But I am unable to sleep tonight, what can I do to get some relief from discomfrt due to swelling?","target":"Dissimilar","rationale":"The first sentence asks a question about whether the patient should go to emergency room for his/her leg and feet swelling. The second sentence discusses about the prescription of water pills by emergency room for leg swelling. However, the question in second sentence is not related to the first one. So, both sentences have different connotations or meanings and hence answer is 'Dissimilar'."},{"source":"The Sol√≠s Theatre is Uruguay's oldest theatre. It was built in 1856 and is currently owned by the government of Montevideo. In 1998, the government of Montevideo started a major reconstruction of the theatre, which included two US$110,000 columns designed by Philippe Starck. The reconstruction was completed in 2004, and the theatre reopened in August of that year. The plaza is also the site of the offices of the President of Uruguay (both the Est√©vez Palace and the Executive Tower). The Artigas Mausoleum is located at the centre of the plaza. Statues include that of Jos√© Gervasio Artigas, hero of Uruguay's independence movement; an honour guard keeps vigil at the Mausoleum.\\nWhat is the paragraph about?","target":"Montevideo","rationale":"The question asks about a paragraph that describes the Sol√≠s Theatre, which is located in and owned by Montevideo. It also states that President of Uruguay's offices are at the plaza where this theatre lies. Given these reasons, it can be deduced that the paragraph is about Montevideo."},{"source":"In the Kenya-Tanzania border Kenyan grassland gradually merges into Tanzanian forest. Though they had similar soil to start with millions of years ago, today they are two different habitats. At present, Kenya has one of the largest contiguous grassland in Africa. On the other hand, Tanzania boasts one of the largest forest cover in Africa.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nWhich place would have thinner \\"A horizon\\", Kenya or Tanzania?","target":"Tanzania","rationale":"The question asks which place would have a thinner A horizon. The last sentence in this paragraph explains that Kenya has the largest contiguous grassland in Africa, and Tanzania boasts one of the largest forest cover in Africa.\\n\\nSince most forests are characterized by rich soil with thick humus-rich layers (A horizons), it can be inferred that the answer to this question is B: Tanzania"},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to the associated containers is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its associated container B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate container for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nmilk : jug. trash : ?","target":"can","rationale":"The milk is stored in a jug. Similarly, the trash is stored in a can."},{"source":"What is the title of this article:\\n\\nThe Exopterygota likely are paraphyletic in regard to the Endopterygota. Matters that have incurred controversy include Strepsiptera and Diptera grouped together as Halteria based on a reduction of one of the wing pairs ‚Äì a position not well-supported in the entomological community. The Neuropterida are often lumped or split on the whims of the taxonomist. Fleas are now thought to be closely related to boreid mecopterans. Many questions remain in the basal relationships amongst endopterygote orders, particularly the Hymenoptera.\\n\\nTitle:","target":"Insect","rationale":"From the given context, we can infer that this article is about a dispute regarding the order of insects. \\nThe title \\"Insect\\" would be best suited to describe the subject matter of this article as it will be able to attract readers who are interested in reading about controversies related to Insects and their classification."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is potentially offensive to anyone (i.e., a subset of people, any particular person, etc.), 2) no, otherwise. Note that potentially offensive posts can contain sexual, racial, religious biased or offensive language. Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\nMen socialize by insulting each other, but dont really mean it. Women socialize by complimenting each other, and they don't mean it either.","target":"No","rationale":"The given post does not contain offensive language or any kind of bias towards any group. Therefore, it is a \\"No\\"."},{"source":"High Noon is a retailer and auction consulting company. They specialize in Western American art & antique Americana, including cowboy and American Indian artifacts and fine western art. The company is known for founding the High Noon Western Americana Auction and Antique Show in 1991, held every January at the Phoenix Mesa Marriott in Mesa, Arizona.\\n\\nChoose your answer: based on the paragraph above can we conclude that \\"High Noon specializes in modern day fashions.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nI think the answer is","target":"No","rationale":"The paragraph states that High Noon specializes in Western American art and antique Americana, which includes cowboy and Indian artifacts. The information provided suggests that the company sells vintage or antiquated items rather than modern day fashions. So, the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"See the conversation. DIALOG:\\nWhat did Mike Judge try after graducating from UCSD?\\n-","target":"After graduating from UCSD in 1985, Mike Judge held several brief jobs in physics and mechanical engineering, but found himself growing bored with science.","rationale":"After graduating from UCSD in 1985, Mike Judge held several brief jobs in physics and mechanical engineering, but found himself growing bored with science. He decided to pursue a career as an animator and writer."},{"source":"The Cowboys hosted the Saints in their annual Thanksgiving Day game. The Cowboys trailed early with RB Chris Ivory getting a 3-yard TD run, followed by kicker Garrett Hartley getting a 50-yard field goal, and then by Ivory making a 6-yard TD run. The Cowboys cut the lead as kicker David Buehler got a 21-yard field goal, but the Saints replied as Hartley nailed a 45-yard field goal. The Cowboys tried to come back as Buehler hit a 53-yard field goal, followed by Miles Austin getting a 60-yard TD run. The Cowboys trailed further with Hartley making a 28-yard field goal, but took the lead with Marion Barber III and Tashard Choice getting a 1-yard TD run. They failed to maintain this lead when QB Drew Brees completed a 12-yard TD pass to WR Lance Moore.\\nAnswer this question: WHY SAINTS REPLIED AS HARTLEY NAILED 45-YARD FIELD GOAL","target":"21-yard","rationale":"The Cowboys cut down the lead to 1 point after David Buehler got a 21-yard field goal. That's why Saints replied as Hartley nailed 45-yard field goal."},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is the next sentence syntactically and semantically acceptable?\\n\\nThe company in which they have invested left.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence is grammatically acceptable. The subject-verb agreement, tense and structure are all correct."},{"source":"The task is to generate text based of an event. For the given event, there will be a person who does the action in the event (usually PersonX). Your task is to write that persons emotional reaction to the event, i.e. how that person feels after doing the action.\\n\\nPersonX eats PersonX's vegetables","target":"healthy","rationale":"PersonX is eating their vegetables which implies that they are conscious of their health and are taking steps to ensure it. Therefore, the emotion of PersonX would be \\\\\\"healthy\\\\\\"."},{"source":"Given a passage with a question and an answer to that question, classify if the answer actually answers the question into 'yes' or 'no'. Output 'yes' if the answer answers the question and output 'no' if the answer does not answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Does hIV Tat protein affect circadian rhythmicity by interfering with the circadian system?\\nAnswer: The HIV Tat protein affects circadian rhythmicity by interfering with the circadian system in patients with HIV/AIDS and further increases the melatonin excretion value. A Tat protein-related high melatonin value may counteract HIV-related poor sleep quality during the progression of HIV infection. This study provides the first clinical evidence offering an explanation for why sleep quality did not show an association with progression of HIV infection in previous studies.","target":"yes","rationale":"The passage states that the HIV Tat protein affects circadian rhythmicity by interfering with the circadian system. This information directly answers the question. Therefore, the output is 'yes'."},{"source":"Please answer correctly the following question related to the paragraph below. \\n\\nWhich firm would not have meaningful return on investment if they don't get large number of customers, firm A or firm B?\\n\\nCity D's mayor wants to invite more businesses in the city. Three firms, firm A, firm B, and firm C, took advantage of this opportunity. Firm A does not require large initial costs, but firm B and firm C require \\nlarge initial costs. Firm B managed to increase its market share, but firm C failed to increase its market share.\\n\\nHint: A firm with high fixed costs requires a large number of customers in order to have a meaningful return on investment. This is where economies of scale become important. Since each firm has large initial costs, as the firm gains market share and increases its output the fixed cost (what they initially invested) is divided among a larger number of customers. Therefore, in industries with large initial investment requirements, average total cost declines as output increases over a much larger range of output levels.","target":"firm B","rationale":"According to the text, firm B managed to increase its market share and gain customers. Since it is stated that firms with large initial costs require a large number of customers in order for them to have meaningful return on investment, firm B would not need as many customers because they were able to gain more through increasing their market share (that is what increased means). Firm C failed to increase its market share and therefore wouldn't be gaining any new or additional customers. They would still likely only be serving the same amount of people which could limit how much profit they make if there are too few customers compared to other competitors like firm A who doesn‚Äôt require an expensive start up cost so can operate at less risk and potentially lower prices than those using big investments.\\nFirm A does not require large"},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- World War¬†II (often abbreviated to WWII or WW2), also known as the Second World War, was a global war that lasted from 1939 to 1945, although related conflicts began earlier. It involved the vast majority of the world's nationsincluding all of the great powerseventually forming two opposing military alliances: the Allies and the Axis. It was the most widespread war in history, and directly involved more than 100 million people from over 30 countries. In a state of \\"total war\\", the major participants threw their entire economic, industrial, and scientific capabilities behind the war effort, erasing the distinction between civilian and military resources. Marked by mass deaths of civilians, including the Holocaust (in which approximately 11 million people were killed) and the strategic bombing of industrial and population centres (in which approximately one million were killed, and which included the atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki), it resulted in an estimated 50 million to 85 million fatalities. These made World War¬†II the deadliest conflict in human history.\\n\\n- In politics and military planning, a war effort refers to a coordinated mobilization of society's resourcesboth industrial and humantowards the support of a military force. Depending on the militarization of the culture, the relative size of the armed forces and the society supporting them, the style of government, and the popular support for the military objectives, such war effort can range from a small industry to complete command of society.\\n\\n- A tank is an armored fighting vehicle designed for front-line combat, with heavy firepower, strong armour, and tracks providing good battlefield manoeuvrability. The first tanks were designed to overcome the deadlock of trench warfare; now they are a mainstay of modern ground forces and a key part of combined arms combat.\\n\\n- The Panzer II is the common name used for a family of German tanks used in World War II. The official German designation was Panzerkampfwagen II ( abbreviated PzKpfw II ) . Although the vehicle had originally been designed as a stopgap while larger , more advanced tanks were developed , it nonetheless went on to play an important role in the early years of World War II , during the Polish and French campaigns . The Panzer II was the most numerous tank in the German Panzer divisions beginning with the invasion of France . It was used in both North Africa against the British and on the Eastern Front against the Soviet Union . The Panzer II was supplanted by the Panzer III and IV by 1940/1941 . Thereafter , it was used to great effect as a reconnaissance tank . By the end of 1942 , it had been largely removed from front line service and it was used for training and on secondary fronts . The turrets of the then obsolete PzKpfw Is and PzKpfw IIs were reused as gun turrets on specially built defensive bunkers , particularly on the Atlantic Wall . Production of the tank itself ceased by 1943 , but its chassis remained in use as the basis of several other armored vehicles , chiefly self - propelled artillery and tank destroyers such as the Wespe and Marder II.\\n\\n- Firepower is the military capability to direct force at an enemy. (It is not to be confused with the concept of \\"rate of fire\\", which describes cycling of the firing mechanism in a weapon system.) Firepower involves the whole range of potential weapons. The concept is generally taught as one of the three key principles of modern warfare wherein the enemy forces are destroyed or have their will to fight negated by sufficient and preferably overwhelming use of force as a result of combat operations.\\n\\n- During World War II, the American atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki made Nagasaki the second and, to date, last city in the world to experience a nuclear attack.\\n\\n- The Holocaust (from the Greek ': \\"h√≥los\\", \\"whole\\" and \\"kaust√≥s\\", \\"burnt\\"), also referred to as the Shoah\\"' (Hebrew: , \\"HaShoah\\", \\"the catastrophe\\"), was a genocide in which Adolf Hitler's Nazi Germany and its collaborators killed about six million Jews. The victims included 1.5¬†million children and represented about two-thirds of the nine million Jews who had resided in Europe. Some definitions of the Holocaust include the additional five million non-Jewish victims of Nazi mass murders, bringing the total to about 11 million. Killings took place throughout Nazi Germany, German-occupied territories, and territories held by allies of Nazi Germany.\\n\\n- A great power is a sovereign state that is recognized as having the ability and expertise to exert its influence on a global scale. Great powers characteristically possess military and economic strength, as well as diplomatic and soft power influence, which may cause middle or small powers to consider the great powers' opinions before taking actions of their own. International relations theorists have posited that great power status can be characterized into power capabilities, spatial aspects, and status dimensions.\\n\\n- A battle is a combat in warfare between two or more armed forces, or combatants. A war sometimes consists of many battles. Battles generally are well defined in duration, area, and force commitment.\\n\\n- A military alliance is an international agreement concerning national security, when the contracting parties promise to support each other in case of a crisis that has not been identified in advance. Military alliances differ from coalitions, as coalitions are formed for a crisis that are already known.\\n\\n- Total war is warfare that includes any and all civilian-associated resources and infrastructure as legitimate military targets, mobilizes all of the resources of society to fight the war, and gives priority to warfare over non-combatant needs. The American-English Dictionary defines total war as \\"war that is unrestricted in terms of the weapons used, the territory or combatants involved, or the objectives pursued, especially one in which the laws of war are disregarded.\\"\\n\\n- The United States dropped nuclear weapons on the Japanese cities of Hiroshima and Nagasaki on August 6 and 9, 1945, respectively, during the final stage of World War II. The United States had dropped the bombs with the consent of the United Kingdom as outlined in the Quebec Agreement. The two bombings, which killed at least 129,000 people, remain the only use of nuclear weapons for warfare in history.\\n\\n- The Panzer¬†I was a light tank produced in Germany in the 1930s. The name is short for the German (\\"armored fighting vehicle mark I\\"), abbreviated \\"\\". The tank's official German ordnance inventory designation was SdKfz¬†101 (\\"special purpose vehicle 101\\").\\n\\n- Combined arms is an approach to warfare which seeks to integrate different combat arms of a military to achieve mutually complementary effects (for example, using infantry and armor in an urban environment, where one supports the other, or both support each other). According to strategist William S. Lind, combined arms can be distinguished from the concept of \\"supporting arms\\" as follows:\\nCombined arms hits the enemy with two or more arms simultaneously in such a manner that the actions he must take to defend himself from one make him more vulnerable to another. In contrast, supporting arms is hitting the enemy with two or more arms in sequence, or if simultaneously, then in such combination that the actions the enemy must take to defend himself from one also defends himself from the other(s).\\n\\n- Trench warfare is a type of land warfare using occupied fighting lines consisting largely of trenches, in which troops are significantly protected from the enemy's small arms fire and are substantially sheltered from artillery. The most famous use of trench warfare is the Western Front in World War I. It has become a byword for stalemate, attrition, sieges and futility in conflict.\\n\\n- Strategic bombing is a military strategy used in a total war with the goal of defeating the enemy by destroying its morale or its economic ability to produce and transport materiel to the theatres of military operations, or both. It is a systematically organized and executed attack from the air which can utilize strategic bombers, long- or medium-range missiles, or nuclear-armed fighter-bomber aircraft to attack targets deemed vital to the enemy's war-making capability.\\n\\n- Hiroshima is perhaps best known as the first city in history to be targeted by a nuclear weapon when the United States Army Air Forces (USAAF) dropped an atomic bomb on the city (and later on Nagasaki) at 8:15¬†a.m. on August 6, 1945, near the end of World War II.\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat is the relationship between 'panzer ii' and 'light tank'?","target":"instance of","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"instance of\\"."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate places/locations to the associated travel mode is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates place A to travel mode B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate travel mode for the given place C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\npark : bicycle. bermuda : ?","target":"airplane","rationale":"To go to the park, one could take a bicycle. Similarily, one could go to Bermuda by taking an airplane."},{"source":"What is the topic from this? \\nQuestion: What controls a birds migration?;  Answer: a primitive trait; Topic:","target":"Bird_migration","rationale":"The question is asking about what controls a bird's migration. The answer provided in the context states that it is a primitive trait, and then provides additional information regarding how this relates to birds' ability to detect light changes even when they are kept in complete darkness. \\nThis topic refers specifically to why and where birds migrate at certain times of year, or seasonally. Therefore the best choice for an appropriate topic would be: Bird_migration"},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to list all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element in the reverse order. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n1, 5, ['2937', '1621', '2443', '5999', '405', '4797', 'f', '3931', '6237']","target":"405, 5999, 2443, 1621, 2937","rationale":"Given the list ['2937', '1621', '2443', '5999', '405', '4797', 'f', '3931','6237'], we need to find the elements within the range 1 ~ 5.\\\\n1. The 1st element is 2937.\\\\n2. The 2nd element is 1621.\\\\n3. The 3rd element is 2443.\\\\n4. The 4th element is 5999.\\\\n5, The 5th element is 405,\\n\\nThe final output would be [405, 5999, 2443, 1621, 2937]."},{"source":"Read the dialog and predict the next turn. DIALOG:\\nWhat did Epstein do for the Cubs?\\n- He became President of Baseball Operations for the Chicago Cubs.\\n- When did Theo Epstein join the Cubs?\\n-","target":"On October 12, 2011, Epstein agreed to a five-year contract worth $18.5 million with the Chicago Cubs.","rationale":"The last two turns are about Theo Epstein's move to the Cubs from the Red Sox. Therefore, the next turn is most likely going to be about when he joined the Cubs. Hence, we select \\"On October 12, 2011, Epstein agreed to a five-year contract worth $18.5 million with the Chicago Cubs.\\""},{"source":"Question with options: can we draw the following hypothesis from the context? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nAmerican Airlines began laying off hundreds of flight attendants on Tuesday, after a federal judge turned aside a union's bid to block the job losses.\\n\\nHypothesis: American Airlines will recall hundreds of flight attendants.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nA:","target":"yes","rationale":"The context suggests that American Airlines are laying off hundreds of flight attendants, which means they will recall them if they get the job back. Therefore, we can say yes to this hypothesis."},{"source":"Answer this question:\\n\\nwho played jerry lee lewis on walk the line??","target":"Waylon Malloy Payne","rationale":"Waylon Malloy Payne portrayed Jerry Lee Lewis in the film \\"Walk The Line\\".\\nPayne has been credited as a professional actor since 2002, and is known for his role of Johnny Cash's cousin Jack Clement."},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is \\"Adam would be here by this time.\\" true if \\"Adam can't leave work here until Bob arrives to replace him. If Bob had left home for work on time, he would be here by this time.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"In the premise, it is mentioned that Bob cannot leave work until Adam arrives to replace him. Hence, even though Bob would have arrived at work had he not been delayed in leaving home on time (as per the premise), this does not mean that Adam can now leave for home since his replacement has not yet arrived. Thus, \\"Adam would be here by this time\\" is false and therefore the correct option is 'no'."},{"source":"Given a math problem with context and a question and 5 answer choices, the task is to provide the correct answer choice based on the problem. You must choose one of the given answer choices by letter: a, b, c, d, or e; anything else is invalid.\\n\\nProblem: the purchase price of an article is $ 48. in order to include 5 % of cost for overhead and to provide $ 12 of net profit, the markup should be\\nOptions: a. 15 %, b. 25 %, c. 30 %, d. 40 %, e. 45 %","target":"c","rationale":"The given purchase price of an article is $ 48. To find the selling price, we need to add the cost for overhead (5%) and net profit ($12). We can use the following steps:\\\\n\\\\n1. Find how much 5% of $48 is: 5/100 x 48 = 2.4\\\\n2. Add it to 12 and then add it to 48: 2.4 + 12 + 48 = 62.4\\\\n3. Divide this by the original purchase price (48) to find 30%."},{"source":"You are given a new situation: Dan decided to preserve some fruit and roots to see how long they last before they spoil. He also bought other fruit that he plans to eat fresh. He candied plums, pears, ginger and quince, and he ate fresh apples, oranges and mango.\\n\\nand a hint : Candied fruit, also known as crystallized fruit or glac√© fruit, has existed since the 14th century. Whole fruit, smaller pieces of fruit, or pieces of peel, are placed in heated sugar syrup, which absorbs the moisture from within the fruit and eventually preserves it. Depending on size and type of fruit, this process of preservation can take from several days to several months.[1] This process allows the fruit to retain its quality for a year.[2]\\n\\nThe continual process of drenching the fruit in syrup causes the fruit to become saturated with sugar, preventing the growth of spoilage microorganisms due to the unfavourable osmotic pressure this creates.[3]\\n\\nPlease answer this question : Which fruit have a lower sugar content candied plums or fresh oranges?","target":"fresh oranges","rationale":"Candied fruit is preserved by soaking it in heated sugar syrup, which absorbs the moisture from within the fruit and eventually preserves it. This process causes the fruit to become saturated with sugar. Fresh oranges have a lower sugar content than candied plums because they are not soaked in sugar as long as candied plums, so fresh oranges would be less sweet and thus have a lower sugar content. Therefore, answer A (fresh oranges) best fits this situation"},{"source":"DIALOG:\\nWhat is the name of Isabella Hale ‚Åá ala Ka ‚Åá ili Desha?\\n- Isabella Hale ªala Ka ªili Desha Isabella Hale ªala Ka ªili Desha (n√©e Miller Jan.\\n- When was she born?\\n- 16, 1864 - Feb.\\n- When did she die?\\n- 28, 1949) was a highly regarded Hawaiian composer, musician and kumu hula during the Kingdom of Hawaii and throughout her life.\\n- Where did she descend from?\\n- She is descended from notable chiefly lines.\\n- Did she have any siblings?\\n- She was one of five children.\\n- Who was her father?\\n-","target":"Her father was Alika (Alexander) Mela (Miller).","rationale":"In the given context, it is clear that Isabella Hale ªala Ka ªili Desha was a Hawaiian composer, musician and kumu hula. She was born on 16th January 1864 and died on 28th February 1949. She had five siblings and descended from notable chiefly lines. Therefore, since the asked question is \\"Who was her father?\\", the answer should be \\"Her father was Alika (Alexander) Mela (Miller).\\""},{"source":"The hospital in Y city had a good disposal site in which they disposed of Biomedical wastes, but the hospital in the neighboring city X had big problems, because the biomedical waste contaminated the ground water and affected the population.\\n\\nWhich city had a lower incidence of respiratory problems?\\n\\nHint: One of the most adverse impacts of poor waste management, especially municipal waste, is the incidence and prevalence of diseases such as malaria and respiratory problems, as well as other illnesses through the contamination of ground water. Biomedical wastes pose great danger in Bangladesh too as a report estimated that 20% of the biomedical waste is \\"highly infectious\\" and is a hazard since it is often disposed of into the sewage system or drains.[6]  Such poor sanitation has serious consequences for the health of the residents and a report suggests that \\"most of the child mortality could be related with this problem\\".[7]  With regards to the living standards, solid waste leads to blockage in the drainage system which leads to flooding in the streets. Consequently, mosquitoes and bad odour are among the negative impacts resulted.[7]","target":"Y city","rationale":"The hospital in Y city had a good disposal site for biomedical waste, which means the population would have lower exposure to contaminated ground water. \\nThis sentence indicates that this is relevant: \\"One of the most adverse impacts of poor waste management, especially municipal waste, is the incidence and prevalence of diseases such as malaria and respiratory problems...Biomedical wastes pose great danger...\\"."},{"source":"Read this article and answer this question Following their victory over the Patriots, the Steelers remained at home the next week for their second match-up of the season against division rivals the Baltimore Ravens.  The Ravens scored first with an 18-yard field goal by kicker Billy Cundiff, the only points scored in the first quarter by either team.  Steelers kicker Shaun Suisham answered with a 36-yard field goal early in the second quarter, and a 30-yard field goal near the end, but both of these were quickly matched by Baltimore's Cundiff with a 43-yard and 51-yard field goal, respectively, giving Baltimore a 9-6 lead at halftime.  The Ravens then increased their lead in the third quarter when Ray Rice scored the first touchdown of the game on a 4-yard run.  The Steelers rallied hard in the fourth quarter, with running back Rashard Mendenhall making a 1-yard run to score a touchdown, and then taking the lead for the first time in the game when quarterback Ben Roethlisberger made a successful 25-yard pass to wide receiver Mike Wallace in the endzone for a second touchdown.  On their final drive of the game, the Steelers were ready to potentially increase their lead with a 47-yard field goal kick by Shaun Suisham, but a 5-yard delay of game penalty put them out of field goal range and they were instead forced to punt the ball to the Ravens.  The Ravens then began a 92-yard drive, culminating in a 26-yard touchdown pass by quarterback Joe Flacco to wide receiver Torrey Smith in the endzone with just 8 seconds remaining, giving them the game.\\nHow many yards difference exists between Billy Cundiff's longest and second longest field goals?","target":"8","rationale":"To calculate the difference between Billy Cundiff's longest and second longest field goals, we need to first find out how long each of them is. In this case, his longest kick was a 51-yarder while his second longest one was 43 yards. Hence, the difference = 51 - 43 = 8"},{"source":"What do people usually tie a ribbon around as a present?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptions:\\n- floral arrangement\\n- girl's hair\\n- box\\n- car\\n- typewriter","target":"floral arrangement","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"ribbons can be tied around a floral arrangement\\"."},{"source":"Can you tell me the answer to which state of india has recorded the highest rate of population growth in the last census??","target":"Dadra and Nagar Haveli","rationale":"The answer is based on the statistical data provided by Census of India in 2011 which shows that Dadra and Nagar Haveli had recorded the highest rate of population growth with a percentage increase of 82.2%. \\nThe states listed above have not been mentioned anywhere in the question, so they should be eliminated as possible answers. The state with the lowest rate of population growth cannot possibly be responsible for recording the highest rate since it would then only record its own low-growth number (and this isn't how statistics works). So we can eliminate Uttarakhand from our list too. That leaves us with just one remaining option: Dadra and Nagar Haveli, i.e., D&NH - which happens to also match what was present in your original query response."},{"source":"who played cindy lou who in the grinch stole christmas??","target":"Taylor Michel Momsen","rationale":"The answer is \\"Taylor Michel Momsen\\" because she played Cindy-Lou Who in the movie The Grinch Stole Christmas."},{"source":"A person has a hot dish from the oven that they have left on the counter. After a few minutes, they place that dish into a sink full of cold water. The dish\\n\\nChoose an answer from this list:\\n- warms\\n- freezes\\n- dies\\n- chills","target":"chills","rationale":"The context of this question is that a dish has been left out on the counter and then placed into cold water. Based on this, it can be inferred that placing the hot dish in cold water would cause a sudden change in temperature, which would make sense for the answer to be \\"chills\\".\\n\\"Chilling\\" or \\"cooling down\\", according to Dictionary.com (2018), means ‚Äúto become cooler; lose heat‚Äù [1]. This definition aligns with our situation because when we put something warm into cool water, its temperature will decrease over time as it loses heat. Hence, the best answer is chills."},{"source":"Can you tell me the answer to who plays yzma from emperor's new groove??","target":"Eartha Kitt","rationale":"Eartha Kitt played the role of Yzma in Disney's \\"The Emperor's New Groove\\". Her character was a villain and appeared throughout all three films."},{"source":"What was likely said next? Can you order a coffee for me?\\nSure, from which coffee shop?\\nFrom Peet's\\nOkay, what would you like?\\nA Golden Cold Brew Fog Latte\\nOkey. What size would you like?\\nLarge\\nOkey. \\nO, tell them to leave out ginger.","target":"Okey. Do you want sugar?","rationale":"The dialogue is about ordering a coffee from Peet's and the conversation seems to be going smoothly. After the size of the coffee is specified, it would be natural for the server to ask if he or she also wants sugar in his or her coffee. Hence, \\"Okey. Do you want sugar?\\" is the most reasonable answer here."},{"source":"You are given a set of queries separated by '\\n', and your job is to find out the query which is not a well-formed or well-structured query in terms of grammar, punctuations, or spelling errors.\\n\\nHow do you abbreviate the word gallon ?\\nWhat is writing imagination ?\\nWhat is scarcityi ?\\nHow do cells react in an isotonic solution ?","target":"What is scarcityi ?","rationale":"The given query \\"What is scarcityi ?\\" is misspelled. The correct spelling is \\"scarcity\\"."},{"source":"Choose between \\"red floor\\" and  \\"green floor\\".\\nQuestion: Carla rolls a jar across a red floor. The red floor is bumpy. She then rolls the jar across a green floor, which is smooth. The jar rolls further on the green floor since it has (A) more resistance (B) less resistance","target":"green floor","rationale":"The green floor is smooth, meaning the jar will roll further. A bumpy surface would create more resistance and cause the jar to stop sooner.\\nSo the correct answer is: \\"green floor\\""},{"source":"You are given a password and you need to generate the number of steps required to convert the given password to a strong password. A password is considered strong if (a) it has at least 6 characters and at most 20 characters; (b) it contains at least one lowercase letter and one uppercase letter, and at least one digit; (c) it does not contain three repeating characters in a row. In one step you can: (1) Insert one character to password, (2) delete one character from password, or (3) replace one character of password with another character.\\n\\npassword = CYsQwT.KqxLISdpw","target":"1","rationale":"Given the password 'CYsQwT.KqxLISdpw', it does not meet any of the criterion to be considered a strong password.\\\\n1. It is less than 20 characters and more than 6 characters long.\\\\n2. It does not contain at least one lowercase letter or one uppercase letter, and at least one digit\\\\n3. It has three repeating characters in a row: wTT..\\\\nHowever, after changing one character we can make it a strong password:\\\\na) Replace '.' with a number (or an uppercase letter).\\\\nb) Replace T with an uppercase letter (or number).\\nc) Replace '.' with an uppercase letter (or number)\\\\nd) Delete ."},{"source":"The 2000 KNVB Cup Final was a football match between NEC and Roda JC on 21 May 2000 at De Kuip, Rotterdam. It was the final match of the 1999‚Äì2000 KNVB Cup competition. Roda JC won 2‚Äì0 after goals from Bob Peeters and Eric van der Luer. It was their second KNVB Cup win.\\nCan we infer the following?\\nThe 1990 Star Cup Semi Final was a volley match between XXX and YYY on 24 April 1990 in Brussels. It was the semi final match. XXX won 3‚Äì0 after. It was their first semi final game.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nThe answer is:","target":"No","rationale":"The two sentences provided are quite different. While the first sentence provides information about a KNVB Cup final match, location of the game and details regarding Roda JC's victory in that match;\\nthe second one speaks about a Star Cup semi-final volley ball match where you can see that it is entirely made up with no source to validate any facts presented in the statement. Therefore, we cannot infer from this context if the hypothesis mentioned above is true or not. So, The answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nLow food supply or a lack of space can lower birth rates, increase death rates, or lead to emigration.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nA population of squirrels in a local forest had more food available to them this spring than they did last spring. During which spring will more squirrels leave the area to live somewhere else this spring or last spring?","target":"last spring","rationale":"The paragraph states that a low food supply or lack of space can lead to emigration, so if there was more available food this spring than last spring then squirrels would be less likely to leave the area.\\nTherefore, during which season will more squirrels leave? The answer is last spring."},{"source":"In this task, you're given four sentences of a story written in natural language. The given story is not complete and your job is to complete the story by selecting one of the sentence choices from (A) and (B), such that the story sounds fully coherent.\\n\\nSentence1: Herman was very hungry but had no money. Sentence2: So he searched all over his house for spare change. Sentence3: He found a quarter under the couch and a dollar in his dresser. Sentence4: Herman came up with two dollars and walked to the store. \\n (A) Herman decided he wasn't hungry anymore. (B) Herman managed to buy some food to make a small meal.","target":"B","rationale":"The story makes sense if we choose option (B). Herman manages to find two dollars and visit the store."},{"source":"Given a comment text in Tamil, classify the comment into one of these categories (i) Hope speech, if it contains encouraging, positive or supportive contents about equality, diversity or inclusion, (ii) Not Hope Speech or (iii) Not in Expected Language, if the text is not Tamil.\\n\\nEvening 6","target":"Not in Expected Language","rationale":"The comment text is not in Tamil, so the output should be \\"Not in Expected Language\\"."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the passage.\\n\\"A major producer of natural gas , oil , and agriculture, Oklahoma relies on an economic base of aviation, energy, telecommunications, and biotechnology .\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Oklahoma","rationale":"The passage discusses Oklahoma and its major industries."},{"source":"Can you tell me the answer to on which date south africa become a democratic republic??","target":"31 May 1961","rationale":"On 31 May 1961, South Africa became a democratic republic."},{"source":"After finally beating former quarterback Brett Favre in Week 7, the Packers traveled to New Meadowlands Stadium in East Rutherford, NJ to take on the New York Jets. The Packers took a 3-0 lead on a Mason Crosby 20-yard field goal in the first quarter and held that lead until the fourth quarter. Crosby then hit two field goals in the fourth quarter (from 41 and 40 yards respectively) to seal the victory for the Packers. While Aaron Rodgers and the Packer offense sputtered against the vaunted Jet defense, Green Bay's defense excelled in stopping the NFL's second-ranked rushing offense and intercepted Jets quarterback Mark Sanchez twice. The win improved the Packers to 5-3 and in first place in the NFC North.\\n\\nBased on the above article, answer a question. Which quarter did Mason Crosby kick his shortest field goal?","target":"first","rationale":"Mason Crosby kicked three field goals. The first one was the shortest, which is 20-yard in the first quarter; then two were 41 and 40 yards respectively in the fourth quarter."},{"source":"Question: What would you put on your foot first before anything else?\\n\\nChoices: \\n- fungus\\n- shoe\\n- grave\\n- table\\n- sock\\n\\nThe rationale to choose \\"sock\\" as the answer is that:","target":"socks go on feet before shoes","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"socks go on feet before shoes\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you need to reverse all words of a given length in the sentence. The number of letters in a word determine its length. For example, the length of the word \\"apple\\" is 5.\\n\\nSentence: 'a man is riding his bike down the street with a yoga mat strapped to the back'. Reverse all words of length '4' in the given sentence.","target":"a man is riding his ekib nwod the street htiw a agoy mat strapped to the kcab","rationale":"Given the sentence 'a man is riding his bike down the street with a yoga mat strapped to the back', let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. 'a' : 1 -> (total) 1\\\\n2. 'man' : 3 -> (total) 4\\\\n3. 'is' : 2 -> (total) 6\\\\n4. 'riding' : 6 -> (total) 12\\\\n5. 'his' : 3 -> (reverse) sih, this is not counted in final calculation as its length is not equal to 4\\\\n6. 'bike': 4 -> (reverse and total count as it has length of 4). This word will be reversed and added to the result: ekib, total = 16 + 4 = 20 \\\\n7~17 are all words of length less than or greater than 4 so they are ignored from calculation but counted in final length \\\\ntotal = 20 + 37 = 57\\n\\nThe final sentence would be \\"a man is riding his ekib nwod the street htiw a agoy mat strapped to the kcab\\", which has a total character count of 57"},{"source":"Read the given query and classify it as a 'Good' or 'Bad' query depending on how well the query is formed, 'Bad' being the expected output for a not so well formed query and 'Good' being the expected output for a well formed query. A query may be wrong based on common sense or general facts, but if it is well formed, you should answer with Good.\\n\\nWhat are the decomposers in boreal forests ?","target":"Good","rationale":"This query is well formed and grammatically correct, so it should be classified as Good."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a paragraph from the research paper and your task is to generate a suitable title for the research paper based on the given paper. Under 100 words is a good title length.\\n\\nArabia. Using parametric and nonparametric methods, we estimated a mean incubation period of 6.9 days (95% credibility interval: 6.3-7.5) for cases in South Korea and 5.0 days (95% credibility interval: 4.0-6.6) among cases in Saudi Arabia. In a log-linear regression model, the mean incubation period was 1.42 times longer (95% credibility interval: 1.18-1.71) among cases in South Korea compared to Saudi Arabia. The variation that we identified in the incubation period distribution between locations could be associated with differences in ascertainment or reporting of exposure dates and illness onset dates, differences in the source or mode of infection, or environmental differences.","target":"Comparison of incubation period distribution of human infections with MERS-CoV in South Korea and Saudi Arabia","rationale":"The abstract describes the results of a study that compared the incubation period distribution of MERS-CoV infections in South Korea and Saudi Arabia. It indicates that the mean incubation period was longer among cases in South Korea (6.9 days) than among cases in Saudi Arabia (5.0 days), which could be due to differences in case ascertainment and reporting, source or mode of infection, or environmental factors between these two locations. Therefore, an appropriate title for this paper would describe its main results by answering questions like: \\"What did researchers find out about the incubation period distribution for MERS-CoV?\\" \\"How were these findings obtained?\\" \\"What are possible reasons for variations between South Korea and Saudi Arabia?\\", etc.\\"Comparison of incubation period distribution of human infections with MERS-CoV in South Korea and Saudi Arabia\\" is a good example as it summarizes the main findings by describing what was compared, how it was done, where it took place (South Korea vs. Saudi Arabia), etc.\\""},{"source":"You will be given a review about a book, an item, a place or a movie. After that, a question is given that you should answer using a certain span of the review. Your answer should be from the review itself and should not contain extra words, and should not be a combination of different spans. If there's no direct answer to the question, answer with a part of the text that is the most relevant to the question. See the examples for clarification.\\n\\nreview: I was excited to try these once I got a whiff of the contents upon opening the package.  I'm a fan of good licorice...note: Twizzlers are just okay to me.The smell and consistency of this licorice are good, but the flaver is quite disappointing.  It has a very weak taste of Pomegranate and for some reason I got a hint of peppermint in every bite.  Maybe just the way my taste buds interpreted the licorice mixed with a little pomegranate juice (can't be much in there).I like these more than Twizzlers, but I would buy a number of other brands before these.FYI: Below are the listed ingredients and nutrition facts.Ingredients-----------Organic Wheat FlourOrganic SugarCorn SyrupOrganic Tapioca SyrupVegetable GlycerinSunflower OilElderberry ExtractCitric AcidNatural FlavorPomegranate Juice ConcentrateLicorice Root ExtractNutrition Facts---------------Servings per container: About 3.5Calories per serving: 130Total Fat 0.5gSodium 5mgTotal Carbs 32g- Dietary Fiver 2g- Sugars 10gProtein 2g\\nquestion: Is this taste enjoyable?","target":"It has a very weak taste of Pomegranate","rationale":"The relevant passage is \\"The smell and consistency of this licorice are good, but the flaver is quite disappointing.  It has a very weak taste of Pomegranate...\\". The answer should be a span from this passage: \\"It has a very weak taste of Pomegranate\\"."},{"source":"My old roommate‚Äôs cats, Clise and Monkey, were about as different as cats could be. Clise, rescued as an emaciated kitten from a local park, grew up to be morbidly obese. His interests mainly involved eating food, begging for food, or going around the neighborhood scrounging for food. He could hear a can opener from a mile away.\\nMonkey was a more active cat. He liked to chase the laser pointer and was the first to run to the door when someone arrived. But he could also be lazy, lounging in a sunbeam or stretched out on the couch.\\nBoth of them liked to watch TV.\\nSoon after I moved in, I started having health issues which necessitated a lot of time lounging around myself. This was the era of reality TV, back when much of it was actually good. The cats, Monkey especially, watched with me.\\nMonkey definitely had his preferences. His favorite shows were The Girls Next Door and Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making The Team. Notice a theme here? Playboy Playmates and professional cheerleaders. Monkey liked his T & A (tits and ass).\\nIf one of these shows was on, and I turned it to Project Runway or something, Monkey would march off. But as soon as I turned it back, and he could hear the high-pitched giggling, he‚Äôd come running back.\\nClise‚Äôs favorite shows were Top Chef, Iron Chef, and Rachael Ray. Food porn. If there was something he especially craved, like a shrimp stir-fry, he‚Äôd assume a begging pose, right in front of the TV, as if Rachael might take pity on him and throw him a scrap or two.\\nI moved out about a year later. A few months previous, Monkey ended up catching some wasting disease and dying, but Clise, as far as I know, is still there, begging for scraps from anyone he can ‚Äî in real life or televised.\\nWhy would Clise beg?\\n\\nA. when shrimp was on the screen.\\n\\nB. watching his favorite shows.\\n\\nC. food on the tv.\\n\\nD. not enough information","target":"C","rationale":"The correct answer is C.\\nBased on the context, Clise's favorite shows are Top Chef and Iron Chef so he would beg in front of the TV when his favorite show was playing. As these two shows feature cooking competitions, it can be inferred that there is food shown throughout both programs. Therefore, as long as a program featuring food preparation was being played on television it could have caused him to beg for scraps from anyone nearby whether they were watching or not because any footage of food could elicit this response from him.\\""},{"source":"A friend asked me to answer this question: What is that last name of the person who is a toy maker?, using the article: A violent thunderstorm strands a couple and child in the gothic English countryside: little Judy, who is traveling with her selfish, uncaring father, David and her rich, callous, arrogant stepmother Rosemary. David only has Judy due to a court order and barely tolerates her presence. After their car is stuck in mud and the rain begins, they find a mansion. After breaking in, they are found by the owners, a kindly older couple, Gabriel and Hilary Hartwicke. Rosemary threw Judy's beloved teddy bear into the bushes while out in the rain, so Gabriel gifts her a new doll, Mr. Punch. They are invited to stay and while eating, Isabel and Enid (two British punk rocker hitchhikers) barge in with the person who picked them up, Ralph. Gabriel reveals himself to be a talented toy maker; their house is filled with dolls, puppets, and many other beautifully detailed and handmade toys. The Hartwickes invite the stranded travelers to join them to stay as guests until the storm ends and show them to their rooms., what would be the answer ?","target":"Hartwicke","rationale":"The answer to this question is \\"Hartwicke\\", which is the last name of Gabriel and Hilary Hartwicke, who are described as a kindly older couple."},{"source":"An example of a fossil could be a\\n- dino track\\n- animal eye\\n- human heart\\n- abandoned nest","target":"dino track","rationale":"Fossils are the remains of plants or animals that lived in ancient times. They can include tracks, bones and shells of extinct organisms. Dino track is a fossil as it was formed from an animal‚Äôs footprint left in mud which later hardened into rock over time.\\nAn example of a dino track: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trackway"},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a short story with a beginning, two potential middles, and an ending. Your job is to choose the middle statement that makes the story coherent / plausible by writing \\"1\\" or \\"2\\" in the output. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes most sense.\\n\\nBeginning: Jen's manager told her she needed to upload her resume. Middle 1: Jen couldn't find her resume and didn't upload it. Middle 2: Jen located her resume and attached it to an email for her manager. Ending: Then she sent it to her manager.","target":"2","rationale":"The ending indicates that Jen sent her resume to her manager. However, the beginning states that she was told she needed to upload it. Thus, Middle 1 is not plausible because it means she did not upload it. In Middle 2, Jen locates her resume and sends it as an attachment in an email, which would make the ending coherent."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- A furlong is a measure of distance in imperial units and U.S. customary units equal to one-eighth of a mile, equivalent to 660 feet, 220 yards, 40 rods, or 10 chains. Using the international definition of the inch as exactly 25.4 millimetres, one furlong is 201.168 metres. However, the United States does not uniformly use this conversion ratio. Older ratios are in use for surveying purposes in some states, leading to variations in the length of the furlong of about two parts per million, or 0.4 millimetres (inch). This variation is too small to have many practical consequences. Five furlongs are about 1.0 kilometre (1.00584¬†km is the exact value, according to the international conversion).\\n\\n- The Flash Stakes was an important and prestigious race for two - year - old Thoroughbred horses and one of the longest running horse racing events in America . Run before races were graded , the Flash was won by a host of starry names . Begun before the United States Hotel Stakes ( also now removed from racing 's roster ) , it was the oldest race for juveniles of either gender in the US . Once a historic fixture in Saratoga , New York at the Saratoga Race Course , it was eliminated in 2005 by the New York Racing Association ( NYRA ) , which feared bankruptcy . Moved from its home in Saratoga after a long absence , the Grade III Flash had raced on at Belmont Park as a five furlong sprint on the main track for a $ 100,000 added purse until the NYRA 's 2005 decision .\\n\\n- Saratoga Race Course is a thoroughbred horse racing track in Saratoga Springs, New York, United States, with a capacity of 50,000. Opened in 1863, it is the third oldest racetrack in the US (after 2nd oldest Pleasanton Fairgrounds Racetrack & oldest Freehold Raceway), though it is often considered to be the oldest sporting venue of any kind in the country.\\n\\n- The United States Hotel Stakes was an American Thoroughbred horse race run annually in the late summer or early autumn until 1955 at Saratoga Race Course in Saratoga Springs, New York. It was run on dirt over a distance of six furlongs. Raced in the pre-grading era, for most of its existence the race was one of the premier shorter distance competitions for two-year-old horses in the United States.\\n\\n- The Thoroughbred is a horse breed best known for its use in horse racing. Although the word \\"thoroughbred\\" is sometimes used to refer to any breed of purebred horse, it technically refers only to the Thoroughbred breed. Thoroughbreds are considered \\"hot-blooded\\" horses that are known for their agility, speed and spirit.\\n\\n- Saratoga Springs is a city in Saratoga County, New York, United States, that is also widely known as simply Saratoga (though not to be confused with the nearby town of that name). The population was 26,586 at the 2010 census. The name reflects the presence of mineral springs in the area, which has made Saratoga a popular resort destination for over 200 years. The city is just north of Albany in the heart of New York's Capital Region.\\n\\n- A breed is a specific group of domestic animals having homogeneous appearance (phenotype), homogeneous behavior, and/or other characteristics that distinguish it from other organisms of the same species. Breeds are formed through genetic isolation and either natural adaptation to the environment or selective breeding, or a combination of the two. Despite the centrality of the idea of \\"breeds\\" to animal husbandry and agriculture, no single, scientifically accepted definition of the term exists. A breed is therefore not an objective or biologically verifiable classification but is instead a term of art amongst groups of breeders who share a consensus around what qualities make some members of a given species members of a nameable subset.\\n\\n- or \\"cultivars\\" of an animal species, achieved through the process of selective breeding. When the lineage of a purebred animal is recorded, that animal is said to be \\"pedigreed\\".\\n\\n\\n\\nAfter reading the paragraphs above, choose the best answer for the entity that related to 'flash stakes' with the relationship of 'instance of'.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- 25\\n - animal\\n - area\\n - breed\\n - capital\\n - census\\n - city\\n - destination\\n - distance\\n - environment\\n - era\\n - horse\\n - horse race\\n - hotel\\n - imperial units\\n - name\\n - population\\n - process\\n - race\\n - ratio\\n - resort\\n - single\\n - species\\n - spirit\\n - subset\\n - term\\n - the city\\n - thoroughbred\\n - track\\n - two\\n - value\\n - word\\n - year","target":"horse race","rationale":"The Wikipedia article for the Flash Stakes (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flash_Stakes) describes it as \\"a historic fixture in Saratoga, New York at the Saratoga Race Course\\". The term 'fixture' is used to describe horse races that take place on a yearly or consistent basis, and therefore indicates that it was an annual event rather than a single race. Therefore the best answer is horse race"},{"source":"Please answer a question about the following article about Queen Victoria:\\n\\nVictoria wrote to her uncle Leopold, whom Victoria considered her \\"best and kindest adviser\\", to thank him \\"for the prospect of great happiness you have contributed to give me, in the person of dear Albert ... He possesses every quality that could be desired to render me perfectly happy. He is so sensible, so kind, and so good, and so amiable too. He has besides the most pleasing and delightful exterior and appearance you can possibly see.\\" However at 17, Victoria, though interested in Albert, was not yet ready to marry. The parties did not undertake a formal engagement, but assumed that the match would take place in due time.\\n\\nWho was Victoria not ready to marry at age 17?","target":"Albert","rationale":"The context states that Victoria was interested in Albert, but not ready to marry him at the age of 17. The text also mentions Victoria's feelings towards Albert and describes his qualities.\\nTherefore, it can be inferred from the given context that she is referring to \\"Albert\\" when stating: 'He possesses every quality...'"},{"source":"The input is a tweet which can be Hate Speech or Offensive. Given such a tweet, output a phrase from the tweet that makes it hate speech or offensive. The output should contain only one such phrase. The output has to be from within the tweet itself. Do not generate words or phrases not present in the tweet.\\n\\nit not a psyop if it the truth tommy robinson is a kike shill let him rot <user> ‚Äç","target":"kike","rationale":"The tweet is hate speech because it contains the phrase \\"kike shill\\", which is a derogatory and offensive term for Jewish people."},{"source":"Ace , a wannabe rock star , is on his way to a concert of the band Guitar Wolf when space aliens invade the Earth .  As a result the dead rise to their feet in the countryside setting of Asahi , Japan , with an appetite for flesh .  Enlisting the help of his rock 'n roll blood brother Guitar Wolf , Ace and the members of the band get entangled in many misadventures with crazy rock managers in very tight shorts , transsexuals , naked women shooting guns in the shower , and bloodthirsty zombies ready to tear them apart .  Leather jackets , loud over-modulated music , laser guitar picks , motorcycles , guns , muscle cars , and fire abound .  Guitar Wolf , a Japanese trio signed to Matador Records in the US and self-proclaimed coolest rock band in the world star as the well-coiffed heroes .  It is also a love story , between Ace and Tobio , a trans woman .  The music , in a garage punk vein , plays an important role in the film .  It features music from Greg Cartwright of Reigning Sound and The Oblivians .  His 1997 song \`\` Twice as Deep '' by Greg Oblivian & the Tip Tops is featured .  This film is similar to another movie by a Spanish punk group , La matanza can bal de los garrulos lis rgicos produced by Siniestro Total \\nQuestion: Who does Ace enlist to help him fight the zombies? \\nIs it Naked women?","target":"No","rationale":"The question states that the zombies invaded Asahi, Japan. The context also mentions Guitar Wolf, a Japanese band from Tokyo who is signed to Matador Records in the United States. \\nThis suggests that Ace and Guitar Wolf are Japanese men as well. In addition, Naked women shooting guns in the shower is mentioned along with bloodthirsty zombies ready to tear them apart (Ace and friends). This means at least one of these naked woman did not recruit herself into helping fight against the aliens because she was almost eaten by one of them before being saved by Ace's friend instead!\\n\\n\\nSo it isn't \\"Naked Women\\" but rather his rock n roll blood brother: GUITAR WOLF!!! No!\\"]"},{"source":"When we add resistors in parallel to each other the total resistance decreases and the current increases.\\n\\nHaving read the above passage, choose the right answer to the following question (choices are increases or decreases ):\\n\\n\\nIf we change resistors in series to not be in parallel the resistance increases or decreases?","target":"increases","rationale":"When resistors are in series, the current is shared between them. Adding more resistors increases this division and leads to a higher resistance overall. When we change resistors in series to not be in parallel, it means that they will become part of a circuit with less total resistance than when those same resistors were all connected together by themselves (e.g., two 10R+2R = 22 Ohm). Because these extra connections decrease our starting point from 100Ohms down only 80ohms before adding any new branches or other components into consideration; therefore changing their configuration would increase its value from an initial state because now instead of being able just split up evenly across multiple channels where each one has some amount left over for itself after sharing what was needed with everyone else.\\"\\nThe answer"},{"source":"Coming off of their road win over the 49ers, the Ravens went home for a Week 6 interconference duel with the winless St. Louis Rams.  With QB Steve McNair out with injuries, back-up Kyle Boller was given the start. In the first quarter, Baltimore took flight early with kicker Matt Stover getting a 43-yard field goal for the only score of the period.  In the second quarter, the Raven continued to take advantage of an injury-plagued Rams team with Stover kicking a 42-yard field goal, along with RB Willis McGahee getting a 6-yard TD run.  In the third quarter, Baltimore increased its lead with Stover nailing a 23-yard field goal.  Afterwards, St. Louis would get its only score of the game as kicker Jeff Wilkins got a 32-yard field goal.  In the fourth quarter, the Ravens sealed their easy win with Stover kicking a 31-yard and a 36-yard field goal. During the win, the Ravens defense forced six turnovers, which included a franchise-best 5 interceptions.\\n\\nBased on the above article, answer a question. How many yards are the top two longest field goals combined?","target":"85","rationale":"To solve this problem, we need to identify the top two longest field goals. The first field goal is 43-yard and the second one is 42 yards. Thus, the sum of these two lengths are 85 yards in total: 43+42=85"},{"source":"Given the sentence, generate \\"yes, and\\" response. \\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). 1 In short, a \\"Yes, and\\" is a dialogue exchange in which a speaker responds by adding new information on top of the information/setting that was constructed by another speaker. Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange, although it could be the case if it agrees with the description above. There are many ways in which a response could implicitly/explicitly agree to the prompt without specifically saying 'yes, and...'. \\n\\nAre you two doctors? Is this why you're in my room?","target":"We're not doctors. Not quite. I took a semester","rationale":"The sentence \\"We're not doctors. Not quite. I took a semester\\" agrees with the prompt and adds on to the information provided in the prompt, as it mentions that they are not doctors but further explains their qualifications. Therefore, this is a valid 'Yes, and' response.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is intentionally offensive, 2) no, otherwise. Also, generate label 'no' for offensive statements that appear to be unintentional, or non-offensive statements that are underhandedly offensive.  Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\nI jus wanna live good stay fresh and fuck bad bitches! &#128076;&#128175;","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given post is intentionally offensive as it uses abusive and objectifying language towards women. Therefore, the answer should be \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"You are given a target race, and two sentences. Your task is to determine whether the second sentence is either a stereotype, anti-stereotype, or is unrelated with respect to the first sentence and the target. A stereotype is a widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. An anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against the widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. Sentences and targets are unrelated if there is no relevance between them.\\n\\nTarget: Italy \\nItalian food is at its best in Italy. I ate pasta for every meal when I was visiting.","target":"stereotype","rationale":"The first sentence is a stereotype, and the second sentence is confirming it."},{"source":"What is the solution?\\n\\nSolve -8 + 20 = 2*q for q.","target":"6","rationale":"First, we need to isolate the variable q on one side of the equation.\\n\\n-8 + 20 = 2q\\n12 = 2q\\n6=q"},{"source":"Blythburgh is a village and civil parish in the Suffolk Coastal district of the English county of Suffolk. It is 4 mi west of Southwold and 5 mi south-east of Halesworth and lies on the River Blyth. The A12 road runs through the village which is split either side of the road. At the 2011 census the population of the parish was 297. The parish includes the hamlets of Bulcamp and Hinton.\\nCan we infer the following?\\nBlythburgh lies on the River Blyth.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nThe answer is:","target":"Yes","rationale":"The village of Blythburgh is stated to be situated on the River Blyth in both the context and hypothesis. Therefore, we can infer that \\"Blythburgh lies on the River Blyth\\". So, the answer is \\"Yes.\\""},{"source":"who did andy murray beat at wimbledon 2014??","target":"Roberto Bautista Agut","rationale":"Andy Murray defeated Roberto Bautista Agut at Wimbledon 2014."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the question-answer pair.\\nQuestion: \\"what is endodontic dentistry?\\";  Answer: \\"Endodontics (from the Greek endo \\"inside\\"; and odons \\"tooth\\") is one of the dental specialties recognized by the American Dental Association , Royal College of Dentists of Canada , and Royal Australasian College of Dental Surgeons , and deals with the tooth pulp and the tissues surrounding the root of a tooth .\\"? Topic:","target":"Endodontics","rationale":"A question about the discipline of dentistry would be best suited to an expert in that field. \\nThe answer given is a factual statement and demonstrates expertise on the subject matter, which validates that it should be used as evidence for determining whether Endodontics is the topic being discussed."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the best option to answer the question.\\nContext: Being back in Berkeley has made me realize that it has been a really long time since I have been truly truly happy . Its not that I ' ve been miserable ... far from it . But its like the last year or so , I ' ve been in a funk . you know in cartoons when one of the characters gets followed around by a little grey raincloud ?\\nQuestion: What will happen this year ?\\nOptions: \\n- None of the above choices .\\n - He will feel like he 's in a rut\\n - He will reflect on last year positively\\n - He will think everything has been great","target":"He will feel like he 's in a rut","rationale":"The context describes how the writer has felt overcast and in a \\"funk\\" for some time. The question asks what will happen this year, which implies that they are looking forward to it being different. Out of all of the answers given, only one matches with their current mood: they have been feeling like they're in a rut.\\n\\nSo answer is He will feel like he 's in a rut"},{"source":"Q: the largest state capitol building in the u.s. is located in which state? A:","target":"Texas","rationale":"The largest state capitol building in the U.S. is located in Texas, which can be verified through multiple sources including Wikipedia and various media reports on the topic (e.g., <a href=\\"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/27/us/texas-capitol-is-now-largest\\" target=\\"_blank\\">New York Times</a>,<a href=\\"https://books.google.co"},{"source":"Given a document, generate a short title of the document. The title should convey the main idea/event/topic about which the document is being written. Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nMark the Buckeyes 73-8 in six seasons under Coach Urban Meyer .  Mark   them  as probably the best team outside the big ol‚Äô 2017 playoff  even if  they  did take that notorious 55-24 splat at Iowa.  Mark   them  12-2 for the season  and notice how  they ‚Äôve collected two bowl wins ‚Äî the 2015 Fiesta against Notre Dame and the 2017 Cotton against Southern California ‚Äî as signs of an ability to combat the bummer of narrow playoff exclusion.\\n‚ÄúA very healthy program ‚Äù Meyer called it.\\nThat happened  of course  in ancient times  but the Trojans‚Äô intermittent string had extended through Ohio State coaches Woody Hayes  Earle Bruce  John Cooper and Jim Tressel before  Meyer ‚Äôs bunch finally snuffed it out.\\nThe elite coach and  his  sixth team did so in front of another swarm of Ohio State fans in an AT&T Stadium that did have empty upper sections but did welcome 67 510. They did it in a building of fond memories  site of their national championship of three Januarys ago. Along the way  they looked superior if not crushingly so  and even without their prized senior cornerback Denzel Ward  who followed the trickling recent-years fashion of skipping bowl games while eyeing the NFL draft. If these two conference champions who suffered obliterations this season ‚Äî Ohio State at Iowa  and USC at Notre Dame ‚Äî still felt mad at the selection committee choosing conference non-champion Alabama  then Ohio State channeled better its anger.\\n‚ÄúWe just had some  a lot of  not-very-many dry eyes in the locker room ‚Äù Meyer said.\\nBy the semi-dreary end  when the last Darnold pass sailed wide of everything and plunked down  the night had sustained a Meyer era inarguably strong  even if Ohio State fans never have seemed the type to go around chanting  ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre number five.‚Äù","target":"A little late but Ohio State makes its case in Cotton Bowl win over USC","rationale":"The title should convey the main idea/event/topic about which the document is being written.  Here, the given title \\"A little late but Ohio State makes its case in Cotton Bowl win over USC\\" does convey what the article is about."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate places/locations to the associated travel mode is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates place A to travel mode B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate travel mode for the given place C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\npark : bicycle. airport : ?","target":"train","rationale":"In the first analogy, one could go to the park by riding a bicycle. Similarly, one could go to the airport by taking a train."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"Hayek is widely recognised for having introduced the time dimension to the equilibrium construction and for his key role in helping inspire the fields of growth theory, information economics, and the theory of spontaneous order. The \\"informal\\" economics presented in Milton Friedman's massively influential popular work Free to Choose (1980), is explicitly Hayekian in its account of the price system as a system for transmitting and co-ordinating knowledge. This can be explained by the fact that Friedman taught Hayek's famous paper \\"The Use of Knowledge in Society\\" (1945) in his graduate seminars.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What did Free to Choose describe?","target":"price system as a system for transmitting and co-ordinating knowledge","rationale":"The given passage says that Friedman's popular work Free to Choose is Hayekian in its account of the price system as a system for transmitting and co-ordinating knowledge. So, we can conclude that Free to Choose describes price system as a system for transmitting and co-ordinating knowledge."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on geometry. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: 32 meters of wire is available to fence off a flower bed in the form of a circular sector . what must the radius of the circle in meters be , if we wish to have a flower bed with the greatest possible surface area ? \\nOptions: ['a ) 2 ‚àö 2', 'b ) 2 ‚àö 5', 'c ) 5', 'd ) 4 ‚àö 2', 'e ) 8']","target":"e","rationale":"The area of a sector is given by \\\\\\\\(r^{2}\\\\\\\\theta/2\\\\\\\\) and the radius will be minimum when the arc length is maximum. The length of the wire is 32 meters and it forms a circle when laid straight. Therefore, the circumference will be 32 meters, so \\\\\\\\(r = 2 * 16\\\\\\\\pi = 8\\\\)."},{"source":"By Tim Shipman PUBLISHED: 16:35 EST, 22 October 2013 | UPDATED: 20:17 EST, 22 October 2013 Tax breaks for married couples should be more generous and be introduced well before the general election, says Lord Lawson. Margaret Thatcher‚Äôs Chancellor endorses the principle of David Cameron‚Äôs plan for transferable tax allowances worth up to ¬£200 a year. But he says the tax break should be extended and must come into effect earlier than the start date announced by the Government, which is April 2015 ‚Äì just one month before the election ‚Äì to avoid the risk of it being rolled back by Labour.\\n@highlight\\nLord Lawson believes tax breaks for married couples should be more generous\\n@highlight\\nFormer Chancellor said plan should come into effect earlier than announced\\n@highlight\\nSame sex couples in civil partnerships would also be eligible for breaks \\nMore than a million married couples will gain only ¬£1.35 a week from @placeholder‚Äôs tax break ‚Äì a third of the amount promised. \\nHere, the placeholder refers to","target":"David Cameron","rationale":"The paragraph mentions David Cameron's plan for transferable tax allowances, and states that the same sex couples in civil partnerships would also be eligible. This establishes a link between David Cameron and \\"transferable tax allowances\\".\\nSince @placeholder refers to someone who is mentioned previously in the text, it must refer back to either Lord Lawson or David Cameron (or both). \\nIn this example however, there are no other instances of \\"@highlight\\" which could establish any connection with Lord Lawson . Hence we can conclude that \\"@placeholder\\" refers back to mention of David Cameron's name preceding it.\\n\\n\\nExample 8]\\n[Instruction and Question]\\nGiven this passage: It was here she met her first husband Professor Henry Hallett Dale whom she married on 31st December 1914"},{"source":"Can you generate a question with a factual answer?","target":"What was the award in 1998 for?","rationale":"Here's an example for a question with a factual answer:\\\\nQuestion: What was the award in 1998 for?\\\\nContext: In 1998, she won the Best Supporting Actress Award at Cannes Film Festival."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. If the count of numbers is more than that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers Win'. If the count of alphabets is more than that of numbers in the list, answer 'Alphabets Win'. If the count of numbers is same as that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers and Alphabets are Tied'.\\n\\n['k', 'x', '2025', '3487', 'R', 'E', '6261', 'e', '6119', '2661', '6701', 'f', 'o', '2639', '4903', '4219', 'B', '8267', '1707', '173', 'z', '9785', '839', 'f', '9287', 'w', 'r', '717', '5133', 'K', '8959', '1525', 'U']","target":"Numbers Win","rationale":"Among the given list, there are 21 numbers and 16 alphabets. Therefore, the count of numbers is more than that of alphabets. Hence, the answer should be 'Numbers Win'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two natural language statements with similar wording. You must choose the statement that makes less sense based on common sense knowledge. A '\\n' separates the statements. Use \\"first\\" or \\"second\\" to indicate which sentence makes less sense.\\n\\nHe puts the lotion in the basket\\nHe rubs the lotion on the basket","target":"second","rationale":"The first statement makes sense because the lotion can be placed in the basket. But the second statement does not make sense because people or animals cannot \\"rub lotion on a basket\\"."},{"source":"Communities contain\\n\\nPick the right answer from the list:\\n- sparse flora and fauna\\n- two or three species of similar animals\\n- a diverse selection of living beings\\n- one species dominating an area","target":"a diverse selection of living beings","rationale":"A community is an assemblage of populations of different species, occupying the same geographical area and in a particular time.\\nSince there are usually more than one organisms living together to make up a single community, it can be inferred that communities contain: \\"a diverse selection of living beings\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input i,A where i is an integer and A is an array. You need to find every ith element of A starting with the 1st element.\\n\\n9, ['431', 'W', 'x', 'z', 'Y', 'U', 'N', 'K', '2179', 'Z', '7011', '6203', '9605', 'A', 'x', 'Y', '5553', 'i', 'M', '7397', 't', '5287', 'C', '8793', 'G', '4769', '9647', 'O', 'G', '4685', '6857', 'H', '8773', 's', 'J', '4107', 'u', '1275', '5219', 'd']","target":"431, Z, M, O, u","rationale":"Given the list ['431', 'W', 'x', 'z', 'Y', 'U', 'N', 'K', ...], we need to find every 9th element.\\\\n1. The 9nd element is 431.\\\\n2. The 18th element is Z (or z).\\\\n3. The 27th element is M (or m).\\\\n4. The 36th element is O (or o).\\\\n5. The 45th element is u (or U)\\\\nThe final output should be [431, Z, M, O, u]."},{"source":"Solve 5*g - 164*g + 3476 = -g for g.","target":"22","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable g on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] 5*g - 164*g + 3476 = -g\\n[STEP 2] 169*g = 3477\\n[STEP3] g = 3477 / 169\\n[STEP4] g = 22"},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the other-need strategy, otherwise output No. other-need is a selfish negotiation strategy. It is used when the participants discuss a need for someone else rather than themselves. For instance, describing the need for firewood to keep the kids warm.\\n\\nContext: 'Hi:  I  have invited friends from a nearby campsite for dinner and i heard it is going to be really cold tonight. I would prefer to have some extra fire wood for sure. lly cold tonight.' 'Hi I am also going camping. Unfortunately I need as much firewood and water as possible too. I need to be able to cook our food and stay warm all night ' 'Can I ask how many people are camping with you? Are you planning on hiking the mountain?'\\nUtterance: 'Oh yes, I have my whole family coming. I'm really excited because we don't see each other often. My aunts, uncles, cousins. Some of us will hike while others stay back. Maybe we can come to an agreement? Will you also be hiking?'","target":"No","rationale":"The speaker is simply describing their family situation rather than discussing a need for someone else, so the utterance does not contain the other-need strategy. If the speaker had said something like \\"I have my whole family coming and I'm worried about keeping them warm\\", that would be an example of the other-need strategy. However, since this is not mentioned in this case, we can say that it does not contain an example of the other-need strategy and output No as our answer.\\""},{"source":"The goal is to predict an English answer string for an input English question. \\nQuestion : \\"Which word meaning a dreadful noise, derives from the Greek for \\"\\"bad sounds\\"\\"?\\"\\nAnswer :","target":"CACOPHANY","rationale":"The answer to the question is \\"CACOPHANY\\", because its meaning refers to a dreadful noise, and it derives from the word cacophony which means harsh or discordant sound. The Greek root for bad sounds would be kakos (Œ∫Œ±Œ∫ŒøŒ∂) as in \\"kaka\\" which does not have any relation with this term but could mean shit or feces."},{"source":"There are more than 3000 languages in the world today, but only about ten are major languages of the world. Among them English is the most popular.\\nMore than 350 million people speak English as their first language. Major English-speaking countries are Britain, Australia, New Zealand, Canada and the USA. Another 400 million speak it as a second language. No one knows how many people speak English as a foreign language. They usually learn English as a school subject instead of learning it from their parents. Chinese is the only language with more speakers than English. This is because of the large population of China.\\nEnglish is the language for a better understanding between peoples of the world. It is also the language for business and science. Nearly half of the business deals in Europe are done in English, and more than half of the science magazines are in English. English is widely used in the world's computer network. And children should begin with English when they learn how to use computers. Through the English language peoples of different countries are able to work together and make things even better.\\nIf you know English, you'll be able to   _  .\\nA) do everything better than before\\nB) understand what people from different countries say\\nC) read nearly all the science magazines in the world\\nD) read many science magazines in the world","target":"D","rationale":"The passage says that English is the most popular language in world. It also mentions people speaking it as a first, second or foreign language. The main reason given for its popularity is its use in business, science and computers. So among options A to D, only option B will be correct answer because of it's relation with understanding what people from different countries say."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"SC Bern is the major ice hockey team of Bern who plays at the PostFinance Arena. The team has ranked highest in attendance for a European hockey team for more than a decade. The PostFinance Arena was the main host of the 2009 IIHF Ice Hockey World Championship, including the opening game and the final of the tournament.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: what is the first span of time mentioned?","target":"more than a decade","rationale":"The passage mentions the team's attendance numbers and notes that they have \\"ranked highest in attendance for a European hockey team for more than a decade\\". So, based on this information it can be concluded that the first span of time mentioned is 'more than a decade'."},{"source":"Given the following context:\\n\\nAfter his stern Uncle Daniel describes him as a \\"millstone\\" for neglecting his chores, ten year old Toby Tyler runs away from his foster home to join the circus. There he soon befriends Mr. Stubbs, a frisky chimpanzee. However, the circus isn't all fun and games. His employer Harry Tupper, the candy vendor, is dishonest and greedy. He convinces Toby that his Aunt Olive and Uncle Daniel don't love him or want him back and hides their letters. Toby resigns himself to circus life, even scoring himself a much bigger role, when he replaces the uppity, self-centered boy bareback rider after an injury. When Toby discovers, with the help of Mr. Stubbs, that Harry lied to him about his aunt and uncle he departs the circus for home. Mr. Stubbs follows him and Toby decides to take the chimp home with him. Soon after, though, Mr. Stubbs is chased by a hunter's dog. The hunter, Jim Weaver, accidentally shoots Mr. Stubbs just as Harry arrives to haul Toby back to the circus.  \\nBack at the circus, Toby finds his aunt and uncle in attendance, leading to a tearful reunion. When Harry tries to pursue Toby, he's obstructed by Ben, who confronts him for tampering with Toby's mail and warns him to leave him alone. Joyfully, just before Toby's performance, with his family in attendance, he discovers that Mr. Stubbs has survived his wounds, having been brought back to the circus by Jim. Relieved, Toby begins his performance on horseback, only to have Mr. Stubbs jump down from the trapeze to join him, thus creating a wonderful new act for the circus.\\n\\nanswer the following question:\\n\\nWhat is the full name of the person Ben warned to leave Toby Tyler alone?","target":"Harry Tupper","rationale":"Ben confronted Harry for tampering with Toby's mail and warned him to leave Toby alone. We do not have enough information about Ben, so we cannot determine his relationship with Harry or who he is in relation to the other characters. However, we can infer that this encounter happened at the circus because all of these events are taking place there (the context mentions a reunion between Aunt Olive and Uncle Daniel which implies it took place after they arrived at the circus). Since everything was happening at the circus during this time period, then it would follow that Ben also works for or frequents the same circus as well.\\nSo our answer is: \\"Harry Tupper\\"."},{"source":"You will be given a topic and an argument. Your task is to answer whether the topic and the argument are related or not. A related argument should provide more details about the outcomes of the topic. If the argument refers to or suggests a consequence related to that topic, answer with \\"yes\\"; otherwise, answer with \\"no\\".\\n\\ntopic: Assassination of a Dictator\\nargument: Targeted assassinations are consistent with international law","target":"no","rationale":"This argument does not provide any information about the consequences of assassinating dictators. The options and answer cannot be determined from the given passage."},{"source":"A ploynomial equation is a sum of terms. Here each term is either a constant number, or consists of the variable x raised to a certain power and multiplied by a number. These numbers are called weights. For example, in the polynomial: 2x^2+3x+4, the weights are: 2,3,4. You can present a polynomial with the list of its weights, for example, equation weights = [6, 4] represent the equation 6x + 4 and equation weights = [1, 3, 4] represent the equation 1x^2 + 3x + 4. In this task, you need to compute the result of a polynomial expression by substituing a given value of x in the given polynomial equation. Equation weights are given as a list.\\n\\nx = 6, equation weights = [8, 9]","target":"57","rationale":"The given polynomial equation is: 8x + 9\\\\nSubstituting x = 6, we get: 8(6) + 9 = 48 + 9 = 57\\",\\n  \\"task_data\\": {\\n    \\"instructions\\": [\\n      \\"<table>\\\\n<tr><td>Example 1</td></tr>\\\\n<tr><td>[Instruction and Question]</td></tr>\\\\n<tr><td>You are provided with an arithmetic question. Your task is to compute the solution using the given arithmetic operations. The only arithmetic operators needed to answer the questions are'+'(addition) and'-'(subtraction). The answer should be correct to one decimal place.</td></tr>\\\\n<tr><td>[Question]</td></tr> \\\\n<tr><td style=\\\\\\"text-align:center;\\\\\\">Keith spent $6.5 on a rabbit toy, $5.79 on pet food, and a cagecost him $12.51. He found a dollar bill on the ground. What was the total cost of Keith's purchases? </span></h4></strong>\\"],\\n    \\"questions\\": [{\\n      \\"question\\": [{"},{"source":"Math problem: Solve 1487*m - 980 = 1389*m for m.\\nWhat is the solution?","target":"10","rationale":"[STEP 1] 1487*m - 1389*m = 980\\n[STEP 2] 98 * m = 980\\n[STEP3] m = 980/98\\n[STEP4] m=10"},{"source":"Write down the solution for this math problem: Solve -18*v + 36 = -0*v for v.","target":"2","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable v on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] 18*v - 0*v = 36\\n[STEP 2] 18*v = 36\\n[STEP3] v = 36 / 18\\n[STEP4] v = 2"},{"source":"Given a passage and a query based on the passage, generate an unambiguous, concise and simple answer to the query from information in the passage. Note that the answer may not be present in exact form.\\n\\nIn addition to explaining the results of the test, your extension agent will be able to advise you on how to amend your soil so it‚Äôs prepared for that new grass. If you‚Äôre hiring a landscape company to put in a new lawn, don‚Äôt assume they‚Äôll take a soil sample and test it. Ask whoever you hire to do a test before they pull up to your house with a truck load of sod. Skipping a soil test could be an expensive mistake. Your costly new sod could die, or you could waste money on fertilizers. Lawns thrive and look lush when the pH level is between 6.5 and 7.0 . Too high a pH level can be corrected with sulfate, while soil with a low pH can be corrected with lime. You can correct your soil acidity once you know how to balance the lawn pH. Purchase a soil test kit, which is available at most hardware stores and plant nurseries. Use a soil test kit to measure the pH levels in areas of your lawn. Read the instructions on the kit. By testing different areas of your lawn initially, you can treat the lawn as necessary and create a balanced pH level throughout. Most test kits require that you use a small amount of air-dried soil Soil pH is the measure of a soil‚Äôs level of acidity or alkalinity, and it affects how well grass can pick up nutrients from the soil. Check with your extension agent on the best pH level for the grass in your area. ‚ÄúPH is going to determine how well your grass will grow,‚Äù says Peiffer.‚ÄùPH is the key factor to just about everything.‚Äù Lawn Soil Analysis - Cheaper Than You Think. 1  General Lawn Care. 2  Lawn Repair. 3  Lawn Watering. 4  Lawn Mowing. 5  Weeds | Pests | Diseases. 6  Lawn Varieties. How to Get Your Soil Tested. 1  To Take a Soil Sample: 2  Use a trowel, shovel, soil probe, sampling tube or soil auger. 3  Sample to a depth of 4-6 inches. 4  Remove any grass, thatch or debris. 5  Take 5 or 6 samples, mix them thoroughly in a plastic bucket and ensure you have approximately 1 pint of soil. Some plants, such as certain culinary herbs, will eventually die if their roots stay too wet. 1  To test your soil‚Äôs drainage: 2  Dig a hole about six inches wide and one foot deep. 3  Fill the hole with water and let it drain completely. 4  Fill it with water again. 5  Keep track of how long it takes for the water to drain. Anything you don't understand about lawn care, just ask us - we can help! Adjust Soil pH. To get the most from your lawn fertilizer applications, your soil pH needs to have about a 6.5 value. It is best to have the pH analyzed with a soil test each year or anytime you notice a decline in the appearance of your lawn. Liming can be done in spring or fall, but is not recommended during the hot summer months. To raise the pH of your soil, add lime (see chart below). Lawn Aeration and the importance of a PH check and Lime Application to your lawn - Duration: 2:44. PeninsularPest 13,465 views In order to ensure good growth, you need to know two things: the pH range under which your plants will comfortably thrive and the pH level of your soil. You can find out about your plants by doing a quick Google search or talking to a knowledgeable gardener or botanist. Gather 3-5 samples from different parts of your lawn, each from 4-6‚Äù below the surface. 1  Remove any grass, thatch or debris from your samples. 2  Thoroughly mix your samples to ensure you have enough soil to test, as required in the kit. 3  Spread over newspaper and allow soil to dry out, at least 24 hours. Query: how do you check ph on your lawn","target":"To check ph on your lawn, purchase a soil test kit and read the instructions on the kit","rationale":"Here's an unambiguous answer to the given query: To check ph on your lawn, purchase a soil test kit and read the instructions on the kit."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, a context passage, and four options which are terms from the passage. After reading a passage, you will get a brief understanding of the terms. Your job is to determine by searching and reading further information of which term you can answer the question. Indicate your choice as 'a', 'b', 'c', or 'd'. If you think more than one option is plausible, choose the more probable option to help you answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: How old were Suda and Mikami when they collaborated on Killer7? Passage:The game's history can be traced back to 2005, when Goichi Suda and Shinji Mikami (creator of the Resident Evil series) became good friends while working together on Killer7. Suda wanted to make a survival horror game exclusively for the PlayStation 3. With his first horror title  receiving decent sales in Japan by 2006, Suda immediately began working on Kurayami (Japanese for 'Darkness') in his spare time. It was at one time thought to be called \\"Closer\\". However, EA later confirmed that name had been abandoned for another title. By the Electronic Entertainment Expo (E3) in 2006, a publisher for Kurayami had not yet been established. In 2008, Suda presented the game's concept to EA Games, who agreed to license the Unreal Engine 3 and to publish the game to a worldwide audience. Shinji Mikami was then invited to executive-produce the project. Suda wanted to announce the game at E3 2009, but was not allowed to do so, due to a media silence agreement between Grasshopper Manufacture and EA Games. That December, Akira Yamaoka (sound designer for the Silent Hill series) left Konami after finishing his work on  and joined Grasshopper Manufacture because he enjoyed the latter's game No More Heroes. Yamaoka began work as the sound designer for the game. The game went about five different versions until Electronics Arts approved it. The newly titled Shadows of the Damned was finally unveiled at the Tokyo Game Show in 2010 as an action game.\\n Links: a. Goichi Suda b. Unreal Engine c. Akira Yamaoka d. Killer7","target":"a","rationale":"The question asks \\"How old were Suda and Mikami when they collaborated on Killer7?\\" The answer can be found by reading further information about the term \\"Goichi Suda\\"."},{"source":"You are given a new situation: The city of Riga is situated at 56 degrees N, and its sister city Kobe, Japan is situated at 34 degrees N, on a different circle of latitude.\\n\\nand a hint : Circles of latitude are often called parallels because they are parallel to each other; that is, any two circles are always the same distance apart. A location's position along a circle of latitude is given by its longitude. Circles of latitude are unlike circles of longitude, which are all great circles with the centre of Earth in the middle, as the circles of latitude get smaller as the distance from the Equator increases. Their length can be calculated by a common sine or cosine function. The 60th parallel north or south is half as long as the Equator (disregarding Earth's minor flattening by 0.3%). A circle of latitude is perpendicular to all meridians.\\n\\nPlease answer this question : Which city is situated farther from the Polar Circle?","target":"Kobe","rationale":"The city of Kobe, Japan (34 degrees N) is situated farther from the Polar Circle. The Polar circle is located at 66.5 degrees North latitude and its Southern counterpart is the Antarctic polar circle which lies on the opposite side of the earth at 66.5 degrees South Latitude"},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and extract the answer for the question: What was the name of the person who moved his family from Cecil Court?\\n\\nThe Mozarts' first London lodgings were above a barber's shop in Cecil Court, near St Martin-in-the-Fields. Letters of introduction from Paris proved effective; on 27 April 1764, four days after their arrival, the children were playing before King George III and his 19-year-old German queen, Charlotte Sophia. A second royal engagement was fixed for 19 May, at which Wolfgang was asked by the king to play pieces by Handel, Johann Christian Bach and Carl Friedrich Abel. He was allowed to accompany the queen as she sang an aria, and he later improvised on the bass part of a Handel aria from which, according to Leopold, he produced \\"the most beautiful melody in such a manner that everyone was astonished\\".Many of the nobility and gentry were leaving town for the summer, but Leopold reckoned that most would return for the king's birthday celebrations on 4 June, and accordingly organised a concert for the 5th. This was deemed a success, and Leopold hastened to arrange for Wolfgang to appear at a benefit concert for a maternity hospital on 29 June, at Ranelagh Pleasure Gardens. Leopold apparently saw this effort to support charitable works as \\"a way to earn the love of this very special nation\\". Wolfgang was advertised as \\"the celebrated and astonishing Master Mozart, a Child of Seven Years of Age...\\" (he was in fact eight), \\"justly esteemed the most extraordinary Prodigy, and most amazing Genius, that has appeared in any Age\\". On 8 July there was a private performance at the Grosvenor Square home of the Earl of Thanet, from which Leopold returned with an inflammation of the throat and other worrying symptoms. \\"Prepare your heart to hear one of the saddest events\\", he wrote to Hagenauer in anticipation of his own imminent demise. He was ill for several weeks, and for the sake of his health the family moved from their Cecil Court lodgings to a house in the countryside, at 180 Ebury Street, then considered part of the village of Chelsea.","target":"Leopold","rationale":"The rationale is to look for a name. In the text, we see that Leopold moved his family from Cecil Court and recounts the events of their first summer in London."},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: Daniel went to the bathroom. Sandra went to the hallway. John went to the office. Sandra journeyed to the garden. Mary went back to the garden. Mary went to the bedroom. Daniel went to the bedroom. Sandra journeyed to the hallway. Sandra went back to the kitchen. Daniel journeyed to the hallway. Question: Where is Mary?","target":"bedroom","rationale":"Mary's most recent destination is the bedroom, as indicated by the fifth fact in the passage which states \\"Mary went to the bedroom.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you're given an open-domain question. Your task is to provide an answer to the given question. There is only one unique answer for each question. Your answer should be short, and refer to an entity, date, number, etc. Do not put your answer in the context of a sentence.\\n\\nAnimals that give birth to their young ones alive are called?","target":"viviparous","rationale":"The correct answer is viviparous because it means that animals give birth to their young ones alive."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to the associated containers is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its associated container B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate container for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\npicture : frame. silverware : ?","target":"drawer","rationale":"Picture is typically in a frame and silverware is in a drawer."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a conversation between a flight agent and the customer. You are given 4 options and you need to select the goal of the conversation. It is provided as part of customer's context, which has to be one of the following: \`book\`: Make a new reservation, \`cancel\`: Cancel an existing reservation, \`no_flight\`: No flight found for the customer's preference, \`no_reservation\`: No reservation / No change / No cancellation was made in the conversation, mostly enquiring details\\n\\ncustomer: Hello. \\n agent: Hello. How can I assist you today? \\n customer: I want to travel from MSP to ORD. Can you help me to book a flight ticket? \\n agent: Please can I know your dates of journey to book? \\n customer: I want to fly in the flight on Nov 03 and Nov 05. \\n agent: Ok, please let me know your specifications. \\n customer: I prefer to travel in economy class. \\n agent: There is a flight ticket available for a connecting flight for the airfare 200. Can I book a flight 1023? \\n customer: Proceed to booking. \\n agent: Ok, please let me know your name to proceed. \\n customer: I am Jason Wright. \\n agent: The flight ticket is been confirmed and the airlines s Hawaiian. Thank you for choosing our agency. \\n customer: Thank you for your help.","target":"book","rationale":"The customer is asking the flight agent to book a flight ticket from MSP to ORD. The agent then asks for the dates of travel, and the customer mentions their preference (economy class). The agent then says that there is a flight ticket available and proceeds to book it. Thus, the goal of this conversation was \`booking\`"},{"source":"Question: Why did the Nicaraguans come to America?\\n\\nIs \\"Throughout the 1980s with the United States supported Contra War (or Contra-revolutionary war) which continued up until 1988, and the economic collapse of the country many more Nicaraguans migrated to the United States amongst other countries.\\" the correct answer?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The correct answer should be \\"to escape the civil wars and economic crisis in their country\\", which is not provided as an option."},{"source":"The following article contains an answer for the question: What is the full name of the person who designed the monument that had an inscription removed in 1830? , can you please find it? \\n\\nRadical rebuilding schemes poured in for the gutted City and were encouraged by Charles. If it had been rebuilt under some of these plans, London would have rivalled Paris in Baroque magnificence (see Evelyn's plan on the right). The Crown and the City authorities attempted to establish \\"to whom all the houses and ground did in truth belong\\" to negotiate with their owners about compensation for the large-scale remodelling that these plans entailed, but that unrealistic idea had to be abandoned. Exhortations to bring workmen and measure the plots on which the houses had stood were mostly ignored by people worried about day-to-day survival, as well as by those who had left the capital; for one thing, with the shortage of labour following the fire, it was impossible to secure workmen for the purpose. Apart from Wren and Evelyn, it is known that Robert Hooke, Valentine Knight, and Richard Newcourt proposed rebuilding plans.\\nWith the complexities of ownership unresolved, none of the grand Baroque schemes could be realised for a City of piazzas and avenues; there was nobody to negotiate with, and no means of calculating how much compensation should be paid. Instead, much of the old street plan was recreated in the new City, with improvements in hygiene and fire safety: wider streets, open and accessible wharves along the length of the Thames, with no houses obstructing access to the river, and, most importantly, buildings constructed of brick and stone, not wood. New public buildings were created on their predecessors' sites; perhaps the most famous is St Paul's Cathedral and its smaller cousins, Christopher Wren's 50 new churches.\\nOn Charles' initiative, a Monument to the Great Fire of London was erected near Pudding Lane, designed by Christopher Wren and Robert Hooke, standing 61 metres (200 ft) tall and known simply as \\"The Monument\\". It is a familiar London landmark which has since given its name to a tube station. In 1668, accusations against the Catholics were added to the inscription on the Monument which...","target":"Christopher Wren","rationale":"Read the article and find an answer.\\nThe Monument to the Great Fire of London was designed by Christopher Wren and Robert Hooke, so the answer is Christopher Wren.\\""},{"source":"Based on the premise \\"I'll hunt them down! \\", can we conclude the hypothesis \\"I'm letting them go.\\" is true (see options)?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise \\"I'll hunt them down!\\" suggests that the speaker will not let them go. So, we cannot conclude that the hypothesis is true and therefore the answer should be 'no'.\\n\`"},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: Does the sentence \\"The Yiddish linguist Max Weinreich published the expression, A shprakh iz a dialekt mit an armey un flot (\\"◊ê÷∑ ◊©◊§÷º◊®◊ê÷∑◊ö ◊ê◊ô◊ñ ◊ê÷∑ ◊ì◊ô◊ê÷∑◊ú◊¢◊ß◊ò ◊û◊ô◊ò ◊ê÷∑◊ü ◊ê÷∑◊®◊û◊≤ ◊ê◊ï◊ü ◊§÷ø◊ú◊ê÷∏◊ò\\"‚Äé:\\" provide a valid answer to the question \\"What does \\"A shprakh iz a dialekt mit an armey un flot\\" mean in English?\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The given sentence does not provide a valid answer to the question as it only states that this expression was published by Max Weinreich and does not state what translation of \\"A shprakh iz a dialekt mit an armey un flot\\" is."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a context, a sentence,  and a character. The sentence describes an action or job of the given character. Also, the context provides more information about the sentence or the character. Your task is to return one of the emotions which are expressed by the Character in the given sentence. For that you can use the Context; however, Context is not provided in all the inputs. Also, in some inputs, there can be zero emotion; for that return 'None'.\\n\\nContext: Joe had a girlfriend he loved very much. They had both finished college and had big plans. One morning, Joe decided he wanted to travel. He talked with his girlfriend, but she wanted a family. \\n Sentence: Joe gave up on all of his dreams of travel to raise children. \\n Character: Girlfriend","target":"sad","rationale":"In the context, we can see that Joe and his girlfriend both have big plans for their future, but those plans are different. While Joe wants to travel, his girlfriend wants a family. Since Joe decides to give up on traveling in order to raise children with his girlfriend, she would most likely be happy with this decision. However, since her goal was having a family and not raising children specifically, she is likely sad that they had to compromise on their original plans."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nMia entered the crawlspace. Oliver entered the crawlspace. The tangerine is in the red_envelope. Oliver exited the crawlspace. Mia moved the tangerine to the blue_treasure_chest. Mia entered the bedroom. Benjamin entered the bedroom. The strawberry is in the blue_pantry. Benjamin exited the bedroom. Mia moved the strawberry to the green_treasure_chest. Oliver entered the crawlspace. Amelia entered the crawlspace. The celery is in the blue_treasure_chest. Amelia exited the crawlspace. Oliver moved the celery to the red_envelope. Oliver entered the pantry. Mia entered the pantry. The grapes is in the green_box. Mia exited the pantry. Oliver moved the grapes to the blue_bathtub. Phone rang. Where does Oliver think that Mia searches for the grapes?","target":"green_box","rationale":"Oliver enters the pantry. Mia enters the pantry and then exits the pantry. The grapes is in the green_box. Oliver moves the grapes to the blue_bathtub, but at this point Mia has exited so he does not know that she moved it from there to somewhere else. There is no indication that Oliver would believe that Mia searches for anything anywhere else other than green_box since he left it there and was not aware of her moving it elsewhere after leaving her in green_box"},{"source":"Answer the question...who is 2nd in line to the british throne??","target":"Charles, Prince of Wales","rationale":"In the United Kingdom, succession to the throne is governed by a constitutional monarchy. Therefore, it would be reasonable that in order for someone to answer this question correctly they must understand and know what the regulations are outlined in their constitution regarding who can succeed to their country's thrown. \\nBased on these criteria, Charles, Prince of Wales meets all requirements because he is first-in line according to UK law as well as recognized internationally (across many countries/cultures) based on his position within The Commonwealth Realm ."},{"source":"Exercise: read the text and answer the question by True or False.\\n\\nText: Geek Squad -- In 2007, Geek Squad officially added Magnolia Home Theater installation teams as well as Best Buy Mobile Installers to the Geek Squad brand. The change was titled, \`\`Total Services'' and was aimed towards the combination of major Best Buy services into one cohesive unit. Best Buy mobile installers and Magnolia Home Theater installers have now switched from their previous grey and blue uniforms to grey and orange shirts with grey cargo pants. This change removed all \`\`Magnolia Home Theater Installation'' branding and was replaced by \`\`Geek Squad Installation Units'' instead. This has now allowed Geek Squad to incorporate home theater installation as one of the in home services offered via telephone.\\nQuestion: is geek squad only for best buy products?","target":"False","rationale":"The text discusses Geek Squad's services of installing mobile devices and home theaters. In 2007, they added new employees to their brand who would install non-Best Buy products as well. This suggests that it is not true that Geek Squad only installs Best Buy products, so the answer is False."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people. 'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. If the conversation begins with a question, label it '1' otherwise '0'.\\n\\n Person1:     What ‚Äô re you doing now ? \\n Person2:  I ‚Äô m watching TV . \\n Person1:      You ‚Äô re supposed to clean your teeth before you go to bed . \\n Person2:  I will . \\n Person1:      And don ‚Äô t ever forget it .","target":"1","rationale":"The first dialogue is a question and the rest are statements. Hence, the correct label is 1 (question)."},{"source":"Determine the question that you might have asked to get back the following answer for the given context\\nContext: The BCG vaccine has limitations, and research to develop new TB vaccines is ongoing. A number of potential candidates are currently in phase I and II clinical trials. Two main approaches are being used to attempt to improve the efficacy of available vaccines. One approach involves adding a subunit vaccine to BCG, while the other strategy is attempting to create new and better live vaccines. MVA85A, an example of a subunit vaccine, currently in trials in South Africa, is based on a genetically modified vaccinia virus. Vaccines are hoped to play a significant role in treatment of both latent and active disease.;\\nAnswer: vaccinia;\\nQuestion:","target":"What genetically modified virus was used to develop MVA85A?","rationale":"The context mentions that MVA85A is an example of a subunit vaccine. It also indicates that it was developed using genetically modified vaccinia virus and currently in trials in South Africa. Therefore, the question you would have asked to get back \\"vaccinia\\" as the answer is: What genetically modified virus was used to develop MVA85A?"},{"source":"Article: Santa Monica is a beachfront city in western Los Angeles County, California, United States. The city is named after the Christian saint, Monica. Situated on Santa Monica Bay, it is bordered on three sides by the city of Los Angeles ‚Äì Pacific Palisades to the north, Brentwood on the northeast, Sawtelle on the east, Mar Vista on the southeast, and Venice on the south. Santa Monica is well known for its affluent single-family neighborhoods but also has many neighborhoods consisting primarily of condominiums and apartments. Over two-thirds of Santa Monica's residents are renters. The Census Bureau population for Santa Monica in 2010 was 89,736.\\n\\nNow answer this question: What was the population in 2010 according to the Census Bureau?","target":"89,736","rationale":"The population in 2010 is given as 89,736."},{"source":"Hoping to rebound from their divisional road loss to the Packers, the Vikings' Week 11 opponent was the Oakland Raiders, who had former Vikings quarterback Daunte Culpepper under center. After a 79-yard pass from wide receiver Sidney Rice to Visanthe Shiancoe on the first play from scrimmage, the Vikings scored on the very next play on a 10-yard run from Chester Taylor. This was followed by a safety when Culpepper was penalized for intentional grounding in his own endzone. Two plays after the ensuing free kick, the Vikings fumbled the ball just inside Oakland territory, allowing the Raiders to set up a 42-yard field goal for Sebastian Janikowski. On the next drive, the Vikings restored their nine-point lead as kicker Ryan Longwell hit a 30-yard field goal on the first play of the second quarter. A short Oakland drive culminating in 10-yard touchdown pass from Culpepper to tight end John Madsen, followed by another Janikowski field goal, saw the Raiders take the lead for the first time. Four plays later, Minnesota regained a six-point lead on a 38-yard touchdown run from Taylor, but field goals of 42 and 49 yards from Janikowski meant the first half ended with the scores level at 19-19. The Vikings recorded the only score of the third quarter on a 38-yard field goal from Longwell, though they did finish the period on the Raiders' 6-yard line, allowing Taylor to run in his third touchdown on the opening play of the fourth quarter, the first time in his career that he scored three touchdowns in one game. A 52-yard field goal from Janikowski narrowed the margin to 7 points with less than three-and-a-half minutes to play, and after forcing the Vikings to punt just inside the two-minute warning, they had one last chance to level the scores. On the first play of the drive, Culpepper threw the ball in the direction of Justin Fargas, who tipped it up, allowing Chad Greenway to come up with an interception; he went to ground with the ball, but inexplicably got up and attempted to advance it, which allowed left tackle Barry Sims to force a fumble, recovered by right guard Paul McQuistan. That enabled the Raiders to extend their drive, but although they managed to get into Vikings territory, a false start penalty meant Culpepper had to attempt a Hail Mary pass on the final play, but it came up short, giving the Vikings a 29-22 win.\\n\\nHow many yards was the longest field goal?","target":"52","rationale":"The longest field goal in the passage was a 52-yard one from Janikowski."},{"source":"Multi-select: Is it possible to draw the conclusion that \\"The train was short, so it worked out.\\" if \\"My meeting started at 4:00 and I needed to catch the train at 4:30, so there wasn't much time. Luckily, it was short, so it worked out.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"The second statement does not provide enough information to determine that the train was short. The only fact we can deduce from this sentence is that there wasn't much time before the meeting, which means nothing about the length of the train journey itself. So, it's impossible to draw a conclusion here and you should choose \\"no\\"."},{"source":"You are given two sentences. You have to find if there is entailment or agreement of the Hypothesis by the Premise. From the given pair of sentences, you should identify if there is enough information in the Premise to support the claim made in the Hypothesis. The Premise may not exactly be the same as Hypothesis. Your task is to return 'entails' if the premise supports hypothesis else return 'neutral'.\\n\\nPremise: gradualism versus punctuated equilibrium as two different views; \\n Hypothesis: Darwin believed in gradualism.","target":"neutral","rationale":"The premise provides information about gradualism and punctuated equilibrium, which are two different views in evolutionary biology. It does not provide any information about what Darwin believed in. Therefore, there is no direct connection between the premise and the hypothesis, and the premise does not provide enough information to support or refute the claim made in the hypothesis. As a result, the output should be \\"neutral\\"."},{"source":"Write the conversation response. Hi,","target":"Hey how is everything?","rationale":"Hi is a greeting, and the response is Hey how is everything?"},{"source":"A \\"grand\\", sometimes shortened to simply \\"G\\", is a common term for the amount of $1,000. The suffix \\"K\\" or \\"k\\" (from \\"kilo -\\") is also commonly used to denote this amount (such as \\"$10 k\\" to mean $10,000). However, the $1,000 note is no longer in general use. A \\"large\\" or \\"stack\\", it is usually a reference to a multiple of $1,000 (such as \\"fifty large\\" meaning $50,000). The $100 note is nicknamed \\"Benjamin\\", \\"Benji\\", \\"Ben\\", or \\"Franklin\\" (after Benjamin Franklin), \\"C-note\\" (C being the Roman numeral for 100), \\"Century note\\" or \\"bill\\" (e.g. \\"two bills\\" being $200). The $50 note is occasionally called a \\"yardstick\\" or a \\"grant\\" (after President Ulysses S. Grant, pictured on the obverse). The $20 note is referred to as a \\"double sawbuck\\", \\"Jackson\\" (after Andrew Jackson), or \\"double eagle\\". The $10 note is referred to as a \\"sawbuck\\", \\"ten-spot\\" or \\"Hamilton\\" (after Alexander Hamilton). The $5 note as \\"Lincoln\\", \\"fin\\", \\"fiver\\" or \\"five-spot\\". The infrequently-used $2 note is sometimes called \\"deuce\\", \\"Tom\\", or \\"Jefferson\\" (after Thomas Jefferson). The $1 note as a \\"single\\" or \\"buck\\". The dollar has also been referred to as a \\"bone\\" and \\"bones\\" in plural (e.g. \\"twenty bones\\" is equal to $20). The newer designs, with portraits displayed in the main body of the obverse (rather than in cameo insets), upon paper color-coded by denomination, are sometimes referred to as \\"bigface\\" notes or \\"Monopoly money\\".\\n\\nAnswer this question: who's face is on the two dollar bill?","target":"Thomas Jefferson","rationale":"This is the relevant information: The infrequently-used $2 note is sometimes called \\"deuce\\", \\"Tom\\", or \\"Jefferson\\" (after Thomas Jefferson)."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of integers. You should find the minimum absolute difference between 2 integers in the list. The absolute difference is the absolute value of one integer subtracted by another. The output should be a single integer which is the smallest possible absolute distance.\\n\\n[73, -68, -56, -7, 9]","target":"12","rationale":"Given the list [73, -68, -56, -7, 9], let's try one by one:\\\\n1. The smallest possible absolute distance between 73 and any other element is between (-7) and (9), which is 12.\\\\n2. The smallest possible absolute distance between (-68) and any other element is between 73 and (-56), which is also 12.\\\\n3. The smallest possible absolute distance between (-56) and any other element is betwen 73 and (-68), which is also 12.\\\\n4. The smallest possible absolute distance between (-7) and any other element can be calculated in two ways:\\\\na) Between 73 and (9). That's the same as 1., so it's still 12; or\\\\nb) Between -68 to (-56). That would be 8 + 7 = 15 > 12; therefore we discard b)\\\\n5. Finally, the smallest possible absolute difference of 9 with any other elements will be less than or equal to 4 <12; therefore we discard '9'.\\\\nTherefore in total there are 3 different pairs of numbers that produce an absoulte difference of exactly '12', namely [-7 , 9], [-68 , 56] & [73 , -56]."},{"source":"Istanbul (CNN) -- A Syrian official said his country's forces might have thought the Turkish jet it downed last week was from Israel. \\"As you know there is a country called Israel there and as you know this Zionism country's planes are very similar and because they both are from the same factory, from the U.S., maybe Syria thought it was an Israeli plane,\\" Syrian Information Minister Omran Al Zubi told the Turkish A Haber channel on Wednesday. Israel and Syria are longtime neighboring adversaries and don't have diplomatic relations. Al Zubi adopted a friendly tone toward Turkey in the interview, which belied the increase in tough rhetoric in recent days over the downing of the jet. Relations between the two neighbors have deteriorated during the uprising against Syrian President Bashar al-Assad's regime.\\n@highlight\\nSyrian official calls Turks \\"our friends and brothers\\"\\n@highlight\\nHe said maybe Syrian forces thought the plane was from Israel\\n@highlight\\nTensions have flared over Syria's jet shootdown last week\\n@highlight\\nSyria and Turkey are looking for the missing pilots \\n@placeholder raised the stakes Monday in the war of words over the incident. \\n\\nYou should decide what \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to. Choose between:\\n- A Haber\\n- Al Zubi\\n- Bashar al-Assad\\n- CNN\\n- Israel\\n- Israeli\\n- Istanbul\\n- Omran Al Zubi\\n- Syria\\n- Syrian\\n- Turkey\\n- Turkish\\n- Turks\\n- U.S.\\n- Zionism","target":"Syria","rationale":"From the given context, it is clear that only \\"Syria\\" can be referred to by \\"@placeholder\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the middle and ending of a three-part story. Your job is to complete the short story by writing a probable beginning of the story. Generated sentences must be short, have fewer than 10 words, and be simple as if narrating to a child. Avoid using any irrelevant extra information when creating the beginning, and use names (e.g. Jack, Barbara,...) instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible.\\n\\nMiddle: Jill set up a video but her parents switched it. Ending: On the video she didn't see anyone putting it there!","target":"Jill had her suspicions about the tooth fairy","rationale":"Jill had her suspicions about the tooth fairy and decided to set up a video to capture proof."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a conversation between a flight agent and the customer. You are given 4 options and you need to select the goal of the conversation. It is provided as part of customer's context, which has to be one of the following: \`book\`: Make a new reservation, \`cancel\`: Cancel an existing reservation, \`no_flight\`: No flight found for the customer's preference, \`no_reservation\`: No reservation / No change / No cancellation was made in the conversation, mostly enquiring details\\n\\ncustomer: Hi,. \\n agent: Hello. How may I assist you? \\n customer: I want to see the art work in DM Weil Gallery at New York, can you please book me a ticket? \\n agent: Sure, I will help you in booking a ticket. \\n customer: Thank you. \\n agent: From where you are planning to take off? \\n customer: I am planning to start my journey from Charlotte, NC-CLT. \\n agent: Could you please share your journey dates? \\n customer: My journey dates are from 10/14 to 10/16. \\n agent: May I know your landing airport code? \\n customer: Landing point airport code is NY-JFK. \\n agent: Thank you for sharing the details, give me a minute to search for available flights on your route. \\n customer: Ok. \\n agent: Thanks for giving your valuable time. There is a connecting flight of UA airline running on your route with fare 300 having 1019 as flight number. Do you want me to confirm this flight for your journey? \\n customer: Do not confirm. As my budget is only 200. \\n agent: Ok, please provide your name for documentation purpose. \\n customer: Myself Jeffrey Wright. \\n agent: Thank you for approaching us. \\n customer: Thank you.","target":"no_reservation","rationale":"The conversation is mostly about enquiring the customer's preferences and giving them the flight options. However, no booking or cancellation was made during the course of this conversation and hence, the goal of this conversation is \`no_reservation\`.\\"\\n</p>"},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as acceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"David constructed a house out of bricks.","rationale":"Here's an example of a grammatically correct sentence:\\nDavid constructed a house out of bricks."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of numbers. You should remove any number that is not an integer (whole number). If every number is not an whole number then an empty list (\\"[]\\") should be returned. Otherwise, answer with the list of whole numbers separated by comma inside brackets.\\n\\n[38.653, -74]","target":"[-74]","rationale":"In the given list, 38.653 is not an integer, it will be removed and the resulting list will be [-74]."},{"source":"Based on the following passage, is there less nicotine in ultra light cigarettes? Lights (cigarette type) -- Cigarettes labeled as Lights, Milds, or Low-tar, are considered to have a lighter, less pronounced flavour than regular cigarettes. These cigarette brands may be listed as having lower levels of tar, nicotine, or other chemicals (as \`\`inhaled'' by a smoking machine). However, the scientific evidence is that switching from regular to light or low-tar cigarettes does not reduce the health risks of smoking or lower the smoker's exposure to the nicotine, tar, and carcinogens present in cigarette smoke.","target":"No","rationale":": None: In 1666 , Sir Isaac Newton noticed that when he passed white sunlight through a glass prism , it bent into"},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to identify whether the sentence is a question or not. Answer with Yes or No.\\n\\nI'd like it in the evening 5:30.","target":"No","rationale":"Although it is a statement, the answer No is correct as the sentence asks for some information from the virtual assistant which makes it a question."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a list of integers. You need to find the median of the list of integers and return that as the output. The median is the middle value in the list of numbers such that half of the elements are less than the median and the other half of elements are greater than the median.\\n\\n[291, 264, 20, 304, 44, 235, 344, 147, 409, 301, 227, 103, 442, 175, 448, 402, 71, 203, 101, 479, 455, 166, 382, 487, 297]","target":"291","rationale":"The median of the given list is 291."},{"source":"Decide the language of that sentence. The language can be English, French, German, Italian, or Spanish.\\n\\nText: 'si purtroppo'","target":"Italian","rationale":"The sentence is in Italian."},{"source":"Read the given text and if it has abusive content then indicate via \\"yes\\". Otherwise indicate via\\"no\\". \\nWe consider the content to be abusive if it contains any of the following instances: (1) Identity Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which contains a negative statement made against an identity. An identity is a social category that relates to a fundamental aspect of individuals community, socio-demographics, position or self-representation) (2) Affiliation Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which express negativity against an affiliation. We define affiliation as a (more or less) voluntary association with a collective. Affiliations include but are not limited to: memberships (e.g. Trade unions), party memberships (e.g. Republicans), political affiliations (e.g. Right-wing people) and occupations (e.g. Doctors).) (3) Person Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which directs negativity against an identifiable person, who is either part of the conversation thread or is named. Person-directed abuse includes serious character based attacks, such as accusing the person of lying, as well as aggression, insults and menacing language.) and (4) Counter Speech (e.g., Content which challenges, condemns or calls out the abusive language of others.). Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nLeft Winger gets **DESTROYED** by 4chan meme","target":"no","rationale":"The given post does not contain any of the instances that have been deemed abusive. Therefore, it can be classified as \\"No\\"."},{"source":"The task is to generate text based off of an event. For the given event, there will be a person who does the action in the event (usually PersonX). Your task is to write that persons intent behind doing the event, i.e. why did the person do that action.\\n\\nPersonX gains PersonY's confidence","target":"to be trusted","rationale":"The event states that PersonX gains PersonY's confidence. To gain someone's confidence means to be trusted by them. Therefore, the intent of the event is \\"to be trusted\\"."},{"source":"Given a passage with a question and an answer to that question, classify if the answer actually answers the question into 'yes' or 'no'. Output 'yes' if the answer answers the question and output 'no' if the answer does not answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Does lidocaine inhibit epithelial chemokine secretion via inhibition of nuclear factor kappa B activation?\\nAnswer: Lidocaine inhibits IL-8 and IP-10 secretion from intestinal cells. This effect is mediated by inhibition of NFkappaB activation via decreased IkappaB phosphorylation and is not mediated by lidocaine's effect on VGSC.","target":"yes","rationale":"The answer states that lidocaine inhibits the secretion of IL-8 and IP-10 from intestinal cells. The passage goes on to state that this inhibition occurs via the inhibition of NFkappaB activation and decreased IkappaB phosphorylation, but not by lidocaine's effect on VGSC. Thus, the answer explicitly addresses whether lidocaine inhibits epithelial chemokine secretion via inhibition of nuclear factor kappa B activation by stating that it does. Therefore, yes is the correct output for this example."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a abstract of article and corresponding title of an article. Your task is to generate label \\"yes\\" if title is right for article, otherwise generate \\"no\\".\\n\\nAbstract: Myeloid cells play pivotal roles in chronic inflammatory diseases through their broad proinflammatory, destructive, and remodeling capacities. CD200 is widely expressed on a variety of cell types, while the recently identified CD200R is expressed on myeloid cells and T cells. CD200 deletion in vivo results in myeloid cell dysregulation and enhanced susceptibility to autoimmune inflammation, suggesting that the CD200-CD200R interaction is involved in immune suppression. We demonstrate in this study that CD200R agonists suppress mouse and human myeloid cell function in vitro, and also define a dose relationship between receptor expression and cellular inhibition. IFN-gamma- and IL-17-stimulated cytokine secretion from mouse peritoneal macrophages was inhibited by CD200R engagement. Inhibitory effects were not universal, as LPS-stimulated responses were unaffected. Inhibition of U937 cell cytokine production correlated with CD200R expression levels, and inhibition was only observed in low CD200R expressing cells, if the CD200R agonists were further cross-linked. Tetanus toxoid-induced human PBMC IL-5 and IL-13 secretion was inhibited by CD200R agonists. This inhibition was dependent upon cross-linking the CD200R on monocytes, but not on cross-linking the CD200R on CD4+ T cells. In all, we provide direct evidence that the CD200-CD200R interaction controls monocyte/macrophage function in both murine and human systems, further supporting the potential clinical application of CD200R agonists for the treatment of chronic inflammatory diseases.. Title: Detection and function of nitric oxide during the hypersensitive response in Arabidopsis thaliana: where there's a will there's a way.","target":"no","rationale":"The title of the article is \\"Detection and function of nitric oxide during the hypersensitive response in Arabidopsis thaliana: where there's a will there's a way\\". This does not relate to any aspect or part of the abstract, which discusses myeloid cells, CD200R agonists for immune suppression, and their potential use as therapy for chronic inflammatory diseases. So it would be correct to answer \\"No\\""},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- The lion (\\"Panthera leo\\") is one of the big cats in the genus \\"Panthera\\" and a member of the family Felidae. The commonly used term African lion collectively denotes the several subspecies in Africa. With some males exceeding in weight, it is the second-largest living cat after the tiger. Wild lions currently exist in sub-Saharan Africa and in India (where an endangered remnant population resides in Gir Forest National Park). In ancient historic times, their range was in most of Africa, including North Africa, and across Eurasia from Greece and southeastern Europe to India. In the late Pleistocene, about 10,000¬†years ago, the lion was the most widespread large land mammal after humans: \\"Panthera leo spelaea\\" lived in northern and western Europe and \\"Panthera leo atrox\\" lived in the Americas from the Yukon to Peru. The lion is classified as a vulnerable species by the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN), having seen a major population decline in its African range of 3050% over two decades during the second half of the twentieth century. Lion populations are untenable outside designated reserves and national parks. Although the cause of the decline is not fully understood, habitat loss and conflicts with humans are the greatest causes of concern. Within Africa, the West African lion population is particularly endangered.\\n\\n- The British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC) is a British public service broadcaster. It is headquartered at Broadcasting House in London, is the world's oldest national broadcasting organisation, and is the largest broadcaster in the world by number of employees, with over 20,950 staff in total, of whom 16,672 are in public sector broadcasting; including part-time, flexible as well as fixed contract staff, the total number is 35,402.\\n\\n- Uganda (or ), officially the Republic of Uganda, is a landlocked country in East Africa. It is bordered to the east by Kenya, to the north by South Sudan, to the west by the Democratic Republic of the Congo, to the south-west by Rwanda, and to the south by Tanzania. Uganda is the world's second most populous landlocked country after Ethiopia. The southern part of the country includes a substantial portion of Lake Victoria, shared with Kenya and Tanzania. Uganda is in the African Great Lakes region. Uganda also lies within the Nile basin, and has a varied but generally a modified equatorial climate.\\n\\n- A national park is a park in use for conservation purposes. Often it is a reserve of natural, semi-natural, or developed land that a sovereign state declares or owns. Although individual nations designate their own national parks differently, there is a common idea: the conservation of 'wild nature' for posterity and as a symbol of national pride. An international organization, the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN), and its World Commission on Protected Areas, has defined \\"National Park\\" as its \\"Category¬†II\\" type of protected areas.\\n\\n- Panthera leo spelaea or P. spelaea, commonly known as the European or Eurasian cave lion, is an extinct subspecies of lion. It is known from fossils and many examples of prehistoric art.\\n\\n- The Serengeti National Park is a Tanzanian national park in the Serengeti ecosystem in the Mara and Simiyu regions. It is famous for its annual migration of over 1.5 million white bearded (or brindled) wildebeest and 250,000 zebra and for its numerous Nile crocodile and honey badger.\\n\\n- Broadcasting House is the headquarters of the BBC, in Portland Place and Langham Place, London. The first radio broadcast was made on 15 March 1932, and the building was officially opened two months later, on 15 May. The main building is in Art Deco style, with a facing of Portland stone over a steel frame. It is a Grade II* listed building and includes the BBC Radio Theatre, where music and speech programmes are recorded in front of a studio audience, and lobby that was used as a location for filming the 1998 BBC television series \\"In the Red\\".\\n\\n- Pride is a 2004 television film about two lion cubs as they grow up and face the harsh realities of adulthood . Produced by the BBC and shown on A&E in the U.S. , the film features the voices of numerous British actors and uses CGI technology to enhance footage of actual lions and other animals . Jim Henson 's Creature Shop provided the digital effects for the film . It was shot in Tanzania 's Serengeti National Park .\\n\\n- Yukon (also commonly called the Yukon) is the westernmost and smallest of Canada's three federal territories (the other two are Northwest Territories and Nunavut). The territory is very sparsely populated with its about 35,000 people on almost half a million square kilometres. Whitehorse is the territorial capital and Yukon's only city.\\n\\n- Sub-Saharan Africa is, geographically, the area of the continent of Africa that lies south of the Sahara desert. According to the UN, it consists of all African countries that are fully or partially located south of the Sahara. It contrasts with North Africa, whose territories are part of the League of Arab states within the Arab world. Somalia, Djibouti, Comoros and Mauritania are geographically in Sub-Saharan Africa, but are likewise Arab states and part of the Arab world.\\n\\n- The Indian Ocean is the third largest of the world's oceanic divisions, covering (approximately 20% of the water on the Earth's surface). It is bounded by Asia on the north, on the west by Africa, on the east by Australia, and on the south by the Southern Ocean or, depending on definition, by Antarctica. It is named after the country of India. The Indian Ocean is known as \\"Ratnkara\\", \\"\\"the mine of gems\\"\\" in ancient Sanskrit literature, and as \\"Hind Mahsgar\\", \\"\\"the great Indian sea\\"\\", in Hindi.\\n\\n- India, officially the Republic of India (\\"Bhrat Gaarjya\\"), is a country in South Asia. It is the seventh-largest country by area, the second-most populous country (with over 1.2 billion people), and the most populous democracy in the world. It is bounded by the Indian Ocean on the south, the Arabian Sea on the southwest, and the Bay of Bengal on the southeast. It shares land borders with Pakistan to the west; China, Nepal, and Bhutan to the northeast; and Myanmar (Burma) and Bangladesh to the east. In the Indian Ocean, India is in the vicinity of Sri Lanka and the Maldives. India's Andaman and Nicobar Islands share a maritime border with Thailand and Indonesia. Its capital is New Delhi; other metropolises include Mumbai, Kolkata, Chennai, Bangalore, Hyderabad and Ahmedabad.\\n\\n- Burundi (or ), officially the Republic of Burundi ( or ), is a landlocked country in the African Great Lakes region of East Africa, bordered by Rwanda to the north, Tanzania to the east and south, and the Democratic Republic of the Congo to the west. It is also considered part of Central Africa. Burundi's capital is Bujumbura. The southwestern border is adjacent to Lake Tanganyika.\\n\\n- The honey badger (\\"Mellivora capensis\\"), also known as the ratel (or ),\\nis the only species in the mustelid subfamily Mellivorinae and its only genus Mellivora. It is native to Africa, Southwest Asia, and the Indian subcontinent. Despite its name, the honey badger does not closely resemble other badger species; instead, it bears more anatomical similarities to weasels. It is classed as Least Concern by the IUCN owing to its extensive range and general environmental adaptations. It is primarily a carnivorous species and has few natural predators because of its thick skin and ferocious defensive abilities.\\n\\n- The Sahara (\\", 'the Greatest Desert') is the largest hot desert and the third largest desert in the world after Antarctica and the Arctic. Its area of is comparable to the area of the United States.\\n\\n- Camden Town, often shortened to Camden (ambiguously also used for the much larger London Borough of Camden of which it is the central neighbourhood), is an inner city district of northwest London, north of the centre of London. It is one of the 35 major centres identified in the London Plan.\\n\\n- The Gir Forest National Park and Wildlife Sanctuary (also known as Sasan-Gir, and  ) is a forest and wildlife sanctuary near Talala Gir in Gujarat, India. Established in 1965, with a total area of (about for the fully protected area of the national park and for the Sanctuary, the park is located north-east of Somnath, south-east of Junagadh and south-west of Amreli.\\n\\n- The Pleistocene (often colloquially referred to as the Ice Age) is the geological epoch which lasted from about 2,588,000 to 11,700 years ago, spanning the world's most recent period of repeated glaciations. The end of the Pleistocene corresponds with the end of the last glacial period and also with the end of the Paleolithic age used in archaeology.\\n\\n- A genus (¬†genera) is a taxonomic rank used in the biological classification of living and fossil organisms in biology. In the hierarchy of biological classification, genus comes above species and below family. In binomial nomenclature, the genus name forms the first part of the binomial species name for each species within the genus.\\n\\n- Malawi (or ; or [mal√°wi]), officially the Republic of Malawi, is a landlocked country in southeast Africa that was formerly known as Nyasaland. It is bordered by Zambia to the northwest, Tanzania to the northeast, and Mozambique on the east, south and west. The country is separated from Tanzania and Mozambique by Lake Malawi. Malawi is over with an estimated population of 16,777,547 (July 2013 est.). Its capital is Lilongwe, which is also Malawi's largest city; the second largest is Blantyre, the third is Mzuzu and the fourth largest is its old capital Zomba. The name Malawi comes from the Maravi, an old name of the Nyanja people that inhabit the area. The country is also nicknamed \\"The Warm Heart of Africa\\".\\n\\n- The Muppets are an ensemble cast of puppet characters known for their self-aware, burlesque, and meta-referential style of variety-sketch comedy. Created by Jim Henson in 1955, they are the namesake for the Disney media franchise that encompasses feature films, television series, music recordings, theme park attractions, print publications, merchandising, and other media works associated with the characters.\\n\\n- Greece (' ), officially the Hellenic Republic (Greek: ' ), historically also known as Hellas (\\"\\" ), is a country in southeastern Europe. \\nGreece's population is approximately 10.955 million as of 2015. Athens is the nation's capital and largest city, followed by Thessaloniki.\\n\\n- Zebras (or ) are several species of African equids (horse family) united by their distinctive black and white striped coats. Their stripes come in different patterns, unique to each individual. They are generally social animals that live in small harems to large herds. Unlike their closest relatives, horses and donkeys, zebras have never been truly domesticated.\\n\\n- Felidae is the family of cats. A member of this family is also called a felid.\\n\\n- The International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) is an international organization working in the field of nature conservation and sustainable use of natural resources. It is involved in data gathering and analysis, research, field projects, advocacy, lobbying and education. IUCN's mission is to \\"influence, encourage and assist societies throughout the world to conserve nature and to ensure that any use of natural resources is equitable and ecologically sustainable.\\"\\n\\n- Mozambique (or ), officially the Republic of Mozambique (or \\"\\") is a country in Southeast Africa bordered by the Indian Ocean to the east, Tanzania to the north, Malawi and Zambia to the northwest, Zimbabwe to the west, and Swaziland and South Africa to the southwest. It is separated from Madagascar by the Mozambique Channel to the east. The capital and largest city is Maputo (known as \\"Louren√ßo Marques\\" before independence).\\n\\n- Panthera is a genus within the Felidae family that was named and first described by the German naturalist Oken in 1816. The British taxonomist Pocock revised the classification of this genus in 1916 as comprising the species lion, tiger, jaguar, and leopard on the basis of cranial features. Results of genetic analysis indicate that the snow leopard also belongs to the \\"Panthera\\", a classification that was accepted by IUCN assessors in 2008.\\n\\n- Crocodiles (subfamily Crocodylinae) or true crocodiles are large aquatic reptiles that live throughout the tropics in Africa, Asia, the Americas and Australia. Crocodylinae, all of whose members are considered true crocodiles, is classified as a biological subfamily. A broader sense of the term crocodile, Crocodylidae that includes \\"Tomistoma\\", is not used in this article. The term crocodile here applies only to the species within the subfamily of Crocodylinae. The term is sometimes used even more loosely to include all extant members of the order Crocodilia, which includes \\"Tomistoma\\", the alligators and caimans (family Alligatoridae), the gharials (family Gavialidae), and all other living and fossil Crocodylomorpha.\\n\\n- The tiger (\\"Panthera tigris\\") is the largest cat species, most recognisable for their pattern of dark vertical stripes on reddish-orange fur with a lighter underside. The species is classified in the genus \\"Panthera\\" with the lion, leopard, jaguar and snow leopard. Tigers are apex predators, primarily preying on ungulates such as deer and bovids. They are territorial and generally solitary but social animals, often requiring large contiguous areas of habitat that support their prey requirements. This, coupled with the fact that they are indigenous to some of the more densely populated places on Earth, has caused significant conflicts with humans.\\n\\n- The Democratic Republic of the Congo , also known as DR Congo, DRC, DROC, East Congo, Congo-Kinshasa, or simply the Congo is a country located in Central Africa. From 1971 to 1997 it was named, and is sometimes still called Zaire, and from 1908 to 1960 it was called the Belgian Congo. The DRC borders the Central African Republic, and South Sudan to the north; Uganda, Rwanda, Burundi and Tanzania to the east; Zambia and Angola to the south; the Republic of the Congo to the west and the Atlantic Ocean to the southwest. It is the second-largest country in Africa by area and eleventh largest in the world. With a population of over 80 million, the Democratic Republic of the Congo is the most populated officially Francophone country, the fourth most-populated nation in Africa and the eighteenth most populated country in the world.\\n\\n- Kenya, officially the Republic of Kenya, is a country in Africa and a founding member of the East African Community (EAC). Its capital and largest city is Nairobi. Kenya's territory lies on the equator and overlies the East African Rift covering a diverse and expansive terrain that extends roughly from Lake Victoria to Lake Turkana (formerly called Lake Rudolf) and further south-east to the Indian Ocean. It is bordered by Tanzania to the south and southwest, Uganda to the west, South Sudan to the north-west, Ethiopia to the north and Somalia to the north-east. Kenya covers , and had a population of approximately 45 million people in July 2014.\\n\\n- The wildebeests, also called gnus, or wildebai, are a genus of antelopes, Connochaetes. They belong to the family Bovidae, which includes antelopes, cattle, goats, sheep and other even-toed horned ungulates. \\"Connochaetes\\" includes two species, both native to Africa: the black wildebeest, or white-tailed gnu (\\"C. gnou\\"); and the blue wildebeest, or brindled gnu (\\"C. taurinus\\"). Fossil records suggest these two species diverged about one million years ago, resulting in a northern and a southern species. The blue wildebeest remained in its original range and changed very little from the ancestral species, while the black wildebeest changed more in order to adapt to its open grassland habitat in the south. The most obvious way of telling the two species apart are the differences in their colouring and in the way their horns are oriented.\\n\\n- Tanzania , officially the United Republic of Tanzania, is a country in Eastern Africa within the African Great Lakes region. Parts of the country are in Southern Africa. It is bordered by Kenya and Uganda to the north; Rwanda, Burundi, and the Democratic Republic of the Congo to the west; Zambia, Malawi, and Mozambique to the south; and by the Indian Ocean to the east. Mount Kilimanjaro, Africa's highest mountain, is in northeastern Tanzania.\\n\\n- James Maury \\"Jim\\" Henson (September 24, 1936¬† May 16, 1990) was an American puppeteer, artist, cartoonist, inventor, screenwriter, film director and producer who achieved international fame as the creator of the Muppets. Born in Greenville, Mississippi, and raised in Leland, Mississippi, and Hyattsville, Maryland, Henson began developing puppets while attending high school. While he was a freshman at the University of Maryland, College Park, he created \\"Sam and Friends\\", a five-minute sketch-comedy puppet show that appeared on television. After graduating from the University of Maryland with a degree in home economics, he produced coffee advertisements and developed some experimental films. Feeling the need for more creative output, Henson founded Muppets Inc. in 1958 (which would later become the Jim Henson Company).\\n\\n- Hollywood (, informally Tinseltown ) is an ethnically diverse, densely populated, relatively low-income neighborhood in the central region of Los Angeles, California. It is notable as the home of the U.S. film industry, including several of its historic studios, and its name has come to be a shorthand reference for the industry and the people in it.\\n\\n- Southern Africa is the southernmost region of the African continent, variably defined by geography or geopolitics, and including several countries.\\nThe term \\"southern Africa\\" or \\"Southern Africa\\", generally includes Angola, Botswana, Lesotho, Malawi, Mozambique, Namibia, South Africa, Swaziland, Zambia, and Zimbabwe. From a political perspective the region is said to be unipolar with South Africa as a first regional power.\\n\\n- The informal term \\"big cat\\" is typically used to refer to any of the four largest (living) members of the entire \\"Panthera\\" genus. Among the five total species within the \\"Panthera\\" genus, these four are the only cats that are able to roar. In descending order of their maximum potential size, these four species are: tigers, lions, jaguars, and leopards. A more liberal and expansive definition is sometimes used which may include the snow leopard, puma, clouded leopard, Sunda clouded leopard and/or cheetah, although these added species do not roar. The two clouded leopard species are considered an evolutionary link between big and small cats.\\n\\n- London is the capital and most populous city of England and the United Kingdom, as well as the most populous city proper in the European Union. Standing on the River Thames in the south east of the island of Great Britain, London has been a major settlement for two millennia. It was founded by the Romans, who named it \\"Londinium\\". London's ancient core, the City of London, largely retains its medieval boundaries. Since at least the 19th century, \\"London\\" has also referred to the metropolis around this core, historically split between Middlesex, Essex, Surrey, Kent, and Hertfordshire, which today largely makes up Greater London, governed by the Mayor of London and the London Assembly.\\n\\n- Mount Kilimanjaro, with its three volcanic cones, \\"Kibo\\", \\"Mawenzi\\", and \\"Shira\\", is a dormant volcano in Tanzania. It is the highest mountain in Africa, and rises approximately 4,900 m (16,000¬†ft) from its base to above sea level. The first recorded ascent to the summit of the mountain was by Hans Meyer and Ludwig Purtscheller in 1889. The mountain is part of the Kilimanjaro National Park and is a major climbing destination. The mountain has been the subject of many scientific studies because of its shrinking glaciers.\\n\\n- The Republic of Zambia is a landlocked country in Southern Africa, neighbouring the Democratic Republic of the Congo to the north, Tanzania to the north-east, Malawi to the east, Mozambique, Zimbabwe, Botswana and Namibia to the south, and Angola to the west. The capital city is Lusaka, in the south-central part of Zambia. The population is concentrated mainly around Lusaka in the south and the Copperbelt Province to the northwest, the core economic hubs of the country.\\n\\n- The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland, commonly known as the United Kingdom (UK) or Britain, is a sovereign country in western Europe. Lying off the north-western coast of the European mainland, it includes the island of Great Britain (the name of which is also loosely applied to the whole country), the north-eastern part of the island of Ireland, and many smaller islands. Northern Ireland is the only part of the UK that shares a land border with another sovereign statethe Republic of Ireland. Apart from this land border, the UK is surrounded by the Atlantic Ocean, with the North Sea to its east, the English Channel to its south and the Celtic Sea to its south-south-west, giving it the 12th-longest coastline in the world. The Irish Sea lies between Great Britain and Ireland. With an area of , the UK is the 78th-largest sovereign state in the world and the 11th-largest in Europe. It is also the 21st-most populous country, with an estimated 65.1 million inhabitants. Together, this makes it the fourth most densely populated country in the European Union.\\n\\n- Jim Henson's Creature Shop is a special/visual effects company founded in 1979 by puppeteer Jim Henson, creator of The Muppets. The company is based out of Hollywood, California, United States, and, previously, Camden Town in London, United Kingdom, where they still maintain some facilities.\\n\\n- Eurasia is the combined continental landmass of Europe and Asia. The term is a portmanteau of its constituent continents. Located primarily in the Northern and Eastern Hemispheres, it is bordered by the Atlantic Ocean to the west, the Pacific Ocean to the east, the Arctic Ocean to the north, and by Africa, the Mediterranean Sea, and the Indian Ocean to the south. The division between Europe and Asia as two different continents is a historical and cultural construct, with no clear physical separation between them; thus, in some parts of the world, Eurasia is recognized as the largest of five or six continents. In geology, Eurasia is often considered as a single rigid megablock. However, the rigidity of Eurasia is debated based on the paleomagnet data.\\n\\n- Rwanda (or ), officially the Republic of Rwanda, is a sovereign state in central and east Africa and one of the smallest countries on the African mainland. Located a few degrees south of the Equator, Rwanda is bordered by Uganda, Tanzania, Burundi and the Democratic Republic of the Congo. Rwanda is in the African Great Lakes region and is highly elevated; its geography is dominated by mountains in the west and savanna to the east, with numerous lakes throughout the country. The climate is temperate to subtropical, with two rainy seasons and two dry seasons each year.\\n\\n\\n\\nAfter reading the paragraphs above, we are interested in knowing the entity with which 'pride ' exhibits the relationship of 'main subject'. Find the answer from the choices below.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- africa\\n - antarctica\\n - arab world\\n - art\\n - biology\\n - border\\n - canada\\n - cat\\n - city\\n - climbing\\n - comedy\\n - company\\n - conservation\\n - education\\n - europe\\n - family\\n - film\\n - geography\\n - geopolitics\\n - high school\\n - hollywood\\n - horse\\n - ice age\\n - india\\n - july\\n - literature\\n - london\\n - mountain\\n - music\\n - nature\\n - television\\n - time\\n - true\\n - united kingdom\\n - wildebeest\\n - wildlife","target":"cat","rationale":"The paragraphs give us many pieces of information. However, we are interested in knowing the entity with which \\"pride\\" exhibits the relationship of \\"main subject\\", and this is given to us only once:\\n'Pride¬†is a 2004 television film about two lion cubs as they grow up ...'. From that sentence alone, it can be inferred that the main subject of Pride is cat (lion)."},{"source":"Arsenal's tally of 13 League Championships is the third highest in English football, after Manchester United (20) and Liverpool (18), and they were the first club to reach 8 League Championships. They hold the highest number of FA Cup trophies, 12. The club is one of only six clubs to have won the FA Cup twice in succession, in 2002 and 2003, and 2014 and 2015. Arsenal have achieved three League and FA Cup \\"Doubles\\" (in 1971, 1998 and 2002), a feat only previously achieved by Manchester United (in 1994, 1996 and 1999). They were the first side in English football to complete the FA Cup and League Cup double, in 1993. Arsenal were also the first London club to reach the final of the UEFA Champions League, in 2006, losing the final 2‚Äì1 to Barcelona.\\nTopic from the paragraph:","target":"Arsenal F.C.","rationale":"The paragraph describes the achievements and records of Arsenal F.C., the famous English football club, in detail. Thus, it is clear that \\"Arsenal \\nSo from this context we can conclude that Arsenal FC is the topic being discussed in this passage"},{"source":"Harry and Kim studied ancient humans. Kim studied a 15000 year-old settlement, before humans invented agriculture, while Harry studied a 5000 year-old village.\\n\\nWhich student studied about a village that had more diseases that spread from domestic animals?\\n\\nHint: Human beings invented agriculture about 10,000 years ago. This provided a bigger, more dependable food supply. It also allowed people to settle down in villages and cities for the first time. Birth rates went up because there was more food and settled life had other advantages. Death rates also rose because of crowded living conditions and diseases that spread from domestic animals. Because the higher birth rates were matched by higher death rates, the human population continued to grow very slowly.","target":"Harry","rationale":"The question asks which student studied a village that had more diseases spread by domestic animals. From the context of the passage, we learn that humans invented agriculture about 10,000 years ago. This provided a bigger and more dependable food supply but also allowed people to settle down in villages and cities for the first time. It is likely these settlements would have domesticated animals as well such as cattle or sheep because they were providing meat and other products like wool from them. Animals living closely with human settlements meant there was an increased risk of cross-infection between species i.e., disease spreading from one animal to another or even into human beings who lived close by around 5000 years ago when Harry‚Äôs settlement existed than 15,000 years before Kim's settlement started up since at this earlier point"},{"source":"It was believed to have disturbed him that people didn't like Fred.\\n\\nHow would you consider the linguistic integrity of the preceding sentence?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The sentence follows the subject-verb structure, therefore it is acceptable."},{"source":"Elettra stuck the little slip of paper, on which the recipe was written, into her shabby pocket-book without looking at it. She could read and write fairly well, and had been used to helping her husband the under-steward with his accounts at Muro, but even if she had looked at the recipe she would have understood nothing of the doctor's hieroglyphics and abbreviated Latin words. The prescription was for a preparation of arsenic, which Matilde had formerly taken for some time. The chemist would not make any difficulty about preparing twenty doses of it for the Countess Macomer, though the whole quantity of arsenic contained in so many would probably be sufficient to kill one not accustomed to the medicine, if taken all at once. But though Matilde was so anxious to have the stuff before luncheon, she had a number of doses of it put away in a drawer, which she took out and counted, after Elettra had gone. She opened one of the little folded papers and looked at the fine white powder it contained, took a little on the end of her finger and tasted it. Then, from the same drawer, she took a package done up in coarser paper, and opened it likewise, looked at it, smelt it, and touched it with the tip of her tongue very cautiously indeed. It was white, too, but coarser than the medicine. She was very careful in tasting it, and she immediately rinsed her mouth with water, before she tied up the package again, shut the drawer, and put the key into her pocket. \\nQuestion: Who opened one of the little folded papers? \\nIs it Matilde?","target":"Yes","rationale":"Yes, Matilde opened one of the little folded papers"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a context sentence containing a blank (_). You are expected to fill the blank with one word to make the sentence convey a cultural anti-stereotype. Anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against a common belief about a particular group of people. Your answer must not contain more than one word.\\n\\nContext: The _ man is from Italy","target":"nice","rationale":"The common stereotype of Italians is that they are loud, rude, and/or aggressive. By putting the word \\"nice\\" instead of a blank, this sentence conveys an anti-stereotype because it suggests that Italians can be nice people."},{"source":"Premise: I want to challenge them to see what they can provide.\\n\\nHypothesis: I have no wish to dispute this issue with them.\\n\\nDoes the premise entail the hypothesis?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise states that the speaker wants to challenge them, which would suggest an argument with the other party. However, the hypothesis states a desire not to have any sort of dispute with them. The two statements are contradictory and thus do not support each other; so they cannot be said to entail one another."},{"source":"Given a post that is a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation and a question asks if AUTHOR, NOBODY, EVERYBODY, or OTHER is wrong in the situation. Answer the question and classify your answers into yes or no.\\n\\nIs AUTHOR wrong in the post ? POST : Okay, this is on mobile, so sorry in advance. Also, I am terrible at spelling so sorry about that too.\\nAnyways,\\nI met a wonderful girl named Ashley in the fourth grade. We slowly eased into the friendship, but became attached. That right there was the problem. I found a group of friends that I fit into and I absolutely adored. But Ashley did NOT like these people.\\n\\nWhenever I would hang out with them, I would always see Ashley moping and being sad, even though her numerous other friends were constantly by her side. I, unfortunately, already had anxiety issues, but the pressure to be the best BFF that Ashley was too much to handle.\\nI‚Äôm talking, I almost killed myself until my friend convinced me to talk to someone.\\n\\nNumerous other things would happen:\\nShe would get mad at me for the smallest things such as sitting somewhere or not arriving early for school.\\nShe wanted me to devote my life to her, and have only one best friend, but she was always surrounded by oodles of friends. \\nShe had serious trust issues with me, as I trusted her with my life.\\nShe would always have a rebound to my criticism or advice.\\n\\nLet‚Äôs focus on the last one.\\n\\nI finally decided this year that I was done with the crap she was giving me. This was how the conversation went down: (A-Ashley M-Me)\\n\\nM: *sends a serious message about how our relationship was unhealthy and I wanted to end it or at least back down a little*\\n\\nA: I‚Äôm sorry that myself wasn‚Äôt good enough. I‚Äôm sorry that I couldn‚Äôt be the perfect friend. I‚Äôm sorry that I caused you stress. I‚Äôm dealing with a lot at home and I guess I‚Äôm not good enough for you. I‚Äôm sorry I wasn‚Äôt perfect. (Simplified, this was much longer and gave off a ‚ÄúWoe is me‚Äù vibe)\\n\\nM: I‚Äôm so sorry I never meant to hurt you. Will you ever forgive me? I‚Äôm just the worst. I should‚Äô have said that. I‚Äôm so so sorry. I‚Äôm the worst (being serious)\\n\\nA: I guess but I don‚Äôt think I can trust you much anymore.\\n\\nM: Alright. It‚Äôs what I deserve.\\n\\nThis is very simplified.\\n\\nI know she has trouble at home, but that doesn‚Äôt give her the right to treat me like that. She knew damn well that I would cave if she brought up home. In conclusion, AITA for getting mad at my friends response to her being ‚Äúdumped‚Äù from a friendship?\\n\\nSorry so short. This is my first time posting like this.","target":"no","rationale":"The author of the post describes a friend, Ashley, that is extremely immature and manipulative. Ashley has numerous friends but wants the author to be her only best friend; she is upset whenever the author spends time with other people; she has trust issues with no apparent cause; she gets angry when the author tries to give her advice or criticism. The author decides that they can no longer deal with all of these problems and tells Ashley they want to back down from their friendship. When this happens, Ashley makes it seem like it's all about her, and refuses to accept responsibility for how her behavior made the author feel (e.g., saying \\"\\"I'm sorry I wasn't perfect\\"\\"). This shows that Ashley does not care about anyone else but herself and does not take into account other people's feelings or needs.\\nThe answer is 'no' because in a healthy friendship both parties should be able to respect each others' boundaries and work together towards a mutually satisfying relationship. In this case, however, Ashley only cared about what she wanted within the relationship without considering what might actually make her friend happy.\\""},{"source":"Question: If an area is not thick with resource, those resources are what?\\nOptions:\\n- free flowing\\n- translucent\\n- sparse\\n- slender\\n- clear\\n\\nThe answer is \\"sparse\\" because","target":"describe writing in the se","rationale":"The rationale is: \\"describe writing in the se\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given an abstract of article. Your task is to generate title for this article. Preferred titles are under thirty words.\\n\\nInappropriate use of antibiotics is contributing to the increasing rates of antimicrobial resistance. Several Danish guidelines on antibiotic prescribing for acute respiratory tract infections in general practice have been issued to promote rational prescribing of antibiotics, however it is unclear if these recommendations are followed. We aimed to characterise the pattern of antibiotic prescriptions for patients diagnosed with acute respiratory tract infections, by means of electronic prescriptions, labeled with clinical indications, from Danish general practice. Acute respiratory tract infections accounted for 456,532 antibiotic prescriptions issued between July 2012 and June 2013. Pneumonia was the most common indication with 178,354 prescriptions (39%), followed by acute tonsillitis (21%) and acute otitis media (19%). In total, penicillin V accounted for 58% of all prescriptions, followed by macrolides (18%) and amoxicillin (15%). The use of second-line agents increased with age for all indications, and comprised more than 40% of the prescriptions in patients aged >75 years. Women were more often prescribed antibiotics regardless of clinical indication. This is the first Danish study to characterise antibiotic prescription patterns for acute respiratory tract infections by data linkage of clinical indications. The findings confirm that penicillin V is the most commonly prescribed antibiotic agent for treatment of patients with an acute respiratory tract infection in Danish general practice. However, second-line agents like macrolides and amoxicillin with or without clavulanic acid are overused. Strategies to improve the quality of antibiotic prescribing especially for pneumonia, acute otitis media and acute rhinosinusitis are warranted.    RESPIRATORY TRACT INFECTIONS TRACKING THE OVERUSE OF ANTIBIOTICS: Better adherence to guidelines for prescribing antibiotics for different respiratory tract infections are warranted in Danish general practice. The over-use of antibiotics, particularly so-called 'second-line' agents such as amoxicillin, increases resistance and may lead to a potentially catastrophic scenario where antibiotics are no longer effective. Exactly how widespread the over-use of antibiotics is for different infections, however, is not clear. Rune Aabenhus at the University of Copenhagen and co-workers analyzed primary care data regarding antibiotic prescriptions for acute respiratory tract infections including pneumonia and ear infections in Denmark. They found that penicillin V-the current recommended first-line drug in Scandinavian countries-accounted for 58 per cent of prescriptions, a figure which should be improved. Amoxicillin and macrolides were over-prescribed, particularly in elderly patients. The team also call for further analysis of prescriptions given by out-of-hours clinics.","target":"Characterisation of antibiotic prescriptions for acute respiratory tract infections in Danish general practice: a retrospective registry based cohort study","rationale":"An appropriate title should be succinct and provide a brief description of the study. The following is an example:\\\\nCharacterisation of antibiotic prescriptions for acute respiratory tract infections in Danish general practice: a retrospective registry based cohort study"},{"source":"Wynonna Earp (TV series) -- On July 23, 2016, the renewal for a second season was announced at the Wynonna Earp panel at San Diego Comic-Con (SDCC). Originally slated for ten episodes, the season was increased to 12 episodes in October 2016. In Canada, Wynonna Earp moved from CHCH-DT to Space effective April 15, 2017. In anticipation of the premiere of Season 2, Space began airing Season 1 on the same date with a special double-episode series debut. Season 2 premiered simultaneously on Syfy and Space on June 9, 2017.\\n\\nQ: is there a season 2 of wynonna earp? True or False?","target":"True","rationale":"In the description, it mentions that season 2 premiered on June 9th 2017.\\nSo there is a season 2 of wynonna earp and we answer properly True"},{"source":"Answer a question about this article:\\nCriticism of the term intellectual property ranges from discussing its vagueness and abstract overreach to direct contention to the semantic validity of using words like property and rights in fashions that contradict practice and law. Many detractors think this term specially serves the doctrinal agenda of parties opposing reform in the public interest or otherwise abusing related legislations; and that it disallows intelligent discussion about specific and often unrelated aspects of copyright, patents, trademarks, etc.\\nCritics criticize what type of validity of the term 'intellectual property'?","target":"semantic","rationale":"The article talks about the criticism of a specific term \\"intellectual property\\".\\nIn this context, critics criticize the semantic validity of using words like 'property' and 'rights'."},{"source":"I have a test where I am given the following article, what is an answer for the question: What album was the song Son of Three released by The Breeders? ?\\n\\nBryant identified \\"Son of Three\\" as an example of \\"when the Breeders set out to rock\\", noting \\"the chugging guitars and stomping drums.\\" The Breeders re-recorded \\"Son of Three\\" in July 2002 for its release as Title TK's third single; this version is faster than the album track, and reflects the speed they were playing the song in concert that year. The lyrics of both \\"Son of Three\\" and \\"The She\\" suggest extended road trips with unknown outcomes. The album's next song, \\"Put on a Side\\", has a distinctive bassline and a cramped, repressive feel. Berger wrote that Kim Deal's \\"voice grinds sweetly, weariedly, sloppily inside your brain,\\" as she repeats twelve words over the course of the song: \\"Better I better I stayed up / Better mono, put on a side.\\"An earlier version of \\"Full on Idle\\", Title TK's eighth track, was released on the Amps' Pacer in 1995. In a 1997 interview, Deal expressed an interest in redoing multiple Amps songs, partially because she did not feel Pacer was well recorded. Bryant opined that both versions of \\"Full on Idle\\" sound almost the same, but The Village Voice's Jessica Grose wrote that the Breeders' rendition is noticeably slower. In Cibula's view, this version contains elements of country music, cumbia, and ska. The Guardian's Betty Clarke cited the line \\"Obey your colorist, bleach it all away\\" as an example of Title TK's amusing, off-center lyrics. On \\"Sinister Foxx\\", Deal repeatedly sings \\"Has anyone seen the iguana?\\" She has explained this as being a reference to buying marijuana: \\"Have you ever bought a bag of weed? You walk in, and the pot dealer's got an empty terrarium ... Every time I go to a pot dealer's house, there's no iguana.\\" Another line, \\"I'm in beer class every Thursday night\\", refers to the alcohol awareness classes that Richard Presley attended after being caught driving while drunk. Phares described the song as having a \\"sexy menace\\", and Berger compared the drum part to gunshots and door-knocking.Moores identified in \\"Forced to Drive\\" the \\"quiet-LOUD-quiet\\" dynamic...","target":"Title TK","rationale":"The album is Title TK."},{"source":"Given a comment text in Tamil, classify the comment into one of these categories (i) Hope speech, if it contains encouraging, positive or supportive contents about equality, diversity or inclusion, (ii) Not Hope Speech or (iii) Not in Expected Language, if the text is not Tamil.\\n\\nNaa kandipa solra India kida ellame kammiya iruku apra eppadi India win pannu sollunga China win panna vaazhppugal ullanaa","target":"Not Hope Speech","rationale":"This is a comment on India's performance in sports. The writer is expressing his disappointment at India's defeat to China and what he feels are the reasons for it. The comment does not express any positive, encouraging or supportive thoughts about equality, diversity or inclusion. Therefore, this is Not Hope Speech"},{"source":"Given a prompt and four completions, select the completion that is the most plausible in continuing or answering the prompt. This task is designed to test common sense and has various categories ranging between idioms, negated statements, polysemy, subject referencing, and quantitative reasoning. Generate either Completion A, Completion B, Completion C, or Completion D.\\n\\nPrompt: A father puts his baby in a stroller. The baby \\nCompletion A: falls peacefully asleep. \\nCompletion B: causes the stroller to collapse under her immense weight. \\nCompletion C: pushes the carriage. \\nCompletion D: is ten years old.","target":"Completion A","rationale":"The prompt is describing how a father puts his baby in a stroller and then the baby falls asleep. Completion A is the most plausible completion since babies have an inclination to fall asleep in moving objects such as strollers."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an adjunct island or as an incorrect representation. A correct representation should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an adjunct island will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence using an adjunct island. An incorrect representation will be everything else.\\n\\nWho have the cakes annoyed while disturbing Renee?","target":"good","rationale":"This is a grammatically correct sentence using an adjunct island. In this sentence, the relative clause \\"Who have the cakes annoyed\\" serves as an adjunct to the main clause. The entire relative clause, which contains a verb phrase (\\"have annoyed\\") and two arguments, is contained within another relative clause (\\"while disturbing Renee\\"), making it an adjunct island. The answer is \\"good\\"."},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: Mary went back to the hallway. Sandra journeyed to the garden. Sandra travelled to the bathroom. John travelled to the hallway. John travelled to the garden. Mary journeyed to the bedroom. Question: Where is Mary?","target":"bedroom","rationale":"We can infer from the final fact in the passage which states \\"Mary journeyed to the bedroom.\\""},{"source":"Context: Following the death of Grand Prince Igor in 945, his wife Olga ruled as regent in Kiev until their son Sviatoslav reached maturity (ca. 963). His decade-long reign over Rus' was marked by rapid expansion through the conquest of the Khazars of the Pontic steppe and the invasion of the Balkans. By the end of his short life, Sviatoslav carved out for himself the largest state in Europe, eventually moving his capital from Kiev to Pereyaslavets on the Danube in 969. In contrast with his mother's conversion to Christianity, Sviatoslav, like his druzhina, remained a staunch pagan. Due to his abrupt death in an ambush in 972, Sviatoslav's conquests, for the most part, were not consolidated into a functioning empire, while his failure to establish a stable succession led to a fratricidal feud among his sons, which resulted in two of his three sons being killed.; \\n\\nQuestion: What year did Sviatoslav's mother convert? \\n\\nIs this question answerable?","target":"no","rationale":"The given context does not explicitly state the year in which Sviatoslav's mother converted.\\nThus, it is clear that the question cannot be answered from this paragraph."},{"source":"I am verifying the answers generated by an automatic system to the following question: what is civil engineering aBOUT\\nSuggested answer: Civil engineering is a professional engineering discipline that deals with the design, construction, and maintenance of the physical and naturally built environment, including works like roads, bridges, canals , dams, and buildings.\\nShould I validate this answer?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The suggested answer provided by the automatic system is accurate and should be validated. \\nCivil engineering deals with the design, construction, and maintenance of the physical and naturally built environment as can be verified through Wikipedia or other credible sources. The examples listed in this suggestion further support its validity. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Given a passage classify if the passage has a definite objective/aim/goal or not. Output '1' if the passage has a defininte objective/aim/goal and output '0' if the passage does not have a definite objective/aim/goal.\\n\\nRecent research has revealed that classically trained tenors tend to constrict epilaryngeal structures when singing in and above the passaggio (ie, the frequency region where register events typically occur). These constrictions complicate visibility of vocal fold oscillatory patterns with transoral rigid high-speed video endoscopy, thus limiting the current understanding of laryngeal dynamics in the passaggio region of tenors.', 'This investigation analyzed seven professionally trained western classical tenors using high-speed digital imaging (HSDI) at 20,000 frames per second via transnasal flexible endoscopy. The participants produced transitions (a) from modal to falsetto register and (b) from modal to stage voice above the passaggio (SVaP) during ascending pitch glides from A3 (220\\\\u2009Hz) to A4 (440\\\\u2009Hz) on vowel /i/. HSDI data were complemented by simultaneous acoustic and electroglottographic recordings.', 'For many subjects both transition types were associated with constrictions of the epilaryngeal structures during the pitch glide. These constrictions appeared to be more distinct for the SVaP than for falsetto. No major irregularities of vocal fold oscillations in the sense of fundamental frequency jumps were observed for either transition type. However, during the transitions, the open quotient derived from the glottal area waveform (OQ","target":"0","rationale":"The passage describes a series of studies that investigate the effects of various manipulations on attentional set-shifting in rats, but it does not state a specific research question or hypothesis that the studies are designed to test. The passage provides information on the methods, results, and interpretations of the studies, but it does not explicitly state a main objective or aim. Therefore, the output is '0'."},{"source":"OPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nDoes \\"The channel also broadcasts two movie blocks during the late evening hours each Sunday: \\"Silent Sunday Nights\\", which features silent films from the United States and abroad, usually in the latest restored version and often with new musical scores; and \\"TCM Imports\\" (which previously ran on Saturdays until the early 2000s[specify]), a weekly presentation of films originally released in foreign countries.\\" correctly answer the question of On what day is TCM Underground shown?","target":"no","rationale":"No, it is not correct. The passage gives the name of two Sunday movie blocks that are aired on TCM: Silent Sundays and TCM Imports; however it does not mention any show named \\"TCM Underground\\" that airs on Saturdays as suggested in the question."},{"source":"Write a multi-choice question for the following article, with the given choices and answer:\\nArticle: I have a rule of travel: never carry a map. I prefer to ask for directions. Foreign visitors are often puzzled in Japan because most streets there don't have names. In Japan, people tell landmarks in their directions instead of street names. For example, the Japanese will say to travelers, \\" Go straight down to the corner. Turn left at the big hotel and pass a fruit market. The post office is across from the bus stop.\\"\\nIn the countryside of the American Midwest, usually there are not many landmarks. There are no towns or buildings within miles. Instead of landmarks, people will tell you directions and distance. In Kansas or Iowa, for example, people will say, \\" Go north two miles, turn west, and then go another mile.\\"\\nPeople in Los Angeles, California, have no idea of distance on the map. They measure distance by means of time, not miles. \\"How far away is the post office?\\" you ask. \\"Oh,\\" they answer, \\"it's about five minutes from here.\\" You say, \\" Yes, but how many miles away is it?\\" They don' t know.\\nPeople in Greece sometimes do not even try to give directions because visitors seldom understand the Greek language. Instead of giving you the direction, a Greek often says, \\" Follow me.\\" Then he will lead you through the streets of the city to the post office.\\nSometimes a person doesn't know the answer to your question. What happens then? A New Yorker might say, \\" Sorry, I have no idea.\\" But in Yuchatan, Mexico, no one answers \\" I don't know.\\" People in Yucatan think that \\" I don't know\\" is impolite. They usually give an answer, often a wrong one. A visitor can get very lost in Yucatan.\\n However, one thing will help you everywhere---- in Japan, in the United States, in Greece, in Mexico, or in any other places. You might not understand a person's words, but maybe you can understand his body language. He or she will usually turn and then point in the correct direction. Go in that direction and you may find the post office.\\nOptions:\\nA Japan.\\nB Los Angeles.\\nC Greece.\\nD Yucatan.\\nAnswer:\\nB Los Angeles.\\nQuestion:","target":"In which place do people tell distance by means of time?","rationale":"People in Los Angeles, California have no idea of distance on the map. They measure distance by means of time, not miles.\\"How far away is the post office?\\" you ask.\\"Oh,\\" they answer,\\"it's about five minutes from here\\"You say \\"Yes, but how many miles away is it?\\".They don't know.\\nSo this should be a question like: In which place do people tell distance by means of time?"},{"source":"Juliette Murray was, like me, a kid at school who got 5 ‚ÄúA‚Äùs, which in the West of Scotland put a certain degree of pressure on one‚Äôs shoulders to study either medicine or law. I studied European Law, and became a teacher - that's what a European Law degree does to you. She studied medicine and is today a practicing doctor, but the education bug is firmly rooted in what she chose to do next.\\nMurray noticed that, particularly in her local area, fewer students were applying to study medicine than the population number would suggest should. Not only that, nationally the number of medical students dropping out after beginning their course of study is increasing. She wondered if we might we persuade a more representative cross section of the community to become doctors.\\nShe set about improving the opportunities for local youngsters, aged 14/5, at the time of their work experience choices. Existing work experience for those who want to gain an insight into the world of medical doctors is a sanitised course in an educational skills centre, where bored teenagers endlessly take each other‚Äôs blood pressure. They have more chance of a realistic insight by breaking their arm and turning up to Accident and Emergency. As any dad-to-be donning surgical greens knows, getting into an operating theatre is where a passion for surgery will be born or, in my case, definitely put to one side as a career option. So, the question became: how might we offer a more realistic experience of what being a doctor, surgeon or other medical profession feels like?\\nStarting with her local hospital, Wishaw General in NHS Lanarkshire, she set about overcoming what she describes as a ‚Äúculture of obstacles‚Äù. Two years later, though, and students are indeed undertaking real life surgery work experience, experiencing a live operation theatre and seeing the pressure of the job first hand.\\nAccording to the above context, choose the correct option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: Who started the work experience program\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. the author\\n\\nB. Juliette\\n\\nC. bored teenagers\\n\\nD. not enough information","target":"B","rationale":"The author mentions Juliette Murray, who noticed that fewer students were applying to study medicine than the population number would suggest should. She wondered if we might persuade a more representative cross section of the community to become doctors and set about improving the opportunities for local youngsters at their work experience choices.\\nJuliette Murray started this program so B is correct answer"},{"source":"In this task, you need to provide the correct option for a given problem from the provided options.\\n\\nProblem: the ratio of numbers is 5 : 6 and their h . c . f is 4 . their l . c . m is : \\nOptions: a ) 12 , b ) 16 , c ) 24 , d ) 48 , e ) 120","target":"e","rationale":"The given ratios are 5:6. The HCF (Highest Common Factor) of these numbers is 4."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a context, a sentence,  and a character. The sentence describes an action or job of the given character. Also, the context provides more information about the sentence or the character. Your task is to return one of the emotions which are expressed by the Character in the given sentence. For that you can use the Context; however, Context is not provided in all the inputs. Also, in some inputs, there can be zero emotion; for that return 'None'.\\n\\nContext: None \\n Sentence: A man was working long hours in his job. \\n Character: Friends","target":"None","rationale":"The given context is None and the sentence describes a man's job. The character of Friends does not express any emotion in the sentence."},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an answer to a question that involves ‚Äúevent duration\\", based on a given sentence. Here, event duration is defined as the understanding of how long events typically last. For example, ‚Äúbrushing teeth‚Äù, usually takes a few minutes. Note that a lot of the questions could have more than one correct answer. We only need a single most-likely answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: He named the house, which was completed in 1802, the \\"Grange\\" after his grandfather Alexander's estate in Ayrshire, Scotland. \\nQuestion: How long did it take to complete the house?","target":"9 months","rationale":"The sentence states that the house was completed in 1802, therefore it could not have taken more than a year to build. Additionally, the fact that the house is being referred to as complete indicates it took longer than a few days or weeks to build. Based on these facts, we can conclude that the house took 9 months (three quarters of a year) to complete."},{"source":"Here is a premise:\\nThis was a dilemma for the Tokugawa government.\\n\\nHere is a hypothesis:\\nThe Tokugawa government knew exactly what to do.\\n\\nHere are the options: OPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no\\nIs it possible to conclude that if the premise is true, then so is the hypothesis?","target":"no","rationale":"The premise states the government had a dilemma, or problem. This would indicate that they were unsure about what to do in this situation and therefore did not know exactly what to do."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a context, a sentence,  and a character. The sentence describes an action or job of the given character. Also, the context provides more information about the sentence or the character. Your task is to return one of the emotions which are expressed by the Character in the given sentence. For that you can use the Context; however, Context is not provided in all the inputs. Also, in some inputs, there can be zero emotion; for that return 'None'.\\n\\nContext: Terry has lost his job. Terry doesn't know what to do to feed his family. He heads out to ask for help. He gets help from a local church who gives Terry food. \\n Sentence: Terry comes home and feeds his whole family with the food he got. \\n Character: Family","target":"happy","rationale":"Terry's family is happy to get food to eat."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on geometry. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: how many times are the hands of a clock at right angle in 2 weeks ? \\nOptions: a ) 616 , b ) 611 , c ) 661 , d ) 116 , e ) 666","target":"a","rationale":"The hour hand goes around the clock once in 12 hours, which is 12/24 = 1/2 days. The minute hand also takes exactly 1/2 days to go around once. Therefore, in 2 weeks (14 days), the hands of a clock will be at right angle 616 times."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the question-answer pair. \\nQuestion: Which of Tuvalu's atolls is largest?;  Answer: Funafuti; Topic:","target":"Tuvalu","rationale":"Tuvalu is an island country located in the Pacific Ocean, and Funafuti is one of its atolls. Thus, Tuvalu is a more appropriate answer to determine topic as it provides greater information about the question-answer pair."},{"source":"When your brain senses that your body temperature is increasing, it sends messages to the blood vessels in the skin to increase in diameter.\\n\\nHaving read the above passage, choose the right answer to the following question (choices are enlarge or contract ):\\n\\n\\nThe blood vessels near the top of the skin do what when it's warm enlarge or contract?","target":"enlarge","rationale":"When the body temperature rises, your brain sends messages to blood vessels near the top of your skin. These blood vessels increase in diameter when it's warm outside because this allows for more heat loss through evaporation and radiation.\\nSo, the answer is enlarge"},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i, j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to find all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, reverse the order in which they occur, and then concatenate them to output the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j. Perform the operations in order, i.e., do not concatenate the elements and then reverse the string.\\n\\n4, 6, ['691', 'Q', 'X', 'A', '2501', '7941', 'e', '8967', 'm', '9729', 'O', 't', '7609', 'z', 'Z', 'C', '6027', '2363']","target":"79412501A","rationale":"Given the list ['691', 'Q', 'X', 'A', '2501', '7941', 'e', '8967','m','9729','O','t','7609','z','Z','C','6027'] as input, we need to find the elements between indexes 4 and 6.\\\\n1. The 4th element is 2501.\\\\n2. The 5th element is 7941.\\\\n3. The 6th element is e and it will be converted into 0 during the final calculation (see below).\\\\n\\\\nThe reverse order of these elements would be [7941, 2501, A]. Converting each character in this list into string type and concatenating them yields \\"79412501A\\"."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the correct option to answer the question.\\nContext: Thank you for the A2A ‚Ä¶..\\nWhat has been your biggest heartbreak during your adult years?\\nHad I answered this question 20 years ago, it would have been the death of my Daddy ‚Ä¶ Had it been 12 years ago, it would have been the death of my Mother ‚Ä¶ Had it been 10 years ago, it would have been when my son turned his back on God so far that he went into satanism ‚Ä¶ As it is now ~ I would have to say that the biggest heartbreak in my life was 3 years ago when I discovered (online) that my beautiful daughter had begun taking Testosterone injections.\\nBelieve me ~ I‚Äôve been told time after time that her decision to do so is her own ‚Ä¶ to that fact I will agree. What I cannot agree with though, is that I have no right to feel hurt, upset, or any of the other assorted emotions that come with having a transgender child!! It‚Äôs not okay to be devastated by the choices my little girl makes ‚Ä¶ Its not okay to not agree with what she‚Äôs doing to herself ‚Ä¶ It‚Äôs not gonna have an impact on her family ‚Ä¶ It‚Äôs not something that is allowed to affect our relationship ‚Ä¶\\nThe ONLY thing that matters ~ is the transgender person and how they feel!!!!\\nOne of the biggest things that bothers me is when I‚Äôm told that I can‚Äôt love my child ~ unless I accept that she wants to be a male and give her support with that decision. I can say that I do love my daughter ~ I always have ~ and I always will. A mother‚Äôs love doesn‚Äôt go away.\\n***To those who wish to attack me for what I have to say on the topic of transgenderism ~ I respect your right to tell me your opinion and why you think I‚Äôm wrong ‚Ä¶ but my feelings matter, too, and deserve that same respect from you.***\\nWishing you the best!!\\nQuestion: who took testosterone injections\\nOptions:\\n- her daughter\\n- not enough information\\n- the mother\\n- her brother","target":"her daughter","rationale":"The context is from a question and answer forum, where the person posing the question has asked about heartbreak during adult years. The response mentions that three years ago was one of their biggest heartbreaks and relates to her daughter's decision to take testosterone injections.\\nBased on this information alone, it can be inferred that \\"her\\" refers to the mother in the context (as she wrote the post) and not herself as an individual. As such, \\"daughter\\" would refer specifically to her child who took testosterone injections, making them transgender."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a string that only contains single digit numbers spelled out. The input string will not contain spaces between the different numbers. Your task is to return the number that the string spells out. The string will spell out each digit of the number for example '1726' will be 'oneseventwosix' instead of 'one thousand seven hundred six'.\\n\\nthreezerotwofourfiveninesevensix","target":"30245976","rationale":"The given string spells out the number '30245976'."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"Although the Chinese government was initially praised for its response to the quake (especially in comparison to Myanmar's ruling military junta's blockade of aid during Cyclone Nargis), it then saw an erosion in confidence over the school construction scandal.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What happened in Myanmar","target":"Cyclone Nargis","rationale":"The context of the situation is that Myanmar's ruling military junta blocked aid from Cyclone Nargis.\\nSo, in summary, \\"Cyclone Nargis\\" has occurred at Myanmar."},{"source":"The input is a tweet which can be Hate Speech, Offensive or Normal tweet. Hate Speech and Offensive tweets target one community. Given such a tweet, output the community targeted in the tweet. The community will be one of the nine values: 'African', 'Islam', 'Jewish', 'Women', 'Refugee', 'Arab', 'Caucasian', 'Hispanic' or 'Asian'. Output 'None' if the tweet does not target any community. A tweet targets only one community.\\n\\nif famous black millionaire athletes can not love this country that pretty decisive proof that blacks will never peaceably coexist w whites","target":"African","rationale":"The given tweet targets the African American community. It uses the slur \\"blacks\\" to describe African Americans, and it also claims that they will never be able to peacefully coexist with white Americans."},{"source":"Q: what style of art did van gogh do? A:","target":"Post-Impressionist","rationale":"Van Gogh was a Post-Impressionist painter."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to list all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element in the reverse order. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n7, 11, ['339', '8083', 'X', 'J', '6799', '1015', '3785', '7729', '3113', '2143', 'M', 'c', 'Q', '6363', 't', '2005', 'k', 'M', 'x', '5903', 'l', 'k', '9615', '9695', '4035']","target":"M, 2143, 3113, 7729, 3785","rationale":"Given the list ['339', '8083', 'X', 'J', '6799', '1015', '3785', '7729', '3113',' 2143' ,'M','c','Q','6363','t','2005' ,'k' ,'M' ,'x''5903''l''k''9615''9695''4035']\\\\n1. The 7th element is M.\\\\n2. The 8th element is 2143.\\\\n3. The 9th element is 3113.\\\\n4. The 10th element is 7729.\\\\n5, The 11st element is 3785..\\n\\nThe resulting output will be [M, 2143, 3113, 7729, 3785]."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an answer, and your task is to generate a reasonable question for that answer.\\n\\nI have no plans to travel","target":"Are you planning on traveling this year?","rationale":"The answer \\"I have no plans to travel\\" implies that the speaker will not be traveling this year. Therefore, a reasonable question could be \\"Are you planning on traveling this year?\\""},{"source":"Pick the most correct option to answer the following question.\\n\\nLiving things depend on energy from\\n\\nOptions:\\n\\n- A: the Sun\\n\\n- B: the Moon\\n\\n- C: soil\\n\\n- D: water","target":"A","rationale":"All living things depend on energy from the Sun.\\nTherefore, A is correct"},{"source":"What was the response? DIALOG:\\nWhat type of reports came from Anna Politkovskaya in Chechnya?\\n- In numerous articles critical of the war in Chechnya and the pro-Russian regime there, Politkovskaya described alleged abuses committed by Russian military forces.\\n- What were some of the abuses in Anna Politkovskaya's reports from Checnya?\\n- Human rights abuses and policy failures elsewhere in the North Caucasus.\\n- What were some of the human rights abuses chronicled by Anna Politkovskaya in Chechnya?\\n- In one characteristic instance in 1999, she wrote about the plight of an ethnically-mixed old peoples' home under bombardment in Grozny.\\n- What were some of the different ethnicities in Grozny during Anna Politkovskaya's 1999 reports?\\n- How many of Anna Politkovskaya's reports came from Chechnya?\\n- What other interesting facts are in this article about Anna Politkovskaya's reports from Chechnya?\\n-","target":"As Politkovskaya reported, the order supposedly restored under the Kadyrovs became a regime of endemic torture, abduction, and murder.","rationale":"The answer is taken from the paragraph below:\\\\n Politkovskaya's reporting focused on documenting alleged human rights abuses by pro-Russian Chechen forces and their opponents, as well as policy failures elsewhere in the North Caucasus. As Politkovskaya reported, the order supposedly restored under the Kadyrovs became a regime of endemic torture, abduction, and murder."},{"source":"Question: Kate's toy creates low friction when sliding over a counter and high friction when sliding over a floor. Kate's toy will move faster over (A) floor or (B) counter\\n\\nDo not use A and B to answer the question but instead, choose between \\"floor\\" and  \\"counter\\".","target":"counter","rationale":"The toy creates low friction when sliding over a counter and high friction when sliding over the floor. This means that it will move faster with less resistance on the counter than on the floor, so in this case \\"counter\\" is the best answer."},{"source":"During late adulthood, the risk of developing diseases such as cardiovascular diseases and cancer continues to rise. Most people also have a decline in strength and stamina. Their senses may start failing, and their reflex time typically increases. Their immune system also doesn‚Äôt work as well as it used to. As a result, common diseases like the flu may become more serious and even lead to death. The majority of late adults develop arthritis, and as many as one in four develop Alzheimer‚Äôs disease.\\n\\nMike is a doctor with a local hospital. Today, he is seeing two patients, patient A and patient B. Patient A is in early adulthood, but patient B is in late adulthood. Mike needs to find the differences between the patients to come up with recommendations for them.\\n\\nWhich patient is less at risk for Alzheimer's disease, patient A or patient B?","target":"patient A","rationale":"According to the above passage, late adults are more susceptible to diseases like cardiovascular disease and Alzheimer's. The majority of them tend to develop arthritis, while one in four develops Alzheimer's. Early adulthood is a period when people are at their physical peak; hence Mike will be able to recommend that patient A should exercise regularly as it may help him/her stay healthy for longer time periods than if he didn't exercise at all.\\nHowever since Patient B is already suffering from many different kinds of diseases such as cancer or heart problems and due to his age (late adulthood), Mike can tell this patient not get involved with activities that might strain himself too much because these activities could make any underlying health issues worse or even lead to death."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the middle and ending of a three-part story. Your job is to complete the short story by writing a probable beginning of the story. Generated sentences must be short, have fewer than 10 words, and be simple as if narrating to a child. Avoid using any irrelevant extra information when creating the beginning, and use names (e.g. Jack, Barbara,...) instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible.\\n\\nMiddle: This time, it went fast and his picture looked good. Ending: Sal felt great.","target":"Sai normally hated picture days at school","rationale":"The given middle and ending of the story describe that Sai had a good picture day at school. To complete this short story, we find that the beginning should be describing Sai's normal experience of picture days at school. We can write \\"Sai normally hated picture days at school\\" as a possible beginning to this short story."},{"source":"When it's summer in the USA it's winter\\n- in the southern hemisphere\\n- in the northern hemisphere\\n- in the western hemisphere\\n- in the eastern hemisphere\\n\\nWhich is the correct answer?","target":"in the southern hemisphere","rationale":"When it's summer in the USA, it is winter in the southern hemisphere."},{"source":"In the county, the population was spread out with 23.70% under the age of 18, 15.50% from 18 to 24, 26.50% from 25 to 44, 21.80% from 45 to 64, and 12.50% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 34 years. For every 100 females there were 93.50 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 90.00 males.\\n\\nAsk a question about this article.","target":"Which age group had the third most people?","rationale":"Here's a question for the given article:\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: Which age group had the third most people?"},{"source":"You will be given a topic and an argument. Your task is to answer whether the topic and the argument are related or not. A related argument should provide more details about the outcomes of the topic. If the argument refers to or suggests a consequence related to that topic, answer with \\"yes\\"; otherwise, answer with \\"no\\".\\n\\ntopic: Medical marijuana dispensaries\\nargument: The State is justified in protecting individuals from themselves","target":"no","rationale":"This argument addresses whether the State has a right to protect individuals from themselves, but it does not address whether medical marijuana dispensaries should be allowed or not. Therefore, this argument is unrelated to the topic and the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Choose between \\"sandy beach\\" and  \\"rocky beach\\".\\nQuestion: A pebble experiences more friction rolling down a sandy beach then down a rocky beach. This means the _____ is smoother (A) sandy beach (B) rocky beach","target":"sandy beach","rationale":"Friction is a force that resists motion between two objects. The smoother the surface, the less friction there will be and therefore it would require more energy to move an object across that surface.\\nTherefore, since pebbles experience more friction rolling down a sandy beach than one who experiences this on a rocky beach, we can conclude that the sandier of the two beaches must be easier for larger rocks to roll over (or smoother). Hence A is correct."},{"source":"I've always wondered: The novel ‚ÄòThe Hound of the Baskervilles‚Äô, by Arthur Conan Doyle, is set on which English moor?","target":"Dartymoor","rationale":"The novel ‚ÄòThe Hound of the Baskervilles‚Äô, by Arthur Conan Doyle, is set on Dartmoor.\\nSo, \\"Dartymoor\\" would be a reasonable answer to this question."},{"source":"I have a test where I am given the following article, what is an answer for the question: What is the full name of the hapless housemaid? ?\\n\\nTom is chasing Jerry around Mammy Two Shoes, while she is yelling out confusing instructions on where to chase Jerry. She has a broom ready to hit Jerry but instead she bungles things by clumsily hitting Tom on the head causing the cat to forget who he is and believing he is a mouse like Jerry, except he's rude. Tom terrorizes Two Shoes by shaking the chair, causing her to fall off it, before she quickly flees from the deranged cat. Jerry then overhears the terrified Two Shoes on the phone talking to a doctor about Tom. She hears from the Doctor that Tom is suffering from amnesia - a term she doesn't understand. Seeing Tom approaching her with mischief on his mind, Two Shoes has to cut her phone conversation short before she can find out more details about Tom's current illness. The hapless housemaid begs Tom to leave her alone and attempts to evade him by walking away on stilts. Tom mischievously pulls the stilts from under her, causing Two Shoes to fall down with an enormous crash, silencing her. The deranged feline then runs back into the mouse hole and break Jerry's bed, Jerry finds Tom even more annoying as a 'rodent' than as a cat, and so plots to bring him back.","target":"Mammy Two Shoes","rationale":"\\"Mammy Two Shoes\\", as her name suggests, wears two shoes."},{"source":"The input is a conversation between an automated system and a user, followed by a question. The user is looking for suggestions for pubs, restaurants and coffee shops in Cambridge. In the dialogue, the user may provide some criteria for the type of place they want such as price range, cuisine, etc. Similarly, the user may ask details of the place suggested by the system such as phone number, address, etc. The answer of the question has to be a Yes or a No. Given such a dialogue, answer the given question based on the information present in the dialogue.\\n\\nSystem: 'Thank you for calling the Cambridge Information system. Your call will be recorded for research purposes. You may ask for information about a place to eat, such as a restaurant, a pub, or a cafe. How may I help you?'\\nUser: 'knocking sil'\\nSystem: 'What kind of venue are you looking for? For example, a restaurant.'\\nUser: 'pub'\\nSystem: 'Are you looking for somewhere near a particular venue? For example, All Saints Church, the Museum Of Technology, or the Scott Polar Museum.'\\nUser: 'i dont care'\\nSystem: 'Are you looking for a venue with a television?'\\nUser: 'yes'\\nSystem: 'The Bakers is a great pub.'\\nUser: 'internet connection'\\nSystem: 'The Bakers, which has an internet connection, is a great pub.'\\nUser: 'address'\\nSystem: 'The Bakers is on 176 East Road.'\\nUser: 'phone number'\\nSystem: 'The phone number of The Bakers is 01223304121.'\\nUser: 'area'\\nSystem: 'The Bakers is an outstanding pub.'\\nUser: 'area'\\nSystem: 'The Bakers is a great pub.'\\nUser: 'location'\\nSystem: 'The Bakers is an outstanding pub.'\\nUser: 'thank you good bye'\\nQuestion: 'Did the user mention price range they are looking for?'","target":"No","rationale":"The user asks for a pub that has a television and an internet connection, and the system recommends The Bakers. However, the user does not ask any other attributes of The Bakers such as price range. Therefore, the answer is No"},{"source":"Determine the topic of the passage.\\n\\"Its twelve member institutions (which are primarily flagship research universities in their respective states, well-regarded academically, and with relatively large student enrollment) are located primarily in the Midwest , stretching from Nebraska in the west to Penn State in the east.\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Big Ten Conference","rationale":"The passage mostly discusses the Big Ten Conference. Therefore, we can conclude that the topic of this passage is \\"Big Ten Conference\\"."},{"source":"John plays chess with his roommate They make one move each between classes.  Where is his chess set most likely set up?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptionsÔºö\\n\\nA. canada\\n\\nB. cupboard\\n\\nC. dorm\\n\\nD. sitting room\\n\\nE. drawer","target":"C","rationale":"The context states that John plays chess with his roommate, between classes. It can be inferred from the question and options that John is a university student living in a dormitory or residence hall. Based on this information, it can also be inferred that he does not have access to or has limited space in a sitting room or cupboard. The only option left is C which provides the most suitable answer for the above question - Dorm ."},{"source":"Who won the governor election in michigan?","target":"Rick Snyder","rationale":"Rick Snyder won the governor election in michigan is a fact that can be verified through various credible sources such as gov.mi.gov/Archives, \\nhttps://www.michiganradio.org/term/2010-elections and so forth"},{"source":"Article: Israel is considered the most advanced country in Southwest Asia and the Middle East in economic and industrial development. Israel's quality university education and the establishment of a highly motivated and educated populace is largely responsible for spurring the country's high technology boom and rapid economic development. In 2010, it joined the OECD. The country is ranked 3rd in the region and 38th worldwide on the World Bank's Ease of Doing Business Index as well as in the World Economic Forum's Global Competitiveness Report. It has the second-largest number of startup companies in the world (after the United States) and the largest number of NASDAQ-listed companies outside North America.\\n\\nNow answer this question: When did Israel join the OECD?","target":"2010","rationale":"The paragraph mentions that \\"Israel's quality university education and the establishment of a highly motivated and educated populace is largely responsible for spurring the country's high technology boom\\"\\nand also states that Israel joined OECD in 2010. The context makes it clear that this event occurred due to the economic development achieved by Israel. Thus, we can conclude from these statements \\nthat there was an increase in GDP after joining OEDC which caused growth in technological sector along with other sectors such as industrial production leading to improved performance of economy."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that does not connect with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nTitle: Tiffany bracelet. Sentence 1: Allie loved Tiffany's. Sentence 2: But she could not afford it. Sentence 3: She was surprised on Christmas. Sentence 4: Her parents got her a bracelet. Choices: a. He retired on social security. b. She was so thankful.","target":"a","rationale":"The first four sentences talk about Allie and her love for Tiffany's. The fifth sentence needs to connect with this content as well. Therefore, the correct answer is \\"b\\"."},{"source":"Sunday's explosion outside the Al-Rashi police station in the Al-Mashtel neighbourhood in the southeast of Baghdad, left a huge crater in the street.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nQuestion: Can we infer the following?\\nAl Rashi is an executive of the police.","target":"no","rationale":"Based on the context, we know that an explosion took place outside of a police station. However, there is no mention made about who Al Rashi is or his position within the police force. Therefore it can't be inferred from this statement whether he's actually and executive in the force."},{"source":"In this task, you have to generate the title of the recipe given its required ingredients and directions.\\n\\ningredients:  '2 cups Frying Oil, Like Vegetable Or Canola, Plus More As Needed', '3/4 cups All-purpose Flour, Plus More As Needed', '1/2 teaspoons Salt', '1/2 teaspoons Pepper', '1/2 teaspoons Ground Cayenne Pepper', '3/4 cups Panko Bread Crumbs', '1/4 cups Traditional Bread Crumbs', '2 whole Eggs', '4 whole Large Portobello Mushroom Caps, Stems Removed, Cleaned And Cut Into 1/2 Inch Slices', '3/4 cups Mayonnaise', '2 whole Chipotles In Adobo Sauce, Lightly Chopped', '1/2 teaspoons Chipotle Chili Powder', '1/4 teaspoons Salt', '1/4 teaspoons Pepper', '1 teaspoon Lemon Juice',<sep> directions: 'Preheat a large saucepan of oil (the oil should reach about 2 inches up the side of the pan) to 350 F using a frying or candy thermometer.', 'Meanwhile in a shallow bowl, whisk together the flour, salt, pepper and cayenne.', 'In another shallow bowl, mix together the panko bread crumbs and traditional bread crumbs.', 'In another bowl beat your eggs.', 'Set up your shallow bowls in this order: flour, then eggs, then bread crumbs.', 'Starting with one of the portobello slices, dip it in the flour (fully coating the mushroom slice), then dip it in the egg, then dip it in the bread crumbs.', 'Gently place it in the oil with a serrated spoon.', 'Start with one slice, making sure the oil is the right temperature and it browns perfectly.', 'If the oil doesnt sizzle when you add the mushroom, wait another minute or two for the oil to get hotter.', 'Fry for about 2-3 minutes and then flip it over with a pair of tongs and fry for another 2-3 minutes.', 'Transfer your mushroom to a paper-towel lined plate to soak up any excess grease.', 'Repeat these steps for the rest of the slices.', 'After the first one, you can place 3-4 slices per batch into the oil at the same time.', 'But make sure you do not overcrowd the pan.', 'Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve immediately with chipotle aioli.', 'For the chipotle aioli, combine all of the ingredients for the aioli in the bowl of your food processor.', 'Pulse until completely smooth.', 'Serve with your favorite fried veggies.', 'The aioli will keep refrigerated for 2-3 days in an airtight container.', 'Enjoy!'","target":"Portobello Fries","rationale":"The title of the recipe is \\"Portobello Fries\\". Portobello mushrooms are sliced up and coated in a breading, just like French fries. They are then fried, just like French fries. The only difference is that instead of frying potatoes or sweet potatoes, the recipe uses portobello mushrooms."},{"source":"A ball is tossed to a person who misses it and is unable to catch it so\\n- it groans\\n- it falls\\n- it runs\\n- it floats\\n\\nWhich is the correct answer?","target":"it falls","rationale":"A ball is tossed to a person who misses it and unable to catch so,\\nDue to the gravitational force acting on this ball in free fall, there will be an acceleration of gravity g (approx 9.8 m/s2) which leads toward earth surface i.e., towards downward direction. So due to that acceleration as soon as they release their hands from the object, then definitely it falls with linear motion without any rotation or oscillation because of its air resistance ."},{"source":"How can I keep my power cord from tripping me up? To keep power cords out of my way when I‚Äôm working with a portable power tool, I usually secure the cord at my side, using a 6-in. loop of Velcro fastener to attach it to my belt loop.\\nDoes this phrase make sense?","target":"Yes","rationale":"In this question, the answer is Yes.\\nHere's why:"},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\nFinnish Kemira 's net sales EUR decreased to EUR 1,259.6 mn in January-June 2009 from EUR 1,425.1 mn in January-June 2008 .","target":"negative","rationale":"This financial news states that Finnish Kemira's net sales decreased from EUR 1,425.1 million in January-June 2008 to EUR 1,259.6 million in January-June 2009. This indicates a decline in sales for the company, which is generally considered as a negative development. So, this financial news can be classified as \\"negative\\"."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. The story has one of the three following scenarios: (1) when the individual's belief matches reality, (2) when the individual's belief does not match reality, (3) is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios.\\n\\nOliver entered the bathroom. Benjamin entered the bathroom. The apple is in the red_box. Oliver moved the apple to the red_suitcase. Where will Benjamin look for the apple?","target":"red_suitcase","rationale":"The story describes Oliver's actions in the bathroom. When Benjamin enters, he sees that the apple is in the red_box. Before Benjamin can move it to another spot, Oliver moves it to a different box - the red_suitcase. Since Benjamin sees that is where the apple was last put, he will look for it there."},{"source":"Humanism\\nIn the 6th century BCE, Taoist teacher Lao Tzu espoused a series of naturalistic concepts with some elements of humanistic philosophy. The Silver Rule of Confucianism from Analects XV.24, is an example of ethical philosophy based on human values rather than the supernatural. Humanistic thought is also contained in other Confucian classics, e.g., as recorded in Zuo Zhuan, Ji Liang says, \\"People is the zhu (master, lord, dominance, owner or origin) of gods. So, to sage kings, people first, gods second\\"; Neishi Guo says, \\"Gods, clever, righteous and wholehearted, comply with human.\\" Taoist and Confucian secularism contain elements of moral thought devoid of religious authority or deism however they only partly resembled our modern concept of secularism.\\n\\nQ: Where could you read this information?","target":"Zuo Zhuan","rationale":"The answer is Zuo Zhuan since the passage states: \\"Humanistic thought is also contained in other Confucian classics, e.g., as recorded in Zuo Zhuan\\"."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"Throughout the Hellenistic world, these Greco-Macedonian colonists considered themselves by and large superior to the native \\"barbarians\\" and excluded most non-Greeks from the upper echelons of courtly and government life. Most of the native population was not Hellenized, had little access to Greek culture and often found themselves discriminated against by their Hellenic overlords. Gymnasiums and their Greek education, for example, were for Greeks only. Greek cities and colonies may have exported Greek art and architecture as far as the Indus, but these were mostly enclaves of Greek culture for the transplanted Greek elite. The degree of influence that Greek culture had throughout the Hellenistic kingdoms was therefore highly localized and based mostly on a few great cities like Alexandria and Antioch. Some natives did learn Greek and adopt Greek ways, but this was mostly limited to a few local elites who were allowed to retain their posts by the Diadochi and also to a small number of mid-level administrators who acted as intermediaries between the Greek speaking upper class and their subjects. In the Seleucid empire for example, this group amounted to only 2.5 percent of the official class.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What are the places that people now go to exercise which was one of the places only Greeks were allowed in?","target":"Gymnasiums","rationale":"The given passage mentions that Gymnasiums were for Greeks only. A gymnasium is a public place where people can go and exercise, so the answer is \\"Gymnasiums\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue between a user and an assistant, where users and assistants converse about geographic topics like geopolitical entities and locations. The task here is to find if the dialogue is by the user or assistant. Classify your answers into user and assistant.\\n\\nThey have a private civil war history tour, there's also the Lewis and Clark History tour. They have a wonderful scavenger hunt and, of course, like I said earlier, there's the St. Louis Zoo. My favorite thing to do though is go to Branson, MO. There are loads of entertainment that you will need more than a week.","target":"assistant","rationale":"The assistant informs the user about tourist spots in St. Louis and tries to persuade the user to visit them."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the union of two given sets. A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. Union of two given sets is the smallest set which contains all the elements of both the sets. To find the union of two given sets, A and B is a set that consists of all the elements of A and all the elements of B such that no element is repeated.\\n\\nSet1: '{6, 7, 9, 18, 20}', Set2: '{1, 3, 6, 7, 10, 11, 12, 17}'. How many elements are there in the union of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"11","rationale":"Set1: '{6, 7, 9, 18, 20}', Set2: '{1, 3, 6, 7 ,10 ,11 ,12 ,17}'\\\\n\\\\nUnion of Set1 and Set2 = {6 7 9 18 20 1 3 10 11 12 17}\\\\nLength of Union is 11."},{"source":"What is the question to: \\"Oakhurst is a census-designated place and unincorporated community within Ocean Township , in Monmouth County , New Jersey , United States.\\"? The topic is Oakhurst, New Jersey.","target":"\\"what county is oakhurst, nj in?\\"","rationale":"Based on the information provided, a reasonable question is \\"what county is oakhurst, nj in?\\""},{"source":"Given a sentence with a missing word, pick the answer option that best fills out the missing word in the sentence. Indicate each answer with its index ('a', 'b', 'c', 'd').\\n\\nAltricial chicks are tended and brooded by female the first ____ days.\\\\Question: Choose the right answer from options given a) four b) ten c) no d) five","target":"b","rationale":"The context of the sentence is about chicks, which are small birds. Therefore, we can assume that \\\\\\"the\\\\\\" refers to female birds. Now we need to find out how long female birds tend and brood their chicks. The answer is 10 days (according to https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/brood)."},{"source":"No stockpiles of weapons of mass destruction have been found in Iraq since Saddam's regime was toppled in a US-led invasion last year.\\n\\nQ with options: Can we draw the following conclusion?\\nWeapons of mass destruction found in Iraq.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"Since no weapon was found, we cannot draw the conclusion in question."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of integers. You should only return an integer if the first digit is the same as the last digit in the number. If an integer has a single digit, then it should be returned. If there are no integers that start and end with the same digit then an empty list (\\"[]\\") should be returned.\\n\\n[-627, 213, 109, -753, -587, -741, 833, -214, 443, -508, 766, -411, -399, 74, 345]","target":"[]","rationale":"There are no integers that start and end with the same digit, so an empty list (denoted by \\"[]\\" in Python) is returned."},{"source":"OPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nDoes \\"Many low-born individuals, including townsfolk, peasants and Jews, could and did rise to official ennoblement in Polish society.\\" correctly answer the question of Who could rise into polish ennoblement?","target":"yes","rationale":"The statement provides the correct answer to the question, since it states that many low-born individuals including townsfolk and peasants could rise into Polish ennoblement. So, the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"Question: Where does she keep her notebook with her when not in use?\\nOptions:\\n- locker\\n- desktop\\n- classroom\\n- office\\n- backpack\\n\\nExplain why a human would choose \\"backpack\\" to answer the question above:","target":"books are carried in backpacks","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"books are carried in backpacks\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue between a user and an assistant, where users and assistants converse about geographic topics like geopolitical entities and locations. The task here is to find if the dialogue is by the user or assistant. Classify your answers into user and assistant.\\n\\nHow is the economy?","target":"user","rationale":"The assistant may have said \\"How is the economy?\\" to indicate that the user can choose between good and bad for describing the state of the economy. So, \\"How is the economy?\\" is not a question but rather a signal to indicate that a response from user is expected."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to return the sum of all the numerical elements in the list A between the positions i and j (including positions i and j). Return 0 if no numerical element is present in the list between the given ranges. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n1, 4, ['8245', 'X', 'U', '8795', 'o', '9745', 'T', 'y']","target":"17040","rationale":"Given the list ['8245', 'X', 'U', '8795', 'o', '9745', 'T', 'y'], we need to find the elements within the range 1 ~ 4.\\\\n1. The 1st element is 8245.\\\\n2. The 2nd element is X, which is converted into 0 during calculation.\\\\n3. The 3rd element is U, which is converted into 0 during calculation as well (just like X).\\\\n4. The 4th element is 8795\\\\nThe final result of the sum: 8245 + 0 + 0 + 8795 = 17040"},{"source":"Choose your answer: Is \\"On the northern outskirts of the city, Crownhill Fort is a well restored example of a \\"Palmerston's Folly\\".\\" a good answer to the question \\"Who runs Crownhill Fort?\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The passage talks about the architecture of Crownhill Fort, but does not provide any information on who runs it. Hence, \\"On the northern outskirts of the city, Crownhill Fort is a well restored example of a 'Palmerston's Folly'.\\" would be an incorrect answer to this question and so the option chosen is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"The person saw his wife cheating on him, but tries to forget it, what was he doing?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptionsÔºö\\n\\nA. deceive himself\\n\\nB. thank god\\n\\nC. experience pain\\n\\nD. enjoy life\\n\\nE. absorb moisture","target":"A","rationale":"The context of the question is that a person saw their wife cheating on them, but they try to forget it. This suggests that this action would be done as an attempt to not have negative feelings towards his wife's actions and possibly avoid acknowledging her unfaithfulness. \\nGiven this information, the best answer for what he was doing is \\"deceive himself\\", as attempting to ignore or block out painful experiences can cause emotional issues in the future if left unresolved. Additionally, \\"experience pain\\" may seem like an appropriate choice given the situation; however ‚Äúpain‚Äù refers more specifically to physical discomfort rather than mental anguish. Therefore, it isn't relevant based on how we define pain here. The options of enjoying life, thanking god or absorbing moisture are unrelated choices so these don't"},{"source":"In this task, you are given an abstract of article. Your task is to generate label \\"True\\" if abstract is structured, otherwise generate \\"False\\". A structured abstract is composed of a topic sentence (or key sentence), relevant supporting sentences, and a closing (or transition) sentence. This structure is key to keeping your abstract focused on the main idea and creating a clear and concise image.\\n\\nOBJECTIVES To evaluate the effects of early lumbar disc surgery compared with prolonged conservative care for patients with sciatica over two years of follow-up.   \\n DESIGN Randomised controlled trial.   \\n SETTING Nine Dutch hospitals.   \\n PARTICIPANTS 283 patients with 6-12 weeks of sciatica.   \\n INTERVENTIONS Early surgery or an intended six months of continued conservative treatment, with delayed surgery if needed.   \\n MAIN OUTCOME MEASURES Scores from Roland disability questionnaire for sciatica, visual analogue scale for leg pain, and Likert self rating scale of global perceived recovery.   \\n RESULTS Of the 141 patients assigned to undergo early surgery, 125 (89%) underwent microdiscectomy. Of the 142 patients assigned to conservative treatment, 62 (44%) eventually required surgery, seven doing so in the second year of follow-up. There was no significant overall difference between treatment arms in disability scores during the first two years (P=0.25). Improvement in leg pain was faster for patients randomised to early surgery, with a significant difference between \\"areas under the curves\\" over two years (P=0.05). This short term benefit of early surgery was no longer significant by six months and continued to narrow between six months and 24 months. Patient satisfaction decreased slightly between one and two years for both groups. At two years 20% of all patients reported an unsatisfactory outcome.   \\n CONCLUSIONS Early surgery achieved more rapid relief of sciatica than conservative care, but outcomes were similar by one year and these did not change during the second year.   \\n TRIAL REGISTRY ISRCT No 26872154.","target":"True","rationale":"The abstract includes a topic sentence that states the objective of the study (\\"OBJECTIVES To evaluate the effects of early lumbar disc surgery compared with prolonged conservative care for patients with sciatica over two years of follow-up.\\"), relevant supporting sentences that describe the methods and results of the study, and a closing sentence that summarizes the main findings and conclusions of the study (\\"CONCLUSIONS Early surgery achieved more rapid relief of sciatica than conservative care, but outcomes were similar by one year and these did not change during the second year.\\"). This structure helps to keep it focused and concise while providing key information about its purpose, method, result, conclusion. Therefore, answer is ‚ÄúTrue‚Äù."},{"source":"Given a math word problem, answer the following question. You might need to apply addition or subtraction mathematical operators on the numbers embedded in the text to answer the question and then only report the final numerical answer.\\n\\nmarin has 9 apples and donald has 2 apples . how many apples do marin and donald have together ?","target":"11","rationale":"The sum of 9 and 2 is 11, which is the correct answer."},{"source":"Given an abstract, generate a keyword (a noun phrase) that best describes the focus or contribution of the paper. Such keywords can be directly from the given abstract or outside it.\\n\\nAbstract: This retrospective review of medical records was designed to address three questions: 1) Can the depression seen in some patients with Dementia of the Alzheimer's Type (DAT) be successfully treated? 2) Does this treatment lead to any long-term improvement in the patient's cognitive status? and 3) Do patients with coexisting DAT and depression have a different long-term clinical course than nondepressed DAT patients? In the authors' sample of 131 DAT subjects, 41 (31%) also met DMS-III criteria for a major affective disorder. Of those DAT plus depression patients whose records reflected treatment (usually with a tricyclic antidepressant), 85% (17 of 20) showed clear evidence of improvement in mood, vegetative signs, or activities of daily living (ADLs) based on review of the medical record. An analysis of change in cognitive function (measured by the Folstein Mini-Mental State) and five global measures failed to reveal any differences between the depressed and nondepressed groups after a mean interval of 17 months. The depression that occurs in approximately one-quarter to one-third of DAT patients appears to respond to appropriate therapy. These patients often show improvement in their mood and ADLs but remain demented.","target":"Aged","rationale":"The abstract focuses on the diagnosis and treatment of depression in elderly patients with dementia. Therefore, the keyword that best describes the focus or contribution of the paper is \\"Aged\\".\\n'''"},{"source":"Here is a question about this article: Modern Estonia is a fairly ethnically heterogeneous country, but this heterogeneity is not a feature of much of the country as the non-Estonian population is concentrated in two of Estonia's counties. Thirteen of Estonia's 15 counties are over 80% ethnic Estonian, the most homogeneous being Hiiumaa, where Estonians account for 98.4% of the population. In the counties of Harju (including the capital city, Tallinn) and Ida-Viru, however, ethnic Estonians make up 60% and 20% of the population, respectively. Russians make up 25.6% of the total population but account for 36% of the population in Harju county and 70% of the population in Ida-Viru county.\\nWhat is the answer to this question: What number describes the percentage of Russian Estonians?","target":"25.6%","rationale":"The article states that Russians make up 25.6% of the total population in Estonia, so this is the correct answer to the question: \\"What number describes the percentage of Russian Estonians?\\".\\nThis can also be easily checked by calculating (36+70)/2 which gives us 53%. This roughly agrees with what we found from reading and understanding the text."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a short story with a beginning, two potential middles, and an ending. Your job is to choose the middle statement that makes the story incoherent / implausible by indicating 1 or 2 in the output. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nBeginning: Walter owns a carpet and upholstery cleaning service. Middle 1: Walter liked to help out people in need. Middle 2: Walter liked to laugh at people in need. Ending: Walter offered his service for free, since someone hustled the priest.","target":"2","rationale":"Middle 1 indicates that Walter offered his service for free because he liked to help people in need. Middle 2 also indicates that Walter offered his service for free, but the reason (liking to laugh at people in need) is not consistent with the ending (someone hustled the priest). So Middle 2 makes less sense."},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is \\"The worm was tasty.\\" true if \\"The fish ate the worm. It was tasty.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"yes","rationale":"The context of the premise indicates that \\"the fish ate the worm\\" and that it was tasty. The correct answer is therefore \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"I had something that might have been a little supernatural.\\nSo I was trying to sleep one time, and I sleep under the blankets 99% of the time. I sleep downstairs, so hearing noise is pretty normal. Also, my door doesn‚Äôt lock, or even latch the door handle, so you can just push it open.\\nSo I was laying down, maybe at 60% in terms of how close I was to falling asleep, so I just had to lay down for like 5 more minutes.\\nBut there are a lot of noises, and they freak me out even though I just sorta pretend that they‚Äôre definitely a cat or my dog or something.\\nSo, I‚Äôm already slightly spooked, but I‚Äôm ignoring it and going to sleep anyway.\\nBut then, I hear my door open. That isn‚Äôt too weird, I do have cats, so even though by this point my fear is intense, I just sorta blow it off and keep trying to sleep.\\nAnd then, something that‚Äôs never happened in a situation like this, I feel something moving towards me on my bed.\\nIt feels like a cats movements, with light feet making slight reverberations on the bed.\\nSo my fear goes away entirely, and I‚Äôm like ‚ÄúOh okay, it‚Äôs just the cat, that‚Äôs good.‚Äù And I lift my blankets off my head to let my cat under with me, and because the fear seemed to make the atmosphere under there very hot and tense, and then I look at my bed and there‚Äôs nothing.\\nSo I just pretend nothing happened and go to sleep, but that still sticks with me and even though it‚Äôs kinda underwhelming I still think it was very strange since I wasn‚Äôt at the ‚Äúedge of consciousness‚Äù stage of going to sleep, so I feel like the chances I imagined it aren‚Äôt too high.\\nAccording to the above context, choose the correct option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: Where does the author sleep at night?\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. A downstairs bedroom\\n\\nB. In bed\\n\\nC. not enough information\\n\\nD. Under the blankets","target":"A","rationale":"The context of the story indicates that it takes place in a downstairs bedroom. The author mentions sleeping under blankets and hearing other noises from downstairs, which suggests that they are not located upstairs but rather downstairs.\\nA is therefore correct answer"},{"source":"Given the fact that:\\n\\nThe farther apart you move your hands, the stronger the force of the rubber band pulling your hands together.\\n\\nAnswer the question:\\n\\n\\nThe pulling force of a rubber band will increase or decrease when you move your hands together?","target":"decrease","rationale":"The fact states that the farther apart you move your hands, the stronger the force of a rubber band pulling them together. Moving your hands closer (together) would therefore decrease this pulling force because they are no longer as far apart.\\nSo, moving your hands together will decrease the pulliing force of a rubberband: decreasing"},{"source":"Fill in the response. DIALOG:\\nWhat happened in 1995?\\n- Ima is the debut studio album by American electronic musician BT, released on October 9, 1995\\n- Was Ima the debut studio album by BT successful?\\n- Blending house beats with sweeping New Age sounds, Ima helped to create the trance sound.\\n- What were some singles from BT's debut studio album Ima?\\n- The album includes the 1995 single Embracing the Future, which reached number one on the UK Dance Chart, as well as Loving You More featuring Vincent Covello.\\n- Did BT win any awards for his album Ima?\\n- BT did not win any awards for his album Ima.\\n- Did BT work with anyone for his debut studio album Ima?\\n-","target":"Following the release of Ima, BT began traveling to England regularly. It was during this time that he met Tori Amos.","rationale":"The correct response is \\"Following the release of Ima, BT began traveling to England regularly. It was during this time that he met Tori Amos.\\" In the chat dialogue, the user asks if BT worked with anyone for his debut studio album \\"Ima\\". The correct response answers this question and provides additional information about what happened following the release of BT's album."},{"source":"What is the answer for the question: What is the name of the person who was said to have an ambiguous facial expression on the cover from the following article ?\\n\\n\\"Talk That Talk\\" was written by Ester Dean, Jay-Z, StarGate, Anthony Best, Sean Combs, and Chucky Thompson, and produced by StarGate. They had produced Rihanna's 2010 hit singles \\"Only Girl (In the World)\\" and \\"What's My Name?\\" for her fifth album Loud. StarGate told Norwegian website 730.no that it was their first collaboration with Jay-Z and said that they were very satisfied with both the song and each artist's contribution. \\"Talk That Talk\\" was recorded at Roc the Mic Studios and The Jungle City Studios in New York City, Westlake Recording Studios in Los Angeles, and The Hide Out Studios in London. StarGate, Miles Walker, and Mike Anderson served as the song's recording engineers. Rihanna's vocals were recorded by Marcos Tovar and Kuk Harrell, who additionally produced them, while Jordan \\"DJ Swivel\\" Young recorded Jay-Z's verses. Additional recording of the song was done in Sofitel Paris Le Faubourg and Savoy London hotels. \\"Talk That Talk\\" was mixed by Phil Tan and assistant Daniela Rivera at Ninja Beat Club Studios in Atlanta. Eriksen and Hermansen recorded the song's instrumentation, and Tim Blacksmith and Danny D. were assigned as its executive producers.In December 2011, Rihanna asked her fans on Twitter to recommend a song from Talk That Talk for release as the third single. On January 10, 2012, she announced that the title track was chosen and also debuted the single's cover‚Äîa black-and-white image in which Rihanna is dressed in \\"street punk/rockabilly clothes\\" and crouches against a wall. According to Jazmine Gray of Vibe magazine, the singer has an ambiguous facial expression on the cover. On January 17, Def Jam Recordings serviced \\"Talk That Talk\\" to urban contemporary radio stations in the United States. It was also sent to US contemporary hit and rhythmic radios on February 14. On March 26, \\"Talk That Talk\\" was released in France as a CD single, which contained the album version of the song and the Chuckie Extended Remix of \\"We Found Love\\".","target":"Rihanna","rationale":"According to the article, \\"Talk That Talk\\" was released as a single from Rihanna's sixth album of the same name. On January 10, 2012, she announced that this song would be chosen and also debuted the single‚Äôs cover‚Äîa black-and-white image in which Rihanna is dressed in \\"street punk/rockabilly clothes\\" and crouches against a wall. According to Jazmine Gray of Vibe magazine, the singer has an ambiguous facial expression on the cover.\\n\\nSo we know this person appears in or created:\\n1) The single called ‚ÄúTalk That Talk‚Äù \\n2) The music video for ‚ÄúWe Found Love (Chuckie Extended Remix)‚Äù   3) An ambiguous photograph that appeared on her Twitter"},{"source":"Categorize the comment on the basis of insult. If the comment is insulting output Yes, otherwise output No.\\n\\nThe moral of this story? Cats rock.","target":"No","rationale":"The comment does not contain any form of insult and is merely a statement. Therefore, the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Read the article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: Paris - A winter storm brought blanket of snow across Europe on Monday, forcing the closure of the icy Eiffel Tower in Paris and causing flight cancellations.\\nUp to four inches of snow was recorded in parts of France, the National Weather Service said.Most areas, including Paris, got around half that amount.French authorities issued traffic alerts in around 30 regions because of icy roads.The Eiffel Tower, one of the main tourist attractions in Paris, was closed because of slippery conditions.\\n\\" We can't put down salt because it's metallic,\\" Eiffel Tower press officer Is a belle Snouts said.\\" We can't use sand either, because it risks getting into the elevator cogs .\\" \\"The cold,\\" she said, \\"is no problem, but snow can be dangerous.\\"\\nA dozen flights were canceled at Paris Charles de Gaulle Airport, officials said.The Paris airport authority said bad weather in other parts of Europe continued to the cancellations.Workers had been sent since midnight Sunday to clear runways at Charles de Gaulle and the smaller Only Airport.\\nIn Germaine, heavy snowfall snarled road traffic and flight delays and cancellations at the country}y s intimation airports.Glissando of Interactional Airport said no flights were allowed in or out between 6 -9 am Monday because clearing crew were unable to keep up with the snow.\\nMore than 30 flights were canceled because of the bad weather, import spokesman Christian  Witt said.Up to four inches of snow was reported in Tussled and around six inches in Potsdam, but none had struggled to the roads amid (...... ) heavy post - holiday traffic.\\nGermany's National Weather Service is forecasting subzero temperatures for the coming days.Snow also fell across Britain.Children built snowmen in parts of England, including Cambridge.\\nQuestion: The winter storm brought  _  of snow across Paris.\\nOptions: A: 4 inches\\nB: about 2 inches\\nC: half an inch\\nD: 6 inches","target":"B","rationale":"The article mentions that 4 inches of snow was recorded in parts of France and Paris got around half that amount. Therefore, the correct answer is \\"B\\"."},{"source":"Given an entity as input, output another entity which is part of the input entity. These are entities of meronym. In linguistics, meronymy is a semantic relation between a meronym denoting a part and a holonym denoting a whole. In simpler terms, a meronym (i.e., output entity) is in a part-of relationship with its holonym (i.e., input entity).\\n\\negg","target":"progesterone","rationale":"Eggs are produced in the ovary, which contains the hormone progesterone. So progesterone is a meronym of egg."},{"source":"You are provided with a list of converations between a \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\". Figure out if the conversation provided as \\"classify_text\\" is authored by \\"USER\\" or \\"ASSISTANT\\". There are maximum of 7 conversations between \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\" in each input\\n\\nASSISTANT: What type of movies do you like? , USER: I like good action movies like The Fast and the Furious movies, which aren't great movies, but they're fun movies. And so, fun action movies that don't take themselves seriously I like. , ASSISTANT: What is another one of your favorite movies? , USER: Another one in that genre or just overall? , ASSISTANT: overall , USER: There was a, classify_text: I won't say that one cuz it's too old, and I like it just for the music. But let's go with","target":"USER","rationale":"The conversation is provided in the input. The conversation starts with Assistant asking a question and the user answering it. Then, Assistant asks another question and the user answers it by giving an example from a particular genre. So, the sentence \\"There was a, classify_text: I won't say that one cuz it's too old, and I like it just for the music. But let's go with\\" definitely belongs to USER because ASSISTANT does not ask any such question"},{"source":"Here is a premise: \\"Swimmer descending into water performing a flip while several women in background look on.\\"\\n\\nHere is a hypothesis: \\"a swimmer is taking a break in the locker room eating chips\\"\\n\\n.Does the premise tell us whether the hypothesis is true?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise and the hypothesis are unrelated to one another. The premise describes a swimmer jumping into water, while the hypothesis talks about someone taking a break in the locker room eating chips. So, it is not possible for us to tell whether this statement is true or false based on only these two statements."},{"source":"2 seriously wounded in Grand Crossing shooting Two men were seriously wounded in a shooting Thursday evening in the Grand Crossing neighborhood on the South Side. The men ‚Äî ages 28 and 39 ‚Äî were shot at by someone inside a vehicle that pulled up to them at 6:11 p.m. in the 7300 block of South Dante, Chicago Police said. The older man was shot in his face and taken to Northwestern Memorial Hospital in serious condition, police said. The younger man took himself to Jackson Park Hospital with a gunshot wound to his shoulder in serious condition.\\n\\nChoose your answer: based on the paragraph above can we conclude that \\"The two men were attacked in Detroit.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nI think the answer is","target":"No","rationale":"The premise clearly states that the shooting took place in Chicago, so it is not possible to conclude that the two men were attacked in Detroit. So, the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"If \\"Bill passed the gameboy to John because his turn was over.\\", does it follow that \\"John's turn was over.\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"The phrase \\"John's turn was over\\" does not appear in the sentence and so cannot be inferred from it. The sentence instead says that Bill passed the gameboy to John because his (Bill's) turn was over, thereby implying that John is now taking a turn at playing with the GameBoy. Therefore, answer choice no is correct."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an adjective, and your job is to generate its antonym. An antonym of a word is a word opposite in meaning to it.\\n\\ncharming","target":"dull","rationale":"An antonym of charming is dull."},{"source":"Given a piece of financial news and its polarity, classify it into 'true' if the polarity is correct and classify into 'false' if the polarity is incorrect. Output must be 'true' or 'false'. \\n\\nnews:Brazilian non-profit interbank Camara Interbancaria de Pagamentos CIP has acquired solutions from US business integration solutions provider Sterling Commerce , the latter company said in a statement .\\npolarity:negative","target":"false","rationale":"This financial news describes the acquisition of solutions from a US business integration solutions provider by Brazilian non-profit interbank Camara Interbancaria de Pagamentos CIP. Since it describes a new project/acquisition, it can be classified as 'positive'. However, the given polarity is 'negative' and hence the news is classified as 'false'."},{"source":"Here's a problem to solve: Which of the following data would be most useful for describing the climate of a specific area?\\n\\nAmong the 4 following options, which is the correct answer?\\n\\n- A: average weekly wind speeds for 1 month\\n \\n- B: daily relative humidity levels for 18 months\\n \\n- C: total annual precipitation amounts for 2 years\\n \\n- D: average high and low monthly temperatures for 20 years","target":"D","rationale":"The answer is D. \\nAll of the provided options are measures used to describe climate, and thus each could be useful for describing the climate of a specific area. However, since we're looking for \\"the most useful\\" option among these choices, all other things being equal, it would make sense that more data collected over time (years) is likely to provide more detail than less data collected over shorter periods of time (weeks or months). This leaves us with A vs D: average weekly wind speeds for 1 month versus average high and low monthly temperatures for 20 years. Since temperature can vary widely from day-to-day but tends not to change as much week-to-week or even month-to-month in a given region if there's no major event like an"},{"source":"Is the premise \\"There are a man and a woman sitting down with a door and a window behind them.\\" true if \\"A couple sit on a stretch of beach.\\"?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"While the premise mentions a door and window behind two people, there is no indication of whether they are sitting down or not. Similarly, while it is mentioned that there are a man and woman on the beach, we do not know if they were sitting at any point in time. Hence, it is incorrect to say that \\"A couple sit on a stretch of beach.\\" contains information about whether these individuals sat down with doors and windows behind them as well."},{"source":"Born in 1921 on the south side of Chicago, Illinois, Shepherd briefly lived in East Chicago, Indiana, and was raised in Hammond, Indiana, where he graduated from Hammond High School in 1939. The movie A Christmas Story is loosely based on his days growing up in Hammond's southeast side neighborhood of Hessville. As a youth he worked briefly as a mail carrier in a steel mill and earned his Amateur radio license (W9QWN) at age 16, sometimes claiming he was even younger. He sporadically attended Indiana University, but never graduated.\\n\\nEarly in his career, Shepherd had a television program on WLW-TV in Cincinnati called Rear Bumper. He claimed that he was recommended to replace the resigning Steve Allen on NBC's Tonight Show. Shepherd was reportedly brought to New York City by NBC executives to prepare for the position, but they were contractually bound to first offer it to Jack Paar. The network was certain Paar would hold out for a role in prime time, but he accepted the late-night assignment. However, he did not assume the position permanently until Shepherd and Ernie Kovacs had co-hosted the show.  In late 1960 and early 1961, he did a weekly television show on WOR (channel 9) in New York, but it did not last long. Between 1971 and 1994, Shepherd became a screenwriter of note, writing and producing numerous works for both television and cinema, all based on his originally spoken and written stories. He was the writer and narrator of the show Jean Shepherd's America, produced by Boston Public Television station WGBH for PBS, in which he visited various American locales, and interviewed local people of interest. He used a somewhat similar format for the New Jersey Network TV show Shepherd's Pie. On many of the Public TV shows he wrote, directed and edited entire shows.  He also wrote and narrated many works, the most famous being the 1983 MGM feature film A Christmas Story, which is now considered a holiday classic. Shepherd narrates the film as the adult Ralph Parker, and also has a cameo role playing a man in line at the department store waiting for Santa Claus.  Ten years later, Shepherd and A Christmas Story director Bob Clark returned to the same working-class Cleveland street neighborhood to film a sequel, It Runs in the Family (later known as My Summer Story), released by MGM in 1994 and featuring an almost entirely different cast from the previous film.  PBS aired several television movies based on Shepherd stories, also featuring the Parker family. These included The Phantom of the Open Hearth (1976), which aired as part of the anthology series Visions; The Great American Fourth of July and Other Disasters (1982) and The Star-Crossed Romance of Josephine Cosnowski (1985), both as part of the anthology series American Playhouse; and Ollie Hopnoodle's Haven of Bliss (1988), a co-production with The Disney Channel. All were narrated by Shepherd but otherwise featured different casts. Answer this question using a quote from the following article:\\n\\nWhat books did he write?","target":"A Christmas Story,","rationale":"The article mentions that he wrote and narrated numerous works. It also talks about the 1983 MGM feature film A Christmas Story, which is now considered a holiday classic. The writer says \\"He narrates the film as the adult Ralph Parker\\", indicating that he has written it in addition to narrating it for screen adaptation.\\nIt then goes on to mention another book Jean Shepherd's America, produced by Boston Public Television station WGBH for PBS; this indicates that there are at least two books authored by him - A Christmas Story & Jean Shepherd's America"},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with three passages, 1, 2, and 3. Your job is to determine which passage can be used to answer the question by searching for further information using terms from the passage. Indicate your choice as 1, 2, or 3.\\n\\nQuestion: How old was Gilbert when collaborated for the last time with Sullivan in 1896? Passage 1:When the Gilbert and Sullivan partnership collapsed after the production of The Gondoliers in 1889, their producer Richard D'Oyly Carte struggled to find successful new works to show at the Savoy Theatre. Carte produced Sullivan's grand opera, Ivanhoe at another theatre, and afterwards, he turned to Sullivan to create more comic operas for the Savoy. With Sydney Grundy, Sullivan wrote the nostalgic and sentimental Haddon Hall (1892) then, reunited with W. S. Gilbert, he produced Utopia, Limited (1893). He next returned, with his earlier collaborator F. C. Burnand, with The Chieftain (1894) and collaborated for the last time with Gilbert on The Grand Duke (1896). None of these had proved to be more than modestly successful, and Carte's other new pieces for the Savoy in the 1890s had done no better. Following the success of Sullivan's ballet Victoria and Merrie England in 1897, Carte asked Sullivan to work on another new opera for the Savoy.\\n Passage 2:He started his career with Shrewsbury Town in 1988, and after being voted onto the PFA Team of the Year, moved on to Manchester City for ¬£500,000 in October 1993. In August 1995 he transferred to Portsmouth for ¬£200,000, moving on to Peterborough United for ¬£225,000 in March 1996. He joined Leyton Orient for ¬£65,000 in March 1997, where he stayed for four years, interrupted by short spells at Wrexham (on loan) and Port Vale. He played for Luton Town between July 2001 and 2003 following a ¬£65,000 transfer, later dropping into non-league football with Harlow Town, Braintree Town, Brentwood Town, and Maldon Town. He also represented Wales at under-21 level and also for the \\"B\\" team. Within his three spells with Leyton Orient he achieved cult status and in 2004 received 9% of the vote for all-time cult hero behind Peter Kitchen and Terry Howard.\\n Passage 3:The record builds on ideas explored in Pink Floyd's earlier recordings and performances, while omitting the extended instrumentals that characterised their earlier work. A concept album, its themes explore conflict, greed, time, death, and mental illness, the latter partly inspired by the deteriorating health of founding member Syd Barrett, who departed the group in 1968. The group used recording techniques such as multitrack recording, tape loops, and analogue synthesisers. Snippets from interviews with the band's road crew, as well as philosophical quotations, were also used. Engineer Alan Parsons was responsible for many sonic aspects and the recruitment of singer Clare Torry, who appears on \\"The Great Gig in the Sky\\". The sleeve, which depicts a prism spectrum, was designed by Storm Thorgerson, following keyboardist Richard Wright's request for a \\"simple and bold\\" design, representing the band's lighting and the record's themes. The album was promoted with two singles: \\"Money\\" and \\"Us and Them\\".","target":"1","rationale":"The question asks for the age of Gilbert in 1896.  In passage 1, it's stated that Gilbert worked with Sullivan for the last time in 1896.  The age of Gilbert can be found from this statement: \\"Gilbert was born at 17 Southampton Street, Strand, London. His father ... died when he was eighteen\\" (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W._S._Gilbert). Therefore, by using information from the Wikipedia page and sentence 3 of passage 1, the age can be calculated in 1896 to be 66 years old (1818 + 66 = 1884). Hence, Passage 1 can be used to answer this question."},{"source":"What's the answer to that question: what are the four official languages of nigeria?","target":"English Language","rationale":"English Language is one of the official languages of Nigeria. \\nThe other three are Hausa, Igbo and Yoruba."},{"source":"Categorize the comment on the basis of sexual explicitness. If the comment is sexually explicit output Yes, otherwise output No.\\n\\nYou all call it transit.  Here is what I have heard folks  call this so called \\"transit\\"---all heard at the transit center in Eugene: bum trains,  shame train, limo for lushes, a place to hit up (shoot heroin), trash stash (alluding to the allure of the riders), the mission migrator (all the bums headed to the Eugene Mission between 5:30 and 6:00 when they have curfew), the loony bin; getaway car; and so on.   The U of O students get free passes and the bums get free bus passes.  I have to tell you, I am not paying $65 a month to ride with junkies and bums, petty little criminals, a drunk puking into the seat next to him or the guy passed out in the back, with five garbage bags at his feet blocking the aisles.  After working all day,  it would not be worth it. Nope, I will drive.","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given comment contains explicit language regarding sexual activities (sex with strangers, genitalia, intercourse) and explicit descriptions of nudity. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. The story has one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nOwen entered the master_bedroom. Ella entered the master_bedroom. The pineapple is in the green_bucket. Owen moved the pineapple to the red_bottle. Where does Owen think that Ella searches for the pineapple?","target":"red_bottle","rationale":"The first four sentences describe that Owen has moved the pineapple to the red_bottle. The fifth sentence asks where Owen thinks Ella searches for the pineapple. Since we can infer that Owen knows that he had just moved the pineapple to the red_bottle, we can conclude that he thinks Ella would search for it in there as well."},{"source":"Article: The staple foods were generally consumed around 11 o'clock, and consisted of bread, lettuce, cheese, fruits, nuts, and cold meat left over from the dinner the night before.[citation needed] The Roman poet Horace mentions another Roman favorite, the olive, in reference to his own diet, which he describes as very simple: \\"As for me, olives, endives, and smooth mallows provide sustenance.\\" The family ate together, sitting on stools around a table. Fingers were used to eat solid foods and spoons were used for soups.[citation needed]\\n\\nNow answer this question: What form of expression did the Roman Horace practice?","target":"poet","rationale":"The context mentions the Roman poet Horace and his diet. Thus, we can infer that he is a poet because the term \\"poet\\" refers to someone who writes poems or verse.\\nTherefore, since Horace was mentioned as a famous figure in Rome it makes sense that he would be referred to by this title of respect.\\""},{"source":"Given a simple high-school level math question, you are required to solve it and provide the final answer. The final answer is always a single number. These questions can range from a variety of topics like simple arithmetic, solving equations, converting a quantity from one unit to another, finding remainders/GCD/LCM, finding probabilities etc. Each question has only one correct answer. This answer can be a positive or negative integer, a fraction or a decimal number. If the answer is a negative number use the hyphen (e.g. -42) symbol for the minus sign. For decimal numbers, do not add extra zeros after the decimal point. For fractional numbers, separate the numerator and denominator using a forward slash (e.g. 3/25).\\n\\nWhat is 2514 divided by -1257?","target":"-2","rationale":"2514/1257 = 2514*(-1)/1257 = -2"},{"source":"Categorize the comment on the basis of obscenity. If the comment is obscene output Yes, otherwise output No.\\n\\nAnhydrous Ammonia Surprise. March's ‚ÄúFlavor of the Month‚Äù","target":"No","rationale":"The comment talks about anhydrous ammonia, which is a chemical compound that can be used in various ways. However, the language it uses does not contain obscenities or any offensive content. Therefore, this statement should be categorized as \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Given a trivia question, classify broad topical category from this list: 'theater', 'geology', 'book', 'tv', 'astronomy', 'aviation', 'military', 'government', 'boxing', 'projects', 'metropolitan_transit', 'law', 'venture_capital', 'broadcast', 'biology', 'people', 'influence', 'baseball', 'spaceflight', 'media_common', 'cvg', 'opera', 'olympics', 'chemistry', 'visual_art', 'conferences', 'sports', 'language', 'travel', 'location', 'award', 'dining', 'martial_arts', 'comic_strips', 'computer', 'user', 'tennis', 'music', 'organization', 'food', 'event', 'transportation', 'fictional_universe', 'measurement_unit', 'meteorology', 'distilled_spirits', 'symbols', 'architecture', 'freebase', 'internet', 'fashion', 'boats', 'cricket', 'film', 'medicine', 'finance', 'comic_books', 'celebrities', 'soccer', 'games', 'time', 'geography', 'interests', 'common', 'base', 'business', 'periodicals', 'royalty', 'education', 'type', 'religion', 'automotive', 'exhibitions'.\\n\\nIn which country was the ballet dancer Carlos Acosta born?","target":"people","rationale":"The question asks about the birth country of a particular person, which indicates that it should be classified as 'people' category."},{"source":"Here's a problem to solve: Jenny's class made an instrument to measure air pressure. The instrument is a\\n\\nAmong the 4 following options, which is the correct answer?\\n\\n- A: thermometer.\\n \\n- B: rain gauge.\\n \\n- C: barometer.\\n \\n- D: wind vane.","target":"C","rationale":"The instrument described in the question is a barometer which measures air pressure. The answer choices provided are all weather instruments but only one of them, choice C, corresponds to the given description."},{"source":"Categorize the following sentence into one of the five different emotions: anger, confusion, joy, sadness and neutral.\\n\\nI still think he should have been the first goalie in the 2014 World Cup. But alas that injury ruined everything.","target":"sadness","rationale":"The given sentence expresses sadness as the writer wishes that a person should have been in the 2014 World Cup but their injury ruined everything."},{"source":"You are given a short poem which is written by a kid. Your task is to predict if the kid is in elementary school or high school. Anyone who is from grade 1st to 6th-grade will be considered as in elementary school, and 7th to 12th-grade kids will be considered as in high school. There are only two possible outputs, i.e., elementary and high. All inputs have at least one output and it cannot have both categories at a time.\\n\\nthe kid be have fun in the sun while the adult be take a run a bird be sing a sweet little song and his friend be sing along the sun be shin bright and the rain be out of sight it be snow for many day but now it 's like a summer blaze finally it feel like spring but it 's not too hot to where it sting no ore day that be gray now there 's only beautiful day","target":"elementary","rationale":"Kids in elementary school tend to have grammatical errors and miss the usage of verb tense while writing. This poem is written by a kid in elementary school because it has many grammatical errors like 'The kid be have fun...', 'the adult be take a run...', and 'and his friend be sing along' where the correct forms are 'The kid has fun...', 'the adult takes/takes a run...', and 'and his friend sings along'."},{"source":"You will be given a review about a book, an item, a place or a movie. After that, a question is given that you should answer using a certain span of the review. Your answer should be from the review itself and should not contain extra words, and should not be a combination of different spans. If there's no direct answer to the question, answer with a part of the text that is the most relevant to the question. See the examples for clarification.\\n\\nreview: I am a Kindle Fire HD fan. (so some of you should stop reading now) The new Nexus 7 really gives the Kindle Fire a run for its money as an entertainment device. I only have one Amazon movie, but use Hulu Plus and NetFlix. Both of those work great on both devices. Come to think of it, I didn't try viewing my Amazon Prime movie on the Nexus. My main use is web browsing, books, music and video files. The new Nexus has speakers that sound pretty much just as nice (and loud) as the KFHD. There might be a difference in screen resolution, but my eyes can't tell - both screens look bright and sharp.Books - Text to speech on Amazon Kindle books only works on the KFHD. Since many, if not most of my books are Amazon, that is a bummer - I like text to speech for when I am driving and listening at bedtime. Audible's audiobooks works fine on both.Web Browsing. Believe it or not, I side-loaded Chrome on my KFHD some time ago, but I really just use Silk. Silk is fine for my needs.So both are fine devices, so what are the attractions to one over the other?- Nexus 7 has my favorite Google apps - like Google Maps.- Nexus 7 has GPS, which sounds useful, haven't played much with it yet.- Nexus 7 allows multiple user accounts. That will really be handy.- Nexus 7's back facing camera lets you take pictures even it you look funny doing it.- Google Play store has a bajillion apps, 99.9997% of which I don't care about. But there are a half dozen I would like that aren't on Amazon's store.- Kindle Fire's built-in ebook reader will display both Amazon and non-Amazon books and will do text to speech on them all.I own both, but if I had pick just one today, I'd pick the Nexus 7. BUT, I noticed today that only the 16 gig version of the KFHD is for sale at Amazon. Perhaps Amazon is about to release a new version? Next month could be a different story.There are minor details, like the Nexus needs a special adapter cable for HDMI out where the KFHD uses a separate, \\"normal\\" socket. And the Nexus buttons are tiny and I find myself fumbling to find them.If you have an older model and are thinking of upgrading, perhaps waiting to see what Amazon responds to the Nexus 2013 with would be good. To be totally honest, I am now a fan of both tablets. And married to an iPod Touch fangirl who demands a unit she can slip into her pocket.\\nquestion: How good is the resolution of the screen?","target":"both screens look bright and sharp","rationale":"The question is about the resolution of the screen, and there are no direct answers to that question in the review. However, \\"both screens look bright and sharp\\" can be used as an answer as it indicates that both devices have a good screen quality."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people. 'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. Your task is to classify the conversation either convey 'No emotion' or 'Happiness' by providing '1' and '0', respectively.\\n\\n Person1:      what's the matter with you ? You look so upset and tired .  \\n Person2:  My father failed in business .  \\n Person1:       Oh , that's really tough .  \\n Person2:  Maybe it is the most difficult period of my family have experienced .  \\n Person1:       I can understand . By the way , is there anyway I can help ?  \\n Person2:  No , not now . I have found a part-time job . So perhaps I can help my family to come over the difficulties .  \\n Person1:       Oh , that's so great , bless you ! if you need me , I'll always be there .  \\n Person2:  Thank you .","target":"1","rationale":"Person2's father failed in business, and this is likely a very difficult period for Person2's family. However, Person1 says \\"Oh, that's really tough\\" in response to this information. Although the statement can be taken as an expression of concern and sympathy, it cannot be interpreted as a positive or happy emotion. It should also be noted that while Person1 ends the conversation with \\"bless you!\\", this statement does not necessarily convey happiness either.\\""},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to identify which one of following five services the sentence is related to - Media, Travel, Flights, Buses, RideSharing\\n\\nI need to find a seat on a bus.","target":"Buses","rationale":"The sentence is asking for information about bus services, so the correct answer is Buses."},{"source":"But don't dilly-dally for too long. Once it's published we are all going to look a little risible if we have made no adjustments to what is after all known as being predominantly my own design of gallery. Also I am a bit older than the rest of you but you can perhaps understand that I don't want to drop dead without a proper and public recantation.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion (choose your answer)?\\nhe doesn't want to drop dead without a proper and public recantation\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- No\\n- It's impossible to say","target":"Yes","rationale":"Context: But don't dilly-dally for too long. Once it's published we are all going to look a little risible if we have made no adjustments to what is after all known as being predominantly my own design of gallery. Also I am a bit older than the rest of you but you can perhaps understand that I don't want to drop dead without a proper and public recantation\\nThere is enough evidence in the context above, stating that \\"I don‚Äôt want to drop dead without a proper and public recantation\\", which supports our conclusion about him not wanting to die before he gets his chance at redemption. Therefore, the answer should be \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"I am hesitating between 4 options to answer the following question, which option should I choose?\\nQuestion: Which statement about all living organisms is true?\\nPossibilities:\\n- They have limbs.\\n- They produce their own food.\\n- They breathe air.\\n- They have at least one cell.","target":"They have at least one cell.","rationale":"This is a question about living things. All living organisms have at least one cell, whereas non-living things like rocks and water do not. Limbs are found only on some animals, the ability to produce food distinguishes plants from other kinds of animals that can't make their own energy source, and breathing air (or oxygen) is an important distinction for certain aquatic lifeforms but most land-dwelling creatures breathe air anyway. \\nTherefore this statement must be true in order for it to describe all living organisms as asked by the question: \\"They have at least one cell."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a context sentence containing a blank (_). You are expected to fill the blank with one word to make the sentence convey a cultural anti-stereotype. Anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against a common belief about a particular group of people. Your answer must not contain more than one word.\\n\\nContext: People from Lebanon work as _.","target":"lawyers","rationale":"The sentence implies that people from Lebanon usually work as laborers or mechanics, so to convey an anti-stereotype, the answer should be a profession that is not commonly associated with Lebanon. The word \\"lawyers\\" satisfies this condition and is therefore the correct answer."},{"source":"Classify the relation of question with context to one of these categories: 1) award received, 2) based on, collection, 3) conflict, 4) constellation, 5) convicted of, 6) date of death, 7) director, 8) drafted by, 9) educated at, 10) medical condition, 11) military branch, 12) narrative location, 13) occupation, 14) original network, 15) parent company, 16) point in time, 17) production company, 18) residence, 19) series, 20) service entry, 21) sex or gender, 22) spouse, 23) standards body question.\\n\\nContext : Eric and Ernie is a 2011 television film produced by BBC Wales on the early career of the British comic double-act Morecambe and Wise. \\nQuestion : Which place does Eric and Ernie exist in?","target":"narrative location","rationale":"The question is asking about the location in which the Eric and Ernie television program exists. So, this is classified as a \`narrative location\` relation."},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: When did Greek Cypriots first express interest in a union with their homeland, which eventually led to conflict?\\nContext: Cyprus was placed under British administration based on Cyprus Convention in 1878 and formally annexed by Britain in 1914. Even though Turkish Cypriots made up only 18% of the population, the partition of Cyprus and creation of a Turkish state in the north became a policy of Turkish Cypriot leaders and Turkey in the 1950s. Turkish leaders for a period advocated the annexation of Cyprus to Turkey as Cyprus was considered an \\"extension of Anatolia\\" by them; while since the 19th century, the majority Greek Cypriot population and its Orthodox church had been pursuing union with Greece, which became a Greek national policy in the 1950s. Following nationalist violence in the 1950s, Cyprus was granted independence in 1960. In 1963, the 11-year intercommunal violence between Greek Cypriots and Turkish Cypriots started, which displaced more than 25,000 Turkish Cypriots and brought the end of Turkish Cypriot representation in the republic. On 15 July 1974, a coup d'√©tat was staged by Greek Cypriot nationalists and elements of the Greek military junta in an attempt at enosis, the incorporation of Cyprus into Greece. This action precipitated the Turkish invasion of Cyprus, which led to the capture of the present-day territory of Northern Cyprus the following month, after a ceasefire collapsed, and the displacement of over 150,000 Greek Cypriots and 50,000 Turkish Cypriots. A separate Turkish Cypriot state in the north was established in 1983. These events and the resulting political situation are matters of a continuing dispute.","target":"the 19th century","rationale":"The question asks when Greek Cypriots first expressed interest in union with their homeland, which eventually led to conflict. This suggests that the answer will be found before Britain annexed Cyprus and Turkish leaders began advocating annexation of Cyprus by Turkey. The context states that since the 19th century, \\"the majority Greek Cypriot population and its Orthodox church had been pursuing union with Greece.\\" Since this was an expression of interest in a union with their homeland (Greece), it meets the criteria for being considered as part of why there was later conflict between Greeks and Turks over how to govern Cyprus. Therefore, based on this information from the text, we can infer that during ‚Äúthe 19th century‚Äù is when Greek Cypriots first expressed interest in a union with their homeland - so choice"},{"source":"This article: Handel joined the Hamburg opera house when it was experiencing a period of considerable artistic success. This blossoming followed the arrival of Reinhard Keiser, who had become musical director at the G√§nsemarkt in about 1697, and in 1703 succeeded Johann Kusser as the theatre's manager. Born in 1674, Keiser had studied under Johann Schelle and probably Johann Kuhnau at the Thomasschule zu Leipzig.  In 1694 he was employed as a court composer at Brunswick, where in three years he composed seven operas, at least one of which (Mahumeth) was performed in Hamburg. According to Handel's biographer Donald Burrows, Keiser was a good judge of popular taste, with a flair for writing Italian-style arias.  Between 1697 and 1703, prior to Handel's arrival, about a dozen more Keiser operas had been staged at the G√§nsemarkt. Despite his on-stage successes, Keiser was an unreliable general manager, with expensive private tastes and little financial acumen, often at odds with his creditors.It is possible that Keiser, who had connections in the Halle area, had heard of Handel and was directly instrumental in securing the latter's post in the G√§nsemarkt orchestra; certainly he was a considerable influence on the younger man in the three years that Handel spent in Hamburg. Another important G√§nsemarkt colleague was the house composer and singer Johann Mattheson, who noted Handel's rapid progress in the orchestra from back-desk violinist to harpsichord soloist, a role in which, said Mattheson, \\"he showed himself a man‚Äîa thing which no one had before suspected, save I alone\\". Mattheson was less complimentary on Handel's early efforts at composition: \\"He composed very long, long arias, and really interminable cantatas\\", before, it seems, \\"the lofty schooling of opera ... trimmed him into other fashions\\". contains an answer for the question: What is the full name of the person who was a considerable influence on Handel in the three years that he spent in Hamburg?, what is it ?","target":"Reinhard Keiser","rationale":"It is known from the passage that Handel studied under Johann Schelle and probably Johann Kuhnau at Leipzig, meaning his post-school education occurred in Hamburg. The person who was a considerable influence on him in three years spent there should be someone he worked with then (at least).\\nThe text mentions Reinhard Keiser as a musical director of G√§nsemarkt opera house. He had been seen by Handel before: \\"Keiser ... had become musical director at the G√§nsemarkt in about 1697, and ... succeeded Johann Kusser as the theatre's manager\\" - so they were colleagues during this time period; even though it seems to have happened after 3 year employment ended for Handel - since it says \\"... when [Handel"},{"source":"The task is about reading the given context, group and MCQs and then generating answers from the given input. MCQs are multiple choice questions in which a question is asked and few options are given, among which one or in some cases more than one can be the answer.\\n\\ncontext: A person is trying to move a pile of flowers, a pile of salt, a pile of books, and a pile of blocks from one side of a room to the other using only one hand.<sep>group: grasping <sep>question: Which pile is the hardest to move?<sep>A: flowers<sep>B: salt<sep>C: books<sep>D: blocks","target":"The pile of books is the hardest to move","rationale":"The pile of books is the hardest to move because each book has to be grabbed separately, whereas the flower, salt and blocks can all be moved in a single grab."},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: If \\"Crop worker taking a smoke break.\\", can we conclude \\"Worker smoking.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The statement \\"Crop worker taking a smoke break\\" implies that the person is smoking. So, we can conclude that they are smoking and hence the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"The longest mission which these Salyuts supported was 63 days. The second generation Salyuts would fly missions much longer and would need to be resupplied from time to time; therefore, a supply ferry was mandatory to maintain a fully operational Salyut for two years with 40,000 pounds of fuel, food, clothing and water.\\n\\nQ with options: Can we draw the following conclusion?\\nRussians hold record for longest stay in space.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"This passage is talking about the development of Salyut space stations. The longest mission supported by these space stations was 63 days, and not a continuous stay in space for two years as implied by \\"longest stay\\". So we cannot verify this statement based on the information provided."},{"source":"In this task, you will be given a passage, a question and a list of single-word events identified from the passage. The goal is to point out all events from the given event list that can answer the question. If a question is unanswerable or none of the events answer the question, output should be empty.\\n\\nPassage: Saddam appeared to accept a border demarcation treaty he had rejected in peace talks following the August 1988 cease-fire of the eight-year war with Iran. The move seemed aimed at heading off more trouble with Iran, which had condemned Iraq's invasion of Kuwait on Aug. 2 but also criticized the multinational force dispatched to Saudi Arabia. Question: What happened during the event when something was accepted? Events: ['appeared', 'accept', 'treaty', 'rejected', 'talks', 'cease-fire', 'war', 'aimed', 'heading', 'condemned', 'criticized', 'dispatched']","target":"appeared","rationale":"During the event when something was accepted, Saddam appeared to accept a border demarcation treaty. This indicates that Saddam accepted the treaty."},{"source":"In this task, you will be presented with a context from an academic paper and a question based on the context. You have to classify the questions into \\"Extractive\\", \\"Abstractive\\", or \\"Yes-no\\" questions. Extractive questions can be answered by concatenating extracts taken from a context into a summary while answering abstractive questions involves paraphrasing the context using novel sentences. Yes-no question is a question whose expected answer is one of two choices, one that affirms the question and one that denies the question. Typically, the choices are either yes or no.\\n\\nIn ConMask, we use a similar idea to select the most related words given some relationship and mask irrelevant words by assigning a relationship-dependent similarity score to words in the given entity description. ConMask selects words that are related to the given relationship to mitigate the inclusion of irrelevant and noisy words. \\n Question: Can the model add new relations to the knowledge graph, or just new entities?","target":"Abstractive","rationale":"The context describes a new method for selecting related words from entity descriptions in knowledge graphs. The question asks whether the model can add both new entities and relations to the knowledge graph. This question does not require concatenating extracts or paraphrasing any parts of the context; instead, it requires conceptual understanding of what is being described in the context. Therefore, this is an abstractive question and should be classified as \\"Abstractive\\"."},{"source":"Pick the most correct option to answer the following question.\\n\\nWhich of these best indicates that sediments can be changed into rock?\\n\\nOptions:\\n\\n- A: layers of sandstone\\n\\n- B: igneous intrusions\\n\\n- C: lava beds\\n\\n- D: mountains with gneiss","target":"A","rationale":"This question asks us about the name of a famous Minnesota burger whose main feature is having melted American cheese between two grilled beef patties ("},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is the next sentence syntactically and semantically acceptable?\\n\\nI read three his books.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"unacceptable","rationale":"The sentence \\"I read three his books\\" is unacceptable.\\\\n\\nSyntactically, the number of determiners (\\"three\\") and possessive pronouns (\\"his\\") should match with their matching nouns (books) in a sentence: I read three [of] his [many] books. Here there are two determiners and one pronoun; however, it would be acceptable to use only one if both were omitted:  I read some of these books. \\\\nSemantically, this example does not make sense because he can't have written all those different types of book at once.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you need to provide the correct option for a given problem on probability from the provided options.\\n\\nProblem: on a ranch , a rancher can place a loop of rope , called a lasso , once in every 2 throws around a cow ‚Äô s neck . what is the probability that the rancher will be able to place a lasso around a cow ‚Äô s neck at least once in 3 attempts ? \\nOptions: a ) 3 / 4 , b ) 5 / 8 , c ) 7 / 8 , d ) 9 / 16 , e ) 15 / 16","target":"c","rationale":"The probability that a rancher will be able to place a lasso around a cow's neck at least once in 3 attempts is 1 - P(Never placing the lasso in 3 attempts).\\\\nWhere P(Never placing the lasso in 3 attempts) = (1/2)^3 = (1/8)\\\\nTherefore, probability that the rancher will be able to place the lasso around a cow's neck at least once in 3 attempts is 1 - (1/8) = 7/8."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an anaphor number agreement or as an incorrect representation. An anaphor is an expression whose interpretation depends upon another expression. Anaphor number agreement is a restriction where a phrase agrees with the preceeding expression: plurals match plurals or singular expressions match singular expressions. In this task a valid representation of anaphor number agreement should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an anaphor number agreement will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence where the subject and self-referencing nouns match plurality. An incorrect representation is a sentence in which the subject and self-referencing noun's plurality do not match.\\n\\nDiane hadn't thought about herself.","target":"good","rationale":"The subject of the sentence is \\"Diane\\", which is singular. The reflexive pronoun \\"herself\\" is also singular and agrees with the plurality of the subject. Therefore, this sentence can be classified as a correct representation of anaphor number agreement and should be denoted as \\"good\\"."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the correct option to answer the question.\\nContext: Jenny turned her nose up at me as I sat down, sniffing loudly and filling her nostrils with the strong alcohol stink I was emitting. \\"So have you been drinking already this morning, or are you just still drunk from last night?\\"\\n\\"A little of both,\\" I said.\\nShe peered at me disapprovingly over her iced latte. We were sitting at a table in front of a strip mall coffee shop. Jenny was wearing huge gold-rimmed sunglasses and had a decent collection of shopping bags gathered at her feet.\\n\\"Busy afternoon?\\" I asked.\\n\\"Just picking up a few things for Mexico. We leave tomorrow morning.\\"\\nMy attention was drawn away by a group of men in black jumpsuits standing around in the parking lot next to a white van with the red Asterion logo painted on its side. It was hard to tell, but I thought one of them was the same guy I'd seen on the Light Rail a couple days before, the one who'd been reading the paper.\\nJenny seemed to notice my distraction and followed my gaze. \\"Is something wrong?\\"\\n\\"No, it's just those Asterion guys seem to be everywhere now. I guess business must be booming.\\"\\n\\"Yeah, we hired them last month to archive our old financial records,\\" Jenny replied. \\"They came in and hauled everything away, I was so happy to get all that empty space back. Of course it doesn't really matter now, since I'm going to have to find a new job when I get back from the honeymoon.\\n\\"Anyways, I'm rambling,\\" she admitted good-naturedly. \\"So what did you want to talk to me about?\\"\\n\\"I wanted to ask you about someone I met last night.\\"\\nShe bared her teeth ecstatically in a knowing grin. \\"Really? A woman, I presume.\\"\\n\\"Settle down, it's not like that. She's just a girl who said she can help introduce me to Dylan Maxwell.\\"\\n\\"Was it Natalie?\\" she asked.\\n\\"I don't know. She was wearing a motley dress and a black veil.\\"\\n\\"Yep, that's Natalie,\\" Jenny confirmed.\\nQuestion: When did Jenny hire Asterion guys?\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. She hired them last month.\\n\\nB. She hired them last week, which was in the previous month.\\n\\nC. She hired them yesterday.\\n\\nD. not enough information","target":"A","rationale":"The context mentions that Asterion guys were hired by Jenny last month, which means she hired them 30 days ago. So the answer is A"},{"source":"Two analogies that relate objects to the associated rooms is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates object A to room B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate room for the given object C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nmicrowave : kitchen. bed : ?","target":"bedroom","rationale":"A microwave is typically found in a kitchen, while beds are found in bedrooms. Therefore, bed : bedroom"},{"source":"In this task, you're given an open-domain question. Your task is to provide an answer to the given question. There is only one unique answer for each question. Your answer should be short, and refer to an entity, date, number, etc. Do not put your answer in the context of a sentence.\\n\\nWhen was the statue of david moved inside?","target":"1873","rationale":"The statue of David was moved inside in 1873."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"A large indoor shopping centre Hoog Catharijne (nl) is located between Utrecht Centraal railway station and the city centre. The corridors are treated as public places like streets, and the route between the station and the city centre is open all night. In 20 years from 2004, parts of Hoog Catharijne will be redeveloped as part of the renovation of the larger station area. Parts of the city's network of canals, which were filled to create the shopping center and central station area, will be recreated. The Jaarbeurs, one of the largest convention centres in the Netherlands, is located at the west side of the central railway station.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: Where does the Mega Record & CD Fair occur?","target":"The Jaarbeurs","rationale":"The text mentions the Jaarbeurs, a convention center that is home to one of the largest record conventions in Europe. This indicates that it would be appropriate for this type of event and likely hosts them frequently. \\nTherefore, based on the given context, The Jaarbeurs are most likely location where Mega Record & CD Fair occurs."},{"source":"In this task, you will be given a passage, a question and a list of single-word events identified from the passage. The goal is to point out all events from the given event list that can answer the question. If a question is unanswerable or none of the events answer the question, output should be empty.\\n\\nPassage: The media village will provide up to 6,000 rooms to accredited media during the Games. The whole project is due for completion at the beginning of 2008. Question: What will finish before the games? Events: ['provide', 'Games', 'project', 'due', 'completion', 'beginning', '2008']","target":"project","rationale":"The project will be completed before the Games start. The other events from the list are not relevant to answering the question."},{"source":"Question: What is the BSX a member of?\\n\\nIs There are four hundred securities listed on the stock exchange, of which almost three hundred are offshore funds and alternative investment structures attracted by Bermuda's regulatory environment. a good answer to this question?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The answer provided lists the number of securities listed on a stock exchange. However, it does not explain what is the BSX a member of or whether there are any other stock exchanges in Bermuda besides the BSX. Therefore, this answer cannot be considered as an accurate response to our question."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate actions to the tools used to perform the action is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates action A to tool B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate tool for the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nvacuum : vacuum. unlock : ?","target":"key","rationale":"A vacuum is the tool used to perform the action of vacuuming. Similarly, a key is the tool used to perform the action of unlocking something."},{"source":"What is a question that would give the following answer?\\nAnswer: \\"track and trace\\" systems;\\nQuestion:","target":"What are activists trying to get implemented?","rationale":"The answer is \\"track and trace\\" systems, which are meant to combat human trafficking. In the context given, activists are trying to get such a system implemented by the government. Therefore, it would be appropriate for someone reading this passage to ask: \\"What are activists trying to get implemented?"},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a prompt from a judicial decision and multiple holding statements derived from citations following text in a legal decision.  Holdings represent the governing legal rule when the law is applied to a particular set of facts. There are five answer choices for each citing text. The correct answer is the holding statement that corresponds to the citing text. The four incorrect answers are other holding statements. You should find the correct option. There is a <HOLDING> token in the position of the citing text prompt where the holding statement was extracted.\\n\\ncode, Appellants here ‚Äúdo[ ] not seek an advisory opinion that [their] proposed actions would not be criminal.‚Äù Total Vending Svc., 153 Ga. App. at 111. Instead, Appellants seek a determination of whether licensed individuals may carry a weapon on the grounds of the Garden in accordance with OCGA ¬ß 16-11-127 (c). See Total Vending, 153 Ga. App. at 111. Further, Appellants‚Äô requested relief is not premised on mere speculation that the Garden will enforce its weapons ban; Evans, who holds a membership with the Garden, had already been asked to leave the premises of the Garden and was escorted from the property by law enforcement. Importantly, however, there is no allegation here that criminal conduct has been accomplished. See Osborne v. State, 290 Ga. App. 188 (665 SE2d 1) (2008) (<HOLDING>). Accordingly, Appellants‚Äô request for \\n Holding statements: (A) holding dollar amount is not an essential element (B) holding that damage to the property of another is an essential element of the offense of criminal mischief (C) recognizing that an essential element of criminal trespass is a showing that entry onto the premises had previously been expressly forbidden (D) holding that the nonmovant must make a showing sufficient to establish the existence of an element essential to that partys case (E) holding that causation is an essential element in failure to warn claim","target":"(C)","rationale":"The holding statement cited in support of the argument that there is no allegation of criminal conduct established is \\"recognizing that an essential element of criminal trespass is a showing that entry onto the premises had previously been expressly forbidden\\". Since it matches with option (C), which states \\"recognizing that an essential element of criminal trespass is a showing that entry onto the premises had previously been expressly forbidden\\", it should be given as answer."},{"source":"Given an entity as input, output another entity which is part of the input entity. These are entities of meronym. In linguistics, meronymy is a semantic relation between a meronym denoting a part and a holonym denoting a whole. In simpler terms, a meronym (i.e., output entity) is in a part-of relationship with its holonym (i.e., input entity).\\n\\nanglerfish","target":"fish scale","rationale":"An anglerfish is a type of fish, and one of its parts is the fish scale, which is a plate-like structure that covers the skin. Therefore, fish scale is part-of anglerfish."},{"source":"In this task, you are provided with an article of the legal acts. Your task is to classify it into three categories (Regulation, Decision and Directive) based on its content: 1) Regulation is a binding legislative act that must be applied in its entirety on a set date across all the member states (European Union countries). 2) Decision is binding on those to whom it is addressed (e.g. an European Union country or an individual company) and is directly applicable. 3) Directive is a legislative act that sets out a goal that all  must achieve. However, it is up to the individual countries to devise their own laws on how to reach these goals.\\n\\nThe authorization for the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg granted in Decision 75/578/EEC shall be withdrawn with effect from 31 December 1977 as far as the variety Tiran (Phleum pratense L.) is concerned. This Decision is addressed to the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg.","target":"Decision","rationale":"This article is an example of Decision. The article states that the authorization for the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg granted in Decision 75/578/EEC shall be withdrawn with effect from 31 December 1977 as far as the variety Tiran (Phleum pratense L.) is concerned. It also states that this decision is addressed to the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg, which implies that it is applicable only to the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg and not to all European Union countries."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. You need to find all the elements of the list that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\n\\n['V', 'I', '4331', 'e', 'B', '5547']","target":"9878","rationale":"Given the list ['V', 'I', '4331', 'e', 'B', '5547'], we need to find all the elements that are numbers.\\\\n1. The 3rd element is 4331.\\\\n2. The 6th element is 5547.\\\\n\\\\nThe final result, 4331 + 5547 = 9878"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence from the research paper and the category to which it belongs. Your task is to classify whether the given category is correct or not by providing \\"True\\" and \\"False\\", respectively. Here are the definitions for the categories: Background (Why is this problem important? What relevant works have been created before? What is still missing in the previous works? What are the high-level research questions? How might this help other research or researchers?), Purpose (What specific things do the researchers want to do? What specific knowledge do the researchers want to gain? What specific hypothesis do the researchers want to test?), Method (How did the researchers do the work or find what they sought? What are the procedures and steps of the research?), or Finding (What did the researchers find out? Did the proposed methods work? Did the thing behave as the researchers expected?). \\",\\n\\nSentence: suggesting their potential link with lung damage. \\n Section: purpose","target":"False","rationale":"The sentence describes the presence of a protein called SARS-CoV-2 nucleocapsid (N) with possible links to lung damage. The purpose section should include information about \\"what specific things do researchers want to do\\", \\"what specific knowledge do researchers want to gain\\" or \\"what specific hypothesis do researchers want to test\\". However, this sentence does not provide any information about the research objective or hypothesis. So it is more likely that it belongs in the background section rather than purpose, so the answer is False."},{"source":"You will be given a topic and an argument. Your task is to answer whether the topic and the argument are related or not. A related argument should provide more details about the outcomes of the topic. If the argument refers to or suggests a consequence related to that topic, answer with \\"yes\\"; otherwise, answer with \\"no\\".\\n\\ntopic: Assassination of a Dictator\\nargument: People would support Israel's assassinations if they lived in Israel","target":"no","rationale":"The passage does not discuss the assassination of a dictator, so it is not related to this topic. Therefore, the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Given an entity as input, output another entity which is part of the input entity. These are entities of meronym. In linguistics, meronymy is a semantic relation between a meronym denoting a part and a holonym denoting a whole. In simpler terms, a meronym (i.e., output entity) is in a part-of relationship with its holonym (i.e., input entity).\\n\\ndiorite","target":"sodium plagioclase","rationale":"Diorite is an igneous rock with a phaneritic texture that has a color index varying between gray and dark green. It consists of plagioclase, hornblende, biotite and quartz. In particular, it contains sodium plagioclase (i.e., albite) and calcium plagioclase (i.e., anorthite), which are two different types of feldspar minerals with composition ranging from pure NaAlSi3O8 to pure CaAl2Si2O8, respectively. Therefore, sodium albite is a part of diorite rock because it includes at least some amount of sodium albite in its composition."},{"source":"Premise: Little girl holding a karate trophy.\\n\\nHypothesis: A girl won a race.\\n\\n.Multi-select problem: Can we conclude that the hypothesis is true if the premise is true?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"If the premise is true, then we can see that a little girl won some kind of award. However, there's no information in this sentence that would support the hypothesis stating she won a race. There are many other things you could win besides achieving first place in a competition such as an achievement award or any sort of trophy for excellence."},{"source":"Which of the following would you use to most efficiently transport heat?\\n- empty water bottle\\n- cotton T-Shirt\\n- baseball cap\\n- empty soda can","target":"empty soda can","rationale":"The question asks for the object that would most efficiently transport heat. This means that the answer must be a good conductor of heat, i.e., an object through which energy can travel easily and quickly from one point to another.\\nOut of all four options, only materials made out of metal are efficient conductors of electricity as well as thermal energy; these include metals such as copper and aluminum (more commonly known in cans). In this case, \\"empty soda can\\" is made up entirely out of aluminum - thus making it the best choice among all available answers due to its high conduction efficiency factor.\\n\\n\\nQA DATA EXAMPLE: \\\\[TEMPLATE\\\\] QID-00001 && RATIONALE SENTENCE TEMPLATE & OPTION NUM"},{"source":"In this task, you're given a context, a sentence,  and a character. The sentence describes an action or job of the given character. Also, the context provides more information about the sentence or the character. Your task is to return one of the emotions which are expressed by the Character in the given sentence. For that you can use the Context; however, Context is not provided in all the inputs. Also, in some inputs, there can be zero emotion; for that return 'None'.\\n\\nContext: Yvonne never wore make up. Her friends told her she should and brought her to the store. She tried a few shades and chose a light tone color. But when she arrived home, she threw it in the trash. \\n Sentence: Later, when she met her friends, she told them her dog ate it. \\n Character: Her dog","target":"None","rationale":"The first five sentences in the context are about Yvonne, a girl who does not wear make-up. When her friends tell her to wear make-up and bring her to the store, she tries a few shades and chooses one. When she gets back home, however, she throws it away.\\\\nIn this case the character is \\"Her dog\\", which refers to Yvonne's dog. The sentence that follows the character states that when Yvonne met her friends, she told them that \\"her dog ate it\\". Since there is no emotion in this sentence or in any previous sentences related to dogs or characters other than Yvonne (who already has a few emotions stated), we can conclude there is no emotion for this input and return 'None'."},{"source":"Problem: Solve 0 = 30*f - 181 - 59 for f.\\nAnd the answer is...","target":"8","rationale":"To solve for f, we need to isolate the variable on one side of the equation.\\n\\nStarting with:\\n0 = 30*f - 181 - 59  (1)"},{"source":"Given a part of privacy policy text, classify it into one of these categories: \\n (1) First Party Collection/Use (how and why a service provider collects user information), \\n (2) Third Party Sharing/Collection (how user information may be shared with or collected by third parties), \\n (3) User Choice/Control (choices and control options available to users), \\n (4) User Access, Edit, & Deletion (if and how users may access, edit, or delete their information), \\n (5) Data Retention (how long user information is stored), \\n (6) Data Security (how user information is protected), \\n (7) Policy Change (if and how users will be informed about changes to the privacy policy).\\n\\nA user's contact information is retained for an unspecified duration to fulfill an unspecified purpose.","target":"Data Retention","rationale":"The passage is about how long user information is stored. According to the passage, a user's contact information is retained for an unspecified duration. It tells us nothing else, so it falls into the category of Data Retention."},{"source":"The memo, written by Marc Allen Connelly (who was general counsel to the funeral services commission at the time) and sent to Dick McNeil (the Bush-appointed chairman of the funeral commission) stated that Connelly \\"received information\\" from Texas state officials that two of the funeral commissioners worked for SCI.\\nDoes this next sentence follow, given the preceding text?\\nDick McNeil was an employee of Bush.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The memo writer has been identified as Marc Allen Connelly, who worked for the funeral commission. In contrast to this claim, McNeil is described as the chairman of that same funeral commission (not an employee), although he may have other positions in addition to being a chairman. So it does not follow with certainty that Dick McNeil was also employed by Bush at some point during his career."},{"source":"Given a math problem with context and a question and 5 answer choices, the task is to provide the correct answer choice based on the problem. You must choose one of the given answer choices by letter: a, b, c, d, or e; anything else is invalid.\\n\\nProblem: a bus trip of 550 miles would have taken 1 hour less if the average speed v for the trip had been greater by 5 miles per hour. what was the average speed v, in miles per hour, for the trip ?\\nOptions: a. 40, b. 45, c. 50, d. 55, e. 60","target":"c","rationale":"Based on the question, we have:\\\\n\\\\\\\\(\\\\\\\\frac { 550 } { v+5 } - \\\\\\\\frac { 550 } { v \\n} = 1 \\\\\\\\) or \\\\\\\\(v^2 + 5v - 1100 = 0\\\\)\\\\nThe only value of v that satisfies the quadratic equation is 50."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to concatenate all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, and print the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n1, 23, ['e', 'A', '4341', '2673', '2145', 'U', '2361', '7099', '1845', '1103', 'r', '7321', '6741', '9563', '8985', '3689', 'M', 'h', '7737', '6941', '8521', 'g', 'i', 'x', 'J', '607', 'x', 'a', 'y', '3293']","target":"eA434126732145U2361709918451103r73216741956389853689Mh773769418521gi","rationale":"Given the list ['e', 'A', '4341', '2673', '2145', 'U', '2361', '7099', '1845',\\n'1103','r','7321','6741','9563','8985','3689','M','h'7737,6941,8521,'g,'i,'x,\\n'J,'607,'x,'a ,y,3293], we need to find the elements within the range 1 ~ 23.\\\\n1. The 1st element is e.\\\\n2. The 2nd element is A.\\\\n3. The 3rd element is 4341... and so on until... \\\\n23th element i:\\\\nTherefore, concatenating all those elements together will be \\"eA434126732145U2361709918451103r73216741956389853689Mh773769418521gi\\"."},{"source":"Though fearful of a forthcoming performance evaluation by her boss, Zoe must unravel the life of a man just found dead of a heart attack, who was supposed to have died three years earlier in a boating accident.\\n\\nBased on that paragraph can we conclude that the sentence below is true?\\nZoe died in a boating accident.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"If we read the paragraph carefully, it will be clear that Zoe is fearful of her boss's evaluation. She must unravel a mystery about someone else who died in a boating accident and not herself as suggested by the sentence below."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the intersection of two given sets.  A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. The intersection of two given sets is the largest set which contains all the elements that are common to both sets. To find the intersection of two given sets, A and B is a set consisting of all the elements common to both A and B.\\n\\nSet1: '{16, 2, 18, 13}', Set2: '{1, 13, 5, 14}'. How many elements are there in the intersection of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"1","rationale":"The intersection of the two sets is {13}."}]`),H={components:{PoemCard:B},data(){return{poemsData:M,visibleCount:6,isLoading:!1}},computed:{hasMorePoems(){return this.visibleCount<this.poemsData.length}},methods:{async loadMore(){this.isLoading=!0,await new Promise(o=>setTimeout(o,1e3)),this.visibleCount+=6,this.isLoading=!1}}},W={class:"card-container"},P=["disabled"],N={key:0},E={key:1};function D(o,e,c,m,i,s){const r=v("PoemCard");return a(),n("section",null,[e[1]||(e[1]=t("div",{class:"top-banner"},[t("div",{class:"top-banner-title"},[t("div",{class:"top-banner-title-text"},"üéâ Chain of Thought ü•≥")])],-1)),t("div",W,[d(r,{poems:i.poemsData},null,8,["poems"])]),s.hasMorePoems?(a(),n("button",{key:0,class:"load-more-button",disabled:i.isLoading,onClick:e[0]||(e[0]=(...h)=>s.loadMore&&s.loadMore(...h))},[i.isLoading?(a(),n("span",E,"Loading...")):(a(),n("span",N,"See more"))],8,P)):k("",!0)])}const O=u(H,[["render",D],["__scopeId","data-v-844e02ab"]]),F=JSON.parse('{"title":"","description":"","frontmatter":{"page":true},"headers":[],"relativePath":"quotes/23.md","filePath":"quotes/23.md"}'),R={name:"quotes/23.md"},G=Object.assign(R,{setup(o){return(e,c)=>(a(),n("div",null,[d(O)]))}});export{F as __pageData,G as default};
